WEBVTT

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:13.380
Thank you.

00:00:13.380 --> 00:00:14.400
Thank you.

00:00:17.280 --> 00:00:23.519
Scholastic Audio presents Wings of Fire

00:00:23.519 --> 00:00:28.079
Book 2, The Lost Air, by 2 E T Sutherland

00:00:28.079 --> 00:00:30.780
Read by Shannon McManus.

00:00:48.899 --> 00:00:52.679
The Dragonette Prophecy.

00:00:52.799 --> 00:00:56.820
When the war has lasted 20 years, the

00:00:56.820 --> 00:00:59.820
dragonettes will come, when the land is

00:00:59.820 --> 00:01:01.560
soaked in blood and tears.

00:01:01.619 --> 00:01:03.600
The dragonettes will come.

00:01:03.659 --> 00:01:07.859
Find the sea wing egg of deepest blue.

00:01:07.920 --> 00:01:10.379
Wings of night shall come to you.

00:01:10.439 --> 00:01:14.400
The largest egg and mountain high will

00:01:14.400 --> 00:01:16.079
give to you the wings of sky.

00:01:16.079 --> 00:01:19.680
For wings of earth, search through the

00:01:19.680 --> 00:01:22.379
mud, for an egg the color of dragon

00:01:22.379 --> 00:01:22.799
blood.

00:01:22.920 --> 00:01:26.640
And hidden alone from the rival queens

00:01:26.640 --> 00:01:29.700
the sand wing egg awaits unseen.

00:01:29.760 --> 00:01:34.200
Of three queens who blister and blaze and

00:01:34.200 --> 00:01:38.459
burn, two shall die, and one shall learn

00:01:38.459 --> 00:01:41.340
if she bows to a fate that is stronger

00:01:41.340 --> 00:01:44.159
and higher, she'll have the power of

00:01:44.159 --> 00:01:45.060
wings of fire.

00:01:45.120 --> 00:01:49.260
Five eggs to hatch on brightest night

00:01:49.260 --> 00:01:52.439
five dragons born to end the fight.

00:01:52.560 --> 00:01:56.099
Darkness will rise to bring the light.

00:01:56.219 --> 00:01:58.200
The dragonettes.

00:01:58.260 --> 00:01:59.400
Are coming.

00:02:11.520 --> 00:02:15.960
Prologue.

00:02:16.080 --> 00:02:19.680
Underwater, Webbs couldn't hear the

00:02:19.680 --> 00:02:21.120
screams of dying dragons.

00:02:21.180 --> 00:02:22.919
Underwater.

00:02:22.979 --> 00:02:25.979
The battle was as far away as the 3

00:02:25.979 --> 00:02:26.280
moons.

00:02:26.400 --> 00:02:28.139
Fire couldn't touch him.

00:02:28.199 --> 00:02:30.539
Talons couldn't scar him.

00:02:30.599 --> 00:02:33.659
The blood washed away from his claws.

00:02:33.719 --> 00:02:34.979
Underwater.

00:02:35.039 --> 00:02:36.180
He was safe.

00:02:36.240 --> 00:02:39.419
Safe, and a coward.

00:02:39.539 --> 00:02:42.719
Still better than loyal, brave, and

00:02:42.719 --> 00:02:43.020
dead.

00:02:43.080 --> 00:02:45.719
Webbs shuddered awake.

00:02:45.840 --> 00:02:48.599
A catfish was staring at him blankly.

00:02:48.659 --> 00:02:51.300
Its whisky tendrils drifted in the

00:02:51.300 --> 00:02:51.599
current.

00:02:51.659 --> 00:02:55.560
The expression on its face said, Why is

00:02:55.560 --> 00:02:57.060
there a dragon sleeping on my river

00:02:57.060 --> 00:02:57.599
stones?

00:02:57.659 --> 00:02:59.879
Webbs ate it.

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:01.979
And that made him feel a little better.

00:03:02.039 --> 00:03:06.060
The talons of peace must know what's

00:03:06.060 --> 00:03:08.520
happened to the dragonets by now, he

00:03:08.520 --> 00:03:08.759
thought.

00:03:08.879 --> 00:03:12.180
They have spies in the Skywing Palace.

00:03:12.240 --> 00:03:14.099
They don't need to hear it from me.

00:03:14.159 --> 00:03:17.699
The other talons did not need him to

00:03:17.699 --> 00:03:20.039
stand up in front of them and say, we

00:03:20.039 --> 00:03:20.520
failed.

00:03:20.580 --> 00:03:22.919
But where could he go?

00:03:22.979 --> 00:03:25.979
He was already hiding from his own tribe

00:03:25.979 --> 00:03:26.939
the sea wings.

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:29.520
Did he have to hide from the talons of

00:03:29.520 --> 00:03:31.259
peace for the rest of his life as well?

00:03:31.319 --> 00:03:35.099
Webbs paddled to the surface of the river

00:03:35.099 --> 00:03:36.419
and cautiously poked his head out.

00:03:36.479 --> 00:03:40.020
It was dark, with the claws of the clouds

00:03:40.020 --> 00:03:42.180
mountains blocking most of the moonlight

00:03:42.180 --> 00:03:43.979
like vast shadowy teeth.

00:03:44.039 --> 00:03:46.979
He'd been swimming down river for days.

00:03:47.039 --> 00:03:50.520
The Sky Kingdom was far away now.

00:03:50.580 --> 00:03:52.439
The sky kingdom.

00:03:52.500 --> 00:03:55.860
And the 5 dragonettes he'd sworn to

00:03:55.860 --> 00:03:56.159
protect.

00:03:56.280 --> 00:04:00.479
Webbs dragged his long, aching body out

00:04:00.479 --> 00:04:02.819
of the water, and took three steps into

00:04:02.819 --> 00:04:05.159
the forest before he noticed the dark

00:04:05.159 --> 00:04:06.419
shapes waiting for him.

00:04:06.479 --> 00:04:10.379
He spun around, but a new dragon loomed

00:04:10.379 --> 00:04:11.699
out of the river to block his escape.

00:04:11.759 --> 00:04:15.000
Black spiral patterns marked his green

00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:17.639
scales, and his teeth gleamed in the

00:04:17.639 --> 00:04:17.939
moonlight.

00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:22.379
Webbs, said the other Sea Wing, in a

00:04:22.379 --> 00:04:22.860
pleasant voice.

00:04:22.980 --> 00:04:25.500
I thought you would never wake up.

00:04:25.560 --> 00:04:28.439
Webb drew his talent through the

00:04:28.439 --> 00:04:29.220
riverbank mud.

00:04:29.279 --> 00:04:32.279
Nautilus, he said.

00:04:32.339 --> 00:04:34.920
He hated the tremble of fear in his

00:04:34.920 --> 00:04:35.100
voice.

00:04:35.220 --> 00:04:38.819
I have important news for the talent.

00:04:38.939 --> 00:04:42.779
You don't say, said Nautilus.

00:04:42.839 --> 00:04:47.040
I suppose you got lost on your way to the

00:04:47.040 --> 00:04:48.300
usual meeting place.

00:04:48.360 --> 00:04:53.339
So we thought we'd come find you, said

00:04:53.339 --> 00:04:55.740
one of the dark figures, in a voice like

00:04:55.740 --> 00:04:56.759
icicles dripping.

00:04:56.819 --> 00:05:00.120
Siri, Webb's thought.

00:05:00.180 --> 00:05:03.240
It was never a good sign when Sirius the

00:05:03.240 --> 00:05:03.959
ice wing appeared.

00:05:04.019 --> 00:05:08.819
The Skywings found our cave Web said.

00:05:08.879 --> 00:05:11.279
Just tell the truth.

00:05:11.339 --> 00:05:12.779
It's not your fault.

00:05:12.899 --> 00:05:17.519
And Queen Scarlet took the dragonette.

00:05:17.639 --> 00:05:21.959
Yes, said Nautilus dryly.

00:05:22.019 --> 00:05:24.360
We gathered that much from how she's

00:05:24.360 --> 00:05:26.579
practically been standing on the tallest

00:05:26.579 --> 00:05:29.339
mountain shouting, I have the dragonettes

00:05:29.339 --> 00:05:30.060
of destiny.

00:05:30.300 --> 00:05:31.019
They're all mine.

00:05:31.079 --> 00:05:33.300
Tell us everything.

00:05:33.360 --> 00:05:35.339
Cyrus hissed.

00:05:35.459 --> 00:05:37.379
How did they find you?

00:05:37.500 --> 00:05:41.939
Well, Webbs said slowly.

00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:46.019
It started when 2 of the dragonets tried

00:05:46.019 --> 00:05:46.680
to run away.

00:05:46.740 --> 00:05:49.500
Maybe three.

00:05:49.560 --> 00:05:52.740
He wasn't sure where glory had been on

00:05:52.740 --> 00:05:54.540
the night he could only find Starlight

00:05:54.540 --> 00:05:56.759
and Sunny, but he knew she couldn't have

00:05:56.759 --> 00:05:58.379
gone into the river with tsunami and

00:05:58.379 --> 00:05:58.680
clay.

00:05:58.740 --> 00:06:01.259
Why would they run away?

00:06:01.319 --> 00:06:03.420
Nautilus asked sharply.

00:06:03.480 --> 00:06:05.399
What did you do to them?

00:06:05.519 --> 00:06:08.699
Webbs felt his gills flare.

00:06:08.759 --> 00:06:12.300
We kept them alive, he snarled.

00:06:12.360 --> 00:06:14.639
And trapped them underground.

00:06:14.699 --> 00:06:17.339
And chained tsunami.

00:06:17.399 --> 00:06:20.879
And planned to kill glory because she

00:06:20.879 --> 00:06:21.899
wasn't part of the prophecy.

00:06:21.959 --> 00:06:24.360
But what choice did we have?

00:06:24.420 --> 00:06:28.079
Surely you call it the runaways and

00:06:28.079 --> 00:06:29.939
brought them back, said a voice in the

00:06:29.939 --> 00:06:30.300
shadows.

00:06:30.360 --> 00:06:34.560
Webbs recognized crocodile, a mudwing new

00:06:34.560 --> 00:06:35.759
to the talents of peace.

00:06:35.819 --> 00:06:37.259
His hopes rose.

00:06:37.379 --> 00:06:40.019
In his few meetings with her, she'd been

00:06:40.019 --> 00:06:40.620
sympathetic.

00:06:40.680 --> 00:06:43.019
Perhaps he had one ally here.

00:06:43.079 --> 00:06:48.779
Er Webb said, no, not exactly.

00:06:48.839 --> 00:06:53.160
They kind of came back on their own to

00:06:53.160 --> 00:06:53.759
get the others.

00:06:53.819 --> 00:06:55.560
He cleared his throat.

00:06:55.620 --> 00:06:58.199
We weren't expecting that.

00:06:58.259 --> 00:07:01.500
Kestrel thought they'd be long gone.

00:07:01.560 --> 00:07:03.120
As soon as they hit the sky.

00:07:03.180 --> 00:07:06.660
It sounds as if they felt like

00:07:06.660 --> 00:07:07.379
prisoners.

00:07:07.439 --> 00:07:10.439
Nautilus said in a soft hiss.

00:07:10.500 --> 00:07:13.980
You told us to keep them underground.

00:07:14.040 --> 00:07:15.000
Webbs protested.

00:07:15.120 --> 00:07:17.879
That was a decision made by all the

00:07:17.879 --> 00:07:18.180
talents.

00:07:18.240 --> 00:07:22.319
But we wanted them agreeable, not

00:07:22.319 --> 00:07:24.300
rebellious, said Nautilus.

00:07:24.360 --> 00:07:27.720
That was the entire point, wasn't it?

00:07:27.779 --> 00:07:30.660
A murmur went around the circle of

00:07:30.660 --> 00:07:31.139
dragons.

00:07:31.199 --> 00:07:34.620
There were 7, including Nautilus, as far

00:07:34.620 --> 00:07:35.459
as Webbs could tell.

00:07:35.519 --> 00:07:37.860
He wondered if he could fight his way

00:07:37.860 --> 00:07:39.360
past 7 dragons.

00:07:39.420 --> 00:07:43.319
It wasn't our fault, he muttered.

00:07:43.379 --> 00:07:46.079
Maybe there's something wrong with them.

00:07:46.139 --> 00:07:49.680
What does this have to do with the sky

00:07:49.680 --> 00:07:50.399
wings?

00:07:50.459 --> 00:07:51.839
Sirius hissed.

00:07:51.899 --> 00:07:55.560
The Skywings followed Clay and Tsunami

00:07:55.560 --> 00:07:56.399
back to the cave.

00:07:56.459 --> 00:07:58.019
Webbs explained.

00:07:58.079 --> 00:08:00.720
That's how Queen Scarlet found us.

00:08:00.779 --> 00:08:04.560
We tried to fight back, but she killed

00:08:04.560 --> 00:08:07.439
Dune, and took Kestrel along with the

00:08:07.439 --> 00:08:08.279
dragonettes.

00:08:08.339 --> 00:08:11.579
Will she make them fight in her arena?

00:08:11.579 --> 00:08:13.079
asked Crocodile.

00:08:13.139 --> 00:08:15.000
Can they win?

00:08:15.060 --> 00:08:18.420
They're only dragonettes.

00:08:18.480 --> 00:08:19.980
Cerrus growled.

00:08:20.040 --> 00:08:23.279
Of course they won't survive the arena.

00:08:23.339 --> 00:08:27.300
Surely she'll spare the sky wing, at

00:08:27.300 --> 00:08:29.040
least, Crocodile said.

00:08:29.100 --> 00:08:31.019
Webb flinched.

00:08:31.079 --> 00:08:33.840
He had never been brave enough to confess

00:08:33.840 --> 00:08:36.600
to the talons of peace, that they'd lost

00:08:36.600 --> 00:08:39.179
their Sky Wing Dragonette, and replaced

00:08:39.179 --> 00:08:40.200
it with a rain wing.

00:08:40.259 --> 00:08:42.720
But now that the dragonets were out in

00:08:42.720 --> 00:08:45.360
the world, everyone would know soon.

00:08:45.419 --> 00:08:49.980
You know what Queen Scarlet did to all

00:08:49.980 --> 00:08:52.200
the sky winged dragonettes who hatched on

00:08:52.200 --> 00:08:53.159
the brightest night.

00:08:53.220 --> 00:08:55.139
Cyrus hissed.

00:08:55.200 --> 00:08:59.039
Mercy is not exactly in her nature.

00:08:59.159 --> 00:09:03.240
Webbs raised his head and looked around

00:09:03.240 --> 00:09:05.340
at the eyes that glittered in the dark.

00:09:05.399 --> 00:09:07.860
Can't we go get them?

00:09:07.919 --> 00:09:09.179
He asked.

00:09:09.240 --> 00:09:12.419
Maybe if all the talons attacked at

00:09:12.419 --> 00:09:12.960
once.

00:09:13.019 --> 00:09:14.279
His voice faltered.

00:09:14.340 --> 00:09:15.960
Who is he kidding?

00:09:16.019 --> 00:09:18.720
He wasn't about to go rushing into the

00:09:18.720 --> 00:09:21.600
Sky Wing Palace to die. and he was closer

00:09:21.600 --> 00:09:23.639
to the dragonettes than any of the talons

00:09:23.639 --> 00:09:24.960
who hadn't even met them.

00:09:25.080 --> 00:09:30.960
All the talons, Sirius hissed. 40 dragons

00:09:30.960 --> 00:09:34.559
against the 100 sky wing palace guards, a

00:09:34.559 --> 00:09:35.820
brilliant plan.

00:09:35.820 --> 00:09:39.120
No wonder we left the dragonette, senor

00:09:39.120 --> 00:09:40.440
capable claws.

00:09:40.500 --> 00:09:44.399
His diamond shaped head darted up and

00:09:44.399 --> 00:09:45.779
snapped a bat out of the air.

00:09:45.840 --> 00:09:49.019
Tiny bones crunched in his teeth.

00:09:49.080 --> 00:09:53.580
A suicide mission may not be necessary.

00:09:53.700 --> 00:09:55.440
Nautilus said.

00:09:55.500 --> 00:09:58.320
Something happened in the Sky Wing Palace

00:09:58.320 --> 00:09:58.799
yesterday.

00:09:58.860 --> 00:10:02.159
We don't have any clear reports yet, but

00:10:02.159 --> 00:10:04.860
one spy said he thought Queen Scarlet was

00:10:04.860 --> 00:10:08.399
dead. killed by the dragonettes.

00:10:08.460 --> 00:10:11.759
Webbs flared his wings in surprise.

00:10:11.820 --> 00:10:15.659
By my dragonettes?

00:10:15.659 --> 00:10:16.320
he asked.

00:10:16.440 --> 00:10:20.580
Maybe they have a talent for escaping.

00:10:20.700 --> 00:10:22.500
Nautila said.

00:10:22.559 --> 00:10:24.779
Although another spy was sure they all

00:10:24.779 --> 00:10:26.460
died trying to fight their way out.

00:10:26.519 --> 00:10:30.299
Webb's stomach felt as if it were full of

00:10:30.299 --> 00:10:31.500
poisonous jellyfish.

00:10:31.620 --> 00:10:34.259
The dragonettes couldn't be dead.

00:10:34.320 --> 00:10:37.559
Not after all he'd given out for the sake

00:10:37.559 --> 00:10:38.039
of the prophecy.

00:10:38.100 --> 00:10:41.399
And to save my own scales.

00:10:41.519 --> 00:10:43.919
A small voice whispered inside him.

00:10:43.980 --> 00:10:47.460
If they are loose in Pyria.

00:10:47.519 --> 00:10:49.559
How do you suggest we find them?

00:10:49.679 --> 00:10:51.240
Nautilus asked.

00:10:51.299 --> 00:10:54.179
Non-suicidal suggestions only please.

00:10:54.240 --> 00:10:56.159
Well, for us.

00:10:56.220 --> 00:10:58.320
You may feel free to kill yourself

00:10:58.320 --> 00:10:59.700
whenever it's convenient.

00:10:59.759 --> 00:11:01.919
I don't know.

00:11:01.980 --> 00:11:03.360
Webbs admitted.

00:11:03.419 --> 00:11:06.120
He had no idea where the dragonettes

00:11:06.120 --> 00:11:06.419
might go.

00:11:06.480 --> 00:11:08.940
He didn't understand why they would want

00:11:08.940 --> 00:11:11.639
to be on their own, cut off from their

00:11:11.639 --> 00:11:12.360
protectors.

00:11:12.419 --> 00:11:15.720
The worst 10 days of his life, were the

00:11:15.720 --> 00:11:17.220
ones between the battle where he had

00:11:17.220 --> 00:11:19.799
abandoned his queen, and the day the

00:11:19.799 --> 00:11:22.019
talents had found him, alone.

00:11:22.080 --> 00:11:25.019
With no tribe to support them, and no

00:11:25.019 --> 00:11:27.600
talents to protect them, how would the

00:11:27.600 --> 00:11:28.440
dragonets survive?

00:11:28.500 --> 00:11:32.100
If we can't get the dragonettes back.

00:11:32.220 --> 00:11:33.720
Nautilus mused.

00:11:33.779 --> 00:11:36.120
I suppose we'll have to consider our

00:11:36.120 --> 00:11:37.080
backup plan.

00:11:37.139 --> 00:11:39.960
He scratched his gills thoughtfully.

00:11:40.019 --> 00:11:43.620
What backup plan?

00:11:43.740 --> 00:11:44.940
Webbs asked.

00:11:45.000 --> 00:11:50.100
The one you don't get to know about, Sarah

00:11:50.100 --> 00:11:50.700
said.

00:11:50.759 --> 00:11:55.139
But, but we have to get them back, Webb

00:11:55.139 --> 00:11:55.379
said.

00:11:55.440 --> 00:11:58.919
They're the dragonettes.

00:11:58.980 --> 00:12:01.320
They're the only ones who can stop the

00:12:01.320 --> 00:12:01.679
war.

00:12:01.799 --> 00:12:05.879
Have a little faith in the prophecy webs

00:12:05.879 --> 00:12:07.019
Nautilus said.

00:12:07.080 --> 00:12:08.580
Yes.

00:12:08.639 --> 00:12:11.460
Don't worry, Crocodile said

00:12:11.460 --> 00:12:12.179
reassuringly.

00:12:12.240 --> 00:12:15.299
The talons of peas wouldn't put all their

00:12:15.299 --> 00:12:16.379
eggs in one nest.

00:12:16.440 --> 00:12:18.179
It's a good backup plan.

00:12:18.240 --> 00:12:21.960
Webbs looked from one shadowed face to

00:12:21.960 --> 00:12:22.259
the next.

00:12:22.320 --> 00:12:25.799
Apart from crocodile, he saw nothing

00:12:25.799 --> 00:12:27.779
friendly in the eyes staring at him.

00:12:27.840 --> 00:12:31.500
I don't understand, he said.

00:12:31.559 --> 00:12:34.320
Was there another prophecy he didn't know

00:12:34.320 --> 00:12:34.559
about?

00:12:34.620 --> 00:12:37.860
Of course, Nautilus said.

00:12:37.919 --> 00:12:40.860
That means you would be a problem.

00:12:40.919 --> 00:12:44.759
Webb's barely had time to say, what?

00:12:44.879 --> 00:12:47.039
before Cyrus was suddenly on his back

00:12:47.039 --> 00:12:48.480
pinning him to the ground.

00:12:48.539 --> 00:12:51.600
His wounds from the sky wing soldiers

00:12:51.600 --> 00:12:53.700
flared up with bright new pain.

00:12:53.759 --> 00:12:57.179
One wing was twisted behind him, and he

00:12:57.179 --> 00:12:59.700
could feel the ice wings serrated claws

00:12:59.700 --> 00:13:00.779
digging into his scales.

00:13:00.840 --> 00:13:02.759
What are you doing?

00:13:02.820 --> 00:13:04.259
Webbs yelped.

00:13:04.320 --> 00:13:05.279
I'm one of you.

00:13:05.340 --> 00:13:07.679
I've been with the talent of peace for 7

00:13:07.679 --> 00:13:07.919
years.

00:13:07.980 --> 00:13:11.220
And you failed us.

00:13:11.340 --> 00:13:13.019
Sirius hissed.

00:13:13.080 --> 00:13:17.399
Now, now, Nautilus said, then paused.

00:13:17.519 --> 00:13:19.860
No, that's fair.

00:13:19.919 --> 00:13:24.120
I'm going to dig your heart out and feed

00:13:24.120 --> 00:13:25.379
it to the fish.

00:13:25.440 --> 00:13:27.120
Cyrus growled.

00:13:27.179 --> 00:13:29.639
Won't that be ironic?

00:13:29.759 --> 00:13:32.639
Webb thought gloomily of the fish he'd

00:13:32.639 --> 00:13:33.299
just eaten.

00:13:33.360 --> 00:13:36.960
But we're the dragons for peace, he

00:13:36.960 --> 00:13:37.259
said.

00:13:37.320 --> 00:13:39.059
His teeth gritted with pain.

00:13:39.120 --> 00:13:40.980
If we kill each other.

00:13:41.100 --> 00:13:44.340
Aren't we as bad as burn and blister and

00:13:44.340 --> 00:13:44.820
blaze?

00:13:44.940 --> 00:13:48.659
Sorry, Webbs, Nautilus said.

00:13:48.720 --> 00:13:51.360
Peace is more important than any one

00:13:51.360 --> 00:13:52.080
dragon.

00:13:52.139 --> 00:13:54.840
And you would disrupt our backup plan.

00:13:54.899 --> 00:13:58.379
We're doing this for your own good, for

00:13:58.379 --> 00:13:59.039
the prophecy.

00:13:59.100 --> 00:14:01.139
For peace.

00:14:01.200 --> 00:14:04.860
Webbs heard the horrible echo of his own

00:14:04.860 --> 00:14:05.100
words.

00:14:05.220 --> 00:14:07.860
The same thing he'd said to the

00:14:07.860 --> 00:14:09.539
dragonettes whenever they complained

00:14:09.539 --> 00:14:10.860
about life under the mountain.

00:14:10.919 --> 00:14:12.659
It's for your own good.

00:14:12.720 --> 00:14:15.480
Peace is the most important thing.

00:14:15.600 --> 00:14:18.539
He'd believed it when he said it.

00:14:18.659 --> 00:14:21.299
No doubt Nautilus did too.

00:14:21.360 --> 00:14:24.480
Nautilus gestured with one talon.

00:14:24.600 --> 00:14:26.159
Sirius.

00:14:26.220 --> 00:14:27.899
Rip out his heart.

00:14:27.960 --> 00:14:32.279
The jaws of the ice wing sprang open, and

00:14:32.279 --> 00:14:35.700
Sirius flung webs down onto his back, his

00:14:35.700 --> 00:14:38.759
icicle sharp claws flexed, ready to tear

00:14:38.759 --> 00:14:39.899
into Web's underbelly.

00:14:39.960 --> 00:14:43.620
Suddenly, crocodile cannoned into him

00:14:43.620 --> 00:14:45.600
knocking Sirius into the undergrowth.

00:14:45.659 --> 00:14:47.580
Webbs didn't hesitate.

00:14:47.639 --> 00:14:50.519
He flipped upright and shot into the sky

00:14:50.519 --> 00:14:52.919
as fast as his wings could carry him.

00:14:52.980 --> 00:14:56.100
He heard shouts as crocodiles struck out

00:14:56.100 --> 00:14:58.259
at the dragons around her, and he felt a

00:14:58.259 --> 00:14:58.919
stab of guilt.

00:14:58.980 --> 00:15:00.779
Should he stay to help her fight?

00:15:00.899 --> 00:15:04.679
But why go back for death when he had a

00:15:04.679 --> 00:15:05.340
chance at life?

00:15:05.399 --> 00:15:09.240
He heard wing beats behind him and flew

00:15:09.240 --> 00:15:09.600
harder.

00:15:09.659 --> 00:15:12.419
He imagined Sirius breathing down his

00:15:12.419 --> 00:15:15.360
tail, or Nautilus hissing closer and

00:15:15.360 --> 00:15:15.840
closer.

00:15:15.899 --> 00:15:18.539
But it was crocodile's voice who called

00:15:18.539 --> 00:15:18.840
to him.

00:15:18.899 --> 00:15:21.179
Fly, Webbs.

00:15:21.240 --> 00:15:22.080
She cried.

00:15:22.139 --> 00:15:23.399
I've knocked them out.

00:15:23.460 --> 00:15:24.899
They didn't see that coming.

00:15:24.960 --> 00:15:25.799
Ha!

00:15:25.919 --> 00:15:27.059
Thank you.

00:15:27.120 --> 00:15:28.500
Webb called back.

00:15:28.559 --> 00:15:31.200
Twisting to see her heavy brown shapes

00:15:31.200 --> 00:15:32.039
soaring behind him.

00:15:32.100 --> 00:15:34.019
Where will you hide?

00:15:34.139 --> 00:15:36.539
she asked He shook his head.

00:15:36.600 --> 00:15:38.039
I have no idea.

00:15:38.100 --> 00:15:40.500
I've heard there's a dragon in Jade

00:15:40.500 --> 00:15:42.480
Mountain who might, you should go home

00:15:42.480 --> 00:15:43.500
she said.

00:15:43.559 --> 00:15:46.200
Tilting her wings to swoop under him.

00:15:46.259 --> 00:15:49.679
From what I hear, Queen Coral is in a

00:15:49.679 --> 00:15:50.639
merciful mood these days.

00:15:50.700 --> 00:15:54.240
The thrill that ran through webs from

00:15:54.240 --> 00:15:56.519
horns to tail nearly took his breath

00:15:56.519 --> 00:15:56.820
away.

00:15:56.940 --> 00:16:02.039
Home, back to the sea, after all these

00:16:02.039 --> 00:16:04.259
years, is it possible?

00:16:04.320 --> 00:16:07.080
She'll never forgive me.

00:16:07.139 --> 00:16:10.080
Not after everything I did, he said.

00:16:10.200 --> 00:16:13.320
It's not just that I deserted her during

00:16:13.320 --> 00:16:13.860
a battle.

00:16:13.919 --> 00:16:17.159
She must know I was the one who stole her

00:16:17.159 --> 00:16:18.179
egg for the prophecy.

00:16:18.299 --> 00:16:21.840
You might be surprised, said Crocodile.

00:16:21.899 --> 00:16:24.179
Isn't she supposed to be one of the

00:16:24.179 --> 00:16:25.559
greatest queens in history?

00:16:25.620 --> 00:16:28.080
That's what all the sea wing scrolls

00:16:28.080 --> 00:16:28.440
say.

00:16:28.500 --> 00:16:30.179
Perhaps she'll forgive you.

00:16:30.240 --> 00:16:31.919
Why not take the chance?

00:16:32.039 --> 00:16:33.899
If it means you can go home again.

00:16:34.019 --> 00:16:36.120
Webbs was silent.

00:16:36.240 --> 00:16:40.080
One of the moons was rising, shimmering

00:16:40.080 --> 00:16:41.460
off his blue green scales.

00:16:41.580 --> 00:16:44.039
From up here, he could see the ocean.

00:16:44.100 --> 00:16:47.639
Far off in the distance, but it seemed as

00:16:47.639 --> 00:16:49.440
unreachable as the moon itself.

00:16:49.440 --> 00:16:53.039
Up to you, Crocodile said.

00:16:53.100 --> 00:16:54.539
Banking away from him.

00:16:54.600 --> 00:16:56.700
Now, I'm just telling you what I've

00:16:56.700 --> 00:16:56.940
heard.

00:16:57.000 --> 00:16:58.139
Good luck.

00:16:58.200 --> 00:16:58.919
Either way.

00:16:58.980 --> 00:17:00.840
Good luck to you too.

00:17:00.899 --> 00:17:02.220
Webbs called.

00:17:02.279 --> 00:17:04.500
She vanished into the trees.

00:17:04.559 --> 00:17:06.539
And he wondered where she would go now.

00:17:06.599 --> 00:17:10.259
He missed the sea with every scale on his

00:17:10.259 --> 00:17:10.499
body.

00:17:10.619 --> 00:17:14.579
He missed the palaces, the currents, the

00:17:14.579 --> 00:17:17.939
whale songs, the feasts, the gardens.

00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:22.920
The other sea wings, If the talons are

00:17:22.920 --> 00:17:23.400
done with me.

00:17:23.460 --> 00:17:27.059
If I promise her, I'll be brave this

00:17:27.059 --> 00:17:27.359
time.

00:17:27.420 --> 00:17:31.619
Maybe, I can go home again.

00:17:31.680 --> 00:17:36.240
Part one.

00:17:36.299 --> 00:17:38.220
The edge of the ocean.

00:17:38.339 --> 00:17:40.799
Chapter one.

00:17:40.859 --> 00:17:44.940
A wave roared onto the beach and crashed

00:17:44.940 --> 00:17:48.119
around Tsunami's talons, her webbed claws

00:17:48.119 --> 00:17:51.000
sank into the wet sand, her blue wings

00:17:51.000 --> 00:17:52.019
billowed in the wind.

00:17:52.079 --> 00:17:55.380
She lifted her head, breathing in the

00:17:55.380 --> 00:17:56.400
wild sea air.

00:17:56.460 --> 00:17:59.460
This was where she was supposed to be.

00:17:59.519 --> 00:18:01.500
This was her ocean.

00:18:01.559 --> 00:18:06.599
Let me guess, Glory said mockingly behind

00:18:06.599 --> 00:18:06.960
her.

00:18:07.019 --> 00:18:10.859
You guys, that's the smell of freedom.

00:18:10.920 --> 00:18:15.660
Freedom, smells a lot like fish, Starfly

00:18:15.660 --> 00:18:18.599
observed, which, to be clear, is kind of

00:18:18.599 --> 00:18:19.920
nose curlingly awful.

00:18:19.980 --> 00:18:23.160
I love it, tsunami said.

00:18:23.279 --> 00:18:26.579
This was what the talons of peace had

00:18:26.579 --> 00:18:27.299
stolen from her.

00:18:27.359 --> 00:18:30.420
They'd kept her trapped in the stale

00:18:30.420 --> 00:18:32.400
dreary air under the mountain her whole

00:18:32.400 --> 00:18:34.799
life when she was meant to be out here

00:18:34.799 --> 00:18:38.099
flying and swimming, and living like a

00:18:38.099 --> 00:18:38.940
real sea wing.

00:18:39.000 --> 00:18:42.660
Starflight glanced up at the sky and

00:18:42.660 --> 00:18:44.759
edged back toward the dark foliage that

00:18:44.759 --> 00:18:45.539
lined the beach.

00:18:45.599 --> 00:18:48.299
Shouldn't we stay under the trees?

00:18:48.359 --> 00:18:50.099
What if a patrol spots us?

00:18:50.160 --> 00:18:53.099
I mean, he stopped and took a deep

00:18:53.099 --> 00:18:53.460
breath.

00:18:53.519 --> 00:18:56.460
We must stay under the trees.

00:18:56.519 --> 00:18:59.460
All right, yes, everyone back into the

00:18:59.460 --> 00:19:00.599
trees right now.

00:19:00.660 --> 00:19:03.059
The others ignored him.

00:19:03.119 --> 00:19:05.460
Although Sunny gave him a pitying

00:19:05.460 --> 00:19:05.759
glance.

00:19:05.819 --> 00:19:08.759
Tsunami bent her head to study the waves

00:19:08.759 --> 00:19:12.059
washing over her talons, small shapes

00:19:12.059 --> 00:19:14.400
silver and green and yellow, darted

00:19:14.400 --> 00:19:15.059
through the shallows.

00:19:15.119 --> 00:19:18.240
The ocean smelled much more alive than

00:19:18.240 --> 00:19:19.200
the cave river.

00:19:19.259 --> 00:19:22.559
Was it only a week since they'd run away

00:19:22.559 --> 00:19:23.579
from their guardians?

00:19:23.640 --> 00:19:26.160
It was hard to remember exactly how long

00:19:26.160 --> 00:19:27.839
they'd been trapped in the Sky Wing

00:19:27.839 --> 00:19:28.140
prison.

00:19:28.200 --> 00:19:30.599
But there was one thing tsunami

00:19:30.599 --> 00:19:31.619
remembered clearly.

00:19:31.680 --> 00:19:35.099
The sound of bone, snapping under her

00:19:35.099 --> 00:19:35.460
talons.

00:19:35.519 --> 00:19:38.400
She poked a hole in the sand with her

00:19:38.400 --> 00:19:38.940
claw.

00:19:39.000 --> 00:19:40.980
I had to kill that ceiling.

00:19:41.039 --> 00:19:43.619
Queen Scarlet forced us to fight.

00:19:43.740 --> 00:19:46.619
There was no other way out of the arena.

00:19:46.680 --> 00:19:47.759
He was crazy.

00:19:47.819 --> 00:19:50.700
It was him, or me.

00:19:50.759 --> 00:19:54.720
The same thoughts kept circling in her

00:19:54.720 --> 00:19:56.519
head like lame winged dragons.

00:19:56.579 --> 00:19:59.279
She shook her head and flared her wings.

00:19:59.339 --> 00:20:01.140
This was ridiculous.

00:20:01.200 --> 00:20:03.720
Was she a dragon or a scavenger?

00:20:03.779 --> 00:20:06.240
Dragons were meant to be fierce

00:20:06.240 --> 00:20:06.720
warriors.

00:20:06.779 --> 00:20:09.660
One little death shouldn't rattle her so

00:20:09.660 --> 00:20:09.839
much.

00:20:09.900 --> 00:20:13.500
Besides, glory had done worse with her

00:20:13.500 --> 00:20:15.480
deadly venom, and she didn't seem

00:20:15.480 --> 00:20:16.140
bothered at all.

00:20:16.200 --> 00:20:18.960
You know what I love?

00:20:19.079 --> 00:20:21.119
Clay said mournfully.

00:20:21.180 --> 00:20:22.380
Fish.

00:20:22.440 --> 00:20:24.480
Lots of fish.

00:20:24.539 --> 00:20:26.759
Big fish I can eat.

00:20:26.819 --> 00:20:29.339
Not these little wriggle scraps.

00:20:29.400 --> 00:20:33.000
The mudwings sat down on the sand beside

00:20:33.000 --> 00:20:33.660
tsunami.

00:20:33.720 --> 00:20:36.359
His stomach growled loud enough for all

00:20:36.359 --> 00:20:36.900
of them to hear.

00:20:36.960 --> 00:20:39.119
Sonny giggled.

00:20:39.180 --> 00:20:42.059
Clay, it's only been a day since you

00:20:42.059 --> 00:20:44.099
caught that enormous pig for all of us.

00:20:44.160 --> 00:20:46.920
Wasn't enormous.

00:20:46.980 --> 00:20:48.420
Clay said.

00:20:48.480 --> 00:20:51.299
He sighed, his wings drooping.

00:20:51.359 --> 00:20:54.420
That was the smallest pig in the whole

00:20:54.420 --> 00:20:55.319
world.

00:20:55.380 --> 00:20:58.079
You should have eaten my carrots.

00:20:58.140 --> 00:21:01.380
Sonny clambered up to sit on his back and

00:21:01.380 --> 00:21:02.460
peer out at the ocean.

00:21:02.519 --> 00:21:05.819
The sun was just rising in a peach pale

00:21:05.819 --> 00:21:08.819
sky, casting broken paths of light across

00:21:08.819 --> 00:21:09.240
the water.

00:21:09.359 --> 00:21:13.380
Two of the moons barely slivers like thin

00:21:13.380 --> 00:21:15.359
claws were vanishing behind the

00:21:15.359 --> 00:21:15.720
mountains.

00:21:15.779 --> 00:21:19.980
I'm serious, everybody, Starflight said.

00:21:20.039 --> 00:21:22.140
It's not safe out on the beach.

00:21:22.200 --> 00:21:24.539
Not with all the mud wings and sky wings

00:21:24.539 --> 00:21:25.019
looking for us.

00:21:25.079 --> 00:21:28.259
The Night Wing was standing well out of

00:21:28.259 --> 00:21:30.599
reach of the waves, trying to shake sand

00:21:30.599 --> 00:21:31.440
off his talons.

00:21:31.559 --> 00:21:35.039
As far as tsunami was concerned, they'd

00:21:35.039 --> 00:21:37.140
already wasted a day flying south of the

00:21:37.140 --> 00:21:38.460
diamond spray delta.

00:21:38.519 --> 00:21:41.099
Basically because Starflight had worried

00:21:41.099 --> 00:21:42.960
and complained until everyone agreed.

00:21:43.019 --> 00:21:46.019
Yes, the sky wings were after them.

00:21:46.079 --> 00:21:49.799
Yes, they were probably mad about the

00:21:49.799 --> 00:21:52.079
Dragonette's escape from Skywing Prison

00:21:52.079 --> 00:21:55.319
and they were pretty definitely mad about

00:21:55.319 --> 00:21:57.660
the part where Glory maybe killed their

00:21:57.660 --> 00:21:58.559
queen on the way out.

00:21:58.619 --> 00:22:01.200
But tsunami didn't want to keep running.

00:22:01.259 --> 00:22:03.240
She wanted to find her family.

00:22:03.359 --> 00:22:06.839
Once they knew who she was, she was sure

00:22:06.839 --> 00:22:08.819
the sea wings would protect her and her

00:22:08.819 --> 00:22:09.000
friends.

00:22:09.119 --> 00:22:12.900
Most of all, she really wanted Starflight

00:22:12.900 --> 00:22:14.940
to stop fretting, complaining, and

00:22:14.940 --> 00:22:15.480
bossing.

00:22:15.539 --> 00:22:18.660
It made the others nervous and harder to

00:22:18.660 --> 00:22:19.140
organize.

00:22:19.200 --> 00:22:22.200
She almost wished the night wings hadn't

00:22:22.200 --> 00:22:22.619
given him back.

00:22:22.680 --> 00:22:25.799
Why are you so worried?

00:22:25.859 --> 00:22:28.740
Tsunami asked him, if they do recapture

00:22:28.740 --> 00:22:30.720
us, won't your nightwing friends come

00:22:30.720 --> 00:22:32.160
swooping in to rescue you again?

00:22:32.220 --> 00:22:34.980
Starflight fluttered his wings

00:22:34.980 --> 00:22:35.759
indignantly.

00:22:35.819 --> 00:22:38.880
I'm not worried for me, he said.

00:22:38.940 --> 00:22:41.339
I'm trying to keep all of us safe.

00:22:41.400 --> 00:22:44.579
He glanced at Sonny and ducked his head.

00:22:44.640 --> 00:22:48.960
I'm keeping us safe just fine, tsunami

00:22:48.960 --> 00:22:49.559
protested.

00:22:49.619 --> 00:22:51.420
When have I ever led us wrong?

00:22:51.480 --> 00:22:56.519
Well, glory pointed out, there was that

00:22:56.519 --> 00:22:59.519
one time we got captured by Sky Wings and

00:22:59.519 --> 00:23:01.079
their queen nearly killed us all.

00:23:01.140 --> 00:23:04.259
Tsunami smacked her tail into the water

00:23:04.259 --> 00:23:06.420
to send a cold wave over glory.

00:23:06.480 --> 00:23:08.700
The rain wing hissed and jumped away from

00:23:08.700 --> 00:23:09.059
the sea.

00:23:09.119 --> 00:23:12.000
Stop it, Sonny said.

00:23:12.059 --> 00:23:13.980
Stop fighting, all of you.

00:23:14.039 --> 00:23:15.180
Clay, stop them.

00:23:15.299 --> 00:23:17.880
She patted the top of his head to pull

00:23:17.880 --> 00:23:19.740
his attention back from the tiny fish

00:23:19.740 --> 00:23:21.000
swimming around his feet.

00:23:21.059 --> 00:23:25.140
Oh yes, let's hear from our big wings.

00:23:25.259 --> 00:23:26.519
Glory teased.

00:23:26.579 --> 00:23:29.400
Her scales this morning were gold, like

00:23:29.400 --> 00:23:31.920
sunny's, but with drifting splashes of

00:23:31.920 --> 00:23:34.799
ocean blue, she sat down and yawned at

00:23:34.799 --> 00:23:37.559
tsunami, displaying her venom spitting

00:23:37.559 --> 00:23:37.799
teeth.

00:23:37.859 --> 00:23:42.660
Hey, Clay said, nudging tsunami's wing

00:23:42.660 --> 00:23:43.019
with his own.

00:23:43.140 --> 00:23:46.200
It's all right for Starflight to worry.

00:23:46.259 --> 00:23:48.960
We don't even know if Queen Scarlet is

00:23:48.960 --> 00:23:49.799
alive or dead.

00:23:49.859 --> 00:23:52.619
But, he added quickly.

00:23:52.680 --> 00:23:55.440
I know you want to find the sea wings as

00:23:55.440 --> 00:23:56.339
fast as possible.

00:23:56.400 --> 00:23:58.859
So let's find them instead of fighting

00:23:58.859 --> 00:24:01.200
about it, and then we can get to safety

00:24:01.200 --> 00:24:01.559
sooner.

00:24:01.619 --> 00:24:05.880
Tsunami shot one more narrow eyed look at

00:24:05.880 --> 00:24:07.799
Starflight, then turned back to the

00:24:07.799 --> 00:24:08.099
ocean.

00:24:08.160 --> 00:24:09.480
Clay was right.

00:24:09.539 --> 00:24:11.700
The important thing was to find her

00:24:11.700 --> 00:24:13.680
family and a safe place for them all to

00:24:13.680 --> 00:24:13.980
hide.

00:24:14.099 --> 00:24:19.799
Oh, Glory said, so wise and big.

00:24:19.859 --> 00:24:22.079
I think he is.

00:24:22.140 --> 00:24:25.140
Sonny said, wrapping her forearms around

00:24:25.140 --> 00:24:26.039
Clay's neck.

00:24:26.160 --> 00:24:29.279
Starflight sat down, flipping his tail

00:24:29.279 --> 00:24:30.900
around his talons unhappily.

00:24:30.960 --> 00:24:33.599
Glory settled her sun colored wings.

00:24:33.720 --> 00:24:35.819
So now what?

00:24:35.880 --> 00:24:39.359
Should we shout, hey, sea wings, we've

00:24:39.359 --> 00:24:41.700
got your missing princess, and wait for

00:24:41.700 --> 00:24:43.740
dragons to bound joyfully out of the

00:24:43.740 --> 00:24:44.039
ocean?

00:24:44.160 --> 00:24:49.019
With a feast, Clay cried, startling a

00:24:49.019 --> 00:24:50.039
seagull into the air.

00:24:50.099 --> 00:24:52.740
There was a feast at the end of the

00:24:52.740 --> 00:24:53.039
story.

00:24:53.099 --> 00:24:55.740
When the missing sea wing princess got

00:24:55.740 --> 00:24:58.799
home, her parents were so happy they made

00:24:58.799 --> 00:24:59.279
a feast.

00:24:59.339 --> 00:25:01.500
I remember the feast.

00:25:01.559 --> 00:25:03.720
They ate a whole whale.

00:25:03.779 --> 00:25:05.880
That was a good feast.

00:25:05.940 --> 00:25:08.279
I bet I could eat a whale.

00:25:08.339 --> 00:25:10.200
Do you think we'll get a feast?

00:25:10.259 --> 00:25:13.559
The missing princess was just a story in

00:25:13.559 --> 00:25:15.539
a scroll, Starflight said.

00:25:15.599 --> 00:25:18.059
We have no idea what we'll actually find

00:25:18.059 --> 00:25:19.259
in the kingdom of the sea.

00:25:19.319 --> 00:25:21.180
That's true.

00:25:21.240 --> 00:25:23.880
Clay's wings drooped.

00:25:23.940 --> 00:25:26.519
It might not be what you're hoping for

00:25:26.519 --> 00:25:27.119
tsunami.

00:25:27.180 --> 00:25:30.660
Like, finding out my mother sold me for a

00:25:30.660 --> 00:25:31.140
cow.

00:25:31.200 --> 00:25:36.359
Hey, said Glory, it was at least 2 cows.

00:25:36.480 --> 00:25:40.500
Hmm, comforting, said Clay.

00:25:40.559 --> 00:25:43.319
It wouldn't be like that for tsunami.

00:25:43.380 --> 00:25:46.799
She was sure of it Maybe Clay's dreams of

00:25:46.799 --> 00:25:49.079
his family had turned out all wrong, but

00:25:49.079 --> 00:25:51.779
hers would be perfect, especially now

00:25:51.779 --> 00:25:53.640
that she knew her egg had been stolen

00:25:53.640 --> 00:25:55.079
from the royal hatchery.

00:25:55.259 --> 00:25:58.319
She was the daughter of the sea wing

00:25:58.319 --> 00:25:59.099
queen.

00:25:59.160 --> 00:26:01.920
Not only that, but according to

00:26:01.920 --> 00:26:04.500
Starflight, none of the Queen's other

00:26:04.500 --> 00:26:06.900
female dragonettes had survived to

00:26:06.900 --> 00:26:07.380
adulthood.

00:26:07.440 --> 00:26:10.619
Tsunami was the only living heir to the

00:26:10.619 --> 00:26:11.519
Sea Wing kingdom.

00:26:11.579 --> 00:26:14.759
One day, she would be queen of the sea

00:26:14.759 --> 00:26:15.240
wings.

00:26:15.299 --> 00:26:18.779
True, that meant one day she'd have to

00:26:18.779 --> 00:26:20.400
fight her own mother to the death to

00:26:20.400 --> 00:26:22.980
become queen, but that day could be as

00:26:22.980 --> 00:26:24.359
far off as she wanted it to be.

00:26:24.420 --> 00:26:26.339
Not something she had to think about

00:26:26.339 --> 00:26:26.579
now.

00:26:26.640 --> 00:26:30.299
She spread her wings and breathed in the

00:26:30.299 --> 00:26:31.500
salt spray air again.

00:26:31.559 --> 00:26:33.720
Out of the corner of her eyes.

00:26:33.779 --> 00:26:36.420
She kept seeing tiny creatures pop out of

00:26:36.420 --> 00:26:38.339
the speckled sand and then vanish again.

00:26:38.400 --> 00:26:41.759
I could just dive in and look for the

00:26:41.759 --> 00:26:42.660
ceiling palace.

00:26:42.720 --> 00:26:44.099
Tsunami suggested.

00:26:44.160 --> 00:26:46.319
Out there?

00:26:46.380 --> 00:26:48.660
Starflight sounded alarmed.

00:26:48.779 --> 00:26:50.940
He spread his wings and shook sand off

00:26:50.940 --> 00:26:52.859
them, blinking anxiously.

00:26:52.920 --> 00:26:55.920
Where else do you suggest I find the sea

00:26:55.920 --> 00:26:56.460
wings?

00:26:56.519 --> 00:26:57.119
She asked.

00:26:57.180 --> 00:27:00.420
Swimming in the ocean is not like

00:27:00.420 --> 00:27:02.160
swimming in an underground cave river.

00:27:02.220 --> 00:27:03.779
Starflight lectured.

00:27:03.839 --> 00:27:06.119
There are strong currents and

00:27:06.119 --> 00:27:09.299
unpredictable waves, and and big things

00:27:09.299 --> 00:27:11.940
with teeth, I'm a big thing with teeth.

00:27:12.059 --> 00:27:13.920
Tsunami grinned at him.

00:27:14.039 --> 00:27:15.299
He didn't laugh.

00:27:15.359 --> 00:27:18.180
It's not safe, he said.

00:27:18.240 --> 00:27:19.859
What if we lose you?

00:27:19.920 --> 00:27:23.039
Tsunami wanted to poke his wrinkled up

00:27:23.039 --> 00:27:24.900
worried snout with our sharpest claw?

00:27:24.960 --> 00:27:26.700
Starflight?

00:27:26.759 --> 00:27:27.420
Cheer up.

00:27:27.539 --> 00:27:28.680
Sonny interjected.

00:27:28.740 --> 00:27:30.480
Tsunami can do anything.

00:27:30.539 --> 00:27:32.519
And how is she supposed to get home to

00:27:32.519 --> 00:27:34.259
her family if she can't go into the sea?

00:27:34.319 --> 00:27:36.240
Oh no.

00:27:36.359 --> 00:27:38.700
Clay heaved himself to his feet

00:27:38.759 --> 00:27:41.220
scattering sand and nearly dislodging

00:27:41.220 --> 00:27:43.380
Sonny, who grabbed his neck with a yelp.

00:27:43.500 --> 00:27:46.799
Sand and seashells and tiny, astonished

00:27:46.799 --> 00:27:49.019
crabs flew through the air as he lashed

00:27:49.019 --> 00:27:49.380
his tail.

00:27:49.440 --> 00:27:51.660
Ow, stop that.

00:27:51.779 --> 00:27:54.359
Glory commanded, covering her eyes.

00:27:54.420 --> 00:27:56.099
What about us?

00:27:56.220 --> 00:27:59.339
Clay's big brown wings flapped.

00:27:59.400 --> 00:28:01.079
I didn't think of that.

00:28:01.140 --> 00:28:02.759
Tsunami.

00:28:02.819 --> 00:28:05.160
We can't go with you to the Sea Wing

00:28:05.160 --> 00:28:05.819
Palace.

00:28:05.880 --> 00:28:07.440
We can't breathe down there.

00:28:07.500 --> 00:28:10.019
How can we stick together if you're

00:28:10.019 --> 00:28:10.619
underwater?

00:28:10.680 --> 00:28:13.980
He clawed at the water, leaving deep

00:28:13.980 --> 00:28:15.420
gouges in the wet sand.

00:28:15.480 --> 00:28:17.339
What are we going to do?

00:28:17.400 --> 00:28:20.700
Tsunami kind of adored Clay when he was

00:28:20.700 --> 00:28:21.480
in a tizzy.

00:28:21.539 --> 00:28:24.180
She also adored that it had taken an

00:28:24.180 --> 00:28:26.579
entire day for it to occur to him that

00:28:26.579 --> 00:28:28.619
the kingdom of the sea was underwater.

00:28:28.619 --> 00:28:30.779
Seriously?

00:28:30.839 --> 00:28:32.759
Glory said to Clay.

00:28:32.819 --> 00:28:36.119
All of those geography lessons, and not a

00:28:36.119 --> 00:28:37.380
single one sunk in.

00:28:37.500 --> 00:28:40.559
Clay turned in a confused circle.

00:28:40.619 --> 00:28:43.140
Crabs scurried out of the way of his

00:28:43.140 --> 00:28:44.339
giant talons.

00:28:44.400 --> 00:28:45.299
What?

00:28:45.420 --> 00:28:48.900
The sea wings have an above water palace

00:28:48.900 --> 00:28:52.799
too, Starflight said, in his, see, you

00:28:52.799 --> 00:28:54.420
should have studied more, voice.

00:28:54.539 --> 00:28:57.599
So they can receive guests, like their

00:28:57.599 --> 00:28:59.579
sandwing ally blister?

00:28:59.640 --> 00:29:01.440
It's on an island somewhere in the Bay of

00:29:01.440 --> 00:29:02.160
a 1000 scales.

00:29:02.279 --> 00:29:04.380
Oh.

00:29:04.500 --> 00:29:07.500
Clay sat down with a whooshing sigh.

00:29:07.559 --> 00:29:09.359
Sonny patted his shoulder.

00:29:09.420 --> 00:29:12.240
I didn't remember that either, she

00:29:12.240 --> 00:29:12.720
offered.

00:29:12.779 --> 00:29:15.000
So we go there, right?

00:29:15.059 --> 00:29:18.839
Not easily, Starflight said.

00:29:18.900 --> 00:29:22.259
Both sea wing palaces, underwater, and on

00:29:22.259 --> 00:29:23.759
land are well hidden.

00:29:23.819 --> 00:29:26.460
That's how they've lasted so long in this

00:29:26.460 --> 00:29:26.640
war.

00:29:26.700 --> 00:29:28.740
Even though they don't have fire like the

00:29:28.740 --> 00:29:29.339
other tribes.

00:29:29.400 --> 00:29:31.440
Nobody can find them to attack their

00:29:31.440 --> 00:29:31.740
homes.

00:29:31.799 --> 00:29:35.759
Sounds like the Night Wings, Glory

00:29:35.759 --> 00:29:36.299
sniped.

00:29:36.359 --> 00:29:39.720
It's nothing like the Night Wings, tsunami

00:29:39.720 --> 00:29:40.140
cried.

00:29:40.259 --> 00:29:42.240
Seawings aren't trying to act all

00:29:42.240 --> 00:29:43.619
mysterious and pretentious.

00:29:43.680 --> 00:29:45.299
They're just being sensible about

00:29:45.299 --> 00:29:46.019
guarding their home.

00:29:46.079 --> 00:29:49.619
There are over a 1000 islands to search

00:29:49.619 --> 00:29:51.420
but it's still probably.

00:29:51.480 --> 00:29:54.900
Starflight stopped mid-sentence and

00:29:54.900 --> 00:29:56.099
glanced to the sky again.

00:29:56.160 --> 00:29:58.980
Does anyone else smell fire?

00:29:59.099 --> 00:30:01.799
Three moon Starfight?

00:30:01.859 --> 00:30:03.539
I'm not hiding in the trees every time

00:30:03.539 --> 00:30:05.880
some little things spooks you, tsunami

00:30:05.880 --> 00:30:06.119
said.

00:30:06.180 --> 00:30:07.680
Wait.

00:30:07.740 --> 00:30:11.160
I think he's right, Sonny said, lifting

00:30:11.160 --> 00:30:11.460
her head.

00:30:11.519 --> 00:30:13.500
I hear wing beats.

00:30:13.559 --> 00:30:15.180
I do too.

00:30:15.240 --> 00:30:16.619
Starflight said.

00:30:16.680 --> 00:30:19.559
The spiny ridge along his back, stood up

00:30:19.559 --> 00:30:21.779
in alarm, and he bolted for the trees

00:30:21.779 --> 00:30:24.059
running as fast as he could.

00:30:24.119 --> 00:30:25.559
From this far away?

00:30:25.680 --> 00:30:27.720
tsunami said skeptically.

00:30:27.779 --> 00:30:29.279
I don't see anything up there.

00:30:29.400 --> 00:30:33.000
But just as she said it, she spotted a

00:30:33.000 --> 00:30:35.400
cluster of red specks like spattered

00:30:35.400 --> 00:30:38.039
blood in the sky, winging down from the

00:30:38.039 --> 00:30:40.799
mountains in the northwest, a Skywing

00:30:40.799 --> 00:30:42.000
patrol was coming their way.

00:30:42.059 --> 00:30:46.440
Chapter 2.

00:30:46.740 --> 00:30:49.619
Quick, into the water.

00:30:49.680 --> 00:30:51.180
Tsunami ordered.

00:30:51.240 --> 00:30:53.640
It was closer than the trees, and would

00:30:53.640 --> 00:30:54.779
hide them just as well.

00:30:54.839 --> 00:30:58.019
No way, said Glory.

00:30:58.079 --> 00:31:00.720
She sank to the ground, spreading her

00:31:00.720 --> 00:31:02.460
wings and shifted color.

00:31:02.519 --> 00:31:05.519
Her scales flowed into the rocky, sandy

00:31:05.519 --> 00:31:07.380
pattern below her until she was

00:31:07.380 --> 00:31:09.660
impossible to see, especially from the

00:31:09.660 --> 00:31:10.140
air.

00:31:10.200 --> 00:31:13.440
It happened so fast, tsunami nearly lost

00:31:13.440 --> 00:31:14.460
track of where she was.

00:31:14.519 --> 00:31:16.680
Glory was getting better at that trick.

00:31:16.740 --> 00:31:18.599
Fine.

00:31:18.660 --> 00:31:19.619
Come on, sonny.

00:31:19.680 --> 00:31:21.660
Tsunami reached for the little sand

00:31:21.660 --> 00:31:22.019
wing.

00:31:22.079 --> 00:31:25.079
I'd rather not, Sonny squeaked.

00:31:25.140 --> 00:31:26.519
I can make it to the trees.

00:31:26.579 --> 00:31:27.900
I'll fly really fast.

00:31:28.019 --> 00:31:30.599
She jumped off Clay's back and flapped

00:31:30.599 --> 00:31:31.619
after Starflight.

00:31:31.680 --> 00:31:34.859
Tsunami stamped her foot, spraying ocean

00:31:34.859 --> 00:31:37.319
water across the sand, glory made a

00:31:37.319 --> 00:31:38.400
muffled, grumpy noise.

00:31:38.460 --> 00:31:41.039
It'll be safer in the sea.

00:31:41.099 --> 00:31:42.480
Tsunami huffed.

00:31:42.539 --> 00:31:44.759
She cast a worried look at the sky.

00:31:44.819 --> 00:31:46.980
The specks were getting closer, fast.

00:31:47.039 --> 00:31:50.160
Maybe faster than Sonny could hide, but

00:31:50.160 --> 00:31:51.420
it was too late to catch her now.

00:31:51.480 --> 00:31:54.180
Tsunami turned and dove into the ocean.

00:31:54.240 --> 00:31:57.059
Clay was already burrowing into the

00:31:57.059 --> 00:31:59.700
shallow mud shelf, displacing startled

00:31:59.700 --> 00:32:01.619
flatfish and sending up clouds of

00:32:01.619 --> 00:32:02.160
minnows.

00:32:02.220 --> 00:32:04.559
The mudwing didn't have a problem with

00:32:04.559 --> 00:32:06.839
water like the others did, since he could

00:32:06.839 --> 00:32:08.220
hold his breath for up to an hour.

00:32:08.279 --> 00:32:12.000
Tsunami breathed in and salt water rushed

00:32:12.000 --> 00:32:12.599
into her gills.

00:32:12.660 --> 00:32:16.200
It surprised her how sharp it felt, like

00:32:16.200 --> 00:32:17.279
inhaling smoke.

00:32:17.339 --> 00:32:20.400
It was nothing like the crystal clear

00:32:20.400 --> 00:32:23.099
water of the underground cave.

00:32:23.160 --> 00:32:25.140
What's more, the current kept trying to

00:32:25.140 --> 00:32:27.420
shove her back to the beach, then yank

00:32:27.420 --> 00:32:27.960
her out again.

00:32:28.019 --> 00:32:31.380
But she plowed forward and down, past

00:32:31.380 --> 00:32:34.319
clay, beating her wings as the water got

00:32:34.319 --> 00:32:34.740
deeper.

00:32:34.799 --> 00:32:38.579
Schools of tiny purple fish whirled away

00:32:38.579 --> 00:32:41.519
from her like stars exploding. over the

00:32:41.519 --> 00:32:42.779
edge of the sand shelf.

00:32:42.839 --> 00:32:45.180
The deeper ocean floor was covered in

00:32:45.180 --> 00:32:46.619
bundles of eel grass.

00:32:46.740 --> 00:32:49.500
Waving dark green tendrils reached up to

00:32:49.500 --> 00:32:51.059
brush tsunami's underbelly.

00:32:51.119 --> 00:32:53.519
She glanced up at the sky above her.

00:32:53.579 --> 00:32:56.460
Still empty, and decided to risk

00:32:56.460 --> 00:32:59.400
surfacing, she had to be sure Sonny was

00:32:59.400 --> 00:33:00.000
safely hidden.

00:33:00.059 --> 00:33:03.299
The thunder of wing beats echoed in her

00:33:03.299 --> 00:33:05.640
ears as she poked her head out and turned

00:33:05.640 --> 00:33:06.359
toward the beach.

00:33:06.420 --> 00:33:09.180
The little sand wing was almost to

00:33:09.180 --> 00:33:09.359
safety.

00:33:09.420 --> 00:33:12.059
Tsunami could see Starflight standing

00:33:12.059 --> 00:33:14.519
under the trees, reaching his front claws

00:33:14.519 --> 00:33:15.779
out to pull Sonny in.

00:33:15.839 --> 00:33:19.740
Overhead, an orange shape shot past

00:33:19.740 --> 00:33:22.920
flying at full sky wing speed, faster

00:33:22.920 --> 00:33:24.539
than any other tribe could fly.

00:33:24.599 --> 00:33:27.599
A red dragon flew close behind the first

00:33:27.599 --> 00:33:29.099
followed by 3 more.

00:33:29.160 --> 00:33:32.700
Their enormous wings nearly blotted out

00:33:32.700 --> 00:33:34.799
the sun as they whooshed over the

00:33:34.799 --> 00:33:36.059
dragonette's heads.

00:33:36.119 --> 00:33:39.539
Tsunami sank a bit lower in the water, but

00:33:39.539 --> 00:33:41.400
it seemed like the patrol was going too

00:33:41.400 --> 00:33:43.799
fast to notice a lone sea wing in the

00:33:43.799 --> 00:33:44.039
ocean.

00:33:44.099 --> 00:33:47.039
Maybe these soldiers weren't hunting for

00:33:47.039 --> 00:33:48.000
the escaped prisoners.

00:33:48.059 --> 00:33:50.759
Then she saw the last dragon.

00:33:50.819 --> 00:33:54.420
Sunset orange, flames flickering from his

00:33:54.420 --> 00:33:57.119
nose, with a jagged tear on the tip of

00:33:57.119 --> 00:33:57.779
his left wing.

00:33:57.839 --> 00:34:01.200
He flew slower than the others, bringing

00:34:01.200 --> 00:34:03.720
up the rear, and his head swung back and

00:34:03.720 --> 00:34:06.359
forth, dark eyes searching the ground

00:34:06.359 --> 00:34:07.019
below them.

00:34:07.079 --> 00:34:09.780
Tsunami found herself holding her

00:34:09.780 --> 00:34:10.260
breath.

00:34:10.320 --> 00:34:13.500
The Skywing's snout swung toward the

00:34:13.500 --> 00:34:16.380
trees just as Sonny's tail whisked out of

00:34:16.380 --> 00:34:16.619
sight.

00:34:16.739 --> 00:34:18.119
He paused.

00:34:18.239 --> 00:34:20.819
Beating his wings back to hover in the

00:34:20.819 --> 00:34:21.419
air for a moment.

00:34:21.480 --> 00:34:23.880
Was he staring at the trees?

00:34:24.000 --> 00:34:25.860
Had he seen Sonny?

00:34:25.920 --> 00:34:28.320
What if he called the others back?

00:34:28.380 --> 00:34:31.440
The patrol dragons were several wing

00:34:31.440 --> 00:34:34.380
beats away already, but one shout could

00:34:34.380 --> 00:34:36.239
bring them hurtling around at lightning

00:34:36.239 --> 00:34:36.840
speed.

00:34:36.900 --> 00:34:40.019
Sunny and Starflight were no match for 6

00:34:40.019 --> 00:34:42.000
full grown sky wing soldiers.

00:34:42.119 --> 00:34:45.539
Actually, they were no match for one Sky

00:34:45.539 --> 00:34:46.199
Wing soldier.

00:34:46.260 --> 00:34:48.300
The 2 of them together would probably

00:34:48.300 --> 00:34:50.039
have trouble fighting a sleepy bat.

00:34:50.099 --> 00:34:53.760
A curl of smoke rose from the sky wing's

00:34:53.760 --> 00:34:55.320
nose, and he opened his mouth.

00:34:55.440 --> 00:34:58.019
If there was any chance of saving her

00:34:58.019 --> 00:35:01.380
friends, tsunami had to shut him up, she

00:35:01.380 --> 00:35:03.719
burst out of the water in a great leap

00:35:03.719 --> 00:35:05.639
smashing her tail behind her for

00:35:05.639 --> 00:35:06.239
momentum.

00:35:06.300 --> 00:35:09.000
Her wings powered her up to ram right

00:35:09.000 --> 00:35:10.739
into the sky wings underbelly.

00:35:10.800 --> 00:35:14.219
He coughed at a puff of fiery smoke and

00:35:14.219 --> 00:35:15.900
clutched his midsection.

00:35:15.960 --> 00:35:17.159
The breath knocked out of him.

00:35:17.280 --> 00:35:20.039
Tsunami had a few moments before he could

00:35:20.039 --> 00:35:21.360
recover enough to call for help.

00:35:21.420 --> 00:35:24.719
She ducked around him, slammed her tail

00:35:24.719 --> 00:35:27.420
into his head, and landed on his back as

00:35:27.420 --> 00:35:27.840
hard as she could.

00:35:27.900 --> 00:35:31.260
The sky wing nearly fell into the water

00:35:31.260 --> 00:35:32.880
but he fought back up into the air.

00:35:32.940 --> 00:35:35.579
Tsunami kicked at his wings with her

00:35:35.579 --> 00:35:37.739
claws and slid back toward his tail

00:35:37.739 --> 00:35:39.960
trying to drag him down with her weight.

00:35:40.019 --> 00:35:43.139
He was too big and too strong for her up

00:35:43.139 --> 00:35:43.320
here.

00:35:43.380 --> 00:35:46.079
Only taking him by surprise, had given

00:35:46.079 --> 00:35:47.400
her a temporary advantage.

00:35:47.460 --> 00:35:50.039
She needed to get him in the ocean to

00:35:50.039 --> 00:35:50.760
even out the fight.

00:35:50.820 --> 00:35:54.420
The orange dragon snarled and twisted

00:35:54.420 --> 00:35:56.699
shooting a blast of flames out of his

00:35:56.699 --> 00:35:58.619
snout, which barely missed her.

00:35:58.679 --> 00:36:01.019
Tsunami yanked him down toward the

00:36:01.019 --> 00:36:01.260
water.

00:36:01.380 --> 00:36:04.559
But his massive wings beat harder and

00:36:04.559 --> 00:36:05.159
harder.

00:36:05.219 --> 00:36:07.739
It felt like a hurricane whistling around

00:36:07.739 --> 00:36:08.099
her ears.

00:36:08.159 --> 00:36:10.980
She could tell that he was gaining height

00:36:10.980 --> 00:36:13.860
and in a moment, he'd be strong enough to

00:36:13.860 --> 00:36:15.059
call the other soldiers back.

00:36:15.179 --> 00:36:19.320
You're not getting my friends, tsunami

00:36:19.320 --> 00:36:20.099
thought fiercely.

00:36:20.159 --> 00:36:22.980
She found the vulnerable spot on his tail

00:36:22.980 --> 00:36:25.019
and sank her teeth in.

00:36:25.079 --> 00:36:28.079
He convulsed with pain, nearly throwing

00:36:28.079 --> 00:36:30.539
her off, and shot another blast of fire

00:36:30.539 --> 00:36:31.559
under his wing at her.

00:36:31.619 --> 00:36:34.920
At first, tsunami thought he had missed.

00:36:34.980 --> 00:36:38.519
Then she felt a searing trail of agony

00:36:38.519 --> 00:36:40.380
spreading along her neck.

00:36:40.440 --> 00:36:42.480
It felt as if someone were trying to saw

00:36:42.480 --> 00:36:44.579
through her scales with a scalding hot

00:36:44.579 --> 00:36:44.880
wire.

00:36:44.940 --> 00:36:48.360
She closed her eyes and clamped her jaw

00:36:48.360 --> 00:36:51.719
harder, determined to hang on, although

00:36:51.719 --> 00:36:53.159
spots were starting to dance in her

00:36:53.159 --> 00:36:53.460
vision.

00:36:53.519 --> 00:36:56.699
Suddenly, the dragon lurched toward the

00:36:56.699 --> 00:36:56.940
sea.

00:36:57.000 --> 00:36:59.460
Tsunami's eyes flew open.

00:36:59.579 --> 00:37:02.159
Clay had flung himself between her and

00:37:02.159 --> 00:37:04.500
the dragon's snout, spreading his

00:37:04.500 --> 00:37:05.639
fireproof wings.

00:37:05.699 --> 00:37:08.699
His claws clamped onto the Skywing's back

00:37:08.699 --> 00:37:11.400
and the extra weight drove the soldier

00:37:11.400 --> 00:37:13.320
down and down toward the sea.

00:37:13.380 --> 00:37:16.920
Together, Clay and Tsunami dragged the

00:37:16.920 --> 00:37:18.059
sky wing into the ocean.

00:37:18.119 --> 00:37:21.480
He fought wildly the whole way, but his

00:37:21.480 --> 00:37:23.400
flames couldn't hurt Clay's fire

00:37:23.400 --> 00:37:26.099
resistant scales, and his giant wings

00:37:26.099 --> 00:37:27.840
couldn't help him once he was underwater

00:37:27.840 --> 00:37:29.400
and cut off from breathing.

00:37:29.460 --> 00:37:32.639
As soon as they hit the water, tsunami

00:37:32.639 --> 00:37:35.039
swam to the Skywing's head and held it

00:37:35.039 --> 00:37:36.480
below the surface until he stopped

00:37:36.480 --> 00:37:37.139
thrashing.

00:37:37.199 --> 00:37:40.199
She let go, and so did Clay.

00:37:40.260 --> 00:37:43.380
The dragon's body began to drift slowly

00:37:43.380 --> 00:37:44.579
toward the seafloor.

00:37:44.639 --> 00:37:47.880
A shudder rippled through tsunami's

00:37:47.880 --> 00:37:48.300
scales.

00:37:48.360 --> 00:37:50.880
Him or me?

00:37:50.940 --> 00:37:53.519
This didn't feel right.

00:37:53.579 --> 00:37:56.940
Why couldn't she be ferocious and not

00:37:56.940 --> 00:37:57.599
care?

00:37:57.659 --> 00:38:01.019
She swam after the dragon and grabbed one

00:38:01.019 --> 00:38:02.820
of his wings, then looked back up at

00:38:02.820 --> 00:38:03.179
clay.

00:38:03.300 --> 00:38:07.079
He met her eyes, and to her relief, didn't

00:38:07.079 --> 00:38:08.760
even hesitate before swimming to the

00:38:08.760 --> 00:38:09.059
other wing.

00:38:09.179 --> 00:38:12.059
They dragged the sky wing up onto the

00:38:12.059 --> 00:38:12.539
beach.

00:38:12.599 --> 00:38:15.179
The current had carried them farther away

00:38:15.179 --> 00:38:17.579
than tsunami had guessed, and it was

00:38:17.579 --> 00:38:19.500
painfully hard to swim back to shore

00:38:19.500 --> 00:38:21.719
especially with a full grown dragon

00:38:21.719 --> 00:38:22.500
weighing them down.

00:38:22.619 --> 00:38:25.800
She gritted her teeth, ignoring her

00:38:25.800 --> 00:38:27.960
exhaustion and the pain from the burn on

00:38:27.960 --> 00:38:28.260
her neck.

00:38:28.320 --> 00:38:30.300
She was a sea wing.

00:38:30.360 --> 00:38:32.400
This was supposed to be her element.

00:38:32.460 --> 00:38:35.460
She was the boss of the ocean, not the

00:38:35.460 --> 00:38:35.940
other way around.

00:38:36.000 --> 00:38:39.420
By the time they reached the beach.

00:38:39.480 --> 00:38:41.039
The rest of the patrol had vanished from

00:38:41.039 --> 00:38:41.400
sight.

00:38:41.460 --> 00:38:44.099
She wondered how long it would be before

00:38:44.099 --> 00:38:46.320
they noticed this one missing, and came

00:38:46.320 --> 00:38:47.219
back to look for him.

00:38:47.280 --> 00:38:51.059
Tsunami collapsed onto the sand beside

00:38:51.059 --> 00:38:51.599
the sky wing.

00:38:51.659 --> 00:38:55.019
Clay peered into the dragon's snout, then

00:38:55.019 --> 00:38:56.219
started thumping his chest.

00:38:56.280 --> 00:38:59.460
What is wrong with you?

00:38:59.579 --> 00:39:01.860
Glory's voice snapped?

00:39:01.920 --> 00:39:04.380
The rain wing materialized from the sandy

00:39:04.380 --> 00:39:06.840
background, turning her scales a darker

00:39:06.840 --> 00:39:08.400
shade of brown so they could see her.

00:39:08.460 --> 00:39:10.679
She glared at tsunami.

00:39:10.739 --> 00:39:12.539
Why did you do that?

00:39:12.599 --> 00:39:17.579
Oh, you're welcome, tsunami said, just

00:39:17.579 --> 00:39:19.139
saving your life as usual.

00:39:19.260 --> 00:39:22.739
By attacking random dragons?

00:39:22.800 --> 00:39:23.820
Glory cried.

00:39:23.940 --> 00:39:25.920
In another moment, they would have been

00:39:25.920 --> 00:39:26.280
gone.

00:39:26.340 --> 00:39:28.139
And what are you doing?

00:39:28.199 --> 00:39:30.960
She jabbed clay in the side with one of

00:39:30.960 --> 00:39:31.380
her wings.

00:39:31.440 --> 00:39:35.519
Oh, Clay mumbled, fixing him.

00:39:35.579 --> 00:39:38.460
He kept thumping the sky wing's chest.

00:39:38.579 --> 00:39:39.599
What?

00:39:39.719 --> 00:39:41.219
Glory yelped.

00:39:41.280 --> 00:39:42.599
You can't let him live?

00:39:42.659 --> 00:39:45.840
She tried to grab one of Clay's forearms

00:39:45.840 --> 00:39:47.340
but tsunami shoved her away.

00:39:47.460 --> 00:39:51.059
We don't have to kill him, tsunami said.

00:39:51.119 --> 00:39:52.800
We'll tie him up and leave him here.

00:39:52.860 --> 00:39:56.039
Great, Glory said.

00:39:56.099 --> 00:39:59.340
How about a trail of cow parts too, and a

00:39:59.340 --> 00:40:00.300
map of where we're going?

00:40:00.360 --> 00:40:02.460
Or perhaps we could set this part of the

00:40:02.460 --> 00:40:04.619
forest on fire, just to make sure

00:40:04.619 --> 00:40:06.119
everyone knows how to find us.

00:40:06.179 --> 00:40:08.099
Would you like me to spell out

00:40:08.099 --> 00:40:11.579
Dragonettes was here in giant rocks?

00:40:11.639 --> 00:40:14.340
Fine, Tsunami said.

00:40:14.400 --> 00:40:15.840
Here he is.

00:40:15.900 --> 00:40:16.920
You kill him.

00:40:16.980 --> 00:40:20.039
Glory looked down at the unconscious

00:40:20.039 --> 00:40:21.420
dragon and hesitated.

00:40:21.480 --> 00:40:24.539
I don't kill dragons who can't fight back

00:40:24.539 --> 00:40:26.219
she said finally.

00:40:26.280 --> 00:40:27.719
Why not?

00:40:27.780 --> 00:40:29.159
Tsunami said.

00:40:29.219 --> 00:40:31.679
Just splat some venom on his face and

00:40:31.679 --> 00:40:33.480
melt him, if it's that easy for you.

00:40:33.539 --> 00:40:36.960
Glory sank her claws into the sand

00:40:36.960 --> 00:40:38.159
scowling.

00:40:38.219 --> 00:40:40.860
Bubbles of dark purple began spreading

00:40:40.860 --> 00:40:42.300
across her scales.

00:40:42.360 --> 00:40:44.880
Sunny and Starflight landed on the beach

00:40:44.880 --> 00:40:45.480
beside them.

00:40:45.539 --> 00:40:48.360
Sonny gave the sky wing a horrified look

00:40:48.360 --> 00:40:51.179
and tsunami remembered that she'd been

00:40:51.179 --> 00:40:52.860
trapped in another part of the palace

00:40:52.860 --> 00:40:54.420
during the arena fights.

00:40:54.480 --> 00:40:56.460
She'd never seen her friends battle

00:40:56.460 --> 00:40:57.599
another dragon.

00:40:57.659 --> 00:40:59.519
Is he all right?

00:40:59.579 --> 00:41:01.619
Sonny asked Clay.

00:41:01.679 --> 00:41:05.159
Troy this, Starflight offered, coming

00:41:05.159 --> 00:41:05.699
over to help.

00:41:05.760 --> 00:41:08.699
Clay shifted aside, and they rolled the

00:41:08.699 --> 00:41:09.780
dragon onto his stomach.

00:41:09.840 --> 00:41:12.059
Why did you attack him?

00:41:12.119 --> 00:41:14.460
Sonny blurted at tsunami.

00:41:14.519 --> 00:41:16.980
The little Sandwings harmless tail

00:41:16.980 --> 00:41:18.599
flicked back and forth anxiously.

00:41:18.659 --> 00:41:23.280
To save you, tsunami said, stung.

00:41:23.340 --> 00:41:26.940
But he wasn't even doing anything, Sonny

00:41:26.940 --> 00:41:27.420
protested.

00:41:27.480 --> 00:41:29.159
He was just flying by.

00:41:29.219 --> 00:41:32.280
All 4 of them were looking at tsunami

00:41:32.280 --> 00:41:34.320
like she was the kind of dragon who hid

00:41:34.320 --> 00:41:36.360
under rocks and bit innocent passers by

00:41:36.360 --> 00:41:36.659
for fun.

00:41:36.719 --> 00:41:39.719
She arched her neck indignantly.

00:41:39.960 --> 00:41:41.699
I thought he saw you.

00:41:41.760 --> 00:41:43.019
She growled.

00:41:43.079 --> 00:41:45.119
He was about to call out to the others.

00:41:45.179 --> 00:41:46.739
I saw him open his mouth.

00:41:46.800 --> 00:41:50.099
So did I, said Glory.

00:41:50.159 --> 00:41:52.380
I'm pretty sure he was yawning.

00:41:52.500 --> 00:41:55.800
Pretty sure, tsunami said.

00:41:55.860 --> 00:41:58.380
Would you risk our lives on pretty sure?

00:41:58.500 --> 00:42:00.719
Was he yawning?

00:42:00.780 --> 00:42:02.940
Did I attack him for nothing?

00:42:03.000 --> 00:42:04.260
That can't be right.

00:42:04.320 --> 00:42:07.199
I saw danger and reacted appropriately.

00:42:07.260 --> 00:42:08.400
Didn't I?

00:42:08.519 --> 00:42:12.960
Maybe if you'd just stopped to think for

00:42:12.960 --> 00:42:13.500
a 2nd.

00:42:13.559 --> 00:42:17.099
Starflight said, or forever, like you?

00:42:17.159 --> 00:42:19.980
Think, think, think, worry, worry, never

00:42:19.980 --> 00:42:20.699
do anything?

00:42:20.760 --> 00:42:22.139
Tsunami cried.

00:42:22.199 --> 00:42:24.960
The Sky Wing suddenly coughed, and

00:42:24.960 --> 00:42:26.699
Seawater flooded out of his snout.

00:42:26.820 --> 00:42:29.219
Clay ruffled his wings with a pleased

00:42:29.219 --> 00:42:29.940
expression.

00:42:30.000 --> 00:42:31.559
Oh, wonderful.

00:42:31.619 --> 00:42:33.719
Our enemy will survive.

00:42:33.780 --> 00:42:34.380
Well done.

00:42:34.440 --> 00:42:37.559
We have to get out of here, Lori said.

00:42:37.619 --> 00:42:39.780
She took a step back and glanced at the

00:42:39.780 --> 00:42:41.400
sky where the other soldiers had

00:42:41.400 --> 00:42:41.880
disappeared.

00:42:41.940 --> 00:42:45.840
So, what do we do with him now, O great

00:42:45.840 --> 00:42:46.320
leader?

00:42:46.380 --> 00:42:49.019
Tsunami had no idea.

00:42:49.079 --> 00:42:51.300
She glanced around frantically.

00:42:51.360 --> 00:42:54.119
Maybe if they could find some vines to

00:42:54.119 --> 00:42:54.960
tie him up with.

00:42:56.039 --> 00:42:59.400
There's a tree, Starflight said, jumping

00:42:59.400 --> 00:43:00.539
to his feet.

00:43:00.599 --> 00:43:01.260
In the forest.

00:43:01.320 --> 00:43:03.599
No way.

00:43:03.659 --> 00:43:08.340
Glory said, a tree in the forest.

00:43:08.400 --> 00:43:10.860
Being sarcastic is not helping.

00:43:10.920 --> 00:43:12.780
Tsunami snapped at her.

00:43:12.840 --> 00:43:16.679
I mean, a fallen tree, Starflight said.

00:43:16.739 --> 00:43:17.820
We can use it.

00:43:17.880 --> 00:43:19.980
Glory, stay and guard him.

00:43:20.039 --> 00:43:21.960
Clay and tsunami, come on, quick.

00:43:22.019 --> 00:43:24.960
Clay charged up the beach behind him.

00:43:25.019 --> 00:43:27.239
Tsunami paused for a moment.

00:43:27.300 --> 00:43:30.119
She didn't like leaving the soldier, even

00:43:30.119 --> 00:43:31.679
if he wasn't fully awake yet.

00:43:31.739 --> 00:43:34.739
She also didn't particularly like taking

00:43:34.739 --> 00:43:36.059
orders from Starflight.

00:43:36.119 --> 00:43:37.619
Go on.

00:43:37.679 --> 00:43:38.639
Hurry.

00:43:38.699 --> 00:43:41.340
Sonny said, nudging her with one wing.

00:43:41.400 --> 00:43:45.059
Not far into the forest, a large tree had

00:43:45.059 --> 00:43:46.980
fallen, with the top of its branches

00:43:46.980 --> 00:43:47.820
brushing the sand.

00:43:47.880 --> 00:43:51.000
Clay and tsunami shoved and rolled it

00:43:51.000 --> 00:43:53.159
onto the beach and dragged it back to the

00:43:53.159 --> 00:43:55.800
sky wing, while Starflight flapped around

00:43:55.800 --> 00:43:57.059
squawking instructions.

00:43:57.119 --> 00:44:00.000
As if we need to be told how to move a

00:44:00.000 --> 00:44:00.300
tree.

00:44:00.420 --> 00:44:02.400
Tsunami thought grumpily.

00:44:02.460 --> 00:44:05.820
The soldier's eyes were blinking awake as

00:44:05.820 --> 00:44:06.239
they reached him.

00:44:06.360 --> 00:44:09.659
He coughed and coughed again, lifting his

00:44:09.659 --> 00:44:10.920
head to peer groggily at the

00:44:10.920 --> 00:44:11.639
dragonettes.

00:44:11.699 --> 00:44:14.159
So how does the tree help?

00:44:14.280 --> 00:44:15.420
Tsunami asked.

00:44:15.480 --> 00:44:19.320
We put it on top of him, Starflight said

00:44:19.320 --> 00:44:21.840
so he'll be trapped in place, at least

00:44:21.840 --> 00:44:22.980
long enough for us to get away.

00:44:23.039 --> 00:44:26.639
Tsunami hated to admit it, but it was a

00:44:26.639 --> 00:44:27.000
good idea.

00:44:27.059 --> 00:44:29.880
She helped Clay wrestle the tree over

00:44:29.880 --> 00:44:31.800
until it lay heavily across the orange

00:44:31.800 --> 00:44:33.239
dragon's back and wings.

00:44:33.300 --> 00:44:36.960
The Sky Wing tried to push himself up, but

00:44:36.960 --> 00:44:38.639
the tree kept him pinned to the sand.

00:44:38.699 --> 00:44:41.280
What if he's stuck here forever?

00:44:41.340 --> 00:44:42.960
Sonny worried?

00:44:43.019 --> 00:44:45.480
She reached over and brushed some sand

00:44:45.480 --> 00:44:47.219
off the Skywings snout.

00:44:47.280 --> 00:44:49.860
He snorted a puff of smoke, and Clay

00:44:49.860 --> 00:44:50.460
pulled her back.

00:44:50.579 --> 00:44:53.099
Maybe we should just let him go.

00:44:53.159 --> 00:44:55.079
We can't do that.

00:44:55.139 --> 00:44:56.460
Tsunami said.

00:44:56.519 --> 00:44:59.039
I wish you hadn't attacked him.

00:44:59.159 --> 00:45:01.320
Sonny said, ducking her head.

00:45:01.380 --> 00:45:04.619
Me too, said Glory.

00:45:04.679 --> 00:45:08.460
It wasn't the smartest move, Starflight

00:45:08.460 --> 00:45:08.820
agreed.

00:45:08.880 --> 00:45:11.460
Tsunami's gills flared, and she spread

00:45:11.460 --> 00:45:11.880
her wings.

00:45:11.940 --> 00:45:14.760
You don't know that, she said.

00:45:14.940 --> 00:45:17.219
Maybe I saved us, again.

00:45:17.340 --> 00:45:20.639
She looked at Clay, but he only shrugged

00:45:20.639 --> 00:45:21.659
as if he wasn't sure.

00:45:21.780 --> 00:45:24.599
Thanks for the support, guys.

00:45:24.659 --> 00:45:26.699
Tsunami thought angrily.

00:45:26.760 --> 00:45:28.679
When all I'm trying to do is keep

00:45:28.679 --> 00:45:29.460
everyone safe.

00:45:29.519 --> 00:45:34.739
Don't worry, sonny, Clay said, patting

00:45:34.739 --> 00:45:35.940
the little sandwings head.

00:45:36.000 --> 00:45:38.219
His friends will come looking for him

00:45:38.219 --> 00:45:38.699
eventually.

00:45:38.760 --> 00:45:43.619
Eventually, or soon, Glory said.

00:45:43.679 --> 00:45:47.039
So like I said, let's seriously get out

00:45:47.039 --> 00:45:47.340
of here.

00:45:47.400 --> 00:45:49.500
Wait.

00:45:49.559 --> 00:45:51.239
The Sky Wing rasped.

00:45:51.300 --> 00:45:53.340
His voice was hoarse and deep.

00:45:53.400 --> 00:45:55.860
He wriggled, lashing his tail across the

00:45:55.860 --> 00:45:56.159
sand.

00:45:56.219 --> 00:45:58.380
Don't leave me like this.

00:45:58.500 --> 00:46:01.679
Starflight stepped into his line of sight

00:46:01.679 --> 00:46:03.239
and gazed down at him.

00:46:03.300 --> 00:46:07.320
Remember, we could have killed you, he

00:46:07.320 --> 00:46:07.619
said.

00:46:07.679 --> 00:46:10.739
Remember that the dragonettes of destiny

00:46:10.739 --> 00:46:11.460
were merciful.

00:46:11.519 --> 00:46:13.980
We want peace, not more death.

00:46:14.039 --> 00:46:16.559
We have come to save Pyria.

00:46:16.619 --> 00:46:20.579
Oh, good grief, tsunami said, as glory

00:46:20.579 --> 00:46:21.360
rolled her eyes.

00:46:21.420 --> 00:46:23.639
No more hanging out with night wings for

00:46:23.639 --> 00:46:24.059
you.

00:46:24.119 --> 00:46:26.460
I thought it sounded nice.

00:46:26.519 --> 00:46:28.199
Sonny said.

00:46:28.260 --> 00:46:30.119
Starflight shot her a grateful look.

00:46:30.179 --> 00:46:34.320
Sonny, don't encourage him, said Glory.

00:46:34.380 --> 00:46:37.380
Carefully, Starflight draped a few large

00:46:37.380 --> 00:46:39.780
leaves over the dragon's head, so he

00:46:39.780 --> 00:46:40.679
couldn't see where they went.

00:46:40.739 --> 00:46:43.559
He pointed toward the forest and mouthed

00:46:43.559 --> 00:46:45.000
just to be safe.

00:46:45.059 --> 00:46:47.340
Tsunami sighed.

00:46:47.460 --> 00:46:49.139
More flying in the wrong direction.

00:46:49.260 --> 00:46:52.980
She wanted to go home already, home to

00:46:52.980 --> 00:46:55.559
the ocean, and the sea wings, and her

00:46:55.559 --> 00:46:56.460
royal parents.

00:46:56.519 --> 00:46:59.159
But she couldn't argue about it with a

00:46:59.159 --> 00:47:01.380
sky wing listening, and the others were

00:47:01.380 --> 00:47:02.460
already nodding.

00:47:02.519 --> 00:47:05.099
All of them were ready to follow anxious

00:47:05.099 --> 00:47:07.380
overly cautious Starflight yet again.

00:47:07.440 --> 00:47:09.659
And none of them thought she'd done the

00:47:09.659 --> 00:47:11.820
right thing by attacking this sky wing

00:47:11.820 --> 00:47:14.099
even though it was to save their stupid

00:47:14.099 --> 00:47:14.519
scales.

00:47:14.579 --> 00:47:16.920
As they lifted into the sky.

00:47:17.039 --> 00:47:19.679
She cast a longing look over her shoulder

00:47:19.679 --> 00:47:20.340
at the ocean.

00:47:20.400 --> 00:47:23.099
Soon, she thought.

00:47:23.159 --> 00:47:26.159
Soon, I'll be with my own dragons.

00:47:26.280 --> 00:47:30.480
Chapter 3.

00:47:30.780 --> 00:47:34.860
The Bay of a Thousand Scales was farther

00:47:34.860 --> 00:47:37.019
away than Tsunami had realized.

00:47:37.079 --> 00:47:39.360
She'd been studying the map of Pirus and

00:47:39.360 --> 00:47:41.760
she was tiny, but it was hard to fit that

00:47:41.760 --> 00:47:43.980
picture over the enormous world below

00:47:43.980 --> 00:47:44.699
her.

00:47:44.760 --> 00:47:47.519
She kept expecting to find neat little

00:47:47.519 --> 00:47:49.380
spirals of islands that would fit in the

00:47:49.380 --> 00:47:50.340
palm of her talons.

00:47:50.400 --> 00:47:53.880
Instead, she found herself flying over

00:47:53.880 --> 00:47:57.480
vast expanses of empty ocean, dotted here

00:47:57.480 --> 00:47:59.579
and there with a solitary outcropping of

00:47:59.579 --> 00:48:00.059
rock.

00:48:00.119 --> 00:48:04.199
After they took a long detour inland to

00:48:04.199 --> 00:48:06.179
convince the Sky Wing they'd gone in the

00:48:06.179 --> 00:48:08.400
opposite direction, they circled around

00:48:08.400 --> 00:48:10.019
south and flew out to sea.

00:48:10.139 --> 00:48:13.559
They managed to make it to a small rocky

00:48:13.559 --> 00:48:16.079
island shortly after night fell, but

00:48:16.079 --> 00:48:18.000
according to Starflight, they were still

00:48:18.000 --> 00:48:19.920
a long way from the Bay of a 1000

00:48:19.920 --> 00:48:20.340
scales.

00:48:20.460 --> 00:48:23.400
He'd calculated the distance and their

00:48:23.400 --> 00:48:25.920
speed and had a long, boring lecture

00:48:25.920 --> 00:48:27.119
ready to explain it all.

00:48:27.179 --> 00:48:29.760
The rest of them fell asleep halfway into

00:48:29.760 --> 00:48:30.000
it.

00:48:30.059 --> 00:48:32.340
And he spent the next day sulking about

00:48:32.340 --> 00:48:32.460
that.

00:48:32.519 --> 00:48:36.900
Still, tsunami had to admit, if only to

00:48:36.900 --> 00:48:39.360
herself, that it was useful having

00:48:39.360 --> 00:48:41.579
someone with all the geography and flight

00:48:41.579 --> 00:48:42.480
plans in his head.

00:48:42.599 --> 00:48:45.119
For a few days, they stopped whenever

00:48:45.119 --> 00:48:47.699
they saw an island, ate a seagull or fish

00:48:47.699 --> 00:48:49.860
if they could catch any, and then flew

00:48:49.860 --> 00:48:50.099
on.

00:48:50.159 --> 00:48:53.039
Tsunami tried diving into the ocean

00:48:53.039 --> 00:48:55.500
several times, and was disappointed to

00:48:55.500 --> 00:48:58.079
discover she couldn't swim as fast as she

00:48:58.079 --> 00:48:58.440
flew.

00:48:58.559 --> 00:49:01.559
The only good news was that the ocean

00:49:01.559 --> 00:49:03.300
water helped to heal the burn on her

00:49:03.300 --> 00:49:03.539
neck.

00:49:03.599 --> 00:49:08.099
It was 4 mornings later, when tsunami

00:49:08.099 --> 00:49:10.440
finally woke up on an island that was

00:49:10.440 --> 00:49:13.139
officially part of the 1000 scales.

00:49:13.199 --> 00:49:16.199
She started awake from a dream in which

00:49:16.199 --> 00:49:18.780
their cave had collapsed and was slowly

00:49:18.780 --> 00:49:21.239
crushing her to death, and discovered

00:49:21.239 --> 00:49:23.219
that clay had rolled over on top of her

00:49:23.219 --> 00:49:24.539
in the middle of the night.

00:49:24.599 --> 00:49:26.760
Grumbling, she wriggled out from under

00:49:26.760 --> 00:49:29.219
him, and let his tail flop over onto

00:49:29.219 --> 00:49:30.179
Starflight's head.

00:49:30.239 --> 00:49:33.360
The 5 dragonettes were packed into a

00:49:33.360 --> 00:49:36.420
cavern, halfway up a tall sea cliff.

00:49:36.480 --> 00:49:39.900
It was cramped and uncomfortable, and

00:49:39.900 --> 00:49:41.219
smelled of seagull droppings.

00:49:41.280 --> 00:49:44.219
Clay had barely been able to scrunch his

00:49:44.219 --> 00:49:45.780
wings low enough to crawl inside.

00:49:45.900 --> 00:49:48.599
And why were they sleeping in this

00:49:48.599 --> 00:49:51.179
horrible spot instead of on the nice

00:49:51.179 --> 00:49:52.559
white, sandy beach below?

00:49:52.619 --> 00:49:56.099
Tsunami sat down in the cave entrance and

00:49:56.099 --> 00:49:58.500
glared at Starflight, which wasn't very

00:49:58.500 --> 00:50:00.420
satisfying since everyone was still

00:50:00.420 --> 00:50:01.260
snoring away.

00:50:01.320 --> 00:50:03.900
Clay was stuffed against the back wall

00:50:03.900 --> 00:50:06.480
with sunny between his front talons, and

00:50:06.480 --> 00:50:07.980
Starflight curled up alongside.

00:50:08.039 --> 00:50:10.920
Even glory had her tail draped over

00:50:10.920 --> 00:50:11.340
clays.

00:50:11.400 --> 00:50:14.460
Her scales glinted orange and gold in the

00:50:14.460 --> 00:50:16.920
light of the rising sun, with bursts of

00:50:16.920 --> 00:50:18.659
red when she shifted sleepily.

00:50:18.719 --> 00:50:22.800
Starflight had been acting so weird since

00:50:22.800 --> 00:50:24.059
the night wings gave him back.

00:50:24.119 --> 00:50:26.639
Suddenly it seemed like he wanted to

00:50:26.639 --> 00:50:28.440
argue with tsunami about everything.

00:50:28.500 --> 00:50:31.619
If she said, let's sleep on the beach

00:50:31.619 --> 00:50:32.280
it'll be fun.

00:50:32.340 --> 00:50:36.360
He'd say, no, no, we have to sleep in a

00:50:36.360 --> 00:50:37.500
hidden cave.

00:50:37.559 --> 00:50:38.460
That'll be much safer.

00:50:38.519 --> 00:50:42.059
Safer, as if there was anything to worry

00:50:42.059 --> 00:50:44.519
about all the way out here in the middle

00:50:44.519 --> 00:50:45.300
of the night.

00:50:45.360 --> 00:50:48.119
But everyone was still mad at her about

00:50:48.119 --> 00:50:50.820
attacking that soldier, so they all voted

00:50:50.820 --> 00:50:51.599
with Starflight.

00:50:51.659 --> 00:50:54.599
She didn't like that development at all.

00:50:54.659 --> 00:50:57.420
Tsunami watched them sleep for a moment.

00:50:57.480 --> 00:51:01.019
It was so hard to lead effectively when

00:51:01.019 --> 00:51:02.880
everyone kept questioning you and

00:51:02.880 --> 00:51:04.619
complaining about everything.

00:51:04.679 --> 00:51:07.380
She only wanted what was best for them.

00:51:07.500 --> 00:51:08.880
Didn't they know that?

00:51:08.940 --> 00:51:11.579
She'd always figured she would fight a

00:51:11.579 --> 00:51:13.019
100 sky wings to protect them.

00:51:13.079 --> 00:51:15.780
But maybe I shouldn't.

00:51:15.900 --> 00:51:18.659
Maybe my friends don't want my protection

00:51:18.659 --> 00:51:19.139
after all.

00:51:19.260 --> 00:51:22.800
Maybe they wanted Starflight to be their

00:51:22.800 --> 00:51:23.699
leader instead.

00:51:23.760 --> 00:51:26.340
Even though he'd never risked one scale

00:51:26.340 --> 00:51:27.420
on his body for them.

00:51:27.480 --> 00:51:30.239
Tsunami glance down at the sea.

00:51:30.300 --> 00:51:32.820
Sparkling aquamarine below her.

00:51:32.880 --> 00:51:37.019
Somewhere, in those blue green depths, was

00:51:37.019 --> 00:51:37.500
her family.

00:51:37.559 --> 00:51:42.300
Her parents, her kingdom, everything that

00:51:42.300 --> 00:51:44.880
should have been hers, if the talons of

00:51:44.880 --> 00:51:47.219
peace hadn't stolen her away and ruined

00:51:47.219 --> 00:51:47.519
her life.

00:51:47.579 --> 00:51:51.000
Perhaps the problem with her friends was

00:51:51.000 --> 00:51:53.219
that they were from different tribes, all

00:51:53.219 --> 00:51:55.440
stubborn and muddled up, instead of

00:51:55.440 --> 00:51:56.820
sensible like sea wings.

00:51:56.880 --> 00:51:59.460
Maybe her own kind would understand her

00:51:59.460 --> 00:51:59.820
better.

00:51:59.880 --> 00:52:03.179
They'd appreciate her instead of yelling

00:52:03.179 --> 00:52:03.480
at her.

00:52:03.539 --> 00:52:06.960
Well, she didn't have to sit here waiting

00:52:06.960 --> 00:52:08.219
for everyone else to wake up.

00:52:08.280 --> 00:52:10.559
It wasn't like they'd be much help when

00:52:10.559 --> 00:52:11.639
it came to searching anyway.

00:52:11.699 --> 00:52:14.639
Tsunami stretched her wings and then

00:52:14.639 --> 00:52:16.380
tipped forward out of the cave opening.

00:52:16.440 --> 00:52:20.099
Wind whistled past her snout, tugging at

00:52:20.099 --> 00:52:21.659
her tail as she plummeted down the

00:52:21.659 --> 00:52:22.019
cliff.

00:52:22.079 --> 00:52:25.559
At the last moment, she snapped her wings

00:52:25.559 --> 00:52:27.719
open and sailed across the top of the

00:52:27.719 --> 00:52:29.940
water, skimming it with her claws.

00:52:30.000 --> 00:52:32.760
Joy tingled through her scales.

00:52:32.820 --> 00:52:35.460
She spun and dove into the water.

00:52:35.579 --> 00:52:39.239
The sea was warmer here, and busy with

00:52:39.239 --> 00:52:40.260
underwater life.

00:52:40.320 --> 00:52:43.860
Her splash sent what seemed like 1000s of

00:52:43.860 --> 00:52:46.320
fish scattering away, several of them

00:52:46.320 --> 00:52:48.539
disappearing into a pinkish orange coral

00:52:48.539 --> 00:52:51.179
reef that curled out of the sand like a

00:52:51.179 --> 00:52:52.079
petrified forest.

00:52:52.139 --> 00:52:56.219
A blobby, dark blue octopus, goggled at

00:52:56.219 --> 00:52:56.820
her from the branches.

00:52:56.940 --> 00:52:59.760
Tsunami kept saying flickers of bright

00:52:59.760 --> 00:53:01.260
yellow and silver at the edge of her

00:53:01.260 --> 00:53:03.960
vision, as fish fled from her webbed

00:53:03.960 --> 00:53:04.380
claws.

00:53:04.440 --> 00:53:07.679
No welcoming committee of delighted sea

00:53:07.679 --> 00:53:08.340
wings, though.

00:53:08.400 --> 00:53:11.579
No glowing jellyfish marking a path to

00:53:11.579 --> 00:53:12.900
Queen Carl's Castle.

00:53:12.960 --> 00:53:16.380
No cavalcade of bowing seahorses and

00:53:16.380 --> 00:53:18.780
bejeweled lobsters to lead the way.

00:53:18.840 --> 00:53:21.420
Not that she'd been picturing the

00:53:21.420 --> 00:53:23.340
homecoming scene from The Missing

00:53:23.340 --> 00:53:24.119
Princess or anything.

00:53:24.179 --> 00:53:28.500
Tsunami swam along the coral reef, peering

00:53:28.500 --> 00:53:30.300
at the creatures hiding in the nooks and

00:53:30.300 --> 00:53:30.599
holes.

00:53:30.659 --> 00:53:33.480
A hideous thing she thought might be an

00:53:33.480 --> 00:53:34.800
eel stared back at her.

00:53:34.860 --> 00:53:38.039
Little orange and white fish nestled in

00:53:38.039 --> 00:53:39.719
the waving lavender anemones.

00:53:39.780 --> 00:53:42.719
She still wasn't used to swimming in the

00:53:42.719 --> 00:53:44.519
sea, and that frustrated her.

00:53:44.579 --> 00:53:47.639
Unexpected currents kept knocking her off

00:53:47.639 --> 00:53:48.059
balance.

00:53:48.119 --> 00:53:50.639
The saltwater felt like it was scraping

00:53:50.639 --> 00:53:51.900
roughly against her gills.

00:53:52.019 --> 00:53:54.420
Where were her natural sea wing

00:53:54.420 --> 00:53:54.960
instincts?

00:53:55.019 --> 00:53:57.179
Her world was supposed to make her

00:53:57.179 --> 00:53:59.460
stronger, faster, tougher.

00:53:59.519 --> 00:54:01.679
Not pathetic.

00:54:01.739 --> 00:54:05.519
She swam all the way to the next island

00:54:05.519 --> 00:54:06.659
fighting the currents.

00:54:06.780 --> 00:54:09.659
More of the pinkish coral reef stretched

00:54:09.659 --> 00:54:12.239
across the sand here as well, dotted with

00:54:12.239 --> 00:54:14.699
waving green fans and lacy dark purple

00:54:14.699 --> 00:54:15.480
ferns.

00:54:15.480 --> 00:54:18.239
Her wings felt sore and tired.

00:54:18.300 --> 00:54:20.880
So she spread them wide and floated near

00:54:20.880 --> 00:54:22.860
the surface, not far from the land.

00:54:22.980 --> 00:54:25.980
Something flashed below her in the

00:54:25.980 --> 00:54:29.340
shadows of the coral reef, something very

00:54:29.340 --> 00:54:29.820
large.

00:54:29.880 --> 00:54:33.420
Tsunami had a brief vision of all the

00:54:33.420 --> 00:54:35.639
large toothy things that might live in

00:54:35.639 --> 00:54:37.260
the ocean, then dismissed it.

00:54:37.320 --> 00:54:40.320
If it was a shark, she would kill it and

00:54:40.320 --> 00:54:41.639
bring it back to the others to eat.

00:54:41.699 --> 00:54:44.219
Mainly so she could see the look on

00:54:44.219 --> 00:54:45.239
Starflight's face.

00:54:45.300 --> 00:54:48.119
She flicked her tail to swim closer.

00:54:48.179 --> 00:54:50.699
It was another sea wing.

00:54:50.760 --> 00:54:53.699
A shiver rippled across her scales when

00:54:53.699 --> 00:54:54.300
she saw him.

00:54:54.360 --> 00:54:56.760
And part of her wanted to bolt right back

00:54:56.760 --> 00:54:57.480
to her friends.

00:54:57.539 --> 00:55:00.059
Don't be a smoke breather.

00:55:00.119 --> 00:55:01.679
She scolded herself.

00:55:01.739 --> 00:55:04.679
This is what you were hoping for, a

00:55:04.679 --> 00:55:06.300
dragon from your own tribe.

00:55:06.360 --> 00:55:08.219
She took a deep breath.

00:55:08.280 --> 00:55:11.760
The strange sea wing had dark blue horns

00:55:11.760 --> 00:55:15.000
and sky blue scales several shades paler

00:55:15.000 --> 00:55:15.420
than hers.

00:55:15.539 --> 00:55:18.780
He was paddling by the reef, shifting his

00:55:18.780 --> 00:55:20.639
talons and wings slightly to change

00:55:20.639 --> 00:55:23.639
course, his head turned alertly from side

00:55:23.639 --> 00:55:24.119
to side.

00:55:24.179 --> 00:55:28.079
Well, it wouldn't hurt to follow him for

00:55:28.079 --> 00:55:28.739
a while first.

00:55:28.800 --> 00:55:30.539
Tsunami told herself.

00:55:30.599 --> 00:55:33.300
She crept along the top of the reef

00:55:33.300 --> 00:55:34.980
peering over the edge at him.

00:55:35.039 --> 00:55:37.679
Her claws caught on small gaps in the

00:55:37.679 --> 00:55:37.980
curl.

00:55:38.039 --> 00:55:40.860
She accidentally poked an indignant black

00:55:40.860 --> 00:55:43.019
lobster, which came bustling out with its

00:55:43.019 --> 00:55:45.179
long whiskers bristling and pincers

00:55:45.179 --> 00:55:45.780
snapping.

00:55:45.840 --> 00:55:48.420
It took one look at her, and hustled

00:55:48.420 --> 00:55:49.320
right back into hiding.

00:55:49.440 --> 00:55:51.179
Up here.

00:55:51.239 --> 00:55:53.579
The reef was covered in a layer of green

00:55:53.579 --> 00:55:54.539
moss like algae.

00:55:54.599 --> 00:55:57.420
Tsunami passed a couple of large sea

00:55:57.420 --> 00:55:59.880
turtles slowly swimming nearby.

00:56:00.119 --> 00:56:02.940
An enormous tentacled thing like a sea

00:56:02.940 --> 00:56:05.579
spider sat nibbling bits of algae.

00:56:05.639 --> 00:56:08.699
The tips of its 8 dark purple legs glowed

00:56:08.699 --> 00:56:11.340
orange yellow, and so did its eyes.

00:56:11.579 --> 00:56:14.760
The sea wing down below stopped suddenly

00:56:14.760 --> 00:56:15.840
and glanced around.

00:56:15.960 --> 00:56:18.539
Tsunami flattened herself against the

00:56:18.539 --> 00:56:19.139
reef.

00:56:19.260 --> 00:56:22.320
Knobbly bits of limestone poked into her

00:56:22.320 --> 00:56:22.920
underbelly.

00:56:22.980 --> 00:56:25.320
She peered through one of the holes of

00:56:25.320 --> 00:56:25.980
the other dragon.

00:56:26.039 --> 00:56:30.179
He spun slowly, staring into the ocean

00:56:30.179 --> 00:56:30.900
depths.

00:56:30.960 --> 00:56:32.099
Had he heard her?

00:56:32.159 --> 00:56:34.199
But he didn't look up.

00:56:34.260 --> 00:56:36.780
The dragon checked around him one more

00:56:36.780 --> 00:56:39.420
time, then lit up the stripes along his

00:56:39.420 --> 00:56:39.719
wings.

00:56:39.840 --> 00:56:43.619
Almost immediately, another dragon swam

00:56:43.619 --> 00:56:45.360
out of a cave in the coral reef.

00:56:45.420 --> 00:56:48.360
Hmm, tsunami thought.

00:56:48.420 --> 00:56:50.219
Much less handsome.

00:56:50.280 --> 00:56:53.880
His green scales were perfectly nice, but

00:56:53.880 --> 00:56:55.559
she didn't care for the black spiral

00:56:55.559 --> 00:56:56.280
patterns on them.

00:56:56.340 --> 00:56:58.980
She'd never seen a pattern like that on a

00:56:58.980 --> 00:57:01.980
dragon before, and his face wasn't nearly

00:57:01.980 --> 00:57:04.320
as handsome or friendly looking as the

00:57:04.320 --> 00:57:06.840
1st dragon, although perhaps that had

00:57:06.840 --> 00:57:08.639
something to do with a giant bruise

00:57:08.639 --> 00:57:10.079
swollen over his left eye.

00:57:10.139 --> 00:57:12.599
She wondered if they were guards

00:57:12.599 --> 00:57:13.739
switching patrol duty.

00:57:13.860 --> 00:57:16.860
If so, they were being quite strange

00:57:16.860 --> 00:57:17.039
about it.

00:57:17.099 --> 00:57:21.059
The 2 dragons floated in place, staring

00:57:21.059 --> 00:57:22.980
at each other for what seemed like an

00:57:22.980 --> 00:57:23.460
eternity.

00:57:23.519 --> 00:57:27.000
Occasionally, the stripes on one sea wing

00:57:27.000 --> 00:57:27.539
would light up.

00:57:27.599 --> 00:57:28.619
Then on the other.

00:57:28.679 --> 00:57:31.139
They moved their talons about as if

00:57:31.139 --> 00:57:33.719
waving away fish, even though no fish

00:57:33.719 --> 00:57:34.860
went anywhere near them.

00:57:34.920 --> 00:57:39.000
And then, the spiral marked dragon ducked

00:57:39.000 --> 00:57:41.099
back into the cave, and the blue dragon

00:57:41.099 --> 00:57:41.639
swam on.

00:57:41.699 --> 00:57:45.599
Some kind of sea wing patrol ritual?

00:57:45.659 --> 00:57:47.400
Tsunami wondered.

00:57:47.639 --> 00:57:49.500
I guess I'll have to learn all that stuff

00:57:49.500 --> 00:57:51.000
in order to become queen.

00:57:51.059 --> 00:57:54.059
She lifted her wings to swim after the

00:57:54.059 --> 00:57:56.760
1st Dragon. and a pair of yellow striped

00:57:56.760 --> 00:57:58.619
fish wriggled out from under her and shot

00:57:58.619 --> 00:57:59.099
away.

00:57:59.159 --> 00:58:02.159
The sky blue dragon swam back the way

00:58:02.159 --> 00:58:04.679
he'd come, toward the stretch of open sea

00:58:04.679 --> 00:58:06.780
between this island and the one where

00:58:06.780 --> 00:58:08.039
tsunami's friends were sleeping.

00:58:08.099 --> 00:58:11.820
Now or never, tsunami thought.

00:58:11.880 --> 00:58:13.980
She'd rather meet this dragon than the

00:58:13.980 --> 00:58:15.960
other one, and she'd rather do it while

00:58:15.960 --> 00:58:17.460
he was alone, if she could.

00:58:17.519 --> 00:58:19.980
That seemed easier than trying to explain

00:58:19.980 --> 00:58:22.139
herself to a whole bunch of dragons at

00:58:22.139 --> 00:58:22.320
once.

00:58:22.380 --> 00:58:26.039
She beat her wings to catch up, dove over

00:58:26.039 --> 00:58:27.840
the edge of the reef and swam around in

00:58:27.840 --> 00:58:28.260
front of him.

00:58:28.320 --> 00:58:31.199
The sea wings started back in an eddy of

00:58:31.199 --> 00:58:31.619
ripples.

00:58:31.679 --> 00:58:34.500
His eyes were a blue so dark, they were

00:58:34.500 --> 00:58:35.039
almost black.

00:58:35.099 --> 00:58:37.679
Tsunami pointed up at the surface.

00:58:37.739 --> 00:58:40.739
Come on out of the water so we can talk.

00:58:40.800 --> 00:58:42.300
She tried to signal.

00:58:42.360 --> 00:58:44.460
Hopefully he'd figure out what she

00:58:44.460 --> 00:58:44.760
meant.

00:58:44.820 --> 00:58:48.239
To her surprise, he whipped around and

00:58:48.239 --> 00:58:48.960
fled.

00:58:49.019 --> 00:58:51.420
His tail smacked a wave of water in her

00:58:51.420 --> 00:58:51.780
face.

00:58:51.840 --> 00:58:56.099
Well, that's unfriendly, she thought.

00:58:56.159 --> 00:58:59.340
She swam after him, swinging her tail to

00:58:59.340 --> 00:59:00.659
propel herself even faster.

00:59:00.719 --> 00:59:03.599
He glanced back over his shoulder, saw

00:59:03.599 --> 00:59:05.639
her chasing him, and put on a burst of

00:59:05.639 --> 00:59:05.880
speed.

00:59:05.940 --> 00:59:08.219
Why was he running away?

00:59:08.280 --> 00:59:10.199
And how was he so fast?

00:59:10.260 --> 00:59:12.420
Stop!

00:59:12.539 --> 00:59:14.159
She tried to yell through the water.

00:59:14.219 --> 00:59:15.900
I just want to talk.

00:59:15.960 --> 00:59:18.000
Of course, that didn't work.

00:59:18.059 --> 00:59:19.739
He didn't even slow down.

00:59:19.800 --> 00:59:21.900
But then he twisted to look back at

00:59:21.900 --> 00:59:22.619
tsunami.

00:59:22.679 --> 00:59:24.960
And so he didn't see the whale that

00:59:24.960 --> 00:59:26.880
suddenly loomed out of the deep in front

00:59:26.880 --> 00:59:27.420
of him.

00:59:27.480 --> 00:59:29.699
Tsunami waved her talons and pointed

00:59:29.699 --> 00:59:33.239
Watch out, she shouted in a cascade of

00:59:33.239 --> 00:59:33.659
bubbles.

00:59:33.719 --> 00:59:36.360
The sea wing smacked into the whale's

00:59:36.360 --> 00:59:37.980
side and careened backward.

00:59:38.039 --> 00:59:40.260
The whale was only slightly bigger than

00:59:40.260 --> 00:59:42.780
the dragon, with ridges all along its

00:59:42.780 --> 00:59:45.360
back, and a flat, mild mannered face.

00:59:45.420 --> 00:59:49.139
It made a weird squeaking groan and

00:59:49.139 --> 00:59:50.880
blinked at the sea wing in confusion.

00:59:50.940 --> 00:59:53.519
The dragon was still shaking his head

00:59:53.519 --> 00:59:55.260
trying to reorient himself.

00:59:55.320 --> 00:59:58.500
When tsunami caught up, grabbed his tail

00:59:58.500 --> 00:59:59.639
and pinned him to the sand.

00:59:59.699 --> 01:00:02.340
The whale blinked again and swam on.

01:00:02.400 --> 01:00:05.820
Eddy's rippled around the 2 dragons as it

01:00:05.820 --> 01:00:06.780
powered away through the water.

01:00:06.840 --> 01:00:09.059
Now what do I do?

01:00:09.179 --> 01:00:10.440
Tsunami thought.

01:00:10.500 --> 01:00:12.780
I have to get him to the surface to talk

01:00:12.780 --> 01:00:13.500
to him.

01:00:13.559 --> 01:00:15.599
But if I let him go, he might try to

01:00:15.599 --> 01:00:16.079
escape again.

01:00:16.139 --> 01:00:19.260
She frowned down at the dragon and

01:00:19.260 --> 01:00:20.340
pointed at the surface again.

01:00:20.400 --> 01:00:23.579
Flashes of sunlight shimmered above them

01:00:23.579 --> 01:00:25.980
like pieces of broken, gold, white glass

01:00:25.980 --> 01:00:27.059
floating on the water.

01:00:27.119 --> 01:00:29.760
The other dragon tipped his head to one

01:00:29.760 --> 01:00:30.059
side.

01:00:30.119 --> 01:00:33.059
Luminescent stripes lit up along his

01:00:33.059 --> 01:00:36.239
wings, flashing fast, then slow.

01:00:36.539 --> 01:00:39.000
All right, tsunami thought.

01:00:39.059 --> 01:00:40.380
I can do that too.

01:00:40.440 --> 01:00:42.059
Maybe he's testing me.

01:00:42.119 --> 01:00:45.599
She lit up her own stripes, illuminating

01:00:45.599 --> 01:00:47.519
the ones on her snout, then the ones

01:00:47.519 --> 01:00:49.800
along her tail, and finally her wings.

01:00:49.920 --> 01:00:51.300
See?

01:00:51.360 --> 01:00:52.980
My stripes flash too.

01:00:53.039 --> 01:00:54.179
I'm a sea wing.

01:00:54.239 --> 01:00:55.920
Now let's go up and talk.

01:00:55.980 --> 01:00:59.099
Slowly, she spread her wings and lift it

01:00:59.099 --> 01:00:59.579
up.

01:00:59.639 --> 01:01:01.619
Prepared to grab him if he tried to bolt

01:01:01.619 --> 01:01:01.860
again.

01:01:01.920 --> 01:01:04.260
He scrambled upright, but stayed with

01:01:04.260 --> 01:01:04.440
her.

01:01:04.500 --> 01:01:07.860
Encouraged, tsunami swam a bit closer to

01:01:07.860 --> 01:01:08.280
the surface.

01:01:08.340 --> 01:01:11.340
He followed, but only for a bit before he

01:01:11.340 --> 01:01:12.239
stopped and looked around.

01:01:12.360 --> 01:01:15.659
His stripes flashed again, this time

01:01:15.659 --> 01:01:16.800
along his neck and tail.

01:01:16.920 --> 01:01:20.039
Impatiently tsunami lit up her stripes

01:01:20.039 --> 01:01:22.679
one more time, mirroring what he'd done.

01:01:22.739 --> 01:01:25.739
The sea wings wings flared open with a

01:01:25.739 --> 01:01:28.860
whoosh. that scared fish into the reef, he

01:01:28.860 --> 01:01:31.139
lunged towards tsunami, fast as a

01:01:31.139 --> 01:01:31.679
minnow.

01:01:31.739 --> 01:01:35.039
His front talons reached for her, tsunami

01:01:35.039 --> 01:01:37.320
roared, blasting him in the eyes with

01:01:37.320 --> 01:01:39.840
bubbles, and sliced her claws across his

01:01:39.840 --> 01:01:40.199
snout.

01:01:40.320 --> 01:01:42.480
She didn't know why he was attacking.

01:01:42.539 --> 01:01:45.480
Maybe he was a traitor's sea wing, or

01:01:45.480 --> 01:01:47.219
maybe he was guarding his territory or

01:01:47.219 --> 01:01:47.699
treasure.

01:01:47.760 --> 01:01:50.280
Perhaps he thought she was an intruder

01:01:50.280 --> 01:01:52.619
although he wasn't much of a guard if his

01:01:52.619 --> 01:01:55.679
1st instinct was to run away and his 2nd

01:01:55.679 --> 01:01:57.179
was to attack with no reason.

01:01:57.239 --> 01:01:59.940
He'll be sorry when he finds out who I

01:01:59.940 --> 01:02:00.179
am.

01:02:00.239 --> 01:02:01.980
She thought fiercely.

01:02:02.039 --> 01:02:04.500
She kicked his underbelly hard with her

01:02:04.500 --> 01:02:05.159
back legs.

01:02:05.219 --> 01:02:07.739
He coughed up a stream of bubbles and

01:02:07.739 --> 01:02:10.260
fell back. tsunami spread her wings

01:02:10.260 --> 01:02:13.320
snarled at him one more time, and shot to

01:02:13.320 --> 01:02:13.739
the surface.

01:02:13.800 --> 01:02:17.400
She burst into the air, and kept beating

01:02:17.400 --> 01:02:19.079
her wings to rise into the sky.

01:02:19.199 --> 01:02:21.840
In the distance, she could see the

01:02:21.840 --> 01:02:24.360
cliffside cave and the worried faces of

01:02:24.360 --> 01:02:25.440
her friends poking out.

01:02:25.500 --> 01:02:28.800
An enormous splash sounded behind her.

01:02:28.860 --> 01:02:31.860
The other sea wing surged out of the

01:02:31.860 --> 01:02:32.099
ocean.

01:02:32.159 --> 01:02:34.920
His massive tail whacked the water twice

01:02:34.920 --> 01:02:37.980
as he lifted into the air, sending giant

01:02:37.980 --> 01:02:39.719
waves rushing in all directions.

01:02:39.780 --> 01:02:42.119
He looked even bigger out here in the

01:02:42.119 --> 01:02:42.360
air.

01:02:42.420 --> 01:02:45.420
His hooked claws gleamed sharply in the

01:02:45.420 --> 01:02:45.900
sunlight.

01:02:45.960 --> 01:02:48.420
His dark blue eyes were fixed on her

01:02:48.420 --> 01:02:48.780
wings.

01:02:48.840 --> 01:02:52.019
The 1st true citizen of her kingdom she'd

01:02:52.019 --> 01:02:54.780
ever met, and he was coming to kill her.

01:02:54.840 --> 01:02:58.920
Chapter 4.

01:02:59.219 --> 01:03:02.699
Tsunami shot toward the island where her

01:03:02.699 --> 01:03:03.059
friends were.

01:03:03.179 --> 01:03:05.340
The sea wing was close on her tail.

01:03:05.460 --> 01:03:08.699
He roared something, but the wind whipped

01:03:08.699 --> 01:03:10.019
it away so she couldn't hear it.

01:03:10.079 --> 01:03:12.840
She saw Clay wriggle out of the cliff and

01:03:12.840 --> 01:03:13.619
take to the air.

01:03:13.679 --> 01:03:16.199
That's what she needed, back up.

01:03:16.260 --> 01:03:18.960
With a quick twist of her wings, she

01:03:18.960 --> 01:03:21.000
aimed for the strip of white, sandy beach

01:03:21.000 --> 01:03:22.559
where she'd wanted to sleep the night

01:03:22.559 --> 01:03:22.800
before.

01:03:22.860 --> 01:03:25.679
The other 3 could stay safely in the cave

01:03:25.679 --> 01:03:27.900
she and Clay together could handle this

01:03:27.900 --> 01:03:28.679
sea wing.

01:03:28.739 --> 01:03:29.820
She hoped.

01:03:29.880 --> 01:03:31.679
Wait.

01:03:31.739 --> 01:03:34.260
Her pursuer yelled, where are you going?

01:03:34.320 --> 01:03:35.219
What's wrong?

01:03:35.280 --> 01:03:38.460
Tsunami's wings missed a beat, and she

01:03:38.460 --> 01:03:39.840
nearly dropped into the ocean.

01:03:39.900 --> 01:03:42.539
She swung around, hovering over the sea

01:03:42.539 --> 01:03:44.699
between the cliff and the beach.

01:03:44.760 --> 01:03:46.559
Out of the corner of her eye, she saw

01:03:46.559 --> 01:03:48.539
clay veer into a circle in the air

01:03:48.539 --> 01:03:50.159
waiting to see what she would do.

01:03:50.219 --> 01:03:52.800
The other sea wing paused as well.

01:03:52.860 --> 01:03:55.619
He kept the length of 2 dragons between

01:03:55.619 --> 01:03:56.400
him and her.

01:03:56.460 --> 01:03:58.440
The scratches on his snout were

01:03:58.440 --> 01:03:58.860
bleeding.

01:03:58.920 --> 01:04:00.599
What's wrong?

01:04:00.719 --> 01:04:02.940
Tsunami cried indignantly.

01:04:03.000 --> 01:04:04.800
Didn't you just attack me?

01:04:04.860 --> 01:04:08.639
I certainly did not. he protested.

01:04:08.699 --> 01:04:11.579
Glowing lines flickered along his snout.

01:04:11.699 --> 01:04:13.139
I thought you.

01:04:13.920 --> 01:04:15.420
That's the normal.

01:04:15.480 --> 01:04:16.920
He seemed to be getting more and more

01:04:16.920 --> 01:04:17.519
embarrassed.

01:04:17.579 --> 01:04:21.480
You said you liked me, he finally burst

01:04:21.480 --> 01:04:21.780
out.

01:04:21.840 --> 01:04:25.559
I didn't say anything of the sort, tsunami

01:04:25.559 --> 01:04:27.000
said, astonished.

01:04:27.059 --> 01:04:29.039
The Sea Wing's brow furrowed.

01:04:29.099 --> 01:04:32.880
You very clearly said you liked me, and

01:04:32.880 --> 01:04:34.739
you'd followed me all the way out here to

01:04:34.739 --> 01:04:35.159
tell me that.

01:04:35.219 --> 01:04:38.579
Tsunami just about fell out of the sky.

01:04:38.639 --> 01:04:41.880
You are a delusional squid brain, she

01:04:41.880 --> 01:04:42.360
cried.

01:04:42.420 --> 01:04:46.320
Well, maybe not in those exact words. he

01:04:46.320 --> 01:04:46.559
said.

01:04:46.619 --> 01:04:48.900
All right, it was a little confusing.

01:04:48.960 --> 01:04:52.019
Maybe a lot confusing, but the message

01:04:52.019 --> 01:04:54.300
was in there, and why else would you be

01:04:54.300 --> 01:04:54.719
chasing me?

01:04:54.780 --> 01:04:58.500
When exactly do you imagine I said all

01:04:58.500 --> 01:04:58.739
this?

01:04:58.800 --> 01:05:01.739
Tsunami demanded shortly after you

01:05:01.739 --> 01:05:02.699
attacked me, perhaps?

01:05:02.760 --> 01:05:06.000
The other dragon touched his snout gently

01:05:06.000 --> 01:05:06.719
and winced.

01:05:06.780 --> 01:05:09.780
You were the only one doing any attacking

01:05:09.780 --> 01:05:10.860
he said.

01:05:10.920 --> 01:05:13.320
I was being friendly after what you

01:05:13.320 --> 01:05:13.679
said.

01:05:13.739 --> 01:05:17.280
Stop, tsunami said.

01:05:17.340 --> 01:05:20.219
Maybe she'd misunderstood his actions.

01:05:20.280 --> 01:05:22.920
Maybe his approach had been a sea wing

01:05:22.920 --> 01:05:25.500
greeting ritual she didn't know, in which

01:05:25.500 --> 01:05:28.019
case, his poor snout.

01:05:28.019 --> 01:05:29.699
She winced guiltily.

01:05:29.760 --> 01:05:31.679
Perhaps she shouldn't have gotten

01:05:31.679 --> 01:05:32.639
defensive so quickly.

01:05:32.699 --> 01:05:36.119
Tell me exactly what you think I said.

01:05:36.239 --> 01:05:37.739
He sighed.

01:05:37.800 --> 01:05:40.920
I said, what are you doing all the way

01:05:40.920 --> 01:05:41.280
out here?

01:05:41.400 --> 01:05:43.320
And you said.

01:05:43.800 --> 01:05:46.380
He paused, rubbing his front talons

01:05:46.380 --> 01:05:47.340
against his head.

01:05:47.400 --> 01:05:51.659
You said, hey, sparkling teeth, I totally

01:05:51.659 --> 01:05:53.820
love 3 of your claws but not the others

01:05:53.820 --> 01:05:56.159
and I wish your nose was a herring so I

01:05:56.159 --> 01:05:56.579
could eat it.

01:05:56.639 --> 01:05:59.340
And also your wings sound like sharks

01:05:59.340 --> 01:05:59.880
snoring.

01:06:00.000 --> 01:06:02.820
Tsunami burst out laughing.

01:06:02.880 --> 01:06:05.519
All right, I get it, she said.

01:06:05.579 --> 01:06:07.320
Although she didn't really.

01:06:07.380 --> 01:06:10.019
Did all sea wings have a strange sense of

01:06:10.019 --> 01:06:10.440
humor?

01:06:10.500 --> 01:06:12.179
Would she have to develop one too?

01:06:12.239 --> 01:06:14.099
You're making this up?

01:06:14.159 --> 01:06:15.719
He stared at her.

01:06:15.780 --> 01:06:18.420
Are you seriously going to pretend you

01:06:18.420 --> 01:06:19.079
didn't say any of that?

01:06:19.139 --> 01:06:21.059
Of course I didn't.

01:06:21.119 --> 01:06:22.500
Tsunami said.

01:06:22.559 --> 01:06:24.119
Maybe he wasn't kidding.

01:06:24.239 --> 01:06:26.639
Maybe he was mentally unbalanced.

01:06:26.699 --> 01:06:29.039
I didn't say anything at all.

01:06:29.099 --> 01:06:31.019
We were underwater, remember?

01:06:31.079 --> 01:06:33.900
The strange dragon hovered for several

01:06:33.900 --> 01:06:36.599
wing beats, glowing stripes lighting up

01:06:36.599 --> 01:06:37.800
along his blue scales.

01:06:37.860 --> 01:06:40.920
His face slowly went from confused to

01:06:40.920 --> 01:06:42.119
angry as he frowned at her.

01:06:42.179 --> 01:06:43.860
Who are you?

01:06:43.920 --> 01:06:45.119
He demanded.

01:06:45.239 --> 01:06:48.179
I'm a sea wing, she said hotly.

01:06:48.239 --> 01:06:50.639
Just like you, so no need to get

01:06:50.639 --> 01:06:51.000
hostile.

01:06:51.059 --> 01:06:55.199
A sea wing who doesn't speak aquatic, he

01:06:55.199 --> 01:06:56.880
growled, not likely.

01:06:56.940 --> 01:06:58.440
What are you really?

01:06:58.559 --> 01:07:00.719
How did you make yourself look like a sea

01:07:00.719 --> 01:07:01.079
wing?

01:07:01.139 --> 01:07:03.539
Tsunami's heart sank?

01:07:03.599 --> 01:07:05.219
Aquatic?

01:07:05.280 --> 01:07:08.219
Sea wings have their own language?

01:07:08.280 --> 01:07:11.880
Of course they do, she realized.

01:07:11.940 --> 01:07:13.980
It felt like the tide was going out

01:07:13.980 --> 01:07:16.619
inside her, leaving nothing but stretches

01:07:16.619 --> 01:07:17.639
of bare sand.

01:07:17.699 --> 01:07:21.059
And of course, nobody ever bothered to

01:07:21.059 --> 01:07:21.659
teach it to me.

01:07:21.719 --> 01:07:24.840
Just one more creative way the talents

01:07:24.840 --> 01:07:25.980
found to ruin my life.

01:07:26.039 --> 01:07:29.039
Why hadn't she thought of that before?

01:07:29.159 --> 01:07:31.260
Three moons.

01:07:31.320 --> 01:07:32.460
She was as thick as clay.

01:07:32.519 --> 01:07:35.159
The dragons of the sea had a whole palace

01:07:35.159 --> 01:07:35.639
underwater.

01:07:35.699 --> 01:07:37.559
Of course, they needed a way to

01:07:37.559 --> 01:07:38.760
communicate down there.

01:07:38.820 --> 01:07:40.679
They couldn't just pop to the surface

01:07:40.679 --> 01:07:42.780
every time they needed to chat.

01:07:42.840 --> 01:07:45.239
She glanced down at her webbed talons and

01:07:45.239 --> 01:07:47.340
remembered the gestures she'd seen the 2

01:07:47.340 --> 01:07:49.260
sea wings making while their luminescent

01:07:49.260 --> 01:07:50.460
stripes flashed.

01:07:50.519 --> 01:07:52.739
Talent signals and glowing stripes.

01:07:52.800 --> 01:07:55.260
She must have said all that nonsense with

01:07:55.260 --> 01:07:56.820
her stripes without realizing it.

01:07:56.940 --> 01:08:00.780
But how can I be queen of the sea wings

01:08:00.780 --> 01:08:02.880
if I don't even speak their language?

01:08:02.940 --> 01:08:05.880
And why didn't anyone ever tell me about

01:08:05.880 --> 01:08:06.059
this?

01:08:06.179 --> 01:08:09.659
Clay had never met a dragon of his own

01:08:09.659 --> 01:08:10.260
kind before.

01:08:10.320 --> 01:08:12.360
That's why he knew nothing about mud

01:08:12.360 --> 01:08:14.579
wings, but tsunami didn't have that

01:08:14.579 --> 01:08:14.880
excuse.

01:08:15.000 --> 01:08:17.579
One of the guardians who'd raised them

01:08:17.579 --> 01:08:18.600
had been a sea wing.

01:08:18.659 --> 01:08:20.039
So why?

01:08:20.100 --> 01:08:21.600
Why?

01:08:21.659 --> 01:08:23.939
Had Webbs never taught her the sea wing

01:08:23.939 --> 01:08:25.859
language, or even told her they had one?

01:08:25.979 --> 01:08:29.039
All those scrolls about sea wings.

01:08:29.100 --> 01:08:30.840
Not that she thought about it.

01:08:30.899 --> 01:08:33.059
There was plenty of dialogue in the

01:08:33.059 --> 01:08:35.279
underwater scenes, like in the missing

01:08:35.279 --> 01:08:37.319
princess when the lost daughter found her

01:08:37.319 --> 01:08:37.679
parents.

01:08:37.800 --> 01:08:40.680
Tsunami had always assumed that was a

01:08:40.680 --> 01:08:42.899
storytelling technique, not an actual

01:08:42.899 --> 01:08:44.220
underwater language.

01:08:44.279 --> 01:08:47.579
She looked up and met the sea wings, dark

01:08:47.579 --> 01:08:48.299
blue eyes.

01:08:48.359 --> 01:08:50.219
His head was tilted curiously.

01:08:50.340 --> 01:08:54.539
You don't look guilty, he observed.

01:08:54.600 --> 01:08:58.140
You look sad, and I imagine it would be

01:08:58.140 --> 01:08:59.579
hard to fake those.

01:08:59.640 --> 01:09:01.859
He nodded at the webs between our claws.

01:09:01.920 --> 01:09:03.779
So where did you come from?

01:09:03.899 --> 01:09:05.639
And what's wrong with you?

01:09:05.699 --> 01:09:07.979
Tsunami bristled.

01:09:08.039 --> 01:09:10.859
There's nothing wrong with me, she

01:09:10.859 --> 01:09:11.399
snapped.

01:09:11.460 --> 01:09:13.619
I just happened to have been raised by

01:09:13.619 --> 01:09:14.159
idiot.

01:09:14.220 --> 01:09:16.680
His gaze suddenly shifted behind her.

01:09:16.739 --> 01:09:18.000
Look out.

01:09:18.060 --> 01:09:20.760
He yelled, his tail whipped around and

01:09:20.760 --> 01:09:22.859
slammed into her, knocking her aside.

01:09:22.920 --> 01:09:25.560
She spun toward the water, dizzy and

01:09:25.560 --> 01:09:26.279
shocked.

01:09:26.279 --> 01:09:28.800
Her wings brushed the ocean waves as she

01:09:28.800 --> 01:09:30.300
righted herself and turned around.

01:09:30.359 --> 01:09:32.939
The strange sea wing was grappling with

01:09:32.939 --> 01:09:34.139
clay up in the sky.

01:09:34.199 --> 01:09:35.819
Tsunami gasped.

01:09:35.880 --> 01:09:38.579
The sea wing was full grown, bigger than

01:09:38.579 --> 01:09:40.859
clay, and he was not afraid to lash out

01:09:40.859 --> 01:09:42.720
with teeth, tail, and claws.

01:09:42.779 --> 01:09:44.939
But she could tell clay was holding back

01:09:45.000 --> 01:09:47.340
worried about hurting a possible ally.

01:09:47.399 --> 01:09:49.559
He ducked his head between his front

01:09:49.559 --> 01:09:52.439
talons and tried to dive away, but the

01:09:52.439 --> 01:09:55.079
sea wing seized Clay's tail and dug his

01:09:55.079 --> 01:09:57.479
talons viciously into Clay's scales.

01:09:57.539 --> 01:09:58.920
Clay howled with pain.

01:09:58.979 --> 01:10:01.739
The other dragons started to drag him

01:10:01.739 --> 01:10:03.720
down to the ocean, where he would have

01:10:03.720 --> 01:10:05.760
all the underwater advantages of sea

01:10:05.760 --> 01:10:08.699
wings, and clay would eventually drown.

01:10:08.760 --> 01:10:09.720
Clay!

01:10:09.779 --> 01:10:12.359
Sonny shrieked, launching herself out of

01:10:12.359 --> 01:10:13.380
the cliffside cave.

01:10:13.439 --> 01:10:15.119
Tsunami got there first.

01:10:15.180 --> 01:10:17.579
She smacked the sea wing over the head

01:10:17.579 --> 01:10:19.859
with her tail, seized his wing and her

01:10:19.859 --> 01:10:22.020
talons, and yanked him away from clay

01:10:22.020 --> 01:10:24.060
when he turned around in surprise.

01:10:24.119 --> 01:10:26.039
He tried to spin around her to get back

01:10:26.039 --> 01:10:28.380
to his prey, but she blocked him with her

01:10:28.380 --> 01:10:30.420
wings and lashed out at his snout again.

01:10:30.479 --> 01:10:33.060
He flinched back, and that was enough

01:10:33.060 --> 01:10:35.039
time for Clay to scramble out of reach.

01:10:35.100 --> 01:10:36.899
What are you doing?

01:10:36.960 --> 01:10:39.060
The sea wing yelled at tsunami.

01:10:39.119 --> 01:10:41.220
I'm saving you from that mud wing.

01:10:41.279 --> 01:10:43.260
Well, don't!

01:10:43.319 --> 01:10:44.460
Tsunami yelled back.

01:10:44.520 --> 01:10:45.420
He's my friend.

01:10:45.479 --> 01:10:49.439
But Sunny slammed into the back of the

01:10:49.439 --> 01:10:51.779
sea wing, landing between his wings and

01:10:51.779 --> 01:10:53.460
wrapping her talons around his neck.

01:10:53.460 --> 01:10:57.000
Leave him alone, she panted.

01:10:57.119 --> 01:10:59.579
The sea wing looked more astonished than

01:10:59.579 --> 01:11:00.119
alarmed.

01:11:00.180 --> 01:11:02.579
He wriggled his shoulders and twisted his

01:11:02.579 --> 01:11:04.319
neck, trying to see what was on his

01:11:04.319 --> 01:11:04.680
back.

01:11:04.739 --> 01:11:07.020
Sonny kicked his wing and he yelped.

01:11:07.079 --> 01:11:10.199
That's my other friend, tsunami said.

01:11:10.260 --> 01:11:12.600
Sunny, try not to hurt him too badly.

01:11:12.659 --> 01:11:13.439
We need his help.

01:11:13.500 --> 01:11:16.619
I hardly think this gnat is going to hurt

01:11:16.619 --> 01:11:16.920
me.

01:11:16.979 --> 01:11:18.779
The sea wing growled.

01:11:18.840 --> 01:11:20.460
Sonny kicked him again.

01:11:20.520 --> 01:11:23.880
Promise me you won't attack clay, she

01:11:23.880 --> 01:11:24.119
said.

01:11:24.180 --> 01:11:26.880
His eyes went to the brown dragon

01:11:26.880 --> 01:11:28.260
circling just above them.

01:11:28.319 --> 01:11:30.300
Clay rubbed his head anxiously.

01:11:30.359 --> 01:11:33.239
The mud wings are our enemies.

01:11:33.300 --> 01:11:35.460
The sea wings snarled at tsunami.

01:11:35.520 --> 01:11:37.800
If you don't know that, then you'd better

01:11:37.800 --> 01:11:40.079
leave the Bay of a 1000 scales, before

01:11:40.079 --> 01:11:42.539
Queen Carl's army finds you and does what

01:11:42.539 --> 01:11:43.920
they always do to traitors.

01:11:43.979 --> 01:11:48.899
I'm not a traitor, tsunami said, and clay

01:11:48.899 --> 01:11:49.680
is not your enemy.

01:11:49.739 --> 01:11:52.800
She glanced up at him, then back at the

01:11:52.800 --> 01:11:53.279
sea wing.

01:11:53.340 --> 01:11:55.859
You'd better learn some respect, squid

01:11:55.859 --> 01:11:56.340
brain.

01:11:56.399 --> 01:11:58.319
We're the dragonettes of destiny.

01:11:58.380 --> 01:12:02.460
Chapter 5.

01:12:02.760 --> 01:12:06.659
Riptide, Sonny said again.

01:12:06.720 --> 01:12:07.979
That's a funny name.

01:12:08.039 --> 01:12:10.920
I like it, tsunami said.

01:12:10.979 --> 01:12:12.840
Fierce and scary, like mine.

01:12:12.960 --> 01:12:16.680
Ribtide was pacing the beach, lashing his

01:12:16.680 --> 01:12:18.840
tail in a long, swishing trail through

01:12:18.840 --> 01:12:19.380
the sand.

01:12:19.439 --> 01:12:22.199
His sky blue scales glinted metallically

01:12:22.199 --> 01:12:23.159
in the morning light.

01:12:23.220 --> 01:12:26.340
He had claw mark scars along his pale

01:12:26.340 --> 01:12:28.619
underbelly, and what looked like an old

01:12:28.619 --> 01:12:29.760
bite mark on his tail.

01:12:29.819 --> 01:12:32.699
Tsunami was pretty sure he was only a

01:12:32.699 --> 01:12:34.619
couple years older than she was.

01:12:34.680 --> 01:12:37.140
The scratches she'd given his snout had

01:12:37.140 --> 01:12:38.460
finally stopped bleeding.

01:12:38.520 --> 01:12:40.560
She hoped those wouldn't leave scars

01:12:40.560 --> 01:12:40.859
too.

01:12:40.979 --> 01:12:43.439
He had a very handsome snout when it

01:12:43.439 --> 01:12:44.399
wasn't all clawed up.

01:12:44.460 --> 01:12:47.279
All right, he said.

01:12:47.340 --> 01:12:50.100
So the talons of peace are real.

01:12:50.159 --> 01:12:54.060
Unfortunately, Glory muttered.

01:12:54.119 --> 01:12:57.000
Ribtide glanced at her, and tsunami felt

01:12:57.000 --> 01:12:58.859
a weird tingle of jealousy run through

01:12:58.859 --> 01:12:59.399
her scales.

01:12:59.460 --> 01:13:02.399
Glory had found a large rock to perch on

01:13:02.399 --> 01:13:05.340
spreading her wings open to the sun, and

01:13:05.340 --> 01:13:07.020
her scales were shimmering silver and

01:13:07.020 --> 01:13:07.260
rose.

01:13:07.380 --> 01:13:10.739
I thought everyone knew about the talons

01:13:10.739 --> 01:13:11.760
Sonny said.

01:13:11.880 --> 01:13:16.500
Just rumors and whispers, said Riptide.

01:13:16.560 --> 01:13:19.260
None of the tribe queens would be pleased

01:13:19.260 --> 01:13:21.119
to find a member of the peace movement in

01:13:21.119 --> 01:13:24.539
their midst, conspiring with other tribes

01:13:24.539 --> 01:13:25.319
stealing eggs?

01:13:25.439 --> 01:13:26.699
He shook his head.

01:13:26.760 --> 01:13:29.579
Queen Coral would kill any dragon she

01:13:29.579 --> 01:13:30.779
found working with a talons.

01:13:30.899 --> 01:13:33.899
He gave tsunami a searching look she

01:13:33.899 --> 01:13:34.619
didn't understand.

01:13:34.680 --> 01:13:37.020
Clay was sitting with his tail in the

01:13:37.020 --> 01:13:37.260
water.

01:13:37.319 --> 01:13:39.899
He had muddy sand packed over the spot

01:13:39.899 --> 01:13:41.399
where riptide had clawed him.

01:13:41.460 --> 01:13:44.460
Sonny sat next to him, giving riptide

01:13:44.460 --> 01:13:46.560
fierce looks whenever he paced too close

01:13:46.560 --> 01:13:47.279
to clay.

01:13:47.279 --> 01:13:50.760
And you're the dragonets of destiny.

01:13:50.819 --> 01:13:53.579
For real, the ones in the prophecy.

01:13:53.640 --> 01:13:55.319
That's real.

01:13:55.439 --> 01:13:59.460
Riptide stopped, inhaled deeply, and blew

01:13:59.460 --> 01:13:59.760
out again.

01:13:59.819 --> 01:14:01.800
And you're here.

01:14:01.859 --> 01:14:03.840
In sea wing territory.

01:14:03.899 --> 01:14:07.560
Just like, He glanced at tsunami again

01:14:07.560 --> 01:14:08.699
then went back to pacing.

01:14:08.760 --> 01:14:12.899
I know, it's thrilling, tsunami said, but

01:14:12.899 --> 01:14:14.460
we're really looking for somewhere safe

01:14:14.460 --> 01:14:14.699
to go.

01:14:14.760 --> 01:14:17.340
The talons of peace treated us terribly

01:14:17.340 --> 01:14:19.619
and I figured the sea wings would welcome

01:14:19.619 --> 01:14:20.340
and protect us.

01:14:20.460 --> 01:14:25.140
I suppose, Riptide said, not very

01:14:25.140 --> 01:14:26.039
reassuringly.

01:14:26.100 --> 01:14:28.859
So you were all raised in a cave?

01:14:28.920 --> 01:14:31.500
He stopped in front of tsunami.

01:14:31.500 --> 01:14:33.600
With no ocean?

01:14:33.720 --> 01:14:34.560
Never.

01:14:34.619 --> 01:14:36.300
You never went into the ocean?

01:14:36.359 --> 01:14:39.119
This seemed to be the hardest part for

01:14:39.119 --> 01:14:39.720
him to believe.

01:14:39.779 --> 01:14:43.380
Not until we escaped, tsunami said.

01:14:43.439 --> 01:14:47.039
But that's awful, said Riptide.

01:14:47.100 --> 01:14:50.520
Thank you, tsunami said, flaring her

01:14:50.520 --> 01:14:50.880
wings.

01:14:50.939 --> 01:14:52.260
I know it was.

01:14:52.319 --> 01:14:54.600
I've always said our life was miserable

01:14:54.600 --> 01:14:56.760
but these dragons keep arguing with me.

01:14:56.819 --> 01:14:59.579
Not me, Glory said.

01:14:59.640 --> 01:15:02.279
I can't believe the talents did that to

01:15:02.279 --> 01:15:05.399
you, Riptide said, clawing the sand.

01:15:05.460 --> 01:15:07.079
Tell me about it.

01:15:07.140 --> 01:15:08.460
Tsunami said.

01:15:08.520 --> 01:15:09.779
They really are the worst.

01:15:09.840 --> 01:15:14.220
Even webs, webs didn't take you to the

01:15:14.220 --> 01:15:14.640
ocean?

01:15:14.699 --> 01:15:16.380
Riptide asked.

01:15:16.439 --> 01:15:18.840
You know about webs?

01:15:18.899 --> 01:15:20.039
Sonny asked.

01:15:20.100 --> 01:15:22.560
Riptide ducked his head and frowned at

01:15:22.560 --> 01:15:23.399
his talons.

01:15:23.399 --> 01:15:25.979
He's pretty infamous in the tribe.

01:15:26.039 --> 01:15:29.520
We all know he deserted during a battle

01:15:29.520 --> 01:15:32.220
and later he came back and stole one of

01:15:32.220 --> 01:15:33.239
the queen's eggs.

01:15:33.300 --> 01:15:35.939
At least, Queen Coral was sure it was

01:15:35.939 --> 01:15:36.119
him.

01:15:36.239 --> 01:15:38.640
But nobody knew if he stole it for the

01:15:38.640 --> 01:15:40.859
talons of peace, or for his own reasons.

01:15:40.920 --> 01:15:43.500
We're not really supposed to talk about

01:15:43.500 --> 01:15:45.000
the talents of peace rumors.

01:15:45.119 --> 01:15:47.939
Didn't anyone think he might have stolen

01:15:47.939 --> 01:15:49.500
the egg to be part of the prophecy?

01:15:49.560 --> 01:15:51.119
Starflight asked.

01:15:51.180 --> 01:15:52.500
Riptide nodded.

01:15:52.560 --> 01:15:54.060
Some of us did.

01:15:54.119 --> 01:15:56.220
But again, nobody talked about it.

01:15:56.279 --> 01:15:58.619
Queen Blister doesn't like hearing about

01:15:58.619 --> 01:16:00.899
the prophecy, so that's also been a

01:16:00.899 --> 01:16:01.979
forbidden topic.

01:16:02.039 --> 01:16:04.380
Tsunami wrinkled her snout.

01:16:04.439 --> 01:16:07.739
Blister gets to decide what sea wings can

01:16:07.739 --> 01:16:08.159
talk about?

01:16:08.220 --> 01:16:11.100
Riptide shifted uncomfortably and picked

01:16:11.100 --> 01:16:12.479
up a large conch shell.

01:16:12.539 --> 01:16:14.220
He twisted it between his talons.

01:16:14.279 --> 01:16:17.520
You'll want to call her Queen blister

01:16:17.520 --> 01:16:19.260
when you meet her, he said.

01:16:19.319 --> 01:16:22.739
Not until we decide she should be queen

01:16:22.739 --> 01:16:25.920
tsunami said stoutly, that's up to us

01:16:25.920 --> 01:16:26.520
remember?

01:16:26.579 --> 01:16:29.699
It looked for a moment like riptide was

01:16:29.699 --> 01:16:30.359
trying not to smile.

01:16:30.479 --> 01:16:34.979
Well, Starflight stammered, she is a

01:16:34.979 --> 01:16:35.520
pretty good.

01:16:35.579 --> 01:16:37.800
I mean, she's the smart one.

01:16:37.859 --> 01:16:41.159
I think we'll probably, tsunami tilted

01:16:41.159 --> 01:16:41.699
her head at him.

01:16:41.760 --> 01:16:43.380
What was he rattling on about?

01:16:43.439 --> 01:16:45.779
He snapped his mouth shut and went back

01:16:45.779 --> 01:16:47.279
to picking sand out of his scales.

01:16:47.340 --> 01:16:50.220
Did you know webs?

01:16:50.279 --> 01:16:51.899
Clay asked riptide.

01:16:51.960 --> 01:16:53.760
The sea wing dropped his gaze.

01:16:53.819 --> 01:16:55.260
Not really.

01:16:55.319 --> 01:16:57.779
He ran away during a battle when I was

01:16:57.779 --> 01:17:00.239
only 2 years old, but I've been hearing

01:17:00.239 --> 01:17:01.800
about his treachery my whole life.

01:17:01.859 --> 01:17:03.659
He sighed.

01:17:03.720 --> 01:17:06.060
I really can't believe he never took you

01:17:06.060 --> 01:17:07.500
to the ocean and all that time.

01:17:07.560 --> 01:17:11.039
It's true, tsunami said.

01:17:11.159 --> 01:17:13.380
And he never taught me aquatic.

01:17:13.439 --> 01:17:15.899
I wish I had all the talons apiece here

01:17:15.899 --> 01:17:16.800
so I could bite them.

01:17:16.859 --> 01:17:20.340
To be fair, the talons were just keeping

01:17:20.340 --> 01:17:22.739
us safe, Sonny interjected.

01:17:22.800 --> 01:17:25.260
They needed us to survive to fulfill the

01:17:25.260 --> 01:17:25.739
prophecy.

01:17:25.800 --> 01:17:28.920
Tsunami snorted, and Sonny gave her an

01:17:28.920 --> 01:17:29.760
injured look.

01:17:29.819 --> 01:17:33.600
But the prophecy, Riptide said.

01:17:33.659 --> 01:17:34.979
He pointed at glory.

01:17:35.039 --> 01:17:37.920
It calls for a sky wing.

01:17:37.979 --> 01:17:39.180
She's not a sky wing.

01:17:39.239 --> 01:17:43.500
It's a little complicated, tsunami said

01:17:43.500 --> 01:17:45.840
as a hint of sea green rippled across

01:17:45.840 --> 01:17:46.800
Glory's scales.

01:17:46.859 --> 01:17:50.100
Anyway, I'm not sure we really care about

01:17:50.100 --> 01:17:52.199
the prophecy, but we do care about

01:17:52.199 --> 01:17:53.819
finding the families we were stolen

01:17:53.819 --> 01:17:54.060
from.

01:17:54.119 --> 01:17:58.020
I care about the prophecy, Sonny

01:17:58.020 --> 01:17:58.500
protested.

01:17:58.560 --> 01:18:00.840
She poked Clay's side, and he nodded

01:18:00.840 --> 01:18:01.380
agreeably.

01:18:01.439 --> 01:18:04.199
Starflight cleared his throat, but

01:18:04.199 --> 01:18:05.819
tsunami hurried on before he could start

01:18:05.819 --> 01:18:06.539
lecturing again.

01:18:06.600 --> 01:18:09.000
His egg hadn't been stolen.

01:18:09.060 --> 01:18:10.859
The night wings had handed it right

01:18:10.859 --> 01:18:11.100
over.

01:18:11.159 --> 01:18:13.260
So maybe he didn't care about getting

01:18:13.260 --> 01:18:15.060
home, but she certainly did.

01:18:15.119 --> 01:18:19.199
Only a few days ago, I found out I was

01:18:19.199 --> 01:18:21.659
stolen from the royal hatchery, tsunami

01:18:21.659 --> 01:18:21.960
said.

01:18:22.020 --> 01:18:25.619
So, So I thought maybe my parents were

01:18:25.619 --> 01:18:26.220
looking for me.

01:18:26.279 --> 01:18:28.500
Like in the missing princess?

01:18:28.560 --> 01:18:29.880
Do you know that scroll?

01:18:29.939 --> 01:18:33.300
Riptide definitely squashed a smile this

01:18:33.300 --> 01:18:33.539
time.

01:18:33.600 --> 01:18:35.880
I do, he said.

01:18:35.939 --> 01:18:37.859
It's required reading in school.

01:18:37.920 --> 01:18:43.439
School, Starflight said, in the wistful

01:18:43.439 --> 01:18:45.359
tones Clay used to talk about food.

01:18:45.359 --> 01:18:47.819
Required reading?

01:18:47.939 --> 01:18:49.439
Tsunami echoed.

01:18:49.500 --> 01:18:50.939
That was odd.

01:18:51.000 --> 01:18:53.159
It was a fairy tale, not a historical

01:18:53.159 --> 01:18:55.680
document, and not perhaps the best

01:18:55.680 --> 01:18:58.079
written scroll she'd ever read, although

01:18:58.079 --> 01:18:59.460
it was still one of her favorites because

01:18:59.460 --> 01:18:59.939
of the story.

01:19:00.000 --> 01:19:03.300
But I can't take you to the palace

01:19:03.300 --> 01:19:06.720
Riptide said firmly, not with him along.

01:19:06.779 --> 01:19:08.939
He jerked his head at clay.

01:19:09.000 --> 01:19:10.800
Weren't you listening?

01:19:10.859 --> 01:19:12.960
Tsunami said, exasperated.

01:19:13.020 --> 01:19:15.300
He's not a regular mudwing.

01:19:15.359 --> 01:19:17.640
He's certainly not allied with Bern or

01:19:17.640 --> 01:19:18.539
the Skywings.

01:19:18.600 --> 01:19:19.560
You can trust him.

01:19:19.619 --> 01:19:23.760
Perhaps you should stay here, Riptide

01:19:23.760 --> 01:19:26.100
suggested, and I'll bring Queen Coral

01:19:26.100 --> 01:19:26.520
back to you.

01:19:26.579 --> 01:19:29.220
He glanced across the water the other

01:19:29.220 --> 01:19:31.319
island, where he'd met the green dragon

01:19:31.319 --> 01:19:33.180
with the black spiral patterns.

01:19:33.180 --> 01:19:34.859
Tsunami wondered if he was wishing for

01:19:34.859 --> 01:19:35.579
reinforcements.

01:19:35.640 --> 01:19:39.300
Nope, she said, we're all coming with

01:19:39.300 --> 01:19:39.479
you.

01:19:39.600 --> 01:19:42.840
I'm in enough trouble with Queen Coral.

01:19:42.960 --> 01:19:44.699
Riptide protested.

01:19:44.760 --> 01:19:46.319
That's why I'm stuck patrolling all the

01:19:46.319 --> 01:19:46.739
way out here.

01:19:46.800 --> 01:19:49.439
If I bring a mud wing back to the palace

01:19:49.439 --> 01:19:51.300
I might as well pull out my own teeth.

01:19:51.420 --> 01:19:54.239
Ew, Sonny cried.

01:19:54.300 --> 01:19:56.939
That's not a real punishment, is it?

01:19:57.000 --> 01:20:00.060
Tsunami, didn't want to know the answer

01:20:00.060 --> 01:20:00.300
to that.

01:20:00.359 --> 01:20:02.399
She wanted to meet her mother without

01:20:02.399 --> 01:20:04.439
images of horrible things in her head.

01:20:04.500 --> 01:20:07.500
Think of it this way, she said quickly.

01:20:07.560 --> 01:20:10.380
What happens if Queen Carl finds out you

01:20:10.380 --> 01:20:12.659
met her missing daughter and didn't bring

01:20:12.659 --> 01:20:13.560
her back to the palace?

01:20:13.619 --> 01:20:16.979
Riptide squirmed and wrinkled his snout.

01:20:17.100 --> 01:20:20.039
Can't I bring you and leave the others?

01:20:20.100 --> 01:20:21.000
he asked.

01:20:21.060 --> 01:20:23.460
At least until Queen Carl gives her

01:20:23.460 --> 01:20:23.699
permission?

01:20:23.760 --> 01:20:27.119
No, she said stoutly.

01:20:27.180 --> 01:20:28.319
We all go together.

01:20:28.380 --> 01:20:31.140
She'll understand once she realizes we're

01:20:31.140 --> 01:20:32.220
the dragonettes of destiny.

01:20:32.279 --> 01:20:34.140
Riptide side.

01:20:34.199 --> 01:20:37.500
All right, but he has to be blindfolded.

01:20:37.560 --> 01:20:40.500
He looked at the other three, rubbing his

01:20:40.500 --> 01:20:40.800
chin.

01:20:40.859 --> 01:20:43.680
It'd be better if they could all be

01:20:43.680 --> 01:20:44.460
blindfolded.

01:20:44.520 --> 01:20:47.460
What am I going to do?

01:20:47.579 --> 01:20:48.779
Glory asked.

01:20:48.840 --> 01:20:51.659
Round up some scary rain wings to come

01:20:51.659 --> 01:20:52.560
sleep on your roof?

01:20:52.619 --> 01:20:54.600
And I thought no one was afraid of my

01:20:54.600 --> 01:20:55.020
tribe.

01:20:55.079 --> 01:20:58.260
We're not, Riptide objected.

01:20:58.319 --> 01:21:00.060
Afraid of rain wings?

01:21:00.119 --> 01:21:00.659
Psst.

01:21:00.720 --> 01:21:01.619
What a thing to say.

01:21:01.680 --> 01:21:05.340
More streaks of pale green appeared along

01:21:05.340 --> 01:21:07.079
Glory's scales and then faded away.

01:21:07.140 --> 01:21:08.399
Wonderful.

01:21:08.460 --> 01:21:09.479
She said.

01:21:09.539 --> 01:21:11.699
So, no blindfold for me then.

01:21:11.819 --> 01:21:13.920
She tossed her head and turned back to

01:21:13.920 --> 01:21:14.279
the ocean.

01:21:14.340 --> 01:21:17.159
Riptide looked doubtfully at Starflight

01:21:17.159 --> 01:21:17.579
and Sunny.

01:21:17.640 --> 01:21:20.579
The night wings know everything.

01:21:20.640 --> 01:21:22.319
Starflight said loftily.

01:21:22.380 --> 01:21:24.720
It's no use trying to keep secrets from

01:21:24.720 --> 01:21:24.899
them.

01:21:24.960 --> 01:21:25.979
I mean, us.

01:21:26.039 --> 01:21:28.560
I could just use my powers to figure out

01:21:28.560 --> 01:21:29.340
where your palace is.

01:21:29.399 --> 01:21:32.100
Tsunami rolled her eyes.

01:21:32.159 --> 01:21:34.739
Starfly had no powers whatsoever.

01:21:34.800 --> 01:21:37.079
As far as any of the dragonettes knew.

01:21:37.140 --> 01:21:39.180
But if he wanted the sea wings to think

01:21:39.180 --> 01:21:40.920
he did, maybe that could be useful

01:21:40.920 --> 01:21:41.460
eventually.

01:21:41.520 --> 01:21:45.300
Please don't argue with him, Tsunami said

01:21:45.300 --> 01:21:46.020
to Riptide.

01:21:46.079 --> 01:21:48.300
Once he starts yammering on about how

01:21:48.300 --> 01:21:50.460
amazing night wings are, we'll never get

01:21:50.460 --> 01:21:51.300
him to shut up.

01:21:51.479 --> 01:21:54.420
Starflight ruffled his wings in outrage.

01:21:54.479 --> 01:21:56.520
Riptide muttered something under his

01:21:56.520 --> 01:21:58.680
breath and started poking around in the

01:21:58.680 --> 01:21:59.939
shallow water below the rocks.

01:22:00.000 --> 01:22:03.539
You can blindfold me, Sonny offered.

01:22:03.600 --> 01:22:04.439
I don't mind.

01:22:04.500 --> 01:22:08.220
If you do that, she can ride on my back

01:22:08.220 --> 01:22:09.600
tsunami suggested.

01:22:09.659 --> 01:22:12.119
She missed having a little sand wing come

01:22:12.119 --> 01:22:13.500
lean against her trustingly.

01:22:13.560 --> 01:22:16.140
Sonny was still acting jumpy and nervous

01:22:16.140 --> 01:22:16.560
around her.

01:22:16.619 --> 01:22:19.979
Four whole days after her fight with a

01:22:19.979 --> 01:22:22.739
Skywing soldier, as if tsunami might

01:22:22.739 --> 01:22:24.420
suddenly attack someone out of nowhere

01:22:24.420 --> 01:22:25.979
for no reason.

01:22:26.039 --> 01:22:29.220
Or my back, Starflight jumped in

01:22:29.220 --> 01:22:29.520
quickly.

01:22:29.640 --> 01:22:31.260
Tsunami frowned at him.

01:22:31.319 --> 01:22:33.659
Why was he trying so hard to take her

01:22:33.659 --> 01:22:33.899
place?

01:22:33.960 --> 01:22:36.119
You think you're strong enough?

01:22:36.180 --> 01:22:37.500
She challenged.

01:22:37.619 --> 01:22:40.079
Sure he is, Sonny said.

01:22:40.140 --> 01:22:42.060
I'll ride with him and you can leave

01:22:42.060 --> 01:22:42.539
Clay.

01:22:42.659 --> 01:22:45.899
Well, fine then, tsunami thought.

01:22:45.960 --> 01:22:48.180
I guess everyone's giving the orders

01:22:48.180 --> 01:22:48.479
now.

01:22:48.539 --> 01:22:51.779
Riptide came stomping back with several

01:22:51.779 --> 01:22:53.939
long strands of thick black seaweed.

01:22:54.000 --> 01:22:56.279
Sonny immediately looked like she was

01:22:56.279 --> 01:22:58.560
regretting her offer, but she let the big

01:22:58.560 --> 01:23:00.600
sea wing wrap the seaweed tightly around

01:23:00.600 --> 01:23:02.460
her head, covering her closed eyes.

01:23:02.520 --> 01:23:04.140
Ew.

01:23:04.199 --> 01:23:05.579
She said, shivering.

01:23:05.640 --> 01:23:07.560
It's all wet and slimy.

01:23:07.619 --> 01:23:12.600
I like wet and slimy, Clay said. ducking

01:23:12.600 --> 01:23:14.520
his head to make it easier for riptide to

01:23:14.520 --> 01:23:15.180
blindfold him.

01:23:15.239 --> 01:23:18.720
That's weird, Clay, said Glory.

01:23:18.840 --> 01:23:21.119
Riptide's attention was focused on

01:23:21.119 --> 01:23:23.699
plastering seaweed all over clay's broad

01:23:23.699 --> 01:23:23.939
head.

01:23:24.000 --> 01:23:26.760
When he was done, it looked more like an

01:23:26.760 --> 01:23:29.399
octopus trying to eat clay's brain than a

01:23:29.399 --> 01:23:29.939
blindfold.

01:23:30.060 --> 01:23:32.279
But of course, Clay didn't complain.

01:23:32.340 --> 01:23:35.220
He never complained about anything except

01:23:35.220 --> 01:23:35.760
being hungry.

01:23:35.819 --> 01:23:38.279
It was one of the things tsunami loved

01:23:38.279 --> 01:23:38.939
about him.

01:23:39.000 --> 01:23:42.239
Tsunami helped Sonny climb awkwardly onto

01:23:42.239 --> 01:23:44.640
Starflight's back, balancing in the

01:23:44.640 --> 01:23:46.380
narrow space between his wings.

01:23:46.619 --> 01:23:49.260
The sand wing was small, but Starflight

01:23:49.260 --> 01:23:51.359
wasn't as burly as tsunami or clay.

01:23:51.420 --> 01:23:54.539
If you can't handle it, tell me, and I'll

01:23:54.539 --> 01:23:56.279
take her, tsunami said to him.

01:23:56.399 --> 01:23:59.100
Starflight nodded, breathing deeply.

01:23:59.159 --> 01:24:02.399
His wings curled in, and he shivered as

01:24:02.399 --> 01:24:04.800
Sunny lay down, rested her head on his

01:24:04.800 --> 01:24:07.739
neck, and clasped her forearms trustingly

01:24:07.739 --> 01:24:08.460
around his shoulders.

01:24:08.520 --> 01:24:11.640
Tsunami turned to clay and brushed one of

01:24:11.640 --> 01:24:12.659
his wing tips with hers.

01:24:12.779 --> 01:24:14.159
Can you feel that?

01:24:14.220 --> 01:24:15.119
She asked.

01:24:15.180 --> 01:24:17.340
If I do that in the air?

01:24:17.399 --> 01:24:17.880
you stay with me?

01:24:17.939 --> 01:24:20.159
I think so.

01:24:20.220 --> 01:24:22.140
Clay said doubtfully.

01:24:22.199 --> 01:24:24.600
I'll fly on your other side.

01:24:24.659 --> 01:24:27.359
Glory said, hopping down from her rock.

01:24:27.420 --> 01:24:29.579
She reached up and nudged his other

01:24:29.579 --> 01:24:29.880
wing.

01:24:29.939 --> 01:24:32.760
That way, we can steer you together.

01:24:32.819 --> 01:24:36.000
Clay shook his head a little, and a loose

01:24:36.000 --> 01:24:38.520
flap of seaweed went glop flop against

01:24:38.520 --> 01:24:39.060
his neck.

01:24:39.119 --> 01:24:42.960
This is really strange, he said.

01:24:43.020 --> 01:24:45.779
It's as dark as the underground river.

01:24:45.840 --> 01:24:48.840
Only with breathing, so better.

01:24:48.899 --> 01:24:50.880
I'm in favor of breathing.

01:24:50.939 --> 01:24:53.760
Definitely better than not breathing.

01:24:53.819 --> 01:24:57.359
Just don't go too fast and listen to me

01:24:57.359 --> 01:24:58.739
tsunami ordered.

01:24:58.800 --> 01:25:03.119
To us, glory chimed in, and we promise

01:25:03.119 --> 01:25:03.899
not to drown you.

01:25:04.020 --> 01:25:06.479
She gave tsunami an arch look.

01:25:06.600 --> 01:25:09.779
If I do decide to drown somebody, I know

01:25:09.779 --> 01:25:12.119
who's at the top of my list, tsunami

01:25:12.119 --> 01:25:14.039
thought, shooting a glare back at her.

01:25:14.100 --> 01:25:17.159
All right, let's go, she said to

01:25:17.159 --> 01:25:17.760
Riptide.

01:25:17.819 --> 01:25:21.779
The sky blue sea wing waved his talent in

01:25:21.779 --> 01:25:23.579
front of Clay's face to make sure there

01:25:23.579 --> 01:25:24.180
was no reaction.

01:25:24.239 --> 01:25:27.899
Finally, he sprang into the sky with the

01:25:27.899 --> 01:25:29.279
dragonettes close behind him.

01:25:29.340 --> 01:25:32.699
Tsunami forgot to be mad at Glorian

01:25:32.699 --> 01:25:34.439
Starflight as they flew over the bay.

01:25:34.500 --> 01:25:37.199
Green and white islands glowed like

01:25:37.199 --> 01:25:39.060
scattered jewels in the ocean below

01:25:39.060 --> 01:25:39.239
them.

01:25:39.300 --> 01:25:42.060
Several of them were shaped like claws

01:25:42.060 --> 01:25:43.560
curving neatly through the water.

01:25:43.619 --> 01:25:46.800
From up by the clouds, she could see part

01:25:46.800 --> 01:25:48.180
of the spiral pattern in the

01:25:48.180 --> 01:25:49.500
archipelago.

01:25:49.560 --> 01:25:51.119
And when they swooped down close to the

01:25:51.119 --> 01:25:54.119
sea, she saw palescent pink dolphins

01:25:54.119 --> 01:25:55.260
leaping in the clear water.

01:25:55.319 --> 01:25:58.800
Glory told Clay about the dolphins, and

01:25:58.800 --> 01:25:59.939
his head went up hopefully.

01:26:00.000 --> 01:26:01.859
Can we eat them?

01:26:01.859 --> 01:26:02.939
he asked.

01:26:03.000 --> 01:26:06.000
No, Riptide called back over his

01:26:06.000 --> 01:26:06.359
shoulder.

01:26:06.420 --> 01:26:08.699
Queen Coral has forbidden it.

01:26:08.760 --> 01:26:10.199
She thinks they might be distantly

01:26:10.199 --> 01:26:10.859
related to us.

01:26:10.920 --> 01:26:14.220
Tsunami glanced down at the sleek darting

01:26:14.220 --> 01:26:16.800
shapes, related to dragons?

01:26:16.859 --> 01:26:18.420
What a bizarre idea.

01:26:18.479 --> 01:26:20.819
It didn't really fit with how she'd

01:26:20.819 --> 01:26:21.600
imagined her mother.

01:26:21.659 --> 01:26:26.399
Well, I can stop imagining soon, she

01:26:26.399 --> 01:26:26.699
thought.

01:26:26.760 --> 01:26:29.640
She had no idea how the sea wings had

01:26:29.640 --> 01:26:31.500
managed to hide a palace on one of these

01:26:31.500 --> 01:26:32.039
islands.

01:26:32.100 --> 01:26:34.439
From the air, it seemed like you could

01:26:34.439 --> 01:26:35.579
see everything.

01:26:35.640 --> 01:26:38.340
The white sand below the azure waters

01:26:38.340 --> 01:26:40.920
around the islands, every hole in the

01:26:40.920 --> 01:26:43.739
twisting rock formations, every palm tree

01:26:43.739 --> 01:26:46.260
and cormorant nest and scraggly bush on

01:26:46.260 --> 01:26:47.100
every cliff.

01:26:47.159 --> 01:26:49.920
There were a lot of small islands, but

01:26:49.920 --> 01:26:51.840
surely the enemy had searched everyone by

01:26:51.840 --> 01:26:54.300
now, after 18 years of war.

01:26:54.359 --> 01:26:57.359
Here comes our welcoming committee.

01:26:57.479 --> 01:27:00.420
Riptide said, just loud enough for

01:27:00.420 --> 01:27:01.380
tsunami to hear.

01:27:01.439 --> 01:27:04.020
She spotted a formation of blue and green

01:27:04.020 --> 01:27:06.960
dragons flying toward them. 15 or more

01:27:06.960 --> 01:27:10.260
with huge wings and bared teeth, she

01:27:10.260 --> 01:27:11.640
could hear them hissing from a distance.

01:27:11.760 --> 01:27:13.680
Uh-oh.

01:27:13.739 --> 01:27:15.180
Riptide muttered.

01:27:15.239 --> 01:27:17.880
Clay, stop and hover.

01:27:17.939 --> 01:27:19.199
Tsunami instructed.

01:27:19.260 --> 01:27:22.199
He paused in the air, with glory close

01:27:22.199 --> 01:27:22.800
beside him.

01:27:22.859 --> 01:27:24.600
What's happening?

01:27:24.659 --> 01:27:27.239
Sonny asked, lifting her head from

01:27:27.239 --> 01:27:29.340
Starflight's shoulder as they caught up.

01:27:29.399 --> 01:27:31.680
Starflight, for once, didn't say

01:27:31.680 --> 01:27:32.039
anything.

01:27:32.100 --> 01:27:34.920
His jaw was set, and it looked like he

01:27:34.920 --> 01:27:37.079
was using all his energy to stay aloft

01:27:37.079 --> 01:27:37.439
with Sonny.

01:27:37.500 --> 01:27:39.779
The advance guard.

01:27:39.840 --> 01:27:41.279
Riptide said.

01:27:41.340 --> 01:27:43.920
He swung in a slow circle around the

01:27:43.920 --> 01:27:46.199
group and stopped in front again, facing

01:27:46.199 --> 01:27:47.279
the incoming dragons.

01:27:47.399 --> 01:27:50.399
They make sure no one even gets close to

01:27:50.399 --> 01:27:51.300
the Summer Palace.

01:27:51.359 --> 01:27:54.060
A few moments later, they were

01:27:54.060 --> 01:27:54.600
surrounded.

01:27:54.659 --> 01:27:57.300
The flapping wing beats filled their ears

01:27:57.300 --> 01:27:59.039
and pushed the air currents around.

01:27:59.100 --> 01:28:03.720
Riptide, growled the dragon in the lead.

01:28:03.720 --> 01:28:06.300
His scales were green, so dull it was

01:28:06.300 --> 01:28:09.000
almost gray, like stone where moss had

01:28:09.000 --> 01:28:09.659
been scraped away.

01:28:09.720 --> 01:28:13.560
He had tiny bone pale eyes that never

01:28:13.560 --> 01:28:16.020
seemed to blink under a knobbly

01:28:16.020 --> 01:28:18.420
protruding forehead, and his horns

01:28:18.420 --> 01:28:20.039
twisted strangely toward each other.

01:28:20.100 --> 01:28:24.180
Tsunami noticed that, unlike riptide, the

01:28:24.180 --> 01:28:26.699
new dragon had no battle scars, which

01:28:26.699 --> 01:28:28.260
either meant he stayed away from the

01:28:28.260 --> 01:28:31.140
fighting, or he was a very skilled

01:28:31.140 --> 01:28:31.560
fighter.

01:28:31.619 --> 01:28:34.859
What are you dragging home now?

01:28:34.920 --> 01:28:36.239
He snarled.

01:28:36.300 --> 01:28:38.699
Riptide looked him straight in the eyes.

01:28:38.760 --> 01:28:40.859
I found the missing princess.

01:28:40.920 --> 01:28:44.340
That's not how I would have put it

01:28:44.340 --> 01:28:45.659
Tsunami thought.

01:28:45.720 --> 01:28:48.060
I was the one doing all the finding out

01:28:48.060 --> 01:28:48.359
there.

01:28:48.420 --> 01:28:51.359
A ripple of shock went through the other

01:28:51.359 --> 01:28:52.199
sea wings.

01:28:52.260 --> 01:28:55.199
Tsunami's scales felt like insects were

01:28:55.199 --> 01:28:57.659
crawling under them as the guards all

01:28:57.659 --> 01:28:58.199
stared at her.

01:28:58.260 --> 01:29:00.840
She lifted her snout and tried to look

01:29:00.840 --> 01:29:01.859
regal and imposing.

01:29:01.920 --> 01:29:04.260
Oh, really?

01:29:04.319 --> 01:29:05.819
said the leader.

01:29:05.880 --> 01:29:07.739
You, riptide?

01:29:07.739 --> 01:29:09.420
Of all dragons.

01:29:09.479 --> 01:29:11.699
What an unusual coincidence.

01:29:11.760 --> 01:29:15.659
His unsettling eyes scanned tsunami from

01:29:15.659 --> 01:29:18.359
wingtips to claws, as if she were a dead

01:29:18.359 --> 01:29:20.460
eel someone had left half eaten on the

01:29:20.460 --> 01:29:20.819
beach.

01:29:20.880 --> 01:29:23.939
Tsunami wanted to shred the skeptical

01:29:23.939 --> 01:29:25.680
arrogant look right off his face.

01:29:25.800 --> 01:29:28.140
And who are you?

01:29:28.140 --> 01:29:29.640
Tsunami demanded.

01:29:29.699 --> 01:29:31.500
Riptide winced.

01:29:31.560 --> 01:29:34.079
This is Shark, he said.

01:29:34.140 --> 01:29:36.840
Commander of Palace Defense and Brother

01:29:36.840 --> 01:29:37.500
to the Queen.

01:29:37.560 --> 01:29:40.020
Oh, really?

01:29:40.680 --> 01:29:42.899
tsunami said, deliberately making her

01:29:42.899 --> 01:29:45.060
tone even more insolent and challenging

01:29:45.060 --> 01:29:45.840
than sharks.

01:29:45.899 --> 01:29:48.239
She was not about to start her life with

01:29:48.239 --> 01:29:50.220
the sea wings by kowtowing to every

01:29:50.220 --> 01:29:53.039
soldier drag who came along, even if he

01:29:53.039 --> 01:29:53.640
was her uncle.

01:29:53.760 --> 01:29:57.239
Shark narrowed his eyes until they nearly

01:29:57.239 --> 01:29:59.100
disappeared into his scales.

01:29:59.159 --> 01:30:02.460
What makes you believe this snip of a

01:30:02.460 --> 01:30:04.859
dragon comes from the stolen royal egg?

01:30:04.979 --> 01:30:06.960
He asked riptide.

01:30:07.020 --> 01:30:08.340
Why?

01:30:08.399 --> 01:30:10.260
Do you lose a lot of eggs?

01:30:10.319 --> 01:30:11.699
Tsunami jumped in.

01:30:11.760 --> 01:30:14.039
Maybe whoever's in charge of defense

01:30:14.039 --> 01:30:15.479
isn't doing such a good job then.

01:30:15.539 --> 01:30:18.720
Oh, wait, that's you. isn't it?

01:30:18.779 --> 01:30:21.060
Her story makes sense.

01:30:21.119 --> 01:30:23.039
Riptide said desperately.

01:30:23.100 --> 01:30:26.340
She knew about, about webs.

01:30:26.399 --> 01:30:27.359
He raised her.

01:30:27.420 --> 01:30:29.640
And look at the glow patterns under her

01:30:29.640 --> 01:30:30.000
wings.

01:30:30.060 --> 01:30:33.180
All of the sea wings craned their necks

01:30:33.180 --> 01:30:34.920
to stare at tsunami's wings.

01:30:34.979 --> 01:30:37.560
She snapped at a couple who got too close

01:30:37.560 --> 01:30:39.479
then peered around to see what they were

01:30:39.479 --> 01:30:39.779
seeing.

01:30:39.840 --> 01:30:43.439
Under her wings, when she lit them up, the

01:30:43.439 --> 01:30:45.960
luminescent stripes formed spirals around

01:30:45.960 --> 01:30:49.319
the outer edges, starbursts, shaped like

01:30:49.319 --> 01:30:51.840
webbed dragon footprints, branched away

01:30:51.840 --> 01:30:52.979
from the lines in the middle.

01:30:53.039 --> 01:30:54.300
Was that weird?

01:30:54.359 --> 01:30:56.939
She glanced at the other sea wings.

01:30:57.000 --> 01:30:59.699
Most of them had smaller starbursts and

01:30:59.699 --> 01:31:00.659
no spirals.

01:31:00.720 --> 01:31:03.180
Only shark's patterns matched her own.

01:31:03.239 --> 01:31:06.060
Because we're both royal.

01:31:06.119 --> 01:31:09.180
She lifted her head and met his gaze

01:31:09.180 --> 01:31:10.020
triumphantly.

01:31:10.079 --> 01:31:14.220
But one day, I shall be queen, and you

01:31:14.220 --> 01:31:16.079
will always be nothing but a soldier.

01:31:16.140 --> 01:31:19.199
Shark let out a long hissing breath.

01:31:19.319 --> 01:31:22.319
Very well, he said.

01:31:22.380 --> 01:31:24.960
Kill the other 4 and bring her.

01:31:25.020 --> 01:31:29.520
Chapter 6.

01:31:29.579 --> 01:31:32.220
Don't you touch them!

01:31:32.279 --> 01:31:33.840
Tsunami yelled.

01:31:33.899 --> 01:31:36.239
She whirled and smacked a sea wing out of

01:31:36.239 --> 01:31:37.920
the sky as you reached for clay.

01:31:37.979 --> 01:31:40.079
Starflight had already ducked below

01:31:40.079 --> 01:31:41.340
Clay's massive wings.

01:31:41.399 --> 01:31:43.800
Glory drew her neck back and bared her

01:31:43.800 --> 01:31:44.279
fangs.

01:31:44.340 --> 01:31:47.399
I am the queen's daughter, and I order

01:31:47.399 --> 01:31:49.140
you to leave these dragonettes alone.

01:31:49.260 --> 01:31:50.880
Tsunami shouted.

01:31:51.000 --> 01:31:54.300
The guards looked from her to Shark

01:31:54.300 --> 01:31:54.720
uncertainly.

01:31:54.779 --> 01:31:58.140
His eyes were pale reflecting pools

01:31:58.140 --> 01:31:58.979
hiding his thoughts.

01:31:59.039 --> 01:32:02.520
He slowly raised one talon, and made a

01:32:02.520 --> 01:32:04.979
strange circling motion with it, a sign

01:32:04.979 --> 01:32:07.199
in the sea wing language tsunami guest.

01:32:07.260 --> 01:32:09.300
Whatever it was, it worked.

01:32:09.359 --> 01:32:11.880
To tsunami's relief, the guards backed

01:32:11.880 --> 01:32:12.060
away.

01:32:12.119 --> 01:32:15.300
But when she glanced at riptide, she

01:32:15.300 --> 01:32:17.340
noticed that he still looked tense and

01:32:17.340 --> 01:32:17.699
unhappy.

01:32:17.760 --> 01:32:21.300
Maybe he's just afraid of shark, she

01:32:21.300 --> 01:32:21.539
thought.

01:32:21.600 --> 01:32:26.100
Very good, she said. trying to sound like

01:32:26.100 --> 01:32:27.000
she was in command.

01:32:27.060 --> 01:32:28.979
Now take us to my mother.

01:32:29.100 --> 01:32:32.760
The queen is conducting business at the

01:32:32.760 --> 01:32:34.920
Deep Palace, Shark said flatly.

01:32:34.979 --> 01:32:37.619
We will take you to the Summer Palace

01:32:37.619 --> 01:32:38.939
where you may wait for her.

01:32:39.000 --> 01:32:42.600
He made another talent signal, and 2 of

01:32:42.600 --> 01:32:44.220
the guards broke away from the group

01:32:44.220 --> 01:32:47.699
winging off across the water, taking the

01:32:47.699 --> 01:32:50.640
message to my mother, tsunami thought, her

01:32:50.640 --> 01:32:52.260
wings expanding with joy.

01:32:52.319 --> 01:32:55.380
They were so close to everything she'd

01:32:55.380 --> 01:32:56.279
always imagined.

01:32:56.340 --> 01:32:58.800
I'm going to meet my parents today.

01:32:58.859 --> 01:33:02.460
Islands flashed by below them as they

01:33:02.460 --> 01:33:03.420
flew on.

01:33:03.479 --> 01:33:05.460
Now, with a tight guard of sea wings.

01:33:05.520 --> 01:33:07.920
Some of the islands were small patches of

01:33:07.920 --> 01:33:10.680
sand, barely big enough for one dragon to

01:33:10.680 --> 01:33:13.560
land on, and others were towering jagged

01:33:13.560 --> 01:33:15.180
rocks shooting out of the water.

01:33:15.239 --> 01:33:18.659
Ahead, tsunami saw one that looked like a

01:33:18.659 --> 01:33:21.539
huge dragon skeleton, with holes and gaps

01:33:21.539 --> 01:33:22.920
all through the pale stone.

01:33:23.039 --> 01:33:26.520
The stone skeleton's nose pointed toward

01:33:26.520 --> 01:33:27.000
another island.

01:33:27.060 --> 01:33:29.460
This one ringed with forbidding looking

01:33:29.460 --> 01:33:32.340
rocks, and presenting only a high, sheer

01:33:32.340 --> 01:33:34.260
cliff face on all sides.

01:33:34.319 --> 01:33:36.479
The top was a rioting jungle.

01:33:36.539 --> 01:33:39.659
Thick green vines and trees pressed so

01:33:39.659 --> 01:33:41.640
close together that there was not a

01:33:41.640 --> 01:33:43.380
single spot clear enough to land on.

01:33:43.439 --> 01:33:46.739
Tsunami was startled when sharks suddenly

01:33:46.739 --> 01:33:48.539
swerved and dove toward the base of the

01:33:48.539 --> 01:33:49.500
cliff.

01:33:49.560 --> 01:33:51.960
He splashed down between 2 spiraling

01:33:51.960 --> 01:33:54.840
rocks, sharp and evenly matched, like

01:33:54.840 --> 01:33:57.840
dragon horns, and vanished into the azure

01:33:57.840 --> 01:33:58.079
water.

01:33:58.140 --> 01:33:59.520
She blinked.

01:33:59.579 --> 01:34:01.020
Where had he gone?

01:34:01.079 --> 01:34:03.359
The water was so clear here that she

01:34:03.359 --> 01:34:05.699
could see fat black turtles strolling

01:34:05.699 --> 01:34:07.140
across the sand at the bottom of the

01:34:07.140 --> 01:34:07.380
sea.

01:34:07.439 --> 01:34:11.520
But then, one by one, half the guards

01:34:11.520 --> 01:34:13.920
around them dove for the same spot, and

01:34:13.920 --> 01:34:15.420
each of them disappeared the same way.

01:34:15.479 --> 01:34:18.600
Gone before the bubbles of their splash

01:34:18.600 --> 01:34:19.260
had cleared.

01:34:19.319 --> 01:34:23.100
Clay stop, she said, brushing his wing.

01:34:23.159 --> 01:34:24.600
Riptide?

01:34:24.659 --> 01:34:27.539
It's the entrance to the Summer Palace.

01:34:27.600 --> 01:34:28.800
Riptide said.

01:34:28.859 --> 01:34:30.300
There's no other way in.

01:34:30.359 --> 01:34:31.920
You'll all have to swim.

01:34:31.979 --> 01:34:35.460
Sunny let out a small and happy noise.

01:34:35.579 --> 01:34:36.960
How far?

01:34:36.960 --> 01:34:38.520
she asked riptide.

01:34:38.579 --> 01:34:41.039
You only have to stay underwater for

01:34:41.039 --> 01:34:43.020
short swims, he answered.

01:34:43.079 --> 01:34:45.899
It has been redesigned, so Queen Blister

01:34:45.899 --> 01:34:47.279
in particular can visit.

01:34:47.340 --> 01:34:49.380
And she hates water.

01:34:49.439 --> 01:34:52.439
Sonny said hopefully, since she's a

01:34:52.439 --> 01:34:53.100
sandwing too.

01:34:53.159 --> 01:34:55.920
Is she uh...

01:34:56.699 --> 01:34:57.779
Is she here now?

01:34:57.840 --> 01:34:59.460
Starflight asked.

01:34:59.520 --> 01:35:01.020
Riptide shook his head.

01:35:01.079 --> 01:35:04.140
She is not fond of swimming, and even

01:35:04.140 --> 01:35:05.579
after all the changes we've made.

01:35:05.640 --> 01:35:06.720
She rarely visits.

01:35:06.779 --> 01:35:10.199
Tsunami was secretly a bit relieved to

01:35:10.199 --> 01:35:10.500
hear that.

01:35:10.560 --> 01:35:12.479
After meeting Bern.

01:35:12.539 --> 01:35:14.220
She wasn't looking forward to

01:35:14.220 --> 01:35:16.680
encountering the other 2 rival sandwing

01:35:16.680 --> 01:35:17.819
sisters.

01:35:17.880 --> 01:35:19.500
What if they were all equally dangerous

01:35:19.500 --> 01:35:21.659
and crazy and controlling?

01:35:21.720 --> 01:35:24.180
But eventually, the dragonettes would

01:35:24.180 --> 01:35:25.979
have to choose one of the 3 to win the

01:35:25.979 --> 01:35:26.220
war.

01:35:26.279 --> 01:35:29.460
To be fair, Tsunami thought they probably

01:35:29.460 --> 01:35:31.979
needed to meet both Blister and Blaze.

01:35:32.039 --> 01:35:35.159
Then again, if tsunami's mother liked

01:35:35.159 --> 01:35:38.039
blister, enough to alter her palace to

01:35:38.039 --> 01:35:38.760
accommodate her.

01:35:38.819 --> 01:35:41.579
Surely that was a sign in blister's favor

01:35:41.579 --> 01:35:41.939
wasn't it?

01:35:42.000 --> 01:35:44.579
Maybe they didn't have to meet Blaze.

01:35:44.640 --> 01:35:46.800
Maybe supporting the sea wings and

01:35:46.800 --> 01:35:48.840
blister would be the obvious right thing

01:35:48.840 --> 01:35:49.199
to do.

01:35:49.260 --> 01:35:51.840
Stay close behind me.

01:35:51.899 --> 01:35:53.460
Riptide said.

01:35:53.520 --> 01:35:56.039
I'll light up my stripes so you can

01:35:56.039 --> 01:35:58.319
follow, and I'll flash them to signal you

01:35:58.319 --> 01:35:59.760
to surface at the breathing spots.

01:35:59.760 --> 01:36:02.819
Um, Clay said.

01:36:02.880 --> 01:36:06.300
So about this blindfold.

01:36:06.359 --> 01:36:10.260
Uh, any chance, once we're in the tunnel

01:36:10.260 --> 01:36:11.699
riptide answered.

01:36:11.760 --> 01:36:14.279
He turned and dove for the dragon horn

01:36:14.279 --> 01:36:15.420
rocks.

01:36:15.479 --> 01:36:17.340
Tsunami flipped her tail into Clay's

01:36:17.340 --> 01:36:19.979
front talons and dove after riptide

01:36:19.979 --> 01:36:21.300
towing clay behind her.

01:36:21.359 --> 01:36:24.060
Her scales tingled with excitement.

01:36:24.119 --> 01:36:26.340
Deep breath clay.

01:36:26.399 --> 01:36:27.239
She called.

01:36:27.300 --> 01:36:29.819
She was not far behind a riptide when he

01:36:29.819 --> 01:36:32.520
dove into the water, but even so, she

01:36:32.520 --> 01:36:34.739
nearly lost him in the fizz of bubbles

01:36:34.739 --> 01:36:36.479
that swarmed up in her face as she

01:36:36.479 --> 01:36:37.199
splashed down.

01:36:37.260 --> 01:36:40.920
She blinked frantically, searching for a

01:36:40.920 --> 01:36:42.479
hole or a tunnel entrance.

01:36:42.539 --> 01:36:45.960
Long, sun colored tendrils of kelp grew

01:36:45.960 --> 01:36:48.300
up from the sandy floor, glowing in

01:36:48.300 --> 01:36:50.399
orange gold, and the light filtering down

01:36:50.399 --> 01:36:50.819
from above.

01:36:50.880 --> 01:36:53.279
They were clustered around the base of

01:36:53.279 --> 01:36:55.680
the cliff, waving like a forest of

01:36:55.680 --> 01:36:58.199
octopus arms, as tall as the 5

01:36:58.199 --> 01:36:59.939
dragonettes laid end to end.

01:37:00.000 --> 01:37:02.699
The hole in the cliff must be hidden by

01:37:02.699 --> 01:37:04.380
the tendrils, but where?

01:37:04.439 --> 01:37:08.340
Then tsunami saw riptide's glowing tail

01:37:08.340 --> 01:37:10.680
knocking the golden kelp curtain aside

01:37:10.680 --> 01:37:12.060
and she plunged after him.

01:37:12.119 --> 01:37:14.880
It was hard to swim as fast as she wanted

01:37:14.880 --> 01:37:16.920
to with clay clinging to her tail.

01:37:16.979 --> 01:37:18.960
She could feel him trying to beat his

01:37:18.960 --> 01:37:21.420
wings and kick helpfully, but he kept

01:37:21.420 --> 01:37:23.460
accidentally whacking into underwater

01:37:23.460 --> 01:37:25.020
boulders and slowing her down.

01:37:25.079 --> 01:37:28.140
She poked her head into the forest, and

01:37:28.140 --> 01:37:30.359
felt the tendrils of kelp slide and

01:37:30.359 --> 01:37:32.220
slither around her snout.

01:37:32.279 --> 01:37:34.800
Up close, she could see little clear

01:37:34.800 --> 01:37:36.359
globules growing on them.

01:37:36.420 --> 01:37:39.899
These were surprisingly sticky, while the

01:37:39.899 --> 01:37:41.579
rest of the tendril was slippery smooth.

01:37:41.640 --> 01:37:45.359
It felt like gigantic golden inch worms

01:37:45.359 --> 01:37:46.380
were swarming around her.

01:37:46.439 --> 01:37:49.800
She had to swim through a thick patch

01:37:49.800 --> 01:37:52.500
following the glimmer of riptide's lit up

01:37:52.500 --> 01:37:54.600
tail before reaching the cliff wall.

01:37:54.659 --> 01:37:58.319
Suddenly, the tendrils slithered away and

01:37:58.319 --> 01:38:00.239
popped her out into a dark underwater

01:38:00.239 --> 01:38:00.720
tunnel.

01:38:00.779 --> 01:38:03.060
Not entirely dark.

01:38:03.119 --> 01:38:05.520
Riptide was directly in front of her.

01:38:05.579 --> 01:38:08.279
His luminescent stripes all glowing.

01:38:08.340 --> 01:38:11.460
He reached around her, guided clay into

01:38:11.460 --> 01:38:13.800
the tunnel, and unwrapped the seaweed

01:38:13.800 --> 01:38:14.579
blindfold.

01:38:14.640 --> 01:38:17.100
Clay blinked and rubbed his talons

01:38:17.100 --> 01:38:19.260
against his eyes, then immediately turned

01:38:19.260 --> 01:38:21.359
back toward the faint sunlight, searching

01:38:21.359 --> 01:38:22.140
for the others.

01:38:22.199 --> 01:38:23.819
Glory came through next.

01:38:23.880 --> 01:38:26.039
Her snout wrinkling as she pushed

01:38:26.039 --> 01:38:27.180
tendrils off her wings.

01:38:27.239 --> 01:38:30.300
Tsunami noticed that her scales had

01:38:30.300 --> 01:38:32.039
ripples of the orange gold color

01:38:32.039 --> 01:38:34.199
crisscrossing the silver that had been

01:38:34.199 --> 01:38:34.560
there before.

01:38:34.619 --> 01:38:36.960
She wondered if Glory had done that

01:38:36.960 --> 01:38:38.880
deliberately, or if her scales

01:38:38.880 --> 01:38:40.619
automatically tried to match their

01:38:40.619 --> 01:38:42.000
environment when she was stressed.

01:38:42.119 --> 01:38:45.899
After a long pause, Starflight burst

01:38:45.899 --> 01:38:46.380
through after her.

01:38:46.439 --> 01:38:49.140
His face was puffed up like he was about

01:38:49.140 --> 01:38:52.560
to explode, and on his back, Sonny was

01:38:52.560 --> 01:38:53.399
shivering violently.

01:38:53.520 --> 01:38:56.819
Riptide flashed the lights in his tail

01:38:56.819 --> 01:38:59.640
and shot upward, aiming for a hole in the

01:38:59.640 --> 01:39:01.739
tunnel roof not far inside the entrance.

01:39:01.800 --> 01:39:05.159
Tsunami was expecting more of a swim, and

01:39:05.159 --> 01:39:06.600
was surprised when her head almost

01:39:06.600 --> 01:39:08.399
immediately popped out into air.

01:39:08.460 --> 01:39:12.960
It wasn't much air, a tiny cavern, barely

01:39:12.960 --> 01:39:15.359
lit by a faraway gleam of sunlight up a

01:39:15.359 --> 01:39:16.560
long, narrow chimney.

01:39:16.619 --> 01:39:19.319
The dragon's bodies were still in the

01:39:19.319 --> 01:39:20.279
watery tunnel below.

01:39:20.340 --> 01:39:22.619
There was only enough room in the cavern

01:39:22.619 --> 01:39:25.199
for their heads, all gathered closely in

01:39:25.199 --> 01:39:25.500
the pool.

01:39:25.619 --> 01:39:28.260
Tsunami could see right away that there

01:39:28.260 --> 01:39:29.279
was nowhere to climb out.

01:39:29.399 --> 01:39:31.800
This was a place to stop and breathe

01:39:31.800 --> 01:39:32.579
nothing more.

01:39:32.640 --> 01:39:36.779
Sunny and Starflight both gasped for air

01:39:36.779 --> 01:39:39.659
like they hadn't breathed in months, Clay

01:39:39.659 --> 01:39:41.640
fumbled in the dark to Pat Sunny's head

01:39:41.640 --> 01:39:43.500
and pulled her blindfold off as well.

01:39:43.560 --> 01:39:47.220
Good thing this breathing hole is here

01:39:47.220 --> 01:39:49.380
Clay remarked to Riptide.

01:39:49.439 --> 01:39:51.659
So close to the entrance, I mean.

01:39:51.720 --> 01:39:54.600
Riptide inclined his head in a sort of

01:39:54.600 --> 01:39:54.960
nod.

01:39:55.020 --> 01:39:57.239
Queen Blister insisted on it.

01:39:57.300 --> 01:40:00.720
Tsunami felt the whoosh of several sea

01:40:00.720 --> 01:40:02.640
wing guards swimming past below them.

01:40:02.760 --> 01:40:04.920
She knew there would be a few of them

01:40:04.920 --> 01:40:07.439
bringing up the rear, making sure none of

01:40:07.439 --> 01:40:09.359
the dragonettes ran off to spread the

01:40:09.359 --> 01:40:11.100
news of the summer palace's secret

01:40:11.100 --> 01:40:11.579
location.

01:40:11.640 --> 01:40:14.399
She couldn't keep her wings still.

01:40:14.460 --> 01:40:17.819
They thrummed like trapped dragonflies

01:40:17.819 --> 01:40:19.199
wanting to spring loose.

01:40:19.260 --> 01:40:21.239
She was so close.

01:40:21.300 --> 01:40:23.220
This was her palace.

01:40:23.279 --> 01:40:26.100
Her dragons were only a few wing beats

01:40:26.100 --> 01:40:26.399
away.

01:40:26.460 --> 01:40:29.579
After 6 years of imagining what this

01:40:29.579 --> 01:40:31.680
would be like, she didn't think she could

01:40:31.680 --> 01:40:33.239
stand another minute of waiting.

01:40:33.300 --> 01:40:37.920
Let's go, let's go. she said, splashing

01:40:37.920 --> 01:40:39.359
the others enthusiastically with her

01:40:39.359 --> 01:40:39.600
tail.

01:40:39.720 --> 01:40:43.380
Good grief, Glory said with a shake.

01:40:43.439 --> 01:40:45.840
It's like you've been possessed by Sonny

01:40:45.840 --> 01:40:46.319
or something.

01:40:46.380 --> 01:40:47.880
Come on.

01:40:47.939 --> 01:40:48.779
We're almost there.

01:40:48.840 --> 01:40:52.260
Tsunami flashed her stripes happily, and

01:40:52.260 --> 01:40:53.699
the other dragonettes covered their

01:40:53.699 --> 01:40:53.880
eyes.

01:40:53.939 --> 01:40:57.479
I can swim from here, Sonny said to

01:40:57.479 --> 01:41:00.239
Starflight, or I'll hold onto clay if you

01:41:00.239 --> 01:41:00.899
all go too fast.

01:41:00.960 --> 01:41:04.199
Starflight looked disappointed and

01:41:04.199 --> 01:41:05.460
relieved at the same time.

01:41:05.579 --> 01:41:09.000
Riptide sank below the surface, and

01:41:09.000 --> 01:41:11.819
tsunami ducked after him. too excited to

01:41:11.819 --> 01:41:12.359
wait for the others.

01:41:12.420 --> 01:41:15.779
Now it was easy to follow riptide's

01:41:15.779 --> 01:41:16.439
glowing scales.

01:41:16.500 --> 01:41:19.319
The tunnel twisted up and down and around

01:41:19.319 --> 01:41:22.260
corners with frequent stops like the 1st

01:41:22.260 --> 01:41:22.920
for breathing.

01:41:23.039 --> 01:41:25.619
Too frequent if you asked tsunami.

01:41:25.680 --> 01:41:27.899
Each one made her want to bang her head

01:41:27.899 --> 01:41:28.979
into the cliff walls.

01:41:29.039 --> 01:41:32.159
She lost count after the 4th stop, but

01:41:32.159 --> 01:41:33.239
there had to be at least 10.

01:41:34.199 --> 01:41:35.399
How long was this tunnel?

01:41:35.460 --> 01:41:39.600
Then suddenly, finally, there was light

01:41:39.600 --> 01:41:40.140
ahead.

01:41:40.199 --> 01:41:42.420
Real light, not glowing scales.

01:41:42.479 --> 01:41:45.359
A moment later, they swam out of the

01:41:45.359 --> 01:41:47.760
tunnel into an open lake, lifted their

01:41:47.760 --> 01:41:50.159
heads above the water and breathed in

01:41:50.159 --> 01:41:50.520
deeply.

01:41:50.579 --> 01:41:54.180
Green tinted sunlight dazzled their eyes

01:41:54.180 --> 01:41:54.659
at first.

01:41:54.720 --> 01:41:57.899
But as her vision cleared, tsunami saw

01:41:57.899 --> 01:41:58.560
dragons.

01:41:58.619 --> 01:42:01.979
Over 100 blue and green dragons

01:42:01.979 --> 01:42:02.819
surrounded them.

01:42:02.880 --> 01:42:06.420
All of them, staring expectantly at

01:42:06.420 --> 01:42:07.199
tsunami.

01:42:07.260 --> 01:42:11.520
Her tribe, her dragons, her future

01:42:11.520 --> 01:42:12.479
subjects.

01:42:12.539 --> 01:42:14.939
They had reached the Summer Palace of the

01:42:14.939 --> 01:42:17.699
Sea Wings, in the heart of the Kingdom of

01:42:17.699 --> 01:42:18.060
the Sea.

01:42:18.180 --> 01:42:24.359
Part 2 Into the deep.

01:42:24.479 --> 01:42:27.000
Chapter 7.

01:42:27.060 --> 01:42:31.439
Overwhelmed, tsunami spread her wings to

01:42:31.439 --> 01:42:33.720
float on the water and gazed around.

01:42:33.779 --> 01:42:37.859
They were inside the island, surrounded

01:42:37.859 --> 01:42:39.779
by towering cliffs on all sides.

01:42:39.840 --> 01:42:41.579
Far above them.

01:42:41.640 --> 01:42:43.619
Sunlight filtered through a thick green

01:42:43.619 --> 01:42:44.279
canopy.

01:42:44.340 --> 01:42:47.220
The vines and treetops she'd seen from

01:42:47.220 --> 01:42:49.319
the sky, woven so thickly.

01:42:49.380 --> 01:42:51.239
It looked like a jungle from above.

01:42:51.300 --> 01:42:54.600
Like an emerald umbrella over the island

01:42:54.600 --> 01:42:56.880
the canopy protected the summer palace

01:42:56.880 --> 01:42:59.460
from view, and gave the light a sea green

01:42:59.460 --> 01:43:01.680
quality that made tsunami feel like she

01:43:01.680 --> 01:43:02.699
was still underwater.

01:43:02.760 --> 01:43:05.880
Waterfalls cascaded down from several

01:43:05.880 --> 01:43:08.579
holes in the cliffs like slender dragon

01:43:08.579 --> 01:43:11.100
tails of silver, bursting into spray as

01:43:11.100 --> 01:43:11.640
they hit the lake.

01:43:11.699 --> 01:43:15.300
The only exit tsunami could see was the

01:43:15.300 --> 01:43:16.020
tunnel behind her.

01:43:16.079 --> 01:43:19.560
Four pillars of blue tinted white stone

01:43:19.560 --> 01:43:22.619
spiraled out of the water, winding toward

01:43:22.619 --> 01:43:25.020
one another until they formed a towering

01:43:25.020 --> 01:43:26.579
pavilion in the middle of the lake.

01:43:26.640 --> 01:43:30.720
The pavilion had 12 circular levels, each

01:43:30.720 --> 01:43:32.100
one smaller than the one below.

01:43:32.159 --> 01:43:35.340
There were a few walls, most of them very

01:43:35.340 --> 01:43:37.979
low, and the whole structure was latticed

01:43:37.979 --> 01:43:40.560
with curving shapes and holes and little

01:43:40.560 --> 01:43:41.340
wading pools.

01:43:41.399 --> 01:43:43.560
It didn't look like it had been built.

01:43:43.619 --> 01:43:45.840
It looked as if it had grown that way

01:43:45.840 --> 01:43:48.600
although tsunami was pretty sure that was

01:43:48.600 --> 01:43:48.960
impossible.

01:43:49.020 --> 01:43:52.380
Dragons were clustered along the edges of

01:43:52.380 --> 01:43:55.500
the pavilion, on ledges of the cliffs, and

01:43:55.500 --> 01:43:56.520
all across the water.

01:43:56.579 --> 01:44:00.119
She'd never seen so many faces like her

01:44:00.119 --> 01:44:03.479
own, dark blues and pale greens, and

01:44:03.479 --> 01:44:05.520
sharp seeing the dark eyes staring.

01:44:05.640 --> 01:44:09.000
The only sound was the splashing of the

01:44:09.000 --> 01:44:11.939
waterfalls, the soft hush of dragons

01:44:11.939 --> 01:44:14.880
breathing, and the quiet lapping of waves

01:44:14.880 --> 01:44:16.140
on the beaches around the lake.

01:44:16.199 --> 01:44:19.979
After a moment, Starflight spotted the

01:44:19.979 --> 01:44:22.439
nearest stretch of sand, and set off for

01:44:22.439 --> 01:44:24.600
it in a frantic paddle that sounded

01:44:24.600 --> 01:44:26.939
horribly loud in the silence.

01:44:27.000 --> 01:44:29.220
Sunny and clay and glory followed him.

01:44:29.279 --> 01:44:33.300
Tsunami stayed where she was, ignoring

01:44:33.300 --> 01:44:34.859
the tiredness that was flooding her

01:44:34.859 --> 01:44:35.159
scales.

01:44:35.279 --> 01:44:37.500
She wanted to make a good impression on

01:44:37.500 --> 01:44:38.760
the dragons of her kingdom.

01:44:38.819 --> 01:44:40.979
Many of them were floating on the water

01:44:40.979 --> 01:44:43.680
like she was, but many more were perched

01:44:43.680 --> 01:44:46.439
in cave openings all along the cliff, or

01:44:46.439 --> 01:44:48.180
on rocks that jutted out of the water

01:44:48.180 --> 01:44:50.880
while others lined the shallow beaches.

01:44:50.939 --> 01:44:53.340
Tsunami wondered what they'd all been

01:44:53.340 --> 01:44:55.020
doing before she appeared to capture

01:44:55.020 --> 01:44:55.500
their attention.

01:44:55.619 --> 01:44:59.220
She spotted shark, hunched on one of the

01:44:59.220 --> 01:45:00.720
spirals of the closest pillar.

01:45:00.840 --> 01:45:03.180
She rather thought he should have given

01:45:03.180 --> 01:45:05.699
some sort of welcome speech, but he only

01:45:05.699 --> 01:45:07.920
stared at her with his pale, unblinking

01:45:07.920 --> 01:45:09.180
little eyes.

01:45:09.239 --> 01:45:12.779
In the story, the royal parents had swept

01:45:12.779 --> 01:45:14.880
forward with a parade and a whole

01:45:14.880 --> 01:45:16.979
orchestra to welcome back their missing

01:45:16.979 --> 01:45:19.380
princess, but her parents weren't here

01:45:19.380 --> 01:45:19.619
yet.

01:45:19.680 --> 01:45:21.720
And now that she thought about it

01:45:21.720 --> 01:45:24.539
dolphins playing harps would probably be

01:45:24.539 --> 01:45:25.319
a bit silly looking.

01:45:25.380 --> 01:45:29.340
Well, she was a future queen, and she

01:45:29.340 --> 01:45:31.319
wasn't going to be intimidated by crowds

01:45:31.319 --> 01:45:32.520
of staring dragons.

01:45:32.579 --> 01:45:34.979
She shook her head and lifted her neck

01:45:34.979 --> 01:45:35.880
out of the water.

01:45:35.880 --> 01:45:38.939
Hello, fellow sea wings?

01:45:39.000 --> 01:45:41.760
She called, and then paused as her voice

01:45:41.760 --> 01:45:44.340
echoed off the rocks, much louder than

01:45:44.340 --> 01:45:45.000
she'd expected.

01:45:45.060 --> 01:45:47.159
I'm tsunami.

01:45:47.220 --> 01:45:51.960
And, um, I'm very happy to be home at

01:45:51.960 --> 01:45:55.260
last, and, and I look forward to meeting

01:45:55.260 --> 01:45:55.739
each of you.

01:45:55.800 --> 01:45:59.100
Three moons.

01:45:59.159 --> 01:46:01.140
Was that the most awful speech in the

01:46:01.140 --> 01:46:02.159
history of Pyria?

01:46:02.220 --> 01:46:05.100
What were all these still silent faces

01:46:05.100 --> 01:46:05.699
thinking?

01:46:05.760 --> 01:46:08.520
Could the dragon see tsunami's natural

01:46:08.520 --> 01:46:09.119
royalty?

01:46:09.180 --> 01:46:11.699
Were they excited that she'd be their

01:46:11.699 --> 01:46:12.300
queen one day?

01:46:12.359 --> 01:46:15.539
She remembered her royal stripe patterns

01:46:15.539 --> 01:46:17.819
and lifted her wings out of the water so

01:46:17.819 --> 01:46:18.779
everyone could see them.

01:46:18.840 --> 01:46:20.579
To be sure they were visible.

01:46:20.640 --> 01:46:21.539
She lit them up.

01:46:21.600 --> 01:46:24.300
And then, with a sinking feeling

01:46:24.300 --> 01:46:26.399
remembered what she'd accidentally said

01:46:26.399 --> 01:46:27.180
to Riptide.

01:46:27.239 --> 01:46:30.659
She really, really hoped she hadn't just

01:46:30.659 --> 01:46:32.760
told her entire kingdom, that they had

01:46:32.760 --> 01:46:34.319
delicious fish breath or something.

01:46:34.380 --> 01:46:37.800
A murmur ran around the gathered dragons

01:46:37.800 --> 01:46:39.659
but she couldn't tell if it was good

01:46:39.659 --> 01:46:41.880
murmuring or bad murmuring.

01:46:41.939 --> 01:46:44.760
She turned to riptide, who was watching

01:46:44.760 --> 01:46:46.380
Shark with a grim expression.

01:46:46.439 --> 01:46:49.380
I think you should take me somewhere I

01:46:49.380 --> 01:46:49.979
can wait for my mother.

01:46:50.100 --> 01:46:54.239
Tsunami suggested in a low voice, or she

01:46:54.239 --> 01:46:56.819
thought it was low, but the echoes still

01:46:56.819 --> 01:46:59.399
skipped back to her across the water, and

01:46:59.399 --> 01:47:00.840
now there was more murmuring.

01:47:00.899 --> 01:47:04.079
Tsunami wished she had nightwing powers

01:47:04.140 --> 01:47:06.060
so she could hear the dragon's thought.

01:47:06.119 --> 01:47:10.500
Up there, said Riptide, nodding to the

01:47:10.500 --> 01:47:12.060
top of the pavilion.

01:47:12.119 --> 01:47:13.199
He glanced at Shark again.

01:47:13.260 --> 01:47:15.180
You should bring your friends.

01:47:15.239 --> 01:47:18.180
The other dragonettes were sprawled on

01:47:18.180 --> 01:47:20.279
the white pebbles of the beach in front

01:47:20.279 --> 01:47:22.619
of a tall cave opening lined with sand.

01:47:22.739 --> 01:47:25.500
They had their wings spread out, and were

01:47:25.500 --> 01:47:27.600
gasping in a rather undignified way.

01:47:27.720 --> 01:47:30.420
All except for Glory, who was sitting

01:47:30.420 --> 01:47:32.220
neatly by the cave, peering in.

01:47:32.279 --> 01:47:35.159
Her silver scales were now modeled with

01:47:35.159 --> 01:47:35.819
azure blue.

01:47:35.880 --> 01:47:38.520
Any sea wings who weren't staring at

01:47:38.520 --> 01:47:40.140
tsunami were staring at her.

01:47:40.260 --> 01:47:43.140
Tsunami thwacked the water with her tail

01:47:43.140 --> 01:47:43.859
to get their attention.

01:47:43.979 --> 01:47:46.920
When Clay finally looked over, she

01:47:46.920 --> 01:47:47.880
pointed to the pavilion.

01:47:48.000 --> 01:47:50.579
He nodded, and she lifted into the air.

01:47:50.640 --> 01:47:54.300
Her wings felt heavy out of the water, and

01:47:54.300 --> 01:47:55.560
it took a few beats to get her balance.

01:47:55.619 --> 01:47:58.260
She wished the sea wings would go back to

01:47:58.260 --> 01:47:59.699
whatever they were supposed to be doing.

01:47:59.760 --> 01:48:02.220
Riptide flew up beside her.

01:48:02.279 --> 01:48:04.439
He looked uncomfortable with all the

01:48:04.439 --> 01:48:05.340
scrutiny as well.

01:48:05.399 --> 01:48:09.239
Tell me about the Summer Palace, Tsunami

01:48:09.239 --> 01:48:11.279
said, trying to distract herself.

01:48:11.340 --> 01:48:13.739
He flicked his tail at the cliffs.

01:48:13.859 --> 01:48:16.199
Guest rooms are in the caves.

01:48:16.260 --> 01:48:19.140
Queen Blister usually stays in the one

01:48:19.140 --> 01:48:20.220
closest to the tunnel.

01:48:20.279 --> 01:48:23.039
We brought in extra sand to line the

01:48:23.039 --> 01:48:25.140
floor for her, and it's the only cave

01:48:25.140 --> 01:48:26.100
where fire is allowed.

01:48:26.159 --> 01:48:29.279
His snout turned toward the pavilion as

01:48:29.279 --> 01:48:29.819
they flew higher.

01:48:29.880 --> 01:48:32.880
She meets with Queen Coral on the 2nd

01:48:32.880 --> 01:48:34.920
level from the top, which is only for

01:48:34.920 --> 01:48:35.819
visiting royalty.

01:48:35.880 --> 01:48:38.100
Each level has a different purpose.

01:48:38.220 --> 01:48:41.039
For instance, there's a floor for dragon

01:48:41.039 --> 01:48:43.260
at school visits, one for celebration

01:48:43.260 --> 01:48:45.600
spectacles, and one for war planning.

01:48:45.659 --> 01:48:48.119
When they are here instead of the deep

01:48:48.119 --> 01:48:50.279
palace, the council meets on this level

01:48:50.279 --> 01:48:51.239
halfway up.

01:48:51.300 --> 01:48:55.319
He paused, beating his wings, so tsunami

01:48:55.319 --> 01:48:57.960
could look across the middle level. 12

01:48:57.960 --> 01:49:00.300
dragon sized pools were arranged in a

01:49:00.300 --> 01:49:02.699
circle, with small channels running from

01:49:02.699 --> 01:49:04.800
one to the next and crisscrossing the

01:49:04.800 --> 01:49:07.500
center, glittering emeralds the size of

01:49:07.500 --> 01:49:09.359
fish eggs, which were embedded in the

01:49:09.359 --> 01:49:11.640
stone, spelled out words by each pool.

01:49:11.699 --> 01:49:15.659
Tsunami saw one marked Treasury, one

01:49:15.659 --> 01:49:18.420
labeled Defense, and another that said

01:49:18.420 --> 01:49:20.340
Secrets and Spies.

01:49:20.399 --> 01:49:23.579
Before she could read any further, Riptide

01:49:23.579 --> 01:49:24.600
turned to fly higher.

01:49:24.659 --> 01:49:28.500
Counsel, tsunami said, catching up to

01:49:28.500 --> 01:49:28.739
him.

01:49:28.800 --> 01:49:32.220
They prefer the Deep Palace, as does the

01:49:32.220 --> 01:49:34.020
Queen, Riptide said.

01:49:34.079 --> 01:49:36.060
Only Shark and Lagoon are here at the

01:49:36.060 --> 01:49:36.239
moment.

01:49:36.300 --> 01:49:39.239
Tsunami had no idea what he was talking

01:49:39.239 --> 01:49:41.520
about, but she didn't want to reveal how

01:49:41.520 --> 01:49:43.800
ignorant she was of sea wing politics.

01:49:43.859 --> 01:49:46.020
She wondered if there was anything about

01:49:46.020 --> 01:49:48.000
a council in Starflight's favorite

01:49:48.000 --> 01:49:48.659
scrolls.

01:49:48.720 --> 01:49:51.840
So, which level is for missing

01:49:51.840 --> 01:49:52.500
princesses?

01:49:52.560 --> 01:49:53.579
She joked.

01:49:53.640 --> 01:49:56.340
I think the top pavilion would be best.

01:49:56.460 --> 01:49:57.960
Riptide said.

01:49:58.020 --> 01:50:00.539
That's for new visitors, and we hardly

01:50:00.539 --> 01:50:01.439
ever have any of those.

01:50:01.500 --> 01:50:04.859
Queen Blister was probably the last.

01:50:04.920 --> 01:50:06.779
Oh no, it was that night wing.

01:50:06.840 --> 01:50:09.840
He landed gracefully on the uppermost

01:50:09.840 --> 01:50:12.779
ledge of the pavilion, his claws catching

01:50:12.779 --> 01:50:14.640
on polished ridges in the bluish white

01:50:14.640 --> 01:50:15.060
stone.

01:50:15.119 --> 01:50:17.399
What night wing?

01:50:17.520 --> 01:50:19.979
Tsunami asked, landing beside him.

01:50:20.039 --> 01:50:21.960
This level was bigger than she'd

01:50:21.960 --> 01:50:22.319
expected.

01:50:22.380 --> 01:50:25.920
A spiraling starburst of webbed talon

01:50:25.920 --> 01:50:27.960
print shapes was carved into the floor

01:50:27.960 --> 01:50:31.020
and filled with glittering water, lined

01:50:31.020 --> 01:50:33.119
all along the bottom with tiny pearls.

01:50:33.180 --> 01:50:36.000
Tsunami realized the pattern was the same

01:50:36.000 --> 01:50:37.020
as the one on her wings.

01:50:37.140 --> 01:50:38.939
I don't know.

01:50:39.000 --> 01:50:40.560
Riptide answered her.

01:50:40.619 --> 01:50:43.319
He only spoke with her majesty and queen

01:50:43.319 --> 01:50:45.420
blister, and all I heard was that he

01:50:45.420 --> 01:50:46.859
wanted to fly out through the canopy

01:50:46.859 --> 01:50:48.899
instead of the tunnel, but of course they

01:50:48.899 --> 01:50:49.619
wouldn't let him do that.

01:50:49.680 --> 01:50:52.439
He looked big and bad tempered.

01:50:52.500 --> 01:50:56.699
Sounds like Maro Seer, tsunami muttered

01:50:56.699 --> 01:50:58.619
although she didn't exactly have a lot of

01:50:58.619 --> 01:51:01.380
other night wings to compare him to, but

01:51:01.380 --> 01:51:03.000
he seemed more meddlesome than the rest

01:51:03.000 --> 01:51:03.300
of them.

01:51:03.359 --> 01:51:05.819
While most of the tribe hid in their

01:51:05.819 --> 01:51:08.640
secret location, being all mysterious and

01:51:08.640 --> 01:51:11.699
unhelpfully powerful, Maro Seer kept

01:51:11.699 --> 01:51:14.100
turning up, delivering the dragonette

01:51:14.100 --> 01:51:16.619
prophecy, inspecting the dragonettes

01:51:16.619 --> 01:51:19.199
trying to get glory killed, saving

01:51:19.199 --> 01:51:22.079
Starflight, but no one else, from the sky

01:51:22.079 --> 01:51:24.720
wings, then giving him back once everyone

01:51:24.720 --> 01:51:25.560
had escaped.

01:51:25.619 --> 01:51:28.439
Tsunami could easily imagine him poking

01:51:28.439 --> 01:51:28.800
around here.

01:51:28.859 --> 01:51:30.720
Although she couldn't guess why.

01:51:30.779 --> 01:51:34.199
Riptie glanced down at the dragons below

01:51:34.199 --> 01:51:37.020
including shark, who hadn't moved from

01:51:37.020 --> 01:51:37.979
his spot on the pillar.

01:51:38.039 --> 01:51:41.100
I can't believe you spoke to shark like

01:51:41.100 --> 01:51:42.600
that, he whispered.

01:51:42.659 --> 01:51:45.600
I've never seen anyone talk back to him

01:51:45.600 --> 01:51:48.300
apart from the queen and queen blister.

01:51:48.359 --> 01:51:52.500
He deserved it, tsunami said, settling

01:51:52.500 --> 01:51:52.979
her wings.

01:51:53.039 --> 01:51:54.899
Arrogant blowfish head.

01:51:54.960 --> 01:51:57.539
When I'm queen, I'll make him go sit in a

01:51:57.539 --> 01:51:58.859
lagoon and grow seaweed.

01:51:58.979 --> 01:52:01.859
Riptide coughed hard to cover a laugh.

01:52:01.920 --> 01:52:05.159
Don't talk like that, he whispered.

01:52:05.220 --> 01:52:06.840
Don't you know the difference between

01:52:06.840 --> 01:52:08.100
brave and reckless?

01:52:08.159 --> 01:52:10.739
Shark will eat you and your friends for

01:52:10.739 --> 01:52:12.300
lunch if he thinks you're a threat to

01:52:12.300 --> 01:52:12.479
him.

01:52:12.539 --> 01:52:15.300
Tsunami said.

01:52:15.359 --> 01:52:16.199
He can try.

01:52:16.260 --> 01:52:19.020
She shoved away the creepy memory of

01:52:19.020 --> 01:52:21.060
sharks, unblinking, malicious eyes.

01:52:21.119 --> 01:52:26.039
By the moons, you make me nervous, Riptide

01:52:26.039 --> 01:52:26.340
said.

01:52:26.399 --> 01:52:29.399
One end of the top floor was raised and

01:52:29.399 --> 01:52:31.859
carved into a magnificent dragon throne

01:52:31.859 --> 01:52:34.920
studded with emeralds and sapphires, and

01:52:34.920 --> 01:52:36.899
shot through with gold lines in the shape

01:52:36.899 --> 01:52:37.380
of waves.

01:52:37.500 --> 01:52:40.380
Beside and below the throne was another

01:52:40.380 --> 01:52:43.260
smaller throne carved to match with the

01:52:43.260 --> 01:52:45.600
same patterns made of tinier gemstones.

01:52:45.600 --> 01:52:47.939
Tsunami tilted her head at the 2nd

01:52:47.939 --> 01:52:48.300
throne.

01:52:48.359 --> 01:52:50.819
It looked too small to be for a king.

01:52:50.880 --> 01:52:53.819
So was this for her?

01:52:53.880 --> 01:52:56.819
Had Queen Coral prepared a throne for her

01:52:56.819 --> 01:52:59.039
missing daughter, waiting all these years

01:52:59.039 --> 01:53:00.300
for her to come fill it?

01:53:00.359 --> 01:53:03.180
She took a step toward it, her heart

01:53:03.180 --> 01:53:04.439
pounding with excitement.

01:53:04.500 --> 01:53:07.380
A throne of her own, already.

01:53:07.439 --> 01:53:11.100
The arrival of her friend stopped her as

01:53:11.100 --> 01:53:13.319
the 4 dragonettes crashed down around the

01:53:13.319 --> 01:53:13.739
ledge.

01:53:13.800 --> 01:53:16.500
Sunny landed lightly, avoiding the

01:53:16.500 --> 01:53:18.840
channels of water, but clay somehow

01:53:18.840 --> 01:53:21.060
stumbled as his claws hit the stone, and

01:53:21.060 --> 01:53:22.859
nearly somersaulted right off the other

01:53:22.859 --> 01:53:23.100
side.

01:53:23.159 --> 01:53:25.859
Glory darted in his way and pushed him

01:53:25.859 --> 01:53:28.380
back, then made another loop around and

01:53:28.380 --> 01:53:29.460
landed close to the throne.

01:53:29.520 --> 01:53:32.460
Her green eyes studied it closely.

01:53:32.520 --> 01:53:34.920
She looked almost ready to climb onto it

01:53:34.920 --> 01:53:35.520
herself.

01:53:35.579 --> 01:53:39.119
Starflight arrived last, catching on to

01:53:39.119 --> 01:53:41.279
the side and pitching forward, as if his

01:53:41.279 --> 01:53:43.020
wings had barely been strong enough to

01:53:43.020 --> 01:53:43.739
carry him.

01:53:43.800 --> 01:53:46.920
He lay there like a woeful black puddle

01:53:46.920 --> 01:53:49.140
for a moment, taking deep breaths.

01:53:49.199 --> 01:53:52.020
Sonny hopped over a watery footprint to

01:53:52.020 --> 01:53:53.039
nudge his wing gently.

01:53:53.100 --> 01:53:56.760
Tsunami managed not to roll her eyes, but

01:53:56.760 --> 01:53:59.699
really, couldn't everyone at least try to

01:53:59.699 --> 01:54:01.079
act a little more impressive?

01:54:01.140 --> 01:54:05.039
This is a really big thing.

01:54:05.100 --> 01:54:07.739
Clay said to her in riptide.

01:54:07.800 --> 01:54:10.859
His tail accidentally splashed glory, but

01:54:10.859 --> 01:54:12.600
she was too busy looking at the throne to

01:54:12.600 --> 01:54:13.260
snap at him.

01:54:13.319 --> 01:54:16.619
I mean, this thing we're standing on?

01:54:16.739 --> 01:54:18.119
What do you call it?

01:54:18.239 --> 01:54:19.619
It's really tall.

01:54:19.680 --> 01:54:22.199
Taller than our prisons in the Sky

01:54:22.199 --> 01:54:22.800
Kingdom, I think.

01:54:22.859 --> 01:54:26.279
He peered over the edge, missing

01:54:26.279 --> 01:54:27.479
riptide's sharp look.

01:54:27.539 --> 01:54:30.479
Tsunami realized they hadn't told him

01:54:30.479 --> 01:54:32.520
about being captured by Queen Scarlet and

01:54:32.520 --> 01:54:33.659
the Sky Wings.

01:54:33.720 --> 01:54:37.920
I like it, Clay went on, sitting down and

01:54:37.920 --> 01:54:38.939
splashing glory again.

01:54:39.000 --> 01:54:42.600
Of course, it's much nicer to be this

01:54:42.600 --> 01:54:44.039
high when your wings are free.

01:54:44.100 --> 01:54:47.279
But at least the Skywings gave us a pig

01:54:47.279 --> 01:54:48.000
sometimes.

01:54:48.119 --> 01:54:49.800
Do you have pigs?

01:54:49.859 --> 01:54:52.920
Octopi would be all right instead, if you

01:54:52.920 --> 01:54:56.579
don't, or squid, or manatees.

01:54:56.699 --> 01:54:58.979
I could go for a manatee right now.

01:54:59.100 --> 01:55:02.640
Or a whale, I'm not fussy is what I'm

01:55:02.640 --> 01:55:02.819
saying.

01:55:02.880 --> 01:55:05.640
Say, how did you make this big thing?

01:55:05.699 --> 01:55:08.520
Did it take forever to build?

01:55:08.579 --> 01:55:11.819
Riptie blinked for a moment, following

01:55:11.819 --> 01:55:13.079
Clay's train of thought?

01:55:13.140 --> 01:55:14.939
The pavilion?

01:55:15.000 --> 01:55:18.180
An animus seawing designed it many

01:55:18.180 --> 01:55:20.699
generations ago, and magicked the stone

01:55:20.699 --> 01:55:23.159
to grow this way, Riptide said.

01:55:23.159 --> 01:55:26.460
Even so, it took nearly 10 years to reach

01:55:26.460 --> 01:55:27.239
this form.

01:55:27.300 --> 01:55:32.220
Wow, said Clay, and tsunami couldn't help

01:55:32.220 --> 01:55:33.060
being impressed too.

01:55:33.119 --> 01:55:36.180
She hadn't realized animus dragons had

01:55:36.180 --> 01:55:36.840
that kind of power.

01:55:36.899 --> 01:55:39.899
In their lessons, Webbs had told them

01:55:39.899 --> 01:55:42.420
animus dragons could enchant chess pieces

01:55:42.420 --> 01:55:43.140
to play themselves.

01:55:43.199 --> 01:55:45.779
Sometimes they left curses on their

01:55:45.779 --> 01:55:47.699
jewels to poison anyone who tried to

01:55:47.699 --> 01:55:48.180
steal them.

01:55:48.239 --> 01:55:51.060
But making a whole pavilion grow from

01:55:51.060 --> 01:55:51.479
stone?

01:55:51.539 --> 01:55:54.840
That seemed like strong magic, more

01:55:54.840 --> 01:55:56.699
powerful than anything the night wings

01:55:56.699 --> 01:55:57.060
could do.

01:55:57.119 --> 01:56:00.180
Starflight was clearly thinking the same

01:56:00.180 --> 01:56:02.640
thing, judging from his disgruntled

01:56:02.640 --> 01:56:03.119
snout.

01:56:03.239 --> 01:56:05.819
Tsunami hurriedly interrupted before he

01:56:05.819 --> 01:56:06.539
could begin a lecture.

01:56:06.600 --> 01:56:10.079
This top level is where Queen Coral meets

01:56:10.079 --> 01:56:11.220
new visitors, like us.

01:56:11.279 --> 01:56:13.739
She said importantly to her friends.

01:56:13.800 --> 01:56:17.340
So when she arrives, everyone, please act

01:56:17.340 --> 01:56:19.380
like dragonettes of destiny instead of

01:56:19.380 --> 01:56:21.600
half drowned seagulls for goodness sake.

01:56:21.659 --> 01:56:25.500
Sonny looked wounded and Starflight

01:56:25.500 --> 01:56:26.340
sniffed loudly.

01:56:26.399 --> 01:56:28.979
While Glory turned up her snout like she

01:56:28.979 --> 01:56:30.899
wasn't taking any orders from tsunami.

01:56:30.960 --> 01:56:33.840
Clay poked his nose over the edge and

01:56:33.840 --> 01:56:35.640
blinked at the lower pavilion tears.

01:56:35.699 --> 01:56:39.180
Which level is the feasting on?

01:56:39.239 --> 01:56:40.500
He asked.

01:56:40.560 --> 01:56:42.960
You do have feasting, right?

01:56:43.020 --> 01:56:46.319
His wide brown eyes turned to ribtide.

01:56:46.380 --> 01:56:48.060
No reason.

01:56:48.119 --> 01:56:49.260
Just wondering.

01:56:49.319 --> 01:56:51.119
Sure.

01:56:51.180 --> 01:56:54.180
Sometimes we have feasts, Riptide said

01:56:54.180 --> 01:56:57.420
especially when Queen Blister is, a

01:56:57.420 --> 01:56:59.579
commotion from below interrupted him.

01:56:59.640 --> 01:57:01.859
Tsunami sprang to the edge and gazed down

01:57:01.859 --> 01:57:02.399
the lake.

01:57:02.460 --> 01:57:06.060
A huge blue sea wing, exactly the color

01:57:06.060 --> 01:57:08.579
of tsunami's scales burst out of the

01:57:08.579 --> 01:57:08.880
tunnel.

01:57:08.939 --> 01:57:12.000
Vines of pearls were woven around her

01:57:12.000 --> 01:57:15.119
horns and neck and wings, and a twisted

01:57:15.119 --> 01:57:16.800
white horn with a wicked looking point

01:57:16.800 --> 01:57:19.079
was attached to the end of her tail.

01:57:19.140 --> 01:57:23.399
She had odd black stains on her claws, but

01:57:23.399 --> 01:57:25.680
she was the most beautiful sight tsunami

01:57:25.680 --> 01:57:26.520
had ever seen.

01:57:26.579 --> 01:57:28.560
All over the palace.

01:57:28.619 --> 01:57:30.960
Dragons were folding down into low

01:57:30.960 --> 01:57:31.500
boughs.

01:57:31.560 --> 01:57:35.100
This had to be her mother, queen of the

01:57:35.100 --> 01:57:35.760
sea wings.

01:57:35.819 --> 01:57:39.119
Tsunami reached to grab Riptide's forearm

01:57:39.119 --> 01:57:40.500
feeling dizzy with joy.

01:57:40.560 --> 01:57:43.859
But as Queen Coral shot out of the water

01:57:43.859 --> 01:57:46.739
tsunami saw that she wore a thin webbed

01:57:46.739 --> 01:57:50.520
harness with a long cord, which led to a

01:57:50.520 --> 01:57:53.340
harness on another dragon flying close

01:57:53.340 --> 01:57:53.760
behind her.

01:57:53.819 --> 01:57:57.300
The 2nd dragon was much smaller, a

01:57:57.300 --> 01:57:59.039
dragonette, only about a year old

01:57:59.039 --> 01:57:59.520
perhaps.

01:57:59.579 --> 01:58:02.460
She flapped her wings frantically, trying

01:58:02.460 --> 01:58:03.060
to keep up.

01:58:03.119 --> 01:58:06.600
With a jolt of shock, tsunami spotted the

01:58:06.600 --> 01:58:08.760
royal pattern of stripes on the underside

01:58:08.760 --> 01:58:09.180
of her wings.

01:58:09.300 --> 01:58:10.920
Who is that?

01:58:10.979 --> 01:58:12.840
She hissed at Riptide.

01:58:12.960 --> 01:58:14.819
He was backing away into the edge of the

01:58:14.819 --> 01:58:17.039
floor, the farthest spot from the

01:58:17.039 --> 01:58:17.340
throne.

01:58:17.460 --> 01:58:21.359
That's anemone. he said, blinking in

01:58:21.359 --> 01:58:21.899
surprise.

01:58:21.960 --> 01:58:23.220
Your sister.

01:58:23.279 --> 01:58:27.539
Chapter 8.

01:58:27.659 --> 01:58:31.319
An enemy, anemone.

01:58:31.380 --> 01:58:32.699
An enemy.

01:58:32.760 --> 01:58:35.880
It took tsunami a few moments to realize

01:58:35.880 --> 01:58:37.859
what riptide had actually said.

01:58:37.859 --> 01:58:42.239
Her skin prickled, hearing an enemy, an

01:58:42.239 --> 01:58:45.060
enemy, until it sank in that he'd been

01:58:45.060 --> 01:58:45.960
saying a name.

01:58:46.020 --> 01:58:50.939
Anemone, tsunami's sister, another heir

01:58:50.939 --> 01:58:51.479
to the throne.

01:58:51.600 --> 01:58:54.539
So much for being special.

01:58:54.539 --> 01:58:56.939
So much for her guaranteed future

01:58:56.939 --> 01:58:57.539
kingdom.

01:58:57.600 --> 01:59:02.640
Uh-oh, Glory said, echoing her thoughts

01:59:02.699 --> 01:59:04.979
looks like you've got some competition.

01:59:05.039 --> 01:59:07.380
Maybe you're not destined to be queen

01:59:07.380 --> 01:59:07.739
after all.

01:59:07.859 --> 01:59:11.460
Tsunami whirled towards Starflight, her

01:59:11.460 --> 01:59:12.359
gills flaring.

01:59:12.479 --> 01:59:15.659
You said I was the only one, she cried.

01:59:15.720 --> 01:59:17.939
You said none of the others survived.

01:59:18.000 --> 01:59:21.600
That's what I read, he protested.

01:59:21.659 --> 01:59:23.520
He spread his black claws.

01:59:23.579 --> 01:59:25.979
Blame the talons, not me.

01:59:26.039 --> 01:59:28.500
Our scrolls were often old and outdated.

01:59:28.560 --> 01:59:31.140
The royal lineage of the sea wings from

01:59:31.140 --> 01:59:33.060
the scorching to the present must have

01:59:33.060 --> 01:59:34.199
been written before this one was

01:59:34.199 --> 01:59:34.619
hatched.

01:59:34.739 --> 01:59:37.739
He nodded at the little dragon flapping

01:59:37.739 --> 01:59:38.279
behind the queen.

01:59:38.340 --> 01:59:42.600
Anemone was a pale, pale blue, almost

01:59:42.600 --> 01:59:45.420
white, like an ice wing, with hints of

01:59:45.420 --> 01:59:47.880
pink along her wings and ears and horns.

01:59:47.880 --> 01:59:50.460
She looked a little bit like the dolphins

01:59:50.460 --> 01:59:53.100
they'd seen earlier, and tsunami wondered

01:59:53.100 --> 01:59:54.960
grumpily if that was really why Queen

01:59:54.960 --> 01:59:57.180
Coral had forbidden sea wings to eat them

01:59:57.180 --> 01:59:59.579
in case one of them ate anemone by

01:59:59.579 --> 02:00:00.060
mistake.

02:00:00.119 --> 02:00:04.020
Anemone's eyes were large and blue, and

02:00:04.020 --> 02:00:05.939
tiny strands of pearls were woven around

02:00:05.939 --> 02:00:08.100
her neck and tail, as if to match her

02:00:08.100 --> 02:00:08.460
mother's.

02:00:08.520 --> 02:00:10.859
That could have been me.

02:00:10.920 --> 02:00:12.420
Tsunami thought.

02:00:12.479 --> 02:00:14.939
I could have been the one with matching

02:00:14.939 --> 02:00:17.640
pearls and a matching throne, and a

02:00:17.640 --> 02:00:18.359
mother who loved me.

02:00:18.420 --> 02:00:20.939
If the talons hadn't stolen me from my

02:00:20.939 --> 02:00:21.180
home.

02:00:21.239 --> 02:00:24.119
She didn't have a chance to notice

02:00:24.119 --> 02:00:26.640
anything else, because suddenly, Queen

02:00:26.640 --> 02:00:28.439
Coral was landing and running toward

02:00:28.439 --> 02:00:28.619
her.

02:00:28.680 --> 02:00:31.079
My baby?

02:00:31.199 --> 02:00:32.880
Kroll cried.

02:00:32.939 --> 02:00:35.399
Enormous blue wings whooshed around

02:00:35.399 --> 02:00:38.039
tsunami, enveloping her in a hug that

02:00:38.039 --> 02:00:40.020
smelled of sea air and starfish.

02:00:40.079 --> 02:00:43.439
Pearls pressed into tsunami's face as

02:00:43.439 --> 02:00:44.699
Coral cuddled her close.

02:00:44.760 --> 02:00:48.180
Her wet scales were warm, and her talons

02:00:48.180 --> 02:00:50.579
were gentle as she stroked tsunami's head

02:00:50.579 --> 02:00:51.479
and back and wings.

02:00:51.539 --> 02:00:55.439
I knew you'd come back to me, she said.

02:00:55.500 --> 02:00:58.560
I knew you were out there, trying to find

02:00:58.560 --> 02:00:59.159
your way back.

02:00:59.220 --> 02:01:01.859
I never stopped searching for you.

02:01:01.920 --> 02:01:06.539
It was exactly. what tsunami had always

02:01:06.539 --> 02:01:07.199
wanted to hear.

02:01:07.319 --> 02:01:11.880
Actually, it was word for word what the

02:01:11.880 --> 02:01:14.819
queen said in The Missing Princess, but

02:01:14.819 --> 02:01:16.739
tsunami shoved that thought aside.

02:01:16.859 --> 02:01:19.439
She leaned into her mother, feeling

02:01:19.439 --> 02:01:22.140
elation flood her from horns to claws.

02:01:22.199 --> 02:01:24.659
Someone does want me.

02:01:24.720 --> 02:01:26.399
I have a place in the world.

02:01:26.460 --> 02:01:31.140
Mother, whined a tiny voice from behind

02:01:31.140 --> 02:01:31.439
them.

02:01:31.500 --> 02:01:34.140
Ow, that was too fast.

02:01:34.199 --> 02:01:36.060
I think I hurt my claws.

02:01:36.119 --> 02:01:39.359
Queen Coral let go of tsunami, whirled

02:01:39.359 --> 02:01:41.520
around and tugged anemone closer with the

02:01:41.520 --> 02:01:44.159
harness cord, the little dragonette crept

02:01:44.159 --> 02:01:45.960
under her wing, and held out her front

02:01:45.960 --> 02:01:47.760
talons with a pitiful expression.

02:01:47.819 --> 02:01:50.159
I'm sorry, sweetheart.

02:01:50.220 --> 02:01:53.520
Carl said, carefully examining anemones

02:01:53.520 --> 02:01:55.439
claws, and then giving them a quick lick

02:01:55.439 --> 02:01:56.460
with her forked tongue.

02:01:56.579 --> 02:01:57.720
Is that better?

02:01:57.779 --> 02:02:02.640
I guess, Anemone said, flexing her talons

02:02:02.640 --> 02:02:03.359
mournfully.

02:02:03.420 --> 02:02:07.199
Look, darling, it's your sister, the one

02:02:07.199 --> 02:02:09.420
I told you about, who was stolen 6 years

02:02:09.420 --> 02:02:09.720
ago.

02:02:09.779 --> 02:02:13.260
Coral reached out and slid one webbed

02:02:13.260 --> 02:02:15.060
talent over tsunami's snout.

02:02:15.119 --> 02:02:17.159
Isn't she gorgeous?

02:02:17.279 --> 02:02:20.460
Anemone blinked at tsunami.

02:02:20.520 --> 02:02:23.520
She was really tiny, no taller than a

02:02:23.520 --> 02:02:25.439
scavenger, and she didn't look very

02:02:25.439 --> 02:02:25.979
strong.

02:02:26.039 --> 02:02:28.680
Maybe I don't have to worry about her.

02:02:28.739 --> 02:02:31.500
Tsunami thought, she'd be easy to

02:02:31.500 --> 02:02:31.920
defeat.

02:02:31.979 --> 02:02:34.560
And obviously, I'd make a better queen.

02:02:34.619 --> 02:02:37.619
Then she felt a stab of guilt for

02:02:37.619 --> 02:02:39.899
thinking about something like that on her

02:02:39.899 --> 02:02:41.460
1st meeting with her real family.

02:02:41.520 --> 02:02:44.340
She held out one of her front talons to

02:02:44.340 --> 02:02:45.000
anemone.

02:02:45.060 --> 02:02:48.180
And after a small pause, Anemone pressed

02:02:48.180 --> 02:02:49.260
her own talent against it.

02:02:49.319 --> 02:02:52.319
Hi, tsunami said.

02:02:52.380 --> 02:02:53.760
I'm tsunami.

02:02:53.819 --> 02:02:58.079
Ah, Queen Coral said, a good name.

02:02:58.140 --> 02:02:59.880
Webbs did one thing right.

02:03:00.000 --> 02:03:02.159
Her green eyes narrowed.

02:03:02.279 --> 02:03:03.539
Where is he now?

02:03:03.600 --> 02:03:06.000
I have been planning his punishment for

02:03:06.000 --> 02:03:06.359
years.

02:03:06.420 --> 02:03:09.960
She glared over tsunami's shoulder, but

02:03:09.960 --> 02:03:11.880
when tsunami looked around, the only

02:03:11.880 --> 02:03:13.319
dragon there was riptide.

02:03:13.439 --> 02:03:15.659
He had his head ducked in his wings

02:03:15.659 --> 02:03:17.220
folded as low as he could get.

02:03:17.279 --> 02:03:20.579
I knew he was a coward and a deserter

02:03:20.579 --> 02:03:23.520
Coral said, but after he returned to

02:03:23.520 --> 02:03:27.720
steal my egg, Well, let's just say, it

02:03:27.720 --> 02:03:28.859
won't be a quick death.

02:03:28.920 --> 02:03:32.579
Oh no, Sonny squeaked.

02:03:32.640 --> 02:03:33.840
Please don't hurt him.

02:03:33.899 --> 02:03:35.819
He was the only one who was really nice

02:03:35.819 --> 02:03:36.239
to us.

02:03:36.300 --> 02:03:40.859
We don't know where he is anyway, tsunami

02:03:40.859 --> 02:03:43.260
said, as Queen Carl turned to stare at

02:03:43.260 --> 02:03:43.680
Sonny.

02:03:43.739 --> 02:03:45.479
He escaped when...

02:03:45.479 --> 02:03:47.880
What are you?

02:03:47.880 --> 02:03:50.100
Coral asked Sonny.

02:03:50.159 --> 02:03:52.739
Her gaze fell on the other dragonettes

02:03:52.739 --> 02:03:54.659
and her tail lashed dangerously.

02:03:54.720 --> 02:03:58.199
Why is there a mud wing in my summer

02:03:58.199 --> 02:03:58.739
palace?

02:03:58.800 --> 02:04:01.260
She took a step toward clay.

02:04:01.319 --> 02:04:02.760
Gills flaring.

02:04:02.819 --> 02:04:04.979
These are my friends.

02:04:05.039 --> 02:04:08.340
Tsunami cried, leaping in front of Clay.

02:04:08.399 --> 02:04:10.859
You can trust them, I promise.

02:04:10.920 --> 02:04:13.199
We were all stolen from our homes as

02:04:13.199 --> 02:04:13.800
eggs.

02:04:13.859 --> 02:04:16.439
We're the dragonettes of destiny, from

02:04:16.439 --> 02:04:17.279
the prophecy.

02:04:17.399 --> 02:04:20.880
Ha. muttered a voice.

02:04:20.939 --> 02:04:24.000
And tsunami realized that Shark was now

02:04:24.000 --> 02:04:25.920
perched on the rim of the ledge along

02:04:25.920 --> 02:04:28.859
with 9 other very large dragons.

02:04:28.920 --> 02:04:30.180
Oh.

02:04:30.300 --> 02:04:32.760
Queen Coral said slowly.

02:04:32.819 --> 02:04:35.460
Oh, I see.

02:04:35.520 --> 02:04:39.119
She studied clay suspiciously, then

02:04:39.119 --> 02:04:42.000
turned her gaze to Starflight, Sunny, and

02:04:42.000 --> 02:04:42.420
glory.

02:04:42.479 --> 02:04:46.260
Yes, that was the rumor.

02:04:46.319 --> 02:04:48.960
If you believe in things like prophecies

02:04:48.960 --> 02:04:49.319
of course.

02:04:49.380 --> 02:04:51.720
Dragonettes of destiny.

02:04:51.960 --> 02:04:54.600
Well, Queen Blister will be so interested

02:04:54.600 --> 02:04:57.300
to meet you, we'd better make sure you

02:04:57.300 --> 02:04:58.020
don't go anywhere.

02:04:58.079 --> 02:05:01.439
She flashed the royal patterns along her

02:05:01.439 --> 02:05:03.659
wings and clapped her front talons

02:05:03.659 --> 02:05:03.899
together.

02:05:03.960 --> 02:05:07.079
Seven burly sea wings rose up behind the

02:05:07.079 --> 02:05:09.779
dragonettes, claws twitching ominously.

02:05:09.840 --> 02:05:13.140
Put these 4 in Blisters Cave.

02:05:13.199 --> 02:05:16.260
Queen Coral commanded. and set a guard so

02:05:16.260 --> 02:05:16.800
they stay there.

02:05:16.859 --> 02:05:18.300
What?

02:05:18.359 --> 02:05:19.619
Sonny cried.

02:05:19.739 --> 02:05:21.479
But we came here to be safe?

02:05:21.539 --> 02:05:23.159
Not to be prisoners again.

02:05:23.220 --> 02:05:26.520
She squeaked in terror as one guard

02:05:26.520 --> 02:05:27.479
snatched her into the air.

02:05:27.539 --> 02:05:30.840
Starflight stared after her, frozen in

02:05:30.840 --> 02:05:32.760
place with his claws half outstretched.

02:05:32.819 --> 02:05:35.159
Nobody touches me.

02:05:35.220 --> 02:05:38.279
Glory snarled at the sea wing who was

02:05:38.279 --> 02:05:38.819
reaching for her.

02:05:38.880 --> 02:05:41.819
Black clouds billowed up in her scales.

02:05:41.880 --> 02:05:44.100
Don't hurt son.

02:05:44.159 --> 02:05:44.819
How?

02:05:44.880 --> 02:05:48.359
Clay yelped, as 3 sea wings landed on him

02:05:48.359 --> 02:05:49.800
at once, pinning him down.

02:05:49.859 --> 02:05:51.899
Ouch, ow.

02:05:51.960 --> 02:05:55.319
One began lashing woven seaweed ropes

02:05:55.319 --> 02:05:57.539
around his wings and claws and snout.

02:05:57.600 --> 02:05:59.939
Wait, tsunami said.

02:06:00.000 --> 02:06:02.399
She clasped her talons pleadingly.

02:06:02.460 --> 02:06:04.140
Your majesty.

02:06:04.260 --> 02:06:05.640
Mother.

02:06:05.760 --> 02:06:09.239
The word felt so odd on her tongue, even

02:06:09.239 --> 02:06:11.520
though she'd imagined saying it a 1000000

02:06:11.520 --> 02:06:12.539
times.

02:06:12.600 --> 02:06:13.560
You don't have to do this.

02:06:13.619 --> 02:06:15.960
They're my friends, and I brought them

02:06:15.960 --> 02:06:17.220
here so you could protect us.

02:06:17.279 --> 02:06:19.319
I swear, they're trustworthy.

02:06:19.439 --> 02:06:22.979
It's for their own safety too, dear.

02:06:23.100 --> 02:06:26.100
Coral said, stroking tsunami's head

02:06:26.100 --> 02:06:26.399
again.

02:06:26.460 --> 02:06:28.260
We won't hurt them, of course.

02:06:28.319 --> 02:06:30.600
You've come to the right place for

02:06:30.600 --> 02:06:31.319
protection.

02:06:31.380 --> 02:06:33.659
But they shouldn't wander the palace

02:06:33.659 --> 02:06:34.619
unsupervised.

02:06:34.680 --> 02:06:37.439
Most of my dragons will attack mud wings

02:06:37.439 --> 02:06:39.720
and unfamiliar sand wings on site.

02:06:39.779 --> 02:06:42.300
Or whatever that is.

02:06:42.420 --> 02:06:45.539
Shark muttered, sniffing at Sonny.

02:06:45.600 --> 02:06:48.420
Starflight shot him a glare, then looked

02:06:48.420 --> 02:06:50.699
away quickly as the Seawing turned his

02:06:50.699 --> 02:06:51.239
gaze to him.

02:06:51.300 --> 02:06:57.060
I guess this means no feast, Clay said

02:06:57.060 --> 02:06:57.659
mournfully.

02:06:57.720 --> 02:07:00.000
He rested his snout on the stone with a

02:07:00.000 --> 02:07:00.359
sigh.

02:07:00.420 --> 02:07:04.199
Food can certainly be arranged, said the

02:07:04.199 --> 02:07:04.500
Queen.

02:07:04.560 --> 02:07:06.960
Lagoon, make sure our guests are well

02:07:06.960 --> 02:07:07.260
fed.

02:07:07.380 --> 02:07:10.979
A plump turquoise dragon bowed and dove

02:07:10.979 --> 02:07:11.640
off the ledge.

02:07:11.699 --> 02:07:13.020
See, darling?

02:07:13.079 --> 02:07:14.520
We'll take good care of you all.

02:07:14.579 --> 02:07:16.859
Please tell that one to stop looking so

02:07:16.859 --> 02:07:17.460
fierce.

02:07:17.520 --> 02:07:21.000
Carl flicked a claw at glory, who was

02:07:21.000 --> 02:07:22.500
still facing all with a nervous looking

02:07:22.500 --> 02:07:23.520
sea wing guard.

02:07:23.579 --> 02:07:26.939
Tsunami thought, uncomfortably, of

02:07:26.939 --> 02:07:28.319
Glory's secret weapon.

02:07:28.319 --> 02:07:31.380
In the Sky Wing Palace, they'd discovered

02:07:31.380 --> 02:07:33.960
Glory could spit a deadly venom, which

02:07:33.960 --> 02:07:36.060
seemed to be a rain wing skill most

02:07:36.060 --> 02:07:37.439
dragons didn't know about.

02:07:37.500 --> 02:07:39.479
It certainly hadn't been in any of the

02:07:39.479 --> 02:07:41.760
scrolls, which rarely mentioned rain

02:07:41.760 --> 02:07:42.420
wings at all.

02:07:42.479 --> 02:07:45.300
But tsunami hoped glory would decide to

02:07:45.300 --> 02:07:46.859
keep her venom a secret for now.

02:07:46.920 --> 02:07:49.260
Melting one of the queen's guards

02:07:49.260 --> 02:07:51.840
probably wasn't the best way to introduce

02:07:51.840 --> 02:07:53.699
the dragonettes of destiny to the sea

02:07:53.699 --> 02:07:54.119
wings.

02:07:54.180 --> 02:07:57.600
You don't have to tie them up, tsunami

02:07:57.600 --> 02:07:57.960
said.

02:07:58.020 --> 02:07:59.100
They'll go with you.

02:07:59.159 --> 02:08:02.760
Speak for yourself, Glory growled.

02:08:02.819 --> 02:08:06.119
Calm down, Glory, tsunami said.

02:08:06.180 --> 02:08:08.220
She hoped her mother and the other

02:08:08.220 --> 02:08:10.380
dragons would see her as the leader of

02:08:10.380 --> 02:08:11.399
the dragonettes.

02:08:11.640 --> 02:08:12.779
You heard the queen.

02:08:12.899 --> 02:08:14.460
It's for your own safety.

02:08:14.520 --> 02:08:15.479
You'll be fine.

02:08:15.539 --> 02:08:18.659
Please don't argue with me in front of my

02:08:18.659 --> 02:08:19.140
mother.

02:08:19.319 --> 02:08:20.640
Tsunami prayed.

02:08:20.699 --> 02:08:23.579
Glory glared at the sea wing guard for a

02:08:23.579 --> 02:08:24.000
moment longer.

02:08:24.060 --> 02:08:27.060
All right, she snarled.

02:08:27.119 --> 02:08:28.079
I'll go with you.

02:08:28.140 --> 02:08:31.140
But I still say, nobody touches me.

02:08:31.199 --> 02:08:33.539
Fair enough.

02:08:33.600 --> 02:08:36.420
Queen Carl purred with another gesture

02:08:36.420 --> 02:08:37.739
and flash of her stripes.

02:08:37.800 --> 02:08:39.539
Off you all go, then.

02:08:39.600 --> 02:08:42.840
Tsunami, darling, come sit with me and

02:08:42.840 --> 02:08:43.319
let's talk.

02:08:43.439 --> 02:08:47.340
She swept over to her throne, towing

02:08:47.340 --> 02:08:48.180
anemone behind her.

02:08:48.239 --> 02:08:50.699
The tiny dragonette settled onto the

02:08:50.699 --> 02:08:53.100
small throne, flicking her pearly wings

02:08:53.100 --> 02:08:55.140
and watching tsunami's friends with big

02:08:55.140 --> 02:08:55.380
eyes.

02:08:55.439 --> 02:08:59.880
It'll be all right, Tsunami said to Clay

02:08:59.880 --> 02:09:01.800
as the guards hefted him into the air.

02:09:01.859 --> 02:09:03.600
I'll come join you very soon.

02:09:03.659 --> 02:09:07.020
He nodded, still looking rather anxious.

02:09:07.079 --> 02:09:10.140
Another guard tentatively tried to shoe

02:09:10.140 --> 02:09:11.520
Starflight off the edge.

02:09:11.579 --> 02:09:13.619
The night wing backed away from him

02:09:13.619 --> 02:09:16.199
unhappily, then turned and flew after the

02:09:16.199 --> 02:09:17.220
guard who had Sonny.

02:09:17.279 --> 02:09:20.699
Tsunami watched her friend spiral down to

02:09:20.699 --> 02:09:21.720
the cave by the entrance.

02:09:21.779 --> 02:09:25.619
Brown and gold, black and silver, all of

02:09:25.619 --> 02:09:26.699
them so out of place here.

02:09:26.760 --> 02:09:29.939
She saw them vanish into the dark hole

02:09:29.939 --> 02:09:32.460
and then the guards emerged and planted

02:09:32.460 --> 02:09:33.060
themselves outside.

02:09:33.119 --> 02:09:36.239
It didn't look like the way you'd treat

02:09:36.239 --> 02:09:36.720
guests.

02:09:36.840 --> 02:09:40.199
At least it's better than the Sky Wing

02:09:40.199 --> 02:09:41.279
Palace, she thought.

02:09:41.340 --> 02:09:43.800
At least we're not being forced to fight

02:09:43.800 --> 02:09:44.340
to the death.

02:09:44.399 --> 02:09:46.560
My mother is keeping us safe.

02:09:46.680 --> 02:09:49.859
She's really being welcoming in her own

02:09:49.859 --> 02:09:50.100
way.

02:09:50.159 --> 02:09:53.460
She glanced up at her mother's warm eyes

02:09:53.460 --> 02:09:55.439
especially to me.

02:09:55.500 --> 02:09:59.100
Her mother reached out her talons to her

02:09:59.100 --> 02:09:59.520
smiling.

02:09:59.579 --> 02:10:00.960
She was perfect.

02:10:01.020 --> 02:10:03.600
Just what tsunami had always imagined.

02:10:03.659 --> 02:10:06.420
Her friends would be all right, tsunami

02:10:06.420 --> 02:10:06.899
was sure.

02:10:06.960 --> 02:10:08.939
They were in the Seawing Palace now.

02:10:09.000 --> 02:10:11.520
She was home with her family.

02:10:11.579 --> 02:10:14.100
This was her lifelong dream.

02:10:14.159 --> 02:10:17.520
There's nothing to worry about, she told

02:10:17.520 --> 02:10:17.939
herself.

02:10:18.000 --> 02:10:19.680
Nothing at all.

02:10:19.739 --> 02:10:24.119
Chapter 9.

02:10:24.180 --> 02:10:29.220
Here, Queen Coral said, taking a strand

02:10:29.220 --> 02:10:30.600
of pearls off her own horns.

02:10:30.659 --> 02:10:34.199
You are so unadorned, my beautiful

02:10:34.199 --> 02:10:35.399
dragonette.

02:10:35.460 --> 02:10:37.920
I have to start making up for all the

02:10:37.920 --> 02:10:39.659
presents I missed giving you.

02:10:39.779 --> 02:10:43.260
She leaned forward and draped the pearls

02:10:43.260 --> 02:10:45.180
around Tsunami's neck.

02:10:45.239 --> 02:10:48.000
They were heavy and smooth, sliding

02:10:48.000 --> 02:10:50.159
coolly across tsunami's scales.

02:10:50.220 --> 02:10:52.859
My 1st treasure.

02:10:52.920 --> 02:10:56.100
It was a strange thrill, having something

02:10:56.100 --> 02:10:56.939
of her very own.

02:10:57.000 --> 02:10:59.819
All dragons loved treasure.

02:10:59.880 --> 02:11:02.159
It was the only thing they had in common

02:11:02.159 --> 02:11:03.119
with scavengers.

02:11:03.180 --> 02:11:05.520
But this was more than a shiny, beautiful

02:11:05.520 --> 02:11:05.880
thing.

02:11:05.939 --> 02:11:09.300
It belonged to tsunami, and nobody else

02:11:09.300 --> 02:11:11.819
and it made her look even more like her

02:11:11.819 --> 02:11:12.119
mother.

02:11:12.180 --> 02:11:15.899
Tsunami stroked the pearls with her claw

02:11:15.899 --> 02:11:17.039
and tucked her tail around her back

02:11:17.039 --> 02:11:17.579
talons.

02:11:17.640 --> 02:11:20.279
She wished anemone would stop staring at

02:11:20.279 --> 02:11:20.460
her.

02:11:20.579 --> 02:11:23.640
She must hate me, she thought.

02:11:23.699 --> 02:11:25.020
I would if I were her.

02:11:25.140 --> 02:11:27.539
She must know I want the throne she

02:11:27.539 --> 02:11:28.140
thought was hers.

02:11:28.199 --> 02:11:29.939
But not yet.

02:11:30.000 --> 02:11:32.340
Now was the time for getting to know her

02:11:32.340 --> 02:11:32.579
mother.

02:11:32.640 --> 02:11:35.760
Can we talk alone?

02:11:35.880 --> 02:11:37.439
Tsunami asked.

02:11:37.500 --> 02:11:40.020
The 10 dragons were still perched like

02:11:40.020 --> 02:11:42.539
creepy sentinels with Shark, the

02:11:42.539 --> 02:11:43.319
creepiest of all.

02:11:43.380 --> 02:11:46.439
Of course, said the queen.

02:11:46.500 --> 02:11:48.180
Counsel you are dismissed.

02:11:48.300 --> 02:11:51.060
Moray, send a message to Queen Blister

02:11:51.060 --> 02:11:52.500
and see how quickly she can get here.

02:11:52.560 --> 02:11:56.220
As for you, creature, go back to your

02:11:56.220 --> 02:11:58.260
guard outpost and stay there until

02:11:58.260 --> 02:11:59.699
someone actually wants to see you.

02:11:59.760 --> 02:12:04.079
Riptide crouched, nodding, and dove over

02:12:04.079 --> 02:12:04.560
the edge.

02:12:04.619 --> 02:12:07.439
Tsunami leaned out to watch him swimming

02:12:07.439 --> 02:12:08.159
into the tunnel.

02:12:08.220 --> 02:12:10.560
What's wrong with riptide?

02:12:10.680 --> 02:12:13.560
she asked, as the other 10 dragons also

02:12:13.560 --> 02:12:15.600
flew away in a thunderclap of wing

02:12:15.600 --> 02:12:16.020
beats.

02:12:16.079 --> 02:12:17.760
I thought he was nice.

02:12:17.819 --> 02:12:20.039
Oh no.

02:12:20.100 --> 02:12:22.500
Queen Coral said with a shudder.

02:12:22.560 --> 02:12:24.180
He can't be trusted.

02:12:24.239 --> 02:12:25.920
Webbs is his father.

02:12:26.039 --> 02:12:28.260
Their bloodline is tainted with

02:12:28.260 --> 02:12:28.979
betrayal.

02:12:29.039 --> 02:12:32.699
Tsunami felt like a giant wave had just

02:12:32.699 --> 02:12:33.359
knocked her over.

02:12:33.420 --> 02:12:36.720
Webbs is his father?

02:12:36.779 --> 02:12:41.399
But she'd liked riptide, and all along, he

02:12:41.399 --> 02:12:43.920
was the son of her kidnapper, which he

02:12:43.920 --> 02:12:45.239
had carefully never mentioned.

02:12:45.300 --> 02:12:47.100
What else hadn't he told her?

02:12:47.159 --> 02:12:50.880
Nasty family, Coral went on.

02:12:50.939 --> 02:12:53.220
She lashed her tail, nearly hitting

02:12:53.220 --> 02:12:54.180
anemone in the head.

02:12:54.239 --> 02:12:57.119
Not fitting company for royalty by any

02:12:57.119 --> 02:12:57.420
means.

02:12:57.479 --> 02:12:59.819
We keep him as far away from us as

02:12:59.819 --> 02:13:00.180
possible.

02:13:00.239 --> 02:13:02.880
Poor Riptide.

02:13:03.000 --> 02:13:04.199
Tsunami thought.

02:13:04.260 --> 02:13:06.779
It wasn't his fault his father had turned

02:13:06.779 --> 02:13:09.119
traitor, but he suffered for it anyway.

02:13:09.180 --> 02:13:12.840
And yet, he had hidden the truth from her

02:13:12.840 --> 02:13:14.939
and she didn't like that at all.

02:13:15.000 --> 02:13:17.279
Was Queen Coral right about him?

02:13:17.340 --> 02:13:20.100
Surely she knew her own subjects better

02:13:20.100 --> 02:13:21.119
than tsunami did.

02:13:21.180 --> 02:13:23.579
But there was still a part of tsunami

02:13:23.579 --> 02:13:25.079
that hoped she'd see him again.

02:13:25.140 --> 02:13:27.539
She glanced at anemone.

02:13:27.600 --> 02:13:32.100
So we were saying, Alone?

02:13:32.159 --> 02:13:37.079
Oh, no, anemone never leaves my side.

02:13:37.140 --> 02:13:38.819
Queen Coral said.

02:13:38.880 --> 02:13:41.399
She reached over and lovingly patted the

02:13:41.399 --> 02:13:42.420
little dragonette's head.

02:13:42.479 --> 02:13:46.020
I finally got a living daughter, and I'm

02:13:46.020 --> 02:13:46.619
keeping her that way.

02:13:46.680 --> 02:13:52.859
By watching me every second, Anemone said

02:13:52.859 --> 02:13:55.680
she widened her eyes at tsunami, who

02:13:55.680 --> 02:13:57.420
wondered if she'd imagined a hint of

02:13:57.420 --> 02:13:58.920
sarcasm in her sister's words.

02:13:58.979 --> 02:14:03.720
And now I have 2 daughters, Queen Coral

02:14:03.720 --> 02:14:06.659
said proudly, possibly 4 by the end of

02:14:06.659 --> 02:14:08.880
next week, if Tortoise does her job

02:14:08.880 --> 02:14:09.119
right.

02:14:09.180 --> 02:14:11.640
She gave tsunami a worried look.

02:14:11.760 --> 02:14:14.880
Maybe we should make a harness for you

02:14:14.880 --> 02:14:15.539
too, dear.

02:14:15.600 --> 02:14:20.220
Oh, no, that's all right, tsunami said

02:14:20.220 --> 02:14:22.079
eyeing the straps that lashed coral and

02:14:22.079 --> 02:14:22.920
anemone together.

02:14:22.979 --> 02:14:25.439
I've managed to take care of myself up to

02:14:25.439 --> 02:14:25.680
now.

02:14:25.739 --> 02:14:27.899
I promise I'll stay alive.

02:14:27.960 --> 02:14:30.720
Much as she already loved her mother, She

02:14:30.720 --> 02:14:32.699
cannot imagine being attached to anyone

02:14:32.699 --> 02:14:34.260
every moment of every day.

02:14:34.319 --> 02:14:37.319
Hmm, said the queen.

02:14:37.380 --> 02:14:39.420
Well, we'll think about it.

02:14:39.479 --> 02:14:42.720
She studied tsunami's shoulders, as if

02:14:42.720 --> 02:14:44.220
she was mentally measuring her for a

02:14:44.220 --> 02:14:44.819
harness anyway.

02:14:44.880 --> 02:14:48.899
I have to tell you something, tsunami

02:14:48.899 --> 02:14:51.000
said, hoping to change the subject.

02:14:51.060 --> 02:14:52.260
I...

02:14:52.260 --> 02:14:54.659
I don't know the underwater language.

02:14:54.779 --> 02:14:56.159
Webbs never taught it to me.

02:14:56.220 --> 02:14:58.680
Queen Coral stared at her.

02:14:58.739 --> 02:15:03.300
What is wrong with that dragon, she

02:15:03.300 --> 02:15:03.779
growled.

02:15:03.840 --> 02:15:05.460
It's all right sweetheart.

02:15:05.520 --> 02:15:07.500
We'll have Whirlpool teach you.

02:15:07.560 --> 02:15:09.000
He's a terrific teacher.

02:15:09.060 --> 02:15:10.439
Right, anemone?

02:15:10.500 --> 02:15:11.939
Anemone shrugged.

02:15:12.000 --> 02:15:17.340
So, what do, you know, Queen Coral asked

02:15:17.340 --> 02:15:19.380
did they teach you anything?

02:15:19.439 --> 02:15:21.239
Of course.

02:15:21.300 --> 02:15:22.439
Tsunami said.

02:15:22.560 --> 02:15:24.539
She didn't want her mother to think she

02:15:24.539 --> 02:15:25.920
was unfit to be queen.

02:15:25.979 --> 02:15:29.640
We had lots of battle training, and Webbs

02:15:29.640 --> 02:15:31.079
taught us the history of Pyria.

02:15:31.140 --> 02:15:33.300
We learned all about the scorching, and

02:15:33.300 --> 02:15:35.340
how the tribes were founded, and how we

02:15:35.340 --> 02:15:37.020
nearly wiped out the scavengers.

02:15:37.079 --> 02:15:39.539
Um, and he did geography too.

02:15:39.600 --> 02:15:41.640
Dune taught us hunting.

02:15:41.699 --> 02:15:43.739
Kestrel was supposed to teach different

02:15:43.739 --> 02:15:46.319
tribes strengths and weaknesses, but

02:15:46.319 --> 02:15:48.300
mostly she just yelled and try to set us

02:15:48.300 --> 02:15:48.960
on fire a lot.

02:15:49.020 --> 02:15:51.840
Anemone's eyes were bright with

02:15:51.840 --> 02:15:52.380
interest.

02:15:52.439 --> 02:15:54.899
Why don't I get to learn those things

02:15:54.899 --> 02:15:55.319
mother?

02:15:55.319 --> 02:15:56.399
she asked.

02:15:56.460 --> 02:15:59.279
You will, dear, said Queen Coral.

02:15:59.340 --> 02:16:00.600
When I think you're ready.

02:16:00.659 --> 02:16:02.819
What do you study?

02:16:02.939 --> 02:16:04.199
Tsunami asked.

02:16:04.260 --> 02:16:06.359
Anemone glanced up at her mother.

02:16:06.479 --> 02:16:09.539
How the council works, she said.

02:16:09.600 --> 02:16:12.600
Aquatic, of course, how to interpret

02:16:12.600 --> 02:16:15.420
battle reports and order our defenses

02:16:15.420 --> 02:16:17.340
managing the food supply and the treasury

02:16:17.340 --> 02:16:19.380
although the council commanders really do

02:16:19.380 --> 02:16:19.619
all that.

02:16:19.680 --> 02:16:23.100
It's still important to stay on top of

02:16:23.100 --> 02:16:24.840
them. purred the queen.

02:16:24.899 --> 02:16:27.600
Dragons do their best work if you watch

02:16:27.600 --> 02:16:29.159
them closely the whole time.

02:16:29.220 --> 02:16:32.879
But mostly I'm stuck in training sessions

02:16:32.879 --> 02:16:35.219
with Whirlpool, Anemone said.

02:16:35.280 --> 02:16:36.780
Her wings drooped.

02:16:36.840 --> 02:16:38.159
For what?

02:16:38.219 --> 02:16:39.419
Tsunami asked.

02:16:39.479 --> 02:16:40.500
Aquatic?

02:16:40.559 --> 02:16:42.479
Never mind, dear.

02:16:42.540 --> 02:16:44.100
Queen Coral interrupted.

02:16:44.159 --> 02:16:45.360
You'll see eventually.

02:16:45.420 --> 02:16:48.479
Were the talents of peace very cruel to

02:16:48.479 --> 02:16:48.719
you?

02:16:48.780 --> 02:16:50.879
Terribly?

02:16:51.000 --> 02:16:52.200
Tsunami said.

02:16:52.260 --> 02:16:54.299
This was one of her favorite topics.

02:16:54.360 --> 02:16:57.059
They never let us out of the caves at

02:16:57.059 --> 02:16:57.659
all.

02:16:57.719 --> 02:16:59.279
They acted like we were brainless

02:16:59.279 --> 02:16:59.879
snails.

02:16:59.940 --> 02:17:02.879
Nobody ever listened to me, and they

02:17:02.879 --> 02:17:04.020
wouldn't tell us anything about our

02:17:04.020 --> 02:17:05.940
families or where we came from.

02:17:06.000 --> 02:17:08.219
I only found out about you a few days

02:17:08.219 --> 02:17:08.579
ago.

02:17:08.639 --> 02:17:12.419
My poor, poor baby.

02:17:12.479 --> 02:17:16.079
Queen Coral said, stroking tsunami's head

02:17:16.079 --> 02:17:16.379
again.

02:17:16.440 --> 02:17:19.440
Exactly, tsunami thought.

02:17:19.500 --> 02:17:22.500
This was the sympathy she'd always wanted

02:17:22.500 --> 02:17:24.959
although she didn't appreciate the

02:17:24.959 --> 02:17:26.700
skeptical look on Anemone's face.

02:17:26.760 --> 02:17:28.739
What are these?

02:17:28.799 --> 02:17:29.879
Tsunami asked.

02:17:30.000 --> 02:17:32.219
She leaned forward and touched the dark

02:17:32.219 --> 02:17:33.959
stains on the queen's talons with one

02:17:33.959 --> 02:17:34.319
claw.

02:17:34.440 --> 02:17:37.139
They looked too dark to be bloodstains

02:17:37.139 --> 02:17:38.639
but she couldn't guess what else they

02:17:38.639 --> 02:17:38.819
were.

02:17:38.879 --> 02:17:43.439
The perils of my job, Queen Carl said

02:17:43.439 --> 02:17:43.979
with a laugh.

02:17:44.040 --> 02:17:46.260
Well, my hobby.

02:17:46.319 --> 02:17:48.540
My art, you might call it.

02:17:48.600 --> 02:17:50.100
I should show you.

02:17:50.219 --> 02:17:53.459
She sprang to her feet, tugging anemone

02:17:53.459 --> 02:17:53.879
up with her.

02:17:53.940 --> 02:17:56.280
And then you can meet Whirlpool.

02:17:56.340 --> 02:17:57.719
You'll adore him.

02:17:57.780 --> 02:18:00.479
He's just the most wonderful, brilliant

02:18:00.479 --> 02:18:01.200
young dragon.

02:18:01.260 --> 02:18:04.260
Tsunami was nearly certain she caught

02:18:04.260 --> 02:18:05.639
anemone rolling her eyes.

02:18:05.760 --> 02:18:08.459
She followed the 2 of them down 4 levels

02:18:08.459 --> 02:18:10.860
to a floor with low walls and several

02:18:10.860 --> 02:18:13.319
shapes like large cauldrons molded into

02:18:13.319 --> 02:18:14.459
the stone.

02:18:14.520 --> 02:18:16.739
Black and blue webbed talon prints

02:18:16.739 --> 02:18:19.260
trailed all around the floor, and a

02:18:19.260 --> 02:18:21.479
raised podium stood at one end, with

02:18:21.479 --> 02:18:23.700
space for an audience of 30 dragons in

02:18:23.700 --> 02:18:23.879
front.

02:18:23.940 --> 02:18:27.000
At the other end was a long gray stone

02:18:27.000 --> 02:18:29.819
table with a scroll spread out on it, held

02:18:29.819 --> 02:18:31.799
down at either end by a small seahorse

02:18:31.799 --> 02:18:33.659
carved of dark brown wood.

02:18:33.719 --> 02:18:36.119
Tsunami peered at the scroll, which

02:18:36.119 --> 02:18:37.499
looked only half written.

02:18:37.559 --> 02:18:39.899
That's my work in progress.

02:18:39.959 --> 02:18:43.739
Queen Coral said proudly, Whirlpool, come

02:18:43.739 --> 02:18:43.979
here.

02:18:44.040 --> 02:18:46.860
She bustled over to one of the cauldrons

02:18:46.860 --> 02:18:49.559
and tsunami realized they were all packed

02:18:49.559 --> 02:18:51.180
with neatly rolled scrolls.

02:18:51.239 --> 02:18:55.559
This is beautiful, she said, lifting one

02:18:55.559 --> 02:18:57.059
of the carved seahorses.

02:18:57.120 --> 02:19:00.059
They were heavy, and intricately detailed

02:19:00.059 --> 02:19:02.399
with curiously dragon like expressions on

02:19:02.399 --> 02:19:03.360
their tiny faces.

02:19:03.420 --> 02:19:08.040
Orca made those, Queen Coral said sadly.

02:19:08.100 --> 02:19:12.299
My 1st daughter, she was a very talented

02:19:12.299 --> 02:19:12.840
sculptor.

02:19:12.899 --> 02:19:15.059
First daughter.

02:19:15.120 --> 02:19:17.040
What happened to her?

02:19:17.100 --> 02:19:19.979
Tsunami hadn't thought any of them lived

02:19:19.979 --> 02:19:21.180
long enough to become artists.

02:19:21.239 --> 02:19:24.239
She gave anemone a quizzical expression

02:19:24.239 --> 02:19:26.159
but her sister was watching the queen

02:19:26.159 --> 02:19:26.760
intently.

02:19:26.879 --> 02:19:29.519
I'll ask Starflight later.

02:19:29.579 --> 02:19:32.520
Orca must be in that lineage scroll he

02:19:32.520 --> 02:19:33.059
was going on about.

02:19:33.120 --> 02:19:36.780
A dark green dragon with pale green eyes

02:19:36.780 --> 02:19:38.940
rose up from the council level.

02:19:39.000 --> 02:19:41.340
He had a remarkably large gold hoop

02:19:41.340 --> 02:19:44.159
piercing one ear, and dappled light green

02:19:44.159 --> 02:19:46.620
scales in wave patterns along his back.

02:19:46.680 --> 02:19:49.079
He also had the same dark stains on his

02:19:49.079 --> 02:19:49.500
talons.

02:19:49.620 --> 02:19:52.739
Your majesty.

02:19:52.860 --> 02:19:55.260
He said with an elaborate bow.

02:19:55.319 --> 02:19:59.280
And your smaller majesties.

02:19:59.399 --> 02:20:03.840
His voice was oily and slow, like squids

02:20:03.840 --> 02:20:05.819
creeping into tsunami's ears.

02:20:05.879 --> 02:20:09.120
She guessed this was whirlpool, although

02:20:09.120 --> 02:20:11.340
he didn't look particularly wonderful or

02:20:11.340 --> 02:20:12.059
brilliant.

02:20:12.120 --> 02:20:15.360
He bowed to anemone and tsunami as he

02:20:15.360 --> 02:20:17.040
settled onto the floor behind the stone

02:20:17.040 --> 02:20:17.520
table.

02:20:17.579 --> 02:20:20.280
His eyes almost immediately went from

02:20:20.280 --> 02:20:22.860
them to the scroll in front of him, and

02:20:22.860 --> 02:20:24.239
he tilted his head thoughtfully.

02:20:24.299 --> 02:20:27.420
After a moment, he reached forward and

02:20:27.420 --> 02:20:29.760
dipped one claw into a small pool of

02:20:29.760 --> 02:20:31.440
black ink in the top corner of the

02:20:31.440 --> 02:20:32.700
table.

02:20:32.760 --> 02:20:34.799
With the ink, he scratched a few more

02:20:34.799 --> 02:20:36.540
words at the point where the scroll went

02:20:36.540 --> 02:20:36.840
blank.

02:20:36.899 --> 02:20:40.920
Oh, tsunami said, glancing from his

02:20:40.920 --> 02:20:42.059
talons to her mother's.

02:20:42.120 --> 02:20:44.700
Oh, it's ink.

02:20:44.760 --> 02:20:48.000
Yes, dear, said Queen Coral.

02:20:48.059 --> 02:20:50.159
She pulled an armful of scrolls out of

02:20:50.159 --> 02:20:50.760
the cauldron.

02:20:50.819 --> 02:20:53.940
It's a special formula made of squid ink

02:20:53.940 --> 02:20:56.399
and a touch of whale blood, so it never

02:20:56.399 --> 02:20:56.940
fades.

02:20:57.000 --> 02:21:00.239
Immortality is worth a few claw stains

02:21:00.239 --> 02:21:00.780
don't you agree?

02:21:00.840 --> 02:21:02.700
Whirlpool invented it.

02:21:02.760 --> 02:21:04.200
He's terribly clever.

02:21:04.260 --> 02:21:06.959
She peered at the words he'd written.

02:21:07.020 --> 02:21:09.059
Exactly what I was thinking.

02:21:09.120 --> 02:21:11.520
This is an exciting one, isn't it?

02:21:11.579 --> 02:21:15.239
Certain to win all the awards in the

02:21:15.239 --> 02:21:16.680
kingdom, your majesty.

02:21:16.739 --> 02:21:18.959
Whirlpool oozed.

02:21:19.020 --> 02:21:21.959
Queen Coral piled 4 scrolls into

02:21:21.959 --> 02:21:23.040
tsunami's talons.

02:21:23.100 --> 02:21:25.739
These are my favorites.

02:21:25.799 --> 02:21:27.659
You can read them all tonight, and

02:21:27.659 --> 02:21:29.520
tomorrow I'll give you 4 of my other

02:21:29.520 --> 02:21:30.479
favorites.

02:21:30.540 --> 02:21:34.260
Read all these tonight?

02:21:34.319 --> 02:21:36.719
Tsunami echoed, dismayed.

02:21:36.840 --> 02:21:39.540
Reading was Starflight's specialty.

02:21:39.600 --> 02:21:42.239
She liked it fine, but only if there were

02:21:42.239 --> 02:21:44.280
exciting stories and female warrior

02:21:44.280 --> 02:21:44.819
dragons.

02:21:44.879 --> 02:21:47.879
She didn't read very fast, and really

02:21:47.879 --> 02:21:49.500
she'd rather be fighting something.

02:21:49.559 --> 02:21:51.659
Start with this one.

02:21:51.780 --> 02:21:54.360
Queen Coral said, plucking one of the

02:21:54.360 --> 02:21:54.959
scrolls free.

02:21:55.020 --> 02:21:57.659
It was the missing princess.

02:21:57.719 --> 02:22:00.479
Relief flooded through tsunami.

02:22:00.540 --> 02:22:02.760
I've read that one, she cried.

02:22:02.819 --> 02:22:05.040
That was my favorite story ever.

02:22:05.100 --> 02:22:06.899
Really?

02:22:06.959 --> 02:22:10.379
Queen Coral looked delighted, and tsunami

02:22:10.379 --> 02:22:12.299
was pretty sure Anemone had rolled her

02:22:12.299 --> 02:22:12.659
eyes again.

02:22:12.719 --> 02:22:14.879
I wrote it for you.

02:22:14.940 --> 02:22:17.340
You...

02:22:17.340 --> 02:22:19.979
Tsunami looked from Queen Coral to

02:22:19.979 --> 02:22:21.719
Whirlpool and the scroll on the table.

02:22:21.780 --> 02:22:25.379
You wrote The Missing Princess?

02:22:25.500 --> 02:22:28.020
I wrote all of these.

02:22:28.079 --> 02:22:30.659
Queen Coral waved your talent at the

02:22:30.659 --> 02:22:31.979
scrolls in the cauldrons.

02:22:32.040 --> 02:22:34.020
I'm really quite prolific.

02:22:34.079 --> 02:22:37.079
Whirlpool makes sure 100s of copies are

02:22:37.079 --> 02:22:39.719
instantly made and distributed all over

02:22:39.719 --> 02:22:42.719
sea wing territory, and wherever else on

02:22:42.719 --> 02:22:43.979
Pyria, we can send them.

02:22:44.040 --> 02:22:47.760
My communications, Herald, Moray, is in

02:22:47.760 --> 02:22:49.559
charge of the printer dragons who make

02:22:49.559 --> 02:22:50.940
the underwater copies.

02:22:51.000 --> 02:22:53.639
She also makes sure they go to all the

02:22:53.639 --> 02:22:56.340
schools, but Whirlpool organizes my

02:22:56.340 --> 02:22:56.819
readings here.

02:22:56.940 --> 02:22:58.979
Isn't he brilliant?

02:22:59.040 --> 02:23:01.440
She lowered her voice and winked at

02:23:01.440 --> 02:23:01.979
tsunami.

02:23:02.040 --> 02:23:05.100
And don't you think he's very handsome?

02:23:05.159 --> 02:23:08.879
Whirlpool looked up and gave tsunami a

02:23:08.879 --> 02:23:10.799
toothy smile that didn't reach his eyes.

02:23:10.860 --> 02:23:14.100
His teeth were weirdly small, and his

02:23:14.100 --> 02:23:17.280
eyes were too pale and blobby, like frog

02:23:17.280 --> 02:23:17.819
eyes.

02:23:17.879 --> 02:23:20.280
Tsunami couldn't help thinking of riptide

02:23:20.280 --> 02:23:22.260
who was much more handsome if you asked

02:23:22.260 --> 02:23:22.500
her.

02:23:22.559 --> 02:23:25.379
Although she knew better than to tell

02:23:25.379 --> 02:23:26.040
Coral that.

02:23:26.159 --> 02:23:29.639
He'll make a fabulous king one day.

02:23:29.760 --> 02:23:32.520
Queen Coral added in a loud whisper.

02:23:32.579 --> 02:23:34.079
Oh, dear.

02:23:34.139 --> 02:23:36.360
Tsunami hid her shudder.

02:23:36.420 --> 02:23:38.760
Is Queen Carl throwing him at me?

02:23:38.819 --> 02:23:41.819
She glanced at anemone, and saw the

02:23:41.819 --> 02:23:43.799
little dragonette quickly erasing a

02:23:43.799 --> 02:23:45.120
hopeful expression from her face.

02:23:45.180 --> 02:23:46.739
Hmm.

02:23:46.860 --> 02:23:49.379
She bet anemone could clear up a lot of

02:23:49.379 --> 02:23:49.860
mysteries.

02:23:49.920 --> 02:23:52.079
If tsunami could get her alone for a

02:23:52.079 --> 02:23:52.440
moment.

02:23:52.500 --> 02:23:54.299
Too bad that was impossible.

02:23:54.420 --> 02:23:56.280
Your majesty?

02:23:56.399 --> 02:23:59.040
They all turned and found another council

02:23:59.040 --> 02:24:00.600
dragon hovering in the air behind the

02:24:00.600 --> 02:24:02.700
queen, with a smaller dragon beside her.

02:24:02.819 --> 02:24:05.879
I'm sorry to interrupt, but urchin just

02:24:05.879 --> 02:24:07.739
arrived with strange news.

02:24:07.799 --> 02:24:08.940
I knew you'd want to hear it right away.

02:24:09.000 --> 02:24:13.139
Of course, Moray, said Queen Coral.

02:24:13.200 --> 02:24:14.760
You always know what's best.

02:24:14.819 --> 02:24:18.540
Moray's scales were the same dull gray

02:24:18.540 --> 02:24:20.760
green as sharks, and her eyes were also

02:24:20.760 --> 02:24:22.260
small and colorless.

02:24:22.319 --> 02:24:24.659
Tsunami wondered if they were related.

02:24:24.719 --> 02:24:27.540
The council dragon pressed her snout into

02:24:27.540 --> 02:24:28.620
a brief, smug look.

02:24:28.680 --> 02:24:31.379
That's because I have had excellent

02:24:31.379 --> 02:24:32.940
training at the side of the most

02:24:32.940 --> 02:24:35.639
wonderful queen in pyrene history, she

02:24:35.639 --> 02:24:35.879
said.

02:24:35.940 --> 02:24:37.860
Oh my word.

02:24:37.920 --> 02:24:39.540
Tsunami thought.

02:24:39.600 --> 02:24:42.540
This time she was able to catch anemone's

02:24:42.540 --> 02:24:45.059
eye, behind the queen's back, to make an

02:24:45.059 --> 02:24:46.379
is she serious?

02:24:46.440 --> 02:24:47.219
Face.

02:24:47.280 --> 02:24:50.399
Anemone looked startled for a moment. then

02:24:50.399 --> 02:24:52.319
made a face back that tsunami was pretty

02:24:52.319 --> 02:24:54.840
sure meant, believe me, it gets worse.

02:24:54.899 --> 02:24:56.819
Moray went on.

02:24:56.879 --> 02:25:00.000
Apparently, a dead dragon has been found

02:25:00.000 --> 02:25:01.739
only a few islands from the summer

02:25:01.739 --> 02:25:02.280
palace.

02:25:02.340 --> 02:25:06.899
Oh, how sad. said Queen Coral with a

02:25:06.899 --> 02:25:07.379
little yawn.

02:25:07.440 --> 02:25:09.780
She glanced at her scrolls as if she

02:25:09.780 --> 02:25:10.620
wanted to get back to them.

02:25:10.680 --> 02:25:13.020
What happened to him?

02:25:13.079 --> 02:25:15.299
Her, said Moray.

02:25:15.360 --> 02:25:17.399
And we don't know yet, but the strange

02:25:17.399 --> 02:25:19.440
part is that it's not a sea wing.

02:25:19.500 --> 02:25:21.239
It's a sky wing.

02:25:21.299 --> 02:25:22.860
What?

02:25:22.920 --> 02:25:25.440
Queen Coral leaped to her talons.

02:25:25.500 --> 02:25:28.139
That close to the palace?

02:25:28.200 --> 02:25:30.180
She snapped at the air and spread her

02:25:30.180 --> 02:25:30.479
wings.

02:25:30.600 --> 02:25:33.360
Get shark and piranha, and take me to the

02:25:33.360 --> 02:25:34.260
body, now.

02:25:34.319 --> 02:25:37.920
The queen shot into the air, with anemone

02:25:37.920 --> 02:25:39.899
flapping wildly to keep up.

02:25:39.959 --> 02:25:41.879
Tsunami dropped the scrolls and jumped

02:25:41.879 --> 02:25:44.579
after them, flying in a tight spiral down

02:25:44.579 --> 02:25:44.940
to the water.

02:25:45.000 --> 02:25:47.819
This was her chance to see the queen in

02:25:47.819 --> 02:25:48.000
action.

02:25:48.120 --> 02:25:50.819
She thought she heard someone shout her

02:25:50.819 --> 02:25:53.879
name as she splashed down, Sonny or

02:25:53.879 --> 02:25:54.299
Clay?

02:25:54.360 --> 02:25:57.299
The water rushed into her ears, muffling

02:25:57.299 --> 02:25:57.719
the cry.

02:25:57.780 --> 02:25:59.340
They didn't have to worry.

02:25:59.399 --> 02:26:00.540
She wouldn't be gone long.

02:26:00.600 --> 02:26:01.920
They'd be safe here.

02:26:01.979 --> 02:26:05.579
Shark whipped past, churning up the water

02:26:05.579 --> 02:26:07.440
as he charged into the tunnel ahead of

02:26:07.440 --> 02:26:07.620
her.

02:26:07.680 --> 02:26:10.739
He was between her and Coral now, but

02:26:10.739 --> 02:26:12.180
tsunami wasn't going to let that stop

02:26:12.180 --> 02:26:12.479
her.

02:26:12.540 --> 02:26:15.059
She swam after them as fast as she

02:26:15.059 --> 02:26:15.299
could.

02:26:15.360 --> 02:26:18.479
She felt another dragon close on her tail

02:26:18.479 --> 02:26:20.459
but didn't turn around or slow down.

02:26:20.520 --> 02:26:24.180
It felt like only moments later, when

02:26:24.180 --> 02:26:26.520
tsunami's snout emerged into the golden

02:26:26.520 --> 02:26:28.979
kelp curtain, she followed the eddies

02:26:28.979 --> 02:26:31.260
left by the dragon tails ahead of her and

02:26:31.260 --> 02:26:32.700
realized they weren't going to the

02:26:32.700 --> 02:26:35.100
surface, so they weren't flying to the

02:26:35.100 --> 02:26:35.399
body.

02:26:35.459 --> 02:26:36.719
They were swimming there.

02:26:36.780 --> 02:26:38.520
Which made sense.

02:26:38.579 --> 02:26:40.079
They were sea wings after all.

02:26:40.200 --> 02:26:42.540
All right, I can do this.

02:26:42.600 --> 02:26:45.959
Tsunami ignored how tired her wings felt

02:26:45.959 --> 02:26:48.540
and beat them harder, determined to keep

02:26:48.540 --> 02:26:49.020
up.

02:26:49.079 --> 02:26:52.079
Even so, the 2 dragons behind her quickly

02:26:52.079 --> 02:26:54.780
passed her, Moray, and another from the

02:26:54.780 --> 02:26:57.000
council, who she guessed was piranha.

02:26:57.059 --> 02:27:00.120
She saw both dragons dipped down in the

02:27:00.120 --> 02:27:01.680
water and suddenly speed up.

02:27:01.739 --> 02:27:04.440
Despairing, she tried to do the same

02:27:04.440 --> 02:27:06.959
thing, tipping her wings to dip down to

02:27:06.959 --> 02:27:08.219
the same level.

02:27:08.280 --> 02:27:10.500
A fierce current immediately caught her

02:27:10.500 --> 02:27:12.299
up and shoved her along after them.

02:27:12.420 --> 02:27:15.540
For a moment, tsunami struggled against

02:27:15.540 --> 02:27:15.840
it.

02:27:15.899 --> 02:27:18.000
She didn't like being caught by anything

02:27:18.000 --> 02:27:18.840
stronger than her.

02:27:18.899 --> 02:27:21.899
But then she realized the other dragons

02:27:21.899 --> 02:27:24.600
were using it to travel faster, and she'd

02:27:24.600 --> 02:27:26.159
have to do the same thing if she wanted

02:27:26.159 --> 02:27:27.180
to stay with them.

02:27:27.479 --> 02:27:30.420
Slowly, she relaxed, and let the current

02:27:30.420 --> 02:27:31.440
sweep her along.

02:27:31.500 --> 02:27:33.600
It gave her a chance to look around.

02:27:33.719 --> 02:27:36.479
A school of black fish with silver

02:27:36.479 --> 02:27:39.239
speckles shot by overhead, like a flock

02:27:39.239 --> 02:27:41.940
of crows or night wings, spinning and

02:27:41.940 --> 02:27:43.500
whirling and shifting formations.

02:27:43.559 --> 02:27:47.040
Large translucent mushrooms sprouted from

02:27:47.040 --> 02:27:49.500
the ocean floor, with tiny orange fish

02:27:49.500 --> 02:27:50.639
clustered around them.

02:27:50.700 --> 02:27:54.600
A pulsing, reddish pink octopus wobbled

02:27:54.600 --> 02:27:54.840
by.

02:27:54.899 --> 02:27:56.579
And tsunami wondered if they were

02:27:56.579 --> 02:27:56.940
delicious.

02:27:57.059 --> 02:27:59.040
They were definitely slow enough to

02:27:59.040 --> 02:27:59.219
catch.

02:27:59.280 --> 02:28:02.879
Out of the corner of her eye, she spotted

02:28:02.879 --> 02:28:05.100
movement behind a swarm of iridescent

02:28:05.100 --> 02:28:05.879
jellyfish.

02:28:05.940 --> 02:28:09.659
She squinted, and realized it was riptide

02:28:09.659 --> 02:28:10.739
following her from a distance.

02:28:10.860 --> 02:28:13.680
She lifted one of her wings and waved to

02:28:13.680 --> 02:28:16.260
him, and after a moment, he sheepishly

02:28:16.260 --> 02:28:16.979
waved back.

02:28:17.340 --> 02:28:19.319
She didn't know what he was supposed to

02:28:19.319 --> 02:28:21.780
be doing, but this probably wasn't it.

02:28:21.840 --> 02:28:25.020
Still, she kind of liked having him there

02:28:25.020 --> 02:28:27.299
so she wasn't going to tell Coral on

02:28:27.299 --> 02:28:27.479
him.

02:28:27.540 --> 02:28:30.479
Not until she decided how mad she was

02:28:30.479 --> 02:28:33.299
about the Webbs being his father secret

02:28:33.299 --> 02:28:33.840
anyway.

02:28:33.899 --> 02:28:37.920
They swam for what felt like miles over

02:28:37.920 --> 02:28:40.260
wide stretches of algae covered coral

02:28:40.260 --> 02:28:43.079
reef that looked like ancient stone ruins

02:28:43.079 --> 02:28:45.659
palaces and temples that had collapsed

02:28:45.659 --> 02:28:46.260
long ago.

02:28:46.319 --> 02:28:49.799
Occasionally, a large greenish silver

02:28:49.799 --> 02:28:52.079
fish would dart up, swim alongside

02:28:52.079 --> 02:28:54.659
tsunami for a moment, notice her with a

02:28:54.659 --> 02:28:56.459
start of alarm, and flash away again.

02:28:56.520 --> 02:28:59.700
She was hungry, but too tired to try

02:28:59.700 --> 02:29:00.360
eating any of them.

02:29:00.420 --> 02:29:03.780
Even with the help of the current, tsunami

02:29:03.780 --> 02:29:04.799
felt ready to collapse.

02:29:04.860 --> 02:29:08.579
Finally, up ahead, she saw Moray and

02:29:08.579 --> 02:29:11.879
Piranha sweep up to the surface, relieved

02:29:11.879 --> 02:29:13.559
she struggled out of the current and

02:29:13.559 --> 02:29:14.940
followed them into the air.

02:29:15.000 --> 02:29:18.059
Queen Coral was already standing on a

02:29:18.059 --> 02:29:20.459
large craggy boulder that jutted out of

02:29:20.459 --> 02:29:22.739
the sea at the base of an enormous

02:29:22.739 --> 02:29:23.040
cliff.

02:29:23.100 --> 02:29:25.620
Anemone was crowded onto a tiny

02:29:25.620 --> 02:29:26.819
outcropping beside her.

02:29:26.879 --> 02:29:30.600
Not far away, a seal edged nervously into

02:29:30.600 --> 02:29:32.700
the water, trying not to attract their

02:29:32.700 --> 02:29:33.180
attention.

02:29:33.239 --> 02:29:36.780
Waves pounded the rocks, roaring like

02:29:36.780 --> 02:29:39.360
angry dragons, and spraying salt water

02:29:39.360 --> 02:29:41.219
over everyone who has clustered around

02:29:41.219 --> 02:29:42.540
the queen on smaller rocks.

02:29:42.600 --> 02:29:45.899
Tsunami found a jagged black rock the

02:29:45.899 --> 02:29:47.700
right size for her, and clambered up.

02:29:47.760 --> 02:29:51.180
For a moment she just breathed, happy not

02:29:51.180 --> 02:29:51.719
to be moving.

02:29:51.780 --> 02:29:54.659
She had no idea how she'd make it back to

02:29:54.659 --> 02:29:55.559
the Summer Palace.

02:29:55.620 --> 02:29:57.360
Deal with that later.

02:29:57.479 --> 02:30:00.719
Far off to the north, she saw a bank of

02:30:00.719 --> 02:30:02.879
dark clouds huddled on the horizon

02:30:02.879 --> 02:30:04.860
muttering and flashing.

02:30:04.920 --> 02:30:07.079
She's been dead a day or two.

02:30:07.200 --> 02:30:10.739
Shark said grimly, killed quite violently

02:30:10.739 --> 02:30:11.879
by the looks of it.

02:30:12.000 --> 02:30:15.239
Tsunami glanced down at the broken red

02:30:15.239 --> 02:30:16.680
body snagged on the rocks.

02:30:16.739 --> 02:30:19.260
Shark was leaning over the corpse

02:30:19.260 --> 02:30:21.840
inspecting the deep slashes across the

02:30:21.840 --> 02:30:22.200
throat.

02:30:22.260 --> 02:30:24.659
He shook his head and stepped back.

02:30:24.719 --> 02:30:28.440
A bolt of shock and terror shot through

02:30:28.440 --> 02:30:29.040
tsunami.

02:30:29.100 --> 02:30:31.739
She knew this sky wing.

02:30:31.799 --> 02:30:34.979
It was Kestrel, the dragon who'd raised

02:30:34.979 --> 02:30:35.399
them.

02:30:35.459 --> 02:30:39.420
Kestrel was dead, and somebody had

02:30:39.420 --> 02:30:40.440
clearly murdered her.

02:30:40.500 --> 02:30:44.760
Chapter 10.

02:30:45.059 --> 02:30:47.340
Tell.

02:30:47.459 --> 02:30:48.479
Don't tell.

02:30:48.600 --> 02:30:51.059
Mother needs to know who it is.

02:30:51.120 --> 02:30:54.180
But what if she thinks we killed her?

02:30:54.299 --> 02:30:56.940
Tsunami didn't know what to do.

02:30:57.000 --> 02:30:59.579
It was too strange a coincidence.

02:30:59.639 --> 02:31:02.159
Kestrel turning up dead, a few islands

02:31:02.159 --> 02:31:04.979
away, at the same time as the dragonettes

02:31:04.979 --> 02:31:06.360
arriving at the Summer Palace.

02:31:06.420 --> 02:31:08.700
If tsunami admitted she knew her.

02:31:08.760 --> 02:31:11.340
Wouldn't her mother's 1st thought be that

02:31:11.340 --> 02:31:12.719
the dragonettes had killed her

02:31:12.719 --> 02:31:13.979
themselves?

02:31:14.040 --> 02:31:15.959
After the way her friends had been

02:31:15.959 --> 02:31:16.860
looking at her lately?

02:31:16.920 --> 02:31:19.200
Tsunami didn't want to risk getting a

02:31:19.200 --> 02:31:21.780
similar reaction from her mother, the

02:31:21.780 --> 02:31:23.520
What kind of dragon are you really?

02:31:23.579 --> 02:31:26.159
And can you be trusted?

02:31:26.219 --> 02:31:29.639
And who else might you attack, looks?

02:31:29.760 --> 02:31:32.399
She worried about it all the way back to

02:31:32.399 --> 02:31:33.420
the Summer Palace.

02:31:33.479 --> 02:31:36.360
Mercifully, they flew back, giving

02:31:36.360 --> 02:31:38.399
tsunamis swimming muscles a rest.

02:31:38.459 --> 02:31:41.040
But in the bustle of orders and flying

02:31:41.040 --> 02:31:43.200
messengers, there wasn't a moment to talk

02:31:43.200 --> 02:31:44.819
to the queen on her own anyway.

02:31:44.879 --> 02:31:48.600
Back at the palace, Queen Coral told

02:31:48.600 --> 02:31:50.819
tsunami to wait for her and took a few

02:31:50.819 --> 02:31:52.860
council dragons off for a war meeting.

02:31:52.920 --> 02:31:55.739
Tsunami sat on one of the pavilion

02:31:55.739 --> 02:31:58.200
pillars, watching dragons dart about.

02:31:58.319 --> 02:32:00.840
Who would kill Kestrel?

02:32:00.899 --> 02:32:03.239
Apart from glory or me, that is?

02:32:03.299 --> 02:32:05.940
She glanced at the cave where her friends

02:32:05.940 --> 02:32:08.280
were being held, where guards were still

02:32:08.280 --> 02:32:08.940
posted outside.

02:32:09.000 --> 02:32:11.940
She knew she should go check on the other

02:32:11.940 --> 02:32:14.280
dragonettes, but what would they think

02:32:14.280 --> 02:32:15.719
when they heard about Kestrel?

02:32:15.780 --> 02:32:18.780
What if our friends decided it wasn't

02:32:18.780 --> 02:32:19.379
safe here?

02:32:19.440 --> 02:32:22.379
Starflight might convince the others, that

02:32:22.379 --> 02:32:24.360
Kestrel's murderer could be nearby

02:32:24.360 --> 02:32:25.860
waiting to kill them too.

02:32:25.920 --> 02:32:28.440
He talked them into leaving the kingdom

02:32:28.440 --> 02:32:30.840
of the sea, and tsunami wasn't ready for

02:32:30.840 --> 02:32:31.020
that.

02:32:31.079 --> 02:32:33.840
They were all too mad at her right now to

02:32:33.840 --> 02:32:35.940
listen to sense, and they were probably

02:32:35.940 --> 02:32:38.340
pretty grumpy about being stuck in a

02:32:38.340 --> 02:32:39.959
guarded cave all afternoon too.

02:32:40.020 --> 02:32:43.260
It'd be better to wait and tell them

02:32:43.260 --> 02:32:45.420
everything after they had a chance to see

02:32:45.420 --> 02:32:46.860
how wonderful it could be here.

02:32:46.920 --> 02:32:50.040
Tomorrow, she'd ask her mother to bring

02:32:50.040 --> 02:32:52.020
them out for a feast or something, and

02:32:52.020 --> 02:32:53.399
that would cheer up at least a couple of

02:32:53.399 --> 02:32:53.819
them.

02:32:53.879 --> 02:32:56.459
Yes, that's a better plan.

02:32:56.520 --> 02:32:59.399
Avoid them until tomorrow, then tell them

02:32:59.399 --> 02:32:59.760
everything.

02:32:59.819 --> 02:33:04.020
Besides, she was so, so tired.

02:33:04.079 --> 02:33:07.020
Darkness had fallen as they flew back to

02:33:07.020 --> 02:33:09.600
the Summer Palace, and now the cavern was

02:33:09.600 --> 02:33:12.059
lit only by trails of glowing jellyfish

02:33:12.059 --> 02:33:13.020
in the water below.

02:33:13.079 --> 02:33:15.959
Not that it mattered to sea wings, who

02:33:15.959 --> 02:33:17.879
could see in the dark, but her friends

02:33:17.879 --> 02:33:19.620
probably wouldn't be too thrilled about

02:33:19.620 --> 02:33:20.940
having no light either.

02:33:21.000 --> 02:33:23.459
Another argument that could wait until

02:33:23.459 --> 02:33:24.000
tomorrow.

02:33:24.059 --> 02:33:26.879
She was relieved when the queen finally

02:33:26.879 --> 02:33:29.399
came down from the council level and led

02:33:29.399 --> 02:33:30.239
her across the lake.

02:33:30.299 --> 02:33:33.180
Queen Coral's chambers at the Summer

02:33:33.180 --> 02:33:36.180
Palace were in a vast underwater cave

02:33:36.180 --> 02:33:38.579
below one of the waterfalls lined with

02:33:38.579 --> 02:33:41.100
waving tendrils of forest green and

02:33:41.100 --> 02:33:42.780
brilliant gold anemones.

02:33:42.840 --> 02:33:45.780
Stone carvings of dolphins danced around

02:33:45.780 --> 02:33:46.379
the entrance.

02:33:46.440 --> 02:33:49.139
The walls were studded with emeralds and

02:33:49.139 --> 02:33:52.020
pearls, and the beds were soft expanses

02:33:52.020 --> 02:33:53.219
of bubbly seaweed.

02:33:53.280 --> 02:33:56.219
A bed was already made up for tsunami

02:33:56.219 --> 02:33:57.299
next to anemones.

02:33:57.360 --> 02:33:59.579
She collapsed onto it with a sigh.

02:33:59.639 --> 02:34:02.159
Sleeping underwater on comfortable

02:34:02.159 --> 02:34:04.920
seaweed instead of a hard ledge of stone

02:34:04.920 --> 02:34:07.139
was even more wonderful than she'd ever

02:34:07.139 --> 02:34:07.620
imagined.

02:34:07.680 --> 02:34:10.319
She fell asleep to the sound of the

02:34:10.319 --> 02:34:12.840
waterfall splashing overhead, and didn't

02:34:12.840 --> 02:34:14.520
wake up until the next morning.

02:34:14.579 --> 02:34:17.879
When she opened her eyes.

02:34:17.940 --> 02:34:20.159
She found the pale pinkish blue head of

02:34:20.159 --> 02:34:21.540
anemone leaning over her.

02:34:21.540 --> 02:34:24.780
Tsunami yelped and leaped back, crashing

02:34:24.780 --> 02:34:26.639
into the stone wall and bouncing off it

02:34:26.639 --> 02:34:27.659
in a stream of bubbles.

02:34:27.719 --> 02:34:30.719
She had a wild, brief moment of thinking

02:34:30.719 --> 02:34:33.360
anemone had been about to kill her, and

02:34:33.360 --> 02:34:35.459
then her sister waved her talons and made

02:34:35.459 --> 02:34:36.420
a shushing gesture.

02:34:36.540 --> 02:34:40.020
Anemone pointed at Queen Coral, who was

02:34:40.020 --> 02:34:40.559
still asleep.

02:34:40.620 --> 02:34:43.440
She clasped her talons in front of her

02:34:43.440 --> 02:34:45.780
and flashed some of the stripes along her

02:34:45.780 --> 02:34:46.500
wings and tail.

02:34:46.559 --> 02:34:49.020
Sorry, little sister.

02:34:49.079 --> 02:34:51.360
Tsunami spread her front talons and shook

02:34:51.360 --> 02:34:51.600
her head.

02:34:51.659 --> 02:34:53.280
I wish I could.

02:34:53.340 --> 02:34:56.819
Anemone flashed her stripes again, then

02:34:56.819 --> 02:34:58.739
smacked her head, remembering that

02:34:58.739 --> 02:35:00.540
tsunami didn't know aquatic.

02:35:00.659 --> 02:35:02.159
She frowned in frustration.

02:35:02.219 --> 02:35:05.340
Tsunami felt equally frustrated.

02:35:05.399 --> 02:35:08.100
They couldn't sneak off to the surface to

02:35:08.100 --> 02:35:08.340
talk.

02:35:08.399 --> 02:35:10.860
Anemone was trapped here by the harness

02:35:10.860 --> 02:35:13.620
tethering her to the queen, and tsunami

02:35:13.620 --> 02:35:14.819
couldn't communicate underwater.

02:35:14.879 --> 02:35:17.340
They'd never had a chance to talk

02:35:17.340 --> 02:35:17.879
privately.

02:35:18.000 --> 02:35:20.760
She swam over to her sister and studied

02:35:20.760 --> 02:35:21.239
the harness.

02:35:21.360 --> 02:35:24.479
It was made of a stretchy, gummy, clear

02:35:24.479 --> 02:35:27.000
material that seemed to cling to anemones

02:35:27.000 --> 02:35:29.399
scales, as if it had grown along with

02:35:29.399 --> 02:35:29.639
her.

02:35:29.700 --> 02:35:33.479
It probably has, tsunami thought

02:35:33.479 --> 02:35:35.579
wondering if the poor dragonette would

02:35:35.579 --> 02:35:37.799
have to wear this until she was tsunami's

02:35:37.799 --> 02:35:39.000
age or even older.

02:35:39.059 --> 02:35:42.600
When tsunami tugged on it lightly, Anemone

02:35:42.600 --> 02:35:43.139
shook her head.

02:35:43.200 --> 02:35:45.719
She mimed trying to wriggle out of the

02:35:45.719 --> 02:35:47.760
harness and pointed to the queen again.

02:35:47.819 --> 02:35:50.940
Not possible without waking her up

02:35:50.940 --> 02:35:52.200
tsunami guessed.

02:35:52.319 --> 02:35:54.299
If it's even possible at all.

02:35:54.360 --> 02:35:57.479
Anemone carefully eased toward the

02:35:57.479 --> 02:35:59.579
entrance, glancing back at the queen.

02:35:59.639 --> 02:36:02.280
The chord between them uncoiled.

02:36:02.340 --> 02:36:04.739
The little dragonette lifted off the

02:36:04.739 --> 02:36:07.079
floor and swam up toward the top of the

02:36:07.079 --> 02:36:09.659
door, stretching the leash to its full

02:36:09.659 --> 02:36:09.959
length.

02:36:10.020 --> 02:36:12.299
She beckoned tsunami after her.

02:36:12.360 --> 02:36:15.600
Where the waterfall met the lake, just

02:36:15.600 --> 02:36:18.059
behind the cascade, and right outside the

02:36:18.059 --> 02:36:20.399
cave entrance, there was a small pocket

02:36:20.399 --> 02:36:21.059
of air.

02:36:21.180 --> 02:36:23.819
At the end of her leash, Anemone was

02:36:23.819 --> 02:36:25.680
barely able to reach it with her snout.

02:36:25.739 --> 02:36:28.139
Tsunami popped her head out beside her.

02:36:28.260 --> 02:36:32.700
Clever, Tsunami said, glancing around.

02:36:32.760 --> 02:36:34.620
Here they were also hidden from view.

02:36:34.680 --> 02:36:37.200
If any sea wings were out and about this

02:36:37.200 --> 02:36:38.459
early in the summer palace.

02:36:38.520 --> 02:36:42.059
I hope she doesn't wake up, Anemone

02:36:42.059 --> 02:36:42.360
said.

02:36:42.420 --> 02:36:44.760
She blinked at tsunami for a moment, then

02:36:44.760 --> 02:36:47.700
burst out, oh, I'm so glad you're here.

02:36:47.819 --> 02:36:50.579
She reached out one of her front talons

02:36:50.579 --> 02:36:52.500
and tsunami pressed it like they had the

02:36:52.500 --> 02:36:52.860
day before.

02:36:52.920 --> 02:36:54.479
Really?

02:36:54.540 --> 02:36:56.639
Tsunami said, astonished.

02:36:56.700 --> 02:36:58.559
But aren't we rivals?

02:36:58.620 --> 02:37:01.620
If I'm here, doesn't that threaten your

02:37:01.620 --> 02:37:02.639
chance at the throne?

02:37:02.700 --> 02:37:05.940
Maybe you can make her less crazy.

02:37:06.000 --> 02:37:08.219
Anemone said in a whisper.

02:37:08.340 --> 02:37:11.459
Or maybe she'll set me free now that she

02:37:11.459 --> 02:37:11.819
has you.

02:37:11.879 --> 02:37:13.860
Maybe you could talk to her.

02:37:13.920 --> 02:37:16.079
I need to get out of this harness.

02:37:16.139 --> 02:37:17.639
Tsunami.

02:37:17.700 --> 02:37:20.159
You have no idea how awful my life has

02:37:20.159 --> 02:37:20.399
been.

02:37:20.520 --> 02:37:24.299
Tsunami stared at her, hearing the echo

02:37:24.299 --> 02:37:25.200
of her own words.

02:37:25.319 --> 02:37:27.420
Your life has been awful?

02:37:27.420 --> 02:37:28.319
she said.

02:37:28.379 --> 02:37:30.600
You can't even imagine awful.

02:37:30.659 --> 02:37:33.059
Try being raised under a mountain with no

02:37:33.059 --> 02:37:35.819
ocean or proper sunlight and only a river

02:37:35.819 --> 02:37:36.659
to swim in.

02:37:36.780 --> 02:37:39.840
Try being raised by 3 dragons who hate

02:37:39.840 --> 02:37:42.540
you and treat you like a blobby tadpole.

02:37:42.600 --> 02:37:46.799
I am treated like a tadpole, Anemone

02:37:46.799 --> 02:37:47.340
protested.

02:37:47.399 --> 02:37:50.520
Mother doesn't trust me to do anything by

02:37:50.520 --> 02:37:50.879
myself.

02:37:50.940 --> 02:37:54.719
You're only what, one year old?

02:37:54.719 --> 02:37:55.920
tsunami guest.

02:37:55.979 --> 02:37:57.299
I'm sure that'll change.

02:37:57.360 --> 02:37:59.940
Well, I'm mostly sure.

02:38:00.000 --> 02:38:01.680
Halfway sure.

02:38:01.739 --> 02:38:03.959
And at least she cares about you.

02:38:04.020 --> 02:38:07.860
She cares about me way too much.

02:38:07.920 --> 02:38:09.479
Anemone said.

02:38:09.540 --> 02:38:11.879
I never get to do anything except

02:38:11.879 --> 02:38:13.020
whatever she's doing.

02:38:13.079 --> 02:38:14.639
At least you have friends.

02:38:14.700 --> 02:38:17.459
I never even see any other dragonettes.

02:38:17.520 --> 02:38:21.239
Well, I was sort of stuck with those four

02:38:21.239 --> 02:38:24.120
tsunami said, and they're always arguing

02:38:24.120 --> 02:38:25.500
with me or getting mad about something.

02:38:25.620 --> 02:38:28.440
She felt a pang of guilt about not

02:38:28.440 --> 02:38:29.639
visiting them the night before.

02:38:29.700 --> 02:38:32.219
They must be wondering where she'd gone.

02:38:32.280 --> 02:38:36.180
Well, maybe if they miss me for a while

02:38:36.180 --> 02:38:38.459
they'll be more pleased to see me when I

02:38:38.459 --> 02:38:39.420
do show up.

02:38:39.479 --> 02:38:41.280
They seem great.

02:38:41.399 --> 02:38:43.620
Anemone said wistfully.

02:38:43.680 --> 02:38:46.260
I always wanted brothers and sisters.

02:38:46.379 --> 02:38:48.360
Don't you have brothers?

02:38:48.479 --> 02:38:50.340
She snorted.

02:38:50.399 --> 02:38:53.459
Yes, but mother thinks they play too

02:38:53.459 --> 02:38:55.260
rough, and she won't let them near me.

02:38:55.319 --> 02:38:58.139
My cousins are all possible suspects in

02:38:58.139 --> 02:39:01.620
her mind, except Moray, who's perfect and

02:39:01.620 --> 02:39:04.440
boring and old, and can do no wrong.

02:39:04.500 --> 02:39:07.559
And non-royal dragonettes aren't special

02:39:07.559 --> 02:39:08.760
enough for me to play with.

02:39:08.879 --> 02:39:12.420
Anemone side, blowing bubbles across the

02:39:12.420 --> 02:39:13.680
water at tsunami.

02:39:13.739 --> 02:39:16.319
I guess my friends are all right when

02:39:16.319 --> 02:39:18.239
they're not complaining, tsunami

02:39:18.239 --> 02:39:18.780
admitted.

02:39:18.840 --> 02:39:20.579
They complain a lot, though.

02:39:20.700 --> 02:39:25.920
I tried complaining once, Anemone said

02:39:25.920 --> 02:39:28.979
with a stab of venom in her voice, Mother

02:39:28.979 --> 02:39:30.780
nearly got me a gag to match the

02:39:30.780 --> 02:39:31.260
harness.

02:39:31.319 --> 02:39:35.459
At least somebody loves you, tsunami said

02:39:35.459 --> 02:39:38.219
and you're with your own kind, and you

02:39:38.219 --> 02:39:39.420
know your own stupid language.

02:39:39.540 --> 02:39:43.260
She loves you too, Anemone offered.

02:39:43.319 --> 02:39:46.260
She paused, glancing down into the cave.

02:39:46.319 --> 02:39:49.799
Queen Coral was still fast asleep, her

02:39:49.799 --> 02:39:52.379
blue scales rising and falling smoothly.

02:39:52.440 --> 02:39:55.680
I hope you'll take Whirlpool, Anemone

02:39:55.680 --> 02:39:56.100
blurted.

02:39:56.159 --> 02:39:57.420
Three moons.

02:39:57.479 --> 02:40:00.059
I was so sure I'd have to marry him, but

02:40:00.059 --> 02:40:01.860
now you're here and you can have him, and

02:40:01.860 --> 02:40:02.879
that'll be much better.

02:40:03.000 --> 02:40:07.739
No way, Tsunami said, lashing her tail.

02:40:07.799 --> 02:40:09.180
No, no, no.

02:40:09.239 --> 02:40:12.600
An image of riptide flashed in her head

02:40:12.600 --> 02:40:15.059
which was ridiculous because she hardly

02:40:15.059 --> 02:40:15.719
knew him either.

02:40:15.780 --> 02:40:17.579
Absolutely not.

02:40:17.639 --> 02:40:19.860
First of all, I don't have time to get

02:40:19.860 --> 02:40:20.159
married.

02:40:20.219 --> 02:40:22.500
I have to stop the war and save the

02:40:22.500 --> 02:40:22.739
world.

02:40:22.799 --> 02:40:26.040
And or learn how to be queen of the sea

02:40:26.040 --> 02:40:26.520
wings.

02:40:26.579 --> 02:40:29.459
Second of all, that dragon?

02:40:29.520 --> 02:40:31.020
No, thank you.

02:40:31.079 --> 02:40:33.299
I'd rather have my tail nibbled off by

02:40:33.299 --> 02:40:34.260
snapping turtles.

02:40:34.319 --> 02:40:36.420
Anemone giggled.

02:40:36.540 --> 02:40:38.819
He's dreadful, isn't he?

02:40:38.879 --> 02:40:42.840
You are smaller in the Hudges to his

02:40:42.899 --> 02:40:45.840
tsunami smarmed, imitating his fake grin

02:40:45.840 --> 02:40:46.680
and tiny bow.

02:40:46.739 --> 02:40:49.680
Anemone had to stick her head under the

02:40:49.680 --> 02:40:51.540
water so her giggling wouldn't shake the

02:40:51.540 --> 02:40:52.739
harness and wake the queen.

02:40:52.799 --> 02:40:56.520
Anyway, mother can't decide who we marry

02:40:56.520 --> 02:40:57.659
tsunami said.

02:40:57.719 --> 02:40:58.920
Really?

02:40:58.979 --> 02:41:00.840
Anemone said doubtfully.

02:41:00.899 --> 02:41:03.059
She gets to decide everything else.

02:41:03.180 --> 02:41:06.959
We're royalty, tsunami pointed out

02:41:06.959 --> 02:41:09.180
meaning we do whatever we want.

02:41:09.239 --> 02:41:10.799
Gosh.

02:41:10.860 --> 02:41:14.219
That is not what I've seen, Anemone

02:41:14.219 --> 02:41:14.520
said.

02:41:14.579 --> 02:41:18.360
More like, we're royalty, so we only get

02:41:18.360 --> 02:41:20.579
to do what historical sea wing queens

02:41:20.579 --> 02:41:22.739
would approve of us doing, for the good

02:41:22.739 --> 02:41:24.899
of our subjects, for the honor of the

02:41:24.899 --> 02:41:28.139
throne, for the yawn claw meter death

02:41:28.139 --> 02:41:28.620
already.

02:41:28.739 --> 02:41:31.799
Tsunami laughed, but her gills felt

02:41:31.799 --> 02:41:33.659
choked, and her scales prickled

02:41:33.659 --> 02:41:34.260
uncomfortably.

02:41:34.319 --> 02:41:36.899
She'd never thought of royalty that way.

02:41:36.959 --> 02:41:39.540
Did queens really have to worry about

02:41:39.540 --> 02:41:42.000
honor and other dragons' approval?

02:41:42.059 --> 02:41:46.079
What would happen if a sea wing queen, or

02:41:46.079 --> 02:41:50.700
potential queen, decided to say, marry

02:41:50.700 --> 02:41:52.559
someone the rest of the tribe disapproved

02:41:52.559 --> 02:41:52.799
of?

02:41:52.860 --> 02:41:55.440
Or chose not to get married at all?

02:41:55.500 --> 02:41:58.500
It would be harder to rule subjects who

02:41:58.500 --> 02:41:59.280
didn't respect you.

02:41:59.340 --> 02:42:01.739
Tsunami had enough trouble with her usual

02:42:01.739 --> 02:42:02.219
for.

02:42:02.219 --> 02:42:05.399
She imagined a whole grumbling tribe full

02:42:05.399 --> 02:42:07.260
of glories and starflights.

02:42:07.319 --> 02:42:09.780
But no one would dare argue with the

02:42:09.780 --> 02:42:11.159
queen, would they?

02:42:11.219 --> 02:42:13.979
Maybe it depended on the kind of queen

02:42:13.979 --> 02:42:14.520
you were.

02:42:14.579 --> 02:42:17.459
No one argued with Scarlet in the Sky

02:42:17.459 --> 02:42:18.540
Wings, that was for sure.

02:42:18.600 --> 02:42:22.260
But Scarlet was murderous and insane.

02:42:22.319 --> 02:42:24.600
Not exactly the role model I want to

02:42:24.600 --> 02:42:24.840
follow.

02:42:24.899 --> 02:42:27.899
She stretched her wings out to feel the

02:42:27.899 --> 02:42:29.159
splashing of the waterfall.

02:42:29.219 --> 02:42:32.100
Outside their hidden spot, she could hear

02:42:32.100 --> 02:42:34.079
the quiet noises of the summer palace

02:42:34.079 --> 02:42:34.500
waking up.

02:42:34.620 --> 02:42:37.500
Dragon wings fluttered overhead.

02:42:37.559 --> 02:42:40.260
Bubbles burbled up from underwater caves

02:42:40.260 --> 02:42:41.819
where most of the sea wings were

02:42:41.819 --> 02:42:42.120
sleeping.

02:42:42.180 --> 02:42:44.760
Pots clattered on the kitchen level of

02:42:44.760 --> 02:42:46.860
the pavilion, reminding her of how hungry

02:42:46.860 --> 02:42:47.399
she was.

02:42:47.459 --> 02:42:51.780
Uh-oh, Anemone whispered, glancing down.

02:42:51.840 --> 02:42:53.639
I think she's waking up.

02:42:53.760 --> 02:42:55.020
We'd better go back in.

02:42:55.079 --> 02:42:57.479
Tsunami hesitated.

02:42:57.540 --> 02:42:59.520
Should she go visit her friends now?

02:42:59.579 --> 02:43:02.040
But what would her mother think if she

02:43:02.040 --> 02:43:04.379
woke up and found tsunami gone?

02:43:04.440 --> 02:43:06.299
All right, she said.

02:43:06.360 --> 02:43:08.280
But I have one more question.

02:43:08.340 --> 02:43:10.260
What happened to Orca?

02:43:10.319 --> 02:43:13.379
If Anemone could tell her, she could put

02:43:13.379 --> 02:43:15.899
off going to ask Starfight about it

02:43:15.899 --> 02:43:18.719
Anemone's pink tinted wings shivered

02:43:18.719 --> 02:43:19.319
under the water.

02:43:19.319 --> 02:43:23.100
She challenged mother for the throne when

02:43:23.100 --> 02:43:26.100
she was only 7 years old, she whispered.

02:43:26.219 --> 02:43:28.500
Everyone says it was horrible.

02:43:28.559 --> 02:43:30.420
She nearly won.

02:43:30.479 --> 02:43:32.459
But mother killed her in the end.

02:43:32.579 --> 02:43:35.100
She glanced down again.

02:43:35.159 --> 02:43:36.420
It's weird.

02:43:36.479 --> 02:43:39.299
Mother worships her and misses her.

02:43:39.299 --> 02:43:43.139
But lots of dragons still hate Orca for

02:43:43.139 --> 02:43:44.340
nearly killing their queen.

02:43:44.459 --> 02:43:47.520
Don't ever mention her name around

02:43:47.520 --> 02:43:48.239
Moray.

02:43:48.299 --> 02:43:51.479
Moray tsunami echoed.

02:43:51.540 --> 02:43:52.620
She seems...

02:43:52.620 --> 02:43:56.579
Trippy, fatuous, about as interesting as

02:43:56.579 --> 02:43:59.819
sea slime, I was going to say odd.

02:43:59.879 --> 02:44:02.219
Tsunami laughed, but those work too.

02:44:02.280 --> 02:44:03.899
Uh-oh.

02:44:03.959 --> 02:44:06.120
Anemone vanished below the water.

02:44:06.239 --> 02:44:09.059
Tsunami followed her, swimming back to

02:44:09.059 --> 02:44:11.280
her bed a few moments before Queen Coral

02:44:11.280 --> 02:44:11.940
opened her eyes.

02:44:12.000 --> 02:44:15.180
The queen sat up and stirred the water

02:44:15.180 --> 02:44:17.340
with her wings as she stretched.

02:44:17.399 --> 02:44:20.040
She beamed at tsunami and anemone

02:44:20.040 --> 02:44:22.079
reaching to stroke their heads gently

02:44:22.079 --> 02:44:22.799
with her talons.

02:44:22.860 --> 02:44:26.100
The queen gathered her strands of pearls

02:44:26.100 --> 02:44:27.719
from the coral branch where they'd hung

02:44:27.719 --> 02:44:28.860
during the night.

02:44:28.920 --> 02:44:30.959
Carefully she draped them around herself

02:44:30.959 --> 02:44:33.479
again, then decorated anemone the same

02:44:33.479 --> 02:44:33.659
way.

02:44:33.719 --> 02:44:37.079
Tsunami hadn't taken off the one she'd

02:44:37.079 --> 02:44:37.860
been given the day before.

02:44:37.920 --> 02:44:40.979
Her mother smiled at this, and produced

02:44:40.979 --> 02:44:42.899
another long strand of pearls.

02:44:42.959 --> 02:44:46.200
These, a shimmering pale purple and oddly

02:44:46.200 --> 02:44:48.059
shaped instead of round.

02:44:48.120 --> 02:44:51.299
With expert talons, Queen Coral wound

02:44:51.299 --> 02:44:53.459
them around tsunami's, chest and wings.

02:44:53.579 --> 02:44:54.959
They were beautiful.

02:44:55.079 --> 02:44:56.879
But it was strange to have something

02:44:56.879 --> 02:44:57.780
weighing her down.

02:44:57.840 --> 02:45:00.959
Tsunami felt almost as if she was wearing

02:45:00.959 --> 02:45:02.100
a harness of treasure.

02:45:02.159 --> 02:45:04.379
She wasn't about to complain, though.

02:45:04.440 --> 02:45:06.719
The talons of peace had never given the

02:45:06.719 --> 02:45:07.979
dragonettes beautiful things.

02:45:08.040 --> 02:45:10.860
Finally, the queen beckoned for them to

02:45:10.860 --> 02:45:12.120
follow her to the pavilion.

02:45:12.180 --> 02:45:15.299
Tsunami wasn't sure how she felt about

02:45:15.299 --> 02:45:17.940
being treated the same as anemone, a one

02:45:17.940 --> 02:45:20.280
year old dragonette, but she did like how

02:45:20.280 --> 02:45:22.500
her mother kept patting her, as if she

02:45:22.500 --> 02:45:24.299
wanted to make sure tsunami was real.

02:45:24.360 --> 02:45:27.899
As they flew up to the pavilion, tsunami

02:45:27.899 --> 02:45:29.879
saw several guards clustered on one of

02:45:29.879 --> 02:45:32.280
the lowest levels, half of them sleeping

02:45:32.280 --> 02:45:33.899
and half of them drinking something

02:45:33.899 --> 02:45:37.200
steaming out of handheld cauldrons, she

02:45:37.200 --> 02:45:39.420
noticed that they looked well fed, well

02:45:39.420 --> 02:45:42.479
rested, and content, not thin and grumpy

02:45:42.479 --> 02:45:44.459
like Queen Scarlet's guards in the Sky

02:45:44.459 --> 02:45:45.659
Wing Palace.

02:45:45.719 --> 02:45:48.059
Proof that my mother is a better queen

02:45:48.059 --> 02:45:50.219
than Scarlet, tsunami thought.

02:45:50.280 --> 02:45:53.100
When Queen Coral landed on the council

02:45:53.100 --> 02:45:55.860
level, a flurry of wing beats sounded all

02:45:55.860 --> 02:45:56.940
over the palace.

02:45:57.239 --> 02:46:00.239
Council members swept down from caves or

02:46:00.239 --> 02:46:01.739
surged up from the water below.

02:46:01.799 --> 02:46:05.100
Coral settled herself in the largest pool

02:46:05.100 --> 02:46:06.479
which was labeled Queen.

02:46:06.540 --> 02:46:09.000
She tugged anemone into the water with

02:46:09.000 --> 02:46:11.340
her, although it was a bit of a squeeze

02:46:11.340 --> 02:46:13.379
and the little dragonette had to curl

02:46:13.379 --> 02:46:14.399
under the queen's wing.

02:46:14.520 --> 02:46:19.319
Mother, Anemone protested, quit squashing

02:46:19.319 --> 02:46:19.979
me.

02:46:20.280 --> 02:46:22.319
She wriggled around until there was a

02:46:22.319 --> 02:46:23.280
little more space for her.

02:46:23.340 --> 02:46:27.120
Small turquoise dragons darted in with

02:46:27.120 --> 02:46:29.340
platters of food, laying them all around

02:46:29.340 --> 02:46:31.799
the pools as council members slipped into

02:46:31.799 --> 02:46:32.219
their places.

02:46:32.280 --> 02:46:35.579
Tsunami stood awkwardly to the side.

02:46:35.639 --> 02:46:37.620
She felt like her tail and wings were in

02:46:37.620 --> 02:46:38.159
the way of everything.

02:46:38.219 --> 02:46:42.420
Oh, said Queen Coral, finally noticing.

02:46:42.420 --> 02:46:44.879
Tsunami, you can sit there.

02:46:44.940 --> 02:46:47.280
Tortoise is guarding the hatry at the

02:46:47.280 --> 02:46:49.260
deep palace, so she won't be joining us

02:46:49.260 --> 02:46:49.620
today.

02:46:49.680 --> 02:46:53.159
The queen pointed her claw at a pool 2

02:46:53.159 --> 02:46:55.860
down from hers, labeled Dragonette Care

02:46:55.860 --> 02:46:56.879
in Tiny Emeralds.

02:46:56.940 --> 02:46:59.819
The Wetstone was chilly under tsunami's

02:46:59.819 --> 02:47:01.020
talons as she climbed into it.

02:47:01.079 --> 02:47:03.899
The pools on either side of the queen

02:47:03.899 --> 02:47:06.780
said, defense and communication.

02:47:06.840 --> 02:47:10.319
Shark splashed down in the 1st one, and a

02:47:10.319 --> 02:47:12.239
moment later, Moray landed in the other.

02:47:12.360 --> 02:47:16.079
Good morning, Your Majesty, Moray said

02:47:16.079 --> 02:47:17.819
bowing and dipping her wings.

02:47:17.879 --> 02:47:20.159
I know yesterday it was a shocking day

02:47:20.159 --> 02:47:21.659
but I hope you slept well.

02:47:21.719 --> 02:47:23.459
I worried about you all night.

02:47:23.520 --> 02:47:26.940
Thank you, dear, said the Queen.

02:47:27.000 --> 02:47:29.219
Her eyes were scanning the rest of the

02:47:29.219 --> 02:47:29.579
council.

02:47:29.700 --> 02:47:32.219
Whirlpool flew up beside Moray.

02:47:32.280 --> 02:47:34.680
His pool was labeled Magic and

02:47:34.680 --> 02:47:35.399
Publishing.

02:47:35.459 --> 02:47:37.440
Tsunami tilted her head at him.

02:47:37.500 --> 02:47:40.200
How did one become an expert in either of

02:47:40.200 --> 02:47:40.860
those things?

02:47:40.920 --> 02:47:42.899
What kind of magic did he know anything

02:47:42.899 --> 02:47:43.260
about?

02:47:43.319 --> 02:47:46.739
She glanced around, wondering if there

02:47:46.739 --> 02:47:48.899
was a pull for the king, but she didn't

02:47:48.899 --> 02:47:49.139
see one.

02:47:49.200 --> 02:47:51.840
Queen Coral hadn't said anything about

02:47:51.840 --> 02:47:54.479
tsunami's father yesterday, and in all

02:47:54.479 --> 02:47:56.459
the excitement about Kestrel's body

02:47:56.459 --> 02:47:58.139
tsunami hadn't had a chance to ask.

02:47:58.200 --> 02:48:00.780
Maybe he was at the deep palace.

02:48:00.840 --> 02:48:02.700
Maybe she could meet him later today.

02:48:02.760 --> 02:48:05.819
She remembered some of the council from

02:48:05.819 --> 02:48:06.360
the day before.

02:48:06.420 --> 02:48:09.600
The plump dragon Lagoon, who'd been sent

02:48:09.600 --> 02:48:12.059
to feed the other dragonettes, sat in a

02:48:12.059 --> 02:48:13.559
pool marked Aquaculture.

02:48:13.620 --> 02:48:16.559
Piranha, the one who'd gone with shark to

02:48:16.559 --> 02:48:19.319
examine and dispose of Kestrel's body, was

02:48:19.319 --> 02:48:19.860
in war.

02:48:19.920 --> 02:48:22.379
Tsunami didn't know any of the other

02:48:22.379 --> 02:48:25.079
dragon's names, but from where she sat

02:48:25.079 --> 02:48:28.200
she could see the labels Treasury, Justice

02:48:28.200 --> 02:48:28.920
and Hunting.

02:48:28.979 --> 02:48:32.280
She didn't really understand this council

02:48:32.280 --> 02:48:32.760
business.

02:48:32.819 --> 02:48:35.399
She wasn't sure what they did or why they

02:48:35.399 --> 02:48:35.940
were necessary.

02:48:36.000 --> 02:48:38.639
Wasn't it enough to have a queen?

02:48:38.700 --> 02:48:40.680
Couldn't Coral just decide everything

02:48:40.680 --> 02:48:41.219
herself?

02:48:41.280 --> 02:48:44.639
That's what I do, she thought.

02:48:44.700 --> 02:48:47.700
I'll get rid of this council and run the

02:48:47.700 --> 02:48:49.020
tribe like a proper queen.

02:48:49.079 --> 02:48:52.379
Maybe it worked for Coral, but tsunami

02:48:52.379 --> 02:48:54.959
didn't need or want 11 dragons following

02:48:54.959 --> 02:48:57.659
her around offering advice all the time.

02:48:57.719 --> 02:49:00.239
Her stomach rumbled, and she tried to

02:49:00.239 --> 02:49:01.920
remember when she'd last eaten.

02:49:01.979 --> 02:49:04.500
The platters around her were loaded with

02:49:04.500 --> 02:49:07.500
raw, ruby red fish, most of it sliced and

02:49:07.500 --> 02:49:09.959
deboned, and arranged into fancy rolls

02:49:09.959 --> 02:49:10.680
with seaweed.

02:49:10.739 --> 02:49:13.620
She'd only ever eaten fish raw and whole

02:49:13.620 --> 02:49:16.079
or sometimes scorched when her friends

02:49:16.079 --> 02:49:17.700
decided to set their dinner on fire.

02:49:17.760 --> 02:49:21.360
A few cauldrons held seething mountains

02:49:21.360 --> 02:49:22.799
of tiny green crabs.

02:49:22.860 --> 02:49:25.680
Three large bowls contained some kind of

02:49:25.680 --> 02:49:28.620
salad of octopus tentacles and herbs that

02:49:28.620 --> 02:49:29.819
tsunami had never seen before.

02:49:29.879 --> 02:49:32.879
She plucked out one of the tentacles and

02:49:32.879 --> 02:49:33.360
tasted it.

02:49:33.479 --> 02:49:36.479
It was rubbery but sweet, with a tang

02:49:36.479 --> 02:49:37.559
like lemons and salt.

02:49:37.680 --> 02:49:40.799
She reached for another one and realized

02:49:40.799 --> 02:49:42.899
the whole council was staring at her.

02:49:42.959 --> 02:49:45.360
Nobody else had started eating yet.

02:49:45.420 --> 02:49:47.219
Oops.

02:49:47.280 --> 02:49:50.459
All the council eyes swiveled toward the

02:49:50.459 --> 02:49:52.440
queen, who was staring at the bit of

02:49:52.440 --> 02:49:54.239
octopus in tsunami's claws.

02:49:54.239 --> 02:49:56.340
Carl shook herself and smiled.

02:49:56.399 --> 02:49:58.260
It's all right.

02:49:58.319 --> 02:50:00.899
The queen said, clapping her talons

02:50:00.899 --> 02:50:01.260
together.

02:50:01.319 --> 02:50:04.139
Naturally, I forgive my long lost

02:50:04.139 --> 02:50:06.780
daughter any accidental impudence.

02:50:06.840 --> 02:50:09.000
As we all know, she was raised by

02:50:09.000 --> 02:50:11.520
barbarians, so she couldn't know any

02:50:11.520 --> 02:50:11.760
better.

02:50:11.819 --> 02:50:14.100
I give you all permission to eat.

02:50:14.159 --> 02:50:17.219
Tsunami crushed the tentacle between her

02:50:17.219 --> 02:50:17.700
claws.

02:50:17.760 --> 02:50:19.979
Raised by barbarians?

02:50:20.040 --> 02:50:23.520
Perhaps it was true, but what a thing to

02:50:23.520 --> 02:50:25.799
say to tsunami's future subjects.

02:50:25.979 --> 02:50:28.139
They'd think of her as the dragon who

02:50:28.139 --> 02:50:30.059
knew nothing about sea wing customs.

02:50:30.120 --> 02:50:31.920
How would she ever earn their respect

02:50:31.920 --> 02:50:33.659
with that reputation?

02:50:33.719 --> 02:50:36.780
Was Coral deliberately making tsunami

02:50:36.780 --> 02:50:38.159
look foolish in front of the other

02:50:38.159 --> 02:50:38.700
dragons?

02:50:38.760 --> 02:50:42.120
Tsunami studied her mother, while Coral

02:50:42.120 --> 02:50:43.920
helped herself to the largest pieces of

02:50:43.920 --> 02:50:46.379
fish and crunched through talonfuls of

02:50:46.379 --> 02:50:46.799
crabs.

02:50:46.860 --> 02:50:49.559
She dropped bits of food into Anemones

02:50:49.559 --> 02:50:50.700
open mouth as she ate.

02:50:50.760 --> 02:50:52.440
Maybe not.

02:50:52.500 --> 02:50:55.020
Maybe tsunami was seeing problems where

02:50:55.020 --> 02:50:55.739
there weren't any.

02:50:55.799 --> 02:50:59.280
But maybe, it wouldn't hurt to be a

02:50:59.280 --> 02:51:00.780
little more careful from now on.

02:51:00.840 --> 02:51:05.159
Chapter 11.

02:51:05.520 --> 02:51:10.200
Pearl, report, ordered the queen, after

02:51:10.200 --> 02:51:12.059
the dragons had eaten in silence for a

02:51:12.059 --> 02:51:12.239
while.

02:51:12.299 --> 02:51:16.200
No change, said the elegant pale green

02:51:16.200 --> 02:51:17.520
dragon in the treasury pool.

02:51:17.579 --> 02:51:20.159
All your jewels are safe, as always.

02:51:20.219 --> 02:51:22.860
No scavengers can get to them, and no

02:51:22.860 --> 02:51:23.940
dragon would dare to try.

02:51:24.000 --> 02:51:26.940
Splendid, said Coral.

02:51:27.059 --> 02:51:29.219
She abended the last of a cauldron of

02:51:29.219 --> 02:51:30.059
crabs into her mouth.

02:51:30.120 --> 02:51:32.219
Shark, report.

02:51:32.280 --> 02:51:36.540
I am concerned about our defenses, snarled

02:51:36.540 --> 02:51:37.500
the gray green dragon.

02:51:37.559 --> 02:51:39.420
He glared at tsunami.

02:51:39.479 --> 02:51:42.780
The intruders in our midst are danger to

02:51:42.780 --> 02:51:42.959
us.

02:51:43.020 --> 02:51:45.540
We have no idea whether they might have

02:51:45.540 --> 02:51:48.120
led others to our palace, or what they

02:51:48.120 --> 02:51:48.899
might be planning.

02:51:48.959 --> 02:51:53.520
Now, now, said the Queen, those are our

02:51:53.520 --> 02:51:55.319
guests, not intruders.

02:51:55.379 --> 02:51:57.719
If my daughter trusts them, then, of

02:51:57.719 --> 02:51:58.500
course, I do too.

02:51:58.620 --> 02:52:03.180
Oh, good, tsunami said quickly, because I

02:52:03.180 --> 02:52:04.860
was thinking maybe they could join us for

02:52:04.860 --> 02:52:05.579
breakfast.

02:52:05.639 --> 02:52:07.799
I'm sure they're hungry, and if they

02:52:07.799 --> 02:52:09.659
could see that they're really welcome

02:52:09.659 --> 02:52:09.959
here.

02:52:10.020 --> 02:52:12.959
She trailed off as Coral shook her head.

02:52:13.020 --> 02:52:16.500
Only council members and royalty are

02:52:16.500 --> 02:52:18.059
allowed at council meetings, darling

02:52:18.059 --> 02:52:21.420
Queen Coral said, running one claw along

02:52:21.420 --> 02:52:22.440
a strand of her pearls.

02:52:22.500 --> 02:52:24.840
But they certainly won't go hungry.

02:52:24.959 --> 02:52:27.239
Lagoon, did you make sure they were

02:52:27.239 --> 02:52:28.559
served an ample breakfast?

02:52:28.620 --> 02:52:31.200
The turquoise dragon nodded.

02:52:31.260 --> 02:52:33.540
They can have the rest of this as well.

02:52:33.600 --> 02:52:36.360
Queen Coral waved her talons at the

02:52:36.360 --> 02:52:37.379
breakfast leftovers.

02:52:37.440 --> 02:52:40.860
The same small dragons from before, darted

02:52:40.860 --> 02:52:42.719
up from the kitchen level, collected the

02:52:42.719 --> 02:52:44.579
platters, and flew down to the cave with

02:52:44.579 --> 02:52:44.760
them.

02:52:44.879 --> 02:52:47.639
Tsunami watched over the edge of the

02:52:47.639 --> 02:52:48.299
pavilion.

02:52:48.360 --> 02:52:50.340
None of our friends even poked their

02:52:50.340 --> 02:52:52.500
heads out, where they sulking in there?

02:52:52.559 --> 02:52:54.180
Were they still mad at her?

02:52:54.239 --> 02:52:57.780
Well, she was doing a fine enough job of

02:52:57.780 --> 02:52:58.799
embarrassing herself.

02:52:58.799 --> 02:53:00.659
She didn't need them to come out and

02:53:00.659 --> 02:53:00.959
help.

02:53:01.020 --> 02:53:04.379
Raised by barbarians, friends with other

02:53:04.379 --> 02:53:07.260
tribes, not the stuff most queens were

02:53:07.260 --> 02:53:07.559
made of.

02:53:07.620 --> 02:53:12.299
Whirlpool report. said the queen, smiling

02:53:12.299 --> 02:53:12.719
at him.

02:53:12.780 --> 02:53:15.780
Whirlpool touched the hoop in his ear and

02:53:15.780 --> 02:53:16.559
flared his wings.

02:53:16.620 --> 02:53:22.200
Anemones lessons are going wonderfully, he

02:53:22.200 --> 02:53:22.500
said.

02:53:22.559 --> 02:53:25.379
Tsunami wasn't sure why his voice was so

02:53:25.379 --> 02:53:26.340
irritating.

02:53:26.399 --> 02:53:28.739
But it felt like claws scraping on stone

02:53:28.739 --> 02:53:29.700
to listen to him.

02:53:29.700 --> 02:53:33.719
And your scrolls have never been more

02:53:33.719 --> 02:53:34.379
popular.

02:53:34.440 --> 02:53:38.159
The latest has been bought by every

02:53:38.159 --> 02:53:40.979
single sea wing in the tribe.

02:53:41.100 --> 02:53:44.100
Mostly the underwater editions.

02:53:44.159 --> 02:53:45.719
Moray jumped in.

02:53:45.780 --> 02:53:47.159
Those tend to sell the best.

02:53:47.219 --> 02:53:49.079
Of course, I spend all my energy

02:53:49.079 --> 02:53:49.979
promoting them.

02:53:50.040 --> 02:53:54.120
But I've organized another reading.

02:53:54.180 --> 02:53:57.180
Whirlpool interrupted.

02:53:57.239 --> 02:54:01.079
Every high ranking dragon is clamoring to

02:54:01.079 --> 02:54:01.500
attend.

02:54:01.559 --> 02:54:05.819
We're charging an emerald apiece this

02:54:05.819 --> 02:54:06.120
time.

02:54:06.180 --> 02:54:09.659
Queen Coral waved her tail thoughtfully.

02:54:09.719 --> 02:54:13.079
I want to be sure, I'm reaching the eel

02:54:13.079 --> 02:54:16.379
eating masses as well, though, she said.

02:54:16.440 --> 02:54:18.840
I mean, my writing should be shared with

02:54:18.840 --> 02:54:21.000
everyone, not just those who can afford

02:54:21.000 --> 02:54:21.239
it.

02:54:21.299 --> 02:54:23.159
Of course.

02:54:23.219 --> 02:54:24.600
Moray said.

02:54:24.659 --> 02:54:26.399
That's why the schools have all changed

02:54:26.399 --> 02:54:28.860
their curriculums again, to be sure the

02:54:28.860 --> 02:54:30.479
dragonettes have enough time to read

02:54:30.479 --> 02:54:31.920
everything you've written.

02:54:31.979 --> 02:54:34.319
It's the most important subject they

02:54:34.319 --> 02:54:34.680
study.

02:54:34.739 --> 02:54:39.420
You can't be serious, tsunami burst out.

02:54:39.479 --> 02:54:40.680
More important than how to fight the

02:54:40.680 --> 02:54:40.860
war?

02:54:40.920 --> 02:54:43.739
Cold, silence.

02:54:43.799 --> 02:54:47.459
Queen Coral pressed a talent to a chest

02:54:47.459 --> 02:54:48.239
looking injured.

02:54:48.299 --> 02:54:52.379
Darling, my riding is about everything.

02:54:52.440 --> 02:54:55.139
As you would know if you'd finished the

02:54:55.139 --> 02:54:56.280
scrolls I gave you yesterday.

02:54:56.340 --> 02:54:58.200
What did you think of them?

02:54:58.260 --> 02:55:01.860
Tsunami guiltily remembered the scrolls

02:55:01.860 --> 02:55:04.020
she'd tossed aside as they flew off to

02:55:04.020 --> 02:55:05.040
see Kestrel's body.

02:55:05.100 --> 02:55:07.260
She hadn't even gone back to the library

02:55:07.260 --> 02:55:08.159
to get them.

02:55:08.219 --> 02:55:10.979
Uh, she mumbled.

02:55:11.040 --> 02:55:13.680
The missing princess is still my

02:55:13.680 --> 02:55:14.100
favorite.

02:55:14.219 --> 02:55:16.979
A chuckle ran around the assembled

02:55:16.979 --> 02:55:17.819
dragons.

02:55:17.879 --> 02:55:20.219
Tsunami felt hot with embarrassment.

02:55:20.280 --> 02:55:22.319
Councils were so stupid.

02:55:22.379 --> 02:55:25.139
She would never, ever have something like

02:55:25.139 --> 02:55:26.399
this when she was queen.

02:55:26.459 --> 02:55:29.940
That reminds me. said the queen.

02:55:30.000 --> 02:55:33.180
Whirlpool, tsunami needs lessons in

02:55:33.180 --> 02:55:33.600
aquatic.

02:55:33.659 --> 02:55:36.000
Can you believe she never learned it?

02:55:36.059 --> 02:55:37.559
Poor thing.

02:55:37.620 --> 02:55:40.440
She tapped her claws on the stone in

02:55:40.440 --> 02:55:40.979
front of her.

02:55:41.040 --> 02:55:44.040
Such a sad upbringing.

02:55:44.100 --> 02:55:47.700
Her face was sympathetic, but her stripes

02:55:47.700 --> 02:55:49.860
were flashing, and Tsunami wondered

02:55:49.860 --> 02:55:51.239
angrily if she was saying something

02:55:51.239 --> 02:55:53.940
different to the council, knowing Tsunami

02:55:53.940 --> 02:55:54.540
couldn't understand.

02:55:54.600 --> 02:55:58.799
Of course, Your Majesty.

02:55:58.860 --> 02:56:00.780
Whirlpool said.

02:56:00.840 --> 02:56:03.239
He inclined his head towards tsunami.

02:56:03.299 --> 02:56:06.840
I would be happy to instruct the

02:56:06.840 --> 02:56:07.620
princess.

02:56:07.739 --> 02:56:10.200
Piranha, report.

02:56:10.260 --> 02:56:13.200
Queen Carl snapped her head around to the

02:56:13.200 --> 02:56:13.860
warpool.

02:56:13.920 --> 02:56:17.040
The war commander was so clawed up that

02:56:17.040 --> 02:56:19.440
she seemed to be more scars than scales.

02:56:19.500 --> 02:56:22.500
One horn was snapped in half and several

02:56:22.500 --> 02:56:23.520
of her teeth were broken.

02:56:23.579 --> 02:56:26.579
Still no information about the dead sky

02:56:26.579 --> 02:56:27.120
wing.

02:56:27.180 --> 02:56:28.440
Piranha growled.

02:56:28.500 --> 02:56:30.600
Tsunami ducked her head.

02:56:30.659 --> 02:56:33.059
Eventually, she had to tell her mother

02:56:33.059 --> 02:56:36.600
the truth, who Kestrel was, how tsunami

02:56:36.600 --> 02:56:37.020
knew her.

02:56:37.079 --> 02:56:39.780
But she didn't want a harness attached to

02:56:39.780 --> 02:56:42.780
her, or some kind of permanent guard, and

02:56:42.780 --> 02:56:44.040
she felt like she should tell her friends

02:56:44.040 --> 02:56:44.579
first.

02:56:44.639 --> 02:56:47.639
I'll tell her later, I will.

02:56:47.700 --> 02:56:50.639
A war party returned early this morning.

02:56:50.700 --> 02:56:52.020
Hirana went on.

02:56:52.079 --> 02:56:53.819
Do you want to hear their report?

02:56:53.879 --> 02:56:56.280
Queen Carl sighed and gestured with her

02:56:56.280 --> 02:56:56.700
claws?

02:56:56.760 --> 02:57:00.360
Piranha culed over the edge, and 2

02:57:00.360 --> 02:57:02.520
soldier sea wings came flying up from a

02:57:02.520 --> 02:57:03.000
lower level.

02:57:03.059 --> 02:57:06.780
One was too injured to fly, so the other

02:57:06.780 --> 02:57:07.379
supported him.

02:57:07.440 --> 02:57:10.260
They spiraled in a jerking, awkward

02:57:10.260 --> 02:57:12.540
motion and landed heavily in the center

02:57:12.540 --> 02:57:13.500
of the council meeting.

02:57:13.559 --> 02:57:16.860
The sea wing who couldn't fly, had long

02:57:16.860 --> 02:57:19.680
burned along his side, and one wing was

02:57:19.680 --> 02:57:21.420
scorched almost entirely black.

02:57:21.479 --> 02:57:24.659
Claw marks along his underbelly were

02:57:24.659 --> 02:57:27.420
still oozing blood, which dripped into

02:57:27.420 --> 02:57:29.100
the sparkling channels between the

02:57:29.100 --> 02:57:31.559
council dragons, staining the pearls

02:57:31.559 --> 02:57:32.219
red.

02:57:32.280 --> 02:57:34.799
Tsunami saw the queen give her decorated

02:57:34.799 --> 02:57:36.239
floor a concerned look.

02:57:36.299 --> 02:57:39.479
The other sea wing had a scorch mark in

02:57:39.479 --> 02:57:41.399
the middle of his tail, and a horrible

02:57:41.399 --> 02:57:42.479
gash in his neck.

02:57:42.540 --> 02:57:45.479
He was breathing heavily, and bubbles of

02:57:45.479 --> 02:57:47.819
pale red blood foamed out of his gills.

02:57:47.879 --> 02:57:49.799
Let's hear it.

02:57:49.860 --> 02:57:51.780
Queen Coral ordered.

02:57:51.840 --> 02:57:55.319
Something strange is happening in the Sky

02:57:55.319 --> 02:57:57.420
Kingdom, Your Majesty, said the one who

02:57:57.420 --> 02:57:57.899
couldn't fly.

02:57:57.959 --> 02:58:01.739
The battalions, it's as if nobody knows

02:58:01.739 --> 02:58:02.940
who's in charge.

02:58:03.000 --> 02:58:05.639
We were patrolling the outer islands, and

02:58:05.639 --> 02:58:07.559
we were attacked by 3 separate wings.

02:58:07.620 --> 02:58:10.620
The 1st squadron was half sky wings and

02:58:10.620 --> 02:58:13.620
half sand wings during the 2nd attack.

02:58:13.680 --> 02:58:17.459
We heard the Skywings yelling, For Ruby.

02:58:17.520 --> 02:58:21.000
And in the 3rd, at least one dragon

02:58:21.000 --> 02:58:23.579
shouted, the queen is not dead.

02:58:23.639 --> 02:58:25.500
Long live the queen.

02:58:25.620 --> 02:58:29.159
Queen Carl sat forward, splashing water

02:58:29.159 --> 02:58:31.379
over the edge of the pool, and squashing

02:58:31.379 --> 02:58:32.459
anemone over to the side.

02:58:32.520 --> 02:58:34.920
For Ruby?

02:58:35.040 --> 02:58:36.059
She echoed.

02:58:36.120 --> 02:58:39.180
One of Scarlett's daughters, growled

02:58:39.180 --> 02:58:39.780
Piranha.

02:58:39.840 --> 02:58:41.940
Does that mean Queen Scarlet is dead?

02:58:42.000 --> 02:58:45.299
Tsunami clenched and unclenched her

02:58:45.299 --> 02:58:45.659
talons.

02:58:45.719 --> 02:58:48.180
How much should she tell the council?

02:58:48.239 --> 02:58:50.579
She didn't want to reveal Glory's secret

02:58:50.579 --> 02:58:51.059
weapon.

02:58:51.120 --> 02:58:53.219
They never knew when they might need it.

02:58:53.280 --> 02:58:55.799
And they weren't even sure glory had

02:58:55.799 --> 02:58:57.600
killed Queen Scarlet during the escape.

02:58:57.659 --> 02:59:00.420
We would have heard if there had been a

02:59:00.420 --> 02:59:02.579
challenge, surely, said Moray.

02:59:02.639 --> 02:59:05.459
Queen Coral shot a stern look at the blue

02:59:05.459 --> 02:59:07.559
dragon in the secrets and spies pool.

02:59:07.620 --> 02:59:10.440
Why don't you know anything about this?

02:59:10.500 --> 02:59:13.739
None of my spies have reported in for

02:59:13.739 --> 02:59:15.299
days, he protested.

02:59:15.360 --> 02:59:17.579
I had no idea anything strange was

02:59:17.579 --> 02:59:18.659
happening in the Sky Kingdom.

02:59:18.719 --> 02:59:21.659
The soldier who couldn't fly was leaning

02:59:21.659 --> 02:59:23.100
more and more dizzily against his

02:59:23.100 --> 02:59:23.819
companion.

02:59:23.879 --> 02:59:26.700
Puddles of blood soaked their claws.

02:59:26.760 --> 02:59:29.639
Mother, tsunami said.

02:59:29.700 --> 02:59:31.440
Shouldn't somebody look at their

02:59:31.440 --> 02:59:31.860
injuries?

02:59:31.979 --> 02:59:33.899
She pointed at the soldiers.

02:59:33.959 --> 02:59:36.479
Coral eyed them up and down.

02:59:36.540 --> 02:59:38.940
Anything else to report?

02:59:39.059 --> 02:59:41.639
12 casualties.

02:59:41.700 --> 02:59:43.200
The soldier croaked.

02:59:43.260 --> 02:59:45.780
All the rest badly injured.

02:59:45.840 --> 02:59:48.659
But nobody followed you back to the

02:59:48.659 --> 02:59:50.819
palace, demanded Shark.

02:59:50.879 --> 02:59:55.139
We were careful, he promised, wincing

02:59:55.139 --> 02:59:55.559
with pain.

02:59:55.620 --> 02:59:58.559
We took the longest roots back.

02:59:58.620 --> 03:00:00.479
Very well.

03:00:00.540 --> 03:00:02.579
Queen Coral waved her talons

03:00:02.579 --> 03:00:03.299
dismissively.

03:00:03.360 --> 03:00:04.739
You may go.

03:00:04.860 --> 03:00:07.139
She flicked her tail at the smallest

03:00:07.139 --> 03:00:09.659
council member in the dragon health pool

03:00:09.659 --> 03:00:10.920
who ushered the soldiers away.

03:00:11.040 --> 03:00:13.920
Moray immediately jumped out of her own

03:00:13.920 --> 03:00:15.719
pool and started cleaning out the blood

03:00:15.719 --> 03:00:16.260
on the floor.

03:00:16.319 --> 03:00:20.280
If there is chaos in the sky kingdom

03:00:20.280 --> 03:00:23.280
maybe this is the time to strike, Carl

03:00:23.280 --> 03:00:23.760
said.

03:00:23.819 --> 03:00:26.040
She wrapped one strand of pearls around

03:00:26.040 --> 03:00:26.579
her claws.

03:00:26.700 --> 03:00:29.760
We should send the rescue mission now.

03:00:29.819 --> 03:00:31.379
We could get him back today.

03:00:31.440 --> 03:00:35.579
We don't know enough, growled the secrets

03:00:35.579 --> 03:00:36.719
and spies, dragon.

03:00:36.780 --> 03:00:38.760
If Scarlet is dead, how did she die?

03:00:38.819 --> 03:00:40.319
Did Ruby kill her?

03:00:40.379 --> 03:00:42.239
Or is she fighting with her sisters for

03:00:42.239 --> 03:00:42.659
the throne?

03:00:42.719 --> 03:00:45.659
Moray hissed at the blood under her

03:00:45.659 --> 03:00:46.200
claws.

03:00:46.260 --> 03:00:49.440
Like the sandwing rivalry all over again

03:00:49.440 --> 03:00:51.899
making the war even worse.

03:00:51.959 --> 03:00:54.000
Or has burn taken over?

03:00:54.059 --> 03:00:55.680
Piranha suggested.

03:00:55.739 --> 03:00:57.479
She would, if she was there.

03:00:57.540 --> 03:01:00.600
But Scarlet's daughters might not listen

03:01:00.600 --> 03:01:03.479
to burn the way Scarlet did, said Moray.

03:01:03.540 --> 03:01:05.760
What could have happened?

03:01:05.819 --> 03:01:07.440
Coral said.

03:01:07.500 --> 03:01:09.899
Queen Scarlet was so strong.

03:01:09.959 --> 03:01:13.920
Tsunami shifted uncomfortably, feeling

03:01:13.920 --> 03:01:15.719
the cold water seeping through her

03:01:15.719 --> 03:01:16.079
scales.

03:01:16.200 --> 03:01:19.620
She couldn't hide what she knew, not when

03:01:19.620 --> 03:01:21.360
her mother needed the information so

03:01:21.360 --> 03:01:21.659
much.

03:01:21.719 --> 03:01:24.540
Or at least she could share some of the

03:01:24.540 --> 03:01:25.500
dramatic highlights.

03:01:25.620 --> 03:01:28.680
Um, tsunami said.

03:01:28.739 --> 03:01:31.079
The entire council turned to stare at

03:01:31.079 --> 03:01:31.260
her.

03:01:31.319 --> 03:01:34.799
That might have been us.

03:01:34.860 --> 03:01:37.979
There was a shocked pause.

03:01:38.040 --> 03:01:40.739
You barked Piranha.

03:01:40.799 --> 03:01:43.979
Ridiculous, snarled Shark.

03:01:44.040 --> 03:01:47.100
Queen Scarlet found us under the mountain

03:01:47.100 --> 03:01:48.360
tsunami said.

03:01:48.420 --> 03:01:51.420
She held us prisoner in her palace, and

03:01:51.420 --> 03:01:54.540
when we escaped, we sort of might have

03:01:54.540 --> 03:01:55.200
killed her.

03:01:55.260 --> 03:01:56.760
Maybe.

03:01:57.239 --> 03:01:57.959
I'm not sure.

03:01:58.079 --> 03:02:00.059
I will say we tried.

03:02:00.120 --> 03:02:03.420
She quite liked the horrified look on

03:02:03.420 --> 03:02:05.280
shark's face at that bit of news.

03:02:05.340 --> 03:02:07.799
Starting to respect us a bit more?

03:02:07.860 --> 03:02:08.879
She thought.

03:02:08.940 --> 03:02:11.819
You were at the Sky Wing Palace?

03:02:11.879 --> 03:02:14.760
Coral lunged out of her pool, swarmed

03:02:14.760 --> 03:02:17.399
across the stone, and seized tsunami's

03:02:17.399 --> 03:02:19.620
front talons in her own, clutching them

03:02:19.620 --> 03:02:21.120
so hard it was a little painful.

03:02:21.180 --> 03:02:22.799
Behind her.

03:02:22.860 --> 03:02:25.020
Anemone was yanked half out of the pool

03:02:25.020 --> 03:02:27.479
with a squeak of protest, but Coral

03:02:27.479 --> 03:02:28.260
didn't seem to notice.

03:02:28.319 --> 03:02:31.620
Did you see a sea wing named Gil?

03:02:31.680 --> 03:02:32.819
The queen cried.

03:02:32.879 --> 03:02:36.120
Green scales, big and powerful with brave

03:02:36.120 --> 03:02:36.540
eyes.

03:02:36.600 --> 03:02:39.239
Tsunami felt sick.

03:02:39.420 --> 03:02:41.100
Gil.

03:02:41.219 --> 03:02:42.239
Yes.

03:02:42.299 --> 03:02:45.540
She remembered Gil, but not the way Queen

03:02:45.540 --> 03:02:47.100
Coral described him.

03:02:47.159 --> 03:02:49.620
She'd been forced to fight Gil in

03:02:49.620 --> 03:02:52.500
Scarlet's Gladiator Arena after he'd been

03:02:52.500 --> 03:02:55.139
deprived of water for months and driven

03:02:55.139 --> 03:02:55.920
mad with thirst.

03:02:56.040 --> 03:02:59.219
He'd been covered in scratches, as if

03:02:59.219 --> 03:03:00.719
he'd tried to drink his own blood.

03:03:00.780 --> 03:03:04.620
The sound of dragon bones snapping

03:03:04.620 --> 03:03:05.639
between my talons.

03:03:05.700 --> 03:03:10.860
I did see him, tsunami said slowly.

03:03:10.920 --> 03:03:14.520
A gasp went up around her, whispers

03:03:14.520 --> 03:03:16.260
traveling from one council member to the

03:03:16.260 --> 03:03:16.500
next.

03:03:16.559 --> 03:03:19.979
Shark's pale, unfriendly eyes were like

03:03:19.979 --> 03:03:22.200
octopus arms coiling around her neck.

03:03:22.260 --> 03:03:24.840
Can you tell us where he is?

03:03:24.899 --> 03:03:27.059
Queen Coral asked urgently.

03:03:27.120 --> 03:03:29.819
We've been planning a rescue mission, but

03:03:29.819 --> 03:03:31.440
he's not in the regular prison with the

03:03:31.440 --> 03:03:33.239
others, and we've got to get him back

03:03:33.239 --> 03:03:33.899
tsunami.

03:03:33.959 --> 03:03:37.020
You have no idea how important it is.

03:03:37.079 --> 03:03:39.959
Tsunami curled her tail in close to her

03:03:39.959 --> 03:03:40.440
talons.

03:03:40.500 --> 03:03:43.920
She wanted to dive into the lake, crawl

03:03:43.920 --> 03:03:45.719
down to the bottom, and stay there

03:03:45.719 --> 03:03:47.700
forever with her wings over her head.

03:03:47.700 --> 03:03:51.479
He is, her voice cracked.

03:03:51.540 --> 03:03:53.459
She swallowed and started again.

03:03:53.520 --> 03:03:55.559
He's dead.

03:03:55.620 --> 03:03:59.159
She'd had no choice but to kill the

03:03:59.159 --> 03:04:00.840
desperate sea wing in the arena.

03:04:00.899 --> 03:04:03.180
It was his life or hers.

03:04:03.239 --> 03:04:05.219
She hadn't wanted to kill him.

03:04:05.280 --> 03:04:08.579
At least, she was pretty sure she hadn't

03:04:08.579 --> 03:04:09.239
wanted to kill him.

03:04:09.299 --> 03:04:13.620
But when she did, the truth was, tsunami

03:04:13.620 --> 03:04:15.959
had loved the look on Queen Scarlet's

03:04:15.959 --> 03:04:17.700
face when she broke Gil's neck.

03:04:17.760 --> 03:04:20.520
She liked the feeling of being powerful

03:04:20.520 --> 03:04:21.959
and dangerous.

03:04:22.020 --> 03:04:25.799
Gil's sanity had been long gone anyway.

03:04:25.860 --> 03:04:28.799
It had been easy for tsunami not to think

03:04:28.799 --> 03:04:31.079
about where he came from, or what his

03:04:31.079 --> 03:04:33.000
life was like before he landed in the Sky

03:04:33.000 --> 03:04:33.540
Wing prison.

03:04:33.600 --> 03:04:36.420
It was easier not to think of him as a

03:04:36.420 --> 03:04:37.200
real dragon.

03:04:37.260 --> 03:04:40.440
She'd never imagined her own mother

03:04:40.440 --> 03:04:43.440
desperately planning to get him back, or

03:04:43.440 --> 03:04:45.180
that she'd have to explain his death to

03:04:45.180 --> 03:04:46.139
anyone.

03:04:46.200 --> 03:04:48.059
Dead?

03:04:48.120 --> 03:04:51.479
Queen Coral released tsunami's talons and

03:04:51.479 --> 03:04:52.260
staggered backward.

03:04:52.319 --> 03:04:54.899
Her claws splashed in the winding

03:04:54.899 --> 03:04:56.700
channels, slipping on pearls.

03:04:56.760 --> 03:04:58.260
How?

03:04:58.319 --> 03:05:01.559
Um, tsunami stammered.

03:05:01.620 --> 03:05:03.659
Did she really have to admit this in

03:05:03.659 --> 03:05:05.219
front of all these dragons?

03:05:05.280 --> 03:05:06.780
In the arena.

03:05:06.899 --> 03:05:10.559
But he refused to fight, Coral said.

03:05:10.620 --> 03:05:13.319
We heard about it through our spies.

03:05:13.379 --> 03:05:15.959
He convinced each of his opponents to lie

03:05:15.959 --> 03:05:17.940
down and refuse to fight along with him.

03:05:18.000 --> 03:05:20.819
He has had a way with words.

03:05:20.940 --> 03:05:23.819
No one who met him would be able to kill

03:05:23.819 --> 03:05:24.239
him.

03:05:24.360 --> 03:05:27.899
A smile flickered across her snout and

03:05:27.899 --> 03:05:28.500
vanished.

03:05:28.559 --> 03:05:31.379
Queen Scarlet was furious.

03:05:31.440 --> 03:05:32.280
I heard.

03:05:32.399 --> 03:05:34.139
She was.

03:05:34.260 --> 03:05:36.239
Tsunami swallowed again.

03:05:36.299 --> 03:05:38.280
She punished him.

03:05:38.340 --> 03:05:41.219
It was really awful.

03:05:41.280 --> 03:05:44.700
What do you know about his death?

03:05:44.760 --> 03:05:46.979
Shark demanded coldly.

03:05:47.100 --> 03:05:49.799
Tsunami stirred the water with her

03:05:49.799 --> 03:05:50.280
claws.

03:05:50.340 --> 03:05:52.319
She drove him mad.

03:05:52.440 --> 03:05:55.319
She kept him away from water until he

03:05:55.319 --> 03:05:58.620
lost his mind, and when he was crazy, he

03:05:58.620 --> 03:05:59.340
was dangerous.

03:05:59.399 --> 03:06:02.159
He was barely even a dragon anymore.

03:06:02.219 --> 03:06:04.079
He had to be killed.

03:06:04.139 --> 03:06:06.059
Really?

03:06:06.120 --> 03:06:07.680
Shark said.

03:06:07.739 --> 03:06:10.739
And tsunami felt horribly sure he had

03:06:10.739 --> 03:06:11.399
guessed the truth.

03:06:11.459 --> 03:06:13.620
Why?

03:06:13.680 --> 03:06:15.000
Tsunami asked.

03:06:15.059 --> 03:06:17.219
Who, who was he?

03:06:17.280 --> 03:06:19.020
An important general?

03:06:19.079 --> 03:06:22.979
More than that, said Queen Coral in a

03:06:22.979 --> 03:06:23.399
hollow voice.

03:06:23.459 --> 03:06:25.139
Much more.

03:06:25.200 --> 03:06:27.239
He was my husband.

03:06:27.299 --> 03:06:30.719
Darkness seemed to be rushing into

03:06:30.719 --> 03:06:33.180
Tsunami's vision, sucking away all her

03:06:33.180 --> 03:06:33.719
breath.

03:06:33.780 --> 03:06:36.360
She knew what Queen Coral was going to

03:06:36.360 --> 03:06:36.899
say next.

03:06:36.959 --> 03:06:38.760
And she would have fled back to the

03:06:38.760 --> 03:06:40.379
mountains to avoid hearing it if she

03:06:40.379 --> 03:06:40.620
could.

03:06:40.680 --> 03:06:42.840
Tsunami.

03:06:42.899 --> 03:06:45.299
Gil was your father.

03:06:45.360 --> 03:06:49.559
Chapter 12.

03:06:49.860 --> 03:06:54.000
Queen Coral dropped her head and slowly

03:06:54.000 --> 03:06:55.620
dragged herself back to her pool.

03:06:55.680 --> 03:06:58.799
Dead, she said.

03:06:58.860 --> 03:07:01.440
My Gil is dead.

03:07:01.500 --> 03:07:04.139
No more eggs?

03:07:04.260 --> 03:07:05.219
Mori whispered.

03:07:05.280 --> 03:07:07.680
She was still crouched in the center of

03:07:07.680 --> 03:07:09.000
the floor, scrubbing at the blood.

03:07:09.120 --> 03:07:12.059
Her eyes had a weird glow to them.

03:07:12.120 --> 03:07:13.799
No more dragonettes.

03:07:13.860 --> 03:07:15.059
No more challenges.

03:07:15.120 --> 03:07:18.180
Not necessarily.

03:07:18.239 --> 03:07:21.780
She could marry again.

03:07:21.840 --> 03:07:24.000
Whirlpool murmured.

03:07:24.059 --> 03:07:25.920
Moray shot him a glare.

03:07:25.979 --> 03:07:28.440
Coral didn't seem to hear either of

03:07:28.440 --> 03:07:28.680
them.

03:07:28.739 --> 03:07:31.559
She pulled anemone into her wings and

03:07:31.559 --> 03:07:32.399
clutched her tightly.

03:07:32.459 --> 03:07:35.399
The little dragonette wriggled a bit, then

03:07:35.399 --> 03:07:37.739
gave up and rested her head on Coral's

03:07:37.739 --> 03:07:38.040
shoulder.

03:07:38.100 --> 03:07:41.340
She blinked in a resigned way at tsunami

03:07:41.340 --> 03:07:42.659
over their mother's back.

03:07:42.780 --> 03:07:45.899
Tsunami felt like oceans were pressing

03:07:45.899 --> 03:07:47.040
against the back of her eyes.

03:07:47.100 --> 03:07:49.979
Her scales were heavy, as if they were

03:07:49.979 --> 03:07:51.059
clogged with seaweed.

03:07:51.120 --> 03:07:53.280
But I didn't have a choice.

03:07:53.399 --> 03:07:54.959
Did I?

03:07:55.020 --> 03:07:57.299
He was my father.

03:07:57.360 --> 03:07:59.340
And I had no idea.

03:07:59.399 --> 03:08:02.639
But he wasn't a real dragon anymore.

03:08:02.700 --> 03:08:05.940
He wasn't anyone inside his parched

03:08:05.940 --> 03:08:06.360
scales.

03:08:06.420 --> 03:08:09.659
He was gone, and I had to survive.

03:08:09.719 --> 03:08:12.120
I had to survive to protect my friends

03:08:12.120 --> 03:08:14.280
and fulfill my destiny.

03:08:14.340 --> 03:08:16.200
Nothing helped.

03:08:16.260 --> 03:08:18.540
She hadn't really thought about other

03:08:18.540 --> 03:08:21.180
options when she'd killed the Seawing in

03:08:21.180 --> 03:08:21.540
the arena.

03:08:21.600 --> 03:08:24.299
It was impulse, and wanting to prove

03:08:24.299 --> 03:08:25.559
something to Queen Scarlet.

03:08:25.620 --> 03:08:28.079
Shark was still staring at her

03:08:28.079 --> 03:08:29.399
unblinking.

03:08:29.459 --> 03:08:31.680
Tsunami bared her teeth at him.

03:08:31.739 --> 03:08:35.340
I must grieve, said the queen.

03:08:35.399 --> 03:08:37.139
Counsel dismissed.

03:08:37.260 --> 03:08:40.139
She stepped to the edge of the pavilion

03:08:40.139 --> 03:08:42.540
and flew off to her cave, still holding

03:08:42.540 --> 03:08:43.200
anemone.

03:08:43.260 --> 03:08:46.559
The council dragons peeled off to various

03:08:46.559 --> 03:08:48.840
caves and other levels of the pavilion.

03:08:48.899 --> 03:08:52.020
Tsunami buried her head in the pool and

03:08:52.020 --> 03:08:52.860
clutched her horns.

03:08:52.920 --> 03:08:55.139
Now what was she supposed to do?

03:08:55.200 --> 03:08:58.620
She definitely was not in the mood for

03:08:58.620 --> 03:08:59.579
seeing her friends.

03:08:59.639 --> 03:09:02.040
It would not make her feel any better to

03:09:02.040 --> 03:09:03.840
face their remarks about what a terrible

03:09:03.840 --> 03:09:06.719
dragon she was, the kind of dragon who

03:09:06.719 --> 03:09:09.479
attacked other dragons for no reason, the

03:09:09.479 --> 03:09:10.920
kind of dragon who did what she thought

03:09:10.920 --> 03:09:12.840
was right, but was always wrong.

03:09:12.899 --> 03:09:16.260
The kind of dragon, who could kill her

03:09:16.260 --> 03:09:16.680
own father.

03:09:16.739 --> 03:09:19.920
Something tapped her on the top of her

03:09:19.920 --> 03:09:20.159
head.

03:09:20.219 --> 03:09:22.860
She emerged from the water and found

03:09:22.860 --> 03:09:24.600
Whirlpool rubbing his claws together.

03:09:24.659 --> 03:09:30.719
Time for your 1st lesson, he said, in his

03:09:30.719 --> 03:09:31.559
oily voice.

03:09:31.620 --> 03:09:34.559
Now, tsunami said.

03:09:34.680 --> 03:09:36.360
Why not?

03:09:36.420 --> 03:09:38.280
He spread his talons.

03:09:38.340 --> 03:09:42.120
It is never too soon to begin filling our

03:09:42.120 --> 03:09:43.739
minds with knowledge.

03:09:43.860 --> 03:09:47.340
Tsunami hissed softly under her breath.

03:09:47.399 --> 03:09:51.540
This was not going to be fun, but perhaps

03:09:51.540 --> 03:09:53.340
it would be distracting.

03:09:53.399 --> 03:09:57.479
Come, he said, strutting to the edge and

03:09:57.479 --> 03:09:58.079
diving over.

03:09:58.139 --> 03:10:01.079
Tsunami reluctantly followed him into the

03:10:01.079 --> 03:10:01.620
cavern lake.

03:10:01.680 --> 03:10:04.139
He was hovering several lengths below the

03:10:04.139 --> 03:10:06.180
surface, flashing his stripes at her.

03:10:06.239 --> 03:10:09.180
Tsunami sank to his level and watched

03:10:09.180 --> 03:10:09.479
him.

03:10:09.540 --> 03:10:11.760
She kept her own scales dark.

03:10:11.819 --> 03:10:14.520
She most definitely did not want to say

03:10:14.520 --> 03:10:16.920
something to him, like what she'd said to

03:10:16.920 --> 03:10:17.579
riptide.

03:10:17.639 --> 03:10:20.399
If Anemone was right about Coral's plans

03:10:20.399 --> 03:10:22.620
for him, Whirlpool did not need any

03:10:22.620 --> 03:10:23.340
encouraging.

03:10:23.399 --> 03:10:27.180
After a few moments, Whirlpool swam up to

03:10:27.180 --> 03:10:27.959
the surface again.

03:10:28.020 --> 03:10:31.139
His pale green eyes seemed far too big

03:10:31.139 --> 03:10:32.280
for his eye sockets.

03:10:32.340 --> 03:10:34.559
What's the matter?

03:10:34.620 --> 03:10:36.000
He said.

03:10:36.059 --> 03:10:38.940
Don't your stripes light up?

03:10:39.000 --> 03:10:42.780
Of course they do, Tsunami snapped, but

03:10:42.780 --> 03:10:44.399
you haven't told me what we're saying or

03:10:44.399 --> 03:10:44.639
anything.

03:10:44.700 --> 03:10:50.520
Just imitate me, he said officiously, and

03:10:50.520 --> 03:10:55.139
dove again before she could argue. tsunami

03:10:55.139 --> 03:10:55.680
growled.

03:10:55.739 --> 03:10:58.860
This time she imitated each flashing path

03:10:58.860 --> 03:11:01.799
of light, along her wings, her tail, her

03:11:01.799 --> 03:11:04.799
sides, alternating and sometimes flashing

03:11:04.799 --> 03:11:06.299
faster, or slower.

03:11:06.360 --> 03:11:08.700
It seemed to go on for an eternity.

03:11:08.760 --> 03:11:11.579
Finally, Whirlpool nodded with

03:11:11.579 --> 03:11:13.979
satisfaction and rose to the air again.

03:11:14.040 --> 03:11:16.200
Excellent.

03:11:16.260 --> 03:11:18.000
He proclaimed.

03:11:18.059 --> 03:11:19.739
What's excellent?

03:11:19.799 --> 03:11:22.379
Tsunami demanded, spreading her wings to

03:11:22.379 --> 03:11:22.739
float.

03:11:22.799 --> 03:11:24.540
What did we just say?

03:11:24.659 --> 03:11:29.639
We recited the 1st chapter of the Queen's

03:11:29.639 --> 03:11:30.959
very 1st work.

03:11:31.020 --> 03:11:34.319
The tragedy of Orca.

03:11:34.379 --> 03:11:39.600
It's extremely moving, glorious writing

03:11:39.600 --> 03:11:42.780
you nearly repeated it perfectly.

03:11:42.840 --> 03:11:46.620
Tsunami wanted to splash seawater up his

03:11:46.620 --> 03:11:49.319
annoying snout, but I didn't learn

03:11:49.319 --> 03:11:49.739
anything.

03:11:49.799 --> 03:11:53.520
Oh, you will, he said.

03:11:53.579 --> 03:11:56.700
With repetition comes perfection.

03:11:56.760 --> 03:12:00.299
Shall we go on to the 2nd chapter?

03:12:00.360 --> 03:12:03.239
No, tsunami said.

03:12:03.299 --> 03:12:04.979
Teach me something I can use.

03:12:05.040 --> 03:12:06.959
How do you greet strangers?

03:12:07.020 --> 03:12:09.239
How do you warn other sea wings of

03:12:09.239 --> 03:12:09.540
danger?

03:12:09.600 --> 03:12:13.079
How do you say, I'm sorry I killed my

03:12:13.079 --> 03:12:13.379
father?

03:12:13.500 --> 03:12:15.420
She shook herself.

03:12:15.479 --> 03:12:18.479
For moon's sake, at least show me how to

03:12:18.479 --> 03:12:20.040
say, I don't speak aquatic.

03:12:20.100 --> 03:12:24.239
All knowledge can be found in the queen's

03:12:24.239 --> 03:12:24.780
writing.

03:12:24.840 --> 03:12:26.520
Whirlpool insisted.

03:12:26.579 --> 03:12:31.139
If we recite 3 chapters a day, we should

03:12:31.139 --> 03:12:33.899
get through her entire body of work in

03:12:33.899 --> 03:12:35.879
about 5 years.

03:12:36.000 --> 03:12:39.899
I have to get out of here, tsunami said

03:12:39.899 --> 03:12:42.719
before I tie your stupid tail around your

03:12:42.719 --> 03:12:45.299
stupid snout and leave you in a bundle at

03:12:45.299 --> 03:12:46.200
the bottom of the lake.

03:12:46.260 --> 03:12:48.840
She turned and swam toward the exit

03:12:48.840 --> 03:12:49.260
tunnel.

03:12:49.319 --> 03:12:52.020
It wasn't quite as dramatic as storming

03:12:52.020 --> 03:12:54.420
out of a cave, which she hoped would be

03:12:54.420 --> 03:12:56.819
the 1st and last time she missed anything

03:12:56.819 --> 03:12:58.620
about life under the mountain.

03:12:58.680 --> 03:13:04.139
I am not impressed with your work ethic.

03:13:04.200 --> 03:13:06.180
Whirlpool called.

03:13:06.239 --> 03:13:10.200
This may take us closer to 7 or 8 years

03:13:10.200 --> 03:13:11.219
if you.

03:13:11.520 --> 03:13:13.739
Tsunami plunged her head under the water

03:13:13.739 --> 03:13:15.299
so she wouldn't have to listen to him

03:13:15.299 --> 03:13:15.600
anymore.

03:13:15.719 --> 03:13:18.780
The exit tunnel yawned ahead of her, and

03:13:18.780 --> 03:13:20.819
she shot into it as fast as her wings

03:13:20.819 --> 03:13:21.120
could beat.

03:13:21.180 --> 03:13:24.899
Outside the summer palace, the sky was

03:13:24.899 --> 03:13:28.079
gray and overcast, which suited tsunami's

03:13:28.079 --> 03:13:28.680
mood perfectly.

03:13:28.739 --> 03:13:31.739
Wind whipped the sea into white tipped

03:13:31.739 --> 03:13:34.200
peaks, knocking tsunami around even more

03:13:34.200 --> 03:13:34.680
than usual.

03:13:34.739 --> 03:13:37.440
She tried paddling away from the palace

03:13:37.440 --> 03:13:40.079
underwater, but currents kept flinging

03:13:40.079 --> 03:13:41.219
her into the jagged boulders.

03:13:41.280 --> 03:13:44.459
She was sick of fighting with the ocean.

03:13:44.520 --> 03:13:47.159
Why wouldn't it welcome her, like it was

03:13:47.159 --> 03:13:47.760
supposed to.

03:13:47.819 --> 03:13:50.399
Why couldn't she start over as a normal

03:13:50.399 --> 03:13:53.340
sea wing with normal problems, instead of

03:13:53.340 --> 03:13:55.620
having her past mistakes suckered onto

03:13:55.620 --> 03:13:57.600
her tail like overgrown leeches.

03:13:57.659 --> 03:14:00.899
Frustrated, she swam to the surface and

03:14:00.899 --> 03:14:01.799
flew into the sky.

03:14:01.920 --> 03:14:04.500
It didn't make sense that flying should

03:14:04.500 --> 03:14:06.059
be easier for her than swimming.

03:14:06.120 --> 03:14:08.579
What kind of sea wing didn't love the

03:14:08.579 --> 03:14:08.879
sea?

03:14:08.940 --> 03:14:11.940
The kind that shouldn't be queen maybe

03:14:11.940 --> 03:14:13.500
tsunami thought.

03:14:13.559 --> 03:14:16.739
Looming out of the water ahead of her was

03:14:16.739 --> 03:14:18.899
the island of rocks shaped like a giant

03:14:18.899 --> 03:14:20.100
dragon skeleton.

03:14:20.159 --> 03:14:23.219
Tsunami banked toward it, studying the

03:14:23.219 --> 03:14:24.059
holes and gaps.

03:14:24.120 --> 03:14:26.459
She chose the cave where the eye should

03:14:26.459 --> 03:14:29.100
be, and landed in cool semi darkness.

03:14:29.159 --> 03:14:31.979
The stone was smooth like pearls under

03:14:31.979 --> 03:14:32.579
her claws.

03:14:32.700 --> 03:14:36.000
She flapped her wings to dry them and

03:14:36.000 --> 03:14:37.379
turned to look out the entrance.

03:14:37.440 --> 03:14:40.500
A dragon head popped into a view, then

03:14:40.500 --> 03:14:41.340
vanished again.

03:14:41.399 --> 03:14:45.899
Wow, tsunami said, you are the worst at

03:14:45.899 --> 03:14:46.739
staying hidden.

03:14:46.799 --> 03:14:49.260
Has anyone ever told you that you should

03:14:49.260 --> 03:14:50.940
definitely never be a spy?

03:14:51.000 --> 03:14:54.180
Riptide slowly poked his head around the

03:14:54.180 --> 03:14:54.899
mouth of the cave.

03:14:54.959 --> 03:14:59.040
I think I'd make a splendid spy, he said

03:14:59.040 --> 03:14:59.700
with dignity.

03:14:59.760 --> 03:15:02.280
Aren't you supposed to be patrolling the

03:15:02.280 --> 03:15:03.600
outer islands where we met?

03:15:03.719 --> 03:15:04.860
Tsunami asked.

03:15:04.979 --> 03:15:08.579
Perhaps, but as you can imagine, I don't

03:15:08.579 --> 03:15:09.420
have a very important job.

03:15:09.479 --> 03:15:12.239
Riptide made a rye expression.

03:15:12.360 --> 03:15:15.000
Her majesty can't trust me with anything

03:15:15.000 --> 03:15:16.020
vital.

03:15:16.079 --> 03:15:19.139
You do seem like a shady character.

03:15:19.200 --> 03:15:21.959
Tsunami said, remembering that she was

03:15:21.959 --> 03:15:23.579
supposed to be mad at him too.

03:15:23.639 --> 03:15:25.139
She could yell at him.

03:15:25.200 --> 03:15:27.719
Her 1st instinct was to yell at him.

03:15:27.780 --> 03:15:30.899
Maybe I should stop listening to all my

03:15:30.899 --> 03:15:31.920
1st instincts.

03:15:32.040 --> 03:15:35.100
She scooted back farther into the cave.

03:15:35.159 --> 03:15:36.360
Come on in.

03:15:36.420 --> 03:15:38.700
I'm just recovering from an aquatic

03:15:38.700 --> 03:15:39.840
lesson with Whirlpool.

03:15:39.899 --> 03:15:43.979
Oh, whirlpool, Queen Coral's favorite

03:15:43.979 --> 03:15:46.799
instrument of torture, cryptide said.

03:15:46.860 --> 03:15:49.020
He climbed into the cave beside her

03:15:49.020 --> 03:15:51.120
shaking water droplets from his scales.

03:15:51.180 --> 03:15:53.879
The cave was only big enough for 3 or 4

03:15:53.879 --> 03:15:56.100
dragons, so they were closer together in

03:15:56.100 --> 03:15:58.020
the dark than tsunami had expected.

03:15:58.139 --> 03:16:01.440
When she was much younger, Tsunami had

03:16:01.440 --> 03:16:03.360
had fleeting crushes on clay and

03:16:03.360 --> 03:16:06.180
Starflight before she realized that

03:16:06.180 --> 03:16:08.219
Starflight could be massively annoying

03:16:08.219 --> 03:16:10.979
and that sweet, loyal clay saw the other

03:16:10.979 --> 03:16:13.500
dragonettes as brothers and sisters.

03:16:13.559 --> 03:16:15.719
But they were the only dragonettes her

03:16:15.719 --> 03:16:17.219
own age that she'd ever met.

03:16:17.340 --> 03:16:19.860
Even though they weren't sea wings, who

03:16:19.860 --> 03:16:21.239
else was she supposed to like?

03:16:21.299 --> 03:16:26.040
Now here she was, alone with a sea wing, a

03:16:26.040 --> 03:16:27.540
sea wing who looked at her as if he

03:16:27.540 --> 03:16:30.000
didn't see a future queen, or a father

03:16:30.000 --> 03:16:32.879
killer, or anything but a dragon whom he

03:16:32.879 --> 03:16:33.479
liked very much.

03:16:33.540 --> 03:16:37.680
Carl told me Webbs is your father, she

03:16:37.680 --> 03:16:39.180
said quickly, awkwardly.

03:16:39.239 --> 03:16:41.579
Why didn't you say something when we

03:16:41.579 --> 03:16:41.819
met?

03:16:41.940 --> 03:16:45.239
It's not how I usually introduce myself

03:16:45.239 --> 03:16:46.319
he said.

03:16:46.379 --> 03:16:49.020
He coiled his tail around his talons.

03:16:49.139 --> 03:16:51.899
It makes dragons see me a certain way.

03:16:51.959 --> 03:16:53.219
I'm sorry.

03:16:53.280 --> 03:16:54.239
I should have told you.

03:16:54.299 --> 03:16:58.979
I was hoping you might, um, I'd like to

03:16:58.979 --> 03:16:59.760
know more about him.

03:16:59.819 --> 03:17:04.379
Tsunami shook her head, tempted to say no

03:17:04.379 --> 03:17:04.979
you wouldn't.

03:17:05.040 --> 03:17:07.559
Is that why you've been hanging around

03:17:07.559 --> 03:17:08.100
watching me?

03:17:08.159 --> 03:17:09.659
she asked instead.

03:17:09.719 --> 03:17:12.780
His dark blue eyes caught the faint light

03:17:12.780 --> 03:17:13.379
from outside.

03:17:13.440 --> 03:17:17.459
That and other reasons, he said.

03:17:17.520 --> 03:17:19.200
I was worried about you.

03:17:19.260 --> 03:17:22.860
There aren't a lot of outspoken dragons

03:17:22.860 --> 03:17:23.700
in the kingdom of the sea.

03:17:23.819 --> 03:17:27.420
I can say whatever I want, Tsunami said

03:17:27.420 --> 03:17:27.899
boldly.

03:17:27.959 --> 03:17:31.200
I'm the missing princess Mother loves me

03:17:31.200 --> 03:17:33.360
so much, she'll have a harness on me by

03:17:33.360 --> 03:17:34.739
the end of the day if I'm not careful.

03:17:34.860 --> 03:17:37.079
Riptide snorted.

03:17:37.139 --> 03:17:39.780
I'd like to see any dragon try to put a

03:17:39.780 --> 03:17:40.379
harness on you.

03:17:40.440 --> 03:17:43.979
Then they'd really find out how outspoken

03:17:43.979 --> 03:17:45.840
I am, Tsunami said.

03:17:45.899 --> 03:17:48.120
She opened and closed her wings

03:17:48.120 --> 03:17:50.040
accidentally brushing against his.

03:17:50.100 --> 03:17:52.680
Oops, say something, quick.

03:17:52.799 --> 03:17:56.159
Webbs wasn't so bad, she blurted.

03:17:56.219 --> 03:17:58.020
Not as bad as the other two.

03:17:58.079 --> 03:18:00.000
He tilted his head.

03:18:00.059 --> 03:18:02.340
We had 3 guardians.

03:18:02.399 --> 03:18:05.340
The other two, Dune and Kestrel hated

03:18:05.340 --> 03:18:08.219
everything, tsunami said, except maybe

03:18:08.219 --> 03:18:08.760
sunny.

03:18:08.819 --> 03:18:10.500
Nobody hates Sonny.

03:18:10.559 --> 03:18:13.200
She's too sweet and simple and lovable.

03:18:13.260 --> 03:18:17.340
She sounds frightful, Riptide said, and

03:18:17.340 --> 03:18:18.360
tsunami laughed.

03:18:18.420 --> 03:18:21.600
But Webbs, he wasn't just trying to keep

03:18:21.600 --> 03:18:22.200
us alive.

03:18:22.260 --> 03:18:25.079
He taught us everything he could, except

03:18:25.079 --> 03:18:26.219
aquatic, I guess.

03:18:26.280 --> 03:18:29.280
He taught us history and geography, and

03:18:29.280 --> 03:18:31.440
all about the prophecy, and he wasn't

03:18:31.440 --> 03:18:32.159
even that boring about it.

03:18:32.219 --> 03:18:35.219
When it was his turn to hunt, he tried to

03:18:35.219 --> 03:18:36.959
bring back prey he knew we liked.

03:18:37.079 --> 03:18:39.540
It would have been worse without him.

03:18:39.600 --> 03:18:42.420
She fell silent, thinking.

03:18:42.540 --> 03:18:45.180
She'd never tried listing good things

03:18:45.180 --> 03:18:46.200
about webs before.

03:18:46.260 --> 03:18:48.420
It was a lot harder than complaining

03:18:48.420 --> 03:18:50.280
about him, like she'd done her whole

03:18:50.280 --> 03:18:50.819
life.

03:18:50.940 --> 03:18:54.180
It's all right, Riptide said.

03:18:54.239 --> 03:18:55.799
You can tell me the truth.

03:18:55.860 --> 03:18:58.739
The end of his tail flicked up and down.

03:18:58.799 --> 03:19:01.020
I want to hear the bad stuff too.

03:19:01.079 --> 03:19:02.520
It's good for me.

03:19:02.579 --> 03:19:04.739
Tsunami took a deep breath.

03:19:04.799 --> 03:19:08.159
He should have protected us better, she

03:19:08.159 --> 03:19:08.459
said.

03:19:08.520 --> 03:19:11.340
If he was the only one who cared, he

03:19:11.340 --> 03:19:13.260
should have stopped Dune and Kestrel from

03:19:13.260 --> 03:19:14.760
hurting us and telling us we were

03:19:14.760 --> 03:19:17.219
worthless, he should have fought for us

03:19:17.219 --> 03:19:20.040
and he never did, except right at the end

03:19:20.040 --> 03:19:22.319
when Scarlet and the Sky Wings attacked.

03:19:22.379 --> 03:19:25.799
That's one thing I do, she thought to

03:19:25.799 --> 03:19:28.860
herself, I fight for my friends, even if

03:19:28.860 --> 03:19:29.760
I'm doing it all wrong.

03:19:29.879 --> 03:19:33.479
Riptide nodded, looking down at the stone

03:19:33.479 --> 03:19:37.860
under his talons, weak and cowardly, he

03:19:37.860 --> 03:19:38.159
said.

03:19:38.219 --> 03:19:40.680
That's how he's always been described to

03:19:40.680 --> 03:19:40.920
me.

03:19:40.979 --> 03:19:43.979
Tsunami reached out and touched his wing

03:19:43.979 --> 03:19:44.879
with one claw.

03:19:44.940 --> 03:19:47.700
That doesn't mean you're anything like

03:19:47.700 --> 03:19:48.000
him.

03:19:48.059 --> 03:19:49.079
She said.

03:19:49.139 --> 03:19:51.420
It's not fair to punish you for what he

03:19:51.420 --> 03:19:51.659
did.

03:19:51.719 --> 03:19:54.719
Something tingled in the air between them

03:19:54.719 --> 03:19:57.600
like the sky outside, waiting for the

03:19:57.600 --> 03:19:57.899
storm.

03:19:57.959 --> 03:20:02.100
This is most improper for the future's

03:20:02.100 --> 03:20:04.379
sea wing queen, tsunami thought.

03:20:04.500 --> 03:20:06.719
But maybe I'd rather have this than a

03:20:06.719 --> 03:20:07.739
throne anyway.

03:20:07.799 --> 03:20:10.860
Would you like a real aquatic lesson?

03:20:10.920 --> 03:20:12.659
Riptide asked with a smile.

03:20:12.719 --> 03:20:15.840
I demand one, she answered.

03:20:15.899 --> 03:20:19.020
It's dark enough in here, he said.

03:20:19.079 --> 03:20:20.159
All right.

03:20:20.219 --> 03:20:22.260
Here's what you say to Whirlpool next

03:20:22.260 --> 03:20:22.920
time you see him.

03:20:22.979 --> 03:20:25.559
The stripe on his tail lit up 3 times.

03:20:25.680 --> 03:20:29.280
Uh oh, tsunami said, copying him.

03:20:29.340 --> 03:20:31.020
What did I just call him?

03:20:31.079 --> 03:20:33.000
A squid brain?

03:20:33.059 --> 03:20:34.079
Riptide said.

03:20:34.200 --> 03:20:36.780
My new favorite insult, thanks to you.

03:20:36.840 --> 03:20:39.959
I'm not sure this lesson is teaching me

03:20:39.959 --> 03:20:41.159
much more than his did.

03:20:41.219 --> 03:20:42.600
Tsunami pointed out.

03:20:42.719 --> 03:20:46.260
Hey, now I'm offended, he said.

03:20:46.319 --> 03:20:48.479
All right, you asked for it.

03:20:48.540 --> 03:20:51.059
He sat down and pointed to his snout.

03:20:51.120 --> 03:20:54.299
These stripes usually indicate a question

03:20:54.299 --> 03:20:58.139
like this for why, and like this for how

03:20:58.139 --> 03:21:00.540
and like this for when.

03:21:00.659 --> 03:21:04.200
Tsunami mimicked him, memorizing the

03:21:04.200 --> 03:21:05.340
patterns of flashes.

03:21:05.399 --> 03:21:07.139
It was easier than she'd expected.

03:21:07.200 --> 03:21:09.420
Maybe there was one part of being a

03:21:09.420 --> 03:21:10.920
ceiling that she wouldn't be a total

03:21:10.920 --> 03:21:12.059
failure at...

03:21:13.020 --> 03:21:15.180
After she had to question patterns down

03:21:15.180 --> 03:21:17.819
Riptide said, try this one.

03:21:17.879 --> 03:21:22.620
I will protect you.

03:21:22.739 --> 03:21:26.159
Stripes flashed along his side and he

03:21:26.159 --> 03:21:27.120
gestured at the same time.

03:21:27.180 --> 03:21:30.840
I don't need protecting, tsunami said.

03:21:30.899 --> 03:21:34.319
I know, he answered, but knowing you

03:21:34.319 --> 03:21:36.239
you'll probably need to say it to someone

03:21:36.239 --> 03:21:36.719
one day.

03:21:36.780 --> 03:21:39.059
Tsunami liked that.

03:21:39.120 --> 03:21:43.440
I will protect you, she echoed, flashing

03:21:43.440 --> 03:21:44.040
it back at him.

03:21:44.159 --> 03:21:46.200
He smiled a little sadly.

03:21:46.319 --> 03:21:49.200
I wish you could, he said.

03:21:49.260 --> 03:21:50.760
Why not?

03:21:50.819 --> 03:21:51.719
She said.

03:21:51.780 --> 03:21:53.100
I am a princess.

03:21:53.159 --> 03:21:54.360
I can do whatever I want.

03:21:54.479 --> 03:21:58.079
Not while someone else's queen, he

03:21:58.079 --> 03:21:58.559
pointed out.

03:21:58.620 --> 03:22:01.319
All right, here's how you indicate

03:22:01.319 --> 03:22:02.280
different kinds of danger.

03:22:02.340 --> 03:22:05.639
Riptide showed her other stripe patterns

03:22:05.639 --> 03:22:07.559
and some of the talent gestures as well.

03:22:07.620 --> 03:22:10.379
It was all fascinating, and tsunami

03:22:10.379 --> 03:22:12.659
wasn't sure how much time had passed when

03:22:12.659 --> 03:22:14.459
she finally glanced out at the wind

03:22:14.459 --> 03:22:16.440
whipped sea and realized she should be

03:22:16.440 --> 03:22:16.799
getting back.

03:22:16.860 --> 03:22:20.159
Mother might be looking for me, she

03:22:20.159 --> 03:22:22.020
explained, but thank you.

03:22:22.079 --> 03:22:24.360
You have no idea how helpful this was.

03:22:24.420 --> 03:22:28.979
All of this, she thought, realizing she'd

03:22:28.979 --> 03:22:30.899
managed to forget about Gil for a little

03:22:30.899 --> 03:22:31.139
while.

03:22:31.200 --> 03:22:33.899
Has Blister arrived yet?

03:22:33.959 --> 03:22:35.280
Riptide asked.

03:22:35.340 --> 03:22:37.379
Tsunami shook her head.

03:22:37.440 --> 03:22:39.659
He took her front talons in his.

03:22:39.780 --> 03:22:42.899
Be wary of her, he said.

03:22:42.959 --> 03:22:46.020
She has her own plans, and I don't think

03:22:46.020 --> 03:22:47.819
protecting sea wings is high on her

03:22:47.819 --> 03:22:48.120
list.

03:22:48.180 --> 03:22:51.180
I will, tsunami said.

03:22:51.239 --> 03:22:54.059
Oh, she added, freeing her talons.

03:22:54.120 --> 03:22:55.739
What does this mean?

03:22:55.799 --> 03:22:58.799
She tried to imitate the circular gesture

03:22:58.799 --> 03:22:59.940
Shark had made yesterday.

03:23:00.000 --> 03:23:02.459
Riptide tilted his head at her.

03:23:02.520 --> 03:23:06.000
If you mean this, he said, doing it

03:23:06.000 --> 03:23:08.520
perfectly, then it means something like

03:23:08.520 --> 03:23:10.799
not right now, we'll finish this later.

03:23:10.860 --> 03:23:13.440
Tsunami stared at him.

03:23:13.500 --> 03:23:14.760
Are you sure?

03:23:14.819 --> 03:23:18.120
Pretty sure, Riptide said.

03:23:18.180 --> 03:23:19.319
Why?

03:23:19.319 --> 03:23:19.860
Who?

03:23:19.920 --> 03:23:22.139
Yesterday, when I stopped Shark and the

03:23:22.139 --> 03:23:24.540
guards from killing my friends, Tsunami

03:23:24.540 --> 03:23:25.920
said, jumping to her feet.

03:23:25.979 --> 03:23:28.079
That's the gesture he made to them.

03:23:28.139 --> 03:23:30.360
You're telling me he was saying, we'll

03:23:30.360 --> 03:23:31.260
just kill them later?

03:23:31.319 --> 03:23:33.659
Riptide rubbed his snout.

03:23:33.719 --> 03:23:38.040
Maybe, he said unhappily, but if Queen

03:23:38.040 --> 03:23:39.899
Coral hasn't ordered it, then I'm sure.

03:23:39.959 --> 03:23:41.459
How would I know?

03:23:41.520 --> 03:23:43.020
Tsunami cried.

03:23:43.079 --> 03:23:45.299
What if she has ordered it and I didn't

03:23:45.299 --> 03:23:45.840
understand her?

03:23:45.899 --> 03:23:48.360
She ran to the mouth of the cave.

03:23:48.420 --> 03:23:49.799
I have to go back.

03:23:49.860 --> 03:23:51.120
I have to check on them.

03:23:51.180 --> 03:23:52.620
I haven't even seen them since

03:23:52.620 --> 03:23:53.040
yesterday.

03:23:53.100 --> 03:23:56.340
She leaped into the air, catching the air

03:23:56.340 --> 03:23:56.879
currents.

03:23:56.940 --> 03:24:00.180
Be careful, Riptide called after her.

03:24:00.239 --> 03:24:02.280
I'll be out here if you need me.

03:24:02.340 --> 03:24:05.219
Just, the wind yanked away his last

03:24:05.219 --> 03:24:05.819
words.

03:24:05.879 --> 03:24:09.659
Tsunami dove into the water between the

03:24:09.659 --> 03:24:11.100
spiral dragon horn rocks.

03:24:11.159 --> 03:24:13.260
She powered through the kelp into the

03:24:13.260 --> 03:24:15.180
tunnel, shooting between the rock walls.

03:24:15.299 --> 03:24:18.899
She was going so fast, she didn't see the

03:24:18.899 --> 03:24:21.420
dark shape wading above her in one of the

03:24:21.420 --> 03:24:22.020
breathing holes.

03:24:22.079 --> 03:24:25.799
She thought she was alone, until Talons

03:24:25.799 --> 03:24:28.860
slammed into her back, and sharp claws

03:24:28.860 --> 03:24:29.760
closed around her neck.

03:24:29.819 --> 03:24:34.319
Chapter 13.

03:24:34.500 --> 03:24:38.879
Giant wings smashed tsunami to the rock

03:24:38.879 --> 03:24:40.379
floor of the tunnel.

03:24:40.440 --> 03:24:42.420
She tried to twist around, but her

03:24:42.420 --> 03:24:44.399
attacker kicked her in the head, and then

03:24:44.399 --> 03:24:46.440
shoved a hood that smelled of seaweed

03:24:46.440 --> 03:24:48.299
over her snout so she couldn't see.

03:24:48.360 --> 03:24:51.719
Tsunami shouted and struggled, lashing

03:24:51.719 --> 03:24:52.920
out with her claws and tail.

03:24:52.979 --> 03:24:55.799
Her attacker was bigger than her, and

03:24:55.799 --> 03:24:56.219
heavier.

03:24:56.280 --> 03:24:58.620
So tsunami could barely move under the

03:24:58.620 --> 03:24:58.979
weight.

03:24:59.100 --> 03:25:01.739
It seemed like he or she was wearing

03:25:01.739 --> 03:25:03.420
something to make them heavier.

03:25:03.479 --> 03:25:06.000
She felt something metallic clank against

03:25:06.000 --> 03:25:06.959
her spines.

03:25:07.020 --> 03:25:10.500
Fish hook claws dug into her gills, and

03:25:10.500 --> 03:25:11.940
tsunami shrieked with pain.

03:25:12.000 --> 03:25:14.459
She felt blood swirling away from her

03:25:14.459 --> 03:25:15.360
neck into the water.

03:25:15.420 --> 03:25:19.020
I'm not going to die here, she thought

03:25:19.020 --> 03:25:21.479
ferociously. killed by a coward.

03:25:21.540 --> 03:25:22.620
I can't even see.

03:25:22.680 --> 03:25:23.459
I don't think so.

03:25:23.520 --> 03:25:26.819
She remembered how Sonny always managed

03:25:26.819 --> 03:25:28.440
to wriggle free during their battle

03:25:28.440 --> 03:25:29.399
training sessions.

03:25:29.459 --> 03:25:32.100
The tiny dragonette used her small size

03:25:32.100 --> 03:25:35.040
to slip out of almost every hold tsunami

03:25:35.040 --> 03:25:35.579
could think of.

03:25:35.639 --> 03:25:38.760
Tsunami scrunched her legs and wings in

03:25:38.760 --> 03:25:41.159
close and ducked her head, rolling into a

03:25:41.159 --> 03:25:42.180
tight, spiky ball.

03:25:42.239 --> 03:25:44.639
Her attacker's grip loosened around her

03:25:44.639 --> 03:25:47.459
neck, and as the dragon fumbled for

03:25:47.459 --> 03:25:49.979
tsunami's snout, tsunami was able to

03:25:49.979 --> 03:25:52.020
squirm down and shove her opponent over

03:25:52.020 --> 03:25:52.379
her head.

03:25:52.440 --> 03:25:55.920
A blast of bubble slammed into her as the

03:25:55.920 --> 03:25:57.239
dragon crashed into the wall.

03:25:57.299 --> 03:26:00.120
Before she could pull her hood off, the

03:26:00.120 --> 03:26:01.799
talons were back, clutching her

03:26:01.799 --> 03:26:02.280
forearms.

03:26:02.340 --> 03:26:04.799
Tsunami kicked viciously at the

03:26:04.799 --> 03:26:06.659
underbelly that had to be in front of her

03:26:06.659 --> 03:26:09.239
and felt her claws snag painfully on

03:26:09.239 --> 03:26:09.840
metal rings.

03:26:09.899 --> 03:26:12.180
Her attacker made no sound.

03:26:12.239 --> 03:26:15.180
But a moment later, the dragon's tail hit

03:26:15.180 --> 03:26:17.459
tsunami so hard, she thought she heard

03:26:17.459 --> 03:26:18.299
bones crack.

03:26:18.360 --> 03:26:21.239
The other dragon's wings began to press

03:26:21.239 --> 03:26:23.040
her down toward the rock floor again.

03:26:23.100 --> 03:26:25.739
Whoever it was, knew how to fight like a

03:26:25.739 --> 03:26:26.399
sea wing.

03:26:26.459 --> 03:26:28.440
They had all the advantages of this

03:26:28.440 --> 03:26:28.680
world.

03:26:28.739 --> 03:26:31.739
So use something they haven't seen

03:26:31.739 --> 03:26:31.979
before.

03:26:32.040 --> 03:26:34.799
Tsunami thought of how glory used

03:26:34.799 --> 03:26:36.959
distraction whenever she fought Kestrel.

03:26:37.020 --> 03:26:39.719
Tsunami's scales couldn't change color

03:26:39.719 --> 03:26:41.399
but she bet she could still be pretty

03:26:41.399 --> 03:26:42.059
distracting.

03:26:42.120 --> 03:26:45.780
She flared her wings open and closed, open

03:26:45.780 --> 03:26:48.659
and closed as fast as she could, stirring

03:26:48.659 --> 03:26:49.500
up the water around them.

03:26:49.559 --> 03:26:52.079
She felt her attacker pause as if

03:26:52.079 --> 03:26:52.559
confused.

03:26:52.680 --> 03:26:54.780
On her 3rd flare open.

03:26:54.840 --> 03:26:57.299
Tsunami suddenly lit up all the stripes

03:26:57.299 --> 03:26:59.520
all over her body, and what she hoped was

03:26:59.520 --> 03:27:00.420
a blinding flash.

03:27:00.479 --> 03:27:03.899
Her attacker's talons slipped, and

03:27:03.899 --> 03:27:06.059
tsunami struck out with her claws again.

03:27:06.360 --> 03:27:08.819
Again, she flared her stripes as bright

03:27:08.819 --> 03:27:11.040
as she could make them, so she could even

03:27:11.040 --> 03:27:12.239
see the light through her hood.

03:27:12.299 --> 03:27:15.180
She reached to shove her attacker away

03:27:15.180 --> 03:27:18.420
and suddenly, whoever it was, was gone.

03:27:18.479 --> 03:27:21.840
Tsunami flailed in the water for a moment

03:27:21.840 --> 03:27:24.299
fending off the attacks she expected from

03:27:24.299 --> 03:27:27.059
every side, before she realized there was

03:27:27.059 --> 03:27:28.020
no one around her anymore.

03:27:28.079 --> 03:27:30.840
She reached up and yanked off the hood

03:27:30.840 --> 03:27:33.180
then felt the movement of somebody coming

03:27:33.180 --> 03:27:34.559
up the tunnel from the outside.

03:27:34.620 --> 03:27:37.559
She whirled around, ready to fight.

03:27:37.620 --> 03:27:41.040
And riptide, leaped back, waving his

03:27:41.040 --> 03:27:41.340
talons.

03:27:41.459 --> 03:27:44.700
Tsunami whipped her head back and forth

03:27:44.700 --> 03:27:45.899
but there was no sign of anyone else.

03:27:45.959 --> 03:27:47.760
All right?

03:27:47.819 --> 03:27:49.379
Riptide signaled.

03:27:49.440 --> 03:27:50.579
Who?

03:27:50.639 --> 03:27:52.860
She signaled back with the stripes on her

03:27:52.860 --> 03:27:53.219
snout.

03:27:53.280 --> 03:27:54.420
Who?

03:27:54.479 --> 03:27:56.819
She didn't have any of the other words

03:27:56.819 --> 03:27:57.719
she needed.

03:27:57.840 --> 03:28:00.479
He spread his webbed claws.

03:28:00.540 --> 03:28:01.799
I don't know.

03:28:01.860 --> 03:28:03.659
Then he pointed at her.

03:28:03.719 --> 03:28:05.100
All right.

03:28:05.159 --> 03:28:08.159
He lit up all his stripes, and she

03:28:08.159 --> 03:28:09.420
guessed he'd seen the light from

03:28:09.420 --> 03:28:09.659
outside.

03:28:09.780 --> 03:28:12.299
She nodded impatiently.

03:28:12.420 --> 03:28:14.940
She didn't have any way to explain she

03:28:14.940 --> 03:28:17.399
was grateful he'd come, but she needed to

03:28:17.399 --> 03:28:19.139
chase down her attacker now.

03:28:19.260 --> 03:28:21.899
All right, she signaled back.

03:28:21.959 --> 03:28:24.899
Then she spun away, swimming fast down

03:28:24.899 --> 03:28:26.340
the tunnel toward the palace.

03:28:26.399 --> 03:28:29.879
Tsunami burst out of the water into a

03:28:29.879 --> 03:28:31.260
scene of eerie calm.

03:28:31.319 --> 03:28:33.780
Dragons were lounging peacefully on

03:28:33.780 --> 03:28:36.239
beaches and cliff edges or playing

03:28:36.239 --> 03:28:38.100
underwater, and darting through the

03:28:38.100 --> 03:28:38.700
waterfalls.

03:28:38.760 --> 03:28:41.700
She searched the water and the pavilion

03:28:41.700 --> 03:28:43.979
with her gaze, looking for anyone who

03:28:43.979 --> 03:28:45.420
might have just been in a fight.

03:28:45.479 --> 03:28:48.180
Surely she had left some kind of mark on

03:28:48.180 --> 03:28:48.780
her attacker.

03:28:48.840 --> 03:28:51.420
No one was acting suspicious.

03:28:51.479 --> 03:28:54.420
Tsunami glanced up and saw her mother's

03:28:54.420 --> 03:28:56.459
tail poking off a level of the pavilion

03:28:56.459 --> 03:28:58.559
near the top, the library level.

03:28:58.620 --> 03:29:01.680
She beat her wings, rose out of the water

03:29:01.680 --> 03:29:02.639
and flew up to her.

03:29:02.700 --> 03:29:04.559
Hello, dear.

03:29:04.680 --> 03:29:07.260
Queen Coral said a tsunami landed.

03:29:07.319 --> 03:29:10.500
She was surrounded by scrolls, several of

03:29:10.500 --> 03:29:11.399
them half unrolled.

03:29:11.459 --> 03:29:14.100
Anemone was curled on a curved white

03:29:14.100 --> 03:29:16.379
boulder beside her, looking bored out of

03:29:16.379 --> 03:29:16.979
her mind.

03:29:17.040 --> 03:29:19.440
I've been reading out loud to your

03:29:19.440 --> 03:29:19.799
sister.

03:29:19.920 --> 03:29:21.840
It's her favorite part of the day.

03:29:21.899 --> 03:29:24.959
We've just finished the story of how I

03:29:24.959 --> 03:29:26.579
chose Gil to be my husband.

03:29:26.639 --> 03:29:28.860
She sighed gustily.

03:29:28.920 --> 03:29:31.079
He adored my writing too.

03:29:31.200 --> 03:29:34.020
Mother, tsunami started.

03:29:34.079 --> 03:29:38.340
He was a perfect candidate for king, Coral

03:29:38.340 --> 03:29:38.639
said.

03:29:38.700 --> 03:29:41.040
He came from a very noble family.

03:29:41.100 --> 03:29:44.100
Nothing to worry about in his ancestry.

03:29:44.159 --> 03:29:46.799
A lot like Whirlpool and his intelligence

03:29:46.799 --> 03:29:47.159
too.

03:29:47.280 --> 03:29:49.200
Coral sighed again.

03:29:49.260 --> 03:29:52.319
Mother, tsunami said again.

03:29:52.379 --> 03:29:55.620
Luckily, you've arrived just in time for

03:29:55.620 --> 03:29:58.139
my epic poem on the differences between

03:29:58.139 --> 03:29:59.760
oysters and clams.

03:29:59.819 --> 03:30:03.420
It's an elegantly well crafted metaphor

03:30:03.420 --> 03:30:05.579
about class differences and genetic

03:30:05.579 --> 03:30:08.159
superiority, as Whirlpool always says.

03:30:08.219 --> 03:30:12.180
Mother, tsunami interrupted firmly.

03:30:12.239 --> 03:30:14.520
Someone just tried to kill me.

03:30:14.579 --> 03:30:17.700
Queen Coral sat up, scattering drops of

03:30:17.700 --> 03:30:18.659
ink from her claws.

03:30:18.719 --> 03:30:19.860
What?

03:30:19.920 --> 03:30:21.899
Who dared?

03:30:21.959 --> 03:30:24.780
I don't know, but they must be here now.

03:30:24.840 --> 03:30:26.219
Tsunami said.

03:30:26.280 --> 03:30:28.379
Somewhere in the palace, we should gather

03:30:28.379 --> 03:30:30.600
everyone and the eggs.

03:30:30.719 --> 03:30:32.159
Queen Coral yelped.

03:30:32.280 --> 03:30:34.020
The eggs must be in danger.

03:30:34.079 --> 03:30:36.600
She started flinging scrolls back into

03:30:36.600 --> 03:30:37.500
cauldrons.

03:30:37.559 --> 03:30:38.579
What?

03:30:38.639 --> 03:30:40.620
Tsunami said, bewildered.

03:30:40.680 --> 03:30:42.180
What eggs?

03:30:42.239 --> 03:30:46.200
Two eggs with female dragonettes, Anemone

03:30:46.200 --> 03:30:47.280
explained to tsunami.

03:30:47.340 --> 03:30:49.500
They're in the royal hatchery, in the

03:30:49.500 --> 03:30:50.219
deep palace.

03:30:50.280 --> 03:30:51.780
They're due to hatch in a couple of

03:30:51.780 --> 03:30:52.260
days.

03:30:52.319 --> 03:30:55.500
And if someone attacked you, they'll

03:30:55.500 --> 03:30:57.719
probably go after the eggs too, Queen

03:30:57.719 --> 03:30:58.500
Coral cried.

03:30:58.559 --> 03:31:01.139
She dashed to the edge of the pavilion.

03:31:01.200 --> 03:31:03.360
Moray, whirlpool.

03:31:03.420 --> 03:31:04.020
Hurry.

03:31:04.079 --> 03:31:07.680
But my attacker is here, tsunami said.

03:31:07.739 --> 03:31:08.760
I'm sure of it.

03:31:08.819 --> 03:31:10.260
Not at the deep palace.

03:31:10.379 --> 03:31:12.659
So we have to get there first.

03:31:12.719 --> 03:31:14.700
Queen Carl insisted.

03:31:14.760 --> 03:31:17.700
But we could catch them here.

03:31:17.760 --> 03:31:20.579
Tsunami didn't understand why her mother

03:31:20.579 --> 03:31:22.319
couldn't see the obvious thing to do.

03:31:22.440 --> 03:31:25.860
Mother, what about tortoise?

03:31:25.920 --> 03:31:27.299
Anemone asked.

03:31:27.360 --> 03:31:29.219
She's supposed to guard them, isn't she?

03:31:29.280 --> 03:31:31.500
That's mother's council chief of

03:31:31.500 --> 03:31:33.239
Dragonette Care, she explained to

03:31:33.239 --> 03:31:33.899
tsunami.

03:31:33.959 --> 03:31:35.399
This week anyway.

03:31:35.459 --> 03:31:37.920
The others have all failed me.

03:31:37.979 --> 03:31:39.899
Queen Carl said with a grimace.

03:31:40.020 --> 03:31:42.059
Tortoise probably will as well.

03:31:42.120 --> 03:31:43.739
She didn't even want the job.

03:31:43.799 --> 03:31:44.940
Nobody wants it.

03:31:45.000 --> 03:31:47.520
The most important duty in the kingdom of

03:31:47.520 --> 03:31:50.340
the sea, and all my cowardly subjects

03:31:50.340 --> 03:31:51.180
hide from it.

03:31:51.239 --> 03:31:53.399
Moray, she bellowed.

03:31:53.459 --> 03:31:55.379
Yes, Your Majesty.

03:31:55.500 --> 03:31:58.260
Moray slithered up from the level below.

03:31:58.319 --> 03:32:00.899
Tsunami eyed her as she climbed onto the

03:32:00.899 --> 03:32:01.979
library floor.

03:32:02.040 --> 03:32:04.200
Did she look like she'd just been in a

03:32:04.200 --> 03:32:04.500
fight?

03:32:04.559 --> 03:32:06.420
Tsunami couldn't tell.

03:32:06.540 --> 03:32:08.639
Moray wouldn't look at her, but that

03:32:08.639 --> 03:32:09.299
wasn't new.

03:32:09.360 --> 03:32:12.959
Moray, we must get to the Deep Palace at

03:32:12.959 --> 03:32:14.700
once, Queen Coral said.

03:32:14.760 --> 03:32:16.739
I feel that my eggs are in danger.

03:32:16.799 --> 03:32:18.420
My scales tell me so.

03:32:18.540 --> 03:32:21.540
What about whoever attacked me?

03:32:21.600 --> 03:32:22.979
Tsunami demanded.

03:32:23.040 --> 03:32:25.139
We had to catch them and punish them.

03:32:25.200 --> 03:32:27.840
It's more important to stop them from

03:32:27.840 --> 03:32:30.180
hurting my eggs, Queen Coral said

03:32:30.180 --> 03:32:30.600
grimly.

03:32:30.659 --> 03:32:33.180
Someone has been killing my daughters for

03:32:33.180 --> 03:32:33.420
years.

03:32:33.479 --> 03:32:36.899
These are the last 2 Gil left me, and I

03:32:36.899 --> 03:32:38.280
won't let anything happen to them.

03:32:38.340 --> 03:32:41.040
She turned to Moray, who was sitting

03:32:41.040 --> 03:32:43.079
close beside her and gazing worshipfully

03:32:43.079 --> 03:32:45.840
at the queen, I wish you would guard them

03:32:45.840 --> 03:32:46.020
dear.

03:32:46.139 --> 03:32:47.940
You never fail me.

03:32:48.059 --> 03:32:51.120
But everything I do for your scrolls is

03:32:51.120 --> 03:32:53.700
so terribly important, Mori said.

03:32:53.760 --> 03:32:55.920
They're like your other children, really.

03:32:55.979 --> 03:32:57.420
I couldn't abandon them.

03:32:57.540 --> 03:32:59.159
That's true.

03:32:59.219 --> 03:33:01.079
Queen Coral said.

03:33:01.139 --> 03:33:03.420
She patted her pearls and flicked her

03:33:03.420 --> 03:33:03.840
wings open.

03:33:03.899 --> 03:33:07.020
Behind your back, tsunami caught Moray

03:33:07.020 --> 03:33:08.879
shooting a look full of hatred at

03:33:08.879 --> 03:33:09.479
anemone.

03:33:09.540 --> 03:33:11.579
Wow, she thought.

03:33:11.639 --> 03:33:13.260
I wonder what that's for.

03:33:13.319 --> 03:33:16.260
Do you hate all of Queen Coral's

03:33:16.260 --> 03:33:16.559
daughters?

03:33:16.620 --> 03:33:18.899
Enough to try to kill me?

03:33:18.959 --> 03:33:22.079
I sent Shark on ahead this morning after

03:33:22.079 --> 03:33:24.239
breakfast, but he never worries enough

03:33:24.239 --> 03:33:27.180
Queen Coral said, clicking her claws

03:33:27.180 --> 03:33:27.420
together.

03:33:27.479 --> 03:33:29.760
He doesn't even believe there's an

03:33:29.760 --> 03:33:30.420
assassin.

03:33:30.479 --> 03:33:32.159
He thinks it's all bad luck.

03:33:32.219 --> 03:33:34.559
She shook herself with a hiss.

03:33:34.620 --> 03:33:37.680
He even told me once that perhaps I

03:33:37.680 --> 03:33:39.000
wasn't meant to have daughters.

03:33:39.059 --> 03:33:42.180
He's lucky he's my brother, and your

03:33:42.180 --> 03:33:44.100
father, Moray, so I let him live.

03:33:44.219 --> 03:33:46.440
Whirlpool, where are you?

03:33:46.559 --> 03:33:49.739
Anemone winced and put her talons over

03:33:49.739 --> 03:33:50.219
her ears.

03:33:50.280 --> 03:33:52.799
Stay very close to me in the deep

03:33:52.799 --> 03:33:53.459
palace.

03:33:53.520 --> 03:33:55.319
The queen ordered tsunami.

03:33:55.379 --> 03:33:58.200
We really have to put a rush order on a

03:33:58.200 --> 03:33:58.799
harness for you.

03:33:58.860 --> 03:34:01.319
They've been working on 2 for the new

03:34:01.319 --> 03:34:03.719
Dragon Eds, but clearly yours is an

03:34:03.719 --> 03:34:04.200
emergency.

03:34:04.260 --> 03:34:08.280
I can take care of myself, Tsunami said

03:34:08.340 --> 03:34:09.059
ruffled.

03:34:09.120 --> 03:34:12.000
Obviously, I'm still alive, so whoever

03:34:12.000 --> 03:34:13.020
attacked me failed.

03:34:13.079 --> 03:34:16.379
She gave Moray a hard look, but the

03:34:16.379 --> 03:34:18.180
council dragon only shifted her wings as

03:34:18.180 --> 03:34:18.899
if she didn't care.

03:34:18.959 --> 03:34:21.719
Pitter patter, pitter patter.

03:34:21.780 --> 03:34:24.600
All the dragons glanced up at the canopy

03:34:24.600 --> 03:34:25.260
far overhead.

03:34:25.319 --> 03:34:27.959
Raindrops were spattering across the

03:34:27.959 --> 03:34:28.500
green leaves.

03:34:28.559 --> 03:34:34.440
Ah, the precipitation I predicted, said

03:34:34.440 --> 03:34:36.659
Whirlpool, landing beside Coral.

03:34:36.719 --> 03:34:40.319
My apologies for not appearing instantly

03:34:40.319 --> 03:34:40.979
Your Majesty.

03:34:41.040 --> 03:34:44.940
I was distributing scrolls to the kitchen

03:34:44.940 --> 03:34:45.479
staff.

03:34:45.600 --> 03:34:49.079
He didn't look as if he'd been in a fight

03:34:49.079 --> 03:34:51.120
and tsunami didn't really think the

03:34:51.120 --> 03:34:52.979
ridiculous dragon could have overpowered

03:34:52.979 --> 03:34:53.639
her for a moment.

03:34:53.700 --> 03:34:56.579
We're going to the Deep Palace.

03:34:56.639 --> 03:34:58.920
Now, as fast as we can.

03:34:58.979 --> 03:35:02.340
Queen Carl dove over the edge so suddenly

03:35:02.340 --> 03:35:04.319
that anemone was yanked off her talons

03:35:04.319 --> 03:35:04.739
after her.

03:35:04.860 --> 03:35:08.100
Tsunami followed and found herself in a

03:35:08.100 --> 03:35:10.799
swarm of dragons midair, as all the

03:35:10.799 --> 03:35:12.959
council members hurried after Queen Coral

03:35:12.959 --> 03:35:13.379
as well.

03:35:13.379 --> 03:35:17.040
They crowded into the tunnel, tales

03:35:17.040 --> 03:35:19.379
smacking into snouts and wings tangling.

03:35:19.500 --> 03:35:22.319
Tsunami got pushed into the middle and

03:35:22.319 --> 03:35:24.420
found herself swimming beside Whirlpool.

03:35:24.479 --> 03:35:27.780
Too late, she remembered she had meant to

03:35:27.780 --> 03:35:29.340
check on her friends.

03:35:29.399 --> 03:35:31.559
Why can't I be a better dragon?

03:35:31.620 --> 03:35:33.299
She berated herself.

03:35:33.360 --> 03:35:36.180
She tried to turn and go back, but

03:35:36.180 --> 03:35:37.920
council dragons were there shoving her

03:35:37.920 --> 03:35:38.159
forward.

03:35:38.219 --> 03:35:41.159
After nearly getting clawed in the face a

03:35:41.159 --> 03:35:42.479
few times, she gave up.

03:35:42.540 --> 03:35:45.840
Surely they're all right, especially if

03:35:45.840 --> 03:35:47.399
shark is in the deep palace already.

03:35:47.459 --> 03:35:49.979
I'll come right back and see them after

03:35:49.979 --> 03:35:51.000
we check on the eggs.

03:35:51.059 --> 03:35:55.680
Out in the sea, Queen Coral immediately

03:35:55.680 --> 03:35:57.360
found a current and swept off.

03:35:57.420 --> 03:36:00.479
One by one, each of the dragons followed

03:36:00.479 --> 03:36:00.659
her.

03:36:00.719 --> 03:36:04.319
Tsunami glanced around, scanning the

03:36:04.319 --> 03:36:06.000
coral reefs and underwater boulders.

03:36:06.120 --> 03:36:08.940
Her heart jumped a little as she caught a

03:36:08.940 --> 03:36:10.500
glimpse of sky blue scales.

03:36:10.500 --> 03:36:13.559
Riptide was still out there, watching for

03:36:13.559 --> 03:36:13.799
her.

03:36:13.860 --> 03:36:16.979
She waited a moment until she saw him

03:36:16.979 --> 03:36:19.079
dart from one rock to another.

03:36:19.319 --> 03:36:22.260
He was following them, following her, to

03:36:22.260 --> 03:36:25.680
the deep palace. pleased, although she

03:36:25.680 --> 03:36:26.940
felt a bit silly about it.

03:36:27.000 --> 03:36:29.579
She swam into the current, and let it

03:36:29.579 --> 03:36:30.840
carry her after the others.

03:36:30.899 --> 03:36:33.239
She was starting to get the trick of how

03:36:33.239 --> 03:36:35.760
to angle her wings, so it could sweep her

03:36:35.760 --> 03:36:37.260
along as fast as possible.

03:36:37.319 --> 03:36:40.500
It was a bit like flying, but with a lot

03:36:40.500 --> 03:36:41.280
more to dodge.

03:36:41.399 --> 03:36:44.639
Then again, fish managed to get out of

03:36:44.639 --> 03:36:46.319
the way pretty fast when they saw the

03:36:46.319 --> 03:36:46.979
dragons coming.

03:36:47.040 --> 03:36:50.940
Above them, rain pattered down harder and

03:36:50.940 --> 03:36:52.559
harder on the water's surface.

03:36:52.620 --> 03:36:56.159
The light faded, and tsunami imagined the

03:36:56.159 --> 03:36:57.719
dark clouds rolling in.

03:36:57.780 --> 03:36:59.819
She hoped her friends would be all right

03:36:59.819 --> 03:37:01.500
in the Summer Palace.

03:37:01.559 --> 03:37:03.059
Surely there were storms there all the

03:37:03.059 --> 03:37:03.299
time.

03:37:03.360 --> 03:37:05.819
At least they were in a cave so they

03:37:05.819 --> 03:37:06.360
wouldn't get wet.

03:37:06.479 --> 03:37:10.559
Two giant sea turtles swam by, going in

03:37:10.559 --> 03:37:11.040
the other direction.

03:37:11.159 --> 03:37:14.520
They eyed the dragons warily, but nobody

03:37:14.520 --> 03:37:15.479
stopped to eat them.

03:37:15.540 --> 03:37:19.020
Explosions of tiny pink fish popped in

03:37:19.020 --> 03:37:21.180
and out of the waving anemones along the

03:37:21.180 --> 03:37:21.959
coral reefs.

03:37:22.020 --> 03:37:24.899
Something large and yellow was lying flat

03:37:24.899 --> 03:37:25.739
against the sand.

03:37:25.799 --> 03:37:29.340
It opened its eyes, stared at tsunami, and

03:37:29.340 --> 03:37:29.879
closed them again.

03:37:29.940 --> 03:37:34.139
After a while, an island loomed in front

03:37:34.139 --> 03:37:36.299
of them, with immense coral reefs

03:37:36.299 --> 03:37:39.059
clustered all around it, orange branches

03:37:39.059 --> 03:37:41.940
twined around purple star shaped clusters

03:37:41.940 --> 03:37:45.719
lacy fans, the color of rust sprouted

03:37:45.719 --> 03:37:47.639
from pale pink umbrella shapes.

03:37:47.700 --> 03:37:50.280
Blue and silver fish darted in and out of

03:37:50.280 --> 03:37:50.760
the holes.

03:37:50.879 --> 03:37:54.479
The sea wings swam out of the current, and

03:37:54.479 --> 03:37:56.879
around the bend of the reef, and then the

03:37:56.879 --> 03:37:59.219
lead dragons ducked into a canyon in the

03:37:59.219 --> 03:37:59.639
ocean floor.

03:37:59.700 --> 03:38:02.760
Tsunami followed them down.

03:38:02.940 --> 03:38:05.219
As her eyes adjusted to the growing

03:38:05.219 --> 03:38:08.280
darkness, she saw a vast expanse of white

03:38:08.280 --> 03:38:10.979
and green coral reef, spreading along the

03:38:10.979 --> 03:38:12.600
sides and floor of the canyon.

03:38:12.719 --> 03:38:15.899
It curled into caves and towers, and

03:38:15.899 --> 03:38:18.000
underwater gardens full of glowing

03:38:18.000 --> 03:38:18.479
colors.

03:38:18.540 --> 03:38:20.399
In the center of the canyon.

03:38:20.459 --> 03:38:23.219
The corals spiraled up into an enormous

03:38:23.219 --> 03:38:25.979
palace, swarming with sea wings.

03:38:26.040 --> 03:38:29.879
Sea wings were everywhere, swimming in

03:38:29.879 --> 03:38:31.680
and out of the windows and doors of the

03:38:31.680 --> 03:38:34.260
palace, shooting up to the surface and

03:38:34.260 --> 03:38:36.059
diving to the bottom of the canyon

03:38:36.059 --> 03:38:38.940
tending the gardens, gently cleaning the

03:38:38.940 --> 03:38:41.459
coral, lugging large fish in from the

03:38:41.459 --> 03:38:43.920
hunt, or sitting in small circles with

03:38:43.920 --> 03:38:46.319
groups of dragonettes, reading from thin

03:38:46.319 --> 03:38:47.280
stone tablets.

03:38:47.340 --> 03:38:50.760
The only signs of the war were a few

03:38:50.760 --> 03:38:52.920
troops drilling in formation around the

03:38:52.920 --> 03:38:55.500
palace, and a group of soldiers gathered

03:38:55.500 --> 03:38:57.780
in one of the gardens, each with terrible

03:38:57.780 --> 03:38:58.979
bandaged wounds.

03:38:59.040 --> 03:39:02.819
Tsunami saw 2 with missing feet, one with

03:39:02.819 --> 03:39:04.739
scorched holes where his eyes should have

03:39:04.739 --> 03:39:07.139
been, and several with black scars

03:39:07.139 --> 03:39:08.760
twisting their wings or tail.

03:39:08.819 --> 03:39:12.420
Several couldn't swim anymore, but had to

03:39:12.420 --> 03:39:13.979
be helped through the water by nurse

03:39:13.979 --> 03:39:14.520
dragons.

03:39:14.579 --> 03:39:18.719
As Queen Carl swam past, dragons snapped

03:39:18.719 --> 03:39:20.819
to attention, saluting or waving.

03:39:20.879 --> 03:39:23.579
She waved to each of them with a wide

03:39:23.579 --> 03:39:23.879
smile.

03:39:23.940 --> 03:39:26.700
Tsunami noticed that most of them waved

03:39:26.700 --> 03:39:29.040
to anemone too, and the little dragonette

03:39:29.040 --> 03:39:30.059
smiled and waved back.

03:39:30.120 --> 03:39:33.479
Surrounded by council members, for once

03:39:33.479 --> 03:39:35.579
tsunami was able to sweep by without a

03:39:35.579 --> 03:39:36.780
whole lot of staring and pointing.

03:39:36.840 --> 03:39:39.659
For a little while at least, nobody knew

03:39:39.659 --> 03:39:40.079
who she was.

03:39:40.139 --> 03:39:43.440
They swam through the wide front entrance

03:39:43.440 --> 03:39:46.020
into a coral cavern, sparkling with

03:39:46.020 --> 03:39:47.520
emeralds and sapphires.

03:39:47.579 --> 03:39:50.579
A statue of queen coral loomed in a

03:39:50.579 --> 03:39:52.620
center, her talons outstretched

03:39:52.620 --> 03:39:53.340
benevolently.

03:39:53.399 --> 03:39:56.219
Seawing servants hurried in from all

03:39:56.219 --> 03:39:58.680
directions, their luminescent stripes

03:39:58.680 --> 03:39:59.700
flashing at the queen.

03:39:59.760 --> 03:40:03.120
Coral swept past them all and charged

03:40:03.120 --> 03:40:04.920
down a tunnel in the back of the hall.

03:40:04.920 --> 03:40:07.620
Some of the council broke away to swim to

03:40:07.620 --> 03:40:10.260
other parts of the palace, but Moray and

03:40:10.260 --> 03:40:12.540
Whirlpool stayed with the queen, and so

03:40:12.540 --> 03:40:13.500
did tsunami.

03:40:13.559 --> 03:40:16.860
The tunnel curved down and around in a

03:40:16.860 --> 03:40:19.620
spiral, getting warmer and warmer as they

03:40:19.620 --> 03:40:20.040
descended.

03:40:20.100 --> 03:40:23.700
Tsunami felt warm jets of water bubbling

03:40:23.700 --> 03:40:25.500
up through the coral under her talons.

03:40:25.559 --> 03:40:28.979
At the bottom was a stone door, and in

03:40:28.979 --> 03:40:31.680
front of the door, a skinny seaweed green

03:40:31.680 --> 03:40:34.020
dragon crouched, gobbling something

03:40:34.020 --> 03:40:35.219
hungrily in her claws.

03:40:35.280 --> 03:40:38.940
Her eyes went wide when she saw the queen

03:40:38.940 --> 03:40:40.860
and she dropped her octopus with a

03:40:40.860 --> 03:40:41.159
shriek.

03:40:41.219 --> 03:40:44.340
The remains floated up to the ceiling as

03:40:44.340 --> 03:40:46.200
she flapped her talons in a panic

03:40:46.200 --> 03:40:49.020
flashing her stripes so fast, she looked

03:40:49.020 --> 03:40:50.639
like a lightning storm gone mad.

03:40:50.700 --> 03:40:54.600
Queen Coral roared and threw the door

03:40:54.600 --> 03:40:56.940
open, smacking the green dragon back

03:40:56.940 --> 03:40:57.540
against the wall.

03:40:57.600 --> 03:41:01.200
The queen shot inside, towing anemone

03:41:01.200 --> 03:41:01.559
behind her.

03:41:01.620 --> 03:41:04.920
This is where I should have hatched

03:41:04.920 --> 03:41:07.799
tsunami thought, with a rush of confused

03:41:07.799 --> 03:41:08.399
excitement.

03:41:08.459 --> 03:41:11.340
She swam through the doorway and gazed

03:41:11.340 --> 03:41:11.639
around.

03:41:11.700 --> 03:41:14.100
The royal hatchery.

03:41:14.159 --> 03:41:18.000
The warm jets bubbled along every wall

03:41:18.000 --> 03:41:20.399
heating the room, which was shaped like

03:41:20.399 --> 03:41:22.680
the inside of a large pale egg.

03:41:22.739 --> 03:41:26.040
A sea wing dragon carved from dark green

03:41:26.040 --> 03:41:28.139
marble stood in the center of the room.

03:41:28.200 --> 03:41:31.079
Garlands of blue and purple underwater

03:41:31.079 --> 03:41:33.479
plants were woven through her horns and

03:41:33.479 --> 03:41:34.260
along her wings.

03:41:34.319 --> 03:41:37.799
The base of the statue said, Orca.

03:41:37.860 --> 03:41:41.219
She looked tough and beautiful at the

03:41:41.219 --> 03:41:41.819
same time.

03:41:41.879 --> 03:41:44.819
Tsunome wondered if Queen Coral's 1st

03:41:44.819 --> 03:41:47.100
daughter had carved her own self portrait

03:41:47.100 --> 03:41:49.680
and if she'd known it would be a memorial

03:41:49.680 --> 03:41:49.979
one day.

03:41:50.040 --> 03:41:53.399
She glanced around and caught the hateful

03:41:53.399 --> 03:41:54.959
look Moray shot the statue.

03:41:55.020 --> 03:41:58.260
Maybe all her fawning over the queen is

03:41:58.260 --> 03:42:01.020
for real, tsunami realized.

03:42:01.079 --> 03:42:03.719
Maybe she actually means it when she goes

03:42:03.719 --> 03:42:06.120
on and on about how wonderful Queen Coral

03:42:06.120 --> 03:42:06.360
is.

03:42:06.479 --> 03:42:10.200
Maybe she would even do anything to

03:42:10.200 --> 03:42:11.879
protect Coral from her daughters.

03:42:11.940 --> 03:42:15.540
Nests made of seaweed were tucked into

03:42:15.540 --> 03:42:18.059
niches in the floor, with wide pathways

03:42:18.059 --> 03:42:19.139
stretching between them.

03:42:19.200 --> 03:42:22.680
Dragon eggs took a year to hatch, so

03:42:22.680 --> 03:42:24.059
there should have been clutches at

03:42:24.059 --> 03:42:26.520
different stages, from newly laid to

03:42:26.520 --> 03:42:28.979
nearly hatched, but there were no new

03:42:28.979 --> 03:42:29.760
eggs to be seen.

03:42:29.819 --> 03:42:32.459
Because Gil has been gone.

03:42:32.520 --> 03:42:35.579
Tsunami thought with a stab of guilt.

03:42:35.639 --> 03:42:37.139
Andy's not coming back.

03:42:37.200 --> 03:42:41.219
One clutch of 3 eggs was tucked against a

03:42:41.219 --> 03:42:43.799
wall, and in the nest farthest from the

03:42:43.799 --> 03:42:45.479
door, there were 2 eggs.

03:42:45.540 --> 03:42:48.840
Queen Coral hurried to the far nest and

03:42:48.840 --> 03:42:52.200
roared again, a howl of fury and despair

03:42:52.200 --> 03:42:53.879
that reverberated through the water.

03:42:53.940 --> 03:42:57.479
She sank down beside the nest and picked

03:42:57.479 --> 03:42:59.219
up a piece of broken eggshell.

03:42:59.340 --> 03:43:00.959
Oh no.

03:43:01.020 --> 03:43:04.920
Tsunami started forward, but Moray pushed

03:43:04.920 --> 03:43:06.780
past her and knelt beside the queen

03:43:06.780 --> 03:43:08.100
leaning against her side.

03:43:08.159 --> 03:43:11.399
Enemone glanced back at tsunami, looking

03:43:11.399 --> 03:43:11.819
sick.

03:43:11.879 --> 03:43:15.780
One of the eggs was still intact, but the

03:43:15.780 --> 03:43:16.559
other was smashed.

03:43:16.680 --> 03:43:19.319
The little blue dragonette inside had

03:43:19.319 --> 03:43:20.399
been strangled to death.

03:43:20.520 --> 03:43:23.219
Her neck was twisted in a horrible way

03:43:23.219 --> 03:43:26.340
and her head flopped sadly as Queen Coral

03:43:26.340 --> 03:43:27.239
gently picked her up.

03:43:27.299 --> 03:43:30.420
Tsunami stared at the body in shock.

03:43:30.479 --> 03:43:34.739
It, she, was so tiny.

03:43:34.799 --> 03:43:37.739
Who would do this to a baby dragonette?

03:43:37.860 --> 03:43:39.360
How could anyone?

03:43:39.479 --> 03:43:41.700
To my sister.

03:43:41.819 --> 03:43:45.540
She felt anemone's cold talons slip into

03:43:45.540 --> 03:43:47.219
hers and she squeezed them tightly.

03:43:47.280 --> 03:43:50.700
Whoever it was, wanted to do this to

03:43:50.700 --> 03:43:51.719
anemone as well.

03:43:51.780 --> 03:43:54.360
This was why the queen insisted on the

03:43:54.360 --> 03:43:56.579
harness and protected her daughter in

03:43:56.579 --> 03:43:57.420
such an extreme way.

03:43:57.540 --> 03:44:00.719
Seeing the broken body of the hatchling

03:44:00.719 --> 03:44:03.000
tsunami felt nearly crazy enough to do

03:44:03.000 --> 03:44:03.600
the same.

03:44:03.600 --> 03:44:08.459
No one would ever, ever hurt anemone, not

03:44:08.459 --> 03:44:09.600
while tsunami was around.

03:44:09.659 --> 03:44:12.299
And whatever she had to do to protect

03:44:12.299 --> 03:44:14.340
that other egg, she would.

03:44:14.399 --> 03:44:20.700
Chapter 14.

03:44:20.879 --> 03:44:25.139
Queen Coral rose to her feet, knocking

03:44:25.139 --> 03:44:25.979
Moray aside.

03:44:26.100 --> 03:44:28.799
She shot back across the cave to the door

03:44:28.799 --> 03:44:30.899
but the skinny green dragon was gone.

03:44:30.959 --> 03:44:34.020
Anemone yelped a stream of bubbles as the

03:44:34.020 --> 03:44:35.819
queen blasted up the tunnel with her in

03:44:35.819 --> 03:44:36.120
tow.

03:44:36.239 --> 03:44:39.899
Tsunami started after them, then turned

03:44:39.899 --> 03:44:42.299
and looked down at the last egg.

03:44:42.360 --> 03:44:44.579
Moray had already followed Coral.

03:44:44.639 --> 03:44:47.459
Whirlpool was hovering uselessly in the

03:44:47.459 --> 03:44:47.819
doorway.

03:44:47.879 --> 03:44:51.540
If tsunami went after Coral as well, who

03:44:51.540 --> 03:44:52.979
would be left to guard the egg?

03:44:52.979 --> 03:44:56.219
But no one can get in except through that

03:44:56.219 --> 03:44:58.739
door, she thought, staring around.

03:44:58.799 --> 03:45:01.500
That door from that tunnel.

03:45:01.559 --> 03:45:04.500
So how did someone get past tortoise?

03:45:04.620 --> 03:45:07.920
She turned in a circle, staring at the

03:45:07.920 --> 03:45:08.940
smooth walls.

03:45:09.000 --> 03:45:12.659
Come to think of it, how did webs get in

03:45:12.659 --> 03:45:13.739
here to steal my egg?

03:45:13.799 --> 03:45:16.559
Surely there had been guards back then

03:45:16.559 --> 03:45:16.979
too.

03:45:17.040 --> 03:45:19.620
Surely the queen had tried to protect her

03:45:19.620 --> 03:45:21.299
eggs even 6 years ago.

03:45:21.360 --> 03:45:23.819
Webbs couldn't have fought past them

03:45:23.819 --> 03:45:24.540
alone.

03:45:24.600 --> 03:45:25.920
So how did he get in?

03:45:25.979 --> 03:45:29.399
Tsunami narrowed her eyes of the nests

03:45:29.399 --> 03:45:30.479
and the stone dragon.

03:45:30.540 --> 03:45:32.520
A secret entrance.

03:45:32.579 --> 03:45:33.780
There must be.

03:45:33.899 --> 03:45:36.479
Well, one thing was for sure.

03:45:36.540 --> 03:45:39.059
She wasn't leaving this egg alone in

03:45:39.059 --> 03:45:39.299
here.

03:45:39.479 --> 03:45:42.899
She crouched beside the nest and gently

03:45:42.899 --> 03:45:44.760
lifted up the last intact egg.

03:45:44.819 --> 03:45:48.600
It was surprisingly heavy, or perhaps not

03:45:48.600 --> 03:45:50.579
that surprising, considering a baby

03:45:50.579 --> 03:45:52.500
dragonette was supposed to pop out of it

03:45:52.500 --> 03:45:53.280
in a day or two.

03:45:53.340 --> 03:45:56.700
Cradling the egg to her chest, tsunami

03:45:56.700 --> 03:45:57.959
swam out the door of the cave.

03:45:58.020 --> 03:46:01.379
Whirlpool flashed a whole lot of stripes

03:46:01.379 --> 03:46:04.139
at her, waving his talons indignantly and

03:46:04.139 --> 03:46:04.920
pointing at the egg.

03:46:04.979 --> 03:46:08.459
Tsunami gave him a wide-eyed, puzzled

03:46:08.459 --> 03:46:08.940
expression.

03:46:09.059 --> 03:46:11.940
Maybe you should have taught me some real

03:46:11.940 --> 03:46:14.940
aquatic sea slug, then you could yell at

03:46:14.940 --> 03:46:16.440
me all you want, she thought.

03:46:16.500 --> 03:46:18.899
He lit up his scales again.

03:46:18.959 --> 03:46:21.479
With a friendly smile, tsunami lit up the

03:46:21.479 --> 03:46:23.879
same patterns back at him, then added

03:46:23.879 --> 03:46:27.299
squid brain, with her tail stripes, like

03:46:27.299 --> 03:46:28.379
riptide had taught her.

03:46:28.440 --> 03:46:31.440
She swam away up the tunnel, leaving him

03:46:31.440 --> 03:46:33.659
gaping in surprise behind her.

03:46:33.719 --> 03:46:37.139
As she swam up and around, she started to

03:46:37.139 --> 03:46:39.239
hear shrieks of pain echoing through the

03:46:39.239 --> 03:46:39.479
water.

03:46:39.540 --> 03:46:42.299
She hesitated, then beat her wings

03:46:42.299 --> 03:46:42.719
faster.

03:46:42.840 --> 03:46:46.500
In the main entrance hall, Queen Coral

03:46:46.500 --> 03:46:49.319
had tortoise pinned under her talons, a

03:46:49.319 --> 03:46:51.600
crowd of sea wings had gathered, watching

03:46:51.600 --> 03:46:52.680
in silence.

03:46:52.860 --> 03:46:56.700
The skinny green dragon was shrieking in

03:46:56.700 --> 03:46:58.979
one long, high pitched scream.

03:46:59.040 --> 03:47:02.100
Tsunami stopped, and pressed herself back

03:47:02.100 --> 03:47:04.260
against the wall, horrified.

03:47:04.379 --> 03:47:07.739
Queen Coral had already yanked out each

03:47:07.739 --> 03:47:09.899
of tortoises' teeth one by one.

03:47:09.959 --> 03:47:13.139
They rose through the water, tiny and

03:47:13.139 --> 03:47:14.459
white toward the roof.

03:47:14.520 --> 03:47:17.760
Now Coral had her claws stabbed into

03:47:17.760 --> 03:47:19.799
tortoises exposed underbelly.

03:47:19.860 --> 03:47:23.399
Clouds of blood filled the water, nearly

03:47:23.399 --> 03:47:25.319
hiding the queen and tortoise in a red

03:47:25.319 --> 03:47:25.860
haze.

03:47:25.920 --> 03:47:28.079
Would I have to do that?

03:47:28.139 --> 03:47:29.579
If I were queen?

03:47:29.639 --> 03:47:32.639
Could I ever, ever do that?

03:47:32.700 --> 03:47:36.120
Anemone had rolled herself into a ball

03:47:36.120 --> 03:47:38.280
floating in the water above her mother

03:47:38.280 --> 03:47:41.100
with her eyes tightly shut and her talons

03:47:41.100 --> 03:47:41.700
over her ears.

03:47:41.819 --> 03:47:45.959
Queen Coral's scales lit up in a slow

03:47:45.959 --> 03:47:46.920
menacing way.

03:47:46.979 --> 03:47:50.459
Tsunami didn't understand most of it, but

03:47:50.459 --> 03:47:51.959
she guessed tortoise was hearing about

03:47:51.959 --> 03:47:53.520
how she'd failed the queen.

03:47:53.579 --> 03:47:56.879
Tortoises' stripes flashed weakly.

03:47:56.940 --> 03:48:00.420
The queen snarled and twisted her claws

03:48:00.420 --> 03:48:02.219
harder into tortoise's underbelly.

03:48:02.280 --> 03:48:04.620
Tortoise gurgled up a bubble of blood.

03:48:04.680 --> 03:48:08.700
Her stripes flashed again, and then, as

03:48:08.700 --> 03:48:11.459
her head began to loll sideways, she

03:48:11.459 --> 03:48:13.620
spotted someone in the crowd around them

03:48:13.620 --> 03:48:16.500
she clutched at the queen's talons and

03:48:16.500 --> 03:48:18.479
pointed, her stripes flashing

03:48:18.479 --> 03:48:19.020
frantically.

03:48:19.079 --> 03:48:22.680
She was pointing, straight at Shark.

03:48:22.739 --> 03:48:26.520
He stared back, unblinking as always.

03:48:26.579 --> 03:48:30.180
Queen Coral leaned down, pressing

03:48:30.180 --> 03:48:31.260
tortoise into the floor.

03:48:31.319 --> 03:48:34.260
One more message flared through her

03:48:34.260 --> 03:48:37.079
scales, and then she seized Tortoise's

03:48:37.079 --> 03:48:39.540
head in her talons and smashed it against

03:48:39.540 --> 03:48:40.920
the rough coral floor.

03:48:40.979 --> 03:48:45.479
Tsunami turned away just in time, huddling

03:48:45.479 --> 03:48:46.920
around the egg with her eyes closed.

03:48:47.040 --> 03:48:49.739
She didn't care if she looked like a one

03:48:49.739 --> 03:48:51.899
year old dragonette, hiding her face.

03:48:51.959 --> 03:48:54.420
She did not want that image in her head

03:48:54.420 --> 03:48:55.799
for the rest of her life.

03:48:55.860 --> 03:48:59.700
What was tortoise saying about shark?

03:48:59.760 --> 03:49:03.059
Whatever it was, hadn't convinced Queen

03:49:03.059 --> 03:49:03.959
Coral anyhow.

03:49:04.079 --> 03:49:07.739
Tsunami kept her eyes closed until she

03:49:07.739 --> 03:49:09.600
felt the eddies from other dragons

03:49:09.600 --> 03:49:10.440
swimming away.

03:49:10.500 --> 03:49:14.100
She peeked around and saw Moray busily

03:49:14.100 --> 03:49:16.020
cleaning up the blood and bone fragments

03:49:16.020 --> 03:49:17.819
that were floating around the main hall.

03:49:17.879 --> 03:49:22.020
Gross, tsunami thought.

03:49:22.079 --> 03:49:25.079
Moray must really adore Coral to be

03:49:25.079 --> 03:49:25.739
willing to do that.

03:49:25.799 --> 03:49:29.100
Tortoise's body was hooked on an

03:49:29.100 --> 03:49:31.079
outcropping of coral by the front door

03:49:31.079 --> 03:49:34.200
like a used up deer carcass waiting to be

03:49:34.200 --> 03:49:35.760
taken to the trash heap after dinner.

03:49:35.819 --> 03:49:39.659
Queen Coral loomed over shark, clutching

03:49:39.659 --> 03:49:42.000
anemone to her chest, and exchanging a

03:49:42.000 --> 03:49:43.979
heated, luminescent conversation with her

03:49:43.979 --> 03:49:44.280
brother.

03:49:44.340 --> 03:49:47.399
All the other sea wings had scattered to

03:49:47.399 --> 03:49:49.500
faraway parts of the palace.

03:49:49.559 --> 03:49:52.319
Tsunami started toward her mother, but

03:49:52.319 --> 03:49:54.780
stopped, as a strange shape flashed by

03:49:54.780 --> 03:49:55.500
one of the windows.

03:49:55.559 --> 03:49:57.360
What the?

03:49:57.659 --> 03:49:59.100
That wasn't a dragon.

03:49:59.219 --> 03:50:02.040
She swam a bit closer and peered out.

03:50:02.100 --> 03:50:03.899
Sharks.

03:50:03.959 --> 03:50:07.559
Actual dead eyed sharks with enormous

03:50:07.559 --> 03:50:10.260
jagged teeth were swarming around the

03:50:10.260 --> 03:50:12.540
front entrance, sniffing at the blood

03:50:12.540 --> 03:50:14.340
that still leaked from tortoise's body.

03:50:14.399 --> 03:50:17.100
They were bigger than tsunami had

03:50:17.100 --> 03:50:19.680
expected, big enough to eat a dragonette

03:50:19.680 --> 03:50:21.299
the size of anemone, she guessed.

03:50:21.360 --> 03:50:24.479
But even as she watched, 2 sea wing

03:50:24.479 --> 03:50:26.639
guards darted down and killed 5 of them

03:50:26.639 --> 03:50:28.079
with a few blows of their tails.

03:50:28.139 --> 03:50:31.440
She turned back, and saw whirlpool

03:50:31.440 --> 03:50:32.700
swimming up to Queen Coral.

03:50:32.760 --> 03:50:35.579
He interrupted her conversation, waving

03:50:35.579 --> 03:50:37.319
his talons furiously and pointing at

03:50:37.319 --> 03:50:37.920
tsunami.

03:50:37.979 --> 03:50:39.600
Uh-oh.

03:50:39.659 --> 03:50:42.239
Tsunami took a deep breath and held the

03:50:42.239 --> 03:50:43.260
eggshell closer.

03:50:43.319 --> 03:50:45.840
Well, I'm not giving this up.

03:50:45.899 --> 03:50:49.559
Queen Coral swam over with a half frown

03:50:49.559 --> 03:50:50.940
on her face.

03:50:51.000 --> 03:50:53.040
She pointed to the egg and gestured

03:50:53.040 --> 03:50:54.899
commandingly for tsunami to give it to

03:50:54.899 --> 03:50:55.020
her.

03:50:55.079 --> 03:50:57.840
Tsunami flashed her stripes in one of the

03:50:57.840 --> 03:50:58.979
few patterns she knew.

03:50:59.040 --> 03:51:01.200
I will protect.

03:51:01.260 --> 03:51:04.200
She wasn't sure how to say it.

03:51:04.319 --> 03:51:06.360
She pointed at the egg.

03:51:06.420 --> 03:51:08.280
I will protect.

03:51:08.399 --> 03:51:10.559
The queen blinked.

03:51:10.620 --> 03:51:13.379
She lit up a few of her stripes, including

03:51:13.379 --> 03:51:15.299
one pattern on her snout, the tsunami

03:51:15.299 --> 03:51:16.979
recognized as how?

03:51:17.040 --> 03:51:18.959
Tsunami shook her head.

03:51:19.020 --> 03:51:21.180
She didn't have enough aquatic to answer

03:51:21.180 --> 03:51:21.659
that.

03:51:21.719 --> 03:51:25.260
I will protect, she said again.

03:51:25.319 --> 03:51:28.440
She spotted the eyes of several sea wings

03:51:28.440 --> 03:51:30.059
peering around doorways at her.

03:51:30.120 --> 03:51:32.340
Most of them looked shocked and

03:51:32.340 --> 03:51:33.180
disbelieving.

03:51:33.239 --> 03:51:36.360
She saw her sister glance from tsunami to

03:51:36.360 --> 03:51:38.340
the crumpled remains of tortoise, then

03:51:38.340 --> 03:51:38.879
back again.

03:51:38.940 --> 03:51:41.879
Anemones' face was pale and anxious.

03:51:41.940 --> 03:51:43.799
Oh.

03:51:43.860 --> 03:51:46.559
Tsunami realized what they were saying.

03:51:46.620 --> 03:51:49.379
She was putting herself in Tortoise's

03:51:49.379 --> 03:51:49.680
place.

03:51:49.739 --> 03:51:52.379
She was taking the job nobody wanted.

03:51:52.440 --> 03:51:54.180
She hadn't even thought of it that way.

03:51:54.299 --> 03:51:58.739
Which meant, if she failed, she might be

03:51:58.739 --> 03:52:00.180
punished the same way too.

03:52:00.239 --> 03:52:04.500
Chapter 15.

03:52:04.920 --> 03:52:08.399
Queen Coral tried flashing some more

03:52:08.399 --> 03:52:10.860
questions at tsunami, but finally she

03:52:10.860 --> 03:52:12.420
flapped her wings and pointed to the

03:52:12.420 --> 03:52:12.719
surface.

03:52:12.780 --> 03:52:15.959
Tsunami pressed the egg to her chest and

03:52:15.959 --> 03:52:19.260
followed her mother up and up and up

03:52:19.260 --> 03:52:21.180
through winding tunnels and cavernous

03:52:21.180 --> 03:52:23.700
palace rooms, through emerald studded

03:52:23.700 --> 03:52:26.159
coral, and pearl laced curtains of golden

03:52:26.159 --> 03:52:26.940
seagrass.

03:52:27.000 --> 03:52:30.120
They swam to the top of the palace, where

03:52:30.120 --> 03:52:32.340
guards stood watch over a view for miles

03:52:32.340 --> 03:52:33.059
underwater.

03:52:33.120 --> 03:52:36.780
He saluted to the queen, and she swam up

03:52:36.780 --> 03:52:38.819
past him toward the gray light overhead

03:52:38.819 --> 03:52:41.100
where raindrops pelted the surface of the

03:52:41.100 --> 03:52:41.399
water.

03:52:41.459 --> 03:52:44.940
Anemone paddled in her wake, glowing like

03:52:44.940 --> 03:52:46.860
a pale blue pearl in the dark sea.

03:52:46.920 --> 03:52:51.059
They emerged into a storm so fierce, it

03:52:51.059 --> 03:52:52.440
almost felt like they hadn't left the

03:52:52.440 --> 03:52:53.040
water at all.

03:52:53.100 --> 03:52:56.280
Tsunami faltered in the air as wind and

03:52:56.280 --> 03:52:57.899
rain tried to sweep her back into the

03:52:57.899 --> 03:52:58.200
ocean.

03:52:58.260 --> 03:53:00.840
The egg was slippery in her talons.

03:53:00.899 --> 03:53:04.620
Don't you dare drop it, she hissed to

03:53:04.620 --> 03:53:05.040
herself.

03:53:05.159 --> 03:53:09.299
This way, shouted the queen, banking

03:53:09.299 --> 03:53:10.139
toward the nearest island.

03:53:10.200 --> 03:53:13.379
A large cave yawned open onto the beach.

03:53:13.440 --> 03:53:15.719
Rough, dirty and muddy.

03:53:15.780 --> 03:53:17.879
It was still the driest spot they could

03:53:17.879 --> 03:53:18.059
see.

03:53:18.120 --> 03:53:20.940
The 3 of them huddled into its shelter.

03:53:21.000 --> 03:53:23.760
What do you think you're doing?

03:53:23.819 --> 03:53:25.440
The queen demanded.

03:53:25.500 --> 03:53:27.959
As soon as tsunami's claws touched the

03:53:27.959 --> 03:53:28.379
ground.

03:53:28.440 --> 03:53:31.139
Someone has to protect this egg.

03:53:31.200 --> 03:53:34.020
Tsunami said, it's not safe in the

03:53:34.020 --> 03:53:34.620
hatchery.

03:53:34.680 --> 03:53:37.799
It'll be safe in a hatchery if I put all

03:53:37.799 --> 03:53:38.819
my guards on it.

03:53:38.879 --> 03:53:40.620
Queen Coral fumed.

03:53:40.680 --> 03:53:42.600
Tsunami shook her head.

03:53:42.659 --> 03:53:44.520
Haven't you tried that before?

03:53:44.579 --> 03:53:46.200
Has it ever worked?

03:53:46.260 --> 03:53:48.959
She paused and glanced at her sister.

03:53:49.020 --> 03:53:51.420
What did you do for anemone?

03:53:51.479 --> 03:53:53.520
The queen shook out her wings.

03:53:53.579 --> 03:53:57.000
I slept by the egg myself for the entire

03:53:57.000 --> 03:53:58.860
year, she said.

03:53:58.920 --> 03:54:00.540
You did?

03:54:00.600 --> 03:54:02.280
Anemone said.

03:54:02.340 --> 03:54:05.100
Rain dripped off her tiny pale wings into

03:54:05.100 --> 03:54:06.180
puddles around her feet.

03:54:06.239 --> 03:54:08.760
I barely left the hatchery.

03:54:08.879 --> 03:54:12.360
I let Gil run the war for me, but that's

03:54:12.360 --> 03:54:12.959
how I lost him.

03:54:13.020 --> 03:54:16.379
Coral's voice caught and she frowned.

03:54:16.500 --> 03:54:19.860
I can't neglect my duties as Queen.

03:54:19.920 --> 03:54:21.299
Now that he's gone.

03:54:21.420 --> 03:54:25.559
So let me do this, Tsunami said.

03:54:25.620 --> 03:54:27.719
Let me protect this egg.

03:54:27.780 --> 03:54:31.440
But you have to stay in the hatchery, the

03:54:31.440 --> 03:54:32.100
queen insisted.

03:54:32.159 --> 03:54:35.879
It must be kept warm, especially right

03:54:35.879 --> 03:54:36.719
before hatching.

03:54:36.780 --> 03:54:39.420
Tsunami glanced down at the egg.

03:54:39.479 --> 03:54:41.700
She didn't trust the hatchery.

03:54:41.760 --> 03:54:43.920
Anyone could sneak in to attack both

03:54:43.920 --> 03:54:46.620
tsunami and the egg, especially if there

03:54:46.620 --> 03:54:47.579
was a secret entrance.

03:54:47.639 --> 03:54:50.579
Besides, she couldn't stay in the deep

03:54:50.579 --> 03:54:52.979
palace, she had to go back and check on

03:54:52.979 --> 03:54:53.340
her friends.

03:54:53.399 --> 03:54:57.420
I have a better idea, she said, trust me

03:54:57.420 --> 03:54:58.920
I'll take it back to the summer palace.

03:54:58.979 --> 03:55:01.440
The Summer Palace?

03:55:01.559 --> 03:55:03.299
The queen flared her wings.

03:55:03.360 --> 03:55:05.819
No, you don't want to do that in this

03:55:05.819 --> 03:55:06.180
weather.

03:55:06.239 --> 03:55:08.579
It gets terribly flooded there during a

03:55:08.579 --> 03:55:08.879
storm.

03:55:08.940 --> 03:55:11.159
Better to wait out the rain here at the

03:55:11.159 --> 03:55:12.899
Deep Palace, where you'll hardly notice

03:55:12.899 --> 03:55:13.440
it's happening.

03:55:13.500 --> 03:55:15.180
Flooded?

03:55:15.239 --> 03:55:16.739
Tsunami echoed.

03:55:16.799 --> 03:55:19.620
Do you mean the caves?

03:55:19.680 --> 03:55:20.760
And the beaches?

03:55:20.819 --> 03:55:22.379
Where my friends are?

03:55:22.440 --> 03:55:24.120
Oh.

03:55:24.180 --> 03:55:26.100
Queen Coral waved her claws

03:55:26.100 --> 03:55:27.059
dismissively.

03:55:27.120 --> 03:55:28.500
I'm sure they'll be all right.

03:55:28.559 --> 03:55:29.639
Can't they swim?

03:55:29.700 --> 03:55:33.000
Not like we can, tsunami said.

03:55:33.059 --> 03:55:35.100
I'm going back to check on them.

03:55:35.159 --> 03:55:36.719
With my egg.

03:55:36.840 --> 03:55:38.219
Coral growled.

03:55:38.280 --> 03:55:40.799
You've tried trusting everyone else

03:55:40.799 --> 03:55:42.299
tsunami said.

03:55:42.360 --> 03:55:44.459
Taking a step back toward the pounding

03:55:44.459 --> 03:55:45.180
rain outside.

03:55:45.299 --> 03:55:46.920
Now trust me.

03:55:46.979 --> 03:55:49.620
I promise this dragonette will hatch

03:55:49.620 --> 03:55:50.100
safely.

03:55:50.159 --> 03:55:52.860
Her heart beat like the thunder in the

03:55:52.860 --> 03:55:53.219
clouds.

03:55:53.340 --> 03:55:56.879
Was this, finally, the right thing to

03:55:56.879 --> 03:55:57.120
do?

03:55:57.180 --> 03:55:59.399
Was she doing it for the right reasons?

03:55:59.459 --> 03:56:02.940
Or was she being impulsive again, trying

03:56:02.940 --> 03:56:05.040
to prove something instead of thinking it

03:56:05.040 --> 03:56:05.579
through?

03:56:05.579 --> 03:56:08.040
I'm doing this for my father.

03:56:08.100 --> 03:56:10.860
I'm doing this to make up for all my

03:56:10.860 --> 03:56:11.340
mistakes.

03:56:11.399 --> 03:56:14.399
And I'm doing this to save my little

03:56:14.399 --> 03:56:14.819
sister.

03:56:14.879 --> 03:56:16.680
How can that be wrong?

03:56:16.739 --> 03:56:21.479
If anything happens to that egg.

03:56:21.540 --> 03:56:23.520
Queen Coral hissed.

03:56:23.639 --> 03:56:26.459
I'll lose 2 daughters that day.

03:56:26.520 --> 03:56:30.299
So much for being a special princess.

03:56:30.360 --> 03:56:34.079
I need a harness for it, tsunami said

03:56:34.079 --> 03:56:35.639
looking her mother in the eye.

03:56:35.700 --> 03:56:37.079
See?

03:56:37.139 --> 03:56:38.459
I'm not afraid of you.

03:56:38.520 --> 03:56:40.680
Maybe you should think about how your

03:56:40.680 --> 03:56:43.079
next queen will come to power before you

03:56:43.079 --> 03:56:44.219
start threatening me.

03:56:44.280 --> 03:56:46.860
The harnesses they were making for the

03:56:46.860 --> 03:56:47.579
dragonettes.

03:56:47.700 --> 03:56:49.260
Anemone piped up.

03:56:49.319 --> 03:56:50.639
One of those should work.

03:56:50.700 --> 03:56:53.219
How will you get back to the Summer

03:56:53.219 --> 03:56:53.879
Palace?

03:56:53.940 --> 03:56:55.739
Coral demanded.

03:56:55.799 --> 03:56:58.139
You don't know the way, and my court is

03:56:58.139 --> 03:56:58.860
staying here with me.

03:56:58.920 --> 03:57:03.420
I'll find it, tsunami said, but a nervous

03:57:03.420 --> 03:57:04.559
shiver went through her wings.

03:57:04.680 --> 03:57:07.379
She did not want to be wandering the

03:57:07.379 --> 03:57:09.899
ocean alone during a storm, especially

03:57:09.899 --> 03:57:11.340
when her friend needed her.

03:57:11.399 --> 03:57:14.159
If riptide is still out there.

03:57:14.219 --> 03:57:17.520
Please let riptide still be out there.

03:57:17.579 --> 03:57:21.899
Wait, she said, as the queen started for

03:57:21.899 --> 03:57:22.620
the entrance.

03:57:22.680 --> 03:57:23.879
I have a question.

03:57:23.940 --> 03:57:26.819
Tortoise pointed at Shark while she was

03:57:26.819 --> 03:57:27.120
dying.

03:57:27.180 --> 03:57:29.459
Was she saying he attacked the egg?

03:57:29.520 --> 03:57:32.760
Carl flared her wings, looking shocked.

03:57:32.819 --> 03:57:35.219
Certainly not, she said.

03:57:35.280 --> 03:57:36.540
My own brother.

03:57:36.600 --> 03:57:37.500
He wouldn't dare.

03:57:37.559 --> 03:57:40.680
She wasn't saying he killed the egg.

03:57:40.739 --> 03:57:42.120
Anemone agreed.

03:57:42.180 --> 03:57:44.340
She said he'd given her permission to

03:57:44.340 --> 03:57:45.659
leave her post.

03:57:45.719 --> 03:57:46.920
He brought her an octopus to eat.

03:57:46.979 --> 03:57:49.139
The fool.

03:57:49.200 --> 03:57:51.180
Coral gnashed her teeth.

03:57:51.239 --> 03:57:54.239
I've told Shark, a 1000000 times that

03:57:54.239 --> 03:57:56.399
vigilance is the only way to protect the

03:57:56.399 --> 03:57:57.180
eggs.

03:57:57.239 --> 03:57:59.700
If that means going days without eating

03:57:59.700 --> 03:58:02.340
then that is what my trusted counselor

03:58:02.340 --> 03:58:02.760
must do.

03:58:02.819 --> 03:58:04.979
He's too soft with them.

03:58:05.100 --> 03:58:08.100
Right, tsunami thought.

03:58:08.159 --> 03:58:11.399
Soft is definitely how I'd describe

03:58:11.399 --> 03:58:12.000
shark.

03:58:12.120 --> 03:58:14.879
Well, tortoise didn't think anything

03:58:14.879 --> 03:58:17.040
could happen, Anemone said.

03:58:17.100 --> 03:58:19.319
Not while she was right outside the door

03:58:19.319 --> 03:58:20.819
and only away from the egg for a few

03:58:20.819 --> 03:58:21.120
moments.

03:58:21.180 --> 03:58:24.659
Why didn't she stay with the egg to eat?

03:58:24.719 --> 03:58:25.920
Tsunami asked.

03:58:25.979 --> 03:58:30.540
Nobody eats inside the royal hatchery.

03:58:30.600 --> 03:58:32.459
Anemone said primly.

03:58:32.520 --> 03:58:35.219
It's a pristine hatching place designed

03:58:35.219 --> 03:58:37.739
for royal dragonettes, and if you get

03:58:37.739 --> 03:58:39.899
blood in the water, sharks will try to

03:58:39.899 --> 03:58:40.500
find their way in.

03:58:40.559 --> 03:58:43.500
Regular sharks who eat dragonettes and

03:58:43.500 --> 03:58:46.200
eggs, that is, hatcheries other than the

03:58:46.200 --> 03:58:48.120
royal hatchery get attacked by them all

03:58:48.120 --> 03:58:48.479
the time.

03:58:48.540 --> 03:58:51.059
Tsunami sugar head.

03:58:51.120 --> 03:58:52.920
She couldn't help feeling like following

03:58:52.920 --> 03:58:54.959
all these rules was only helping the

03:58:54.959 --> 03:58:55.559
assassin.

03:58:55.620 --> 03:58:58.680
And it was pretty convenient that Shark

03:58:58.680 --> 03:59:01.079
had set toward us up like that, not to

03:59:01.079 --> 03:59:03.059
mention giving himself a chance to sneak

03:59:03.059 --> 03:59:04.500
in and kill the dragonette.

03:59:04.620 --> 03:59:06.600
She shook out her wings.

03:59:06.659 --> 03:59:09.719
Take me to the harness, she said.

03:59:09.780 --> 03:59:12.959
Queen Coral reached toward the egg, then

03:59:12.959 --> 03:59:13.979
stopped herself.

03:59:14.040 --> 03:59:16.799
She gave tsunami another hard look, and

03:59:16.799 --> 03:59:18.180
led the way out into the storm.

03:59:18.239 --> 03:59:22.319
This time, they swam down through the

03:59:22.319 --> 03:59:24.719
murky churning water, and around to the

03:59:24.719 --> 03:59:26.040
back entrance to the palace.

03:59:26.100 --> 03:59:28.920
The queen burst into a room that seemed

03:59:28.920 --> 03:59:31.620
to be a workshop, where small sea wings

03:59:31.620 --> 03:59:33.659
crouched over seagrass weavings and

03:59:33.659 --> 03:59:34.500
marble carvings.

03:59:34.559 --> 03:59:37.799
Tsunami paused as her mother thundered to

03:59:37.799 --> 03:59:38.639
the far end of the room.

03:59:38.700 --> 03:59:41.340
She lifted one of the weavings in her

03:59:41.340 --> 03:59:43.799
claws and realized it was made of the

03:59:43.799 --> 03:59:46.500
same material as the harness, rubbery

03:59:46.500 --> 03:59:48.540
stretchy, and waterproof.

03:59:48.600 --> 03:59:51.120
Only these were woven in colors, not

03:59:51.120 --> 03:59:52.379
clear like the harness.

03:59:52.440 --> 03:59:55.620
Queen Coral flared her stripes angrily at

03:59:55.620 --> 03:59:57.540
a dragon who had frozen over a marble

03:59:57.540 --> 03:59:58.020
carving.

03:59:58.079 --> 04:00:00.899
He hurried into a back room and returned

04:00:00.899 --> 04:00:02.760
with a tiny harness, flopping in his

04:00:02.760 --> 04:00:03.899
talons.

04:00:03.959 --> 04:00:06.360
Coral pointed at tsunami, and he took it

04:00:06.360 --> 04:00:06.780
over to her.

04:00:06.840 --> 04:00:10.680
This dragon was old, she noticed, and

04:00:10.680 --> 04:00:12.780
shaking with fear as he tried to fit

04:00:12.780 --> 04:00:14.879
straps around tsunami's neck and

04:00:14.879 --> 04:00:15.479
shoulders.

04:00:15.540 --> 04:00:17.219
They flapped loosely.

04:00:17.280 --> 04:00:19.620
It was meant for coral and was too big

04:00:19.620 --> 04:00:21.780
for her, and of course, the smaller

04:00:21.780 --> 04:00:23.340
harness was supposed to fit a little

04:00:23.340 --> 04:00:26.100
dragonette with limbs and a tail, not a

04:00:26.100 --> 04:00:27.059
smooth round egg.

04:00:27.120 --> 04:00:30.059
The old dragon gestured helplessly at the

04:00:30.059 --> 04:00:32.340
harness, and Queen Coral poked it

04:00:32.340 --> 04:00:34.440
growling a stream of bubbles.

04:00:34.680 --> 04:00:37.440
The queen yanked anemone closer, and

04:00:37.440 --> 04:00:39.780
pointed at the harness, flashing some of

04:00:39.780 --> 04:00:41.579
the royal stripes in her wings.

04:00:41.700 --> 04:00:45.239
Anemone hesitated, then reached out

04:00:45.239 --> 04:00:47.159
unhappily and touched the harness.

04:00:47.219 --> 04:00:49.979
To tsunami's astonishment.

04:00:50.040 --> 04:00:52.319
The straps around her shoulders suddenly

04:00:52.319 --> 04:00:54.180
shrank until they fit perfectly.

04:00:54.239 --> 04:00:57.299
The other webs snaked and wove closer

04:00:57.299 --> 04:00:59.639
until the egg was securely bound to her

04:00:59.639 --> 04:00:59.940
chest.

04:01:00.000 --> 04:01:03.120
She grabbed Anemone's talon.

04:01:03.180 --> 04:01:06.360
Her sister felt cold and weirdly hard to

04:01:06.360 --> 04:01:08.340
the touch, and her eyes were out of

04:01:08.340 --> 04:01:09.180
focus.

04:01:09.239 --> 04:01:12.059
Tsunami shook her, and anemone blinked

04:01:12.059 --> 04:01:13.559
until she was looking at tsunami.

04:01:13.620 --> 04:01:14.940
What?

04:01:15.000 --> 04:01:17.399
Tsunami flashed the stripes on her

04:01:17.399 --> 04:01:17.760
snout.

04:01:17.819 --> 04:01:20.700
Anemone shook her head and made the

04:01:20.700 --> 04:01:21.299
circular gesture.

04:01:21.360 --> 04:01:22.860
Not right now.

04:01:22.920 --> 04:01:24.600
We'll finish later.

04:01:24.659 --> 04:01:27.840
Tsunami wanted to know more, but a

04:01:27.840 --> 04:01:29.459
gesture reminded her of Shark and her

04:01:29.459 --> 04:01:29.760
friends.

04:01:29.819 --> 04:01:32.219
She had to get back to them.

04:01:32.280 --> 04:01:34.799
Protecting this egg was important, but

04:01:34.799 --> 04:01:36.780
watching out for the other 4 dragonettes

04:01:36.780 --> 04:01:38.940
had been her 1st duty her whole life.

04:01:39.000 --> 04:01:42.540
She bowed politely at the queen and the

04:01:42.540 --> 04:01:44.940
old harness maker. then swam out of the

04:01:44.940 --> 04:01:47.040
palace and back through the gardens she'd

04:01:47.040 --> 04:01:47.879
seen on their way in.

04:01:47.940 --> 04:01:50.520
She wasn't going unnoticed now.

04:01:50.579 --> 04:01:53.819
Everywhere she passed, Sea Wings stopped

04:01:53.819 --> 04:01:54.479
to stare.

04:01:54.540 --> 04:01:56.700
Then lit up their wings and hurried

04:01:56.700 --> 04:01:58.200
conversations after she went by.

04:01:58.260 --> 04:02:00.659
She could sense them pointing at the

04:02:00.659 --> 04:02:00.959
egg.

04:02:01.020 --> 04:02:03.540
She wasn't sure if they knew she was the

04:02:03.540 --> 04:02:05.819
missing princess, or if they only knew

04:02:05.819 --> 04:02:08.159
she'd volunteered for the suicide mission

04:02:08.159 --> 04:02:10.020
of saving the Queen's last female

04:02:10.020 --> 04:02:10.979
dragonette.

04:02:11.040 --> 04:02:13.739
She remembered swimming into the canyon

04:02:13.739 --> 04:02:16.139
so she climbed out and swam around the

04:02:16.139 --> 04:02:17.280
bend in the coral reef.

04:02:17.399 --> 04:02:20.340
The deep palace disappeared behind her

04:02:20.340 --> 04:02:22.920
and the wide dark ocean yawned in front

04:02:22.920 --> 04:02:23.219
of her.

04:02:23.280 --> 04:02:26.579
All right, you ask for this.

04:02:26.700 --> 04:02:28.260
Now what?

04:02:28.319 --> 04:02:32.879
Chapter 16.

04:02:33.120 --> 04:02:36.959
Tsunami twisted around, hoping to see

04:02:36.959 --> 04:02:37.799
something familiar.

04:02:37.860 --> 04:02:41.700
To be honest, hoping to see riptide, but

04:02:41.700 --> 04:02:44.459
the ocean was dark and wild, and it

04:02:44.459 --> 04:02:46.319
seemed like everything alive had gone

04:02:46.319 --> 04:02:48.120
into hiding until the storm passed.

04:02:48.180 --> 04:02:51.000
So I figured out myself.

04:02:51.059 --> 04:02:53.280
Tsunami set her jaw.

04:02:53.340 --> 04:02:55.379
She patted the egg through the harness.

04:02:55.440 --> 04:02:57.479
Don't worry, I can do this.

04:02:57.540 --> 04:03:00.540
They'd ridden a current most of the way

04:03:00.540 --> 04:03:00.780
here.

04:03:00.840 --> 04:03:02.760
Did she have to fight it all the way

04:03:02.760 --> 04:03:03.059
back?

04:03:03.120 --> 04:03:06.420
She swam slowly forward until she felt

04:03:06.420 --> 04:03:08.219
the water try to shove her away.

04:03:08.280 --> 04:03:10.739
Maybe she could just keep a wingtip in

04:03:10.739 --> 04:03:12.239
the current and follow it that way.

04:03:12.299 --> 04:03:14.639
Several wing beats later.

04:03:14.700 --> 04:03:16.920
She pulled away from the current to rest

04:03:16.920 --> 04:03:18.659
exhausted and confused.

04:03:18.719 --> 04:03:20.940
Why was this so hard?

04:03:21.059 --> 04:03:23.040
Riptide?

04:03:23.100 --> 04:03:24.059
Where are you?

04:03:24.120 --> 04:03:27.000
Perhaps she could find her way back in

04:03:27.000 --> 04:03:27.659
the air instead.

04:03:27.719 --> 04:03:29.819
She just had to look for the island

04:03:29.819 --> 04:03:31.860
shaped like a dragon skeleton.

04:03:31.920 --> 04:03:33.180
How hard could that be?

04:03:33.239 --> 04:03:36.360
Tsunami lashed her tail to power to the

04:03:36.360 --> 04:03:36.840
surface.

04:03:36.899 --> 04:03:39.899
She burst out into a pounding cacophony

04:03:39.899 --> 04:03:42.780
of thunder and roaring waves.

04:03:42.840 --> 04:03:44.700
Rain crashed down on her scales like

04:03:44.700 --> 04:03:45.540
hailstones.

04:03:45.600 --> 04:03:48.120
The wind immediately tried to grab her

04:03:48.120 --> 04:03:48.899
and carry her off.

04:03:48.959 --> 04:03:52.079
She fought to stay balanced and fly

04:03:52.079 --> 04:03:54.420
straight, but she was already lost.

04:03:54.479 --> 04:03:57.000
She could see an island to her left, but

04:03:57.000 --> 04:03:58.440
she didn't know if that was the one close

04:03:58.440 --> 04:04:00.600
to the deep palace, or if she'd been

04:04:00.600 --> 04:04:02.879
swept to another, and whether it was on

04:04:02.879 --> 04:04:04.559
the way back to the summer palace or

04:04:04.559 --> 04:04:04.799
not.

04:04:04.860 --> 04:04:07.979
A dark shape on the surface of the water

04:04:07.979 --> 04:04:08.819
caught her eye.

04:04:08.879 --> 04:04:11.280
She rubbed her snout, shaking off

04:04:11.280 --> 04:04:11.940
raindrops.

04:04:12.059 --> 04:04:13.799
Riptide?

04:04:13.860 --> 04:04:15.420
She flew lower.

04:04:15.479 --> 04:04:17.700
It wasn't a dragon.

04:04:17.760 --> 04:04:20.520
It was some kind of odd vessel, like a

04:04:20.520 --> 04:04:22.979
large bowl floating on the water, and

04:04:22.979 --> 04:04:25.379
huddled inside of it were 2 scavengers

04:04:25.379 --> 04:04:27.120
scrawny and soaking wet.

04:04:27.180 --> 04:04:30.780
That doesn't help me at all, Tsunami

04:04:30.780 --> 04:04:31.200
thought.

04:04:31.260 --> 04:04:32.819
I'm not even hungry right now.

04:04:32.879 --> 04:04:36.540
She beat her wings to soar upward again

04:04:36.540 --> 04:04:38.100
and one of the scavengers looked up.

04:04:38.159 --> 04:04:42.000
Its eyes were as green as glory's, in a

04:04:42.000 --> 04:04:44.219
smooth face, the same brown color as

04:04:44.219 --> 04:04:45.059
clay's scales.

04:04:45.120 --> 04:04:48.120
Tangled dark hair snarled around its

04:04:48.120 --> 04:04:48.479
shoulders.

04:04:48.540 --> 04:04:51.899
Tsunami had seen a few scavengers up

04:04:51.899 --> 04:04:54.719
close before, one in the mountains, and 2

04:04:54.719 --> 04:04:55.979
in the Skywing arena.

04:04:56.040 --> 04:04:58.680
It struck her again how dragon like their

04:04:58.680 --> 04:04:59.100
eyes were.

04:04:59.219 --> 04:05:01.500
It was sort of unsettling, really.

04:05:01.559 --> 04:05:03.959
She wondered if they could breathe

04:05:03.959 --> 04:05:06.780
underwater or swim, because these 2 were

04:05:06.780 --> 04:05:08.760
about to get swamped and end up at the

04:05:08.760 --> 04:05:09.479
bottom of the ocean.

04:05:09.600 --> 04:05:14.159
Unless I help them, as if I have time for

04:05:14.159 --> 04:05:14.399
that.

04:05:14.459 --> 04:05:16.379
She hesitated.

04:05:16.440 --> 04:05:19.200
Maybe all scavengers looked that way all

04:05:19.200 --> 04:05:22.260
the time, but if she had to guess, she'd

04:05:22.260 --> 04:05:23.760
say their expressions were terrified.

04:05:23.819 --> 04:05:27.180
On the other hand, I might as well help

04:05:27.180 --> 04:05:27.659
somebody.

04:05:27.780 --> 04:05:29.520
Maybe it'll give me luck.

04:05:29.579 --> 04:05:33.360
Tsunami swooped down and snatched up the

04:05:33.360 --> 04:05:34.440
vessel in her talons.

04:05:34.500 --> 04:05:37.079
It was heavier than it looked, and she

04:05:37.079 --> 04:05:38.159
immediately dropped it.

04:05:38.219 --> 04:05:40.860
The 2 scavengers let out their long

04:05:40.860 --> 04:05:43.079
piercing bird shrieks as the vessel

04:05:43.079 --> 04:05:44.219
smacked back into the water.

04:05:44.280 --> 04:05:48.059
Oh, calm down, tsunami thought.

04:05:48.120 --> 04:05:50.879
She flew around in a circle, fighting the

04:05:50.879 --> 04:05:53.520
gusts of wind, and wrapped a front talon

04:05:53.520 --> 04:05:54.600
around each scavenger.

04:05:54.659 --> 04:05:57.600
They both shrieked some more and banged

04:05:57.600 --> 04:05:58.920
uselessly against her claws.

04:05:58.979 --> 04:06:02.219
How do scavengers accomplish anything?

04:06:02.280 --> 04:06:04.920
Tsunami wondered, flapping toward the

04:06:04.920 --> 04:06:05.159
island?

04:06:05.219 --> 04:06:07.920
They don't seem to have any useful dragon

04:06:07.920 --> 04:06:10.620
qualities, and yet they managed to steal

04:06:10.620 --> 04:06:12.899
treasure and occasionally kill a queen

04:06:12.899 --> 04:06:13.680
and start a war.

04:06:13.739 --> 04:06:17.399
That's right, she remembered, giving the

04:06:17.399 --> 04:06:18.600
scavengers a little shake.

04:06:18.659 --> 04:06:20.340
I'm mad at your kind.

04:06:20.399 --> 04:06:22.079
It's your fault all of this is

04:06:22.079 --> 04:06:22.379
happening.

04:06:22.440 --> 04:06:25.799
They screamed in a satisfyingly terrified

04:06:25.799 --> 04:06:26.040
way.

04:06:26.159 --> 04:06:29.940
On the other hand, it's pretty unlikely

04:06:29.940 --> 04:06:32.219
that it was these exact scavengers who

04:06:32.219 --> 04:06:34.379
killed Queen Oasis and set off the sand

04:06:34.379 --> 04:06:35.700
wing war of succession.

04:06:35.760 --> 04:06:38.280
So I suppose I'll let them live.

04:06:38.340 --> 04:06:41.100
She dropped them on the island beach.

04:06:41.159 --> 04:06:43.620
They staggered to their feet and fled out

04:06:43.620 --> 04:06:45.420
toward the trees and the caves without a

04:06:45.420 --> 04:06:46.139
backward glance.

04:06:46.200 --> 04:06:48.659
Pathetic little creatures.

04:06:48.719 --> 04:06:51.719
Tsunami's wings ached from fighting the

04:06:51.719 --> 04:06:52.020
storm.

04:06:52.079 --> 04:06:54.780
She had to try going back underwater.

04:06:54.840 --> 04:06:57.959
She dove in with a splash and spun

04:06:57.959 --> 04:06:59.879
searching the dark water again for

04:06:59.879 --> 04:07:00.600
riptide.

04:07:00.659 --> 04:07:02.459
Had he given up on her?

04:07:02.520 --> 04:07:05.040
Was he hiding from the storm like a smart

04:07:05.040 --> 04:07:05.819
dragon wood?

04:07:05.879 --> 04:07:08.340
Figuring she'd be safe in a deep palace?

04:07:08.399 --> 04:07:11.399
Well, there was one thing that had gotten

04:07:11.399 --> 04:07:12.180
his attention before.

04:07:12.239 --> 04:07:15.180
She opened her wings and lit up all her

04:07:15.180 --> 04:07:17.819
stripes, like she had done in a tunnel.

04:07:17.879 --> 04:07:20.700
The glow blazed through the water, and

04:07:20.700 --> 04:07:22.379
then she shut them down again and

04:07:22.379 --> 04:07:22.739
waited.

04:07:22.860 --> 04:07:24.600
Nothing.

04:07:24.659 --> 04:07:26.579
She tried again.

04:07:26.639 --> 04:07:29.520
It gave her a bit of a headache, lighting

04:07:29.520 --> 04:07:31.379
up all her stripes like that, and left

04:07:31.379 --> 04:07:33.299
her dazzled blind for a few moments

04:07:33.299 --> 04:07:33.719
afterward.

04:07:33.780 --> 04:07:36.600
She'd done it sometimes for the other

04:07:36.600 --> 04:07:38.760
dragonettes when the caves got too

04:07:38.760 --> 04:07:41.520
depressingly dark, or Kestrel tried to

04:07:41.520 --> 04:07:43.139
punish them by taking away all the

04:07:43.139 --> 04:07:43.620
torches.

04:07:43.680 --> 04:07:45.780
Glory hated that the most.

04:07:45.840 --> 04:07:47.399
She couldn't stand the dark.

04:07:47.459 --> 04:07:50.579
Tsunami thought about the summer palace

04:07:50.579 --> 04:07:52.979
where there was no fire allowed except in

04:07:52.979 --> 04:07:55.500
one cave, and all the light came through

04:07:55.500 --> 04:07:56.639
the canopy up above.

04:07:56.700 --> 04:07:59.100
Not much light could be filtering down

04:07:59.100 --> 04:08:00.780
from the sky in the middle of the storm.

04:08:00.840 --> 04:08:03.360
Her friends were probably sitting in the

04:08:03.360 --> 04:08:05.459
dark right now, listening to the water

04:08:05.459 --> 04:08:07.739
climb up the beach toward them.

04:08:07.799 --> 04:08:09.420
I have to get back to them.

04:08:09.479 --> 04:08:11.040
Tsunami thought.

04:08:11.100 --> 04:08:13.020
Blazing all her stripes on again.

04:08:13.079 --> 04:08:16.500
Right in front of her, Riptide flung up

04:08:16.500 --> 04:08:17.760
his wings to shield his eyes.

04:08:17.819 --> 04:08:21.000
Tsunami grabbed his claws and turned down

04:08:21.000 --> 04:08:21.719
her stripes.

04:08:21.780 --> 04:08:23.760
She jabbed her talent in the direction

04:08:23.760 --> 04:08:27.780
she thought the summer palace was, Oh, why

04:08:27.780 --> 04:08:29.579
don't I know how to say anything useful?

04:08:29.639 --> 04:08:32.459
He rubbed his eyes and squinted at the

04:08:32.459 --> 04:08:33.540
egg attached to her.

04:08:33.600 --> 04:08:36.420
His expression said, something you forgot

04:08:36.420 --> 04:08:36.899
to mention.

04:08:36.959 --> 04:08:39.780
She whacked his tail with hers and

04:08:39.780 --> 04:08:40.319
pointed again.

04:08:40.379 --> 04:08:43.500
She remembered the pattern for urgent, and

04:08:43.500 --> 04:08:44.040
lit it up.

04:08:44.100 --> 04:08:47.159
Riptide nodded and began paddling toward

04:08:47.159 --> 04:08:47.639
the surface.

04:08:47.700 --> 04:08:50.940
We don't have time to chat, Tsunami

04:08:50.940 --> 04:08:53.340
thought, frustrated, but she followed him

04:08:53.340 --> 04:08:54.299
because she had no choice.

04:08:54.360 --> 04:08:57.659
But before he reached the air.

04:08:57.719 --> 04:08:59.700
Riptide swung around and slid into

04:08:59.700 --> 04:09:00.479
another current.

04:09:00.540 --> 04:09:03.540
As far as tsunami could tell, it went in

04:09:03.540 --> 04:09:05.340
the direction of the summer palace.

04:09:05.399 --> 04:09:07.979
He beckoned her after him, and tsunami

04:09:07.979 --> 04:09:09.299
ducked into the current as well.

04:09:09.360 --> 04:09:12.540
All right, I suppose I could have looked

04:09:12.540 --> 04:09:13.200
for one of those.

04:09:13.260 --> 04:09:16.260
Maybe traveling the sea wasn't about

04:09:16.260 --> 04:09:18.120
being strong and fighting with it all the

04:09:18.120 --> 04:09:18.360
time.

04:09:18.420 --> 04:09:21.059
Maybe it was about trusting the currents

04:09:21.059 --> 04:09:22.260
and knowing where they were.

04:09:22.319 --> 04:09:24.959
Maybe it would just take time before she

04:09:24.959 --> 04:09:25.559
figured them out.

04:09:25.620 --> 04:09:28.620
She lashed her tail to keep up with

04:09:28.620 --> 04:09:31.379
riptide as they swung around islands and

04:09:31.379 --> 04:09:33.479
dodged billowing clouds of translucent

04:09:33.479 --> 04:09:34.200
jellyfish.

04:09:34.260 --> 04:09:37.020
The current sped them along, but the

04:09:37.020 --> 04:09:39.540
journey still felt endless, and tsunami

04:09:39.540 --> 04:09:40.680
couldn't stop thinking about her

04:09:40.680 --> 04:09:40.920
friends.

04:09:40.979 --> 04:09:43.799
She should have fought harder to make her

04:09:43.799 --> 04:09:44.579
mother accept them.

04:09:44.639 --> 04:09:47.459
How could anyone not trust clay?

04:09:47.579 --> 04:09:49.799
Every thought he had was written all over

04:09:49.799 --> 04:09:51.600
his big, sweet, goofy face.

04:09:51.659 --> 04:09:52.739
And Sonny?

04:09:52.799 --> 04:09:55.139
Those 2 were the most trustworthy of the

04:09:55.139 --> 04:09:55.440
bunch.

04:09:55.500 --> 04:09:58.379
Tsunami didn't think Sonny had ever had a

04:09:58.379 --> 04:09:59.579
negative thought in her life.

04:09:59.639 --> 04:10:02.280
She did what she was told, and happily.

04:10:02.399 --> 04:10:05.459
She believed the best of everyone, even

04:10:05.459 --> 04:10:06.840
Kestrel and Dune.

04:10:06.899 --> 04:10:09.479
Which didn't say much for Sonny's

04:10:09.479 --> 04:10:11.639
judgment or intelligence, but the point

04:10:11.639 --> 04:10:14.040
was, the littlest dragonette would never

04:10:14.040 --> 04:10:15.540
hurt or betray anyone.

04:10:15.600 --> 04:10:18.540
Not even a bunch of sea wings she barely

04:10:18.540 --> 04:10:18.719
knew.

04:10:18.780 --> 04:10:22.020
Starflight was the opposite of Sunny.

04:10:22.079 --> 04:10:25.799
Very smart, totally unreliable, terrified

04:10:25.799 --> 04:10:26.340
of the world.

04:10:26.399 --> 04:10:29.879
He tried so hard to know everything, just

04:10:29.879 --> 04:10:31.260
so he could be useful in some way.

04:10:31.319 --> 04:10:34.260
He wasn't brave, he wasn't a good

04:10:34.260 --> 04:10:34.620
fighter.

04:10:34.680 --> 04:10:37.079
He didn't even have any useful night wing

04:10:37.079 --> 04:10:37.680
powers yet.

04:10:37.739 --> 04:10:40.680
Most of the time, tsunami felt sorry for

04:10:40.680 --> 04:10:41.340
him.

04:10:41.399 --> 04:10:43.559
At least, when he wasn't trying to steal

04:10:43.559 --> 04:10:45.360
her position as leader of the group.

04:10:45.420 --> 04:10:48.000
But if Queen Coral would give him a

04:10:48.000 --> 04:10:49.860
chance, she might see that his

04:10:49.860 --> 04:10:51.719
intelligence could be really useful

04:10:51.719 --> 04:10:54.059
especially in fighting the other tribes.

04:10:54.120 --> 04:10:56.879
He probably knew more about the war and

04:10:56.879 --> 04:10:58.440
the different tribes than any other

04:10:58.440 --> 04:10:59.459
Dragon Empirea.

04:10:59.520 --> 04:11:01.260
Glory.

04:11:01.319 --> 04:11:04.379
Well, Coral didn't know it.

04:11:04.440 --> 04:11:05.700
The glory was probably the least

04:11:05.700 --> 04:11:08.280
trustworthy and most dangerous of all of

04:11:08.280 --> 04:11:08.459
them.

04:11:08.520 --> 04:11:10.799
Her secret venom proved that.

04:11:10.860 --> 04:11:13.319
Tsunami curled her talons in.

04:11:13.379 --> 04:11:16.620
In the Skywing Palace, why had Glory

04:11:16.620 --> 04:11:18.239
waited so long to save her friends?

04:11:18.299 --> 04:11:21.360
If she'd used the venom on Queen Scarlet

04:11:21.360 --> 04:11:23.579
earlier, tsunami wouldn't have had to

04:11:23.579 --> 04:11:24.000
kill her father.

04:11:24.120 --> 04:11:27.299
Plus, she always talked like she didn't

04:11:27.299 --> 04:11:29.399
care about the prophecy, then got mad

04:11:29.399 --> 04:11:31.379
when other dragons pointed out that she

04:11:31.379 --> 04:11:31.920
wasn't in it.

04:11:31.979 --> 04:11:34.379
It was hard to figure out what she really

04:11:34.379 --> 04:11:35.100
wanted.

04:11:35.159 --> 04:11:37.680
And tsunami could definitely live without

04:11:37.680 --> 04:11:39.239
her sarcastic comments.

04:11:39.299 --> 04:11:43.139
But glory had saved them all, in the end

04:11:43.139 --> 04:11:44.340
in the sky kingdom.

04:11:44.399 --> 04:11:46.920
She'd killed to protect her friends.

04:11:46.979 --> 04:11:50.760
And I notice nobody seems all mad at her

04:11:50.760 --> 04:11:53.159
about that, tsunami thought bitterly.

04:11:53.219 --> 04:11:56.459
Instead, I'm the crazy impulsive one.

04:11:56.459 --> 04:11:58.020
Like, that's fair.

04:11:58.139 --> 04:12:01.139
Still, if glory would do that for them

04:12:01.139 --> 04:12:03.059
then Queen Coral should learn to trust

04:12:03.059 --> 04:12:03.420
her too.

04:12:03.479 --> 04:12:06.059
When mother gets back to the Summer

04:12:06.059 --> 04:12:08.639
Palace, tsunami thought, I'll talk to

04:12:08.639 --> 04:12:08.879
her.

04:12:08.940 --> 04:12:11.280
I'll make sure she treats them like my

04:12:11.280 --> 04:12:13.020
friends, not prisoners.

04:12:13.079 --> 04:12:16.799
No matter how mad they made her, tsunami

04:12:16.799 --> 04:12:18.719
didn't want anything bad to happen to any

04:12:18.719 --> 04:12:21.659
of them, and after 2 days of sea wings

04:12:21.659 --> 04:12:23.760
she had to admit she kind of missed them

04:12:23.760 --> 04:12:26.040
even Starflight and Glory.

04:12:26.100 --> 04:12:30.000
The spiral horn rocks loomed out of the

04:12:30.000 --> 04:12:32.100
dark ahead of her, with a golden sea

04:12:32.100 --> 04:12:33.239
grass curtain behind them.

04:12:33.299 --> 04:12:36.420
Riptide paused at the rocks, swimming

04:12:36.420 --> 04:12:38.100
backward as if he was going to leave her

04:12:38.100 --> 04:12:38.280
there.

04:12:38.399 --> 04:12:41.579
Tsunami wound her tail around his and

04:12:41.579 --> 04:12:42.059
faced him.

04:12:42.120 --> 04:12:45.840
Come, she said, wishing she knew the

04:12:45.840 --> 04:12:48.180
patterns for please, and I might need

04:12:48.180 --> 04:12:50.639
your help, and the queen is far away and

04:12:50.639 --> 04:12:52.260
won't return until the storm is over.

04:12:52.319 --> 04:12:55.620
But all she could say was, come.

04:12:55.739 --> 04:12:58.559
Apparently, that was all she needed to

04:12:58.559 --> 04:12:58.799
say.

04:12:58.860 --> 04:13:01.260
Riptide nodded and gestured to the

04:13:01.260 --> 04:13:03.420
curtain, letting her lead the way.

04:13:03.479 --> 04:13:05.639
She unwound her tail and ducked through

04:13:05.639 --> 04:13:06.299
into the tunnel.

04:13:06.420 --> 04:13:09.719
The current in the tunnel felt faster and

04:13:09.719 --> 04:13:10.620
heavier than before.

04:13:10.680 --> 04:13:13.379
She splashed out into the summer palace

04:13:13.379 --> 04:13:15.180
cavern and turned toward the beach.

04:13:15.239 --> 04:13:18.180
The white pebbles had been swallowed by

04:13:18.180 --> 04:13:20.520
the rising water, and the cave mouth was

04:13:20.520 --> 04:13:21.659
already partly underwater.

04:13:21.780 --> 04:13:25.020
There were no sea wing guards, and no

04:13:25.020 --> 04:13:26.700
sign of her friends outside the cave.

04:13:26.760 --> 04:13:29.819
Tsunami looked up, wondering if they'd

04:13:29.819 --> 04:13:31.139
been moved to a higher cave.

04:13:31.200 --> 04:13:34.200
But all she saw was a few curious sea

04:13:34.200 --> 04:13:35.340
wing faces peering down.

04:13:35.399 --> 04:13:38.639
Most of the dragons had taken refuge out

04:13:38.639 --> 04:13:40.260
of the way of the dripping canopy.

04:13:40.319 --> 04:13:43.379
Being all wet was wonderful, but having

04:13:43.379 --> 04:13:46.020
your head splatted one annoying drop at a

04:13:46.020 --> 04:13:47.340
time was not as much fun.

04:13:47.399 --> 04:13:50.700
Tsunami paddled over to the beach and

04:13:50.700 --> 04:13:52.739
felt the pebbles scrape under her claws

04:13:52.739 --> 04:13:54.180
as she climbed up to the cave.

04:13:54.239 --> 04:13:57.360
The water was only up to her underbelly

04:13:57.360 --> 04:13:58.799
but she could tell it was rising

04:13:58.799 --> 04:13:59.100
quickly.

04:13:59.159 --> 04:14:02.280
It lapped around the egg, chilly and

04:14:02.280 --> 04:14:03.000
unwelcoming.

04:14:03.059 --> 04:14:05.100
And tsunami remembered that she was

04:14:05.100 --> 04:14:06.059
supposed to keep it warm.

04:14:06.120 --> 04:14:09.000
Hang in there, little sister. she

04:14:09.000 --> 04:14:09.299
thought.

04:14:09.360 --> 04:14:10.440
Not much longer.

04:14:10.500 --> 04:14:12.239
Hello?

04:14:12.299 --> 04:14:13.979
She called into the cave.

04:14:14.040 --> 04:14:16.860
Her eyes adjusted to the darkness, and

04:14:16.860 --> 04:14:19.500
she saw one giant lump of shadows piled

04:14:19.500 --> 04:14:20.280
near the back.

04:14:20.340 --> 04:14:22.139
Her heart lurched.

04:14:22.200 --> 04:14:23.399
No.

04:14:23.459 --> 04:14:25.680
Were those her friends' bodies?

04:14:25.739 --> 04:14:27.780
Had she come too late?

04:14:27.840 --> 04:14:32.219
Chapter 17.

04:14:32.399 --> 04:14:36.000
A small head lifted up from the top of

04:14:36.000 --> 04:14:36.360
the lamp.

04:14:36.479 --> 04:14:38.459
Tsunami?

04:14:38.520 --> 04:14:40.139
Squeaked Sonny's voice.

04:14:40.200 --> 04:14:41.879
Are you all right?

04:14:41.940 --> 04:14:43.500
Tsunami blurted.

04:14:43.559 --> 04:14:46.260
She waited over and realized the bottom

04:14:46.260 --> 04:14:48.899
of the lump was clay, stretched out in

04:14:48.899 --> 04:14:50.940
the water, half submerged.

04:14:51.000 --> 04:14:54.059
Lying on top of him was glory, and on top

04:14:54.059 --> 04:14:56.340
of her was Starflight, and at the top of

04:14:56.340 --> 04:14:58.920
the pile sat Sunny, well out of reach of

04:14:58.920 --> 04:14:59.159
the water.

04:14:59.219 --> 04:15:02.579
This is a terrible strategy.

04:15:02.639 --> 04:15:05.040
Tsunami pointed out, as her friends

04:15:05.040 --> 04:15:06.840
opened their eyes one by one.

04:15:06.899 --> 04:15:09.299
She covered her relief that they were

04:15:09.299 --> 04:15:10.559
alive by scolding them.

04:15:10.620 --> 04:15:13.500
Seriously, whose idea was this?

04:15:14.040 --> 04:15:14.579
Starflights?

04:15:14.639 --> 04:15:17.340
Look, once the cave fills with water

04:15:17.340 --> 04:15:18.299
you'll be stuck in here.

04:15:18.360 --> 04:15:21.120
And even if it only covers clay, he can't

04:15:21.120 --> 04:15:22.680
hold his breath for the entire storm.

04:15:22.739 --> 04:15:24.840
Why haven't you moved to another cave?

04:15:24.899 --> 04:15:28.379
Oh, Glory said icily.

04:15:28.440 --> 04:15:31.860
The sea wing princess has time for us all

04:15:31.860 --> 04:15:32.700
of a sudden.

04:15:32.700 --> 04:15:36.600
It's only been a day, tsunami said

04:15:36.600 --> 04:15:37.379
uncomfortably.

04:15:37.440 --> 04:15:39.059
Mothers kept me busy.

04:15:39.120 --> 04:15:42.959
Well, we feel so blessed that you found

04:15:42.959 --> 04:15:43.680
time to visit.

04:15:43.739 --> 04:15:46.200
Please to impart some more incredibly

04:15:46.200 --> 04:15:47.280
brilliant wisdom on us.

04:15:47.340 --> 04:15:50.100
Glory wriggled and twisted her neck to

04:15:50.100 --> 04:15:51.540
glare up at Starflight.

04:15:51.600 --> 04:15:54.719
Get your honking gray claws off my wings

04:15:54.719 --> 04:15:55.799
before I bite you.

04:15:55.860 --> 04:15:58.799
We can't go anywhere, tsunami?

04:15:58.920 --> 04:16:01.319
Sonny said, as Starflight hurriedly

04:16:01.319 --> 04:16:02.219
adjusted his position.

04:16:02.280 --> 04:16:04.260
We couldn't leave clay.

04:16:04.379 --> 04:16:07.379
She pointed down at Clay's talons.

04:16:07.440 --> 04:16:09.899
Clay lifted his front talons with an

04:16:09.899 --> 04:16:11.399
apologetic expression.

04:16:11.639 --> 04:16:14.760
Silver chains ran around each ankle and

04:16:14.760 --> 04:16:16.260
were bolted to rings in the floor.

04:16:16.319 --> 04:16:18.899
He had them around his back talons as

04:16:18.899 --> 04:16:19.260
well.

04:16:19.319 --> 04:16:23.340
Shock stabbed through tsunami, followed

04:16:23.340 --> 04:16:24.000
by fury.

04:16:24.059 --> 04:16:26.940
Had her mother ordered this?

04:16:27.000 --> 04:16:29.159
If so, she must have known Clay could

04:16:29.159 --> 04:16:31.079
drown in the storm, and she didn't care.

04:16:31.139 --> 04:16:34.139
She'd lied to tsunami that her friends

04:16:34.139 --> 04:16:34.920
would be all right.

04:16:34.979 --> 04:16:37.440
But maybe she didn't know.

04:16:37.500 --> 04:16:39.780
Maybe this was sharks doing.

04:16:39.840 --> 04:16:43.079
If that's the case, I'll rip him apart.

04:16:43.139 --> 04:16:45.659
I knew you'd come for us, though.

04:16:45.780 --> 04:16:46.979
Sonny said.

04:16:47.040 --> 04:16:49.200
I mean, I thought you'd come yesterday, or

04:16:49.200 --> 04:16:51.780
this morning, or when the storm started

04:16:51.780 --> 04:16:54.180
but I knew you would come, eventually.

04:16:54.239 --> 04:16:56.639
Well, I was pretty sure.

04:16:56.760 --> 04:17:00.540
I was sure you wouldn't, Glory said.

04:17:00.600 --> 04:17:03.600
Don't you have a feast or a coronation or

04:17:03.600 --> 04:17:05.159
a beheading to attend?

04:17:05.399 --> 04:17:07.079
She squinted at tsunami.

04:17:07.139 --> 04:17:09.719
Is that an egg?

04:17:09.780 --> 04:17:11.219
Wow.

04:17:11.280 --> 04:17:13.379
They work fast in the kingdom of the

04:17:13.379 --> 04:17:13.620
sea.

04:17:13.680 --> 04:17:15.299
Who's the lucky father?

04:17:15.420 --> 04:17:19.319
Glory, stop sniping at me for 2 seconds

04:17:19.319 --> 04:17:19.799
please.

04:17:19.860 --> 04:17:21.299
Tsunami said.

04:17:21.420 --> 04:17:23.700
She slung the harness off and carefully

04:17:23.700 --> 04:17:24.780
passed it up to Sonny.

04:17:24.840 --> 04:17:27.059
Sunny, I need you to take care of this.

04:17:27.120 --> 04:17:29.819
It has to stay warm, and you're the only

04:17:29.819 --> 04:17:30.959
one who can keep it that way.

04:17:31.020 --> 04:17:34.139
She hoped the natural warmth from a sand

04:17:34.139 --> 04:17:36.299
wings scales would be similar to what the

04:17:36.299 --> 04:17:37.379
egg would have in the nursery.

04:17:37.440 --> 04:17:39.000
Me?

04:17:39.059 --> 04:17:41.639
Sonny's voice was filled with delight.

04:17:41.700 --> 04:17:44.100
You want me to do something important?

04:17:44.219 --> 04:17:46.139
Really important?

04:17:46.260 --> 04:17:47.700
Tsunami said.

04:17:47.760 --> 04:17:50.280
That's the very last female dragonette

04:17:50.280 --> 04:17:51.719
Queen Coral may ever have.

04:17:51.780 --> 04:17:54.540
Somebody wants it dead, and we're going

04:17:54.540 --> 04:17:55.799
to make sure that doesn't happen.

04:17:55.860 --> 04:17:58.739
Sonny wrapped the harness around herself

04:17:58.739 --> 04:18:01.260
twice and nestled the egg into our warm

04:18:01.260 --> 04:18:01.799
scales.

04:18:01.860 --> 04:18:04.979
When tsunami glanced up, she thought she

04:18:04.979 --> 04:18:07.139
saw a pulse of dark blue moving inside

04:18:07.139 --> 04:18:07.620
the egg.

04:18:07.680 --> 04:18:10.860
So keep it warm and safe, and for

04:18:10.860 --> 04:18:12.299
goodness sake, don't break it.

04:18:12.420 --> 04:18:14.760
And don't let clay anywhere near it in

04:18:14.760 --> 04:18:16.200
case he accidentally sits on it.

04:18:16.260 --> 04:18:19.739
I would never play protested.

04:18:19.799 --> 04:18:22.379
His stomach growled loudly.

04:18:22.440 --> 04:18:25.079
Haven't they at least fed you?

04:18:25.079 --> 04:18:26.280
tsunami asked.

04:18:26.399 --> 04:18:30.059
We got some breakfast leftovers this

04:18:30.059 --> 04:18:32.159
morning, Clay said with a sigh.

04:18:32.280 --> 04:18:37.200
Very extremely tiny small crabs.

04:18:37.260 --> 04:18:41.639
I am going to claw someone, tsunami

04:18:41.639 --> 04:18:42.239
snarled.

04:18:42.299 --> 04:18:46.020
So was Lagoon lying to Queen Coral, or

04:18:46.020 --> 04:18:48.000
was she neglecting the dragonettes on the

04:18:48.000 --> 04:18:49.020
Queen's orders?

04:18:49.079 --> 04:18:52.020
Tsunami crouched to study the chains.

04:18:52.079 --> 04:18:54.120
Did you try melting them?

04:18:54.180 --> 04:18:57.180
She asked Sonny and Starflight, like you

04:18:57.180 --> 04:18:58.680
did when you freed me under the

04:18:58.680 --> 04:18:58.920
mountain?

04:18:59.040 --> 04:19:02.219
Starflight leaned over and pointed at a

04:19:02.219 --> 04:19:04.379
few blackened sections of the chain.

04:19:04.440 --> 04:19:06.959
We tried, he said.

04:19:07.020 --> 04:19:09.120
His voice sounded more deflated than

04:19:09.120 --> 04:19:09.479
usual.

04:19:09.540 --> 04:19:12.059
It didn't work.

04:19:12.120 --> 04:19:14.340
This metal must be like the Skywing wires

04:19:14.340 --> 04:19:15.899
reinforced in some way.

04:19:15.959 --> 04:19:18.659
Tsunami heard splashing behind her and

04:19:18.659 --> 04:19:19.440
whirled around.

04:19:19.500 --> 04:19:21.059
But it was only riptide.

04:19:21.180 --> 04:19:23.639
How do we get these off?

04:19:23.700 --> 04:19:24.360
she demanded.

04:19:24.479 --> 04:19:27.120
He rubbed his snout nervously.

04:19:27.180 --> 04:19:29.940
You'll need the key from the guards, he

04:19:29.940 --> 04:19:32.040
said, but they'll never give it to you.

04:19:32.100 --> 04:19:34.200
We'll see about that.

04:19:34.260 --> 04:19:36.000
Tsunami growled.

04:19:36.059 --> 04:19:38.940
Hide if you need to, she said to

04:19:38.940 --> 04:19:39.420
Riptide.

04:19:39.479 --> 04:19:41.340
I might have to bring a guard back with

04:19:41.340 --> 04:19:41.579
me.

04:19:41.639 --> 04:19:44.579
By force, with my claws through his ears

04:19:44.579 --> 04:19:47.219
she muttered, as she stomped out of the

04:19:47.219 --> 04:19:47.459
cave.

04:19:47.520 --> 04:19:51.360
Seawing faces disappeared all over the

04:19:51.360 --> 04:19:53.579
palace when they saw her glaring around.

04:19:53.639 --> 04:19:55.979
But she remembered the lower pavilion

04:19:55.979 --> 04:19:58.319
level where she'd seen guards resting and

04:19:58.319 --> 04:19:59.459
drinking from cauldrons.

04:19:59.520 --> 04:20:01.979
She could see a few huddled shapes there

04:20:01.979 --> 04:20:02.219
now.

04:20:02.280 --> 04:20:04.739
Perhaps they assumed they could watch the

04:20:04.739 --> 04:20:06.659
cave from over there, out of the rain.

04:20:06.780 --> 04:20:10.680
Tsunami flapped over to the pavilion and

04:20:10.680 --> 04:20:12.600
landed next to a large cauldron that

04:20:12.600 --> 04:20:14.459
bubbled and smelled like green tea.

04:20:14.520 --> 04:20:17.100
Four guards were clustered around a low

04:20:17.100 --> 04:20:19.020
table, playing a game that involved

04:20:19.020 --> 04:20:20.159
rolling fish bones.

04:20:20.219 --> 04:20:22.979
They all froze when they heard her talons

04:20:22.979 --> 04:20:23.879
thud down.

04:20:23.940 --> 04:20:27.120
Slowly they turned toward her, and she

04:20:27.120 --> 04:20:29.040
guessed by their guilty faces that they

04:20:29.040 --> 04:20:30.360
weren't supposed to leave the cave.

04:20:30.420 --> 04:20:33.180
She couldn't tell if they felt guilty

04:20:33.180 --> 04:20:35.579
about leaving her friends to drown too, or

04:20:35.579 --> 04:20:37.079
if they were only worried about how the

04:20:37.079 --> 04:20:39.120
queen would react, when she found out

04:20:39.120 --> 04:20:41.340
tsunami had sauntered right into the

04:20:41.340 --> 04:20:42.360
Dragonette's cave.

04:20:42.420 --> 04:20:46.200
Give me the key, she growled.

04:20:46.260 --> 04:20:49.559
Ah, mumbled one of the guards.

04:20:49.620 --> 04:20:50.940
What key?

04:20:51.000 --> 04:20:54.540
Don't make me bite you, tsunami shouted.

04:20:54.600 --> 04:20:56.100
The key right now.

04:20:56.159 --> 04:20:59.159
She stepped forward, lashing her tail

04:20:59.159 --> 04:21:00.000
threateningly.

04:21:00.059 --> 04:21:03.000
Although all 4 of the guards were larger

04:21:03.000 --> 04:21:04.799
than her, they quailed backward.

04:21:04.860 --> 04:21:06.959
She wondered how many of them she could

04:21:06.959 --> 04:21:08.399
hurt if she attacked quickly.

04:21:08.459 --> 04:21:12.360
We can't. protested a 2nd guard.

04:21:12.420 --> 04:21:13.500
We have orders.

04:21:13.559 --> 04:21:17.639
Orders from whom tsunami demanded.

04:21:17.700 --> 04:21:22.079
Our, our commander, said the 1st guard.

04:21:22.139 --> 04:21:23.459
Shark.

04:21:23.520 --> 04:21:26.520
They all nodded fervently, as if they

04:21:26.520 --> 04:21:28.620
were hoping she'd now go away and yell at

04:21:28.620 --> 04:21:30.299
him instead of them.

04:21:30.360 --> 04:21:32.819
Too bad for him, tsunami said.

04:21:32.879 --> 04:21:34.379
Key.

04:21:34.440 --> 04:21:36.120
She held out her talon.

04:21:36.180 --> 04:21:40.500
But we can't, said the 2nd guard again.

04:21:40.620 --> 04:21:44.040
Tsunami studied his scales, looking for

04:21:44.040 --> 04:21:44.819
weak spots.

04:21:44.879 --> 04:21:47.819
She knew she was fast and strong, and she

04:21:47.819 --> 04:21:49.680
was pretty sure she could knock 2 guards

04:21:49.680 --> 04:21:51.659
over the side with her tail while she

04:21:51.659 --> 04:21:53.100
clawed a 3rd in the face with her

04:21:53.100 --> 04:21:53.579
talons.

04:21:53.639 --> 04:21:56.040
Perhaps she could use her teeth on the

04:21:56.040 --> 04:21:56.340
fourth.

04:21:56.399 --> 04:21:59.579
She remembered the feeling of sea wing

04:21:59.579 --> 04:22:01.739
scales, sliding under her claws, and

04:22:01.739 --> 04:22:02.280
shuddered.

04:22:02.340 --> 04:22:05.579
She'd looked at Gil this way too, in the

04:22:05.579 --> 04:22:08.219
arena, sizing him up so she could defeat

04:22:08.219 --> 04:22:08.579
him.

04:22:08.700 --> 04:22:10.379
What was she about to do?

04:22:10.440 --> 04:22:13.680
Hurt more dragons, just for being in her

04:22:13.680 --> 04:22:13.920
way?

04:22:14.040 --> 04:22:16.739
Dragons she didn't even know.

04:22:16.799 --> 04:22:19.079
Dragons who could be her brothers.

04:22:19.139 --> 04:22:22.799
Her cousins, Dragons who had families, who

04:22:22.799 --> 04:22:24.360
were more than nameless guards to

04:22:24.360 --> 04:22:24.719
somebody.

04:22:24.780 --> 04:22:27.959
Maybe her friends were right about her.

04:22:28.020 --> 04:22:31.860
The guards looked terrified, as if they

04:22:31.860 --> 04:22:33.000
were waiting for her to attack them.

04:22:33.059 --> 04:22:35.940
But they also knew what coral was capable

04:22:35.940 --> 04:22:38.399
of, and surely shark as well.

04:22:38.459 --> 04:22:40.739
Tsunami couldn't think of anything

04:22:40.739 --> 04:22:43.079
scarier than what her mother had done to

04:22:43.079 --> 04:22:43.620
tortoise.

04:22:43.680 --> 04:22:45.299
She didn't really want to try.

04:22:45.360 --> 04:22:49.079
So if she couldn't be more scary than her

04:22:49.079 --> 04:22:51.239
mother, maybe there was another way.

04:22:51.299 --> 04:22:53.760
Maybe she could convince the guards

04:22:53.760 --> 04:22:55.139
instead of fighting them.

04:22:55.200 --> 04:22:58.379
She remembered the dragons in the Skywing

04:22:58.379 --> 04:23:00.239
prison, singing the song about the

04:23:00.239 --> 04:23:02.219
dragonettes coming to save the day.

04:23:02.219 --> 04:23:04.620
Maybe these guards were like those

04:23:04.620 --> 04:23:07.260
dragons, believing in the prophecy

04:23:07.260 --> 04:23:08.700
wanting it to come true.

04:23:08.819 --> 04:23:11.940
Maybe she could use that instead of just

04:23:11.940 --> 04:23:13.559
hitting them with her tail like she was

04:23:13.559 --> 04:23:14.100
tempted to.

04:23:14.159 --> 04:23:18.299
Listen, she said fiercely, don't you know

04:23:18.299 --> 04:23:19.079
about the prophecy?

04:23:19.139 --> 04:23:21.959
The guards exchanged glances.

04:23:22.020 --> 04:23:24.540
She guessed that the prophecy had been

04:23:24.540 --> 04:23:26.579
talked about plenty since the dragonets

04:23:26.579 --> 04:23:27.000
arrived.

04:23:27.059 --> 04:23:28.559
Great.

04:23:28.620 --> 04:23:30.600
So do you remember anything in the

04:23:30.600 --> 04:23:33.180
prophecy about a group of octopus heads

04:23:33.180 --> 04:23:35.280
letting the mud wing drown before he

04:23:35.280 --> 04:23:37.020
could save the world?

04:23:37.079 --> 04:23:37.979
Did I miss that part?

04:23:38.040 --> 04:23:40.079
She lashed her tail.

04:23:40.139 --> 04:23:42.899
Do you want to be the ones who ruined

04:23:42.899 --> 04:23:45.059
Pira's only chance of stopping the war?

04:23:45.120 --> 04:23:48.780
No, blurted the 3rd guard.

04:23:48.840 --> 04:23:50.159
The war has to end.

04:23:50.280 --> 04:23:52.020
He ducked his head.

04:23:52.079 --> 04:23:54.120
You saved my brother today.

04:23:54.180 --> 04:23:56.280
When you sent him to have his wounds

04:23:56.280 --> 04:23:56.700
tended.

04:23:56.760 --> 04:23:58.739
She would have kept him standing there

04:23:58.739 --> 04:24:00.239
for the rest of the council meeting.

04:24:00.299 --> 04:24:03.659
Tsunami was shocked into silence for a

04:24:03.659 --> 04:24:03.959
moment.

04:24:04.020 --> 04:24:05.159
Was that true?

04:24:05.280 --> 04:24:08.520
Did Queen Coral let soldiers die like

04:24:08.520 --> 04:24:08.760
that?

04:24:08.879 --> 04:24:10.139
For no reason?

04:24:10.200 --> 04:24:12.600
Which one was your brother?

04:24:12.659 --> 04:24:13.620
She asked.

04:24:13.680 --> 04:24:16.979
He indicated his throat, the one with the

04:24:16.979 --> 04:24:18.659
gash, and the blood coming from his

04:24:18.659 --> 04:24:19.260
gills.

04:24:19.319 --> 04:24:21.899
Oh, tsunami said.

04:24:21.959 --> 04:24:23.760
What happened to his friend?

04:24:23.819 --> 04:24:26.819
All the guards shook their heads.

04:24:26.879 --> 04:24:30.299
Too late, said the 1st guard.

04:24:30.360 --> 04:24:32.700
She crushed the fish bones between her

04:24:32.700 --> 04:24:34.139
front claws and looked away.

04:24:34.200 --> 04:24:38.219
We want to help you, said the 3rd guard.

04:24:38.280 --> 04:24:40.799
But if we support a new queen before the

04:24:40.799 --> 04:24:43.319
challenge is even made, it could go

04:24:43.319 --> 04:24:44.280
really badly for us.

04:24:44.399 --> 04:24:49.500
So, somebody does see me as a potential

04:24:49.500 --> 04:24:52.139
queen, tsunami thought, pleased.

04:24:52.200 --> 04:24:55.920
I told you, she can't be our new queen

04:24:55.920 --> 04:24:57.540
said the 1st guard.

04:24:57.600 --> 04:24:59.700
The dragonettes and the prophecy have to

04:24:59.700 --> 04:25:01.620
be outside the war to stop it.

04:25:01.680 --> 04:25:04.979
Besides, anemone is supposed to be our

04:25:04.979 --> 04:25:07.440
next queen, growled the 4th guard.

04:25:07.559 --> 04:25:10.260
You don't know what a prophecy means

04:25:10.260 --> 04:25:11.940
argued the 3rd guard.

04:25:12.000 --> 04:25:13.920
Maybe they're all supposed to rule their

04:25:13.920 --> 04:25:15.420
tribes and stop the war that way.

04:25:15.540 --> 04:25:19.260
That's not possible, insisted the 2nd

04:25:19.260 --> 04:25:19.680
guard.

04:25:19.739 --> 04:25:21.059
Two of them are male.

04:25:21.180 --> 04:25:23.879
Tsunami got the feeling they've been

04:25:23.879 --> 04:25:25.139
having this argument for a while.

04:25:25.200 --> 04:25:27.719
The 3rd guard turned to her suddenly.

04:25:27.780 --> 04:25:30.479
You tell us, he said.

04:25:30.540 --> 04:25:31.500
What's your plan?

04:25:31.620 --> 04:25:33.780
If you really are the dragonette of the

04:25:33.780 --> 04:25:35.399
prophecy, How are you going to make it

04:25:35.399 --> 04:25:36.059
come true?

04:25:36.120 --> 04:25:38.700
Tsunami shifted her weight on her

04:25:38.700 --> 04:25:39.180
talons?

04:25:39.239 --> 04:25:41.459
That was the question she couldn't

04:25:41.459 --> 04:25:41.760
answer.

04:25:41.819 --> 04:25:44.520
The talons of peace hadn't taught them

04:25:44.520 --> 04:25:44.940
what to do.

04:25:45.000 --> 04:25:47.579
Nobody seemed to know.

04:25:47.579 --> 04:25:49.440
As much as she liked to talk about how

04:25:49.440 --> 04:25:51.420
the dragonettes would choose the next

04:25:51.420 --> 04:25:52.620
sand wing queen.

04:25:52.680 --> 04:25:54.479
She couldn't imagine how that would

04:25:54.479 --> 04:25:54.719
work.

04:25:54.780 --> 04:25:56.520
Who would listen to them?

04:25:56.579 --> 04:25:58.739
Even if they went around the whole

04:25:58.739 --> 04:26:01.020
continent saying, how about blister?

04:26:01.079 --> 04:26:03.059
We like her, let's have blister win.

04:26:03.120 --> 04:26:04.379
What good would that do?

04:26:04.440 --> 04:26:07.139
It wouldn't stop burn and blaze from

04:26:07.139 --> 04:26:07.500
fighting.

04:26:07.559 --> 04:26:10.379
But some dragons believed in the

04:26:10.379 --> 04:26:10.920
prophecy.

04:26:10.979 --> 04:26:14.040
Soldiers, exactly like these four.

04:26:14.159 --> 04:26:16.379
She couldn't let them see that she had no

04:26:16.379 --> 04:26:17.459
idea what she was doing.

04:26:17.520 --> 04:26:20.219
Listen, she said.

04:26:20.280 --> 04:26:22.739
I don't know if I'm supposed to be the

04:26:22.739 --> 04:26:24.239
next sea wing queen or not.

04:26:24.299 --> 04:26:26.940
Sometimes I think Queen Coral is doing

04:26:26.940 --> 04:26:30.600
everything right, and then sometimes, she

04:26:30.600 --> 04:26:32.639
stopped, remembering tortoise.

04:26:32.760 --> 04:26:35.280
Would anemone be a better queen?

04:26:35.340 --> 04:26:38.340
One day when she was old enough, would

04:26:38.340 --> 04:26:39.120
tsunami?

04:26:39.180 --> 04:26:42.120
But I do know this, she went on.

04:26:42.180 --> 04:26:45.479
We can't fulfill the prophecy without

04:26:45.479 --> 04:26:45.899
clay.

04:26:45.959 --> 04:26:49.079
He's the heart of our group, without him

04:26:49.079 --> 04:26:51.420
the rest of us will fall apart, and we

04:26:51.420 --> 04:26:53.280
won't be worthy of any destiny at all.

04:26:53.340 --> 04:26:56.219
She stepped toward the 1st guard.

04:26:56.280 --> 04:26:58.440
Whose expression was wavering between

04:26:58.440 --> 04:26:59.819
belief and worry.

04:26:59.879 --> 04:27:02.760
I know you don't trust Mudwings.

04:27:02.819 --> 04:27:06.059
I know you obey Shark in everything, but

04:27:06.059 --> 04:27:07.739
we're talking about the end of the war.

04:27:07.799 --> 04:27:10.500
You thought nothing you ever did could

04:27:10.500 --> 04:27:13.020
bring peace or save the dragons you care

04:27:13.020 --> 04:27:13.260
about.

04:27:13.319 --> 04:27:16.319
But right now, you can make all the

04:27:16.319 --> 04:27:16.739
difference.

04:27:16.799 --> 04:27:19.680
She took another step closer.

04:27:19.799 --> 04:27:22.260
Just give me the key.

04:27:22.319 --> 04:27:26.639
The guard twisted her talons together and

04:27:26.639 --> 04:27:27.479
looked at the others.

04:27:27.540 --> 04:27:29.159
Two of them nodded.

04:27:29.219 --> 04:27:30.899
The 4th looked away.

04:27:30.959 --> 04:27:33.600
Her tail twitching as if she wanted to be

04:27:33.600 --> 04:27:35.100
left out of the blame.

04:27:35.159 --> 04:27:37.920
I'll do everything I can to protect you.

04:27:37.979 --> 04:27:39.659
Tsunami promised.

04:27:39.719 --> 04:27:42.840
The 1st guard reached into a niche in the

04:27:42.840 --> 04:27:44.520
table and pulled out a pair of heavy

04:27:44.520 --> 04:27:45.360
silver keys.

04:27:45.420 --> 04:27:48.239
She placed them carefully in tsunami's

04:27:48.239 --> 04:27:48.600
talons.

04:27:48.659 --> 04:27:51.420
Thank you, Tsunami said.

04:27:51.479 --> 04:27:53.040
What are your names?

04:27:53.100 --> 04:27:56.280
Snail, said the 1st guard.

04:27:56.399 --> 04:27:58.139
She pointed at the others.

04:27:58.200 --> 04:28:00.540
Flounder, herring, and kelp.

04:28:00.600 --> 04:28:01.979
Please.

04:28:02.100 --> 04:28:03.059
She paused.

04:28:03.120 --> 04:28:05.879
If you do become queen, please remember

04:28:05.879 --> 04:28:06.180
us.

04:28:06.239 --> 04:28:08.219
Whatever she does to punish us.

04:28:08.280 --> 04:28:11.040
Please, take care of our families.

04:28:11.159 --> 04:28:15.180
And stop the war, Herring said fiercely.

04:28:15.239 --> 04:28:16.799
Whatever you have to do.

04:28:16.860 --> 04:28:20.879
Tsunami stepped back, curling her claws

04:28:20.879 --> 04:28:22.799
around the keys, and saluted to the

04:28:22.799 --> 04:28:23.100
guards.

04:28:23.159 --> 04:28:25.920
She took off from the pavilion and flew

04:28:25.920 --> 04:28:26.760
back down to the cave.

04:28:26.819 --> 04:28:30.420
The water was nearly up to her wings by

04:28:30.420 --> 04:28:30.719
now.

04:28:30.780 --> 04:28:33.540
Clay was standing, watching the rising

04:28:33.540 --> 04:28:36.239
water unhappily, with Sonny still perched

04:28:36.239 --> 04:28:36.719
on his back.

04:28:36.780 --> 04:28:39.180
Glory and Starflight were in the water

04:28:39.180 --> 04:28:40.260
with riptide.

04:28:40.379 --> 04:28:43.379
They both looked tremendously irritated

04:28:43.379 --> 04:28:44.639
at how wet they were.

04:28:44.700 --> 04:28:46.500
Hooray!

04:28:46.559 --> 04:28:49.200
Sonny yelped when tsunami held up the

04:28:49.200 --> 04:28:49.500
keys.

04:28:49.559 --> 04:28:51.180
Wow.

04:28:51.239 --> 04:28:52.500
Glory said.

04:28:52.559 --> 04:28:55.139
Swirling waves of bright yellow shifted

04:28:55.139 --> 04:28:55.920
through her scales.

04:28:55.979 --> 04:28:58.260
I did not think that was going to work.

04:28:58.319 --> 04:29:01.319
Tsunami plunged her head under the water

04:29:01.319 --> 04:29:03.840
and lifted the shackles around Clay's

04:29:03.840 --> 04:29:04.200
ankles.

04:29:04.260 --> 04:29:06.899
She found the lock for the front talons

04:29:06.899 --> 04:29:09.059
quickly, inserted one of the keys and

04:29:09.059 --> 04:29:09.540
freed him.

04:29:09.600 --> 04:29:12.180
The other key unlocked the chains on his

04:29:12.180 --> 04:29:13.079
back talons.

04:29:13.139 --> 04:29:15.719
Clay kicked them away and shook out his

04:29:15.719 --> 04:29:17.340
wings as tsunami stood up again.

04:29:17.459 --> 04:29:21.479
All better, he said, grinning at her.

04:29:21.540 --> 04:29:24.000
His stomach roared in disagreement.

04:29:24.059 --> 04:29:28.920
Well, almost all better, he amended.

04:29:28.979 --> 04:29:31.979
Let's find somewhere dry, and I'll see

04:29:31.979 --> 04:29:34.139
about food, tsunami said.

04:29:34.200 --> 04:29:36.479
She herded them out of the cave ahead of

04:29:36.479 --> 04:29:36.659
her.

04:29:36.719 --> 04:29:40.319
Riptide paused, still in the shadows, and

04:29:40.319 --> 04:29:41.100
she turned to him.

04:29:41.159 --> 04:29:43.799
Thank you, she whispered.

04:29:43.860 --> 04:29:45.719
You saved my friends.

04:29:45.780 --> 04:29:49.079
I didn't do much, he whispered back.

04:29:49.139 --> 04:29:51.600
I could never boss anybody into doing

04:29:51.600 --> 04:29:52.079
what I want.

04:29:52.200 --> 04:29:53.760
You're really good at it.

04:29:53.819 --> 04:29:56.459
Well, tsunami said.

04:29:56.520 --> 04:29:59.340
Sometimes bossing doesn't work, and you

04:29:59.340 --> 04:30:00.239
have to try something else.

04:30:00.299 --> 04:30:03.659
It'd be much easier if everyone just did

04:30:03.659 --> 04:30:04.379
as I told them.

04:30:04.440 --> 04:30:06.059
He laughed.

04:30:06.180 --> 04:30:08.159
I should get out of here before someone

04:30:08.159 --> 04:30:08.879
sees me.

04:30:08.940 --> 04:30:11.760
She nodded and wound her tail around

04:30:11.760 --> 04:30:12.540
his.

04:30:12.600 --> 04:30:15.120
I'll look for you again tomorrow, if I

04:30:15.120 --> 04:30:15.299
can.

04:30:15.360 --> 04:30:17.579
There's a lot of aquatic.

04:30:17.639 --> 04:30:18.360
I still have to learn.

04:30:18.479 --> 04:30:21.780
He smiled, and slipped out of the cave

04:30:21.780 --> 04:30:22.379
into the water.

04:30:22.440 --> 04:30:25.680
She waited onto the beach and watched his

04:30:25.680 --> 04:30:27.899
sky blue scales vanish into the

04:30:27.899 --> 04:30:28.680
underwater tunnel.

04:30:28.739 --> 04:30:31.440
She was glad she'd found at least one

04:30:31.440 --> 04:30:33.299
dragon she could trust in the kingdom of

04:30:33.299 --> 04:30:33.600
the sea.

04:30:33.719 --> 04:30:38.219
Ooh, glory started.

04:30:38.280 --> 04:30:42.000
Don't you dare, tsunami said, shoving her

04:30:42.000 --> 04:30:43.260
into the lake.

04:30:43.319 --> 04:30:45.840
The rain wing squawked indignantly and

04:30:45.840 --> 04:30:48.180
flapped up into the air, showering them

04:30:48.180 --> 04:30:49.620
all with cold droplets.

04:30:49.739 --> 04:30:52.200
Rain was still dripping down through the

04:30:52.200 --> 04:30:54.959
canopy, and small waves scudded across

04:30:54.959 --> 04:30:55.920
the surface of the bay.

04:30:55.979 --> 04:30:59.760
Let's try that cave, tsunami said

04:30:59.760 --> 04:31:02.459
pointing to one far up the cliff.

04:31:02.520 --> 04:31:04.260
If there's anyone in it, I'll clear them

04:31:04.260 --> 04:31:04.500
out.

04:31:04.559 --> 04:31:06.719
Glory snorted.

04:31:06.780 --> 04:31:09.420
But the cave turned out to be empty and

04:31:09.420 --> 04:31:12.360
dry, and once they all huddled into it, it

04:31:12.360 --> 04:31:13.260
felt warm as well.

04:31:13.260 --> 04:31:16.440
Sunny immediately curled around the egg

04:31:16.440 --> 04:31:18.420
stroking it and murmuring to it.

04:31:18.479 --> 04:31:21.360
Starflight blew a small spurt of flame

04:31:21.360 --> 04:31:22.440
into the air to heat them up.

04:31:22.500 --> 04:31:25.139
The dragonette can't hear you.

04:31:25.200 --> 04:31:27.420
Tsunami pointed out to Sonny.

04:31:27.479 --> 04:31:29.219
We don't know that.

04:31:29.280 --> 04:31:30.360
Sonny said.

04:31:30.420 --> 04:31:31.620
She might be scared.

04:31:31.680 --> 04:31:34.200
I'm just telling her it's all right, and

04:31:34.200 --> 04:31:34.979
we'll take care of her.

04:31:35.040 --> 04:31:37.440
Tsunami hit a smile.

04:31:37.500 --> 04:31:39.899
She was glad Sonny had agreed to take the

04:31:39.899 --> 04:31:40.860
egg.

04:31:40.920 --> 04:31:42.540
She'd been a little worried that the

04:31:42.540 --> 04:31:44.639
little sand wing might still be too mad

04:31:44.639 --> 04:31:45.959
at tsunami to want to help.

04:31:46.020 --> 04:31:48.780
But maybe she'd forgotten about tsunami

04:31:48.780 --> 04:31:51.360
attacking the Sky Wing soldier, or maybe

04:31:51.360 --> 04:31:52.860
Sonny was always willing to help.

04:31:52.979 --> 04:31:55.319
She didn't fight about everything just to

04:31:55.319 --> 04:31:57.059
be difficult. like glory did.

04:31:57.120 --> 04:32:00.540
Clay nudged tsunami with his snout.

04:32:00.659 --> 04:32:02.639
We're happy to see you.

04:32:02.760 --> 04:32:05.879
He said, tell us about the tribe.

04:32:05.940 --> 04:32:07.860
Does everyone adore you?

04:32:07.920 --> 04:32:09.239
Are they good fighters?

04:32:09.299 --> 04:32:10.920
What do they eat?

04:32:10.979 --> 04:32:12.959
He finished wistfully.

04:32:13.020 --> 04:32:16.680
Let me find you some food first, tsunami

04:32:16.680 --> 04:32:19.260
said, turning toward the cave entrance.

04:32:19.319 --> 04:32:21.479
She was surprised at how warm and happy

04:32:21.479 --> 04:32:23.100
she felt to be back with her friends

04:32:23.100 --> 04:32:23.340
again.

04:32:23.399 --> 04:32:26.700
This was how she'd expected to feel among

04:32:26.700 --> 04:32:29.040
the sea wings, like she was coming home.

04:32:29.100 --> 04:32:31.860
So why don't I?

04:32:31.979 --> 04:32:36.479
Chapter 18.

04:32:36.659 --> 04:32:40.440
Tsunami dropped three cauldrons on the

04:32:40.440 --> 04:32:41.100
cave floor.

04:32:41.159 --> 04:32:43.860
One packed with fish, one with clear

04:32:43.860 --> 04:32:46.319
water, and one with a seaweed mushroom

04:32:46.319 --> 04:32:46.680
salad.

04:32:46.739 --> 04:32:48.780
She'd found them on the kitchen level

04:32:48.780 --> 04:32:50.940
unguarded, so she thought they might as

04:32:50.940 --> 04:32:52.139
well go to the dragonettes.

04:32:52.200 --> 04:32:55.200
Sunny seized the salad cauldron and

04:32:55.200 --> 04:32:56.280
shoved her nose into it.

04:32:56.399 --> 04:32:59.280
Starflight peered at the fish, and then

04:32:59.280 --> 04:33:01.500
without even asking the others if they'd

04:33:01.500 --> 04:33:03.780
mind, he shot a burst of fire into the

04:33:03.780 --> 04:33:05.819
cauldron, which left all the fish

04:33:05.819 --> 04:33:07.380
blackened and smoky tasting.

04:33:07.500 --> 04:33:11.700
Hey, tsunami protested, I like them raw.

04:33:11.759 --> 04:33:15.779
Overruled, Glory said, raw fish is

04:33:15.779 --> 04:33:16.199
gross.

04:33:16.259 --> 04:33:18.779
Raw fish is awesome.

04:33:18.900 --> 04:33:20.700
Tsunami insisted.

04:33:20.759 --> 04:33:23.999
You have unreliable taste, said Glory.

04:33:24.119 --> 04:33:25.979
You think your terrifying mother is

04:33:25.979 --> 04:33:26.219
awesome.

04:33:26.279 --> 04:33:30.539
She is not terrifying, tsunami said.

04:33:30.599 --> 04:33:32.219
She's a wonderful queen.

04:33:32.279 --> 04:33:35.039
That is what all the scrolls say.

04:33:35.099 --> 04:33:37.259
Starflight pointed out, through a

04:33:37.259 --> 04:33:38.579
mouthful of charred fish.

04:33:38.639 --> 04:33:41.819
Tsunami looked up at the cave ceiling and

04:33:41.819 --> 04:33:43.740
shifted from talon to talon.

04:33:43.799 --> 04:33:45.959
Er, she said.

04:33:46.020 --> 04:33:50.819
Well, apparently she wrote a lot of those

04:33:50.819 --> 04:33:51.419
herself.

04:33:51.479 --> 04:33:52.860
Really?

04:33:52.979 --> 04:33:55.680
Starflight blinked in astonishment.

04:33:55.740 --> 04:33:57.540
She's a writer?

04:33:57.599 --> 04:33:59.159
I had no idea.

04:33:59.220 --> 04:34:03.060
That's so, I mean, I wish I...

04:34:03.360 --> 04:34:04.500
Do you think she'd read something?

04:34:04.500 --> 04:34:05.159
I...

04:34:05.700 --> 04:34:07.799
He stammered to a stop and fidgeted for a

04:34:07.799 --> 04:34:08.759
moment with a cauldron.

04:34:08.819 --> 04:34:12.900
It's cool, is all, he mumbled, shoving a

04:34:12.900 --> 04:34:13.560
fish in his mouth.

04:34:13.619 --> 04:34:16.799
Anyway, it's not just the scrolls.

04:34:16.860 --> 04:34:18.959
Her subjects think she's a great queen

04:34:18.959 --> 04:34:19.259
too.

04:34:19.319 --> 04:34:21.240
Tsunami said loyally.

04:34:21.299 --> 04:34:23.580
Most of them, I think.

04:34:23.700 --> 04:34:28.080
Compelling, said Glory, except for the

04:34:28.080 --> 04:34:29.639
part where she's killing off all her

04:34:29.639 --> 04:34:30.119
daughters.

04:34:30.180 --> 04:34:33.959
Tsunami stared at glory, to shocked to

04:34:33.959 --> 04:34:34.259
respond.

04:34:34.319 --> 04:34:36.840
Well, wait.

04:34:36.900 --> 04:34:39.779
Clay said, that's just a theory.

04:34:39.900 --> 04:34:44.099
A good theory, Starflight observed, with

04:34:44.099 --> 04:34:45.779
her daughter's dead and no sisters

04:34:45.779 --> 04:34:46.139
either.

04:34:46.200 --> 04:34:48.299
No one will ever be able to challenge her

04:34:48.299 --> 04:34:49.139
for the throne.

04:34:49.200 --> 04:34:51.720
She could be queen for 100 years, and die

04:34:51.720 --> 04:34:53.400
peacefully in her sleep instead of in

04:34:53.400 --> 04:34:53.759
combat.

04:34:53.819 --> 04:34:57.000
Sonny pulled the egg closer to her and

04:34:57.000 --> 04:34:58.139
patted it reassuringly.

04:34:58.200 --> 04:35:01.080
No, tsunami blurted.

04:35:01.139 --> 04:35:02.159
You're so wrong.

04:35:02.220 --> 04:35:03.659
She would never.

04:35:03.720 --> 04:35:06.119
You haven't seen how protective she is.

04:35:06.180 --> 04:35:08.459
I mean, look at how she takes care of

04:35:08.459 --> 04:35:09.000
anemone.

04:35:09.060 --> 04:35:11.819
Like a crazy dragon.

04:35:11.880 --> 04:35:15.000
Glory interjected, waving a smoky fish at

04:35:15.000 --> 04:35:15.779
tsunami.

04:35:15.840 --> 04:35:18.180
It's a good way to make herself look

04:35:18.180 --> 04:35:18.900
innocent.

04:35:18.959 --> 04:35:20.340
Starflight offered.

04:35:20.400 --> 04:35:23.220
Besides, think about when the murders

04:35:23.220 --> 04:35:23.700
started.

04:35:23.759 --> 04:35:27.299
He waited, with an isn't it obvious?

04:35:27.299 --> 04:35:28.019
Look on his face.

04:35:28.139 --> 04:35:30.119
Oh, dear.

04:35:30.180 --> 04:35:32.580
Clay said, rubbing his head.

04:35:32.639 --> 04:35:35.159
Did we really study this?

04:35:35.220 --> 04:35:37.020
I don't know either.

04:35:37.139 --> 04:35:38.939
Sonny whispered to him.

04:35:39.000 --> 04:35:42.180
Starflight, tsunami growled.

04:35:42.240 --> 04:35:43.319
Just tell us.

04:35:43.439 --> 04:35:46.619
Very well, he said.

04:35:46.680 --> 04:35:48.599
It was right after the only challenge

04:35:48.599 --> 04:35:50.040
Queen Coral has ever faced.

04:35:50.099 --> 04:35:52.679
Her 1st clutch of eggs had one female in

04:35:52.679 --> 04:35:52.919
it.

04:35:52.979 --> 04:35:55.799
Orca, tsunami guest.

04:35:55.860 --> 04:35:58.319
Starfly nodded with a pleased

04:35:58.319 --> 04:35:58.860
expression.

04:35:58.919 --> 04:36:00.419
You do remember?

04:36:00.479 --> 04:36:02.819
She challenged the queen almost the

04:36:02.819 --> 04:36:03.840
moment she was full grown.

04:36:03.900 --> 04:36:06.479
I'm sure Coral was more shocked than

04:36:06.479 --> 04:36:09.060
anyone, especially when Orca almost

04:36:09.060 --> 04:36:09.779
killed her.

04:36:09.840 --> 04:36:13.799
Queen Coral only won by accident. impaling

04:36:13.799 --> 04:36:16.139
Orca on that narwhal horn she has on the

04:36:16.139 --> 04:36:16.859
end of her tail.

04:36:16.919 --> 04:36:19.739
So, Tsunami said.

04:36:19.799 --> 04:36:21.840
Why would that make her murder all her

04:36:21.840 --> 04:36:22.500
future daughters?

04:36:22.560 --> 04:36:24.360
Seriously?

04:36:24.419 --> 04:36:25.859
Glory scoffed.

04:36:25.919 --> 04:36:28.319
She saw how close she could come to

04:36:28.319 --> 04:36:28.859
death.

04:36:28.919 --> 04:36:31.259
She realized if she let any of her female

04:36:31.259 --> 04:36:33.599
children grow up, she might be dead

04:36:33.599 --> 04:36:36.599
within 7 years, much easier to kill them

04:36:36.599 --> 04:36:38.459
all in their eggs, or as little

04:36:38.459 --> 04:36:40.379
dragonettes, before they become a

04:36:40.379 --> 04:36:40.619
threat.

04:36:40.740 --> 04:36:42.360
Stop it!

04:36:42.419 --> 04:36:44.339
Tsunami clutched her head.

04:36:44.400 --> 04:36:45.959
It couldn't be true.

04:36:46.080 --> 04:36:48.299
She's not like that.

04:36:48.360 --> 04:36:49.919
She loves her daughters.

04:36:49.979 --> 04:36:52.259
When she found the other egg broken.

04:36:52.319 --> 04:36:55.860
Tsunami paused, realizing how much they

04:36:55.860 --> 04:36:56.340
didn't know.

04:36:56.400 --> 04:36:59.220
She backed up to tell them all about the

04:36:59.220 --> 04:37:02.040
council, her mother's scrolls, the

04:37:02.040 --> 04:37:03.959
mysterious dragon who'd tried to kill her

04:37:03.959 --> 04:37:06.240
in the tunnel, and the way Queen Coral

04:37:06.240 --> 04:37:07.979
had reacted when Tortoise failed her.

04:37:08.040 --> 04:37:09.840
So you see?

04:37:09.959 --> 04:37:11.099
She finished.

04:37:11.159 --> 04:37:13.139
It can't be her killing off the female

04:37:13.139 --> 04:37:14.159
dragonettes.

04:37:14.220 --> 04:37:15.900
She wants them alive more than anyone.

04:37:15.959 --> 04:37:18.900
Someone tried to kill you?

04:37:19.020 --> 04:37:20.220
Clay said.

04:37:20.279 --> 04:37:21.479
Are you all right?

04:37:21.540 --> 04:37:24.240
I'd like to know what would have happened

04:37:24.240 --> 04:37:26.279
to us if they'd succeeded?

04:37:26.340 --> 04:37:27.779
Glory said angrily.

04:37:27.840 --> 04:37:30.659
Are you saying Sonny's in danger now?

04:37:30.720 --> 04:37:33.000
Starflight demanded at the same time?

04:37:33.060 --> 04:37:34.680
Because of that egg?

04:37:34.740 --> 04:37:36.299
Why would you do that to her?

04:37:36.360 --> 04:37:40.560
I don't mind, Sonny said, cuddling the

04:37:40.560 --> 04:37:41.639
egg to her chest.

04:37:41.759 --> 04:37:43.559
But she looked paler than usual.

04:37:43.619 --> 04:37:47.579
No, listen, tsunami said.

04:37:47.639 --> 04:37:50.040
She took a step back toward the cave

04:37:50.040 --> 04:37:50.459
entrance.

04:37:50.520 --> 04:37:51.959
Don't you see?

04:37:52.020 --> 04:37:54.180
We're doing a good thing by keeping this

04:37:54.180 --> 04:37:54.779
egg alive.

04:37:54.840 --> 04:37:57.540
And now Queen Coral has to take care of

04:37:57.540 --> 04:37:59.880
all of us, because we're protecting her

04:37:59.880 --> 04:38:00.119
daughter.

04:38:00.240 --> 04:38:03.060
She can't chain you up and not feed you

04:38:03.060 --> 04:38:03.479
anymore.

04:38:03.540 --> 04:38:06.060
If that was even her idea in the 1st

04:38:06.060 --> 04:38:06.360
place.

04:38:06.479 --> 04:38:10.380
Glory and Starflight exchanged, yeah

04:38:10.380 --> 04:38:10.860
right.

04:38:10.919 --> 04:38:11.759
Glances.

04:38:11.819 --> 04:38:13.680
Tsunami frowned at them.

04:38:13.740 --> 04:38:17.099
And if we find the real assassin, she

04:38:17.099 --> 04:38:19.139
hurried on, then we'll be heroes.

04:38:19.200 --> 04:38:23.819
Not if it's your mom, Glory said firmly.

04:38:23.880 --> 04:38:25.139
Which it is.

04:38:25.259 --> 04:38:28.019
Tsunami wanted to kick her.

04:38:28.080 --> 04:38:31.740
It can't be my mother, she said again.

04:38:31.799 --> 04:38:34.259
The dragon who attacked me in the tunnel

04:38:34.259 --> 04:38:35.939
didn't have a dragonette attached.

04:38:36.000 --> 04:38:38.819
Where are you suggesting she stashed

04:38:38.819 --> 04:38:40.380
anemone while she came after me?

04:38:40.439 --> 04:38:42.719
And how could she have broken one of her

04:38:42.719 --> 04:38:44.819
eggs when anemone is with her at all

04:38:44.819 --> 04:38:45.119
times?

04:38:45.180 --> 04:38:48.419
She could have sent someone else

04:38:48.419 --> 04:38:51.599
Starflight said, or the attack on you

04:38:51.599 --> 04:38:53.279
could be unrelated to the princess

04:38:53.279 --> 04:38:53.819
murders.

04:38:53.880 --> 04:38:56.040
Perhaps there's another reason someone

04:38:56.040 --> 04:38:56.759
wants you dead.

04:38:56.880 --> 04:39:01.139
Ooh, I have a few guesses, Glory said.

04:39:01.200 --> 04:39:05.819
I think it's Shark, tsunami said, ignoring

04:39:05.819 --> 04:39:06.180
her.

04:39:06.240 --> 04:39:08.819
Tortoise pointed at him before she died.

04:39:08.880 --> 04:39:11.580
He was at the deep palace before the rest

04:39:11.580 --> 04:39:12.360
of the council.

04:39:12.419 --> 04:39:14.819
If I'm right, and there's a secret

04:39:14.819 --> 04:39:17.099
entrance to the hatchery, he could have

04:39:17.099 --> 04:39:18.959
snuck in to kill the dragonettes without

04:39:18.959 --> 04:39:21.239
anyone knowing, and he could have

04:39:21.239 --> 04:39:22.619
attacked me in the tunnel too.

04:39:22.680 --> 04:39:25.200
Queen Coral thought she'd sent him on

04:39:25.200 --> 04:39:27.779
ahead already, so nobody knew where he

04:39:27.779 --> 04:39:28.380
was exactly.

04:39:28.439 --> 04:39:33.299
Tsunami, Clay said, nosing her with his

04:39:33.299 --> 04:39:33.899
snout.

04:39:34.020 --> 04:39:36.240
His forehead crinkled worriedly.

04:39:36.299 --> 04:39:38.819
It doesn't sound like you're safe here.

04:39:38.880 --> 04:39:40.919
Maybe we should go.

04:39:41.040 --> 04:39:43.919
Or at least we should go.

04:39:43.979 --> 04:39:45.540
Glory suggested.

04:39:45.599 --> 04:39:47.700
You can stay here if you really want to.

04:39:47.759 --> 04:39:50.040
We could leave now while no one is

04:39:50.040 --> 04:39:50.580
guarding us.

04:39:50.639 --> 04:39:53.159
Tsunami hesitated.

04:39:53.220 --> 04:39:55.680
It was so much harder to fit in with a

04:39:55.680 --> 04:39:58.200
sea wings than she'd expected, and she

04:39:58.200 --> 04:39:59.580
didn't like seeing sides of her mother

04:39:59.580 --> 04:40:00.360
that scared her.

04:40:00.419 --> 04:40:03.119
She preferred the image in her head that

04:40:03.119 --> 04:40:05.700
she'd dreamed about her whole life, the

04:40:05.700 --> 04:40:07.740
loving queen from the missing princess.

04:40:07.799 --> 04:40:10.380
She fingered the pearls around her neck

04:40:10.380 --> 04:40:12.900
thinking of how Coral had given them to

04:40:12.900 --> 04:40:15.479
her the moment she saw her, and how happy

04:40:15.479 --> 04:40:16.020
she had been.

04:40:16.080 --> 04:40:19.860
No, Sonny said unexpectedly.

04:40:19.919 --> 04:40:22.200
I'm not leaving this egg until it

04:40:22.200 --> 04:40:22.919
hatches.

04:40:23.159 --> 04:40:24.900
She rested her talons on it

04:40:24.900 --> 04:40:25.500
protectively.

04:40:25.560 --> 04:40:27.659
And we can't split up.

04:40:27.720 --> 04:40:30.119
We have to fulfill the prophecy

04:40:30.119 --> 04:40:30.959
together.

04:40:31.020 --> 04:40:34.380
I agree with Sonny, said Starflight.

04:40:34.439 --> 04:40:36.599
I don't love it here either, but we have

04:40:36.599 --> 04:40:37.979
to stay until we meet blister.

04:40:38.099 --> 04:40:39.479
That was the whole point of coming here.

04:40:39.540 --> 04:40:41.340
Not for me.

04:40:41.400 --> 04:40:43.020
Tsunami thought.

04:40:43.080 --> 04:40:45.419
She'd forgotten that blister would be

04:40:45.419 --> 04:40:46.799
coming to meet the dragonettes.

04:40:46.860 --> 04:40:49.259
She was not at all sure that was

04:40:49.259 --> 04:40:50.220
something to look forward to.

04:40:50.279 --> 04:40:53.880
Then, I think you should stay with us

04:40:53.880 --> 04:40:55.259
Clay said.

04:40:55.380 --> 04:40:58.799
Taking tsunami's talents in his again, so

04:40:58.799 --> 04:41:00.180
we can keep one another safe.

04:41:00.240 --> 04:41:03.779
That was what tsunami had planned to do

04:41:03.779 --> 04:41:04.319
anyway.

04:41:04.380 --> 04:41:07.560
But hearing it from Clay and seeing Sonny

04:41:07.560 --> 04:41:09.840
nodding vigorously behind him, made her

04:41:09.840 --> 04:41:10.500
feel much better.

04:41:10.560 --> 04:41:13.080
They couldn't hate her too much if they

04:41:13.080 --> 04:41:13.979
wanted her to stay with them.

04:41:14.040 --> 04:41:18.240
All right, she said, as if he'd convinced

04:41:18.240 --> 04:41:18.419
her.

04:41:18.479 --> 04:41:21.119
Then I can help you protect the egg as

04:41:21.119 --> 04:41:21.240
well.

04:41:21.360 --> 04:41:23.400
You'd better.

04:41:23.459 --> 04:41:26.279
Starflight muttered, glancing at Sonny

04:41:26.279 --> 04:41:27.060
with a worried look.

04:41:27.119 --> 04:41:30.299
They curled up together to sleep

04:41:30.299 --> 04:41:32.400
sheltering the egg in the middle of their

04:41:32.400 --> 04:41:32.759
pile.

04:41:32.819 --> 04:41:35.400
Tsunami rested her head on Clay's

04:41:35.400 --> 04:41:37.139
shoulder, and listened to the rain

04:41:37.139 --> 04:41:39.720
pattering on the canopy far above them.

04:41:39.900 --> 04:41:42.959
Last night, she'd slept underwater on

04:41:42.959 --> 04:41:45.180
seaweed, and it had been the most

04:41:45.180 --> 04:41:47.580
comfortable sleep she'd ever had.

04:41:47.639 --> 04:41:50.040
But even though she was back in a cave

04:41:50.099 --> 04:41:52.680
Something about the rise and fall of

04:41:52.680 --> 04:41:55.619
clay's deep breathing under her snout was

04:41:55.619 --> 04:41:58.259
more calming than any seaweed bed, or

04:41:58.259 --> 04:42:00.060
pearl studded underwater palace.

04:42:00.119 --> 04:42:03.419
It wasn't until she was almost asleep

04:42:03.419 --> 04:42:05.639
that she remembered she'd forgotten to

04:42:05.639 --> 04:42:07.200
tell the others about Kestrel.

04:42:07.259 --> 04:42:11.580
Chapter 19.

04:42:11.759 --> 04:42:14.459
Where are they?

04:42:14.520 --> 04:42:17.639
Tsunami bolted awake out of a nightmare

04:42:17.639 --> 04:42:19.680
about the last egg slipping through her

04:42:19.680 --> 04:42:22.139
claws and smashing on a coral reef?

04:42:22.200 --> 04:42:24.119
She blinked and checked under her wing.

04:42:24.240 --> 04:42:27.360
Sunny was still curled neatly around the

04:42:27.360 --> 04:42:28.560
egg, keeping it warm.

04:42:28.680 --> 04:42:31.799
The little sand wing lifted her head as

04:42:31.799 --> 04:42:33.659
if something had woken her up as well.

04:42:33.720 --> 04:42:34.500
What was it?

04:42:34.560 --> 04:42:37.500
Where are the dragonettes?

04:42:37.560 --> 04:42:38.759
Where is my daughter?

04:42:38.819 --> 04:42:40.139
Where is my egg?

04:42:40.200 --> 04:42:44.639
Up here, called an unfamiliar voice with

04:42:44.639 --> 04:42:45.840
a weird hiss to it.

04:42:45.900 --> 04:42:48.360
Tsuname leaped to her feet.

04:42:48.419 --> 04:42:51.419
A shape was coiled in the cave entrance

04:42:51.419 --> 04:42:52.860
watching them.

04:42:52.919 --> 04:42:55.380
Glittering black eyes met tsunamis.

04:42:55.439 --> 04:42:59.340
A poisonous tail barb flicked up and

04:42:59.340 --> 04:42:59.819
down.

04:42:59.880 --> 04:43:02.639
White gold scales marked with black

04:43:02.639 --> 04:43:04.680
diamond patterns caught the glint of

04:43:04.680 --> 04:43:06.540
sunlight, now trickling through the

04:43:06.540 --> 04:43:07.080
canopy.

04:43:07.139 --> 04:43:09.060
The storm had passed.

04:43:09.180 --> 04:43:12.240
And there was a sand wing watching them

04:43:12.240 --> 04:43:12.479
sleep.

04:43:12.540 --> 04:43:15.599
Tsunami didn't have to remember the

04:43:15.599 --> 04:43:17.759
illustrations in their scrolls to guess

04:43:17.759 --> 04:43:18.299
who it was.

04:43:18.360 --> 04:43:20.520
She poked her friends with her claws.

04:43:20.639 --> 04:43:24.060
Wake up, you lazy snoring manatees?

04:43:24.119 --> 04:43:24.959
She hissed.

04:43:25.020 --> 04:43:28.500
You're a lazy, snoring manatee.

04:43:28.619 --> 04:43:31.200
Glory mumbled, with her wings over her

04:43:31.200 --> 04:43:33.479
head, and you smell like one too.

04:43:33.540 --> 04:43:36.900
You're going to feel very silly in a

04:43:36.900 --> 04:43:37.200
minute.

04:43:37.319 --> 04:43:39.360
Tsunami whispered crossly.

04:43:39.419 --> 04:43:44.819
Oh, if you insist, Clay muttered, mostly

04:43:44.819 --> 04:43:48.360
asleep, I suppose I could eat one more

04:43:48.360 --> 04:43:49.080
hippo.

04:43:49.139 --> 04:43:51.000
Clay!

04:43:51.060 --> 04:43:53.759
tsunami yanked on his ears and he sat up

04:43:53.759 --> 04:43:55.680
with a bewildered look, shaking his

04:43:55.680 --> 04:43:55.919
head.

04:43:55.979 --> 04:44:00.299
Aw, he said, his wings drooping.

04:44:00.360 --> 04:44:02.880
What happened to the hippos?

04:44:02.939 --> 04:44:04.439
Look.

04:44:04.500 --> 04:44:07.080
Tsunami whispered, pointing toward the

04:44:07.080 --> 04:44:07.740
cave entrance.

04:44:07.799 --> 04:44:11.099
Her friends all went silent as they saw

04:44:11.099 --> 04:44:12.540
the sand wing in the shadows.

04:44:12.599 --> 04:44:18.000
Well, hello, said the stranger with a sly

04:44:18.000 --> 04:44:18.360
smile.

04:44:18.479 --> 04:44:21.599
Tsunami shivered, without quite knowing

04:44:21.599 --> 04:44:21.840
why.

04:44:21.900 --> 04:44:25.200
So nice to meet you.

04:44:25.259 --> 04:44:27.540
I'm Queen Blister.

04:44:27.599 --> 04:44:30.840
They're up here, she called again.

04:44:30.900 --> 04:44:35.040
Staying dry out of the storm, I presume?

04:44:35.159 --> 04:44:37.200
She went on conversationally.

04:44:37.259 --> 04:44:38.939
Very wise.

04:44:39.000 --> 04:44:40.860
I would have done the same thing.

04:44:40.979 --> 04:44:44.400
A flurry of wing beats announced Queen

04:44:44.400 --> 04:44:46.319
Coral's arrival on the ledge behind her

04:44:46.319 --> 04:44:49.319
followed by anemone, and 3 sea wing

04:44:49.319 --> 04:44:49.680
guards.

04:44:49.740 --> 04:44:51.959
The queen poked her head into the cave

04:44:51.959 --> 04:44:53.099
and saw tsunami.

04:44:53.159 --> 04:44:55.500
Where is my egg?

04:44:55.560 --> 04:44:57.959
She demanded, eyeing the other 4

04:44:57.959 --> 04:44:58.799
dragonettes.

04:44:58.860 --> 04:45:02.340
Safe and warm, like I promised.

04:45:02.400 --> 04:45:05.040
Tsunami stepped aside and let her see

04:45:05.040 --> 04:45:06.659
Sunny coiled around the egg.

04:45:06.720 --> 04:45:09.540
Queen Coral hissed and lashed her tail.

04:45:09.599 --> 04:45:13.200
You never said anything about a sand wing

04:45:13.200 --> 04:45:13.979
touching my egg.

04:45:14.040 --> 04:45:18.119
Oh, but think about it, Coral.

04:45:18.180 --> 04:45:19.619
Blister interjected.

04:45:19.680 --> 04:45:22.979
These are not ordinary dragons.

04:45:23.040 --> 04:45:26.159
These are the dragonettes of destiny.

04:45:26.220 --> 04:45:28.860
If they can't be trusted with our

04:45:28.860 --> 04:45:29.220
future.

04:45:29.279 --> 04:45:30.659
Who can?

04:45:30.779 --> 04:45:34.319
She smiled again, but tsunami couldn't

04:45:34.319 --> 04:45:36.060
shake a weird feeling of uneasiness.

04:45:36.119 --> 04:45:39.119
Queen Coral took a deep breath, then

04:45:39.119 --> 04:45:41.159
turned to blister with outstretched arms

04:45:41.159 --> 04:45:42.659
and wings spread wide.

04:45:42.779 --> 04:45:44.639
Queen blister.

04:45:44.700 --> 04:45:47.939
My friend, she said, you got my message.

04:45:48.000 --> 04:45:49.740
I'm so glad you came.

04:45:49.799 --> 04:45:52.259
I knew you'd want to hear right away that

04:45:52.259 --> 04:45:53.580
we found the dragonettes.

04:45:53.639 --> 04:45:56.099
She waved her tail at tsunami and her

04:45:56.099 --> 04:45:57.119
friends.

04:45:57.180 --> 04:45:59.099
Tsunami squashed a flare of irritation.

04:45:59.159 --> 04:46:02.880
Blister clasped Coral's front talons in

04:46:02.880 --> 04:46:04.860
hers and quickly let go.

04:46:04.919 --> 04:46:08.700
I was thrilled to hear it, she said.

04:46:08.759 --> 04:46:11.279
And one of them was your beautiful

04:46:11.279 --> 04:46:14.159
missing daughter, as we always

04:46:14.159 --> 04:46:14.939
suspected.

04:46:15.000 --> 04:46:18.419
I knew the talons of peace must have sent

04:46:18.419 --> 04:46:19.319
webs to steal her.

04:46:19.380 --> 04:46:22.860
Queen Coral said, Tsunami, say hello to

04:46:22.860 --> 04:46:24.659
my ally, Queen Blister.

04:46:24.720 --> 04:46:28.020
We've met, said tsunami.

04:46:28.080 --> 04:46:29.880
She felt her friends behind her.

04:46:29.939 --> 04:46:33.779
Starflight, frozen in fear, Sonny craning

04:46:33.779 --> 04:46:36.000
her neck for a better view, Glory

04:46:36.000 --> 04:46:37.979
studying her claws as if she wasn't that

04:46:37.979 --> 04:46:38.400
interested.

04:46:38.459 --> 04:46:41.459
Clay curious, but mostly trying to keep

04:46:41.459 --> 04:46:43.380
his stomach from growling too loudly.

04:46:43.439 --> 04:46:46.139
Then introduce your friends.

04:46:46.200 --> 04:46:49.080
Coral ordered, smiling at blister again.

04:46:49.139 --> 04:46:55.080
Clay, sunny, Starflight, glory, tsunami

04:46:55.080 --> 04:46:57.240
said, flicking a claw at each of them as

04:46:57.240 --> 04:46:58.619
she said their names.

04:46:58.680 --> 04:47:00.299
Queen Cor frowned at her.

04:47:00.360 --> 04:47:05.040
Marvelous, said blister smoothly.

04:47:05.099 --> 04:47:08.400
All so brave and clever looking.

04:47:08.459 --> 04:47:11.939
I heard you weren't a sky wing glory, but

04:47:11.939 --> 04:47:13.979
that doesn't bother me.

04:47:14.040 --> 04:47:16.200
Sky Wings are overrated.

04:47:16.259 --> 04:47:17.340
Don't you agree?

04:47:17.400 --> 04:47:21.119
Glory's wings twitched, and a ripple of

04:47:21.119 --> 04:47:23.279
dark pink shifted across her stone gray

04:47:23.279 --> 04:47:23.700
scales.

04:47:23.759 --> 04:47:26.639
You heard?

04:47:26.639 --> 04:47:27.959
Tsunami demanded.

04:47:28.020 --> 04:47:29.220
How?

04:47:29.279 --> 04:47:31.860
Nobody knew that except our 3 guardians.

04:47:31.919 --> 04:47:34.080
They didn't even tell the other talons of

04:47:34.080 --> 04:47:34.319
peace.

04:47:34.439 --> 04:47:37.979
Anemone gazed at her from behind Coral's

04:47:37.979 --> 04:47:39.659
wing, her blue eyes wide.

04:47:39.779 --> 04:47:42.180
The sea wing guards shuffled on their

04:47:42.180 --> 04:47:43.020
feet nervously.

04:47:43.080 --> 04:47:46.259
Hmm, said Blister.

04:47:46.380 --> 04:47:49.080
Her eyes flicked to tsunami and away.

04:47:49.139 --> 04:47:53.040
Let's just say, I have friends.

04:47:53.099 --> 04:47:55.619
Nightwing, friends.

04:47:55.680 --> 04:47:58.979
She slithered up to Starflight, and

04:47:58.979 --> 04:48:01.860
brushed one claw slowly down his neck.

04:48:01.979 --> 04:48:05.340
So I've heard a lot about you.

04:48:05.400 --> 04:48:09.540
The Nightwing Dragonette really looked as

04:48:09.540 --> 04:48:11.340
if he might turn to stone and never move

04:48:11.340 --> 04:48:11.700
again.

04:48:11.759 --> 04:48:14.040
Tsunami would have kicked him if she'd

04:48:14.040 --> 04:48:14.520
been closer.

04:48:14.580 --> 04:48:17.040
Don't be so impressed by her.

04:48:17.099 --> 04:48:19.259
We're the ones with the power.

04:48:19.319 --> 04:48:22.139
According to the prophecy, we choose the

04:48:22.139 --> 04:48:24.240
next sandwing queen and she knows it.

04:48:24.299 --> 04:48:27.959
Blister glanced down at Sonny, who was

04:48:27.959 --> 04:48:28.319
frowning.

04:48:28.380 --> 04:48:33.479
Sweet, she said, chucking Sonny under the

04:48:33.479 --> 04:48:33.779
chin.

04:48:33.900 --> 04:48:38.040
And you must be the burly one, she said

04:48:38.040 --> 04:48:38.700
to Clay.

04:48:38.759 --> 04:48:40.860
She reached out and squeezed one of the

04:48:40.860 --> 04:48:42.299
muscles in his forearm.

04:48:42.360 --> 04:48:44.520
I, I, I guess.

04:48:44.580 --> 04:48:46.139
Clay stammered.

04:48:46.200 --> 04:48:50.099
I'm sure you've heard things about me too

04:48:50.099 --> 04:48:53.340
Blister said, returning to Queen Coral's

04:48:53.340 --> 04:48:53.880
side.

04:48:53.939 --> 04:48:56.340
Her tail slid across the cave floor like

04:48:56.340 --> 04:48:59.099
a snake, the poisonous tip rattling on

04:48:59.099 --> 04:48:59.400
the stone.

04:48:59.459 --> 04:49:03.840
But you can't always trust rumors and

04:49:03.840 --> 04:49:04.680
propaganda.

04:49:04.740 --> 04:49:07.319
Especially when it comes to a big

04:49:07.319 --> 04:49:09.720
responsibility like the prophecy.

04:49:09.840 --> 04:49:12.360
So ask me anything you like.

04:49:12.419 --> 04:49:15.479
I'd be delighted to help you make your

04:49:15.479 --> 04:49:16.080
decision.

04:49:16.200 --> 04:49:20.099
Although, of course, I hope you'll choose

04:49:20.099 --> 04:49:20.819
me.

04:49:20.939 --> 04:49:24.060
Her glittering eyes swept over all of

04:49:24.060 --> 04:49:25.919
them again, and back to Coral.

04:49:25.979 --> 04:49:30.000
So, Coral, what's for breakfast?

04:49:30.060 --> 04:49:33.840
Let me guess, Glory muttered.

04:49:33.900 --> 04:49:35.040
Fish.

04:49:35.099 --> 04:49:37.860
Clay blinked at the queen, hopefully.

04:49:37.919 --> 04:49:41.040
Yes, what a good idea.

04:49:41.099 --> 04:49:44.759
Let's go eat, said Queen Coral, and then

04:49:44.759 --> 04:49:46.740
you can tell me the latest updates from

04:49:46.740 --> 04:49:47.340
the war.

04:49:47.340 --> 04:49:49.259
We hear something odd is going on with

04:49:49.259 --> 04:49:50.159
the Sky Wings.

04:49:50.220 --> 04:49:52.319
Anemone, tsunami, come.

04:49:52.380 --> 04:49:55.380
Tsunami's gills flared.

04:49:55.439 --> 04:49:57.599
She was not a baby dragonette to be

04:49:57.599 --> 04:49:58.080
ordered around.

04:49:58.139 --> 04:50:01.139
And she had no intention of leaving her

04:50:01.139 --> 04:50:01.979
friends alone again.

04:50:02.040 --> 04:50:05.580
Let the others come too.

04:50:05.639 --> 04:50:08.580
Blister said, before tsunami could speak

04:50:08.580 --> 04:50:08.759
up.

04:50:08.819 --> 04:50:11.340
I'd love to get to know them better.

04:50:11.400 --> 04:50:14.279
Carl wrinkled her snout at the

04:50:14.279 --> 04:50:15.000
dragonettes.

04:50:15.060 --> 04:50:18.000
All right, she said doubtfully.

04:50:18.060 --> 04:50:20.639
You can leave that here.

04:50:20.700 --> 04:50:23.700
Blister said, nodding at the egg.

04:50:23.759 --> 04:50:27.240
No, Coral and Sonny said at the same

04:50:27.240 --> 04:50:27.540
time.

04:50:27.599 --> 04:50:29.639
The sea wing queen gave the little

04:50:29.639 --> 04:50:31.200
dragonette a surprised look.

04:50:31.259 --> 04:50:33.659
Sonny hugged the egg closer.

04:50:33.720 --> 04:50:35.700
No way, she said.

04:50:35.759 --> 04:50:37.139
It stays with me.

04:50:37.200 --> 04:50:40.560
Blister shrugged, and Tsunami suddenly

04:50:40.560 --> 04:50:42.000
wondered how she felt about new

04:50:42.000 --> 04:50:44.040
dragonettes, who might threaten her

04:50:44.040 --> 04:50:45.240
allies life.

04:50:45.299 --> 04:50:48.360
Maybe it was in Blister's best interests

04:50:48.360 --> 04:50:50.759
to make sure no one survived to challenge

04:50:50.759 --> 04:50:51.299
Coral.

04:50:51.419 --> 04:50:53.759
She certainly seemed sinister enough to

04:50:53.759 --> 04:50:54.540
be the assassin.

04:50:54.599 --> 04:50:57.659
The blister couldn't breathe underwater

04:50:57.659 --> 04:50:59.400
so she couldn't get to the royal

04:50:59.400 --> 04:51:00.060
hatchery.

04:51:00.060 --> 04:51:02.819
She might be involved, but she couldn't

04:51:02.819 --> 04:51:04.500
actually be committing the murders.

04:51:04.560 --> 04:51:06.720
It had to be a fellow sea wing.

04:51:06.779 --> 04:51:10.200
The feasting hall was 2 levels above the

04:51:10.200 --> 04:51:12.659
kitchens, so the smells of pickled fish

04:51:12.659 --> 04:51:15.540
and roasting seagulls, in honor of our

04:51:15.540 --> 04:51:18.479
sand wing guests, Queen Coral explained

04:51:18.479 --> 04:51:20.759
surrounded them as they arranged

04:51:20.759 --> 04:51:23.220
themselves around the long, low oval

04:51:23.220 --> 04:51:23.639
table.

04:51:23.700 --> 04:51:25.919
Queen Coral's seat was higher than

04:51:25.919 --> 04:51:28.380
everyone else's, but blisters, right

04:51:28.380 --> 04:51:30.000
beside her, was not much lower.

04:51:30.060 --> 04:51:33.840
Starflight was seeded to blister's right

04:51:33.840 --> 04:51:36.240
with tsunami next to anemone on her

04:51:36.240 --> 04:51:39.060
mother's left, on tsunami's other side

04:51:39.060 --> 04:51:41.880
was Whirlpool, who played with his hoop

04:51:41.880 --> 04:51:45.240
earring, slurped loudly as he ate, and

04:51:45.240 --> 04:51:48.000
droned on about Coral's latest book, even

04:51:48.000 --> 04:51:49.500
when nobody seemed to be listening.

04:51:49.560 --> 04:51:52.860
Seawing guards were arranged around the

04:51:52.860 --> 04:51:55.319
perimeter of the floor. interspersed with

04:51:55.319 --> 04:51:57.720
sandwing soldiers, who had arrived with

04:51:57.720 --> 04:51:58.200
blister.

04:51:58.259 --> 04:52:00.779
The sea wings stamped their talons and

04:52:00.779 --> 04:52:03.240
swished their tails, casting dark looks

04:52:03.240 --> 04:52:04.200
at the sand wings.

04:52:04.319 --> 04:52:08.099
Tsunami spotted snail and herring among

04:52:08.099 --> 04:52:08.759
the guards.

04:52:08.819 --> 04:52:11.700
Their eyes darted anxiously from side to

04:52:11.700 --> 04:52:13.799
side, as if they were wondering how they

04:52:13.799 --> 04:52:14.459
were still alive.

04:52:14.520 --> 04:52:18.000
Because mother wants to make a spectacle

04:52:18.000 --> 04:52:20.040
of them, tsunami guest.

04:52:20.159 --> 04:52:22.560
Coral was probably waiting for the right

04:52:22.560 --> 04:52:25.139
moment to punish them in public, the way

04:52:25.139 --> 04:52:26.400
she'd punished tortoise.

04:52:26.459 --> 04:52:30.419
Well, 2 can play the spectacle game, Your

04:52:30.419 --> 04:52:30.900
Majesty.

04:52:30.959 --> 04:52:33.119
Mother!

04:52:33.180 --> 04:52:36.119
Tsunami declared dramatically, as the

04:52:36.119 --> 04:52:38.159
wait staff said bowls of soup in front of

04:52:38.159 --> 04:52:41.340
each dragon, beside her, Whirlpool jumped

04:52:41.340 --> 04:52:44.220
and nearly tipped his bowl onto himself

04:52:44.220 --> 04:52:45.900
even Queen Coral looked startled.

04:52:46.020 --> 04:52:51.000
I have something dreadfully shocking to

04:52:51.000 --> 04:52:53.279
tell you, Tsunami announced.

04:52:53.340 --> 04:52:55.799
She wanted this to be loud, so every

04:52:55.799 --> 04:52:56.939
dragon could witness it.

04:52:57.000 --> 04:52:59.880
Oh, said Coral.

04:52:59.939 --> 04:53:03.599
Could we discuss it after breakfast in a

04:53:03.599 --> 04:53:04.500
civilized fashion?

04:53:04.560 --> 04:53:08.880
No, tsunami said, louder than before.

04:53:08.939 --> 04:53:11.580
This is too shocking.

04:53:11.639 --> 04:53:15.180
Even Sea Wings not invited to the feast.

04:53:15.240 --> 04:53:17.159
We're starting to peer out of their caves

04:53:17.159 --> 04:53:19.380
and poke their heads out of the lake to

04:53:19.380 --> 04:53:20.099
hear what was going on.

04:53:20.159 --> 04:53:23.880
Well, perhaps Carl started.

04:53:23.939 --> 04:53:28.619
Would you believe, tsunami said, that my

04:53:28.619 --> 04:53:32.099
friends, the dragonettes of destiny

04:53:32.099 --> 04:53:38.759
remember, were chained up and starved in

04:53:38.759 --> 04:53:42.419
your caves by your dragons?

04:53:42.479 --> 04:53:44.040
What?

04:53:44.159 --> 04:53:46.619
Carl said. flapping her wings.

04:53:46.680 --> 04:53:48.599
She looked thoroughly alarmed.

04:53:48.659 --> 04:53:50.759
So Navi couldn't tell whether that was

04:53:50.759 --> 04:53:53.400
because the news actually surprised her

04:53:53.400 --> 04:53:55.080
or because she was being confronted

04:53:55.080 --> 04:53:57.180
openly with what she'd done.

04:53:57.240 --> 04:53:58.799
I know.

04:53:58.860 --> 04:54:01.319
Tsunami practically bellowed.

04:54:01.439 --> 04:54:03.299
It's unbelievable.

04:54:03.360 --> 04:54:05.639
I'm sure you didn't know anything about

04:54:05.639 --> 04:54:06.599
it, of course.

04:54:06.720 --> 04:54:10.919
Of course, Carl said in a hurry.

04:54:10.979 --> 04:54:13.619
I would never treat any dragonettes that

04:54:13.619 --> 04:54:16.500
way, especially my dearest daughter's

04:54:16.500 --> 04:54:18.900
dearest friends, who are part of the

04:54:18.900 --> 04:54:20.220
prophecy and everything.

04:54:20.279 --> 04:54:23.040
And I'm sure you'll want to punish the

04:54:23.040 --> 04:54:26.220
dragons who disobeyed you by treating my

04:54:26.220 --> 04:54:28.979
friends so terribly, tsunami said.

04:54:29.040 --> 04:54:29.880
Right?

04:54:29.939 --> 04:54:33.119
Like, for instance, the one who lied to

04:54:33.119 --> 04:54:36.180
you about keeping them well fed, She shot

04:54:36.180 --> 04:54:39.000
a glare at Lagoon, who froze with a sea

04:54:39.000 --> 04:54:41.220
snail halfway to her mouth, suddenly

04:54:41.220 --> 04:54:43.259
realizing what was going on.

04:54:43.319 --> 04:54:45.720
Absolutely, said the queen.

04:54:45.779 --> 04:54:48.240
Guards, throw lagoon in one of the

04:54:48.240 --> 04:54:49.200
underwater dungeons.

04:54:49.259 --> 04:54:54.840
But, Lagoon said, but I was only, next

04:54:54.840 --> 04:54:57.299
time you'll obey my orders, said the

04:54:57.299 --> 04:54:57.659
Queen.

04:54:57.779 --> 04:55:00.479
A stripe quickly flashed under her wings

04:55:00.479 --> 04:55:03.000
but tsunami spotted it, and it was one

04:55:03.000 --> 04:55:04.080
riptide had taught her.

04:55:04.139 --> 04:55:06.299
Silence.

04:55:06.360 --> 04:55:10.259
Oh, mother, tsunami thought sadly.

04:55:10.319 --> 04:55:11.939
Can't I even?

04:55:11.939 --> 04:55:14.580
Lagoon said, reaching wistfully for her

04:55:14.580 --> 04:55:16.439
cauldron of soup as the guards pulled her

04:55:16.439 --> 04:55:16.619
away.

04:55:16.680 --> 04:55:20.459
No breakfast for you, the queen ordered.

04:55:20.520 --> 04:55:23.099
Think about how that feels as you sit in

04:55:23.099 --> 04:55:23.639
my dungeon.

04:55:23.700 --> 04:55:27.240
Tsunami was fairly sure Lagoon wouldn't

04:55:27.240 --> 04:55:28.319
actually suffer very much.

04:55:28.380 --> 04:55:30.419
Queen Coral would have her back at

04:55:30.419 --> 04:55:32.939
council meetings before long, but tsunami

04:55:32.939 --> 04:55:33.599
wasn't done.

04:55:33.659 --> 04:55:38.099
And guess who ordered your guards to

04:55:38.099 --> 04:55:39.180
chain up clay?

04:55:39.240 --> 04:55:40.740
Tsunami demanded?

04:55:40.860 --> 04:55:42.959
She flung an accusing talent toward

04:55:42.959 --> 04:55:43.500
Shark.

04:55:43.560 --> 04:55:45.540
Commander Shark.

04:55:45.599 --> 04:55:48.540
Of all the dragons who should obey you in

04:55:48.540 --> 04:55:48.900
everything.

04:55:48.959 --> 04:55:52.139
Is that not utterly shocking?

04:55:52.200 --> 04:55:55.560
It is, Carl said.

04:55:55.619 --> 04:55:57.779
Tsunami thought she might be grinding her

04:55:57.779 --> 04:55:59.159
teeth, but she hit it well.

04:55:59.279 --> 04:56:02.759
I find it quite hard to believe.

04:56:02.819 --> 04:56:06.779
Imagine the distress the poor guards felt

04:56:06.779 --> 04:56:07.979
tsunami said.

04:56:08.040 --> 04:56:10.680
When I explained to them that you would

04:56:10.680 --> 04:56:12.720
never have ordered those chains on clay

04:56:12.720 --> 04:56:14.939
to have to choose between their commander

04:56:14.939 --> 04:56:15.840
and their queen.

04:56:15.900 --> 04:56:18.599
Naturally they chose you, of course.

04:56:18.659 --> 04:56:21.540
That's why they gave me the key to Clay's

04:56:21.540 --> 04:56:23.880
chains, because they understood that's

04:56:23.880 --> 04:56:25.619
what you would have wanted them to do.

04:56:25.680 --> 04:56:27.060
Right?

04:56:27.119 --> 04:56:30.360
Queen Coral gave tsunami an appraising

04:56:30.360 --> 04:56:30.959
glance.

04:56:31.020 --> 04:56:33.779
Beside her, Blister was eating her soup

04:56:33.779 --> 04:56:35.159
with an amused expression.

04:56:35.220 --> 04:56:40.380
Very good, Carl said slowly.

04:56:40.439 --> 04:56:43.380
It sounds like those guards are

04:56:43.380 --> 04:56:44.459
practically heroes.

04:56:44.520 --> 04:56:48.419
And Shark tsunami prodded her.

04:56:48.479 --> 04:56:51.900
To the dungeon with him as well, the

04:56:51.900 --> 04:56:52.860
queen said with a wave.

04:56:52.919 --> 04:56:56.220
Shark didn't protest like Lagoon had.

04:56:56.279 --> 04:56:58.259
He snarled at the guards who approached

04:56:58.259 --> 04:57:01.139
him, shot tsunami a look full of hatred

04:57:01.139 --> 04:57:03.180
and headed off to the dungeon without

04:57:03.180 --> 04:57:03.659
another word.

04:57:03.720 --> 04:57:07.919
Splendid, Tsunami thought to herself.

04:57:08.040 --> 04:57:10.560
It didn't guarantee that Snail and the

04:57:10.560 --> 04:57:12.840
other guards would be safe, but surely

04:57:12.840 --> 04:57:14.279
that had to make it more difficult for

04:57:14.279 --> 04:57:16.560
Queen Coral to punish them for last night

04:57:16.560 --> 04:57:19.860
not only that, but with Shark in the

04:57:19.860 --> 04:57:23.159
Dungeon, even for only a day or 2, Tsunami

04:57:23.159 --> 04:57:25.139
felt like she and her friends and the egg

04:57:25.139 --> 04:57:26.759
would all be a lot safer.

04:57:26.819 --> 04:57:31.799
Such excitement, Blister said.

04:57:31.919 --> 04:57:34.619
If we're quite finished with our morning

04:57:34.619 --> 04:57:36.060
theatrics.

04:57:36.119 --> 04:57:38.580
I would love to ask you brilliant little

04:57:38.580 --> 04:57:40.500
dragonettes about the prophecy.

04:57:40.560 --> 04:57:44.520
Starflight can recite it for you, Tsunami

04:57:44.520 --> 04:57:44.819
said.

04:57:44.880 --> 04:57:47.880
He's really good at memorizing things, and

04:57:47.880 --> 04:57:49.979
then repeating those things over and over

04:57:49.979 --> 04:57:51.840
especially when no one cares to hear

04:57:51.840 --> 04:57:52.020
them.

04:57:52.080 --> 04:57:55.380
She shot a grin at Starflight, wishing he

04:57:55.380 --> 04:57:55.799
would relax.

04:57:55.860 --> 04:57:58.080
He looked too petrified to eat.

04:57:58.139 --> 04:58:00.779
How splendid.

04:58:00.840 --> 04:58:02.700
How impressive.

04:58:02.759 --> 04:58:05.759
Whirlpool said from beside her, in a

04:58:05.759 --> 04:58:07.259
voice of sincere admiration.

04:58:07.319 --> 04:58:09.900
Tsunami wrinkled her snout at him.

04:58:09.959 --> 04:58:12.180
He probably would get along well with

04:58:12.180 --> 04:58:14.340
Starflight, now that she thought about it

04:58:14.340 --> 04:58:16.919
but Starflight was not even remotely as

04:58:16.919 --> 04:58:19.020
awful or annoying as Whirlpool.

04:58:19.080 --> 04:58:23.220
I assume you have a plan about how to

04:58:23.220 --> 04:58:24.959
fulfill this prophecy.

04:58:25.020 --> 04:58:26.459
Blister said.

04:58:26.580 --> 04:58:29.880
I mean, you must, right?

04:58:29.939 --> 04:58:32.700
A tense hush fell over the feasting

04:58:32.700 --> 04:58:33.060
table.

04:58:33.119 --> 04:58:35.580
Ears were pricked all over the palace.

04:58:35.639 --> 04:58:38.580
Every dragon empirea wanted to hear the

04:58:38.580 --> 04:58:39.180
answer to this.

04:58:39.240 --> 04:58:42.119
Tsunami felt like bees were crawling

04:58:42.119 --> 04:58:42.779
under her scales.

04:58:42.840 --> 04:58:45.180
Of course, they didn't have a plan.

04:58:45.240 --> 04:58:47.220
They'd only recently escaped from under

04:58:47.220 --> 04:58:49.319
the mountain, and then the Skywing

04:58:49.319 --> 04:58:49.680
Palace.

04:58:49.740 --> 04:58:52.080
They'd barely had time to stop and think

04:58:52.080 --> 04:58:53.939
or even a safe place to do that.

04:58:54.000 --> 04:58:56.400
And nothing they'd ever been taught had

04:58:56.400 --> 04:58:57.900
prepared them for what they had to do.

04:58:57.959 --> 04:59:02.400
Thanks for that too, talons of peace, she

04:59:02.400 --> 04:59:03.060
thought bitterly.

04:59:03.119 --> 04:59:05.700
But they couldn't admit that to all these

04:59:05.700 --> 04:59:08.220
dragons, especially the ones who were

04:59:08.220 --> 04:59:08.759
counting on them.

04:59:08.819 --> 04:59:12.240
We are working on it, she said.

04:59:12.299 --> 04:59:14.459
Obviously we can't say too much.

04:59:14.580 --> 04:59:18.959
This is the information gathering phase.

04:59:19.080 --> 04:59:21.000
Glory offered unexpectedly.

04:59:21.060 --> 04:59:23.639
Blister gave Starflight a significant

04:59:23.639 --> 04:59:23.759
look.

04:59:23.880 --> 04:59:26.520
Um, he blurted.

04:59:26.580 --> 04:59:31.979
But, we think you, of course, I mean

04:59:31.979 --> 04:59:36.900
obviously you er, you'd make a great, uh

04:59:36.900 --> 04:59:40.680
queen of the sand wings, that is, the

04:59:40.680 --> 04:59:43.200
other two, hardly any competition

04:59:43.200 --> 04:59:43.919
really.

04:59:43.979 --> 04:59:49.560
It's um, a clear, so to speak, sort of, um

04:59:49.560 --> 04:59:50.459
choice.

04:59:50.520 --> 04:59:54.299
Starflight, tsunami said sharply.

04:59:54.360 --> 04:59:55.080
What are you doing?

04:59:55.200 --> 04:59:56.700
You don't speak for all of us.

04:59:56.759 --> 05:00:00.240
Oh, said blister.

05:00:00.299 --> 05:00:02.520
She narrowed her eyes at Starflight.

05:00:02.580 --> 05:00:04.139
Then who does?

05:00:04.200 --> 05:00:09.540
We each speak for ourselves, Glory said

05:00:09.540 --> 05:00:10.919
before tsunami could answer.

05:00:10.979 --> 05:00:13.680
Yeah, Sonny piped up.

05:00:13.740 --> 05:00:16.200
And we haven't decided anything.

05:00:16.319 --> 05:00:18.000
Tsunami said firmly.

05:00:18.060 --> 05:00:20.099
She wished she were close enough to kick

05:00:20.099 --> 05:00:21.599
Starflight and make him shut up.

05:00:21.659 --> 05:00:24.540
I'm just saying she'd be all right.

05:00:24.599 --> 05:00:26.580
He mumbled, subsiding.

05:00:26.639 --> 05:00:29.159
Blister looked mildly disgusted.

05:00:29.220 --> 05:00:32.279
You're quite right, Nightwing.

05:00:32.340 --> 05:00:35.220
Coral said, patting blister's talent.

05:00:35.279 --> 05:00:36.959
She is an excellent queen.

05:00:37.080 --> 05:00:40.619
Blister smiled, but tsunami noticed that

05:00:40.619 --> 05:00:42.180
she moved her talent away as soon as she

05:00:42.180 --> 05:00:42.419
could.

05:00:42.479 --> 05:00:45.240
She also noticed that blister called her

05:00:45.240 --> 05:00:48.180
mother simply coral, while the queen of

05:00:48.180 --> 05:00:50.159
the sea wings kept referring to her ally

05:00:50.159 --> 05:00:52.200
as queen blister.

05:00:52.259 --> 05:00:54.540
Tsunami wasn't sure she liked the way

05:00:54.540 --> 05:00:55.740
they acted around each other.

05:00:55.799 --> 05:00:58.500
Tsunami wanted to trust her mother's

05:00:58.500 --> 05:00:58.979
choices.

05:00:59.040 --> 05:01:01.500
She wanted to like blister.

05:01:01.560 --> 05:01:03.720
It would be uncomplicated to choose

05:01:03.720 --> 05:01:05.520
blister as the sand wing queen.

05:01:05.580 --> 05:01:07.919
Then the dragonettes could stay safely in

05:01:07.919 --> 05:01:09.900
the kingdom of the sea and support the

05:01:09.900 --> 05:01:11.159
sea wing side of the war.

05:01:11.220 --> 05:01:13.860
So why didn't she want to do that?

05:01:13.919 --> 05:01:16.979
What was it about blister that felt so

05:01:16.979 --> 05:01:18.779
wrong?

05:01:18.840 --> 05:01:21.720
Oh, Queen Coral said.

05:01:21.779 --> 05:01:22.919
Queen blister.

05:01:22.979 --> 05:01:25.319
I meant to tell you, the strangest thing

05:01:25.319 --> 05:01:25.860
happened.

05:01:25.919 --> 05:01:28.860
We found a dead sky wing in our territory

05:01:28.860 --> 05:01:29.340
the other day.

05:01:29.400 --> 05:01:31.380
Oops.

05:01:31.439 --> 05:01:33.659
Tsunami still hadn't told the others

05:01:33.659 --> 05:01:36.180
about Kestrel, something new for them to

05:01:36.180 --> 05:01:36.959
be mad at her about.

05:01:37.020 --> 05:01:38.459
She sighed.

05:01:38.520 --> 05:01:40.139
Really?

05:01:40.200 --> 05:01:41.400
Blister said.

05:01:41.459 --> 05:01:44.279
That sounds like good news to me.

05:01:44.400 --> 05:01:46.319
Carl laughed.

05:01:46.380 --> 05:01:48.840
You're right, that's true, but what's

05:01:48.840 --> 05:01:50.880
really strange is she's been poison

05:01:50.880 --> 05:01:53.700
stabbed by a sandwing, why would a

05:01:53.700 --> 05:01:56.159
sandwing and a skywing be fighting all

05:01:56.159 --> 05:01:57.180
the way out here?

05:01:57.240 --> 05:02:00.419
Tsunami had known about the sandwing

05:02:00.419 --> 05:02:01.020
poison.

05:02:01.080 --> 05:02:03.299
She only remembered the blood pouring

05:02:03.299 --> 05:02:06.479
from Kestrel's neck, her tail uncoiled as

05:02:06.479 --> 05:02:07.020
she realized.

05:02:07.139 --> 05:02:09.419
I don't have to worry then.

05:02:09.479 --> 05:02:11.939
Mother will know it wasn't us who killed

05:02:11.939 --> 05:02:12.419
her.

05:02:12.540 --> 05:02:14.939
None of us could do that, not with

05:02:14.939 --> 05:02:16.439
Sonny's useless tail.

05:02:16.500 --> 05:02:19.259
At the same time, questions began

05:02:19.259 --> 05:02:20.340
pounding in her head.

05:02:20.400 --> 05:02:22.560
What sandwing would want to kill

05:02:22.560 --> 05:02:23.279
Kestrel?

05:02:23.340 --> 05:02:26.040
She scratched her gills, puzzled.

05:02:26.099 --> 05:02:29.159
Had Bern found her and punished her for

05:02:29.159 --> 05:02:30.720
what happened to Queen Scarlet?

05:02:30.779 --> 05:02:33.479
But why would either of them be in sea

05:02:33.479 --> 05:02:34.319
wing territory?

05:02:34.380 --> 05:02:37.380
Blister shrugged, resettling her wings.

05:02:37.439 --> 05:02:41.639
That is very peculiar, she said.

05:02:41.700 --> 05:02:45.599
I wonder who she was, said Queen Coral.

05:02:45.659 --> 05:02:48.299
She had these odd burn scars on her

05:02:48.299 --> 05:02:48.779
palms.

05:02:48.840 --> 05:02:51.540
Tsunami reached over Whirlpool and

05:02:51.540 --> 05:02:53.580
grabbed for Sonny's forearm, but it was

05:02:53.580 --> 05:02:55.319
too late to stop her gasp of horror.

05:02:55.439 --> 05:02:58.020
Oh no, Sonny cried.

05:02:58.080 --> 05:03:00.900
That sounds like Kestrel. tsunami?

05:03:00.959 --> 05:03:02.639
What if it was Kestrel?

05:03:02.759 --> 05:03:05.220
She pressed her claws to her snout?

05:03:05.279 --> 05:03:06.840
Her eyes welling with tears.

05:03:06.900 --> 05:03:10.139
A heavy silence fell over the table.

05:03:10.200 --> 05:03:12.419
Every sea wing in the entire palace

05:03:12.419 --> 05:03:14.639
seemed to be staring at sunny and

05:03:14.639 --> 05:03:15.360
tsunami.

05:03:15.419 --> 05:03:17.939
Queen Coral was giving tsunami a

05:03:17.939 --> 05:03:19.319
particularly intent look.

05:03:19.380 --> 05:03:22.919
Across the table, Glory and Starflight

05:03:22.919 --> 05:03:24.659
both had their mouths open in shock.

05:03:24.720 --> 05:03:27.240
Tsunami?

05:03:27.299 --> 05:03:28.680
Carl said slowly.

05:03:28.740 --> 05:03:31.380
Is there something you want to tell us?

05:03:31.439 --> 05:03:36.060
All right, tsunami said squirming.

05:03:36.119 --> 05:03:38.340
Yes, I'm sorry.

05:03:38.400 --> 05:03:39.659
I saw her.

05:03:39.720 --> 05:03:41.520
It was Kestrel.

05:03:41.580 --> 05:03:45.000
Sonny let out a sob and buried her head

05:03:45.000 --> 05:03:45.720
in her talons.

05:03:45.779 --> 05:03:48.779
Clay patted her on the back awkwardly.

05:03:48.840 --> 05:03:53.040
Your sand wing seems surprisingly

05:03:53.040 --> 05:03:55.500
distressed about this sky wing.

05:03:55.560 --> 05:03:57.180
Blister observed.

05:03:57.240 --> 05:04:00.240
Kestrel was one of the guardians who

05:04:00.240 --> 05:04:01.979
raised us, Tsunami said.

05:04:02.040 --> 05:04:04.799
Although she wasn't very nice, Sonny.

05:04:04.860 --> 05:04:06.540
She doesn't deserve your grief.

05:04:06.659 --> 05:04:09.599
Sonny's wings trembled and she didn't

05:04:09.599 --> 05:04:09.900
look up.

05:04:09.959 --> 05:04:14.880
So, Carl said, leaning towards tsunami

05:04:14.880 --> 05:04:16.439
explain this to me.

05:04:16.500 --> 05:04:20.580
You recognized this sky wing, a sky wing

05:04:20.580 --> 05:04:23.220
I have now been wondering about for days

05:04:23.220 --> 05:04:25.259
and you chose not to tell us who she

05:04:25.259 --> 05:04:25.500
was.

05:04:25.560 --> 05:04:27.299
Why is that?

05:04:27.360 --> 05:04:31.020
I didn't think knowing who she was would

05:04:31.020 --> 05:04:33.419
explain anything, tsunami said.

05:04:33.479 --> 05:04:36.779
I knew her, but I have no idea why she

05:04:36.779 --> 05:04:38.939
was out here, or who killed her.

05:04:39.000 --> 05:04:42.180
She glanced at glory and Starflight and

05:04:42.180 --> 05:04:43.259
clay apologetically.

05:04:43.319 --> 05:04:46.439
And I wanted to tell my friends first.

05:04:46.500 --> 05:04:50.099
Kestrel wasn't a good parent, but she was

05:04:50.099 --> 05:04:51.540
one of the only parents we ever knew.

05:04:51.599 --> 05:04:54.779
I thought they should know, and I just

05:04:54.779 --> 05:04:56.040
haven't had a chance to tell them.

05:04:56.099 --> 05:05:00.599
I understand perfectly.

05:05:00.659 --> 05:05:02.759
Blister purred.

05:05:02.819 --> 05:05:05.580
She stroked Coral's talon with one claw.

05:05:05.639 --> 05:05:07.860
Forgive her coral.

05:05:07.919 --> 05:05:11.700
It can be very shocking, saying the dead

05:05:11.700 --> 05:05:14.580
body of a dragon you know, especially

05:05:14.580 --> 05:05:17.340
when you've probably wanted to slash your

05:05:17.340 --> 05:05:19.619
throat yourself once or twice in your

05:05:19.619 --> 05:05:21.299
lifetime, right?

05:05:21.360 --> 05:05:22.139
tsunami?

05:05:22.200 --> 05:05:25.139
I know I felt that way about my mother

05:05:25.139 --> 05:05:26.040
most of the time.

05:05:26.099 --> 05:05:30.840
Tsunami looked up slowly, her green eyes

05:05:30.840 --> 05:05:33.180
meeting blisters, cold, black gaze.

05:05:33.240 --> 05:05:35.220
How did she know?

05:05:35.279 --> 05:05:39.000
Queen Coral had only said that Kestrel

05:05:39.000 --> 05:05:40.319
was stabbed by a sandwing.

05:05:40.439 --> 05:05:42.840
Tsunami clenched her talons under the

05:05:42.840 --> 05:05:43.200
table.

05:05:43.259 --> 05:05:46.860
So how did blister know that Kestrel's

05:05:46.860 --> 05:05:47.880
throat was slashed?

05:05:47.939 --> 05:05:52.139
Chapter 20.

05:05:52.439 --> 05:05:55.500
Tsunami didn't know what to do.

05:05:55.560 --> 05:05:58.799
Should she accuse blister of lying, of

05:05:58.799 --> 05:06:01.500
murder, in front of all these dragons?

05:06:01.560 --> 05:06:03.419
How would Queen Coral react?

05:06:03.479 --> 05:06:06.299
Stop yourself, she thought.

05:06:06.419 --> 05:06:07.500
Think.

05:06:07.560 --> 05:06:10.259
Don't lash out immediately the way you

05:06:10.259 --> 05:06:10.740
want to.

05:06:10.799 --> 05:06:13.380
She shot a glance at Starflight.

05:06:13.439 --> 05:06:15.299
He was smart enough to have noticed

05:06:15.299 --> 05:06:18.119
Blister's mistake, and sure enough there

05:06:18.119 --> 05:06:19.619
was a puzzled expression on his face.

05:06:19.680 --> 05:06:22.919
He met her eyes and shook his head a tiny

05:06:22.919 --> 05:06:23.159
bit.

05:06:23.220 --> 05:06:26.400
Tsunami took a deep breath and let it out

05:06:26.400 --> 05:06:26.880
slowly.

05:06:26.939 --> 05:06:28.500
Perhaps he was right.

05:06:28.560 --> 05:06:31.619
She might put her friends at risk if she

05:06:31.619 --> 05:06:33.720
picked a fight with blister right now

05:06:33.720 --> 05:06:37.080
better to wait and watch, and hope that

05:06:37.080 --> 05:06:39.479
Starflight could use that giant brain to

05:06:39.479 --> 05:06:41.759
figure out why in the world blister would

05:06:41.759 --> 05:06:42.720
have killed Kestrel.

05:06:42.779 --> 05:06:46.080
Blister's dark tongue flickered in and

05:06:46.080 --> 05:06:46.619
out of her mouth.

05:06:46.680 --> 05:06:49.979
She leaned toward Coral, smiled at

05:06:49.979 --> 05:06:53.759
anemone and said, how is our secret

05:06:53.759 --> 05:06:55.080
weapon coming along?

05:06:55.139 --> 05:06:58.860
Anemone dropped her head and stared

05:06:58.860 --> 05:07:00.060
unhappily at the table.

05:07:00.119 --> 05:07:03.360
Wonderfully, Coral said.

05:07:03.419 --> 05:07:06.240
She patted Anemone's head, beaming with

05:07:06.240 --> 05:07:06.599
pride.

05:07:06.659 --> 05:07:08.759
Why don't we show you?

05:07:08.819 --> 05:07:09.720
Whirlpool?

05:07:09.779 --> 05:07:10.139
Come along.

05:07:10.259 --> 05:07:13.200
Whirlpool puffed out his chest and stood

05:07:13.200 --> 05:07:13.380
up.

05:07:13.439 --> 05:07:16.200
Curious, tsunami got to her feet at the

05:07:16.200 --> 05:07:18.240
same time, but Queen Coral shook her

05:07:18.240 --> 05:07:18.479
head.

05:07:18.540 --> 05:07:20.580
Her pearls dancing in the green light.

05:07:20.700 --> 05:07:22.979
You can skip this, dear.

05:07:23.040 --> 05:07:24.419
I'm sure it won't interest you.

05:07:24.479 --> 05:07:28.860
I'd like her to come, Anemone piped up.

05:07:28.919 --> 05:07:29.700
Please?

05:07:29.819 --> 05:07:33.000
Coral and Blister exchanged a significant

05:07:33.000 --> 05:07:33.240
look.

05:07:33.299 --> 05:07:37.080
They don't trust me, tsunami guest.

05:07:37.139 --> 05:07:39.299
They don't want me to know about any

05:07:39.299 --> 05:07:42.180
secret weapon until they're sure I'm on

05:07:42.180 --> 05:07:43.139
blisters side.

05:07:43.200 --> 05:07:45.299
Well, too bad.

05:07:45.419 --> 05:07:48.840
I'm sure it'll be very interesting

05:07:48.840 --> 05:07:52.080
Tsunami said, with earnest enthusiasm.

05:07:52.139 --> 05:07:54.540
Everything you do is interesting, mother.

05:07:54.659 --> 05:07:57.419
She blinked her large green eyes at Queen

05:07:57.419 --> 05:07:58.080
Coral.

05:07:58.139 --> 05:08:01.439
Across the table, Glory snorted, and then

05:08:01.439 --> 05:08:02.520
tried to hide it with a bout of

05:08:02.520 --> 05:08:02.880
coughing.

05:08:02.939 --> 05:08:06.479
Please, Anemone said again.

05:08:06.540 --> 05:08:10.919
All right, Carl said with a sigh, but not

05:08:10.919 --> 05:08:11.459
the others.

05:08:11.520 --> 05:08:14.639
Her gaze flicked suspiciously to clay.

05:08:14.759 --> 05:08:19.500
Tsunami followed coral, blister, anemone

05:08:19.500 --> 05:08:21.659
and whirlpool to a high level of the

05:08:21.659 --> 05:08:23.159
pavilion she hadn't visited before.

05:08:23.220 --> 05:08:27.180
It was shaped like a bowl, with low walls

05:08:27.180 --> 05:08:29.340
and a slight slope down to the center.

05:08:29.459 --> 05:08:32.759
Weapons were lined up along one side

05:08:32.759 --> 05:08:35.340
white, twisting horn spears, like the one

05:08:35.340 --> 05:08:38.340
attached to coral's tail, battle armor of

05:08:38.340 --> 05:08:40.860
chain link, or scales hammered over more

05:08:40.860 --> 05:08:43.500
scales, gleaming metal claws like the

05:08:43.500 --> 05:08:45.180
ones scavengers carried in all the

05:08:45.180 --> 05:08:45.599
scrolls.

05:08:45.720 --> 05:08:48.659
None of the weapons looked particularly

05:08:48.659 --> 05:08:50.040
special or secret.

05:08:50.099 --> 05:08:54.360
But tsunami looked sharply at the wall of

05:08:54.360 --> 05:08:56.880
weapons again, that battle armor.

05:08:56.939 --> 05:08:59.340
Surely that was what her attacker had

05:08:59.340 --> 05:09:00.180
been wearing in the tunnel.

05:09:00.240 --> 05:09:02.700
That was why she hadn't been able to claw

05:09:02.700 --> 05:09:03.840
him, or her.

05:09:03.959 --> 05:09:06.720
She remembered her claws scraping

05:09:06.720 --> 05:09:09.299
uselessly against metal, and one of the

05:09:09.299 --> 05:09:11.220
vests definitely had a nick in it.

05:09:11.279 --> 05:09:13.619
So who had access to this level?

05:09:13.680 --> 05:09:18.060
Probably everyone, she thought ruefully.

05:09:18.119 --> 05:09:20.340
May I?

05:09:20.459 --> 05:09:23.580
Whirlpool said officiously, gesturing to

05:09:23.580 --> 05:09:25.439
one of the strands of pearls on Coral's

05:09:25.439 --> 05:09:27.599
wings, she dipped her wings so he could

05:09:27.599 --> 05:09:28.020
remove it.

05:09:28.080 --> 05:09:31.200
He strutted to the center of the bowl, and

05:09:31.200 --> 05:09:33.000
carefully laid the rope of pearls on the

05:09:33.000 --> 05:09:33.900
floor in front of him.

05:09:33.900 --> 05:09:38.400
All right, he said, rubbing his talons

05:09:38.400 --> 05:09:38.759
together.

05:09:38.819 --> 05:09:42.840
See if you can make it crawl over to the

05:09:42.840 --> 05:09:43.139
wall.

05:09:43.200 --> 05:09:45.659
Tsunami looked around.

05:09:45.720 --> 05:09:47.700
Who on earth was he talking to?

05:09:47.819 --> 05:09:50.040
Where was the secret weapon?

05:09:50.099 --> 05:09:53.639
Anemone sat down next to tsunami inside?

05:09:53.700 --> 05:09:55.439
Do I have to?

05:09:55.560 --> 05:09:56.520
she said.

05:09:56.580 --> 05:09:58.380
It seems like a waste.

05:09:58.500 --> 05:10:00.419
Tsunami stared at her.

05:10:00.479 --> 05:10:06.419
Practicing is never time wasted, Whirlpole

05:10:06.419 --> 05:10:08.759
said, wagging a claw in a way that made

05:10:08.759 --> 05:10:10.080
tsunami want to snap it off.

05:10:10.139 --> 05:10:14.159
But I don't want to end up like albatross

05:10:14.159 --> 05:10:15.479
Anemone said.

05:10:15.540 --> 05:10:17.759
She flicked her wings and edged a little

05:10:17.759 --> 05:10:18.840
closer to tsunami.

05:10:18.900 --> 05:10:23.459
He made an entire pavilion grow from

05:10:23.459 --> 05:10:27.240
stone before he went mad and tried to

05:10:27.240 --> 05:10:28.020
kill everyone.

05:10:28.080 --> 05:10:30.599
Whirlpool said patronizingly.

05:10:30.659 --> 05:10:33.840
You have a way to go before that

05:10:33.840 --> 05:10:34.439
happens.

05:10:34.500 --> 05:10:37.799
Now, the necklace, please.

05:10:37.919 --> 05:10:40.259
Anemone sighed again.

05:10:40.319 --> 05:10:43.259
She held out her front talons and to

05:10:43.259 --> 05:10:45.659
tsunami's amazement, the necklace began

05:10:45.659 --> 05:10:48.959
to slowly wind toward the wall, moving in

05:10:48.959 --> 05:10:50.040
curves like a snake.

05:10:50.099 --> 05:10:53.759
Oh my gosh, tsunami blurted.

05:10:53.819 --> 05:10:56.099
Suddenly everything made sense.

05:10:56.159 --> 05:11:00.119
The magic in whirlpool's title, the self

05:11:00.119 --> 05:11:02.459
adjusting harness in the deep palace.

05:11:02.520 --> 05:11:03.659
Anemone.

05:11:03.720 --> 05:11:05.340
You're an animus.

05:11:05.400 --> 05:11:08.279
Anemone dropped her talons, and the

05:11:08.279 --> 05:11:09.180
necklace stopped moving.

05:11:09.299 --> 05:11:13.500
I know, she said, with an expression like

05:11:13.500 --> 05:11:15.240
she would rather be descended from sea

05:11:15.240 --> 05:11:16.080
cucumbers.

05:11:16.139 --> 05:11:19.799
We've had a few animas dragons in the

05:11:19.799 --> 05:11:20.639
royal family.

05:11:20.700 --> 05:11:23.520
Carl said proudly, but not in several

05:11:23.520 --> 05:11:24.479
generations.

05:11:24.479 --> 05:11:28.080
Anemone was hatched just in time to help

05:11:28.080 --> 05:11:29.400
us win this war.

05:11:29.520 --> 05:11:33.360
Careful, Blister said with a hiss.

05:11:33.419 --> 05:11:35.939
She doesn't have to know our whole plan

05:11:35.939 --> 05:11:38.939
to guess. that an animus dragon would be

05:11:38.939 --> 05:11:40.139
very useful in battle.

05:11:40.200 --> 05:11:41.520
Coral said.

05:11:41.580 --> 05:11:44.159
There are lots of marvelous things we can

05:11:44.159 --> 05:11:45.240
do with this power.

05:11:45.299 --> 05:11:47.459
Yes.

05:11:47.520 --> 05:11:51.119
Watch this, Whirlpool said.

05:11:51.180 --> 05:11:54.000
He picked up a metal armor breastplate

05:11:54.000 --> 05:11:56.220
and flung it up in the air over the

05:11:56.220 --> 05:11:56.459
edge.

05:11:56.520 --> 05:12:00.119
Catch it with a spear, he called to

05:12:00.119 --> 05:12:00.540
anemone.

05:12:00.599 --> 05:12:02.520
None of the spears moved.

05:12:02.580 --> 05:12:04.860
The breastplate plummeted toward the

05:12:04.860 --> 05:12:05.099
lake.

05:12:05.159 --> 05:12:09.479
Sorry, anemone said, not looking very

05:12:09.479 --> 05:12:09.840
sorry.

05:12:09.900 --> 05:12:12.119
You didn't give me enough warning.

05:12:12.240 --> 05:12:14.040
Ow!

05:12:14.099 --> 05:12:15.599
Someone yelled from below.

05:12:15.659 --> 05:12:18.360
Anemone.

05:12:18.419 --> 05:12:20.580
Whirlpool said with a sigh.

05:12:20.700 --> 05:12:23.880
Battle is all about quick thinking.

05:12:23.939 --> 05:12:26.939
How would you know that?

05:12:26.939 --> 05:12:27.900
she said.

05:12:27.959 --> 05:12:29.400
He frowned at her.

05:12:29.520 --> 05:12:33.299
Try it again, Queen Coral said, clapping

05:12:33.299 --> 05:12:34.500
her front talons together.

05:12:34.560 --> 05:12:36.599
And this time, do as you're told

05:12:36.599 --> 05:12:37.080
anemone.

05:12:37.200 --> 05:12:39.959
Whirlpool flung another flat piece of

05:12:39.959 --> 05:12:43.080
metal armor into the air, instantly, one

05:12:43.080 --> 05:12:45.299
of the narwhal spears shot after it and

05:12:45.299 --> 05:12:46.200
pierced it through.

05:12:46.259 --> 05:12:49.500
Blister and coral applauded, but tsunami

05:12:49.500 --> 05:12:51.119
thought it was more interesting that the

05:12:51.119 --> 05:12:53.159
spear then carefully brought the armor

05:12:53.159 --> 05:12:55.080
back to rest safely on the floor.

05:12:55.139 --> 05:13:00.720
Impressive, Blister said, but not much

05:13:00.720 --> 05:13:02.819
more impressive than what I saw last

05:13:02.819 --> 05:13:03.119
time.

05:13:03.180 --> 05:13:05.340
What about progress?

05:13:05.400 --> 05:13:07.139
What about bigger objects?

05:13:07.200 --> 05:13:10.080
How much longer must this training go

05:13:10.080 --> 05:13:10.259
on?

05:13:10.319 --> 05:13:14.459
I'm sure she's nearly ready, said Queen

05:13:14.459 --> 05:13:15.060
Coral.

05:13:15.119 --> 05:13:19.680
Years, lots more years, Anemone said at

05:13:19.680 --> 05:13:20.159
the same time.

05:13:20.279 --> 05:13:23.099
Blisters forked black tongue slipped

05:13:23.099 --> 05:13:24.959
through her teeth, and she narrowed her

05:13:24.959 --> 05:13:25.799
eyes at anemone.

05:13:25.860 --> 05:13:27.659
Coral.

05:13:27.720 --> 05:13:29.459
She said, tilting her head.

05:13:29.580 --> 05:13:31.139
Stay here.

05:13:31.200 --> 05:13:34.319
Coral ordered She slid as far away as the

05:13:34.319 --> 05:13:36.419
harness would reach, and crouched with

05:13:36.419 --> 05:13:38.400
her wings spread, whispering to blister.

05:13:38.459 --> 05:13:41.759
Whirlpool strutted over to tsunami and

05:13:41.759 --> 05:13:44.700
anemone, anemone gave him a glare, and

05:13:44.700 --> 05:13:46.380
suddenly the pearl necklace he'd left on

05:13:46.380 --> 05:13:48.959
the floor, whirled around, whipped under

05:13:48.959 --> 05:13:51.419
his belly, and soared off the ledge.

05:13:51.479 --> 05:13:53.939
With a yelp, the green dragon raced after

05:13:53.939 --> 05:13:55.500
it, diving over the edge.

05:13:55.560 --> 05:13:58.799
This is what you have to save me from

05:13:58.799 --> 05:14:00.659
Anemone whispered quickly.

05:14:00.720 --> 05:14:03.419
Boring lessons with Whirlpool?

05:14:03.479 --> 05:14:04.439
Tsunami answered.

05:14:04.500 --> 05:14:05.939
Sure, I'll get right on that.

05:14:06.060 --> 05:14:11.040
No, not just that, Anemone said, wrinkling

05:14:11.040 --> 05:14:13.319
her snout, although he is awful.

05:14:13.380 --> 05:14:16.020
All he ever asked me to do is make things

05:14:16.020 --> 05:14:16.439
move.

05:14:16.500 --> 05:14:19.979
I can enchant any inanimate object to do

05:14:19.979 --> 05:14:22.439
my bidding, and he's like, make this

05:14:22.439 --> 05:14:23.220
spear dance.

05:14:23.279 --> 05:14:26.099
Now make that chair walk from here to

05:14:26.099 --> 05:14:26.340
here.

05:14:26.400 --> 05:14:28.319
It's insulting, really.

05:14:28.439 --> 05:14:31.020
What else could you do?

05:14:31.080 --> 05:14:32.340
Tsunami asked.

05:14:32.400 --> 05:14:34.919
She glanced at coral and blister, but

05:14:34.919 --> 05:14:36.540
they both had their backs turned and were

05:14:36.540 --> 05:14:37.740
sharing their own secrets.

05:14:37.799 --> 05:14:40.080
According to blister.

05:14:40.139 --> 05:14:42.599
I should be able to enchant the sky

05:14:42.599 --> 05:14:45.240
kingdom's palace to cave in on all the

05:14:45.240 --> 05:14:45.900
sky wings.

05:14:46.020 --> 05:14:49.080
Anemone said softly, looking up at

05:14:49.080 --> 05:14:49.619
tsunami.

05:14:49.680 --> 05:14:53.759
She also wants me to curse a spear, so it

05:14:53.759 --> 05:14:56.040
will search for Burns' heart and not stop

05:14:56.040 --> 05:14:57.000
until it kills her.

05:14:57.060 --> 05:15:00.299
Tsunami coiled her tail closer.

05:15:00.360 --> 05:15:02.639
Try not to look as shaken as she felt.

05:15:02.700 --> 05:15:05.459
If anemone could do either of those

05:15:05.459 --> 05:15:08.279
things, she really was a secret weapon

05:15:08.279 --> 05:15:11.400
power like that could end this war in a

05:15:11.400 --> 05:15:11.819
week.

05:15:11.819 --> 05:15:15.119
I don't know for sure if I can do any of

05:15:15.119 --> 05:15:15.360
that.

05:15:15.419 --> 05:15:19.619
Anemone said, I'm scared to try, I don't

05:15:19.619 --> 05:15:20.400
want to try.

05:15:20.459 --> 05:15:23.759
Every time an animus dragon uses her

05:15:23.759 --> 05:15:24.060
power.

05:15:24.119 --> 05:15:25.919
She loses a bit of herself.

05:15:25.979 --> 05:15:29.700
Tsunami's sister held out her talons as

05:15:29.700 --> 05:15:31.380
if they might not really be hers.

05:15:31.439 --> 05:15:35.159
Albatross was a prince, and a hero at

05:15:35.159 --> 05:15:37.259
first, but they didn't know about the

05:15:37.259 --> 05:15:39.060
price of animus magic then.

05:15:39.180 --> 05:15:41.700
Building the pavilion turned him evil.

05:15:41.759 --> 05:15:45.000
She slipped one talon into tsunami's

05:15:45.000 --> 05:15:45.299
grasp.

05:15:45.360 --> 05:15:48.060
It felt colder than ice and hard as

05:15:48.060 --> 05:15:48.360
stone.

05:15:48.419 --> 05:15:50.880
I don't want that to happen to me.

05:15:50.939 --> 05:15:53.939
How can I possibly save you?

05:15:54.000 --> 05:15:55.380
Tsunami wondered.

05:15:55.500 --> 05:15:58.560
Even she was tempted by the kind of power

05:15:58.560 --> 05:16:00.360
that could bring peace so quickly.

05:16:00.419 --> 05:16:03.299
But she couldn't ignore the fear in

05:16:03.299 --> 05:16:04.319
Anemone's eyes.

05:16:04.380 --> 05:16:07.979
First, I'll catch the dragon who's trying

05:16:07.979 --> 05:16:10.919
to kill us, she said, curling one wing

05:16:10.919 --> 05:16:11.759
around anemone.

05:16:11.819 --> 05:16:14.639
Maybe then, mother will let you off the

05:16:14.639 --> 05:16:17.220
harness and start to trust you more.

05:16:17.400 --> 05:16:18.959
Maybe she'll listen when you tell her you

05:16:18.959 --> 05:16:19.979
don't want to use your power.

05:16:20.099 --> 05:16:23.639
Ha, Anemone muttered.

05:16:23.700 --> 05:16:25.919
Tsunami didn't know what else to say.

05:16:25.979 --> 05:16:28.619
She had no words of advice ready for

05:16:28.619 --> 05:16:31.740
dealing with strange magical problems, but

05:16:31.740 --> 05:16:33.360
she did have a lot of other questions for

05:16:33.360 --> 05:16:35.700
anemone, and this might be her only time

05:16:35.700 --> 05:16:36.599
to ask them.

05:16:36.659 --> 05:16:38.939
Can I ask you a question?

05:16:38.939 --> 05:16:39.900
she said.

05:16:39.959 --> 05:16:44.279
If none of Coral's daughters survived, who

05:16:44.279 --> 05:16:45.180
would be queen after her?

05:16:45.240 --> 05:16:48.240
Anemone flicked her tail around and

05:16:48.240 --> 05:16:49.020
studied the end of it.

05:16:49.080 --> 05:16:50.759
Who knows?

05:16:50.819 --> 05:16:53.459
I don't think a queen has ever died and

05:16:53.459 --> 05:16:56.040
passed on the throne peacefully, at least

05:16:56.040 --> 05:16:57.299
not in our kingdom.

05:16:57.360 --> 05:16:59.580
And who else would challenge her?

05:16:59.639 --> 05:17:02.880
I heard Uncle Shark say once that maybe a

05:17:02.880 --> 05:17:03.900
son should inherit.

05:17:03.959 --> 05:17:06.180
But I guess it would probably be our

05:17:06.180 --> 05:17:08.880
cousin Moray, except she doesn't want the

05:17:08.880 --> 05:17:09.180
job.

05:17:09.240 --> 05:17:11.939
She wants Coral to be queen forever.

05:17:12.000 --> 05:17:13.919
At least, that's what she says.

05:17:14.040 --> 05:17:16.439
You don't believe her?

05:17:16.500 --> 05:17:17.700
Tsunami asked.

05:17:17.759 --> 05:17:20.159
There's just something weird about her

05:17:20.159 --> 05:17:21.900
Anemone said.

05:17:21.959 --> 05:17:23.220
Isn't there?

05:17:23.279 --> 05:17:26.340
It's like, she must be faking, because

05:17:26.340 --> 05:17:28.259
nobody could really act like that all the

05:17:28.259 --> 05:17:29.159
time and mean it.

05:17:29.220 --> 05:17:32.520
Maybe, tsunami said.

05:17:32.580 --> 05:17:35.159
But I think the assassin is Shark.

05:17:35.220 --> 05:17:38.340
I bet he wants Moray to be queen, and if

05:17:38.340 --> 05:17:40.439
none of Carl's daughters survive, it'll

05:17:40.439 --> 05:17:40.919
have to be her.

05:17:40.979 --> 05:17:43.439
Anemone snorted.

05:17:43.500 --> 05:17:46.200
Moray would rather die than challenge the

05:17:46.200 --> 05:17:46.500
Queen.

05:17:46.560 --> 05:17:50.220
Tsunami saw Queen Coral's wings flutter

05:17:50.220 --> 05:17:50.580
closed.

05:17:50.639 --> 05:17:53.639
In the meanwhile, she whispered quickly.

05:17:53.700 --> 05:17:55.979
Keep acting like you need more training.

05:17:56.040 --> 05:17:58.500
Make mistakes sometimes if you have to.

05:17:58.560 --> 05:18:01.020
Make them think you aren't ready for as

05:18:01.020 --> 05:18:01.560
long as possible.

05:18:01.680 --> 05:18:03.900
Mistakes.

05:18:04.020 --> 05:18:06.119
Anemone said with a sigh.

05:18:06.240 --> 05:18:08.159
Why didn't I think of that?

05:18:08.220 --> 05:18:11.759
Queen Coral slid back to them, twisting

05:18:11.759 --> 05:18:13.020
our snout from side to side.

05:18:13.080 --> 05:18:15.299
Where's Whirlpool?

05:18:15.360 --> 05:18:16.319
she asked.

05:18:16.380 --> 05:18:18.779
I think he lost something.

05:18:18.840 --> 05:18:20.639
Anemone said innocently.

05:18:20.700 --> 05:18:24.060
Queen Blister wants you to try.

05:18:24.119 --> 05:18:26.340
Carl started, but stopped as the

05:18:26.340 --> 05:18:28.080
Sandwings head suddenly went up.

05:18:28.139 --> 05:18:31.319
Blister stared around the cavern, poised

05:18:31.319 --> 05:18:33.720
in her eerie stillness, nothing but her

05:18:33.720 --> 05:18:34.259
eyes moving.

05:18:34.319 --> 05:18:37.319
Tsunami felt hypnotized by her.

05:18:37.380 --> 05:18:40.200
Anemone and coral were equally silent

05:18:40.200 --> 05:18:40.979
waiting.

05:18:41.040 --> 05:18:45.180
Blisters gaze slowly lifted to the canopy

05:18:45.180 --> 05:18:47.099
of leaves and vines overhead.

05:18:47.159 --> 05:18:48.840
Then tsunami heard it too.

05:18:48.900 --> 05:18:51.299
Something was moving around up there.

05:18:51.360 --> 05:18:53.520
Something big.

05:18:53.639 --> 05:18:58.319
Chapter 21.

05:18:58.680 --> 05:19:01.740
Queen Coral hissed softly.

05:19:01.799 --> 05:19:05.159
I'll call my guards, she said.

05:19:05.220 --> 05:19:07.259
Wait.

05:19:07.380 --> 05:19:10.139
Blister lifted one claw.

05:19:10.200 --> 05:19:12.180
Her voice barely stirred the air.

05:19:12.299 --> 05:19:17.279
We want to catch whoever it is, not scare

05:19:17.279 --> 05:19:17.819
them away.

05:19:17.880 --> 05:19:19.680
She flicked her tail.

05:19:19.740 --> 05:19:21.060
Come.

05:19:21.119 --> 05:19:24.060
Quietly, she slid over the side of the

05:19:24.060 --> 05:19:26.040
pavilion, and flew to the cliff wall.

05:19:26.099 --> 05:19:29.340
Coral and Anemone went after her, and

05:19:29.340 --> 05:19:30.599
tsunami followed close behind.

05:19:30.659 --> 05:19:33.540
She wasn't sure she'd been invited, but

05:19:33.540 --> 05:19:34.080
she didn't care.

05:19:34.139 --> 05:19:37.500
Blister landed on a ledge beside the

05:19:37.500 --> 05:19:38.340
tallest waterfall.

05:19:38.400 --> 05:19:41.040
The water spilled out of a hole high

05:19:41.040 --> 05:19:43.139
above, nearly at the level of the

05:19:43.139 --> 05:19:43.740
canopy.

05:19:43.799 --> 05:19:46.500
It rushed in torrents down the cliff wall

05:19:46.500 --> 05:19:49.020
dividing around boulders, and sending out

05:19:49.020 --> 05:19:50.159
small clouds of spray.

05:19:50.220 --> 05:19:53.819
And it was loud, loud enough to hide the

05:19:53.819 --> 05:19:55.919
sound of their wing beats, as the 4 of

05:19:55.919 --> 05:19:57.779
them flew higher, staying close to the

05:19:57.779 --> 05:19:58.139
falls.

05:19:58.200 --> 05:20:02.700
She is clever, tsunami thought, glancing

05:20:02.700 --> 05:20:03.419
at blister.

05:20:03.479 --> 05:20:06.180
Why does that make me more nervous about

05:20:06.180 --> 05:20:07.799
her instead of less?

05:20:07.860 --> 05:20:11.220
At the top of the waterfall, the sand

05:20:11.220 --> 05:20:13.500
wing hovered for a moment, studying the

05:20:13.500 --> 05:20:15.419
canopy with her glittering dark eyes.

05:20:15.479 --> 05:20:18.360
From this high, the dragons far below

05:20:18.360 --> 05:20:20.700
looked like lizards, scurrying around the

05:20:20.700 --> 05:20:22.500
pavilion and swimming in the lake.

05:20:22.500 --> 05:20:25.680
Tsunami spotted whirlpool, paddling

05:20:25.680 --> 05:20:27.479
frantically in circles with his talons

05:20:27.479 --> 05:20:28.139
outstretched.

05:20:28.259 --> 05:20:30.840
He was still trying to catch the pearl

05:20:30.840 --> 05:20:32.220
necklace as it twisted away from him.

05:20:32.279 --> 05:20:36.119
The canopy was thick and green, with

05:20:36.119 --> 05:20:38.939
vines twisted together over centuries, and

05:20:38.939 --> 05:20:40.979
leaves the size of dragon talons.

05:20:41.040 --> 05:20:44.340
Up close, tsunami could also see small

05:20:44.340 --> 05:20:47.099
blue flowers shaped like broken eggshells

05:20:47.099 --> 05:20:49.979
shining in the small sunlit gaps.

05:20:50.040 --> 05:20:51.900
Something stirred the leaves.

05:20:51.959 --> 05:20:54.720
Something was crawling through the vines

05:20:54.720 --> 05:20:56.580
not far from the edge of the cliff.

05:20:56.639 --> 05:20:59.340
Something the size of a dragon.

05:20:59.400 --> 05:21:03.180
A spy, Queen Coral hissed under her

05:21:03.180 --> 05:21:03.419
breath.

05:21:03.479 --> 05:21:06.180
Suddenly blister darted up into the

05:21:06.180 --> 05:21:09.240
leaves, quick as a cobra striking, she

05:21:09.240 --> 05:21:11.099
sank her talons into the hidden dragon

05:21:11.099 --> 05:21:13.020
and ripped it out of the canopy.

05:21:13.080 --> 05:21:15.599
In the same movement, she whirled and

05:21:15.599 --> 05:21:17.220
threw the dragon as tsunami.

05:21:17.279 --> 05:21:20.040
Startled, tsunami reached to catch him

05:21:20.040 --> 05:21:22.500
and found herself face to face with

05:21:22.500 --> 05:21:22.979
webs.

05:21:23.040 --> 05:21:26.700
Webbs, one of the guardians from the

05:21:26.700 --> 05:21:27.900
talons of peace.

05:21:27.959 --> 05:21:30.299
The trader who had stolen her egg from

05:21:30.299 --> 05:21:32.520
the royal hatchery, who had never taught

05:21:32.520 --> 05:21:33.779
her the underwater language.

05:21:33.840 --> 05:21:36.959
She barely had time to register the

05:21:36.959 --> 05:21:39.360
terror on his face before he slammed into

05:21:39.360 --> 05:21:41.459
her, and they both crashed into the cliff

05:21:41.459 --> 05:21:41.819
wall.

05:21:41.880 --> 05:21:45.180
He flapped his wings, pulling back, and

05:21:45.180 --> 05:21:46.680
she caught her breath as she righted

05:21:46.680 --> 05:21:47.580
herself.

05:21:47.639 --> 05:21:51.659
Oh, blister said, sounding disappointed.

05:21:51.720 --> 05:21:54.240
It's just a sea wing.

05:21:54.299 --> 05:21:57.240
Not just a sea wing.

05:21:57.299 --> 05:21:59.639
Queen Coral seized Webbs by his neck and

05:21:59.639 --> 05:22:00.060
shook him.

05:22:00.119 --> 05:22:02.939
Her green eyes were sparks of rage and

05:22:02.939 --> 05:22:03.360
triumph.

05:22:03.419 --> 05:22:05.459
This is webs.

05:22:05.520 --> 05:22:07.560
Our tribe's biggest traitor.

05:22:07.619 --> 05:22:09.240
I've been looking for him for years.

05:22:09.299 --> 05:22:13.500
Your majesty, Webbs croaked.

05:22:13.560 --> 05:22:15.060
He scrabbled at his throat.

05:22:15.119 --> 05:22:18.479
Please, I've come to beg for mercy.

05:22:18.599 --> 05:22:20.220
Mercy.

05:22:20.340 --> 05:22:21.720
Coral Hist.

05:22:21.779 --> 05:22:23.340
After what you did.

05:22:23.459 --> 05:22:25.979
She shook him again harder.

05:22:26.040 --> 05:22:27.659
Mercy denied.

05:22:27.720 --> 05:22:30.900
She flung him into the air and slammed

05:22:30.900 --> 05:22:32.700
her tail into the side of his head with a

05:22:32.700 --> 05:22:33.959
horrible sounding crack.

05:22:34.020 --> 05:22:35.939
Webbs went limp.

05:22:36.000 --> 05:22:38.819
His eyes closed, and he plummeted toward

05:22:38.819 --> 05:22:39.360
the lake below.

05:22:39.419 --> 05:22:42.240
Webbs, tsunami yelled.

05:22:42.360 --> 05:22:44.400
She knew she should hate him too

05:22:44.459 --> 05:22:46.919
considering the life he'd forced on her

05:22:46.919 --> 05:22:49.319
but she found herself diving after him.

05:22:49.380 --> 05:22:51.959
All over the summer palace.

05:22:52.020 --> 05:22:55.319
Sea Wings stopped to look up, gaping at

05:22:55.319 --> 05:22:56.939
the side of a dragon falling from the

05:22:56.939 --> 05:22:57.180
sky.

05:22:57.240 --> 05:22:59.400
None of them moved to help him.

05:22:59.520 --> 05:23:02.700
Tsunami beat her wings desperately trying

05:23:02.700 --> 05:23:03.360
to catch up.

05:23:03.419 --> 05:23:05.639
Would he die if he hit the water from

05:23:05.639 --> 05:23:06.240
such a height?

05:23:06.299 --> 05:23:08.759
Clay, she shouted.

05:23:08.819 --> 05:23:10.080
Clay, help.

05:23:10.139 --> 05:23:12.959
Clay immediately burst out of their cave

05:23:12.959 --> 05:23:14.819
blinking and befuddled, but ready.

05:23:14.880 --> 05:23:16.979
Catch him!

05:23:17.040 --> 05:23:18.840
Tsunami shouted, pointing.

05:23:18.900 --> 05:23:22.080
Clay shot away from the cliff, banking

05:23:22.080 --> 05:23:24.000
around to intercept Webb's body as he

05:23:24.000 --> 05:23:24.180
fell.

05:23:24.240 --> 05:23:27.779
The 2 dragons collided in midair, and

05:23:27.779 --> 05:23:29.939
Clay tumbled, trying to hang on to the

05:23:29.939 --> 05:23:31.439
heavier, larger dragon.

05:23:31.500 --> 05:23:34.259
But he slowed him down enough for tsunami

05:23:34.259 --> 05:23:34.860
to catch up.

05:23:34.919 --> 05:23:38.040
She lifted webs from the other side until

05:23:38.040 --> 05:23:41.040
his front half rested on Clay's back, and

05:23:41.040 --> 05:23:43.020
his back half lay across her shoulders.

05:23:43.080 --> 05:23:46.439
Carefully, she and Clay struggled over to

05:23:46.439 --> 05:23:48.900
the pavilion, collapsing on the 1st level

05:23:48.900 --> 05:23:49.619
they could reach.

05:23:49.680 --> 05:23:51.659
The library, as it turned out.

05:23:51.720 --> 05:23:54.840
Webbs sprawled across the black and blue

05:23:54.840 --> 05:23:57.479
talon prints, his head lolling to the

05:23:57.479 --> 05:23:58.139
side.

05:23:58.200 --> 05:24:00.060
Blood trickled out of one ear.

05:24:00.180 --> 05:24:04.200
Wake up, tsunami said, shaking him.

05:24:04.259 --> 05:24:05.580
Come on.

05:24:05.639 --> 05:24:07.919
You can't die, not before I get a chance

05:24:07.919 --> 05:24:08.700
to yell at you.

05:24:08.759 --> 05:24:11.279
Where did he come from?

05:24:11.400 --> 05:24:12.540
Clay asked.

05:24:12.599 --> 05:24:14.939
Bump, bump, bump.

05:24:15.000 --> 05:24:17.400
The other 3 dragonettes landed around

05:24:17.400 --> 05:24:17.639
them.

05:24:17.700 --> 05:24:20.880
Glory looked down her nose at Webbs, dark

05:24:20.880 --> 05:24:22.919
green, zigzagging through her wings.

05:24:22.979 --> 05:24:25.200
Sonny crouched beside his head.

05:24:25.319 --> 05:24:28.080
The egg was cradled underneath her, making

05:24:28.080 --> 05:24:30.659
it hard for her to get too close, but she

05:24:30.659 --> 05:24:32.340
reached out and touched his snout with

05:24:32.340 --> 05:24:33.299
one front talon.

05:24:33.419 --> 05:24:35.459
Webbs?

05:24:35.520 --> 05:24:36.720
She said softly.

05:24:36.779 --> 05:24:38.400
What are you doing here?

05:24:38.459 --> 05:24:41.040
Search the area.

05:24:41.099 --> 05:24:43.860
Tsunami heard Queen Carl's voice barking

05:24:43.860 --> 05:24:44.400
orders.

05:24:44.459 --> 05:24:47.400
Make sure there are no more talons of

05:24:47.400 --> 05:24:49.020
peace lurking around.

05:24:49.080 --> 05:24:53.099
She spat out the words talons of peace, as

05:24:53.099 --> 05:24:54.720
if they tasted like rotten fish.

05:24:54.840 --> 05:24:58.680
Tsunami glanced up uneasily at the canopy

05:24:58.680 --> 05:24:59.099
overhead.

05:24:59.220 --> 05:25:02.159
Where a dragon-sized gap now yawned in

05:25:02.159 --> 05:25:03.419
the green leaves.

05:25:03.479 --> 05:25:06.060
A bolt of sunlight shone through, and she

05:25:06.060 --> 05:25:07.740
couldn't help but worry what else might

05:25:07.740 --> 05:25:09.840
find its way through the protective cover

05:25:09.840 --> 05:25:12.240
had blister thought about that at all

05:25:12.240 --> 05:25:13.439
before she struck?

05:25:13.500 --> 05:25:16.259
Surely she wouldn't deliberately endanger

05:25:16.259 --> 05:25:18.840
her allies, but maybe she didn't care

05:25:18.840 --> 05:25:20.580
about them enough to treat their defenses

05:25:20.580 --> 05:25:21.180
cautiously.

05:25:21.240 --> 05:25:25.500
Queen Coral swooped into the library, her

05:25:25.500 --> 05:25:27.000
face majestic with fury.

05:25:27.060 --> 05:25:31.020
She loomed over webs as blister, anemone

05:25:31.020 --> 05:25:32.700
and moray all arrived behind her.

05:25:32.759 --> 05:25:35.819
Why would you save his life?

05:25:35.939 --> 05:25:38.040
The queen hissed at tsunami.

05:25:38.099 --> 05:25:39.720
After everything he did to you.

05:25:39.840 --> 05:25:43.200
I don't know, tsunami thought.

05:25:43.259 --> 05:25:45.720
Why didn't she want Webbs dead?

05:25:45.779 --> 05:25:48.240
It had been instinct that sent her flying

05:25:48.240 --> 05:25:48.659
after him.

05:25:48.720 --> 05:25:52.380
Maybe I want to give riptide a chance to

05:25:52.380 --> 05:25:54.419
meet his father, like I never really got

05:25:54.419 --> 05:25:54.720
to.

05:25:54.779 --> 05:25:57.779
Or maybe I'm not ready to lose our last

05:25:57.779 --> 05:25:58.560
guardian yet.

05:25:58.619 --> 05:26:02.700
For most of her life, she'd only known 7

05:26:02.700 --> 05:26:05.400
dragons, and 2 of them had died in the

05:26:05.400 --> 05:26:08.159
last 10 days, that seemed like more than

05:26:08.159 --> 05:26:08.880
enough to her.

05:26:08.939 --> 05:26:11.880
I thought he might have information we

05:26:11.880 --> 05:26:12.419
need.

05:26:12.599 --> 05:26:16.680
She lied, maybe about the talons, or

05:26:16.680 --> 05:26:18.540
blister interjected smoothly.

05:26:18.599 --> 05:26:22.259
Perhaps now we can find out how he snuck

05:26:22.259 --> 05:26:24.419
into the royal hatchery to steal the

05:26:24.419 --> 05:26:24.840
egg.

05:26:24.900 --> 05:26:26.580
Clever dragonette.

05:26:26.639 --> 05:26:30.000
Tsunami must get her brains from you.

05:26:30.060 --> 05:26:33.180
Queen Coral hissed and glared down at

05:26:33.180 --> 05:26:33.659
Webbs.

05:26:33.720 --> 05:26:36.299
I suppose interrogating him would be

05:26:36.299 --> 05:26:37.619
useful, she said.

05:26:37.680 --> 05:26:39.779
More, wake him up.

05:26:39.840 --> 05:26:42.900
Morey dove over the edge and returned

05:26:42.900 --> 05:26:45.000
with a large clamshell full of seawater.

05:26:45.060 --> 05:26:48.540
She threw this in Webb's face with no

05:26:48.540 --> 05:26:49.560
particular gentleness.

05:26:49.619 --> 05:26:52.799
Sonny let out a little yelp and jumped

05:26:52.799 --> 05:26:53.639
away from the splash.

05:26:53.700 --> 05:26:57.659
Webbs coughed and sputtered, and snorted

05:26:57.659 --> 05:26:59.099
water back out his nostrils.

05:26:59.159 --> 05:27:02.700
He sat up slowly, holding his head, and

05:27:02.700 --> 05:27:04.380
gingerly wiping his snout dry.

05:27:04.439 --> 05:27:08.040
His gaze landed first on the dragonettes

05:27:08.040 --> 05:27:10.560
and tsunami was surprised to see his

05:27:10.560 --> 05:27:12.119
whole face light up with joy.

05:27:12.180 --> 05:27:15.360
He stared from clay to glory to

05:27:15.360 --> 05:27:17.459
Starflight, as if he couldn't believe

05:27:17.459 --> 05:27:18.419
they were all alive.

05:27:18.479 --> 05:27:21.720
He held out his front talons, and Sunny

05:27:21.720 --> 05:27:24.000
clutched the one closest to her, smiling

05:27:24.000 --> 05:27:24.540
back at him.

05:27:24.659 --> 05:27:28.020
But the sky wings, he said.

05:27:28.080 --> 05:27:29.759
I thought you were dead.

05:27:29.819 --> 05:27:31.020
How did you?

05:27:31.619 --> 05:27:32.520
We escaped.

05:27:32.580 --> 05:27:34.439
Glory said coldly.

05:27:34.500 --> 05:27:38.400
No thanks to the talons of peace, tsunami

05:27:38.400 --> 05:27:38.759
added.

05:27:38.819 --> 05:27:41.759
Or stupid, unhelpful morrow seer.

05:27:41.819 --> 05:27:44.939
It was amazing, Sonny said.

05:27:45.000 --> 05:27:46.139
You should have seen us.

05:27:46.200 --> 05:27:48.959
We will tell you about it some other time

05:27:48.959 --> 05:27:50.520
Clay interrupted.

05:27:50.580 --> 05:27:53.279
Sunny looked up at him. then over the sea

05:27:53.279 --> 05:27:55.319
wings, and snapped her mouth shut.

05:27:55.439 --> 05:27:59.159
Webb saw Queen Coral and the thunderous

05:27:59.159 --> 05:28:01.680
look on her face, and blister coiled

05:28:01.680 --> 05:28:02.700
menacingly behind her.

05:28:02.759 --> 05:28:06.060
He shuddered, then winced as if that had

05:28:06.060 --> 05:28:07.740
made his head hurt even more.

05:28:07.799 --> 05:28:10.080
Welcome back.

05:28:10.139 --> 05:28:12.240
Coral snarled at him.

05:28:12.299 --> 05:28:14.759
I thought you were too cowardly to ever

05:28:14.759 --> 05:28:15.479
return here.

05:28:15.540 --> 05:28:19.439
I know, I am not worthy of your mercy.

05:28:19.500 --> 05:28:22.139
Your majesty, Webb said.

05:28:22.200 --> 05:28:24.419
Staggering to his feet so he could kneel

05:28:24.419 --> 05:28:24.900
in front of her.

05:28:24.959 --> 05:28:28.200
But I heard, I hoped.

05:28:28.319 --> 05:28:31.680
Why did you steal one of my eggs?

05:28:31.799 --> 05:28:33.419
Queen Coral demanded.

05:28:33.479 --> 05:28:35.639
You could have stolen from any other

05:28:35.639 --> 05:28:37.139
dragon in the kingdom of the sea.

05:28:37.259 --> 05:28:40.080
Tsunami's wings twitched.

05:28:40.200 --> 05:28:42.540
And that would have been all right.

05:28:42.599 --> 05:28:45.659
Are you only angry because he stole from

05:28:45.659 --> 05:28:46.139
you?

05:28:46.200 --> 05:28:48.540
Not because a dragonette's life was

05:28:48.540 --> 05:28:49.020
ruined?

05:28:49.080 --> 05:28:52.860
It had to be an egg due to hatch on the

05:28:52.860 --> 05:28:55.860
brightest night, Webb said, in a wavering

05:28:55.860 --> 05:28:56.159
voice.

05:28:56.220 --> 05:28:59.040
And it had to fit the prophecy.

05:28:59.159 --> 05:29:02.159
The sea wing egg of deepest blue.

05:29:02.220 --> 05:29:05.340
I'd seen your eggs when I was guarding

05:29:05.340 --> 05:29:07.259
them before I, before I left.

05:29:07.319 --> 05:29:11.819
You mean ran away, Carl snarled.

05:29:11.880 --> 05:29:13.439
In the middle of a battle.

05:29:13.560 --> 05:29:15.419
Looking at webs.

05:29:15.479 --> 05:29:18.180
Tsunami couldn't believe he was Riptide's

05:29:18.180 --> 05:29:18.479
father.

05:29:18.599 --> 05:29:21.659
Riptide was so much stronger and braver

05:29:21.659 --> 05:29:23.400
than this shivering old dragon.

05:29:23.459 --> 05:29:26.700
I remembered her egg.

05:29:26.759 --> 05:29:30.119
Webbs pressed on, his wings drooping.

05:29:30.180 --> 05:29:32.279
It was so blue.

05:29:32.340 --> 05:29:34.200
It had to be the right one.

05:29:34.259 --> 05:29:38.220
I'm so sorry, Your Majesty, he said in a

05:29:38.220 --> 05:29:41.400
rush, but the prophecy is so important, I

05:29:41.400 --> 05:29:42.720
would never have betrayed you for

05:29:42.720 --> 05:29:44.400
anything else, but for peace.

05:29:44.459 --> 05:29:47.580
How could I not do as the talents asked?

05:29:47.639 --> 05:29:50.459
So how did you get into the hatchery?

05:29:50.520 --> 05:29:52.979
Corals tell lashed threateningly.

05:29:53.040 --> 05:29:55.680
I had guards posted at that door every

05:29:55.680 --> 05:29:57.479
moment until the eggs hatched.

05:29:57.540 --> 05:30:00.000
Tsunami leaned toward him.

05:30:00.060 --> 05:30:03.000
If he knew of a secret way in, surely

05:30:03.000 --> 05:30:04.259
that would point them to the Dragonette

05:30:04.259 --> 05:30:04.619
killer.

05:30:04.680 --> 05:30:06.900
Webbs hung his head.

05:30:06.959 --> 05:30:10.259
I drugged the guards, he said.

05:30:10.319 --> 05:30:14.759
I, I knew someone who helped me slip a

05:30:14.759 --> 05:30:16.560
sleeping potion into their evening meal.

05:30:16.619 --> 05:30:19.439
They were asleep when I crawled in and

05:30:19.439 --> 05:30:20.459
out again with the egg.

05:30:20.520 --> 05:30:22.319
It wasn't their fault.

05:30:22.380 --> 05:30:25.500
Well, Coral said dismissively.

05:30:25.560 --> 05:30:27.060
I killed them anyway.

05:30:27.119 --> 05:30:29.819
As for the someone who helped you.

05:30:29.880 --> 05:30:31.979
Your wife, I assume?

05:30:32.099 --> 05:30:33.959
Webb flinched.

05:30:34.020 --> 05:30:37.259
I wondered about that, Carl said.

05:30:37.319 --> 05:30:40.500
Her expression was mildly pleased, as if

05:30:40.500 --> 05:30:42.119
she was finally putting the pieces of an

05:30:42.119 --> 05:30:43.200
old puzzle into place.

05:30:43.319 --> 05:30:46.080
Stupid of her not to run away with you.

05:30:46.139 --> 05:30:49.740
Of course, that's why she was reassigned

05:30:49.740 --> 05:30:52.319
from the kitchens to active duty in the

05:30:52.319 --> 05:30:53.279
war soon after.

05:30:53.340 --> 05:30:56.819
Too bad that 1st battle was such a

05:30:56.819 --> 05:30:57.479
bloodbath.

05:30:57.540 --> 05:31:01.259
Webbs looked as if all the light had been

05:31:01.259 --> 05:31:02.400
scraped out of his scales.

05:31:02.520 --> 05:31:05.639
Sonny made a woeful, sympathetic noise

05:31:05.639 --> 05:31:08.639
and edged closer, twining her tail around

05:31:08.639 --> 05:31:08.939
his.

05:31:09.000 --> 05:31:11.520
Even glory looked a little sorry for

05:31:11.520 --> 05:31:12.060
him.

05:31:12.119 --> 05:31:15.180
Tsunami had never thought about webs

05:31:15.180 --> 05:31:17.220
leaving behind a family until she met

05:31:17.220 --> 05:31:17.819
Riptide.

05:31:17.939 --> 05:31:20.819
Even then, she hadn't pictured him

05:31:20.819 --> 05:31:23.580
abandoning a wife and baby dragonette.

05:31:23.639 --> 05:31:25.380
Maybe he really did care about the

05:31:25.380 --> 05:31:27.779
prophecy more than anything, if he was

05:31:27.779 --> 05:31:29.159
willing to give up so much for it.

05:31:29.220 --> 05:31:31.560
She would not have made the same choice

05:31:31.560 --> 05:31:31.860
herself.

05:31:31.979 --> 05:31:36.599
Now I know the dragonettes are safe, Webb

05:31:36.599 --> 05:31:37.139
said quietly.

05:31:37.200 --> 05:31:39.900
So you can do whatever you like to me.

05:31:40.020 --> 05:31:42.240
I will.

05:31:42.360 --> 05:31:43.740
Coral rumbled.

05:31:43.860 --> 05:31:46.200
We can start with you telling me where to

05:31:46.200 --> 05:31:47.520
find the talons of peace.

05:31:47.639 --> 05:31:49.500
Why?

05:31:49.560 --> 05:31:52.500
Tsunami asked, as Webbs shook his head.

05:31:52.560 --> 05:31:54.479
Why would you want to find them?

05:31:54.540 --> 05:31:58.380
Coral showed all her sharp white teeth?

05:31:58.439 --> 05:32:00.419
Revenge, dear?

05:32:00.540 --> 05:32:04.020
They stole from me, and no one has ever

05:32:04.020 --> 05:32:05.040
gotten away with that.

05:32:05.099 --> 05:32:08.279
Now I must hunt them down and exterminate

05:32:08.279 --> 05:32:08.459
them.

05:32:08.580 --> 05:32:11.759
Don't you have more important things to

05:32:11.759 --> 05:32:12.119
do?

05:32:12.180 --> 05:32:13.680
Tsunami demanded.

05:32:13.740 --> 05:32:16.740
I think they're awful dragons, yes, with

05:32:16.740 --> 05:32:18.900
a really misguided sense of how to raise

05:32:18.900 --> 05:32:21.180
dragonettes to fulfill a prophecy.

05:32:21.240 --> 05:32:23.220
But all they want to do is end the war.

05:32:23.279 --> 05:32:25.319
Isn't that what everyone wants?

05:32:25.380 --> 05:32:29.520
We're not trying to end the war.

05:32:29.639 --> 05:32:32.700
Blister said in her slithering voice.

05:32:32.759 --> 05:32:34.799
We're trying to win it.

05:32:34.860 --> 05:32:37.380
I hope you can see the difference.

05:32:37.500 --> 05:32:41.040
But killing the talons at peace won't

05:32:41.040 --> 05:32:41.400
help with that.

05:32:41.459 --> 05:32:44.279
They haven't heard anyone but us 5

05:32:44.279 --> 05:32:47.040
tsunami said, waving her talons at the

05:32:47.040 --> 05:32:48.060
other dragonettes.

05:32:48.119 --> 05:32:51.779
In fact, Starflight said, out of the

05:32:51.779 --> 05:32:52.080
blue.

05:32:52.139 --> 05:32:54.779
They almost certainly saved tsunami's

05:32:54.779 --> 05:32:54.959
life.

05:32:55.020 --> 05:32:58.860
The Nightwing froze as everyone turned to

05:32:58.860 --> 05:32:59.580
stare at him.

05:32:59.639 --> 05:33:01.979
Queen Coral hissed menacingly.

05:33:02.099 --> 05:33:04.020
Even Webbs looked confused.

05:33:04.080 --> 05:33:05.939
What?

05:33:06.000 --> 05:33:07.259
Coral growled.

05:33:07.319 --> 05:33:10.080
Well, Starflight stammered.

05:33:10.139 --> 05:33:14.580
The, the, the other female dragonettes in

05:33:14.580 --> 05:33:16.319
her hatching all died.

05:33:16.380 --> 05:33:19.139
The same way every one of your potential

05:33:19.139 --> 05:33:20.279
heirs has died.

05:33:20.400 --> 05:33:22.619
Whoever is killing them.

05:33:22.680 --> 05:33:24.599
Webbs took her egg away before the

05:33:24.599 --> 05:33:25.740
assassin could get to it.

05:33:25.799 --> 05:33:28.860
If her egg had stayed in a hatchery, she'd

05:33:28.860 --> 05:33:29.159
be dead.

05:33:29.220 --> 05:33:32.700
By stealing her, he, and the talons of

05:33:32.700 --> 05:33:34.740
peace. actually saved her life.

05:33:34.799 --> 05:33:37.020
Uh, right?

05:33:37.080 --> 05:33:40.919
Tsunami felt like she was shape shifting

05:33:40.919 --> 05:33:43.319
all of her bones being shoved from one

05:33:43.319 --> 05:33:44.220
skin into another.

05:33:44.279 --> 05:33:45.900
No.

05:33:45.959 --> 05:33:48.659
The talents of peace ruined my life.

05:33:48.720 --> 05:33:50.040
I've always known that.

05:33:50.099 --> 05:33:52.139
It's the truest thing I know.

05:33:52.200 --> 05:33:53.939
They didn't save me.

05:33:54.000 --> 05:33:57.419
But she knew in her scales. that

05:33:57.419 --> 05:33:58.380
Starflight was right.

05:33:58.439 --> 05:33:59.939
They did save her.

05:34:00.000 --> 05:34:02.580
By accident, but they did.

05:34:02.639 --> 05:34:04.860
Webbs did.

05:34:04.919 --> 05:34:07.560
She remembered all her dreams of how her

05:34:07.560 --> 05:34:09.419
life should have been if she'd hatched

05:34:09.419 --> 05:34:11.400
here and been raised by her own mother.

05:34:11.459 --> 05:34:13.380
None of them would have happened.

05:34:13.439 --> 05:34:16.200
She'd have been dead within the 1st week

05:34:16.200 --> 05:34:18.659
her neck snapped, like the sad little

05:34:18.659 --> 05:34:20.220
dragonette in the eggshell.

05:34:20.279 --> 05:34:22.080
Your majesty?

05:34:22.139 --> 05:34:24.720
The small messenger dragon from before

05:34:24.720 --> 05:34:27.599
urchin tsunami remembered, tumbled out of

05:34:27.599 --> 05:34:29.400
the air and skidded to a stop at Queen

05:34:29.400 --> 05:34:30.479
Coral's claws.

05:34:30.540 --> 05:34:33.900
He bowed as low as he could, covering his

05:34:33.900 --> 05:34:34.080
head.

05:34:34.139 --> 05:34:36.840
We found a suspicious dragon lurking

05:34:36.840 --> 05:34:37.139
outside.

05:34:37.200 --> 05:34:39.180
He must be working with webs.

05:34:39.240 --> 05:34:41.220
Bring him to me.

05:34:41.279 --> 05:34:44.700
Queen Coral growled, in a voice that rang

05:34:44.700 --> 05:34:46.020
off the cavern walls.

05:34:46.139 --> 05:34:48.840
Urchin pointed down at the tunnel, and

05:34:48.840 --> 05:34:51.060
they all leaned over to see Piranha and a

05:34:51.060 --> 05:34:52.860
troop of sea wing soldiers dragging

05:34:52.860 --> 05:34:54.779
someone into the summer palace.

05:34:54.840 --> 05:34:56.759
They heaved him out of the water to fly

05:34:56.759 --> 05:34:57.720
him up to the queen.

05:34:57.779 --> 05:35:00.540
His webbed talons flocked to the side.

05:35:00.599 --> 05:35:03.360
His eyes were closed, and a claw mark

05:35:03.360 --> 05:35:05.580
slashed along his sky blue scales was

05:35:05.580 --> 05:35:06.419
bleeding heavily.

05:35:06.479 --> 05:35:09.720
Tsunami's stomach flipped inside out like

05:35:09.720 --> 05:35:10.560
a jellyfish.

05:35:10.619 --> 05:35:12.299
It was riptide.

05:35:12.419 --> 05:35:16.680
Chapter 22.

05:35:16.919 --> 05:35:21.479
Webb's green scales paled nearly to gray

05:35:21.540 --> 05:35:23.340
as riptide was tossed onto the floor

05:35:23.340 --> 05:35:25.500
between him and Queen Coral.

05:35:25.560 --> 05:35:27.720
No, he cried.

05:35:27.779 --> 05:35:29.639
He had nothing to do with this.

05:35:29.759 --> 05:35:32.220
He's never had any contact with me.

05:35:32.279 --> 05:35:35.639
Moray tossed another clamshell of water

05:35:35.639 --> 05:35:38.400
over riptide, and he groaned, shielding

05:35:38.400 --> 05:35:38.700
his eyes.

05:35:38.819 --> 05:35:42.659
It's true, tsunami said desperately.

05:35:42.720 --> 05:35:44.939
Ribtide wasn't here with webs.

05:35:45.000 --> 05:35:46.919
He's, he's been helping me.

05:35:46.979 --> 05:35:49.500
Um, with my aquatic.

05:35:49.560 --> 05:35:53.099
It was true, but it sounded like a lie

05:35:53.099 --> 05:35:54.180
even to her own ears.

05:35:54.240 --> 05:35:57.779
Whirlpool is supposed to teach you that

05:35:57.779 --> 05:36:01.439
not this miserable creature, Queen Coral

05:36:01.439 --> 05:36:02.939
said, with narrowed eyes.

05:36:03.000 --> 05:36:07.560
Whirlpool is a horrible teacher, tsunami

05:36:07.560 --> 05:36:08.159
flared.

05:36:08.220 --> 05:36:10.200
I'd be better off taking lessons from a

05:36:10.200 --> 05:36:10.799
barnacle.

05:36:10.860 --> 05:36:13.919
Riptide pushed himself slowly up to

05:36:13.919 --> 05:36:14.279
sitting.

05:36:14.340 --> 05:36:16.560
He glanced around at all the faces

05:36:16.560 --> 05:36:17.580
staring at him.

05:36:17.639 --> 05:36:20.580
His gaze stopped on webs, and the 2

05:36:20.580 --> 05:36:22.319
dragons looked at each other for a long

05:36:22.319 --> 05:36:23.099
moment.

05:36:23.159 --> 05:36:25.799
Admit your treachery.

05:36:25.860 --> 05:36:29.580
Said the queen, betrayal runs in your

05:36:29.580 --> 05:36:30.779
family after all.

05:36:30.840 --> 05:36:34.020
She swiped at Riptide's snout, but he

05:36:34.020 --> 05:36:34.799
stepped out of reach.

05:36:34.860 --> 05:36:37.380
Pirana hissed and poked him in the side

05:36:37.380 --> 05:36:38.639
with a narwhal spear.

05:36:38.700 --> 05:36:42.000
Don't hurt him, tsunami said.

05:36:42.060 --> 05:36:44.700
Please, he's not working for the talent

05:36:44.700 --> 05:36:46.139
of peace, I promise.

05:36:46.259 --> 05:36:48.840
She was surprised to see Riptide wince.

05:36:48.900 --> 05:36:51.540
He looked down at his claws, avoiding her

05:36:51.540 --> 05:36:51.779
eyes.

05:36:51.840 --> 05:36:54.360
Was there something he hadn't told her?

05:36:54.419 --> 05:36:57.900
Throw them both in the new prison?

05:36:58.020 --> 05:37:00.060
Carl said with deep disgust.

05:37:00.119 --> 05:37:02.520
We'll find out what we need to know about

05:37:02.520 --> 05:37:05.340
the talents later, when I'm feeling a

05:37:05.340 --> 05:37:06.000
little more violent.

05:37:06.060 --> 05:37:10.139
Don't you have one more question for

05:37:10.139 --> 05:37:10.439
them?

05:37:10.500 --> 05:37:12.299
Blister interjected.

05:37:12.360 --> 05:37:14.939
She'd been quiet for so long, it made

05:37:14.939 --> 05:37:16.860
tsunami jump to hear her voice.

05:37:16.919 --> 05:37:18.720
Carl swung her head to look at the sand

05:37:18.720 --> 05:37:19.139
wing.

05:37:19.200 --> 05:37:23.099
Why, they killed all of your heirs.

05:37:23.159 --> 05:37:25.080
Blister purred.

05:37:25.139 --> 05:37:28.139
I mean, obviously.

05:37:28.200 --> 05:37:30.360
It was them, right?

05:37:30.419 --> 05:37:35.459
Obviously, Coral burst out, she glared at

05:37:35.459 --> 05:37:36.720
webs and riptide.

05:37:36.779 --> 05:37:38.639
Working together.

05:37:38.700 --> 05:37:42.840
Blister murmured, it's the perfect climax

05:37:42.840 --> 05:37:44.099
to the story.

05:37:44.159 --> 05:37:48.000
It is Coral agreed.

05:37:48.060 --> 05:37:50.520
No, tsunami said.

05:37:50.580 --> 05:37:51.840
That makes no sense.

05:37:51.900 --> 05:37:55.979
Just like one of your brilliant

05:37:55.979 --> 05:37:57.119
mysteries.

05:37:57.180 --> 05:38:00.360
Blister went on, ignoring tsunami.

05:38:00.419 --> 05:38:04.799
The claws of murder, for instance, or a

05:38:04.799 --> 05:38:05.759
tale of blood.

05:38:05.880 --> 05:38:07.979
That one was genius.

05:38:08.040 --> 05:38:12.479
It was, Carl agreed, even more

05:38:12.479 --> 05:38:13.139
fervently.

05:38:13.200 --> 05:38:15.419
They're the perfect murderers.

05:38:15.540 --> 05:38:16.439
It all fits.

05:38:16.500 --> 05:38:20.400
No, it doesn't, Tsunami shouted.

05:38:20.459 --> 05:38:21.779
Why would they do that?

05:38:21.840 --> 05:38:22.979
There's no motive.

05:38:23.040 --> 05:38:25.319
Of course there is.

05:38:25.380 --> 05:38:27.000
Carl snarled.

05:38:27.060 --> 05:38:29.099
Blister, explain it to her.

05:38:29.159 --> 05:38:33.779
So that tsunami could return as the only

05:38:33.779 --> 05:38:35.340
living heir, of course.

05:38:35.400 --> 05:38:37.919
Blister said smoothly.

05:38:37.979 --> 05:38:41.340
If they killed off all the other possible

05:38:41.340 --> 05:38:42.000
airs.

05:38:42.060 --> 05:38:45.959
She would become more and more valuable, a

05:38:45.959 --> 05:38:49.439
bargaining chip, if they ever needed it, a

05:38:49.439 --> 05:38:51.479
powerful tool when they wanted to use

05:38:51.479 --> 05:38:51.840
her.

05:38:51.900 --> 05:38:54.599
Nobody uses me.

05:38:54.659 --> 05:38:56.159
Tsunami spat.

05:38:56.220 --> 05:39:00.840
Wait, webs can't be the murderer, Clay

05:39:00.840 --> 05:39:01.139
said.

05:39:01.200 --> 05:39:03.779
His large brown head tilted to the side.

05:39:03.840 --> 05:39:06.419
He hates killing other dragons.

05:39:06.479 --> 05:39:08.880
That's why he ran away from you in the

05:39:08.880 --> 05:39:09.360
1st place.

05:39:09.419 --> 05:39:13.919
Nonsense, Queen Coral said, waving a

05:39:13.919 --> 05:39:14.340
talon.

05:39:14.400 --> 05:39:16.680
He ran away to protect his own scales.

05:39:16.740 --> 05:39:20.819
Even so, I'm not sure that theory works

05:39:20.819 --> 05:39:23.759
Starflight said, gazing vaguely into the

05:39:23.759 --> 05:39:25.439
air as if he was trying to solve a math

05:39:25.439 --> 05:39:26.040
equation.

05:39:26.099 --> 05:39:28.979
The princess murders started 2 years

05:39:28.979 --> 05:39:31.560
before they stole tsunami's egg, so the

05:39:31.560 --> 05:39:34.439
talons, and especially webs, wouldn't

05:39:34.439 --> 05:39:36.119
have known they were going to steal a

05:39:36.119 --> 05:39:37.439
royal egg at that point.

05:39:37.500 --> 05:39:40.139
Webbs didn't even know he was going to be

05:39:40.139 --> 05:39:41.520
a talent at that point.

05:39:41.580 --> 05:39:43.860
And Webbs has been underground with us

05:39:43.860 --> 05:39:45.000
for the last 6 years.

05:39:45.060 --> 05:39:47.700
He couldn't have flown here and back

05:39:47.700 --> 05:39:49.500
every time he wanted to murder a

05:39:49.500 --> 05:39:50.400
dragonette.

05:39:50.520 --> 05:39:52.439
Starflight shook his head.

05:39:52.500 --> 05:39:54.959
No, I'm afraid it doesn't.

05:39:55.080 --> 05:39:58.139
His eyes met blisters, and he abruptly

05:39:58.139 --> 05:39:59.159
slammed his mouth shut.

05:39:59.220 --> 05:40:03.119
What he said, tsunami said desperately

05:40:03.119 --> 05:40:03.840
exactly.

05:40:03.900 --> 05:40:09.720
So, his allies in the talons of peace did

05:40:09.720 --> 05:40:13.259
his dirty work, Blister said, unperturbed

05:40:13.259 --> 05:40:16.380
you know it makes sense, Coral.

05:40:16.439 --> 05:40:19.259
The talons have been your enemies for so

05:40:19.259 --> 05:40:19.680
long.

05:40:19.740 --> 05:40:22.740
Of course, it would turn out that they're

05:40:22.740 --> 05:40:24.180
the ones behind the murders.

05:40:24.240 --> 05:40:27.959
It's the ending that wraps everything

05:40:27.959 --> 05:40:28.919
together.

05:40:29.040 --> 05:40:31.080
Coral nodded.

05:40:31.139 --> 05:40:33.240
Her talent twitched toward the nearest

05:40:33.240 --> 05:40:35.520
scroll, as if she couldn't wait to write

05:40:35.520 --> 05:40:36.540
all this down.

05:40:36.599 --> 05:40:38.220
Why are you doing this?

05:40:38.279 --> 05:40:39.959
Tsunami demanded.

05:40:40.020 --> 05:40:41.759
Stepping closer to blister.

05:40:41.819 --> 05:40:44.759
Why pin the murders on Webbs and riptide

05:40:44.759 --> 05:40:46.560
unless you're covering your own tracks?

05:40:46.619 --> 05:40:49.619
Blister gave a hoot of laughter.

05:40:49.680 --> 05:40:53.159
It doesn't matter to me what happens to

05:40:53.159 --> 05:40:54.599
sea wing princesses.

05:40:54.659 --> 05:40:58.259
She said, except that I feel my poor

05:40:58.259 --> 05:41:00.240
allies, pain, of course.

05:41:00.299 --> 05:41:03.060
I'm merely pointing out the obvious to

05:41:03.060 --> 05:41:03.419
her.

05:41:03.479 --> 05:41:06.060
These 2 should be executed for their

05:41:06.060 --> 05:41:08.700
crimes as soon as possible.

05:41:08.759 --> 05:41:14.279
You want webs dead, tsunami thought, and

05:41:14.279 --> 05:41:15.419
you killed Kestrel.

05:41:15.479 --> 05:41:16.139
I'm sure of it.

05:41:16.200 --> 05:41:17.340
But why?

05:41:17.400 --> 05:41:22.439
Brilliant, just brilliant, Coral said

05:41:22.500 --> 05:41:23.880
clapping her talons together.

05:41:23.939 --> 05:41:26.459
Take them away, and we'll plan their

05:41:26.459 --> 05:41:27.060
execution later.

05:41:27.119 --> 05:41:30.360
Piranha and her guards closed around webs

05:41:30.360 --> 05:41:31.139
and riptide.

05:41:31.259 --> 05:41:33.240
Tsunami didn't have a chance to say

05:41:33.240 --> 05:41:34.799
anything more to them before they were

05:41:34.799 --> 05:41:37.560
dragged off, and riptide still wouldn't

05:41:37.560 --> 05:41:38.099
meet her eyes.

05:41:38.159 --> 05:41:40.740
She cleansed her talons and frustration.

05:41:40.799 --> 05:41:43.560
You know what this means?

05:41:43.680 --> 05:41:46.020
Coral went on, delighted.

05:41:46.080 --> 05:41:48.360
We can return the egg to the royal

05:41:48.360 --> 05:41:48.959
hatchery.

05:41:49.020 --> 05:41:49.979
It's safe now.

05:41:50.099 --> 05:41:53.099
It isn't, Sonny cried.

05:41:53.159 --> 05:41:54.900
She wrapped her talons around the egg.

05:41:54.959 --> 05:41:59.340
It certainly is, said the queen, with

05:41:59.340 --> 05:42:00.360
webs locked up.

05:42:00.419 --> 05:42:02.580
The egg can hatch in the royal hatchery

05:42:02.580 --> 05:42:04.020
just like it's supposed to.

05:42:04.139 --> 05:42:07.139
You're wrong, tsunami said.

05:42:07.259 --> 05:42:09.419
I'm not risking a dragonette's life

05:42:09.419 --> 05:42:10.860
because you've fallen for this crazy

05:42:10.860 --> 05:42:12.779
story. blister has invented.

05:42:12.840 --> 05:42:16.319
Blisters, obsidian black eyes glittered

05:42:16.319 --> 05:42:17.880
malevolently at tsunami.

05:42:17.939 --> 05:42:22.020
It will be perfectly safe, Coral said

05:42:22.020 --> 05:42:23.220
waving her claws.

05:42:23.279 --> 05:42:26.700
Besides, every queen in sea wing history

05:42:26.700 --> 05:42:28.680
has hatched in the royal hatchery.

05:42:28.799 --> 05:42:32.520
Silence prickled between them, Tsunami

05:42:32.520 --> 05:42:34.319
was thinking, I didn't.

05:42:34.439 --> 05:42:36.479
And surely Coral was too.

05:42:36.540 --> 05:42:39.419
You'll eat those words when I'm Queen

05:42:39.419 --> 05:42:40.439
tsunami thought.

05:42:40.500 --> 05:42:42.479
But she wasn't sure she meant it

05:42:42.479 --> 05:42:42.779
anymore.

05:42:42.840 --> 05:42:45.240
Did she even want to be queen here?

05:42:45.299 --> 05:42:48.119
Especially if it meant allying herself

05:42:48.119 --> 05:42:50.400
with blister, or breaking away from her

05:42:50.400 --> 05:42:52.380
and then dealing with the consequences.

05:42:52.439 --> 05:42:55.979
Only one dragon could change Coral's mind

05:42:55.979 --> 05:42:56.520
about the egg.

05:42:56.580 --> 05:42:59.759
Tsunami glanced at blister and realized

05:42:59.759 --> 05:43:01.020
at least one thing was true.

05:43:01.080 --> 05:43:03.540
Blister couldn't care less what happened

05:43:03.540 --> 05:43:04.919
to the sea wing airs.

05:43:04.979 --> 05:43:07.680
She was studying her claws, looking

05:43:07.680 --> 05:43:08.520
slightly bored.

05:43:08.580 --> 05:43:12.419
Fine, tsunami said, squaring her

05:43:12.419 --> 05:43:14.639
shoulders, but I'm staying with it until

05:43:14.639 --> 05:43:15.299
it hatches.

05:43:15.360 --> 05:43:17.700
Queen Coral tilted her head.

05:43:17.880 --> 05:43:20.759
In the royal hatchery, she said.

05:43:20.819 --> 05:43:22.200
All night.

05:43:22.259 --> 05:43:26.580
I'll make sure she hatches safely, tsunami

05:43:26.580 --> 05:43:26.819
said.

05:43:26.939 --> 05:43:30.119
She glanced at the egg, glowing blue and

05:43:30.119 --> 05:43:31.439
green below the white shell.

05:43:31.500 --> 05:43:33.900
The dragonette was close to hatching

05:43:33.900 --> 05:43:36.180
pressed against the thinning walls.

05:43:36.240 --> 05:43:38.700
Every once in a while the egg rocked in

05:43:38.700 --> 05:43:39.419
Sonny's arms.

05:43:39.479 --> 05:43:42.419
But when I catch the real murderer

05:43:42.419 --> 05:43:45.240
tsunami went on, I want you to promise

05:43:45.240 --> 05:43:47.580
that you'll let riptide and webs go

05:43:47.580 --> 05:43:47.880
free.

05:43:47.939 --> 05:43:49.799
Ha!

05:43:49.860 --> 05:43:51.060
Carl snorted.

05:43:51.119 --> 05:43:53.220
Webbs will never be free again.

05:43:53.279 --> 05:43:57.419
Even if I save your last air, tsunami

05:43:57.419 --> 05:43:57.900
demanded.

05:43:57.959 --> 05:44:00.240
Coral scraped your claws across the

05:44:00.240 --> 05:44:00.479
rock.

05:44:00.540 --> 05:44:03.240
You won't have to, she said.

05:44:03.299 --> 05:44:05.279
We have the assassins now.

05:44:05.340 --> 05:44:08.459
So it should be an easy bargain to make

05:44:08.459 --> 05:44:09.779
tsunami said.

05:44:09.840 --> 05:44:11.880
Blister stared at her coldly.

05:44:12.000 --> 05:44:16.860
All right, Coral said, waving one talon.

05:44:16.919 --> 05:44:21.000
I'll promise you riptide, but Webbs has

05:44:21.000 --> 05:44:22.259
too much to answer for.

05:44:22.319 --> 05:44:25.860
Tsunami noticed blisters settling back.

05:44:25.919 --> 05:44:29.220
So it was definitely webs she wanted dead

05:44:29.220 --> 05:44:30.779
not riptide.

05:44:30.840 --> 05:44:33.119
That was the best she could do for now.

05:44:33.180 --> 05:44:35.159
She'd have to think of another way to

05:44:35.159 --> 05:44:35.880
save webs.

05:44:35.939 --> 05:44:38.400
But tsunami.

05:44:38.459 --> 05:44:41.400
We should stay together, Clay protested.

05:44:41.459 --> 05:44:43.259
We can't protect you down there.

05:44:43.319 --> 05:44:47.220
And whoever's coming after the eggs will

05:44:47.220 --> 05:44:48.840
be just as happy to kill you too.

05:44:48.900 --> 05:44:50.459
Glory pointed out.

05:44:50.520 --> 05:44:54.060
Tsunami shook her head and flexed her

05:44:54.060 --> 05:44:54.419
claws.

05:44:54.479 --> 05:44:56.400
Not if I catch him first.

05:44:56.459 --> 05:45:00.959
Part three.

05:45:01.020 --> 05:45:02.880
Out of the egg.

05:45:03.000 --> 05:45:05.939
Chapter 23.

05:45:06.180 --> 05:45:09.900
It was pitch dark in the royal hatchery

05:45:09.900 --> 05:45:12.479
dark, and horribly quiet.

05:45:12.540 --> 05:45:15.479
Tsunami could see in the dark, of course

05:45:15.479 --> 05:45:17.759
but everything was gray and a little

05:45:17.759 --> 05:45:18.240
blurry.

05:45:18.299 --> 05:45:20.939
The only flashes of color came from the

05:45:20.939 --> 05:45:22.860
eggs when the dragonettes inside moved.

05:45:22.919 --> 05:45:26.939
Across the cave, she could see the 3 male

05:45:26.939 --> 05:45:28.860
eggs peacefully leaning against one

05:45:28.860 --> 05:45:32.220
another, they had nothing to worry about

05:45:32.220 --> 05:45:34.439
guards were stationed outside the door

05:45:34.439 --> 05:45:37.319
but tsunami was the only one in the

05:45:37.319 --> 05:45:37.860
hatchery.

05:45:37.979 --> 05:45:41.400
As soon as the door closed behind her, she

05:45:41.400 --> 05:45:44.099
prowled around all the walls, poking

05:45:44.099 --> 05:45:46.080
everything that stuck out, and hoping a

05:45:46.080 --> 05:45:47.700
hole would suddenly yawn open in the

05:45:47.700 --> 05:45:47.939
floor.

05:45:48.000 --> 05:45:51.000
She circled the statue of orcas several

05:45:51.000 --> 05:45:54.360
times, shoving at its talons and tail and

05:45:54.360 --> 05:45:56.279
pedestal, but nothing happened.

05:45:56.340 --> 05:45:58.799
There was no sign of a secret entrance

05:45:58.799 --> 05:45:59.459
anywhere.

05:45:59.520 --> 05:46:03.659
Finally, she curled up beside the egg and

05:46:03.659 --> 05:46:05.040
stared fiercely around the room.

05:46:05.099 --> 05:46:09.720
All right, assassin, she thought, I'm

05:46:09.720 --> 05:46:10.139
ready for you.

05:46:10.200 --> 05:46:13.380
She had a narwhal spear lying on the

05:46:13.380 --> 05:46:14.159
floor beside her.

05:46:14.220 --> 05:46:16.259
Although she had no idea how to use it

05:46:16.259 --> 05:46:18.419
but she wouldn't be taken by surprise

05:46:18.419 --> 05:46:18.599
again.

05:46:18.659 --> 05:46:22.439
The warm jets of water billowed silently

05:46:22.439 --> 05:46:24.180
up through tiny holes in the coral

05:46:24.180 --> 05:46:26.580
surrounding the eggs in a bath of heat

05:46:26.580 --> 05:46:27.599
and small bubbles.

05:46:27.659 --> 05:46:31.380
It was a little too hot for tsunami, but

05:46:31.380 --> 05:46:32.580
she didn't want to move away from the

05:46:32.580 --> 05:46:32.880
egg.

05:46:32.939 --> 05:46:35.880
She poked her nose underneath it, checking

05:46:35.880 --> 05:46:37.619
again for a secret trap door.

05:46:37.680 --> 05:46:40.139
But the floor was smooth and polished

05:46:40.139 --> 05:46:41.580
like the egg itself.

05:46:41.639 --> 05:46:44.700
A flutter moved in the eggshell, like a

05:46:44.700 --> 05:46:47.580
heartbeat, as the dragonette inside tried

05:46:47.580 --> 05:46:48.779
to stretch her wings.

05:46:48.779 --> 05:46:51.599
Tsunami rested her front talons on it for

05:46:51.599 --> 05:46:51.900
a moment.

05:46:51.959 --> 05:46:54.599
She wondered if Sonny was right that the

05:46:54.599 --> 05:46:55.619
dragonette could hear them.

05:46:55.680 --> 05:46:58.319
She pressed her snout up to the egg and

05:46:58.319 --> 05:46:59.400
whispered through the water.

05:46:59.459 --> 05:47:02.939
Don't worry, I'm here to protect you.

05:47:03.000 --> 05:47:06.000
The tiny wings fluttered again.

05:47:06.119 --> 05:47:09.119
Tsunami leaned closer, wishing for some

05:47:09.119 --> 05:47:13.259
noise, some light in the hot, silent, dark

05:47:13.259 --> 05:47:13.680
room.

05:47:13.740 --> 05:47:17.040
Scrape.

05:47:17.099 --> 05:47:19.139
Tsunami's head shut up.

05:47:19.200 --> 05:47:22.020
Stillness, darkness.

05:47:22.080 --> 05:47:25.799
And yet, she had a creeping feeling that

05:47:25.799 --> 05:47:28.020
someone was suddenly in the room with

05:47:28.020 --> 05:47:28.200
her.

05:47:28.259 --> 05:47:31.740
Screw...

05:47:31.799 --> 05:47:35.220
Her scales tingle between her wings as if

05:47:35.220 --> 05:47:36.659
squirrels were scuttling down her back.

05:47:36.720 --> 05:47:40.020
She stood up and flexed her claws.

05:47:40.080 --> 05:47:42.959
The one door to the hatchery was closed.

05:47:43.020 --> 05:47:44.400
The eggs were still.

05:47:44.459 --> 05:47:46.979
The only movement in the room was the

05:47:46.979 --> 05:47:48.959
blip of small bubbles rising from the

05:47:48.959 --> 05:47:49.200
floor.

05:47:49.259 --> 05:47:52.619
But wait, the statue.

05:47:52.740 --> 05:47:55.319
Hadn't it been facing the door before?

05:47:55.380 --> 05:47:58.799
She stared at it until her eyes hurt.

05:47:58.860 --> 05:48:01.979
Had it turned its head?

05:48:02.040 --> 05:48:03.240
Was it looking at her?

05:48:03.299 --> 05:48:06.119
Tsunami's whole body was shaking.

05:48:06.180 --> 05:48:08.459
She blinked through the darkness at the

05:48:08.459 --> 05:48:09.659
statue of Orca.

05:48:09.720 --> 05:48:12.119
The statue stared back.

05:48:12.180 --> 05:48:15.479
Its eyes were sapphires, she remembered

05:48:15.479 --> 05:48:17.939
but in the shades of gray here, they

05:48:17.939 --> 05:48:20.759
gleamed as obsidian dark and vicious as

05:48:20.759 --> 05:48:21.479
blisters.

05:48:21.540 --> 05:48:24.119
She was sure the statue had been facing

05:48:24.119 --> 05:48:25.200
the door when she came in.

05:48:25.259 --> 05:48:28.319
But now, its head was turned toward her

05:48:28.319 --> 05:48:31.259
and the egg, watching them darkly.

05:48:31.319 --> 05:48:35.400
Impossible, she started to think, and

05:48:35.400 --> 05:48:37.139
then scrape.

05:48:37.259 --> 05:48:40.560
Scrape, scrape.

05:48:40.619 --> 05:48:43.860
Stone claws curled around the top of the

05:48:43.860 --> 05:48:44.520
pedestal.

05:48:44.639 --> 05:48:47.580
A stone tongue flicked between jagged

05:48:47.580 --> 05:48:48.419
shark like teeth.

05:48:48.479 --> 05:48:52.919
Nobody's sneaking in Tsunami had a moment

05:48:52.919 --> 05:48:53.220
to think.

05:48:53.340 --> 05:48:55.740
The assassin's already here.

05:48:55.799 --> 05:48:57.479
She's been here all along.

05:48:57.540 --> 05:49:01.139
And then the statue hurtled off the

05:49:01.139 --> 05:49:03.419
pedestal, talons reaching to snatch the

05:49:03.419 --> 05:49:03.659
egg.

05:49:03.720 --> 05:49:06.479
Tsunami flung herself between the statue

05:49:06.479 --> 05:49:07.740
and her unhatched sister.

05:49:07.799 --> 05:49:11.580
Green marble claws raked tsunami's neck

05:49:11.580 --> 05:49:14.099
heavier and thicker than a real dragon's

05:49:14.099 --> 05:49:16.740
like shards of rock stabbing between her

05:49:16.740 --> 05:49:17.099
scales.

05:49:17.159 --> 05:49:20.099
One caught in her gills and ripped a

05:49:20.099 --> 05:49:23.099
wider hole, blood bubbled out as tsunami

05:49:23.099 --> 05:49:24.180
shoved the statue away.

05:49:24.240 --> 05:49:26.819
Sorry, broke the rules.

05:49:26.880 --> 05:49:28.080
Blood in the hatchery.

05:49:28.139 --> 05:49:29.639
Tsunami thought dizzily.

05:49:29.759 --> 05:49:32.700
She staggered back, pressing one talon to

05:49:32.700 --> 05:49:33.060
her neck.

05:49:33.119 --> 05:49:35.220
How could she fight a statue?

05:49:35.279 --> 05:49:38.159
How could anyone beat a dragon of solid

05:49:38.159 --> 05:49:38.520
stone?

05:49:38.580 --> 05:49:40.680
It attacked again.

05:49:40.740 --> 05:49:42.720
Relentless as the tide.

05:49:42.779 --> 05:49:45.659
The statue plowed into tsunami and

05:49:45.659 --> 05:49:46.259
knocked her backward.

05:49:46.319 --> 05:49:49.319
Its weight bore down on her, crushing her

05:49:49.319 --> 05:49:49.919
against the floor.

05:49:49.979 --> 05:49:53.939
She struggled, clawing at its snout, but

05:49:53.939 --> 05:49:55.740
her claws scraped uselessly against

05:49:55.740 --> 05:49:57.599
marble and sang with pain.

05:49:57.659 --> 05:50:01.080
The statue was trying to walk over her

05:50:01.080 --> 05:50:03.240
willing to trample her on its way to the

05:50:03.240 --> 05:50:03.540
egg.

05:50:03.599 --> 05:50:06.720
One foot came down heavily on tsunami's

05:50:06.720 --> 05:50:09.360
chest, and she felt tiny crack, crack

05:50:09.360 --> 05:50:10.860
cracks stabbing through her ribs.

05:50:10.979 --> 05:50:14.400
You are not getting to that egg.

05:50:14.459 --> 05:50:17.639
Tsunami reached up and wrapped her front

05:50:17.639 --> 05:50:19.680
talons around the dragon's snout.

05:50:19.740 --> 05:50:22.439
She yanked it down toward her, dug her

05:50:22.439 --> 05:50:24.720
claws into the eye sockets, and popped

05:50:24.720 --> 05:50:25.979
the 2 sapphires free.

05:50:26.099 --> 05:50:29.099
They tumbled into her palms, gleaming and

05:50:29.099 --> 05:50:29.340
heavy.

05:50:29.400 --> 05:50:33.180
The stone dragon didn't roar in pain or

05:50:33.180 --> 05:50:35.639
collapse, or any of the things tsunami

05:50:35.639 --> 05:50:36.299
had been hoping for.

05:50:36.360 --> 05:50:39.599
It stopped, swung its head from side to

05:50:39.599 --> 05:50:41.880
side for a moment, and sat back on its

05:50:41.880 --> 05:50:44.279
haunches, lifting its weight just long

05:50:44.279 --> 05:50:45.659
enough for her to wriggle free.

05:50:45.720 --> 05:50:49.200
She took a deep breath, thick with

05:50:49.200 --> 05:50:52.740
gurgling blood, and yelled, help, as loud

05:50:52.740 --> 05:50:55.319
as she could, even muffled by the water

05:50:55.319 --> 05:50:57.479
surely a scream would be heard by the

05:50:57.479 --> 05:50:58.619
guards outside.

05:50:58.680 --> 05:50:59.939
Help, help.

05:51:00.000 --> 05:51:02.459
If there were still guards outside.

05:51:02.520 --> 05:51:05.400
Queen Coral, convinced of her own theory

05:51:05.400 --> 05:51:07.740
might have promised them to tsunami and

05:51:07.740 --> 05:51:09.599
then sent them away, certain they

05:51:09.599 --> 05:51:10.319
wouldn't be needed.

05:51:10.380 --> 05:51:13.560
Whether they couldn't hear her or weren't

05:51:13.560 --> 05:51:13.979
there at all.

05:51:14.040 --> 05:51:15.060
Nobody came.

05:51:15.119 --> 05:51:18.299
The statue felt its empty eye sockets

05:51:18.299 --> 05:51:20.459
curiously, then padded the floor around

05:51:20.459 --> 05:51:22.799
it, as if it thought its eyes might have

05:51:22.799 --> 05:51:24.000
accidentally slipped out.

05:51:24.060 --> 05:51:27.240
Tsunami took a step back and dropped the

05:51:27.240 --> 05:51:29.099
sapphires through 2 of the water jet

05:51:29.099 --> 05:51:29.580
holes.

05:51:29.639 --> 05:51:31.619
She needed all the advantages she could

05:51:31.619 --> 05:51:31.860
get.

05:51:31.919 --> 05:51:35.459
Carefully, she reached over the egg and

05:51:35.459 --> 05:51:37.020
picked up the narwhal spear.

05:51:37.080 --> 05:51:40.020
Would this do anything against stone?

05:51:40.080 --> 05:51:43.200
The statue flicked its tongue in and out

05:51:43.200 --> 05:51:44.700
tasting the water.

05:51:44.759 --> 05:51:47.520
Slowly, it turned its sightless face

05:51:47.520 --> 05:51:48.840
towards tsunami.

05:51:48.900 --> 05:51:51.599
She knew an animus dragon must have

05:51:51.599 --> 05:51:53.700
cursed the statue, but she didn't know

05:51:53.700 --> 05:51:55.799
how these enchantments worked, would

05:51:55.799 --> 05:51:56.880
blinding it stop it?

05:51:56.939 --> 05:52:00.180
Or was it set to keep trying, to kill no

05:52:00.180 --> 05:52:02.520
matter what, until all the royal heirs

05:52:02.520 --> 05:52:03.900
and the hatchery were dead?

05:52:03.959 --> 05:52:07.080
She guessed it was enchanted to kill only

05:52:07.080 --> 05:52:09.959
when it was sure no guards were around, no

05:52:09.959 --> 05:52:12.540
queen, no one to witness its crimes and

05:52:12.540 --> 05:52:13.860
stop it from striking again.

05:52:13.919 --> 05:52:16.500
But tsunami was an heir.

05:52:16.560 --> 05:52:17.700
She wasn't a witness.

05:52:17.759 --> 05:52:19.439
She was a target.

05:52:19.500 --> 05:52:21.360
It stepped toward her.

05:52:21.419 --> 05:52:23.880
The floor trembled a little at the weight

05:52:23.880 --> 05:52:25.439
of each talon coming down.

05:52:25.560 --> 05:52:28.560
Tsunami wanted to lead it away from the

05:52:28.560 --> 05:52:28.860
egg.

05:52:28.919 --> 05:52:31.439
If she could open the door, would that be

05:52:31.439 --> 05:52:33.360
enough to turn it into a frozen statue

05:52:33.360 --> 05:52:33.599
again?

05:52:33.659 --> 05:52:36.360
Or if there was no one there, would it

05:52:36.360 --> 05:52:37.439
chase her into the palace?

05:52:37.500 --> 05:52:40.799
But she was afraid to leave the egg, even

05:52:40.799 --> 05:52:43.259
for a moment, the statue was fast.

05:52:43.319 --> 05:52:46.200
It could crush the egg with one foot and

05:52:46.200 --> 05:52:48.000
keep chasing her without missing a beat.

05:52:48.060 --> 05:52:50.340
And if she tried to carry the egg with

05:52:50.340 --> 05:52:52.740
her, the statue could crash down on both

05:52:52.740 --> 05:52:54.720
of them, shattering it easily.

05:52:54.779 --> 05:52:57.959
It was safest in the nest, as long as

05:52:57.959 --> 05:52:59.159
tsunami stood in front of it.

05:52:59.220 --> 05:53:02.580
She hefted the spear and pointed it at

05:53:02.580 --> 05:53:03.119
the dragon.

05:53:03.180 --> 05:53:05.700
Normal fight rules didn't apply here.

05:53:05.819 --> 05:53:08.880
She could try piercing the eye socket, but

05:53:08.880 --> 05:53:11.220
there was no brain in there to skewer, no

05:53:11.220 --> 05:53:13.799
heart to find through the scales, not

05:53:13.799 --> 05:53:15.959
even the vulnerable spot on the tail all

05:53:15.959 --> 05:53:16.919
dragons had.

05:53:16.979 --> 05:53:19.560
The statue's snout lifted.

05:53:19.619 --> 05:53:22.560
It's empty eye holes as dark as deep sea

05:53:22.560 --> 05:53:23.220
canyons.

05:53:23.279 --> 05:53:25.020
Was it smelling her?

05:53:25.080 --> 05:53:26.939
Tasting her in the water?

05:53:27.000 --> 05:53:28.560
Or could it hear her?

05:53:28.619 --> 05:53:30.419
Whatever it was doing?

05:53:30.479 --> 05:53:32.880
It seemed to know exactly where she was

05:53:32.880 --> 05:53:34.380
eyes or no eyes.

05:53:34.439 --> 05:53:37.680
The statue leaped straight at her.

05:53:37.740 --> 05:53:40.259
She braced the spear against the floor

05:53:40.259 --> 05:53:42.479
and the statue's chest slammed into it.

05:53:42.540 --> 05:53:46.139
Jarring shock thrummed through tsunami's

05:53:46.139 --> 05:53:48.360
talons as if she'd been stabbed in both

05:53:48.360 --> 05:53:48.959
palms.

05:53:49.020 --> 05:53:52.319
The statue ricocheted back, and tsunami

05:53:52.319 --> 05:53:54.900
saw bits of dark green stone crumble away

05:53:54.900 --> 05:53:55.619
into the water.

05:53:55.680 --> 05:53:59.220
So maybe it can be smashed into little

05:53:59.220 --> 05:53:59.520
pieces.

05:53:59.580 --> 05:54:04.020
The statue came on again, fast, but this

05:54:04.020 --> 05:54:05.700
time reaching out in front of it.

05:54:05.759 --> 05:54:08.340
Tsunami tried to move the spear out of

05:54:08.340 --> 05:54:11.040
its reach, but it caught the narwhal horn

05:54:11.040 --> 05:54:13.500
in its front talons and yanked it sharply

05:54:13.500 --> 05:54:14.459
out of her grasp.

05:54:14.520 --> 05:54:17.459
It swung the spear around in an arc, and

05:54:17.459 --> 05:54:19.500
tsunami had to duck and roll away to

05:54:19.500 --> 05:54:20.459
avoid being skewered.

05:54:20.520 --> 05:54:23.939
The only sound the statue made was the

05:54:23.939 --> 05:54:26.099
scraping of stone against stone.

05:54:26.159 --> 05:54:30.240
It didn't roar, or growl, or grunt like a

05:54:30.240 --> 05:54:31.439
regular dragon in battle.

05:54:31.500 --> 05:54:34.680
It was as horribly silent as the rest of

05:54:34.680 --> 05:54:35.340
the hatchery.

05:54:35.400 --> 05:54:38.819
Tsunami wondered if it could talk, or

05:54:38.819 --> 05:54:41.340
hear, or communicate in any way.

05:54:41.400 --> 05:54:42.720
Can you hear me?

05:54:42.779 --> 05:54:45.540
She shouted at it, throwing caution to

05:54:45.540 --> 05:54:46.020
the currents.

05:54:46.080 --> 05:54:47.639
Who enchanted you?

05:54:47.759 --> 05:54:51.000
Instead of answering, it tossed the spear

05:54:51.000 --> 05:54:53.759
aside and leaped at her once more, tsunami

05:54:53.759 --> 05:54:56.819
dove underneath it, grabbed the spear, and

05:54:56.819 --> 05:54:58.439
whirled to put herself in front of the

05:54:58.439 --> 05:54:58.979
egg again.

05:54:59.040 --> 05:55:01.560
She couldn't smash the statue while it

05:55:01.560 --> 05:55:01.919
was moving.

05:55:01.979 --> 05:55:04.259
It was too fast and too strong.

05:55:04.319 --> 05:55:06.000
But if she could trap it somehow.

05:55:06.060 --> 05:55:09.360
The statue spun, and crashed its tail

05:55:09.360 --> 05:55:10.080
into her side.

05:55:10.139 --> 05:55:13.560
Tsunami was knocked off her feet, flying

05:55:13.560 --> 05:55:14.639
through the water into the wall.

05:55:14.700 --> 05:55:18.419
Crack, went something in her chest, and

05:55:18.419 --> 05:55:21.060
stab, went another bolt of pain through

05:55:21.060 --> 05:55:21.720
her whole body.

05:55:21.779 --> 05:55:24.900
Breathless, she forced herself back to

05:55:24.900 --> 05:55:27.419
the egg, jabbing at the statue with a

05:55:27.419 --> 05:55:28.200
spear to push it away.

05:55:28.259 --> 05:55:30.900
It reached for the spear again.

05:55:30.900 --> 05:55:34.020
This time, she tilted the spear up and

05:55:34.020 --> 05:55:36.000
stabbed it violently into the statue's

05:55:36.000 --> 05:55:36.419
open mouth.

05:55:36.479 --> 05:55:39.540
The spear lodged in the stone and stuck.

05:55:39.599 --> 05:55:42.659
The statue's claws scrabbled along the

05:55:42.659 --> 05:55:44.700
shaft of the horn and tried to yank it

05:55:44.700 --> 05:55:46.860
out, but it was wedged in tightly.

05:55:46.919 --> 05:55:49.680
Tsunami shook the spear from side to side

05:55:49.680 --> 05:55:51.779
and the statue's head wobbled along with

05:55:51.779 --> 05:55:51.959
it.

05:55:52.020 --> 05:55:55.680
She leaped to an empty nest and jammed

05:55:55.680 --> 05:55:57.540
the blunt end of the spear into one of

05:55:57.540 --> 05:55:58.259
the crevices.

05:55:58.319 --> 05:56:01.080
Now the statue was pinned like a sheep in

05:56:01.080 --> 05:56:02.220
a dragon's claws.

05:56:02.340 --> 05:56:04.919
It whipped its tail and beat the floor

05:56:04.919 --> 05:56:07.439
with its talons, trying to push itself

05:56:07.439 --> 05:56:07.860
free.

05:56:07.919 --> 05:56:10.680
Its wings thrashed the water into wild

05:56:10.680 --> 05:56:13.319
currents, so tsunami could barely stay

05:56:13.319 --> 05:56:13.740
upright.

05:56:13.799 --> 05:56:16.740
Tsunami fought her way back to the egg

05:56:16.740 --> 05:56:17.639
and picked it up.

05:56:17.700 --> 05:56:19.259
Just as she did.

05:56:19.319 --> 05:56:22.680
Tap, tap, tap.

05:56:22.740 --> 05:56:25.860
The egg cracked down the middle, and a

05:56:25.860 --> 05:56:27.479
small green head poked out.

05:56:27.540 --> 05:56:30.599
Dark green eyes blinked at tsunami.

05:56:30.659 --> 05:56:33.599
Tsunami smiled, and flashed a few tiny

05:56:33.599 --> 05:56:35.400
stripes along her snout to say hello.

05:56:35.459 --> 05:56:38.700
The statue was writhing and smashing the

05:56:38.700 --> 05:56:39.180
floor now.

05:56:39.240 --> 05:56:41.880
Tsunami was afraid it would knock itself

05:56:41.880 --> 05:56:42.720
free in a minute.

05:56:42.779 --> 05:56:45.599
She clutched the dragonette and swam for

05:56:45.599 --> 05:56:46.860
the door as fast as she could.

05:56:46.919 --> 05:56:49.439
When she kicked it open, she found that

05:56:49.439 --> 05:56:51.959
indeed, there were no guards outside.

05:56:52.020 --> 05:56:55.439
But as the door opened, the statue went

05:56:55.439 --> 05:56:55.860
still.

05:56:55.919 --> 05:56:58.740
Tsunami turned in the open doorway to

05:56:58.740 --> 05:56:59.220
look at it.

05:56:59.279 --> 05:57:02.520
The enchantment only worked in secret.

05:57:02.580 --> 05:57:04.919
It dropped away when the door was open.

05:57:04.979 --> 05:57:08.040
Whoever had said the curse didn't want

05:57:08.040 --> 05:57:10.380
anyone to look in and catch the statue at

05:57:10.380 --> 05:57:11.220
its deadly work.

05:57:11.279 --> 05:57:14.340
Tsunami guessed that the spell also

05:57:14.340 --> 05:57:16.080
alerted the statue when someone was

05:57:16.080 --> 05:57:18.060
coming down the passageway, so it

05:57:18.060 --> 05:57:19.500
normally had time to return to its

05:57:19.500 --> 05:57:20.099
pedestal.

05:57:20.220 --> 05:57:23.220
And the statue would remain still, as

05:57:23.220 --> 05:57:25.619
long as anyone else was around, like the

05:57:25.619 --> 05:57:26.939
queen, or her guards.

05:57:27.000 --> 05:57:29.880
This statue was meant to keep murdering

05:57:29.880 --> 05:57:32.040
dragonettes for as long as it could.

05:57:32.099 --> 05:57:36.779
Well, not anymore, tsunami thought

05:57:36.779 --> 05:57:37.439
fiercely.

05:57:37.500 --> 05:57:39.959
Even Queen Coral would have to believe

05:57:39.959 --> 05:57:40.619
the truth.

05:57:40.680 --> 05:57:43.200
Once she saw the statue as it was now

05:57:43.200 --> 05:57:47.580
Marble Orca, once serene and regal on her

05:57:47.580 --> 05:57:50.099
pedestal, was trapped by the spear in

05:57:50.099 --> 05:57:50.880
battle position.

05:57:50.939 --> 05:57:54.299
Her claws reached out hungrily, and a

05:57:54.299 --> 05:57:55.740
snarl transfigured her face.

05:57:55.799 --> 05:57:58.860
Coral would know for certain that this

05:57:58.860 --> 05:58:00.599
was the killer who had been hiding in her

05:58:00.599 --> 05:58:01.680
hatchery all these years.

05:58:01.740 --> 05:58:06.180
Now the question was, who had enchanted

05:58:06.180 --> 05:58:06.360
it?

05:58:06.419 --> 05:58:09.599
An animus dragon of course, but it

05:58:09.599 --> 05:58:11.759
couldn't be anemone, who hadn't hatched

05:58:11.759 --> 05:58:13.319
yet when the princess murders began.

05:58:13.380 --> 05:58:15.599
Tsunami had a new theory.

05:58:15.659 --> 05:58:18.840
Animus power runs in the royal family.

05:58:18.900 --> 05:58:22.020
But if shark or moray had this kind of

05:58:22.020 --> 05:58:24.180
power, they would be using it for so much

05:58:24.180 --> 05:58:24.479
more.

05:58:24.540 --> 05:58:27.240
They would use it to fight battles, to

05:58:27.240 --> 05:58:29.700
win the queen's favor, to be the secret

05:58:29.700 --> 05:58:31.740
weapon she wanted so badly.

05:58:31.799 --> 05:58:34.439
If Shark's goal was the throne for his

05:58:34.439 --> 05:58:36.840
daughter, he'd have used his magic to get

05:58:36.840 --> 05:58:39.240
rid of Coral herself instead of knocking

05:58:39.240 --> 05:58:40.259
off her dragonettes.

05:58:40.319 --> 05:58:43.860
And if the animus was Moray, she'd have

05:58:43.860 --> 05:58:45.840
offered her power to the queen long ago

05:58:45.840 --> 05:58:48.180
for coral to use however she wanted.

05:58:48.240 --> 05:58:52.200
No, it was another royal dragon.

05:58:52.259 --> 05:58:53.759
Tsunami was sure of it.

05:58:53.819 --> 05:58:56.639
She stepped back into the room, leaving

05:58:56.639 --> 05:58:57.360
the door open.

05:58:57.419 --> 05:58:59.819
She remembered Coral's words.

05:58:59.880 --> 05:59:03.299
My 1st daughter was a very talented

05:59:03.299 --> 05:59:03.840
sculptor.

05:59:03.900 --> 05:59:06.900
Tsunami settled the newly hatched

05:59:06.900 --> 05:59:09.419
dragonette around her neck, wincing at

05:59:09.419 --> 05:59:10.380
the pain from her gills.

05:59:10.439 --> 05:59:13.860
Orca may have died years ago.

05:59:13.919 --> 05:59:16.200
But she left a deadly gift behind.

05:59:16.259 --> 05:59:20.099
Carefully, she stepped over the nests and

05:59:20.099 --> 05:59:23.099
stared into the statue's face, empty

05:59:23.099 --> 05:59:24.599
lifeless.

05:59:24.720 --> 05:59:26.459
Just a statue now.

05:59:26.580 --> 05:59:29.459
A statue that she and Coral would be

05:59:29.459 --> 05:59:33.419
happy to smash and smash and smash until

05:59:33.419 --> 05:59:35.279
it became a 1000000 of the smallest

05:59:35.279 --> 05:59:37.020
pieces of rock in the ocean.

05:59:37.080 --> 05:59:40.200
Orca's weapon would never assassinate

05:59:40.200 --> 05:59:42.540
another dragonette or crush another egg.

05:59:42.659 --> 05:59:45.360
Its killing days were over.

05:59:45.419 --> 05:59:50.099
Chapter 24.

05:59:50.340 --> 05:59:53.819
Bright morning light filtered through the

05:59:53.819 --> 05:59:56.880
canopy, casting puddles of green sunshine

05:59:56.880 --> 05:59:58.740
all across the Summer Palace.

05:59:58.799 --> 06:00:01.500
Tsunami opened and closed her wings

06:00:01.500 --> 06:00:03.299
grateful that she didn't have to be at

06:00:03.299 --> 06:00:04.919
the council meeting with a blister that

06:00:04.919 --> 06:00:05.759
was going on overhead.

06:00:05.819 --> 06:00:08.759
After last night's battle in the hatchery

06:00:08.759 --> 06:00:11.340
Tsunami just wanted a break from scheming

06:00:11.340 --> 06:00:13.380
Dragon Queens and war plans for a little

06:00:13.380 --> 06:00:13.619
while.

06:00:13.680 --> 06:00:16.740
The little emerald green dragonette

06:00:16.740 --> 06:00:19.380
romped on the beach, kicking up sand and

06:00:19.380 --> 06:00:21.119
stopping in surprise when it drifted into

06:00:21.119 --> 06:00:23.520
her nose, she sneezed hard enough to

06:00:23.520 --> 06:00:25.860
knock herself backward, then sat up and

06:00:25.860 --> 06:00:27.659
gave tsunami an indignant look.

06:00:27.720 --> 06:00:31.139
Well, stop putting sand in your nose then

06:00:31.139 --> 06:00:32.520
tsunami suggested.

06:00:32.580 --> 06:00:36.360
Her little sister shook herself, spotted

06:00:36.360 --> 06:00:38.580
a tiny crab digging in the sand, and

06:00:38.580 --> 06:00:39.119
pounced.

06:00:39.180 --> 06:00:42.000
The crab vanished into its hole, and the

06:00:42.000 --> 06:00:43.860
dragonette looked at her empty talons in

06:00:43.860 --> 06:00:44.279
confusion.

06:00:44.340 --> 06:00:46.560
What's her name?

06:00:46.619 --> 06:00:47.759
Sonny asked.

06:00:47.819 --> 06:00:50.340
She leaned into tsunami's side for a

06:00:50.340 --> 06:00:53.099
moment, and tsunami felt a fizz of relief

06:00:53.099 --> 06:00:54.000
in her chest.

06:00:54.060 --> 06:00:57.180
Sonny had forgiven her, or forgotten she

06:00:57.180 --> 06:00:58.139
was mad in the 1st place.

06:00:58.200 --> 06:01:00.479
Either one was fine with tsunami.

06:01:00.540 --> 06:01:03.479
I'm trying to think of the perfect name

06:01:03.479 --> 06:01:06.299
Tsunami said, Mother said it was up to

06:01:06.299 --> 06:01:06.479
me.

06:01:06.540 --> 06:01:09.180
The dragonette glanced up from her

06:01:09.180 --> 06:01:09.540
digging.

06:01:09.599 --> 06:01:12.000
Sand covered her snout like a mustache.

06:01:12.060 --> 06:01:15.419
Maybe you should call her walrus.

06:01:15.479 --> 06:01:17.880
Glory offered, dissolving in giggles.

06:01:17.939 --> 06:01:19.979
She's not a walrus.

06:01:20.040 --> 06:01:21.119
Tsunami said.

06:01:21.180 --> 06:01:22.919
She's much more dignified than that.

06:01:22.979 --> 06:01:25.860
The dragonette jumped at an insect in the

06:01:25.860 --> 06:01:28.560
air, lost her balance, and landed with

06:01:28.560 --> 06:01:30.000
her head in the sand and her tail

06:01:30.000 --> 06:01:30.900
sticking straight up.

06:01:30.959 --> 06:01:33.840
She flailed her wings furiously until

06:01:33.840 --> 06:01:35.459
Sonny gently lifted her free.

06:01:35.520 --> 06:01:39.720
Very, glory said, very dignified.

06:01:39.779 --> 06:01:44.220
She's awfully cute, Clay said, I think

06:01:44.220 --> 06:01:46.020
she has your snout, tsunami.

06:01:46.139 --> 06:01:49.259
Tsunami flicked her tail, pleased.

06:01:49.319 --> 06:01:51.659
She looked around proudly and noticed

06:01:51.659 --> 06:01:53.459
that Starflight was sitting a short way

06:01:53.459 --> 06:01:55.259
from the rest of them.

06:01:55.319 --> 06:01:57.060
He was staring up at the pavilion with an

06:01:57.060 --> 06:01:59.639
anxious expression, running sand through

06:01:59.639 --> 06:02:00.299
his claws.

06:02:00.360 --> 06:02:02.700
Glory followed her gaze.

06:02:03.000 --> 06:02:04.740
She leaned over and poked the night wing

06:02:04.740 --> 06:02:05.580
sharply in the ribs.

06:02:05.639 --> 06:02:07.799
What's going on with you?

06:02:07.860 --> 06:02:09.119
Glory demanded.

06:02:09.180 --> 06:02:11.759
Why are you crawling around licking

06:02:11.759 --> 06:02:12.779
blisters talons?

06:02:12.900 --> 06:02:15.599
I'm not, he protested.

06:02:15.659 --> 06:02:18.540
You really are, tsunami said.

06:02:18.599 --> 06:02:20.400
Starflight wouldn't meet their eyes.

06:02:20.459 --> 06:02:24.299
I just think she'd be a good queen, he

06:02:24.299 --> 06:02:24.840
mumbled.

06:02:24.900 --> 06:02:27.599
No, you don't, Glory said.

06:02:27.659 --> 06:02:29.159
Back under the mountain.

06:02:29.220 --> 06:02:31.439
You specifically said she was kind of

06:02:31.439 --> 06:02:34.259
evil and probably had sinister plans for

06:02:34.259 --> 06:02:35.099
all of Pyria.

06:02:35.159 --> 06:02:39.659
Oh, you did say that, Clay agreed.

06:02:39.720 --> 06:02:41.700
He poked a hole in the sand for the

06:02:41.700 --> 06:02:42.720
dragonette to climb into.

06:02:42.779 --> 06:02:44.580
I remember that.

06:02:44.639 --> 06:02:47.459
Starflight flashed him an annoyed look.

06:02:47.520 --> 06:02:49.500
That, you remember?

06:02:49.560 --> 06:02:54.180
So why do you suddenly love her so much?

06:02:54.299 --> 06:02:55.680
Tsunami asked.

06:02:55.740 --> 06:02:57.840
Her little sister rolled into the hole

06:02:57.840 --> 06:03:00.119
and then jumped back out, flapping her

06:03:00.119 --> 06:03:01.319
wings to shake off the sand.

06:03:01.380 --> 06:03:05.639
Blisters smart, Starflight stammered.

06:03:05.700 --> 06:03:09.299
She's, uh, she's better than burn or

06:03:09.299 --> 06:03:09.720
blaze.

06:03:09.840 --> 06:03:11.639
I don't like her.

06:03:11.759 --> 06:03:14.580
Sonny said to tsunami's surprise.

06:03:14.639 --> 06:03:16.319
Really?

06:03:16.380 --> 06:03:19.259
Starflight said, his wings drooping.

06:03:19.319 --> 06:03:21.180
Sonny shook her head.

06:03:21.240 --> 06:03:24.180
She called me sweet, like that's all

06:03:24.180 --> 06:03:25.319
anyone needs to know about me.

06:03:25.439 --> 06:03:29.759
But you are sweet, Clay said, patting her

06:03:29.759 --> 06:03:29.939
head.

06:03:30.000 --> 06:03:33.119
It kind of does sum you up, tsunami

06:03:33.119 --> 06:03:33.540
agreed.

06:03:33.599 --> 06:03:36.119
Sunny scowled at both of them in a way

06:03:36.119 --> 06:03:37.680
tsunami thought was pretty cute.

06:03:37.740 --> 06:03:40.200
But I agree that I don't like her

06:03:40.200 --> 06:03:40.500
either.

06:03:40.560 --> 06:03:43.080
More than that, I don't trust her.

06:03:43.139 --> 06:03:45.240
I think we need to meet Blaze.

06:03:45.299 --> 06:03:47.220
Maybe all the stories about her

06:03:47.220 --> 06:03:48.840
brainlessness have been exaggerated.

06:03:48.900 --> 06:03:53.099
Doubtful, said Starflight glumly.

06:03:53.159 --> 06:03:55.680
So, we can go?

06:03:55.740 --> 06:03:57.720
Glory asked tsunami.

06:03:57.779 --> 06:03:59.580
And look for Blaze?

06:03:59.639 --> 06:04:01.979
You mean we're done here?

06:04:02.099 --> 06:04:05.159
Even the baby dragon stopped digging for

06:04:05.159 --> 06:04:06.659
a moment to look at tsunami.

06:04:06.720 --> 06:04:09.299
She felt a stab of guilt at the hopeful

06:04:09.299 --> 06:04:11.159
expressions on her friends' faces.

06:04:11.220 --> 06:04:13.979
Jan realized they wanted to leave the

06:04:13.979 --> 06:04:15.299
kingdom of the sea so badly.

06:04:15.360 --> 06:04:18.840
Wing beats sounded in the air above them

06:04:18.840 --> 06:04:21.180
and they all looked up to see Coral

06:04:21.180 --> 06:04:23.939
Anemone, Blister, and Moray, circling

06:04:23.939 --> 06:04:25.680
down from the Summer Palace pavilion.

06:04:25.740 --> 06:04:28.319
The green dragonette scampered up to

06:04:28.319 --> 06:04:30.240
Anemone as soon as she landed, and

06:04:30.240 --> 06:04:32.700
tackled one of her talons, and Emone

06:04:32.700 --> 06:04:33.779
laughed and flipped her over.

06:04:33.840 --> 06:04:36.299
Their little sister yelped, struggled

06:04:36.299 --> 06:04:38.400
upright again, and started clawing her

06:04:38.400 --> 06:04:39.840
way up Anemone's leg.

06:04:39.840 --> 06:04:41.819
Have you picked a name?

06:04:41.880 --> 06:04:43.799
Anemone asked tsunami?

06:04:43.860 --> 06:04:46.860
What do you think of Aucklet?

06:04:46.919 --> 06:04:48.119
Tsunami said.

06:04:48.180 --> 06:04:51.000
That's a kind of seabird.

06:04:51.060 --> 06:04:53.459
Starflight said, in his know it all voice

06:04:53.459 --> 06:04:54.000
to clay.

06:04:54.060 --> 06:04:56.400
Oh, Clay said.

06:04:56.459 --> 06:04:57.299
Cool.

06:04:57.360 --> 06:04:59.759
I mean, I knew that.

06:04:59.819 --> 06:05:02.700
Tsunami liked the look on her mother's

06:05:02.700 --> 06:05:04.380
face watching the 2 sisters.

06:05:04.439 --> 06:05:07.740
She looked proud, protective, happy for

06:05:07.740 --> 06:05:07.919
them.

06:05:08.040 --> 06:05:10.139
Tsunami was right about her.

06:05:10.200 --> 06:05:12.360
Queen Coral wouldn't kill her own

06:05:12.360 --> 06:05:14.400
daughters, even though one of them would

06:05:14.400 --> 06:05:15.959
one day grow up to take her place.

06:05:16.020 --> 06:05:17.819
She cared about them.

06:05:17.880 --> 06:05:21.060
Perhaps a little too much, but tsunami

06:05:21.060 --> 06:05:22.680
thought that was better than not caring

06:05:22.680 --> 06:05:22.860
at all.

06:05:22.919 --> 06:05:26.459
She wondered if blister or burn had any

06:05:26.459 --> 06:05:27.180
dragonettes.

06:05:27.240 --> 06:05:28.500
Starflight would know.

06:05:28.560 --> 06:05:30.599
It must be in the scrolls somewhere.

06:05:30.659 --> 06:05:33.240
Tsunami had a feeling blister would

06:05:33.240 --> 06:05:35.159
happily kill off her own dragonettes if

06:05:35.159 --> 06:05:35.939
she thought it was necessary.

06:05:36.000 --> 06:05:38.880
Those glittering black eyes hid more

06:05:38.880 --> 06:05:41.520
secrets and plans than tsunami wanted to

06:05:41.520 --> 06:05:41.880
know about.

06:05:42.000 --> 06:05:45.299
Orca's statue has been destroyed.

06:05:45.360 --> 06:05:47.520
Queen Coral said with a sigh.

06:05:47.639 --> 06:05:49.919
It was so beautiful too.

06:05:49.979 --> 06:05:51.779
She was so talented.

06:05:51.900 --> 06:05:54.959
I can't believe she hid her animus powers

06:05:54.959 --> 06:05:55.319
from me.

06:05:55.380 --> 06:05:57.779
She could have trained with Whirlpool

06:05:57.779 --> 06:05:58.080
too.

06:05:58.200 --> 06:05:59.819
Wow.

06:05:59.880 --> 06:06:02.939
She really missed out, tsunami said

06:06:02.939 --> 06:06:04.500
winking at anemone.

06:06:04.560 --> 06:06:07.080
We'll have to examine all the things she

06:06:07.080 --> 06:06:10.259
carved, coral mused, just to make sure

06:06:10.259 --> 06:06:12.060
there aren't any other enchantments

06:06:12.060 --> 06:06:12.959
lurking around.

06:06:13.020 --> 06:06:16.680
We are sure it was Orca, right?

06:06:16.740 --> 06:06:17.880
Tsunami asked.

06:06:17.939 --> 06:06:20.220
No one else in the palace could be an

06:06:20.220 --> 06:06:20.639
animus.

06:06:20.700 --> 06:06:23.159
She wasn't able to stop herself from

06:06:23.159 --> 06:06:25.319
glancing at Moray, who glared back.

06:06:25.380 --> 06:06:28.919
Coral shook her head. before we destroyed

06:06:28.919 --> 06:06:29.159
it.

06:06:29.220 --> 06:06:32.700
Anemone reanimated the statue and made it

06:06:32.700 --> 06:06:34.139
reveal who had enchanted it.

06:06:34.200 --> 06:06:37.319
It said Orca, plain as day.

06:06:37.380 --> 06:06:39.419
She sighed again.

06:06:39.479 --> 06:06:43.259
Orca carved that statue, and dedicated it

06:06:43.259 --> 06:06:44.939
to the hatchery shortly before she

06:06:44.939 --> 06:06:45.720
challenged me.

06:06:45.779 --> 06:06:49.500
I gather she expected to win, so she was

06:06:49.500 --> 06:06:51.119
setting up a way to get rid of her

06:06:51.119 --> 06:06:52.860
possible airs and challengers.

06:06:52.979 --> 06:06:57.840
That explains her last words to you, Moray

06:06:57.840 --> 06:06:58.439
hissed.

06:06:58.500 --> 06:07:01.439
Yes, said Carl sadly.

06:07:01.500 --> 06:07:04.619
She said, I did this all wrong.

06:07:04.740 --> 06:07:07.680
You're going to rule forever, aren't you

06:07:07.680 --> 06:07:07.860
Mother?

06:07:07.979 --> 06:07:09.419
You should thank me.

06:07:09.479 --> 06:07:11.340
No one can stop you now.

06:07:11.400 --> 06:07:14.700
The queen looked down at anemone and

06:07:14.700 --> 06:07:16.439
Aucklet, playing in the sand.

06:07:16.500 --> 06:07:19.319
She stroked Anemone's head with a wistful

06:07:19.319 --> 06:07:19.799
expression.

06:07:19.860 --> 06:07:23.700
But, Clay said hesitantly.

06:07:23.759 --> 06:07:27.900
But if Orca was the assassin, then who

06:07:27.900 --> 06:07:29.700
attacked tsunami in the tunnel?

06:07:29.700 --> 06:07:33.240
Queen Coral shrugged, We'll catch them

06:07:33.240 --> 06:07:34.680
eventually, she said.

06:07:34.740 --> 06:07:36.479
That's how stories work.

06:07:36.540 --> 06:07:40.200
Anemone gave tsunami a frustrated look.

06:07:40.259 --> 06:07:43.139
Tsunami still thought that her attacker

06:07:43.139 --> 06:07:44.099
might have been shark.

06:07:44.159 --> 06:07:47.340
He was already out of prison, patrolling

06:07:47.340 --> 06:07:49.080
the summer palace with a bad tempered

06:07:49.080 --> 06:07:51.360
expression on his snout, and he certainly

06:07:51.360 --> 06:07:53.759
hadn't been pleased or supportive when

06:07:53.759 --> 06:07:55.560
she staggered out of the hatchery with a

06:07:55.560 --> 06:07:57.479
dragonette, blood pouring from her

06:07:57.479 --> 06:07:57.840
gills.

06:07:57.900 --> 06:08:00.900
She reached up and touched the seaweed

06:08:00.900 --> 06:08:01.680
bandage on her neck.

06:08:01.740 --> 06:08:04.799
Her ribs ached whenever she moved too.

06:08:04.860 --> 06:08:07.860
But the healers said she just had to rest

06:08:07.860 --> 06:08:09.959
and let the fractures fix themselves.

06:08:10.020 --> 06:08:12.180
Rest?

06:08:12.240 --> 06:08:14.520
The dragonettes of destiny have no time

06:08:14.520 --> 06:08:15.419
for rest?

06:08:15.479 --> 06:08:16.560
she thought ruefully.

06:08:16.619 --> 06:08:19.619
Now that we know the real assassin

06:08:19.619 --> 06:08:22.500
tsunami reminded Coral, you promise to

06:08:22.500 --> 06:08:23.520
set riptide free.

06:08:23.580 --> 06:08:28.439
I know I did, said the queen, but I'm not

06:08:28.439 --> 06:08:29.819
quite sure what to do with him.

06:08:29.880 --> 06:08:32.700
Clearly he can't stay in my kingdom.

06:08:32.759 --> 06:08:35.279
He'll have to crawl back to those talons

06:08:35.279 --> 06:08:37.259
of peace and see if they'll take him.

06:08:37.319 --> 06:08:41.340
Maybe he can come with us, tsunami said

06:08:41.340 --> 06:08:43.799
then snapped her mouth shut, but it was

06:08:43.799 --> 06:08:44.099
too late.

06:08:44.159 --> 06:08:47.220
Coral and blister were both staring at

06:08:47.220 --> 06:08:49.020
her in a very uncomfortable way.

06:08:49.080 --> 06:08:53.040
With you, Coral said slowly.

06:08:53.099 --> 06:08:55.439
Are you going somewhere?

06:08:55.500 --> 06:09:02.759
We, I, yes, I think we should, tsunami

06:09:02.759 --> 06:09:03.060
said.

06:09:03.180 --> 06:09:05.819
She felt her friend shifting closer

06:09:05.819 --> 06:09:06.540
together behind her.

06:09:06.599 --> 06:09:09.240
I don't belong here, mother.

06:09:09.299 --> 06:09:13.080
I wanted to, but I'm only causing trouble

06:09:13.080 --> 06:09:15.180
and I'm not doing what I was hatched to

06:09:15.180 --> 06:09:15.360
do.

06:09:15.419 --> 06:09:18.000
I don't speak the underwater language.

06:09:18.060 --> 06:09:20.040
I don't understand the council.

06:09:20.099 --> 06:09:22.560
You have 2 daughters now who could be

06:09:22.560 --> 06:09:23.639
great queens one day.

06:09:23.700 --> 06:09:26.040
She nodded at anemone.

06:09:26.040 --> 06:09:28.439
But my destiny is somewhere else.

06:09:28.500 --> 06:09:30.180
I have to go stop the war.

06:09:30.240 --> 06:09:32.279
With my friends.

06:09:32.400 --> 06:09:36.060
And how do you plan to do that?

06:09:36.119 --> 06:09:37.979
Blister said softly.

06:09:38.040 --> 06:09:41.099
I don't know, Tsunami said.

06:09:41.159 --> 06:09:42.479
We'll figure it out.

06:09:42.540 --> 06:09:46.560
We were thinking we should go meet

06:09:46.560 --> 06:09:47.220
Blaze.

06:09:47.279 --> 06:09:49.979
Clay suggested, just to be fair.

06:09:50.040 --> 06:09:53.520
Acc, clay, shut up.

06:09:53.580 --> 06:09:55.380
Tsunami thought with a wince.

06:09:55.439 --> 06:09:59.159
But it won't change how we, I mean, that

06:09:59.159 --> 06:10:01.740
we think your Starflight said hurriedly

06:10:01.740 --> 06:10:03.779
to blister, then trailed off under

06:10:03.779 --> 06:10:05.220
tsunami's baleful look.

06:10:05.340 --> 06:10:08.520
No, said Blister.

06:10:08.639 --> 06:10:11.340
The diamond patterns on her back writhed

06:10:11.340 --> 06:10:12.360
as she stepped closer.

06:10:12.419 --> 06:10:14.819
No one is leaving.

06:10:14.880 --> 06:10:17.580
You can't tell us what to do.

06:10:17.639 --> 06:10:19.020
Tsunami said.

06:10:19.080 --> 06:10:22.319
I am your choice.

06:10:22.439 --> 06:10:24.000
Blister hissed.

06:10:24.060 --> 06:10:25.319
The nah.

06:10:25.319 --> 06:10:28.020
The talons of peace want me.

06:10:28.080 --> 06:10:31.020
Oh, Glory said.

06:10:31.139 --> 06:10:32.340
Do they know that?

06:10:32.400 --> 06:10:36.060
It's not their decision anyway, tsunami

06:10:36.060 --> 06:10:36.419
said.

06:10:36.479 --> 06:10:40.500
Your lives could be very easy from here

06:10:40.500 --> 06:10:42.240
on. said blister.

06:10:42.299 --> 06:10:45.540
All you have to do is tell everyone the

06:10:45.540 --> 06:10:48.599
dragonettes of destiny have chosen me as

06:10:48.599 --> 06:10:51.659
the next sand wing queen, and you can do

06:10:51.659 --> 06:10:54.060
that from here, where I can keep an eye

06:10:54.060 --> 06:10:54.419
on you.

06:10:54.479 --> 06:10:57.840
Where you can keep us prisoner, you mean

06:10:57.840 --> 06:10:59.759
tsunami said angrily.

06:10:59.819 --> 06:11:01.919
We've had quite enough of that, thank

06:11:01.919 --> 06:11:02.159
you.

06:11:02.220 --> 06:11:04.860
Mother, tell her you wouldn't do that to

06:11:04.860 --> 06:11:04.979
me.

06:11:05.040 --> 06:11:08.159
Queen Coral gave blister an anxious

06:11:08.159 --> 06:11:08.400
look.

06:11:08.459 --> 06:11:11.700
My dear, I'm sure they will still choose

06:11:11.700 --> 06:11:13.380
you after meeting Blaise.

06:11:13.439 --> 06:11:16.139
No one would choose her in a 1000000

06:11:16.139 --> 06:11:16.259
years.

06:11:16.319 --> 06:11:18.240
Perhaps.

06:11:18.299 --> 06:11:21.360
But 1st they have to survive that long

06:11:21.360 --> 06:11:23.639
Blister said smoothly.

06:11:23.700 --> 06:11:26.520
You know better than anyone how dangerous

06:11:26.520 --> 06:11:28.259
it is out there, Coral.

06:11:28.319 --> 06:11:30.540
Remember what happened to Gil.

06:11:30.659 --> 06:11:33.599
We'll really be protecting the dragonette

06:11:33.599 --> 06:11:34.439
by keeping them here.

06:11:34.500 --> 06:11:38.040
Oh, that makes sense.

06:11:38.099 --> 06:11:40.619
Coral said, sounding relieved.

06:11:40.680 --> 06:11:42.779
She's right, tsunami.

06:11:42.840 --> 06:11:44.340
Just stay here and we'll take good care

06:11:44.340 --> 06:11:44.819
of all of you.

06:11:44.939 --> 06:11:47.759
Tsunami looked back at her friends.

06:11:47.819 --> 06:11:50.639
Starflight looked miserable, but the

06:11:50.639 --> 06:11:53.279
others, they looked hopeful, as if they

06:11:53.279 --> 06:11:54.659
trusted tsunami to get them out.

06:11:54.720 --> 06:11:57.720
This isn't the right place for my friends

06:11:57.720 --> 06:11:59.700
either, tsunami said.

06:11:59.759 --> 06:12:01.319
Glory wants to go home.

06:12:01.380 --> 06:12:02.700
Right, Glory?

06:12:02.759 --> 06:12:04.619
And Sonny should find your parents.

06:12:04.680 --> 06:12:06.900
It's not fair that I get to do those

06:12:06.900 --> 06:12:08.040
things and they don't.

06:12:08.099 --> 06:12:09.779
We just.

06:12:10.439 --> 06:12:11.520
She squared her wings.

06:12:11.580 --> 06:12:13.500
We have to go.

06:12:13.560 --> 06:12:15.479
And if you try to keep us, you'll be no

06:12:15.479 --> 06:12:18.000
better than the Talons or Queen Scarlet.

06:12:18.060 --> 06:12:21.060
Blister glared at Starflight.

06:12:21.180 --> 06:12:23.880
Don't you have something to say about

06:12:23.880 --> 06:12:25.139
this Nightwing?

06:12:25.200 --> 06:12:28.020
He stared miserably at his talents and

06:12:28.020 --> 06:12:28.860
didn't respond.

06:12:28.919 --> 06:12:31.919
She hissed, Useless.

06:12:32.040 --> 06:12:35.099
There is something wrong with all of you

06:12:35.099 --> 06:12:35.520
isn't there?

06:12:35.580 --> 06:12:39.060
But you're the dragonets I have, and I'm

06:12:39.060 --> 06:12:39.779
not letting you go.

06:12:39.840 --> 06:12:42.240
Blister turned to Coral.

06:12:42.299 --> 06:12:44.340
Throw them in your prison.

06:12:44.459 --> 06:12:47.700
She wouldn't do that, tsunami said.

06:12:47.759 --> 06:12:48.840
Mother?

06:12:48.900 --> 06:12:49.919
Right?

06:12:49.979 --> 06:12:51.900
You wouldn't do that.

06:12:51.959 --> 06:12:55.200
It might help your decision.

06:12:55.259 --> 06:12:56.759
Blister hissed.

06:12:56.819 --> 06:12:59.759
If you knew exactly who killed your

06:12:59.759 --> 06:13:01.740
husband in the Sky Wing arena.

06:13:01.799 --> 06:13:05.459
Tsunami felt her scales turn to ice.

06:13:05.520 --> 06:13:07.259
This was it.

06:13:07.319 --> 06:13:10.139
The moment her secrets came out, and she

06:13:10.139 --> 06:13:11.220
got what she deserved.

06:13:11.279 --> 06:13:14.099
Coral's gills flared and her eyes

06:13:14.099 --> 06:13:14.819
widened.

06:13:14.880 --> 06:13:16.799
What are you saying?

06:13:16.919 --> 06:13:21.599
You know he died in the arena, Blister

06:13:21.599 --> 06:13:22.080
said.

06:13:22.139 --> 06:13:25.139
But do you know who his opponent was?

06:13:25.259 --> 06:13:28.560
The dragon who ripped the life out of

06:13:28.560 --> 06:13:28.740
him.

06:13:28.860 --> 06:13:33.180
Maybe you should also know, Starflight

06:13:33.180 --> 06:13:33.900
said suddenly.

06:13:33.959 --> 06:13:36.720
That blister killed Kestrel and is lying

06:13:36.720 --> 06:13:37.200
to about it.

06:13:37.259 --> 06:13:39.959
And that she wants Webbs dead for her own

06:13:39.959 --> 06:13:41.580
reasons and doesn't care about your

06:13:41.580 --> 06:13:42.419
daughters at all.

06:13:42.479 --> 06:13:46.319
Blister arched her neck like a cobra and

06:13:46.319 --> 06:13:46.979
hissed at him.

06:13:47.040 --> 06:13:50.099
Starflight threw his wings over his head

06:13:50.099 --> 06:13:52.139
as if he expected her tail to come

06:13:52.139 --> 06:13:54.599
stabbing down, but all she said was

06:13:54.599 --> 06:13:58.380
you'll be sorry for that, useless night

06:13:58.380 --> 06:13:58.860
wing.

06:13:58.979 --> 06:14:02.340
Coral wrapped her wings around anemone

06:14:02.340 --> 06:14:04.439
and Aucklet, and took a step back toward

06:14:04.439 --> 06:14:04.860
the water.

06:14:04.919 --> 06:14:08.040
She looked from blister to tsunami, like

06:14:08.040 --> 06:14:09.659
she wasn't sure who to trust anymore.

06:14:09.720 --> 06:14:14.459
Don't listen to them, Coral, Blister

06:14:14.459 --> 06:14:14.880
said.

06:14:14.939 --> 06:14:18.180
They're only dragonettes, and dragonettes

06:14:18.180 --> 06:14:19.740
never know what's best for them.

06:14:19.860 --> 06:14:23.400
I think we can be pretty sure prison

06:14:23.400 --> 06:14:25.080
isn't at the top of the list, though

06:14:25.080 --> 06:14:28.619
tsunami snapped, and from now on, blister

06:14:28.619 --> 06:14:31.080
you show some respect, and address my

06:14:31.080 --> 06:14:32.400
mother as queen coral.

06:14:32.459 --> 06:14:36.060
Smoke curled from blisters, snout.

06:14:36.180 --> 06:14:38.580
Tsunami wondered what coral would do if

06:14:38.580 --> 06:14:40.680
the sand wing attacked the dragonettes of

06:14:40.680 --> 06:14:41.700
destiny right in front of her.

06:14:41.759 --> 06:14:45.959
I don't know what's going on, Coral said

06:14:45.959 --> 06:14:48.720
signaling with her tail, a platoon of sea

06:14:48.720 --> 06:14:50.099
wing guards appeared from one of the

06:14:50.099 --> 06:14:53.220
caves, but for your own safety tsunami.

06:14:53.279 --> 06:14:54.779
You're staying here for now.

06:14:54.840 --> 06:14:57.720
Mother, Tsunami yelled.

06:14:57.779 --> 06:14:59.759
She smacked a guard in the snout with her

06:14:59.759 --> 06:15:01.319
tail and bared her teeth at another.

06:15:01.439 --> 06:15:03.599
Think for yourself for once.

06:15:03.659 --> 06:15:04.500
Let us go.

06:15:04.619 --> 06:15:08.520
The Queen Coral turned away, avoiding

06:15:08.520 --> 06:15:09.959
blisters gaze as well.

06:15:10.020 --> 06:15:12.720
She curled Aucklet into one of her talons

06:15:12.720 --> 06:15:14.700
and flew back to the pavilion with her

06:15:14.700 --> 06:15:15.060
daughters.

06:15:15.119 --> 06:15:18.659
Tsunami fought the guards, but there were

06:15:18.659 --> 06:15:20.939
too many of them, and her ribs were still

06:15:20.939 --> 06:15:22.500
screaming with pain from the night

06:15:22.500 --> 06:15:22.799
before.

06:15:22.860 --> 06:15:26.580
One by one, each of the dragonettes was

06:15:26.580 --> 06:15:28.439
overpowered and dragged off to the same

06:15:28.439 --> 06:15:31.380
prison cave where riptide and webs had

06:15:31.380 --> 06:15:32.340
disappeared the day before.

06:15:32.400 --> 06:15:35.700
Seawings watched from all over the

06:15:35.700 --> 06:15:36.360
pavilion.

06:15:36.479 --> 06:15:39.360
Tsunami had never been so humiliated.

06:15:39.419 --> 06:15:42.479
Some dragonettes of destiny they were

06:15:42.479 --> 06:15:44.759
tossed around like lumps of treasure to

06:15:44.759 --> 06:15:45.240
be hoarded.

06:15:45.299 --> 06:15:47.939
They'd come to the kingdom of the sea

06:15:47.939 --> 06:15:51.360
looking for safety, and instead, they

06:15:51.360 --> 06:15:52.560
were prisoners once again.

06:15:52.619 --> 06:15:56.220
Chapter 25.

06:15:56.340 --> 06:15:59.819
The prison cave was high on the cliff

06:15:59.819 --> 06:16:03.119
wall, not far from the canopy, overlooking

06:16:03.119 --> 06:16:04.080
the pavilion below.

06:16:04.139 --> 06:16:06.779
Tsunami hadn't paid much attention to it

06:16:06.779 --> 06:16:09.900
before, except to notice that riptide and

06:16:09.900 --> 06:16:11.580
webs had been taken there.

06:16:11.639 --> 06:16:13.619
But as the guards flew them up to the

06:16:13.619 --> 06:16:16.500
cave, she realized that it glowed with a

06:16:16.500 --> 06:16:18.599
weird blue light, and she could hear

06:16:18.599 --> 06:16:20.639
strange crackling sounds coming from

06:16:20.639 --> 06:16:20.939
inside.

06:16:21.060 --> 06:16:24.900
Sharp spears prodded her into the cave

06:16:24.900 --> 06:16:27.659
entrance, and she felt damp stone under

06:16:27.659 --> 06:16:28.319
her claws.

06:16:28.380 --> 06:16:31.680
As her eyes adjusted to the dim light, she

06:16:31.680 --> 06:16:33.959
saw a path winding into the huge cavern

06:16:33.959 --> 06:16:34.619
ahead of them.

06:16:34.680 --> 06:16:38.459
This wasn't the underwater prison, lagoon

06:16:38.459 --> 06:16:39.419
and shark had been sent to.

06:16:39.479 --> 06:16:42.419
This was where Queen Coral kept the real

06:16:42.419 --> 06:16:46.200
threats, including Tsunami realized, as

06:16:46.200 --> 06:16:47.639
she was shoved along the stone floor

06:16:47.700 --> 06:16:50.040
several prisoners of war.

06:16:50.099 --> 06:16:53.580
She saw at least 3 Sky Wings, hissing

06:16:53.580 --> 06:16:55.740
short blasts of flame at their captors.

06:16:55.799 --> 06:16:58.619
An ice wing lay with his wings spread out

06:16:58.619 --> 06:17:01.259
gasping faintly from the heat he wasn't

06:17:01.259 --> 06:17:01.680
used to.

06:17:01.740 --> 06:17:04.439
Two sand wings were caged together.

06:17:04.500 --> 06:17:06.779
One of them curled in a ball with his

06:17:06.779 --> 06:17:09.419
eyes pressed shut, the other pacing and

06:17:09.419 --> 06:17:09.959
snarling.

06:17:10.080 --> 06:17:13.500
There was even a giant mud wing with

06:17:13.500 --> 06:17:15.720
chains around her ankles, like the ones

06:17:15.720 --> 06:17:17.040
that had been on clay.

06:17:17.099 --> 06:17:20.159
She tilted her head curiously at clay as

06:17:20.159 --> 06:17:20.759
he went by.

06:17:20.819 --> 06:17:23.819
But the strangest thing about the prison

06:17:23.819 --> 06:17:26.880
wasn't the dragon prisoners, or even the

06:17:26.880 --> 06:17:29.099
staggeringly large size of the cavern.

06:17:29.159 --> 06:17:31.619
It was the cages.

06:17:31.680 --> 06:17:34.799
There were no bars, no doors.

06:17:34.860 --> 06:17:38.880
Instead, a channel of water as wide as 2

06:17:38.880 --> 06:17:41.819
dragons encircled each prisoner, trapping

06:17:41.819 --> 06:17:44.400
them on islands of stone, some large

06:17:44.400 --> 06:17:47.159
enough from multiple dragons, some with

06:17:47.159 --> 06:17:48.180
barely room for one.

06:17:48.240 --> 06:17:51.240
More water poured from grooves in the

06:17:51.240 --> 06:17:53.759
ceiling down to the channels, creating

06:17:53.759 --> 06:17:55.919
cascading walls around the islands.

06:17:55.979 --> 06:17:59.340
And all the water walls, and all the

06:17:59.340 --> 06:18:02.580
moats glowed the same bright blue, and

06:18:02.580 --> 06:18:04.680
gave off the same fizzing, crackling

06:18:04.680 --> 06:18:04.919
sound.

06:18:04.979 --> 06:18:08.340
The imprisoned dragons flinched away from

06:18:08.340 --> 06:18:10.740
any stray droplets that splashed toward

06:18:10.740 --> 06:18:13.020
them, and they kept their tails carefully

06:18:13.020 --> 06:18:14.520
tucked up on dry land.

06:18:14.639 --> 06:18:17.759
The path wound around and between the

06:18:17.759 --> 06:18:19.020
islands like a long bridge.

06:18:19.080 --> 06:18:22.200
The ceiling above was covered in glow

06:18:22.200 --> 06:18:24.900
worms, casting an eerie light over all

06:18:24.900 --> 06:18:26.340
the strange prison cells.

06:18:26.400 --> 06:18:29.400
Tsunami twisted to peer into the moats.

06:18:29.520 --> 06:18:31.979
What were the prisoners so afraid of?

06:18:32.040 --> 06:18:35.819
Iridescent purple jellyfish pulsed here

06:18:35.819 --> 06:18:38.220
and there, adding their light to the glow

06:18:38.220 --> 06:18:39.000
worms up above.

06:18:39.060 --> 06:18:41.819
Tsunami knew that their tentacles could

06:18:41.819 --> 06:18:44.279
sting, but surely not badly enough to

06:18:44.279 --> 06:18:47.939
keep the prisoners in, if it were her, and

06:18:47.939 --> 06:18:51.419
soon it will be, she thought, she'd leap

06:18:51.419 --> 06:18:53.400
right through the water wall, splash

06:18:53.400 --> 06:18:55.020
through the moat, and fight her way out

06:18:55.020 --> 06:18:57.419
no matter how many jellyfish were in her

06:18:57.419 --> 06:18:57.599
way.

06:18:57.659 --> 06:19:01.139
Suddenly, she caught sight of a dark

06:19:01.139 --> 06:19:03.000
green shape swimming in one of the

06:19:03.000 --> 06:19:03.419
channels.

06:19:03.479 --> 06:19:07.259
It was as long as a scavenger, and as

06:19:07.259 --> 06:19:09.720
thick around as a dragon tail, with no

06:19:09.720 --> 06:19:12.060
legs or arms or wings.

06:19:12.119 --> 06:19:14.340
As she squinted at it, another one

06:19:14.340 --> 06:19:16.919
surfaced not far away, and she caught a

06:19:16.919 --> 06:19:19.500
glimpse of a flat head, with sunken dead

06:19:19.500 --> 06:19:19.979
eyes.

06:19:20.040 --> 06:19:23.580
Nostrils flared at the end of its snout

06:19:23.580 --> 06:19:25.080
and then it sank into the water again.

06:19:25.139 --> 06:19:28.380
Bubbles fizzed and snapped for a long

06:19:28.380 --> 06:19:29.880
moment where it had been.

06:19:29.939 --> 06:19:33.060
Sonny pressed close against clay.

06:19:33.119 --> 06:19:35.939
Her gray green eyes enormous and

06:19:35.939 --> 06:19:36.540
terrified.

06:19:36.599 --> 06:19:39.900
Tsunami glanced around at Starflight and

06:19:39.900 --> 06:19:41.520
saw him studying the cages as well.

06:19:41.580 --> 06:19:43.860
Maybe he would understand what was going

06:19:43.860 --> 06:19:44.099
on.

06:19:44.159 --> 06:19:48.299
She didn't spot webs or riptide, but the

06:19:48.299 --> 06:19:50.880
dragonettes were pushed along so fast, and

06:19:50.880 --> 06:19:52.619
the water blurred the features of the

06:19:52.619 --> 06:19:54.900
prisoners, so it was hard to distinguish

06:19:54.900 --> 06:19:57.000
between the few imprisoned sea wings she

06:19:57.000 --> 06:19:57.419
could see.

06:19:57.479 --> 06:20:00.779
The guards finally stopped at one of the

06:20:00.779 --> 06:20:02.159
largest prison islands.

06:20:02.220 --> 06:20:05.340
There was the same moat around it, but no

06:20:05.340 --> 06:20:06.659
water came from the ceiling here.

06:20:06.720 --> 06:20:09.240
Tsunami couldn't see anything swimming in

06:20:09.240 --> 06:20:09.900
the moat either.

06:20:09.959 --> 06:20:13.380
Hop over, growled one of the guards.

06:20:13.439 --> 06:20:14.279
All of you.

06:20:14.340 --> 06:20:16.200
What if we don't?

06:20:16.319 --> 06:20:17.400
Tsunami asked.

06:20:17.459 --> 06:20:19.619
Then you'll be dragged off to separate

06:20:19.619 --> 06:20:22.319
cages instead of getting to share one, he

06:20:22.319 --> 06:20:22.680
answered.

06:20:22.740 --> 06:20:26.159
Clay jumped over the moat immediately, his

06:20:26.159 --> 06:20:27.959
talons scraped against the hard rock

06:20:27.959 --> 06:20:29.819
floor as he landed with a heavy thud.

06:20:29.880 --> 06:20:32.340
He turned and reached out to catch Sonny

06:20:32.340 --> 06:20:33.299
as she leaped after him.

06:20:33.360 --> 06:20:36.840
Starflight followed, and then glory, and

06:20:36.840 --> 06:20:39.840
finally, reluctantly, tsunami flapped her

06:20:39.840 --> 06:20:41.819
wings to lift herself over the chasm and

06:20:41.819 --> 06:20:42.779
land beside her friends.

06:20:42.840 --> 06:20:46.259
Another guard pulled on a chain that hung

06:20:46.259 --> 06:20:46.979
along the wall.

06:20:47.040 --> 06:20:49.560
Something clanked and groaned from within

06:20:49.560 --> 06:20:52.259
the stone, as she drew the links through

06:20:52.259 --> 06:20:52.860
her claws.

06:20:52.919 --> 06:20:55.979
Tsunami leaned forward and saw a small

06:20:55.979 --> 06:20:57.959
door opening in the underwater wall of

06:20:57.959 --> 06:20:58.380
the moat.

06:20:58.500 --> 06:21:01.319
Three of the thick green creatures

06:21:01.319 --> 06:21:03.479
wriggled through it, their dead eyes

06:21:03.479 --> 06:21:04.860
staring creepily up at her.

06:21:04.919 --> 06:21:09.119
A whoosh sounded from above, and talons

06:21:09.119 --> 06:21:11.159
yanked her back from the edge just as

06:21:11.159 --> 06:21:12.419
water came sluicing down.

06:21:12.479 --> 06:21:15.779
Tsunami looked up at the cave roof, then

06:21:15.779 --> 06:21:17.639
around to see that it was Starflight who

06:21:17.639 --> 06:21:18.540
had pulled her back.

06:21:18.540 --> 06:21:21.360
He let her go, and twisted to watch the

06:21:21.360 --> 06:21:22.979
waterfall that now surrounded them.

06:21:23.040 --> 06:21:25.740
His claws tapped nervously against one

06:21:25.740 --> 06:21:26.099
another.

06:21:26.159 --> 06:21:29.099
What are those creepy things in the

06:21:29.099 --> 06:21:29.400
water?

06:21:29.459 --> 06:21:30.959
Tsunami asked him.

06:21:31.020 --> 06:21:35.939
I think, I think they're electric eels, he

06:21:35.939 --> 06:21:36.180
said.

06:21:36.240 --> 06:21:42.000
Oh, Glory said, shaking out her wings as

06:21:42.000 --> 06:21:43.139
if they were covered in bugs.

06:21:43.200 --> 06:21:46.020
The scrolls about them gave me nightmares

06:21:46.020 --> 06:21:46.380
for months.

06:21:46.439 --> 06:21:49.680
Sonny twined her tail around one of

06:21:49.680 --> 06:21:52.080
Clay's forelegs as if she was trying to

06:21:52.080 --> 06:21:53.400
get even closer to him.

06:21:53.459 --> 06:21:55.680
What's an electric eel?

06:21:55.680 --> 06:21:56.700
she asked.

06:21:56.759 --> 06:21:59.819
They give off a kind of shock.

06:21:59.880 --> 06:22:01.560
Starflight explained.

06:22:01.619 --> 06:22:05.040
Behind him, a blue fizzing light sparked

06:22:05.040 --> 06:22:06.659
up the waterfall and vanished again

06:22:06.659 --> 06:22:07.860
making them all jump.

06:22:07.919 --> 06:22:11.220
It would feel like getting hit by

06:22:11.220 --> 06:22:11.700
lightning.

06:22:11.759 --> 06:22:12.900
Glory added.

06:22:12.959 --> 06:22:15.720
And it can be strong enough to kill a

06:22:15.720 --> 06:22:18.599
dragon. said Starflight, especially in

06:22:18.599 --> 06:22:20.880
salt water, and when the eels are as big

06:22:20.880 --> 06:22:21.720
as the ones down there.

06:22:21.779 --> 06:22:26.340
So all this water around us, tsunami

06:22:26.340 --> 06:22:26.819
started.

06:22:26.880 --> 06:22:29.880
Could be charged with deadly force at any

06:22:29.880 --> 06:22:31.860
time, Starflight said.

06:22:31.919 --> 06:22:33.240
Not all the time.

06:22:33.299 --> 06:22:36.180
It's not a constant current, but if

06:22:36.180 --> 06:22:38.279
they're mad or hungry, they're probably

06:22:38.279 --> 06:22:40.799
giving off shocks pretty frequently, and

06:22:40.799 --> 06:22:42.599
then just touching the water could

06:22:42.599 --> 06:22:45.119
transfer that to you, even if it only

06:22:45.119 --> 06:22:45.720
stunned you.

06:22:45.779 --> 06:22:47.220
It would hurt a lot.

06:22:47.279 --> 06:22:50.040
Tsunami frowned at the cascade.

06:22:50.099 --> 06:22:52.500
Through it, she could see the blurry

06:22:52.500 --> 06:22:54.779
outline of the guards slithering away.

06:22:54.840 --> 06:22:57.659
Evidently, they trusted their nasty

06:22:57.659 --> 06:22:59.700
prison setup to keep the dragonets in.

06:22:59.759 --> 06:23:03.299
I can't believe we're prisoners again.

06:23:03.419 --> 06:23:05.520
Clay said with a sigh.

06:23:05.639 --> 06:23:08.099
Why does this keep happening to us?

06:23:08.159 --> 06:23:11.400
I know, Sonny agreed.

06:23:11.459 --> 06:23:14.040
Doesn't anyone trust the prophecy?

06:23:14.159 --> 06:23:16.500
If they believe in it, can't they have

06:23:16.500 --> 06:23:17.880
faith that will do the right thing?

06:23:17.939 --> 06:23:20.880
Everyone is trying to make sure the

06:23:20.880 --> 06:23:22.740
prophecy turns out the way they want it

06:23:22.740 --> 06:23:24.419
to, tsunami said.

06:23:24.479 --> 06:23:27.659
She turned in a circle, but there wasn't

06:23:27.659 --> 06:23:30.240
enough room to pace without brushing her

06:23:30.240 --> 06:23:31.740
wings or tail into the water.

06:23:31.799 --> 06:23:34.080
She sat back down with a growl.

06:23:34.139 --> 06:23:37.319
It would be helpful if the stupid

06:23:37.319 --> 06:23:39.419
prophecy had been a little more clear

06:23:39.419 --> 06:23:41.400
about what was supposed to happen.

06:23:41.459 --> 06:23:45.599
Why didn't you use your venom when they

06:23:45.599 --> 06:23:46.139
grabbed us?

06:23:46.200 --> 06:23:48.360
Starflight asked Glory?

06:23:48.419 --> 06:23:51.000
Believe me, I will.

06:23:51.119 --> 06:23:53.159
The rain wing said fiercely.

06:23:53.220 --> 06:23:54.840
I'm waiting for the right moment.

06:23:54.900 --> 06:23:58.799
I think that's smart, tsunami said.

06:23:58.860 --> 06:24:01.860
Even with Glory's magical death spit, we

06:24:01.860 --> 06:24:03.180
probably couldn't have fought off the

06:24:03.180 --> 06:24:05.040
whole palace, and it would have given

06:24:05.040 --> 06:24:06.659
away our best secret weapon.

06:24:06.720 --> 06:24:09.180
Glory looked surprised.

06:24:09.240 --> 06:24:13.259
Well, thank you. she said, although I'm

06:24:13.259 --> 06:24:15.180
going to vote against calling it magical

06:24:15.180 --> 06:24:16.259
death spit, please.

06:24:16.319 --> 06:24:20.880
Maybe tonight. tsunami said, lowering her

06:24:20.880 --> 06:24:23.340
voice, when most of the palace is

06:24:23.340 --> 06:24:25.500
sleeping, maybe we can fight our way out

06:24:25.500 --> 06:24:25.919
then.

06:24:26.040 --> 06:24:29.220
Pass the water with the shocks that might

06:24:29.220 --> 06:24:29.759
kill us?

06:24:29.819 --> 06:24:32.880
Sonny asked, what good is magical death

06:24:32.880 --> 06:24:34.860
spit against lightning eels?

06:24:34.919 --> 06:24:37.139
Electric eels.

06:24:37.200 --> 06:24:38.759
Starflight corrected her.

06:24:38.819 --> 06:24:42.659
We are not calling it magical death spit

06:24:42.659 --> 06:24:43.439
Glory said.

06:24:43.500 --> 06:24:47.759
Or Tsunami remembered the guards who had

06:24:47.759 --> 06:24:48.419
given her the key.

06:24:48.479 --> 06:24:51.240
Maybe we can convince someone to let us

06:24:51.240 --> 06:24:51.479
go.

06:24:51.540 --> 06:24:56.040
I like that plan, Clay said, bombing his

06:24:56.040 --> 06:24:56.220
head.

06:24:56.279 --> 06:24:59.459
I like the one where we melt everyone's

06:24:59.459 --> 06:25:01.259
eyeballs on our way out the door.

06:25:01.319 --> 06:25:02.279
Glory said.

06:25:02.340 --> 06:25:06.779
With magical death spit, Sonny said, then

06:25:06.779 --> 06:25:08.459
buried her head in Clay's wings to hide

06:25:08.459 --> 06:25:10.680
her giggles as Glory glared at her.

06:25:10.740 --> 06:25:14.700
Three moons, Glory, said tsunami.

06:25:14.759 --> 06:25:15.599
That's horrible.

06:25:15.659 --> 06:25:17.759
Who are you?

06:25:17.819 --> 06:25:18.959
Gloria asked.

06:25:19.020 --> 06:25:21.180
What happened to the sea wing who'd fight

06:25:21.180 --> 06:25:21.900
her way out of anything?

06:25:21.959 --> 06:25:24.540
I'll still fight?

06:25:24.599 --> 06:25:25.319
Tsunami said.

06:25:25.380 --> 06:25:28.439
An image of Gil flashed in her mind, and

06:25:28.439 --> 06:25:28.860
she shivered.

06:25:28.919 --> 06:25:31.740
I'm just saying, there are a lot of these

06:25:31.740 --> 06:25:33.360
guards who are really on our side.

06:25:33.419 --> 06:25:36.060
I bet we can find someone to help us.

06:25:36.119 --> 06:25:38.040
Sonny lifted her snout.

06:25:38.099 --> 06:25:40.020
Did you hear something?

06:25:40.080 --> 06:25:42.299
Like what?

06:25:42.360 --> 06:25:44.040
Starflight asked.

06:25:44.099 --> 06:25:45.959
The little Sandwing hesitated.

06:25:46.020 --> 06:25:48.479
It's hard to be sure over the water

06:25:48.479 --> 06:25:49.020
sounds.

06:25:49.080 --> 06:25:51.299
Probably nothing.

06:25:51.360 --> 06:25:52.380
Tsunami said.

06:25:52.439 --> 06:25:53.700
Nothing helpful anyway.

06:25:53.759 --> 06:25:55.740
Sonny frowned at her.

06:25:55.799 --> 06:25:59.099
Someone's coming, Glory observed.

06:25:59.159 --> 06:26:01.200
They could see a pale shape flitting

06:26:01.200 --> 06:26:03.360
along the path toward them, although it

06:26:03.360 --> 06:26:04.500
was blurred by the waterfall.

06:26:04.560 --> 06:26:06.900
Is that what you heard?

06:26:06.959 --> 06:26:08.700
Starflight asked Sonny.

06:26:08.759 --> 06:26:11.099
She shook her head, looking perplexed.

06:26:11.159 --> 06:26:14.459
As the dragon came closer.

06:26:14.520 --> 06:26:15.900
Tsunami thought she recognized her

06:26:15.900 --> 06:26:18.299
coloring, but surely it couldn't be?

06:26:18.419 --> 06:26:19.979
Anemone?

06:26:20.040 --> 06:26:20.639
She called.

06:26:20.700 --> 06:26:22.680
There you are.

06:26:22.740 --> 06:26:25.200
Anemone hurried over to their cage.

06:26:25.259 --> 06:26:27.959
She stood as close as she could get to

06:26:27.959 --> 06:26:29.819
the moat and the crackling water.

06:26:29.880 --> 06:26:32.159
Tsunami wished she could reach over and

06:26:32.159 --> 06:26:33.840
wrap her wings around her little sister.

06:26:33.959 --> 06:26:37.200
You're unharnessed, she cried.

06:26:37.259 --> 06:26:38.459
I know.

06:26:38.520 --> 06:26:39.419
Isn't it wonderful?

06:26:39.479 --> 06:26:42.240
Anemone stretched her wings wide and

06:26:42.240 --> 06:26:42.720
beamed.

06:26:42.779 --> 06:26:45.180
It's only for a little while.

06:26:45.240 --> 06:26:46.979
She tugged at the web that was still

06:26:46.979 --> 06:26:48.720
fitted closely around her chest.

06:26:48.779 --> 06:26:50.520
I'll be snapped in again later.

06:26:50.639 --> 06:26:52.860
But Queen Coral said I could go fly

06:26:52.860 --> 06:26:55.319
around while she has aucklet fitted for

06:26:55.319 --> 06:26:57.599
her harness, as long as I don't leave the

06:26:57.599 --> 06:26:58.259
summer palace.

06:26:58.319 --> 06:27:01.020
This would be the happiest day of my life

06:27:01.020 --> 06:27:03.000
if I weren't so worried about you.

06:27:03.060 --> 06:27:05.880
Can you set us free?

06:27:05.939 --> 06:27:07.500
Clay asked hopefully.

06:27:07.560 --> 06:27:09.419
And then come with us?

06:27:09.479 --> 06:27:12.360
Tsunami suggested, we'll never make you

06:27:12.360 --> 06:27:13.799
use your powers, I promise.

06:27:13.860 --> 06:27:16.259
Anemone shook her head.

06:27:16.319 --> 06:27:19.619
I wish I could, but coral and blister

06:27:19.619 --> 06:27:21.599
will be furious enough about losing the

06:27:21.599 --> 06:27:22.919
dragonettes of destiny.

06:27:22.919 --> 06:27:24.000
Think about it.

06:27:24.060 --> 06:27:26.459
If their secret weapon disappears too

06:27:26.459 --> 06:27:28.619
they'll hunt you down like sharks after

06:27:28.619 --> 06:27:29.040
prey.

06:27:29.099 --> 06:27:33.720
That's a good point, Starfight agreed, in

06:27:33.720 --> 06:27:35.639
his let's all be sensible voice.

06:27:35.759 --> 06:27:39.060
I don't care, tsunami said.

06:27:39.119 --> 06:27:41.759
I don't care if every Dragon Empire is

06:27:41.759 --> 06:27:42.299
searching for us.

06:27:42.360 --> 06:27:45.180
We'll keep you safe, a lot safer than you

06:27:45.180 --> 06:27:45.479
are here.

06:27:45.540 --> 06:27:49.560
Anemones shifted her wings, even through

06:27:49.560 --> 06:27:51.959
the water, tsunami could see the mournful

06:27:51.959 --> 06:27:53.040
expression on her snout.

06:27:53.159 --> 06:27:57.360
I just, I just don't think I'm ready to

06:27:57.360 --> 06:27:59.880
live my life like Webbs did, never able

06:27:59.880 --> 06:28:02.099
to return home, she said.

06:28:02.159 --> 06:28:05.159
I'd miss Aucklet, and I think the sea

06:28:05.159 --> 06:28:06.060
wings need me here.

06:28:06.119 --> 06:28:07.919
I think mother needs me.

06:28:07.979 --> 06:28:10.380
So she's hearing another voice besides

06:28:10.380 --> 06:28:11.159
blisters.

06:28:11.220 --> 06:28:14.700
Tsunami knew that was all very logical

06:28:14.700 --> 06:28:17.400
but it still made her scales itch to

06:28:17.400 --> 06:28:18.840
think she'd have to abandon her sister

06:28:18.840 --> 06:28:21.180
when she'd only just met her.

06:28:21.240 --> 06:28:23.759
All right, Clay said.

06:28:23.819 --> 06:28:26.279
You could still set us free though

06:28:26.279 --> 06:28:26.700
right?

06:28:26.759 --> 06:28:30.720
They'd know it was her, Glory pointed

06:28:30.720 --> 06:28:30.959
out.

06:28:31.020 --> 06:28:33.900
That's true, tsunami agreed.

06:28:33.959 --> 06:28:35.099
It's too dangerous.

06:28:35.220 --> 06:28:38.099
But there's something else I wanted to do

06:28:38.099 --> 06:28:40.020
for you, Anemone said.

06:28:40.080 --> 06:28:42.479
She lifted something in her front talons

06:28:42.479 --> 06:28:44.819
and tsunami realized she was holding a

06:28:44.819 --> 06:28:46.619
pure white narwhal spear.

06:28:46.680 --> 06:28:50.580
Spear, anemone said solemnly.

06:28:50.639 --> 06:28:53.759
Find the dragon who attacked tsunami in

06:28:53.759 --> 06:28:55.979
the entrance tunnel and bring him or her

06:28:55.979 --> 06:28:56.459
to us.

06:28:56.580 --> 06:29:00.060
She let go, and the spear flew up the

06:29:00.060 --> 06:29:00.959
path out of the cave.

06:29:01.020 --> 06:29:03.599
The other dragonettes stared at her in

06:29:03.599 --> 06:29:03.900
awe.

06:29:04.020 --> 06:29:06.540
Is that really possible?

06:29:06.599 --> 06:29:07.740
Clay asked.

06:29:07.799 --> 06:29:09.299
That'll actually work.

06:29:09.360 --> 06:29:13.680
We'll see, Anemone said, pressing her

06:29:13.680 --> 06:29:14.520
claws together.

06:29:14.580 --> 06:29:17.939
You didn't have to do that, tsunami said

06:29:17.939 --> 06:29:18.779
worried.

06:29:18.840 --> 06:29:19.979
Do you feel all right?

06:29:20.040 --> 06:29:24.299
Just a little cold, Anemone answered.

06:29:24.360 --> 06:29:26.759
She rubbed her tail between her talons

06:29:26.759 --> 06:29:28.080
with a rough, scraping sound.

06:29:28.139 --> 06:29:29.939
They waited.

06:29:30.000 --> 06:29:31.560
And waited.

06:29:31.680 --> 06:29:35.400
And finally, they saw someone stumbling

06:29:35.400 --> 06:29:36.479
down the path toward them.

06:29:36.479 --> 06:29:39.419
The spear seemed to glow in the dark as

06:29:39.419 --> 06:29:41.340
it jabbed the dragon in the back and

06:29:41.340 --> 06:29:43.500
wings and tail, driving it along.

06:29:43.560 --> 06:29:45.779
Ow!

06:29:45.840 --> 06:29:47.639
A voice echoed through the cavern.

06:29:47.700 --> 06:29:51.419
What is the meaning of, why am I?

06:29:51.540 --> 06:29:52.200
ow?

06:29:52.259 --> 06:29:53.340
What?

06:29:53.340 --> 06:29:54.540
Ow, stop.

06:29:54.659 --> 06:29:55.680
Ow.

06:29:55.740 --> 06:29:59.279
I will report you to the ow.

06:29:59.340 --> 06:30:03.060
Well, that's not coral, said glory.

06:30:03.119 --> 06:30:06.419
And it's not shark, said tsunami.

06:30:06.479 --> 06:30:08.759
She scratched her horns, confused.

06:30:08.819 --> 06:30:11.279
She'd been so sure it had to be shark.

06:30:11.340 --> 06:30:13.919
Not Moray either.

06:30:13.979 --> 06:30:16.380
Anemone stood up as he approached.

06:30:16.439 --> 06:30:19.439
The spear prodded the dragon into place

06:30:19.439 --> 06:30:21.599
beside Anemone, on the edge of the

06:30:21.599 --> 06:30:22.380
electric moat.

06:30:22.439 --> 06:30:24.959
It was Whirlpool.

06:30:25.020 --> 06:30:29.459
Chapter 26.

06:30:29.759 --> 06:30:32.340
Whirlpool?

06:30:32.400 --> 06:30:35.459
Tsunami said, thoroughly astonished.

06:30:35.639 --> 06:30:37.259
Why would you want to kill me?

06:30:37.319 --> 06:30:40.139
She'd rather thought he was too boring to

06:30:40.139 --> 06:30:40.740
be a suspect.

06:30:40.799 --> 06:30:45.000
Rubbish, said the green dragon with a

06:30:45.000 --> 06:30:45.659
haughty air.

06:30:45.720 --> 06:30:47.759
I would never.

06:30:47.880 --> 06:30:49.439
The spear poked him again.

06:30:49.500 --> 06:30:51.119
A little harder this time.

06:30:51.180 --> 06:30:52.200
Ow.

06:30:52.259 --> 06:30:53.700
My goodness.

06:30:53.759 --> 06:30:55.799
Anemone.

06:30:55.860 --> 06:30:59.279
I had no idea you were capable of such

06:30:59.279 --> 06:31:00.360
powerful magic.

06:31:00.419 --> 06:31:03.479
I must be a brilliant teacher.

06:31:03.540 --> 06:31:07.380
Of course, I'd be more impressed if it

06:31:07.380 --> 06:31:09.659
weren't stabbing me, ow.

06:31:09.779 --> 06:31:12.419
Anemone shifted on her talons

06:31:12.419 --> 06:31:13.080
uncomfortably.

06:31:13.139 --> 06:31:16.259
I didn't think it would be you, she

06:31:16.259 --> 06:31:16.500
said.

06:31:16.560 --> 06:31:20.459
We should tell Queen Blister.

06:31:20.520 --> 06:31:22.860
How accomplished you are.

06:31:22.919 --> 06:31:27.900
Whirlpool said, in his oozy voice, she'll

06:31:27.900 --> 06:31:30.060
be so terribly pleased.

06:31:30.180 --> 06:31:33.299
Don't you dare?

06:31:33.419 --> 06:31:34.740
Tsunami snapped.

06:31:34.799 --> 06:31:38.520
Do you really think I'll find you

06:31:38.520 --> 06:31:40.319
threatening from in there?

06:31:40.439 --> 06:31:41.580
He asked.

06:31:41.639 --> 06:31:45.000
If you do, I'll tell mother you tried to

06:31:45.000 --> 06:31:46.259
kill me, she said.

06:31:46.319 --> 06:31:48.599
How do you think she'll feel about that?

06:31:48.720 --> 06:31:51.479
He shrugged and reached up to play with a

06:31:51.479 --> 06:31:52.860
gold hoop earring in his ear.

06:31:52.919 --> 06:31:56.580
She may find it quite admirable

06:31:56.580 --> 06:31:56.939
actually.

06:31:57.000 --> 06:32:00.959
After all, I was merely trying to ensure

06:32:00.959 --> 06:32:03.479
that anemone deer would be queen.

06:32:03.599 --> 06:32:05.159
Me?

06:32:05.220 --> 06:32:07.919
Anemone's wings fluttered open and

06:32:07.919 --> 06:32:08.220
closed.

06:32:08.279 --> 06:32:10.919
You don't even like me that much.

06:32:11.040 --> 06:32:12.840
Why do anything for me?

06:32:12.900 --> 06:32:19.200
Well, Whirlpool said, frankly, I don't

06:32:19.200 --> 06:32:20.279
want to marry her.

06:32:20.340 --> 06:32:22.680
He pointed at tsunami.

06:32:22.799 --> 06:32:25.919
Wow, Glory said cheerfully.

06:32:25.979 --> 06:32:28.740
That was totally on my list of reasons

06:32:28.740 --> 06:32:30.180
why someone might want to kill you.

06:32:30.240 --> 06:32:33.540
Don't worry, tsunami snapped.

06:32:33.599 --> 06:32:36.180
I'd rather be torn apart by tiger sharks

06:32:36.180 --> 06:32:36.959
than ever marry you.

06:32:37.080 --> 06:32:40.860
But I do want to be king.

06:32:40.919 --> 06:32:42.659
Whirlpool said.

06:32:42.720 --> 06:32:45.720
He held out his talons, as if imagining

06:32:45.720 --> 06:32:47.759
more gold rings looping around his

06:32:47.759 --> 06:32:48.360
claws.

06:32:48.419 --> 06:32:53.040
So I thought if I got rid of you, I'd

06:32:53.040 --> 06:32:55.560
improve my chances of marrying a more

06:32:55.560 --> 06:32:57.840
agreeable daughter.

06:32:57.900 --> 06:33:01.020
I don't ever want to marry you either.

06:33:01.080 --> 06:33:02.520
Anemone cried.

06:33:02.580 --> 06:33:06.840
It's not really up to you, Whirlpool

06:33:06.840 --> 06:33:07.200
said.

06:33:07.259 --> 06:33:09.479
Taking a step back up the path to the

06:33:09.479 --> 06:33:10.200
cave entrance.

06:33:10.259 --> 06:33:15.060
Once I tell Queen Coral and Queen Blister

06:33:15.060 --> 06:33:16.860
about what you can do.

06:33:16.919 --> 06:33:20.099
They'll be so grateful, they'll let me

06:33:20.099 --> 06:33:22.020
have anything I want.

06:33:22.080 --> 06:33:26.400
But of course, then you'll be very busy

06:33:26.400 --> 06:33:29.340
using your powers to win the war.

06:33:29.400 --> 06:33:32.580
And you probably won't survive that.

06:33:32.639 --> 06:33:36.840
So I should really ask for Aucklet

06:33:36.840 --> 06:33:37.139
instead.

06:33:37.259 --> 06:33:41.099
He tapped his snout thoughtfully, as if

06:33:41.099 --> 06:33:42.119
he was musing to himself.

06:33:42.180 --> 06:33:46.500
You can't tell them, tsunami shouted.

06:33:46.560 --> 06:33:49.080
She was supposed to protect anemone from

06:33:49.080 --> 06:33:50.099
being used like this.

06:33:50.159 --> 06:33:53.040
It was the one thing her sister had asked

06:33:53.040 --> 06:33:56.340
of her, and instead, now it would be her

06:33:56.340 --> 06:33:59.400
fault if anemone became blisters pawn.

06:33:59.459 --> 06:34:03.060
She lunged toward the waterfall, but Clay

06:34:03.060 --> 06:34:04.860
jumped forward at the same time and held

06:34:04.860 --> 06:34:07.919
her back, blue light crackled in front of

06:34:07.919 --> 06:34:11.099
them, and down below, the eels clustered

06:34:11.099 --> 06:34:13.259
menacingly like a sinister clump of

06:34:13.259 --> 06:34:14.459
seaweed.

06:34:14.520 --> 06:34:16.979
But at the same time, on the other side

06:34:16.979 --> 06:34:19.200
of the waterfall, Anemone was moving

06:34:19.200 --> 06:34:19.500
too.

06:34:19.619 --> 06:34:22.860
She seized the spear from the air, spun

06:34:22.860 --> 06:34:25.200
it around, and smacked the side of it

06:34:25.200 --> 06:34:26.459
into Whirlpool's head.

06:34:26.520 --> 06:34:29.459
He staggered forward, then crumpled

06:34:29.459 --> 06:34:30.180
without a sound.

06:34:30.240 --> 06:34:33.900
His wings tipped sideways, overbalancing

06:34:33.900 --> 06:34:36.779
him, and in one sudden movement, his body

06:34:36.779 --> 06:34:38.759
slipped over the edge into the electric

06:34:38.759 --> 06:34:39.779
eel moat.

06:34:39.900 --> 06:34:42.720
Anemone yelped with fear and dropped her

06:34:42.720 --> 06:34:43.080
weapon.

06:34:43.139 --> 06:34:45.479
She reached her talons toward the water.

06:34:45.540 --> 06:34:47.159
But it was too late.

06:34:47.220 --> 06:34:51.180
A blinding flash of blue sizzled up the

06:34:51.180 --> 06:34:54.180
cascading waterfall, tsunami jumped back

06:34:54.180 --> 06:34:57.060
and all 5 dragonettes huddled close in

06:34:57.060 --> 06:34:57.900
the center of the island.

06:34:57.959 --> 06:35:01.080
The water in the moat, churned and

06:35:01.080 --> 06:35:03.360
seethed around the spot where Whirlpool

06:35:03.360 --> 06:35:04.380
had disappeared.

06:35:04.439 --> 06:35:06.840
Thick green tails thrashed through the

06:35:06.840 --> 06:35:09.540
bubbles, and sparks flew, as if several

06:35:09.540 --> 06:35:11.159
bolts of lightning were striking at

06:35:11.159 --> 06:35:12.060
once.

06:35:12.119 --> 06:35:15.299
Sunny covered her eyes, and Clay put his

06:35:15.299 --> 06:35:15.959
wing around her.

06:35:16.020 --> 06:35:18.599
Tsunami wished she could do the same for

06:35:18.599 --> 06:35:21.180
anemone on the far side of the moat.

06:35:21.299 --> 06:35:24.000
Her little sister looked petrified in

06:35:24.000 --> 06:35:24.180
place.

06:35:24.240 --> 06:35:29.159
Slowly, the flashes calmed down until

06:35:29.159 --> 06:35:31.560
only an occasional zap appeared in the

06:35:31.560 --> 06:35:31.799
wall.

06:35:31.860 --> 06:35:34.200
And then they all stopped.

06:35:34.259 --> 06:35:37.860
The waterfall was quiet, and so was the

06:35:37.860 --> 06:35:38.220
moat.

06:35:38.279 --> 06:35:41.700
Tsunami could see the eels, still

06:35:41.700 --> 06:35:44.159
clustered around a large, dark shape at

06:35:44.159 --> 06:35:46.799
the bottom of the pool, but their frenzy

06:35:46.799 --> 06:35:49.259
had subsided, and she guessed she was

06:35:49.259 --> 06:35:51.540
lucky she couldn't see any details of

06:35:51.540 --> 06:35:52.380
what they were doing now.

06:35:52.439 --> 06:35:55.439
Anemone, she called.

06:35:55.500 --> 06:35:56.459
Are you all right?

06:35:56.580 --> 06:35:58.740
Anemone didn't answer.

06:35:58.799 --> 06:36:02.040
Her blurred outline was motionless, as if

06:36:02.040 --> 06:36:03.659
she were one of Orca's statues.

06:36:03.720 --> 06:36:07.200
I'm not sure I should tell you this

06:36:07.200 --> 06:36:10.080
Starflight said, but you might be able to

06:36:10.080 --> 06:36:11.220
go through the water right now.

06:36:11.279 --> 06:36:13.860
Tsunami whipped around toward him.

06:36:13.919 --> 06:36:14.939
Really?

06:36:15.000 --> 06:36:15.599
Why?

06:36:15.659 --> 06:36:17.700
He pointed to the eels.

06:36:17.759 --> 06:36:20.639
After a burst like that, they'll need a

06:36:20.639 --> 06:36:24.060
while to recharge, I think, so they might

06:36:24.060 --> 06:36:26.279
not be able to let off any shocks for at

06:36:26.279 --> 06:36:27.240
least a minute or two.

06:36:27.360 --> 06:36:31.200
Wait, he added, as tsunami flared her

06:36:31.200 --> 06:36:33.180
wings, but I'm not sure.

06:36:33.240 --> 06:36:36.299
I didn't read those scrolls as often as

06:36:36.299 --> 06:36:37.500
the ones about dragons.

06:36:37.560 --> 06:36:38.459
I'm sorry.

06:36:38.580 --> 06:36:41.580
Starflight's black head drooped.

06:36:41.639 --> 06:36:44.040
It's probably not worth the risk.

06:36:44.279 --> 06:36:45.240
I wouldn't listen to me.

06:36:45.299 --> 06:36:48.060
But Starflight.

06:36:48.119 --> 06:36:50.279
You know everything, Sonny said.

06:36:50.340 --> 06:36:51.659
I'm sure you're right.

06:36:51.720 --> 06:36:54.540
I could go through and turn off the

06:36:54.540 --> 06:36:55.080
waterfall.

06:36:55.139 --> 06:36:56.400
Tsunami said.

06:36:56.520 --> 06:36:58.500
Then it would only be me risking it.

06:36:58.560 --> 06:37:00.959
Starflight looked miserable.

06:37:01.020 --> 06:37:05.819
But it was my idea, he said, and if I

06:37:05.819 --> 06:37:07.680
might be wrong. shouldn't I?

06:37:07.799 --> 06:37:09.720
Poor Starflight.

06:37:09.779 --> 06:37:12.240
Tsunami twined her tail around his.

06:37:12.299 --> 06:37:15.299
She knew he wanted to be brave and

06:37:15.299 --> 06:37:17.759
helpful, but this was the kind of thing

06:37:17.759 --> 06:37:19.259
she did, not him.

06:37:19.319 --> 06:37:21.840
Don't be silly, she said.

06:37:21.900 --> 06:37:23.700
This is my kingdom.

06:37:23.819 --> 06:37:25.680
I'm responsible for doing the crazy

06:37:25.680 --> 06:37:26.459
things here.

06:37:26.520 --> 06:37:30.299
Do you remember what the scroll said

06:37:30.299 --> 06:37:31.619
about electric eels?

06:37:31.619 --> 06:37:33.000
Clay asked glory.

06:37:33.119 --> 06:37:35.700
The rain wing lifted her wings slightly.

06:37:35.759 --> 06:37:39.360
I don't think it was specific, she said.

06:37:39.419 --> 06:37:41.880
They can run out of charge for short

06:37:41.880 --> 06:37:44.099
periods of time, but I don't know if this

06:37:44.099 --> 06:37:46.560
is definitely one of them or how long it

06:37:46.560 --> 06:37:46.979
might last.

06:37:47.040 --> 06:37:49.500
Think it through.

06:37:49.619 --> 06:37:51.599
Be more like Starflight.

06:37:51.659 --> 06:37:53.099
Don't be impulsive.

06:37:53.159 --> 06:37:54.419
Tsunami thought.

06:37:54.479 --> 06:37:57.959
But then, what if this is our only chance

06:37:57.959 --> 06:37:58.680
to escape?

06:37:58.740 --> 06:38:01.500
She glanced over at anemone.

06:38:01.560 --> 06:38:03.240
And I have to help her.

06:38:03.299 --> 06:38:06.720
But if I die, what happens to the

06:38:06.720 --> 06:38:07.020
others?

06:38:07.080 --> 06:38:09.479
She clansed her talons.

06:38:09.540 --> 06:38:12.000
An image of her mother's counsel flashed

06:38:12.000 --> 06:38:12.599
through her head.

06:38:12.659 --> 06:38:14.759
All right, she said.

06:38:14.819 --> 06:38:16.139
Let's vote.

06:38:16.200 --> 06:38:19.860
Holy moons, Glory said.

06:38:19.919 --> 06:38:22.439
Seriously, what have you done with a real

06:38:22.439 --> 06:38:23.159
tsunami?

06:38:23.220 --> 06:38:26.939
Quickly, tsunami said, shooting a glance

06:38:26.939 --> 06:38:28.080
at the quiet waterfall.

06:38:28.139 --> 06:38:31.380
I believe Starflight, Sonny said.

06:38:31.439 --> 06:38:32.759
I think you can make it through.

06:38:32.880 --> 06:38:33.779
Definitely.

06:38:33.840 --> 06:38:37.860
I don't, Starflight said glumly.

06:38:37.919 --> 06:38:40.380
I vote that nobody tries, just to be

06:38:40.380 --> 06:38:40.560
safe.

06:38:40.680 --> 06:38:44.580
Well, I want to get out of here, Glory

06:38:44.580 --> 06:38:44.880
said.

06:38:44.939 --> 06:38:48.060
And I'm willing to risk tsunami's bossy

06:38:48.060 --> 06:38:48.720
scales to do it.

06:38:48.779 --> 06:38:51.540
She shot tsunami a toothy grin.

06:38:51.599 --> 06:38:53.400
Clay shook his head slowly.

06:38:53.459 --> 06:38:55.319
I don't know.

06:38:55.380 --> 06:38:57.479
You're too important to all of a

06:38:57.479 --> 06:38:58.200
tsunami.

06:38:58.259 --> 06:38:59.939
I don't think you should do it.

06:39:00.000 --> 06:39:03.659
Well, that doesn't help, Tsunami said

06:39:03.659 --> 06:39:04.259
with a snort.

06:39:04.319 --> 06:39:06.419
Now I just have to decide for myself

06:39:06.419 --> 06:39:06.959
anyway.

06:39:07.020 --> 06:39:09.000
Some council you guys are.

06:39:09.060 --> 06:39:11.700
But those were pretty much the votes

06:39:11.700 --> 06:39:14.639
she'd been expecting, and she'd listened

06:39:14.639 --> 06:39:16.799
to all of them, and she knew what she

06:39:16.799 --> 06:39:17.819
wanted to do.

06:39:17.880 --> 06:39:21.360
She took a deep breath, spun around, and

06:39:21.360 --> 06:39:22.860
launched herself at the wall of water.

06:39:22.979 --> 06:39:25.799
It felt like leaping into a freezing

06:39:25.799 --> 06:39:28.860
hailstorm, icy drops pelting her snout

06:39:28.860 --> 06:39:31.740
and closed eyes, slicing into her gills

06:39:31.740 --> 06:39:34.319
through the seaweed bandage, hammering

06:39:34.319 --> 06:39:35.520
the fractures in her ribs.

06:39:35.580 --> 06:39:38.159
She braced herself for a lightning sharp

06:39:38.159 --> 06:39:41.040
pain, but a moment later, her talons

06:39:41.040 --> 06:39:42.180
thumped onto solid rock.

06:39:42.299 --> 06:39:45.779
Tsunami opened her eyes as she skidded to

06:39:45.779 --> 06:39:46.080
a stop.

06:39:46.139 --> 06:39:48.540
She'd made it to the other side of the

06:39:48.540 --> 06:39:50.580
moat, and her scales were still intact.

06:39:50.639 --> 06:39:53.939
She grabbed Anemone's shoulders and shook

06:39:53.939 --> 06:39:56.220
her until the pale little dragon looked

06:39:56.220 --> 06:39:56.939
up to meet her eyes.

06:39:57.000 --> 06:39:59.459
You have to get out of here.

06:39:59.520 --> 06:40:00.840
Tsunami said.

06:40:00.900 --> 06:40:03.240
We're going to escape, and I don't want

06:40:03.240 --> 06:40:04.380
it to look like you were involved.

06:40:04.500 --> 06:40:07.619
Go find mother and hang around where she

06:40:07.619 --> 06:40:09.360
can see you so you have an alibi.

06:40:09.419 --> 06:40:10.080
All right?

06:40:10.139 --> 06:40:11.580
Are you listening?

06:40:11.639 --> 06:40:13.799
But look what I did.

06:40:13.860 --> 06:40:16.979
Anemone whispered, pointing to the pool.

06:40:17.040 --> 06:40:20.759
You didn't mean to do that, Tsunami

06:40:20.759 --> 06:40:21.000
said.

06:40:21.060 --> 06:40:24.240
She knew way too clearly how anemone felt

06:40:24.240 --> 06:40:24.659
right now.

06:40:24.720 --> 06:40:26.459
Anemone?

06:40:26.520 --> 06:40:27.599
It was an accident.

06:40:27.659 --> 06:40:29.819
You didn't push him into the moat.

06:40:29.880 --> 06:40:32.880
And if it hadn't happened, think how many

06:40:32.880 --> 06:40:34.619
dragons you might have had to kill with

06:40:34.619 --> 06:40:35.040
your powers.

06:40:35.099 --> 06:40:37.560
Now you can tell mother that with no

06:40:37.560 --> 06:40:39.779
trainer, your powers seem to be getting

06:40:39.779 --> 06:40:40.200
weaker.

06:40:40.259 --> 06:40:42.360
Mess up all the time.

06:40:42.419 --> 06:40:45.419
Make sure she thinks you aren't ready and

06:40:45.419 --> 06:40:46.680
won't be for a long time.

06:40:46.740 --> 06:40:51.000
But one day, anemone started.

06:40:51.060 --> 06:40:54.360
One day, very soon, this war will be

06:40:54.360 --> 06:40:54.659
over.

06:40:54.720 --> 06:40:56.340
We're going to end it.

06:40:56.400 --> 06:40:57.900
Trust me.

06:40:57.959 --> 06:41:01.319
Tsunami squeezed Anemones front talons in

06:41:01.319 --> 06:41:01.740
hers.

06:41:01.799 --> 06:41:03.599
Now get out of here.

06:41:03.659 --> 06:41:06.840
Good luck, Anemone whispered.

06:41:06.900 --> 06:41:09.479
Tsunami wrapped her wings around her

06:41:09.479 --> 06:41:09.720
sister.

06:41:09.779 --> 06:41:11.639
Good luck to you too.

06:41:11.700 --> 06:41:14.759
Anemone fled out the cave path.

06:41:14.819 --> 06:41:17.819
Her pale wings fluttered like moths as

06:41:17.819 --> 06:41:19.020
she disappeared around the bend.

06:41:19.080 --> 06:41:22.139
Tsunami hurried to the chain on the

06:41:22.139 --> 06:41:22.439
wall.

06:41:22.500 --> 06:41:24.540
The guard had yanked it down.

06:41:24.599 --> 06:41:26.040
Could she pull it back up?

06:41:26.099 --> 06:41:28.500
She tried hauling the chain in the

06:41:28.500 --> 06:41:30.659
opposite direction, and felt it slide

06:41:30.659 --> 06:41:32.279
jerkily through her claws.

06:41:32.340 --> 06:41:34.860
Clanking noises rattled from the ceiling

06:41:34.860 --> 06:41:37.619
and she stopped for a moment, glancing up

06:41:37.619 --> 06:41:39.900
the path where the guards had gone.

06:41:39.959 --> 06:41:41.279
Were there guards at the entrance?

06:41:41.340 --> 06:41:42.479
What if they heard her?

06:41:42.540 --> 06:41:46.979
Hey, kid, a raspy voice croaked.

06:41:47.040 --> 06:41:48.720
Tsunami jumped and looked around.

06:41:48.779 --> 06:41:52.139
A scrawny sandwing was watching her from

06:41:52.139 --> 06:41:54.360
his prison island, even through the

06:41:54.360 --> 06:41:56.459
waterfall, Tsunami could see the dark

06:41:56.459 --> 06:41:57.360
glitter of his eyes.

06:41:57.419 --> 06:42:01.319
You could do the same thing for me, he

06:42:01.319 --> 06:42:01.860
hissed.

06:42:01.919 --> 06:42:03.240
Set me free.

06:42:03.360 --> 06:42:06.240
Tsunami turned back to the chain and kept

06:42:06.240 --> 06:42:06.840
pulling.

06:42:06.900 --> 06:42:08.939
She didn't know what was in store for

06:42:08.939 --> 06:42:11.459
Coral's prisoners, but she also didn't

06:42:11.459 --> 06:42:13.500
know why they were here, or whether they

06:42:13.500 --> 06:42:14.099
deserved it.

06:42:14.159 --> 06:42:16.200
Except for 2 of them.

06:42:16.259 --> 06:42:19.860
Somewhere in this cavern, riptide and

06:42:19.860 --> 06:42:22.380
webs were trapped, possibly awaiting

06:42:22.380 --> 06:42:24.659
execution, she had to find them too.

06:42:24.720 --> 06:42:28.139
What sounded like an enormous metallic

06:42:28.139 --> 06:42:31.380
groan echoed overhead, and then suddenly

06:42:31.380 --> 06:42:33.659
the cascading water around her friends

06:42:33.659 --> 06:42:34.259
shut off.

06:42:34.319 --> 06:42:37.619
There was a beat of silence as they all

06:42:37.619 --> 06:42:38.520
stared up at the ceiling.

06:42:38.580 --> 06:42:42.060
Sunny leaped off 1st, flapping her wings

06:42:42.060 --> 06:42:43.740
to clear the moat, and the others

06:42:43.740 --> 06:42:45.180
followed her quickly.

06:42:45.240 --> 06:42:47.639
Tsunami pushed past them to lead the way

06:42:47.639 --> 06:42:48.240
up the path.

06:42:48.360 --> 06:42:50.459
What about me?

06:42:50.520 --> 06:42:52.860
yelled the imprisoned Sandwing.

06:42:52.919 --> 06:42:56.700
I have to find riptide and webs, tsunami

06:42:56.700 --> 06:42:58.860
said to her friends, did anyone see them

06:42:58.860 --> 06:42:59.459
on the way in?

06:42:59.520 --> 06:43:02.400
I did, Clay said.

06:43:02.459 --> 06:43:05.580
They're on one island together, not far

06:43:05.580 --> 06:43:06.299
from the entrance.

06:43:06.419 --> 06:43:09.599
The 5 of them hurried along the path.

06:43:09.659 --> 06:43:12.540
Tsunami kept her wings curled in and

06:43:12.540 --> 06:43:14.279
tried not to look at the fizzing blue

06:43:14.279 --> 06:43:16.560
water walls or the lurking eels.

06:43:16.680 --> 06:43:20.279
They rounded the last corner, and saw the

06:43:20.279 --> 06:43:22.139
greenish light of the summer palace up

06:43:22.139 --> 06:43:22.439
ahead.

06:43:22.560 --> 06:43:26.159
Tsunami spotted the guards 1st and pushed

06:43:26.159 --> 06:43:27.659
her friends back into the shadows.

06:43:27.720 --> 06:43:30.360
Only three, she thought.

06:43:30.419 --> 06:43:33.180
Three guards stood on the ledge outside

06:43:33.180 --> 06:43:35.819
the prison, chatting, and tossing their

06:43:35.819 --> 06:43:37.439
spears from talon to talon.

06:43:37.500 --> 06:43:39.840
They didn't look very threatening, and

06:43:39.840 --> 06:43:41.220
perhaps they were secretly on the

06:43:41.220 --> 06:43:43.439
dragonette's side, if they had allowed

06:43:43.439 --> 06:43:45.419
anemone through to see tsunami.

06:43:45.479 --> 06:43:47.459
She didn't want to fight them if she

06:43:47.459 --> 06:43:48.060
could avoid it.

06:43:48.119 --> 06:43:50.819
She didn't want to shed any more sea wing

06:43:50.819 --> 06:43:51.659
blood ever again.

06:43:51.720 --> 06:43:53.639
There.

06:43:53.700 --> 06:43:55.380
Clay whispered in her ear.

06:43:55.439 --> 06:43:57.119
He pointed over her shoulder.

06:43:57.180 --> 06:44:00.360
That island, just inside the entrance.

06:44:00.419 --> 06:44:03.959
Tsunami spotted the 2 blue shapes moving

06:44:03.959 --> 06:44:05.819
beyond the wall of water.

06:44:05.880 --> 06:44:07.860
She also saw a chain running along the

06:44:07.860 --> 06:44:10.139
stone beside their island, if she could

06:44:10.139 --> 06:44:12.659
get to it without the guards noticing, and

06:44:12.659 --> 06:44:14.220
then move the mechanism without the

06:44:14.220 --> 06:44:15.119
guards hearing it.

06:44:15.180 --> 06:44:17.939
Riptide and webs would be free to escape

06:44:17.939 --> 06:44:19.200
with the dragonettes.

06:44:19.259 --> 06:44:22.619
There it is again, Sonny whispered.

06:44:22.680 --> 06:44:24.119
Don't you all hear that?

06:44:24.180 --> 06:44:26.040
Hear what?

06:44:26.099 --> 06:44:27.419
Clay whispered back.

06:44:27.479 --> 06:44:30.180
I don't know, Sonny said.

06:44:30.240 --> 06:44:31.619
I keep hearing.

06:44:31.680 --> 06:44:33.779
I think I'm hearing wing beats.

06:44:33.840 --> 06:44:37.139
There are sea wings flying all over the

06:44:37.139 --> 06:44:38.880
palace, Glory pointed out.

06:44:38.939 --> 06:44:41.639
I know, Sonny said.

06:44:41.700 --> 06:44:43.740
This is bigger, higher.

06:44:43.799 --> 06:44:44.939
I'm not sure.

06:44:45.000 --> 06:44:48.599
Don't worry so much, tsunami said.

06:44:48.659 --> 06:44:50.159
I'm sure you're imagining things.

06:44:50.279 --> 06:44:53.639
Sunny stamped one of her feet and craned

06:44:53.639 --> 06:44:54.779
her neck toward the outside.

06:44:54.900 --> 06:44:58.500
No, I'm definitely sure, she said

06:44:58.500 --> 06:44:59.099
firmly.

06:44:59.159 --> 06:45:01.560
I hear wing beats above the canopy.

06:45:01.619 --> 06:45:03.479
Lots and lots of them.

06:45:03.540 --> 06:45:07.799
Sunny, tsunami started, but then Clay's

06:45:07.799 --> 06:45:09.900
head shot up, and so did Starflights.

06:45:09.959 --> 06:45:13.259
I think she's right, Clay said.

06:45:13.319 --> 06:45:16.500
Tsunami inhaled sharply, realizing what

06:45:16.500 --> 06:45:16.919
that meant.

06:45:16.979 --> 06:45:19.020
You don't think?

06:45:19.259 --> 06:45:21.060
Starflight lashed his tail.

06:45:21.119 --> 06:45:23.220
I smell fire too.

06:45:23.279 --> 06:45:26.520
Tsunami didn't have time to think, or

06:45:26.520 --> 06:45:28.319
come up with a safe, logical solution.

06:45:28.439 --> 06:45:30.840
She burst out of their hiding spot and

06:45:30.840 --> 06:45:31.799
ran toward the guards.

06:45:31.860 --> 06:45:34.080
Look out, she yelled.

06:45:34.200 --> 06:45:35.159
Warn the palace.

06:45:35.220 --> 06:45:38.220
All 3 guards jumped, and 2 of them

06:45:38.220 --> 06:45:39.959
accidentally dropped their spears over

06:45:39.959 --> 06:45:40.619
the ledge.

06:45:40.680 --> 06:45:43.439
They stared at tsunami as if her horns

06:45:43.439 --> 06:45:44.880
were blazing columns of fire.

06:45:44.880 --> 06:45:46.319
Move!

06:45:46.380 --> 06:45:47.340
she shouted.

06:45:47.400 --> 06:45:50.220
Tsunami shoved them aside, stood on the

06:45:50.220 --> 06:45:53.400
ledge and yelled, Sea Wings, Mother, look

06:45:53.400 --> 06:45:53.700
out!

06:45:53.759 --> 06:45:55.080
We're under attack.

06:45:55.139 --> 06:45:59.220
And then the 1st fire bomb crashed

06:45:59.220 --> 06:46:00.060
through the canopy.

06:46:00.119 --> 06:46:04.439
Chapter 27.

06:46:04.680 --> 06:46:06.659
Panic.

06:46:06.720 --> 06:46:10.319
Screaming, for a palace surrounded by

06:46:10.319 --> 06:46:10.680
water.

06:46:10.740 --> 06:46:12.900
It was surprising how much caught on fire

06:46:12.900 --> 06:46:13.560
so quickly.

06:46:13.619 --> 06:46:17.220
Large sections of the canopy collapsed

06:46:17.220 --> 06:46:20.220
carrying flaming branches and leaves and

06:46:20.220 --> 06:46:22.080
debris down onto the summer palace.

06:46:22.139 --> 06:46:25.380
Tsunami saw dragons spiraling toward the

06:46:25.380 --> 06:46:27.959
lake, their wings alight with flames

06:46:27.959 --> 06:46:29.099
shrieking with pain.

06:46:29.159 --> 06:46:32.700
The fire bombs were just logs set on fire

06:46:32.700 --> 06:46:35.639
but they caused terrible damage as they

06:46:35.639 --> 06:46:37.500
crashed through the pavilion and knocked

06:46:37.500 --> 06:46:38.700
sea wings out of the air.

06:46:38.759 --> 06:46:42.299
The Skywings found us, said one of the

06:46:42.299 --> 06:46:44.340
guards, looking skyward in terror.

06:46:44.459 --> 06:46:47.340
As he said it, they all saw a wing of red

06:46:47.340 --> 06:46:50.639
and orange dragons soar overhead, dropping

06:46:50.639 --> 06:46:52.860
more bombs and breathing more fire down

06:46:52.860 --> 06:46:53.639
on the canopy.

06:46:53.700 --> 06:46:55.380
But how?

06:46:55.380 --> 06:46:56.520
said the 2nd guard.

06:46:56.580 --> 06:46:59.639
Tsunami thought of the hole left in the

06:46:59.639 --> 06:47:01.560
canopy when blister ripped webs out of

06:47:01.560 --> 06:47:02.459
it.

06:47:02.520 --> 06:47:04.259
Would that have been enough to lead the

06:47:04.259 --> 06:47:05.099
sky wings here?

06:47:05.159 --> 06:47:06.599
So quickly?

06:47:06.659 --> 06:47:08.279
What were the chances?

06:47:08.340 --> 06:47:10.799
A scout had spotted the hole, reported

06:47:10.799 --> 06:47:13.200
back, and gathered the forces for an

06:47:13.200 --> 06:47:14.520
attack only a day later.

06:47:14.580 --> 06:47:16.319
It had to be something else.

06:47:16.439 --> 06:47:19.799
She looked down and saw the lake water

06:47:19.799 --> 06:47:21.959
churning as frantic dragons tried to

06:47:21.959 --> 06:47:23.639
shove their way into the exit tunnel.

06:47:23.700 --> 06:47:27.180
Only one way in meant only one way out

06:47:27.180 --> 06:47:29.459
and it wasn't big enough for everyone at

06:47:29.459 --> 06:47:29.700
once.

06:47:29.759 --> 06:47:33.180
She felt sick at the thought of all those

06:47:33.180 --> 06:47:35.099
dragons crammed into the small space

06:47:35.099 --> 06:47:35.580
together.

06:47:35.639 --> 06:47:39.540
There was one other way, but flying out

06:47:39.540 --> 06:47:41.700
through the canopy, into the claws of the

06:47:41.700 --> 06:47:43.560
sky wings, could be suicide.

06:47:43.619 --> 06:47:46.680
Tsunami searched the mass of dragons for

06:47:46.680 --> 06:47:48.840
her mother, but she couldn't see ropes of

06:47:48.840 --> 06:47:51.000
pearls or wings the exact shade of her

06:47:51.000 --> 06:47:52.259
own anywhere.

06:47:52.380 --> 06:47:54.599
At least Coral wasn't one of the shapes

06:47:54.599 --> 06:47:56.700
with charred wings floating limply in the

06:47:56.700 --> 06:47:56.880
water.

06:47:56.939 --> 06:48:00.240
Blister was nowhere to be seen either.

06:48:00.299 --> 06:48:03.959
Shark swooped past, yelling order.

06:48:04.020 --> 06:48:06.720
Most of the dragons seemed too panic

06:48:06.720 --> 06:48:08.759
stricken to listen to him, but a few

06:48:08.759 --> 06:48:10.439
rallied around and followed him up into

06:48:10.439 --> 06:48:10.860
the sky.

06:48:10.919 --> 06:48:14.040
Surely they would be outnumbered, tsunami

06:48:14.040 --> 06:48:14.400
thought.

06:48:14.459 --> 06:48:16.319
Surely they didn't stand a chance.

06:48:16.380 --> 06:48:19.319
She took a step toward the edge and felt

06:48:19.319 --> 06:48:20.220
someone grab her tail.

06:48:20.279 --> 06:48:22.200
Don't do it.

06:48:22.259 --> 06:48:24.299
Clay said, pulling her back.

06:48:24.360 --> 06:48:26.340
I know you want to fight.

06:48:26.400 --> 06:48:28.319
But we can't lose you like that.

06:48:28.439 --> 06:48:30.779
Tsunami stopped.

06:48:30.840 --> 06:48:33.720
Every muscle in her body wanted to be up

06:48:33.720 --> 06:48:36.900
there. clawing at Skywing snouts and

06:48:36.900 --> 06:48:38.580
smashing them out of the sky with her

06:48:38.580 --> 06:48:38.819
tail.

06:48:38.880 --> 06:48:41.220
The impulsive thing to do.

06:48:41.279 --> 06:48:42.479
She thought.

06:48:42.540 --> 06:48:45.540
Or she could listen to her friends.

06:48:45.599 --> 06:48:48.720
She turned to the guards, who were all 3

06:48:48.720 --> 06:48:51.299
trembling with fear, their eyes fixed on

06:48:51.299 --> 06:48:52.860
the fiery canopy up above.

06:48:52.919 --> 06:48:55.139
Go, she said.

06:48:55.259 --> 06:48:57.180
Defending the palace is more important

06:48:57.180 --> 06:48:58.319
than guarding the prisoners.

06:48:58.439 --> 06:49:01.139
But one of them started.

06:49:01.200 --> 06:49:04.020
But we can't let you, you have to save

06:49:04.020 --> 06:49:06.060
yourselves, tsunami said.

06:49:06.119 --> 06:49:07.080
And so do we.

06:49:07.139 --> 06:49:10.380
Trust me, fate wants the dragonettes of

06:49:10.380 --> 06:49:11.400
destiny to survive this.

06:49:11.459 --> 06:49:14.520
The guards didn't stick around to argue.

06:49:14.580 --> 06:49:17.340
They launched themselves off the ledge

06:49:17.340 --> 06:49:20.099
and tsunami saw one fly down to join the

06:49:20.099 --> 06:49:22.439
crush of dragons around the tunnel, but

06:49:22.439 --> 06:49:24.900
the other 2 flew up to fight alongside

06:49:24.900 --> 06:49:25.740
Commander Shark.

06:49:25.799 --> 06:49:28.799
She spun and ran back to the prison

06:49:28.799 --> 06:49:30.959
island, where webs and riptide were

06:49:30.959 --> 06:49:31.259
trapped.

06:49:31.319 --> 06:49:34.319
Clay was already there, fumbling with a

06:49:34.319 --> 06:49:34.919
chain on the wall.

06:49:34.979 --> 06:49:37.259
Tsunami showed him which way to pull it.

06:49:37.319 --> 06:49:39.000
Can you hear me?

06:49:39.060 --> 06:49:40.799
She called to the prisoners.

06:49:40.860 --> 06:49:42.240
We're getting you out of there.

06:49:42.299 --> 06:49:43.799
Get ready to fly.

06:49:43.919 --> 06:49:45.779
Tsunami?

06:49:45.840 --> 06:49:48.540
Riptide's voice was lost in the creaking

06:49:48.540 --> 06:49:50.159
and clanking and rumbling of things

06:49:50.159 --> 06:49:51.419
moving in the ceiling.

06:49:51.479 --> 06:49:54.720
Abruptly, the water stopped flowing, and

06:49:54.720 --> 06:49:56.639
tsunami found herself standing across

06:49:56.639 --> 06:49:58.319
from the sky blue sea wing.

06:49:58.380 --> 06:50:00.299
He smiled at her.

06:50:00.360 --> 06:50:02.939
Hey there, she said.

06:50:03.000 --> 06:50:05.340
The dragonettes of destiny specialize in

06:50:05.340 --> 06:50:06.540
dramatic rescues, you know.

06:50:06.540 --> 06:50:07.560
Are you impressed?

06:50:07.680 --> 06:50:11.759
Very, he said. hopping over the moat to

06:50:11.759 --> 06:50:12.419
land beside her.

06:50:12.479 --> 06:50:15.599
Webb staggered after him, landing

06:50:15.599 --> 06:50:16.680
unevenly on the stone.

06:50:16.740 --> 06:50:19.259
It didn't seem like a good sign that a

06:50:19.259 --> 06:50:21.060
thin line of blood was still trickling

06:50:21.060 --> 06:50:22.139
from his ear.

06:50:22.200 --> 06:50:24.959
Another pair of fiery logs crashed past

06:50:24.959 --> 06:50:27.840
outside. and more screams echoed from

06:50:27.840 --> 06:50:28.139
below.

06:50:28.200 --> 06:50:31.020
Riptide flared his wings, looking

06:50:31.020 --> 06:50:32.520
startled and horrified.

06:50:32.639 --> 06:50:36.119
The palace is under attack, tsunami

06:50:36.119 --> 06:50:36.659
explained.

06:50:36.720 --> 06:50:39.840
It'll make escape tricky, but wait

06:50:39.840 --> 06:50:42.240
Riptide said, catching one of her

06:50:42.240 --> 06:50:42.720
talons.

06:50:42.779 --> 06:50:44.220
Tsunami.

06:50:44.279 --> 06:50:45.779
I have to tell you something.

06:50:45.840 --> 06:50:49.500
I, I do work for the talons of peace.

06:50:49.560 --> 06:50:51.900
Tsunami stared at him.

06:50:51.959 --> 06:50:55.020
Her mother was right about riptide?

06:50:55.080 --> 06:50:57.659
He was working with the dragons who'd

06:50:57.659 --> 06:50:58.380
ruined her life.

06:50:58.439 --> 06:51:01.200
She'd always hated the talent of peace.

06:51:01.259 --> 06:51:03.119
How could she have fallen for one of

06:51:03.119 --> 06:51:03.299
them?

06:51:03.360 --> 06:51:06.060
Please, listen.

06:51:06.119 --> 06:51:08.700
I joined them because I wanted to find

06:51:08.700 --> 06:51:10.919
out more about my father, but they

06:51:10.919 --> 06:51:12.659
wouldn't tell me anything except that he

06:51:12.659 --> 06:51:12.959
was safe.

06:51:13.020 --> 06:51:14.700
He looked down.

06:51:14.759 --> 06:51:16.979
I've been working with them for a few

06:51:16.979 --> 06:51:19.439
years now, passing them information about

06:51:19.439 --> 06:51:20.220
the sea wings.

06:51:20.279 --> 06:51:22.979
Sounds like betrayal to me.

06:51:23.040 --> 06:51:26.220
Tsunami thought, although she wasn't sure

06:51:26.220 --> 06:51:27.959
whether she felt more betrayed for her

06:51:27.959 --> 06:51:29.400
tribe or for herself.

06:51:29.520 --> 06:51:34.139
You have a very bad habit, she said, of

06:51:34.139 --> 06:51:35.819
not telling me some critically important

06:51:35.819 --> 06:51:36.240
things.

06:51:36.299 --> 06:51:38.040
I know.

06:51:38.099 --> 06:51:38.939
I'm sorry.

06:51:39.000 --> 06:51:40.979
I was meeting with one of their agents

06:51:40.979 --> 06:51:41.939
right before I met you.

06:51:42.060 --> 06:51:45.240
Tsunami remembered the dragon with the

06:51:45.240 --> 06:51:46.799
black spirals on his scales.

06:51:46.860 --> 06:51:49.860
He told me to keep an eye out, in case

06:51:49.860 --> 06:51:51.840
the dragonettes of destiny showed up in

06:51:51.840 --> 06:51:52.680
the kingdom of the sea.

06:51:52.740 --> 06:51:55.979
Tsunami pulled her talon out of his

06:51:55.979 --> 06:51:56.340
grasp.

06:51:56.459 --> 06:51:59.520
Riptide had acted surprised to hear the

06:51:59.520 --> 06:52:00.720
talons even existed.

06:52:00.779 --> 06:52:03.299
He'd pretended not to know anything about

06:52:03.299 --> 06:52:04.740
the dragonettes of destiny.

06:52:04.799 --> 06:52:08.220
Clearly, he was a good actor, hiding a

06:52:08.220 --> 06:52:10.139
secret like this while living in the

06:52:10.139 --> 06:52:10.979
tribe all these years.

06:52:11.040 --> 06:52:14.279
So could she believe anything he'd said

06:52:14.279 --> 06:52:14.580
to her?

06:52:14.639 --> 06:52:17.700
Blood trickled from the gash on his side

06:52:17.700 --> 06:52:18.299
as he moved?

06:52:18.419 --> 06:52:22.020
I stayed close to make sure you and the

06:52:22.020 --> 06:52:23.099
other dragonettes were safe.

06:52:23.220 --> 06:52:26.279
He spread his wings and held out his

06:52:26.279 --> 06:52:27.479
talons to tsunami.

06:52:27.540 --> 06:52:29.880
I'm sorry, I couldn't tell you the

06:52:29.880 --> 06:52:30.119
truth.

06:52:30.180 --> 06:52:32.819
I didn't think you'd trust me if you

06:52:32.819 --> 06:52:32.939
knew.

06:52:33.060 --> 06:52:35.159
He was right about that.

06:52:35.220 --> 06:52:37.979
But she didn't particularly trust him now

06:52:37.979 --> 06:52:38.459
either.

06:52:38.580 --> 06:52:42.119
An enormous crash sounded outside as

06:52:42.119 --> 06:52:44.220
something smashed into the pavilion.

06:52:44.279 --> 06:52:47.459
We have to go, said Glory from behind

06:52:47.459 --> 06:52:48.419
tsunami.

06:52:48.479 --> 06:52:51.900
For once, she didn't add anything snide

06:52:51.900 --> 06:52:53.639
and tsunami wondered if she'd overheard

06:52:53.639 --> 06:52:54.840
Riptide's confession.

06:52:54.900 --> 06:53:00.119
Um, Clay's voice said behind them, Tsunami

06:53:00.119 --> 06:53:02.159
Webbs, do we know this dragon?

06:53:02.220 --> 06:53:05.639
They all turned and saw a large mud wing

06:53:05.639 --> 06:53:07.380
looming in the mouth of the cave.

06:53:07.439 --> 06:53:09.840
Her brown wings were creased with soot

06:53:09.840 --> 06:53:12.240
and a horrible scar pulled down one

06:53:12.240 --> 06:53:13.560
corner of her mouth into a strange

06:53:13.560 --> 06:53:14.939
grimace.

06:53:15.000 --> 06:53:17.759
Webbs flicked his tail in surprise.

06:53:17.819 --> 06:53:19.979
I do, he said.

06:53:20.040 --> 06:53:22.619
She's with the talons of peace.

06:53:22.680 --> 06:53:23.639
She saved my life.

06:53:23.700 --> 06:53:25.139
Crocodile.

06:53:25.200 --> 06:53:26.459
What are you doing here?

06:53:26.580 --> 06:53:28.380
The Medwing chuckled.

06:53:28.439 --> 06:53:30.599
Poor webs.

06:53:30.659 --> 06:53:32.580
So wrong in so many ways.

06:53:32.639 --> 06:53:35.400
She stepped into the cavern and gave the

06:53:35.400 --> 06:53:36.840
dragonettes an appraising look.

06:53:36.900 --> 06:53:40.020
These are the brats the talons are so

06:53:40.020 --> 06:53:40.680
obsessed with.

06:53:40.740 --> 06:53:42.360
Scrawny.

06:53:42.479 --> 06:53:45.240
She lashed her tail, but the sky wings

06:53:45.240 --> 06:53:47.400
want you back anyway, for the next queen

06:53:47.400 --> 06:53:48.599
to play with, I assume.

06:53:48.659 --> 06:53:51.479
Queen Scarlet is dead?

06:53:51.540 --> 06:53:52.680
Glory blurted.

06:53:52.740 --> 06:53:53.759
For sure?

06:53:53.819 --> 06:53:57.299
You're not working with the sky wings?

06:53:57.360 --> 06:53:58.860
Webbs cried at the same time.

06:53:58.919 --> 06:54:02.400
Of course I am, Crocodile said.

06:54:02.459 --> 06:54:04.979
Who knew that infiltrating the talons of

06:54:04.979 --> 06:54:06.900
peace would be so useful.

06:54:06.959 --> 06:54:09.419
I never thought I'd get the chance to

06:54:09.419 --> 06:54:11.639
follow an idiot seawing back to the

06:54:11.639 --> 06:54:13.500
secret palace we've been searching for

06:54:13.500 --> 06:54:14.159
all this time.

06:54:14.220 --> 06:54:18.180
Webbs blanched, and his wings drooped

06:54:18.180 --> 06:54:20.819
heavily, as if a whole new mountain of

06:54:20.819 --> 06:54:22.319
guilt had just landed on him.

06:54:22.380 --> 06:54:26.580
Plus, bonus dragonettes of destiny

06:54:26.580 --> 06:54:29.639
crocodile said, I am so getting a

06:54:29.639 --> 06:54:30.119
promotion.

06:54:30.180 --> 06:54:33.959
Is Queen Scarlet really dead?

06:54:34.020 --> 06:54:35.700
Glory asked again.

06:54:35.759 --> 06:54:39.119
Nobody knows, Crocodile said with a

06:54:39.119 --> 06:54:39.599
shrug.

06:54:39.659 --> 06:54:41.040
She seems to have vanished.

06:54:41.099 --> 06:54:43.500
Nobody can even tell the same story about

06:54:43.500 --> 06:54:44.159
what happened to her.

06:54:44.220 --> 06:54:48.540
Well, lucky you, said Glory.

06:54:48.659 --> 06:54:50.459
You're about to find out.

06:54:50.520 --> 06:54:54.119
She snapped her mouth open, and shot her

06:54:54.119 --> 06:54:56.220
black venom straight into crocodile's

06:54:56.220 --> 06:54:56.400
eyes.

06:54:56.459 --> 06:54:59.819
The mud wing bellowed in agony and fell

06:54:59.819 --> 06:55:02.520
back, scraping her wings against the cave

06:55:02.520 --> 06:55:02.880
walls.

06:55:02.939 --> 06:55:06.119
She clawed at her snout, but the acid was

06:55:06.119 --> 06:55:07.680
already eating into her scales.

06:55:07.740 --> 06:55:10.200
With another shrieking roar.

06:55:10.259 --> 06:55:12.959
She shot out of the cave and dove for the

06:55:12.959 --> 06:55:13.560
lake below.

06:55:13.619 --> 06:55:17.819
Let's go, tsunami shouted, spreading her

06:55:17.819 --> 06:55:18.060
wings.

06:55:18.119 --> 06:55:21.360
The 5 dragonettes, riptide, and webs

06:55:21.360 --> 06:55:22.979
burst out of the cave.

06:55:23.099 --> 06:55:24.360
Below them.

06:55:24.419 --> 06:55:26.700
Dragons were still trying to shove their

06:55:26.700 --> 06:55:29.040
way into the tunnel, and the churning

06:55:29.040 --> 06:55:31.080
mass of wings and scales around the exit

06:55:31.080 --> 06:55:33.360
didn't look any smaller than it had

06:55:33.360 --> 06:55:33.540
before.

06:55:33.599 --> 06:55:37.619
We can't go that way, Starflight said.

06:55:37.680 --> 06:55:40.080
We'll have to go out through the canopy.

06:55:40.139 --> 06:55:41.400
Tsunami said.

06:55:41.459 --> 06:55:44.400
They all looked up and saw 3 red dragons

06:55:44.400 --> 06:55:45.959
shoot by, breathing fire.

06:55:46.020 --> 06:55:49.619
I don't really love that plan either

06:55:49.619 --> 06:55:52.380
Starflight said, in a smaller voice.

06:55:52.439 --> 06:55:54.959
Tsunami spotted her mother at last.

06:55:55.020 --> 06:55:57.540
Queen Coral was standing on the library

06:55:57.540 --> 06:56:00.419
level, casting one last look at her

06:56:00.419 --> 06:56:00.840
scrolls.

06:56:00.959 --> 06:56:03.959
They weren't on fire yet, but they were

06:56:03.959 --> 06:56:06.060
the most flammable things in the palace.

06:56:06.119 --> 06:56:08.639
If they went up, the smoke would fill the

06:56:08.639 --> 06:56:10.500
palace and kill even more dragons.

06:56:10.560 --> 06:56:13.380
Her littlest dragonette was wrapped

06:56:13.380 --> 06:56:15.959
tightly to the queen's chest, Anemones

06:56:15.959 --> 06:56:17.520
stood on the edge of the pavilion

06:56:17.520 --> 06:56:19.380
unharnessed, waiting.

06:56:19.439 --> 06:56:22.439
As they watched, Queen Coral began

06:56:22.439 --> 06:56:24.299
flinging her scrolls over the edge into

06:56:24.299 --> 06:56:24.659
the water.

06:56:24.779 --> 06:56:28.319
After a moment, Anemone joined her, and

06:56:28.319 --> 06:56:30.299
the queen paused to touch her daughter's

06:56:30.299 --> 06:56:31.080
head affectionately.

06:56:31.139 --> 06:56:33.659
She can be a good mother.

06:56:33.720 --> 06:56:37.259
Tsunami thought sadly, and a good queen.

06:56:37.380 --> 06:56:40.500
She wondered if there was any version of

06:56:40.500 --> 06:56:42.360
Pyria where they could have grown up as a

06:56:42.360 --> 06:56:42.659
family.

06:56:42.720 --> 06:56:47.040
She and Coral, and Gil, and Anemone, and

06:56:47.040 --> 06:56:50.580
Aucklet, normal and happy, with no one

06:56:50.580 --> 06:56:51.540
trying to kill anyone.

06:56:51.599 --> 06:56:53.819
Too late now.

06:56:53.880 --> 06:56:56.220
She had this other family.

06:56:56.279 --> 06:56:59.459
Not at all normal, and they needed her

06:56:59.459 --> 06:57:00.180
more than anyone.

06:57:00.299 --> 06:57:03.299
She soared up toward the tattered remains

06:57:03.299 --> 06:57:04.139
of the canopy.

06:57:04.200 --> 06:57:06.959
Another flaming log came barreling down

06:57:06.959 --> 06:57:09.599
toward them, and tsunami yanked glory out

06:57:09.599 --> 06:57:10.139
of its path.

06:57:10.200 --> 06:57:13.200
It plummeted toward the lake, careening

06:57:13.200 --> 06:57:14.580
off the pavilion and setting another

06:57:14.580 --> 06:57:16.860
dragon on fire as it fell.

06:57:16.919 --> 06:57:19.080
Sonny, tsunami called.

06:57:19.139 --> 06:57:21.840
Starflight, stable O'Clay's wings.

06:57:21.959 --> 06:57:24.779
Clay stretched his fireproof wings out

06:57:24.779 --> 06:57:27.060
and the 2 dragonettes ducked underneath

06:57:27.060 --> 06:57:28.200
on either side of him.

06:57:28.380 --> 06:57:31.439
Tsunami surged ahead to scout the sky

06:57:31.439 --> 06:57:32.220
outside.

06:57:32.279 --> 06:57:35.279
She flew out past the smoking leaves and

06:57:35.279 --> 06:57:37.020
nearly collided with a sky wing.

06:57:37.080 --> 06:57:40.380
He held a log in his claws, and was about

06:57:40.380 --> 06:57:42.840
to breathe his fire onto it before

06:57:42.840 --> 06:57:45.479
dropping it into the palace, but tsunami

06:57:45.479 --> 06:57:47.819
sent him swerving out of the way, and

06:57:47.819 --> 06:57:50.040
when she saw what he held, she slammed

06:57:50.040 --> 06:57:51.419
her tail into his side.

06:57:51.479 --> 06:57:53.639
The law flew out of his claws into the

06:57:53.639 --> 06:57:55.619
ocean, and he tumbled after it.

06:57:55.680 --> 06:57:59.099
Five more sky wings were flying around in

06:57:59.099 --> 06:58:00.360
formation to make another pass.

06:58:00.419 --> 06:58:02.939
Off to her left.

06:58:03.000 --> 06:58:05.580
Tsunami spotted a wing of huge mud wings

06:58:05.580 --> 06:58:06.959
carrying extra logs.

06:58:07.020 --> 06:58:10.080
The sky wings zipped up to them, took a

06:58:10.080 --> 06:58:12.299
log apiece, and flew back to the palace

06:58:12.299 --> 06:58:13.139
to set them alight.

06:58:13.200 --> 06:58:15.840
She hissed with anger.

06:58:15.900 --> 06:58:19.200
This was a brutal, carefully planned

06:58:19.200 --> 06:58:21.779
attack on a palace full of dragonettes

06:58:21.779 --> 06:58:22.919
and innocent civilians.

06:58:22.979 --> 06:58:25.740
There was nothing fair or honorable about

06:58:25.740 --> 06:58:26.340
this bite.

06:58:26.400 --> 06:58:29.759
Shark and his sea wings were fighting

06:58:29.759 --> 06:58:31.680
another set of sky wings in the sky to

06:58:31.680 --> 06:58:32.099
her right.

06:58:32.220 --> 06:58:35.700
Fire blazed, and talons clashed against

06:58:35.700 --> 06:58:36.360
scales.

06:58:36.419 --> 06:58:38.400
She wanted to join them.

06:58:38.459 --> 06:58:41.880
She itched to be over there, slashing and

06:58:41.880 --> 06:58:44.340
clawing, and battling the intruders who'd

06:58:44.340 --> 06:58:46.139
dared attack her family's palace.

06:58:46.200 --> 06:58:48.180
That was the kind of fighting.

06:58:48.240 --> 06:58:49.380
She wouldn't feel guilty about

06:58:49.380 --> 06:58:49.799
afterward.

06:58:49.860 --> 06:58:53.040
But the other dragonettes were flying up

06:58:53.040 --> 06:58:55.080
beside her now, and she couldn't leave

06:58:55.080 --> 06:58:55.380
them.

06:58:55.439 --> 06:58:59.580
That way, she said, jerking her head at

06:58:59.580 --> 06:59:01.500
the biggest swath of clear sky.

06:59:01.560 --> 06:59:04.380
From the sun she guessed it was south

06:59:04.380 --> 06:59:06.299
south toward the continent, which was

06:59:06.299 --> 06:59:07.200
where they needed to go.

06:59:07.259 --> 06:59:10.740
Glory shot past her immediately, and as

06:59:10.740 --> 06:59:13.020
she reached the sky, her scales turned

06:59:13.020 --> 06:59:15.900
pale blue and white and gold, and she

06:59:15.900 --> 06:59:17.099
shimmered into nothingness.

06:59:17.159 --> 06:59:20.159
Tsunami couldn't even see a ripple in the

06:59:20.159 --> 06:59:21.659
air as the rain wing flew away.

06:59:21.720 --> 06:59:25.439
Clay went next, spreading his wings to

06:59:25.439 --> 06:59:27.240
shield Sonny and Starflight.

06:59:27.240 --> 06:59:29.639
A sky wing in the battle spotted them and

06:59:29.639 --> 06:59:31.080
swerved in their direction.

06:59:31.259 --> 06:59:34.380
Tsunami lunged at her, grabbed her snout

06:59:34.380 --> 06:59:36.180
and kicked her underbelly as hard as she

06:59:36.180 --> 06:59:36.419
could.

06:59:36.479 --> 06:59:39.060
The Skywing kicked her back, sending

06:59:39.060 --> 06:59:41.700
bright arcs of pain along tsunami's

06:59:41.700 --> 06:59:42.779
fractured ribs.

06:59:42.840 --> 06:59:45.599
Tsunami lost her grip, and the sky wing

06:59:45.599 --> 06:59:47.939
roared a blast of flame at Clay's

06:59:47.939 --> 06:59:48.479
departing back.

06:59:48.599 --> 06:59:52.200
He shuddered as the heat licked along his

06:59:52.200 --> 06:59:54.720
scales, but beat his wings and flew on

06:59:54.720 --> 06:59:56.759
the other 2 dragonettes safely

06:59:56.759 --> 06:59:57.240
protected.

06:59:57.299 --> 07:00:00.599
The sky wing blinked with astonishment as

07:00:00.599 --> 07:00:03.180
clay's wings faded back to brown instead

07:00:03.180 --> 07:00:05.520
of turning black or twisting into painful

07:00:05.520 --> 07:00:06.000
burns.

07:00:06.060 --> 07:00:09.840
Surprise, tsunami said, and punched her

07:00:09.840 --> 07:00:10.259
in the snout.

07:00:10.319 --> 07:00:13.500
The sky wing crumpled, and fell toward

07:00:13.500 --> 07:00:15.959
the ocean, landing with a splash and

07:00:15.959 --> 07:00:17.880
banishing instantly below the waves.

07:00:17.939 --> 07:00:21.540
Riptide soared up out of the canopy

07:00:21.540 --> 07:00:23.639
twisting around to make sure Webbs was

07:00:23.639 --> 07:00:24.240
safe behind him.

07:00:24.299 --> 07:00:27.119
Tsunami turned to fly south and heard

07:00:27.119 --> 07:00:28.860
riptide call her name.

07:00:28.919 --> 07:00:32.459
I have to help them, he called, lashing

07:00:32.459 --> 07:00:34.200
his tail toward the fighting sea wings.

07:00:34.259 --> 07:00:36.599
But they'll put you back in prison

07:00:36.599 --> 07:00:38.099
tsunami protested.

07:00:38.159 --> 07:00:40.500
They'll punish you because we escaped.

07:00:40.560 --> 07:00:42.779
Maybe, he said.

07:00:42.840 --> 07:00:45.779
Probably, but I have to help if I can.

07:00:45.840 --> 07:00:47.700
This is my home.

07:00:47.700 --> 07:00:50.880
She knew exactly how he felt.

07:00:50.939 --> 07:00:52.979
Tsunami.

07:00:53.040 --> 07:00:54.119
He paused.

07:00:54.240 --> 07:00:55.919
I really am sorry.

07:00:55.979 --> 07:00:57.360
I hope next time.

07:00:57.419 --> 07:01:00.959
Well, I hope there is a next time.

07:01:01.020 --> 07:01:03.419
When things are better for everyone.

07:01:03.479 --> 07:01:05.759
She hoped so too.

07:01:05.819 --> 07:01:09.119
She wasn't sure she'd forgiven him, but

07:01:09.119 --> 07:01:11.099
she wanted the chance to decide.

07:01:11.159 --> 07:01:13.680
She wanted him to survive the war, and

07:01:13.680 --> 07:01:15.779
she wanted to meet him again in a world

07:01:15.779 --> 07:01:19.080
with no talons of peace, or destinies, or

07:01:19.080 --> 07:01:20.099
secrets to worry about.

07:01:20.220 --> 07:01:22.860
But there wasn't time to say all that.

07:01:22.919 --> 07:01:25.860
Tsunami flashed one of the patterns he

07:01:25.860 --> 07:01:26.459
taught her.

07:01:26.520 --> 07:01:27.659
All right.

07:01:27.720 --> 07:01:32.279
Then she added, Squid Brain, and Riptide

07:01:32.279 --> 07:01:34.200
smiled before turning to fly away into

07:01:34.200 --> 07:01:34.979
the heart of the battle.

07:01:35.099 --> 07:01:38.639
Webbs and tsunami swerved south together

07:01:38.639 --> 07:01:40.500
wings beating side by side.

07:01:40.619 --> 07:01:42.720
But other wing beats were close behind

07:01:42.720 --> 07:01:43.020
them.

07:01:43.080 --> 07:01:45.900
Tsunami twisted just in time to see

07:01:45.900 --> 07:01:48.180
blister, lunge out of the canopy and

07:01:48.180 --> 07:01:49.619
seize webs by the tail.

07:01:49.680 --> 07:01:52.439
She yanked him back toward her, and

07:01:52.439 --> 07:01:54.240
stabbed her poisonous barb toward his

07:01:54.240 --> 07:01:54.479
heart.

07:01:54.540 --> 07:01:57.779
With a yell, tsunami barreled into them

07:01:57.779 --> 07:01:59.819
knocking the sandwing off of webs.

07:01:59.880 --> 07:02:01.979
Blister fell back toward the palace

07:02:01.979 --> 07:02:02.639
hissing.

07:02:02.700 --> 07:02:05.700
Tsunami grabbed webs by his front talons

07:02:05.700 --> 07:02:06.599
and towed him after her.

07:02:06.659 --> 07:02:10.139
A few wing beats later, Webbs groaned

07:02:10.139 --> 07:02:10.500
softly.

07:02:10.560 --> 07:02:12.540
Did she get you?

07:02:12.659 --> 07:02:13.979
Tsunami demanded.

07:02:14.040 --> 07:02:19.619
She missed my heart. he said He lifted

07:02:19.619 --> 07:02:21.900
his wing to show an oozing graze near his

07:02:21.900 --> 07:02:22.139
tail.

07:02:22.259 --> 07:02:25.560
It's still poisonous, he said.

07:02:25.619 --> 07:02:28.560
We'll find a way to fix it, Tsunami

07:02:28.560 --> 07:02:28.860
said.

07:02:28.919 --> 07:02:31.740
Just keep flying until we get to land.

07:02:31.799 --> 07:02:35.159
She looked back again, and saw blister

07:02:35.159 --> 07:02:37.259
hovering in the air, watching them go.

07:02:37.319 --> 07:02:40.860
Her cold, glittering black eyes seemed to

07:02:40.860 --> 07:02:43.380
follow tsunami all the way to the edge of

07:02:43.380 --> 07:02:43.619
the sky.

07:02:43.740 --> 07:02:48.360
Chapter 28.

07:02:48.599 --> 07:02:51.599
Tsunami was on a beach again.

07:02:51.659 --> 07:02:55.619
This time it was dark, long after sunset

07:02:55.619 --> 07:02:58.919
and small stars shone in the sky, like

07:02:58.919 --> 07:03:00.840
the silver scales on the underside of

07:03:00.840 --> 07:03:02.459
Starflight's wings.

07:03:02.520 --> 07:03:05.279
Tsunamis stared down at the waves, lapping

07:03:05.279 --> 07:03:06.299
over her talons.

07:03:06.360 --> 07:03:08.939
She wondered if she'd ever see riptide

07:03:08.939 --> 07:03:09.180
again.

07:03:09.240 --> 07:03:13.979
Or anemone, or Aucklet, or her mother.

07:03:14.040 --> 07:03:17.400
I know it's dark, Starflight said

07:03:17.400 --> 07:03:18.419
uncomfortably behind her.

07:03:18.479 --> 07:03:21.540
But tsunami sighed.

07:03:21.720 --> 07:03:23.819
But we should stay under the trees.

07:03:23.880 --> 07:03:26.520
She stood up and followed him into the

07:03:26.520 --> 07:03:29.340
woods, shaking the sand off her talons.

07:03:29.400 --> 07:03:31.860
I am trying to be more like you, you know

07:03:31.860 --> 07:03:33.240
she said to him.

07:03:33.299 --> 07:03:35.819
I'm trying to stop and think and use my

07:03:35.819 --> 07:03:38.520
head, and all that smart stuff, but it

07:03:38.520 --> 07:03:40.020
drives me a little crazy sometimes.

07:03:40.080 --> 07:03:43.740
Starflight stumbled on a tree root and

07:03:43.740 --> 07:03:44.819
turned to stare at her.

07:03:44.880 --> 07:03:46.619
Be more like me?

07:03:46.680 --> 07:03:47.759
he echoed.

07:03:47.880 --> 07:03:49.500
Why would you want to do that?

07:03:49.560 --> 07:03:52.439
I wish I were anything like you

07:03:52.439 --> 07:03:53.700
especially brave.

07:03:53.759 --> 07:03:56.700
Tsunami brushed his wing with hers.

07:03:56.759 --> 07:03:59.700
You're all right the way you are, she

07:03:59.700 --> 07:04:00.119
said.

07:04:00.180 --> 07:04:02.459
Someone has to be the thoughtful, careful

07:04:02.459 --> 07:04:05.159
one, and you've made blister pretty mad.

07:04:05.220 --> 07:04:06.720
That took some courage.

07:04:06.840 --> 07:04:09.779
Besides, I don't think this group could

07:04:09.779 --> 07:04:10.680
handle 2 of me.

07:04:10.740 --> 07:04:13.799
In the moonlight, she caught a half smile

07:04:13.799 --> 07:04:15.419
flitting across his face.

07:04:15.479 --> 07:04:19.439
Webbs lay on a patch of moss, breathing

07:04:19.439 --> 07:04:20.700
in a nasty shallow way.

07:04:20.759 --> 07:04:24.119
Sonny was curled up beside him, so her

07:04:24.119 --> 07:04:25.619
scales could give him a little warmth.

07:04:25.680 --> 07:04:28.500
Clay was peering at the scratch near his

07:04:28.500 --> 07:04:31.200
tail, which was still oozing, and

07:04:31.200 --> 07:04:32.880
starting to turn black around the edges.

07:04:33.000 --> 07:04:36.540
We need help, Clay said.

07:04:36.599 --> 07:04:39.240
I have no idea how to fix this.

07:04:39.299 --> 07:04:41.819
His expression was woeful.

07:04:41.880 --> 07:04:44.759
Who would know how to cure someone of

07:04:44.759 --> 07:04:45.659
sandwing venom?

07:04:45.720 --> 07:04:46.799
Sonny asked.

07:04:46.860 --> 07:04:48.659
Sandwings, I guess?

07:04:48.720 --> 07:04:51.419
She answered herself, but I don't know

07:04:51.419 --> 07:04:52.860
where we'd find one we could trust.

07:04:52.919 --> 07:04:55.619
The talons of peace?

07:04:55.680 --> 07:04:57.959
Starflight suggested doubtfully.

07:04:58.020 --> 07:05:00.659
I can't go back there.

07:05:00.720 --> 07:05:04.439
Webb said, and you shouldn't either.

07:05:04.500 --> 07:05:07.439
Tsunami tilted her head at him

07:05:07.439 --> 07:05:07.919
curiously.

07:05:07.979 --> 07:05:10.680
After all of these years of being a good

07:05:10.680 --> 07:05:13.259
talent foot soldier, obeying their every

07:05:13.259 --> 07:05:15.779
command, suddenly he'd changed his mind.

07:05:15.840 --> 07:05:21.000
If crocodile was an infiltrator, he said

07:05:21.000 --> 07:05:22.020
catching her look.

07:05:22.080 --> 07:05:23.759
There could be others.

07:05:23.819 --> 07:05:27.659
I don't know who's safe for you, and

07:05:27.659 --> 07:05:28.439
who's not?

07:05:28.500 --> 07:05:30.299
Seriously.

07:05:30.360 --> 07:05:33.180
Even the good dragons all seem to have

07:05:33.180 --> 07:05:36.419
plans for us, tsunami said, thinking of

07:05:36.419 --> 07:05:36.720
her mother.

07:05:36.779 --> 07:05:40.259
Gosh, I hope Blaze is better than the

07:05:40.259 --> 07:05:42.540
other two, Sonny said fervently.

07:05:42.599 --> 07:05:45.299
Starflight winced, but didn't argue with

07:05:45.299 --> 07:05:45.479
her.

07:05:45.540 --> 07:05:48.840
We can probably find her with the ice

07:05:48.840 --> 07:05:51.959
wings, he said, but we'll have to be very

07:05:51.959 --> 07:05:53.040
very careful this time.

07:05:53.099 --> 07:05:56.220
Yeah, Clay agreed.

07:05:56.340 --> 07:05:59.279
I vote for not getting locked up ever

07:05:59.279 --> 07:05:59.700
again.

07:05:59.759 --> 07:06:03.419
Maybe we should try a different approach

07:06:03.419 --> 07:06:04.799
Glory suggested.

07:06:04.860 --> 07:06:07.619
Maybe this time we could not barge in

07:06:07.619 --> 07:06:09.900
yelling, we are the dragonettes of

07:06:09.900 --> 07:06:10.439
destiny.

07:06:10.500 --> 07:06:12.299
We're awesome and special.

07:06:12.360 --> 07:06:14.520
We'd make terrific prisoners.

07:06:14.580 --> 07:06:16.020
Just an idea.

07:06:16.080 --> 07:06:18.959
Do you know what we're supposed to do?

07:06:19.080 --> 07:06:21.240
Sonny asked Webbs, hopefully?

07:06:21.299 --> 07:06:24.180
Did the talents have any plans about how

07:06:24.180 --> 07:06:25.860
we could fulfill the prophecy?

07:06:25.919 --> 07:06:29.220
If they did, Webb said.

07:06:29.279 --> 07:06:31.500
They didn't share them with me.

07:06:31.560 --> 07:06:35.400
Awesome, Gloria muttered.

07:06:35.459 --> 07:06:37.259
Tsunami glanced at her.

07:06:37.319 --> 07:06:39.599
The rain wings scales were shades of

07:06:39.599 --> 07:06:42.299
black and dark green, blending in with a

07:06:42.299 --> 07:06:43.319
dark forest around them.

07:06:43.380 --> 07:06:45.180
An idea struck her.

07:06:45.240 --> 07:06:49.020
I know who might help Webbs with a poison

07:06:49.020 --> 07:06:49.680
tsunami said.

07:06:49.740 --> 07:06:51.000
Who?

07:06:51.119 --> 07:06:51.959
Clay asked.

07:06:52.020 --> 07:06:54.360
The rain wings, she said.

07:06:54.479 --> 07:06:57.299
Glory twisted around to give her a sharp

07:06:57.299 --> 07:06:57.540
look.

07:06:57.599 --> 07:06:59.279
Think about it.

07:06:59.340 --> 07:07:00.720
Tsunami went on.

07:07:00.779 --> 07:07:02.939
They have Venom too, obviously.

07:07:03.000 --> 07:07:05.159
They must know something about what to do

07:07:05.159 --> 07:07:06.779
when you poison the wrong dragon.

07:07:06.840 --> 07:07:11.520
True, Starflight said, even if it's a

07:07:11.520 --> 07:07:13.979
different kind of venom, that's still a

07:07:13.979 --> 07:07:14.340
good point.

07:07:14.400 --> 07:07:17.880
And then we can look for Glory's family

07:07:17.880 --> 07:07:20.459
Tsunami said, which I think is only

07:07:20.459 --> 07:07:20.819
fair.

07:07:20.880 --> 07:07:24.419
Glory's face was expressionless, but

07:07:24.419 --> 07:07:26.819
small puffs of rose pink were blooming in

07:07:26.819 --> 07:07:27.479
her scales.

07:07:27.540 --> 07:07:29.880
Tsunami guessed that meant she was happy

07:07:29.880 --> 07:07:32.040
since it wasn't a color they saw very

07:07:32.040 --> 07:07:32.639
often on her.

07:07:32.700 --> 07:07:34.500
Are you?

07:07:35.159 --> 07:07:35.700
Are you sure?

07:07:35.759 --> 07:07:36.900
Glory said.

07:07:37.020 --> 07:07:39.360
That's what we should do next?

07:07:39.419 --> 07:07:42.779
Absolutely, Sonny said.

07:07:42.840 --> 07:07:44.939
We should definitely go find your home

07:07:44.939 --> 07:07:45.299
Glory.

07:07:45.360 --> 07:07:50.220
I bet it's beautiful, Clay said, in his

07:07:50.220 --> 07:07:53.099
sweet, earnest way, and your family will

07:07:53.099 --> 07:07:54.419
be so happy to see you.

07:07:54.479 --> 07:07:58.439
Webb let out a small groan, but when they

07:07:58.439 --> 07:08:00.959
turned to look at him, he closed his eyes

07:08:00.959 --> 07:08:02.340
as if he'd fallen asleep.

07:08:02.400 --> 07:08:06.000
Tsunami was sure he was pretending, but

07:08:06.000 --> 07:08:07.500
what they did next wasn't up to him

07:08:07.500 --> 07:08:07.799
anyway.

07:08:07.860 --> 07:08:12.000
It's also closer to here than most of the

07:08:12.000 --> 07:08:12.840
other tribes.

07:08:12.900 --> 07:08:14.639
Starflight pointed out.

07:08:14.700 --> 07:08:17.580
We have to cross the outskirts of mudwing

07:08:17.580 --> 07:08:19.740
territory, but the rainforest should be

07:08:19.740 --> 07:08:21.419
basically due southwest of here.

07:08:21.479 --> 07:08:25.259
I know that, Glory said crossly.

07:08:25.319 --> 07:08:27.119
You're not the only one who can memorize

07:08:27.119 --> 07:08:28.139
Maps, Starflight.

07:08:28.200 --> 07:08:31.080
Perfect, tsunami said.

07:08:31.139 --> 07:08:32.580
That's what we'll do.

07:08:32.700 --> 07:08:34.979
After we rest?

07:08:35.040 --> 07:08:36.720
Sonny asked hopefully.

07:08:36.779 --> 07:08:39.900
Tsunami thought she could keep flying all

07:08:39.900 --> 07:08:40.799
night as she had to.

07:08:40.860 --> 07:08:42.720
She wanted to put as much distance

07:08:42.720 --> 07:08:45.000
between them and blister as possible.

07:08:45.060 --> 07:08:47.279
She wanted to shove all the other

07:08:47.279 --> 07:08:49.259
dragonettes ahead of her all the way to

07:08:49.259 --> 07:08:50.639
the rainforest without stopping.

07:08:50.700 --> 07:08:54.299
But she looked at Sonny's tired eyes, and

07:08:54.299 --> 07:08:56.639
Starflight's drooping wings, and she

07:08:56.639 --> 07:08:58.560
settled herself close to Webb's tail.

07:08:58.619 --> 07:09:01.439
After we rest, she agreed.

07:09:01.500 --> 07:09:04.619
Sonny lay down again with a relieved

07:09:04.619 --> 07:09:05.040
sigh.

07:09:05.159 --> 07:09:08.580
A few moments later, tsunami saw her back

07:09:08.580 --> 07:09:11.099
rising and falling in deep sleep.

07:09:11.159 --> 07:09:14.279
Clay flopped down next to tsunami, his

07:09:14.279 --> 07:09:15.540
tail draped over hers.

07:09:15.599 --> 07:09:20.520
I'm sorry about your mother. he said, and

07:09:20.520 --> 07:09:21.240
the palace.

07:09:21.299 --> 07:09:25.080
And blister, and whirlpool.

07:09:25.139 --> 07:09:27.360
And riptide.

07:09:27.419 --> 07:09:30.299
And, all right, I get it.

07:09:30.360 --> 07:09:33.000
Tsunami said, cutting him off with a

07:09:33.000 --> 07:09:33.419
nudge.

07:09:33.479 --> 07:09:35.759
I hope they all make it through the

07:09:35.759 --> 07:09:37.799
attack, he said quietly.

07:09:37.860 --> 07:09:40.439
Me too, she said.

07:09:40.500 --> 07:09:43.259
But they'll be safe in the deep palace.

07:09:43.319 --> 07:09:45.840
At least they have somewhere else to go.

07:09:45.900 --> 07:09:47.639
She thought for a moment.

07:09:47.700 --> 07:09:50.520
And I think anemone will be a good queen

07:09:50.520 --> 07:09:50.939
one day.

07:09:51.000 --> 07:09:54.180
She has Coral's good qualities, but she

07:09:54.180 --> 07:09:56.040
thanks for herself, and she's still

07:09:56.040 --> 07:09:56.340
young.

07:09:56.400 --> 07:09:58.799
She'll get stronger and more independent

07:09:58.799 --> 07:09:59.520
as she gets older.

07:09:59.580 --> 07:10:03.360
If she's anything like you, independent

07:10:03.360 --> 07:10:05.880
will be an understatement, Glory said.

07:10:05.939 --> 07:10:08.220
She tucked herself along Clay's other

07:10:08.220 --> 07:10:10.139
side, and he put one wing over her.

07:10:10.259 --> 07:10:13.259
Starflight had tentatively nosed in

07:10:13.259 --> 07:10:15.479
beside Sonny, and now his eyes were

07:10:15.479 --> 07:10:16.380
closed as well.

07:10:16.439 --> 07:10:19.319
The kingdom of the sea wasn't the right

07:10:19.319 --> 07:10:22.680
place for me anyway, tsunami said, partly

07:10:22.680 --> 07:10:23.459
to convince herself.

07:10:23.520 --> 07:10:27.000
What about your great royal destiny?

07:10:27.060 --> 07:10:28.619
Glory teased.

07:10:28.680 --> 07:10:30.599
What about how you'd be the greatest

07:10:30.599 --> 07:10:31.919
queen of all time?

07:10:32.040 --> 07:10:35.700
Well, tsunami said with a shrug.

07:10:35.759 --> 07:10:37.560
I guess I'll have to settle for being the

07:10:37.560 --> 07:10:38.220
boss of you guys.

07:10:38.279 --> 07:10:42.720
Ha, Gloria said, but not in her usual

07:10:42.720 --> 07:10:43.560
sarcastic way.

07:10:43.619 --> 07:10:46.380
Amused yellow bubbles floated through her

07:10:46.380 --> 07:10:48.540
wings, and she reached over to nose

07:10:48.540 --> 07:10:49.680
tsunami's shoulder.

07:10:49.740 --> 07:10:52.259
You can certainly keep trying.

07:10:52.380 --> 07:10:57.060
I will. tsunami thought, but not because

07:10:57.060 --> 07:10:58.979
I think I'm the greatest, and everyone

07:10:58.979 --> 07:10:59.759
should listen to me.

07:10:59.819 --> 07:11:03.419
I'll keep trying to lead you because it's

07:11:03.419 --> 07:11:04.979
the only way I know to keep you all

07:11:04.979 --> 07:11:05.279
safe.

07:11:05.340 --> 07:11:08.279
And maybe sometimes I'll have to listen.

07:11:08.340 --> 07:11:10.860
The way mother listens to her counsel.

07:11:10.919 --> 07:11:13.500
And sometimes I won't be able to do

07:11:13.500 --> 07:11:14.520
exactly what I want.

07:11:14.580 --> 07:11:18.060
But even when she was mad at her friends

07:11:18.060 --> 07:11:19.740
she knew she could trust them.

07:11:19.799 --> 07:11:22.080
And she had to be the kind of dragon

07:11:22.080 --> 07:11:23.099
naked trust as well.

07:11:23.159 --> 07:11:26.880
She glanced up at the moons, 2 of them

07:11:26.880 --> 07:11:28.560
glowing pale and ghostly beyond the

07:11:28.560 --> 07:11:29.159
trees.

07:11:29.159 --> 07:11:31.680
There were more important things than

07:11:31.680 --> 07:11:32.459
becoming queen.

07:11:32.520 --> 07:11:34.680
Stopping the war was one of them.

07:11:34.740 --> 07:11:37.380
If the 5 of them were the only ones who

07:11:37.380 --> 07:11:39.599
could, then maybe that was what they had

07:11:39.599 --> 07:11:39.900
to do.

07:11:40.020 --> 07:11:43.020
Whether tsunami believed in destiny or

07:11:43.020 --> 07:11:43.200
not.

07:11:43.259 --> 07:11:46.380
She wriggled closer to her friends.

07:11:46.439 --> 07:11:49.259
All of them were sleeping soundly now.

07:11:49.319 --> 07:11:52.860
So the kingdom of the sea wasn't home

07:11:52.860 --> 07:11:54.479
after all, she thought.

07:11:54.540 --> 07:11:57.720
I wonder if anywhere ever will be.

07:11:57.840 --> 07:12:02.220
Epilogue.

07:12:02.279 --> 07:12:06.360
Well, Maro Sears said.

07:12:06.419 --> 07:12:09.060
So that didn't go as planned.

07:12:09.180 --> 07:12:12.959
You neglected to mention a few things

07:12:12.959 --> 07:12:14.880
said Blister calmly.

07:12:14.939 --> 07:12:18.299
Such is the fact that your 5 dragonettes

07:12:18.299 --> 07:12:20.040
are remarkably annoying.

07:12:20.099 --> 07:12:23.459
She draped her barbed tail pointedly over

07:12:23.459 --> 07:12:25.500
her talons and folded her wings back.

07:12:25.560 --> 07:12:29.040
Yes, said the night wing.

07:12:29.099 --> 07:12:30.180
True.

07:12:30.240 --> 07:12:32.639
But you might have tried to be a little

07:12:32.639 --> 07:12:35.220
less sinister at them.

07:12:35.279 --> 07:12:38.279
He stared down at the charred ruins of

07:12:38.279 --> 07:12:39.060
the summer palace.

07:12:39.119 --> 07:12:41.759
Fires were still smoldering on a few

07:12:41.759 --> 07:12:42.959
floors of the pavilion.

07:12:43.020 --> 07:12:46.200
Three days after the battle, nothing

07:12:46.200 --> 07:12:48.720
remained but smoke and corpses.

07:12:48.779 --> 07:12:53.819
At least Webbs is dead, he said.

07:12:53.880 --> 07:12:58.439
Should be by now, she answered, flipping

07:12:58.439 --> 07:12:59.279
her tail up and down.

07:12:59.340 --> 07:13:03.599
Queen Coral survived, he asked.

07:13:03.720 --> 07:13:07.080
And both her brats as well, said

07:13:07.080 --> 07:13:07.680
Blister.

07:13:07.740 --> 07:13:10.680
It wouldn't be convenient for me if she

07:13:10.680 --> 07:13:11.040
died.

07:13:11.099 --> 07:13:14.159
She bared her teeth and hissed softly.

07:13:14.220 --> 07:13:15.840
Of course.

07:13:15.959 --> 07:13:18.959
Now she's hiding in her deep palace where

07:13:18.959 --> 07:13:22.319
I can't get to her, and she insists that

07:13:22.319 --> 07:13:25.259
my secret weapon will be no use to me for

07:13:25.259 --> 07:13:26.159
years still.

07:13:26.220 --> 07:13:29.880
She's gotten all squeamish about anima's

07:13:29.880 --> 07:13:32.459
powers since finding out about her 1st

07:13:32.459 --> 07:13:32.939
daughter.

07:13:33.000 --> 07:13:36.119
Like she'd rather waste that little one's

07:13:36.119 --> 07:13:37.860
magic just to keep her from turning

07:13:37.860 --> 07:13:38.700
homicidal.

07:13:38.759 --> 07:13:41.880
Blister sighed a small burst of flame.

07:13:41.939 --> 07:13:44.880
It's not been my favorite week of the

07:13:44.880 --> 07:13:45.180
war.

07:13:45.240 --> 07:13:48.060
She batted away a piece of smoking

07:13:48.060 --> 07:13:48.779
foliage.

07:13:48.840 --> 07:13:54.840
So, Nightwing, I hope for your sake, that

07:13:54.840 --> 07:13:56.520
you bring me news I want to hear.

07:13:56.580 --> 07:14:02.220
There is another option, Morrissier

07:14:02.220 --> 07:14:02.520
said.

07:14:02.520 --> 07:14:05.220
But I'm not sure you'll like it much

07:14:05.220 --> 07:14:05.520
better.

07:14:05.639 --> 07:14:08.880
He spread his wings and beckoned to a

07:14:08.880 --> 07:14:10.619
green shape circling in the sky

07:14:10.619 --> 07:14:10.919
overhead.

07:14:10.979 --> 07:14:13.979
The sea wing landed carefully on the

07:14:13.979 --> 07:14:16.979
cliffside, vines crumbling to ashes below

07:14:16.979 --> 07:14:17.580
his claws.

07:14:17.580 --> 07:14:20.279
He glanced down at the palace and

07:14:20.279 --> 07:14:20.759
shuddered.

07:14:20.819 --> 07:14:23.939
Morosier noticed that he stayed well away

07:14:23.939 --> 07:14:24.720
from blister.

07:14:24.779 --> 07:14:28.500
Perhaps he'd heard, or guessed, what had

07:14:28.500 --> 07:14:29.819
happened to Kestrel.

07:14:29.880 --> 07:14:35.099
This is Nautilus, Marosir explained, one

07:14:35.099 --> 07:14:37.259
of the leaders of the talons of peace.

07:14:37.259 --> 07:14:40.619
Nautilus, explain your backup plan to the

07:14:40.619 --> 07:14:40.979
queen.

07:14:41.099 --> 07:14:45.000
Possible, future, queen.

07:14:45.060 --> 07:14:47.819
Nautilus corrected, then jumped back

07:14:47.819 --> 07:14:49.979
nervously as blister raised her poisonous

07:14:49.979 --> 07:14:50.279
tail.

07:14:50.340 --> 07:14:53.099
Err, he said quickly.

07:14:53.159 --> 07:14:56.159
We have a set of alternatives.

07:14:56.220 --> 07:14:59.220
Blister's black eyes glittered with

07:14:59.220 --> 07:14:59.580
interest.

07:14:59.639 --> 07:15:03.000
Alternatives, she said.

07:15:03.060 --> 07:15:04.020
Really?

07:15:04.080 --> 07:15:05.700
My, my.

07:15:05.759 --> 07:15:08.580
I had no idea the talons of peace could

07:15:08.580 --> 07:15:09.299
be so devious.

07:15:09.419 --> 07:15:12.299
Nautilus frowned.

07:15:12.360 --> 07:15:15.599
We prefer to think of it as planning for

07:15:15.599 --> 07:15:17.759
every contingency, he said.

07:15:17.819 --> 07:15:20.639
We have to do whatever's necessary so the

07:15:20.639 --> 07:15:21.419
prophecy will come true.

07:15:21.479 --> 07:15:26.939
Or true ish, Maro Seer interjected.

07:15:27.000 --> 07:15:30.360
Of course, Blister said.

07:15:30.419 --> 07:15:33.299
Dragonettes can be so unpredictable.

07:15:33.419 --> 07:15:35.220
You are very wise.

07:15:35.340 --> 07:15:39.299
Well, Nautilus said, pleased.

07:15:39.360 --> 07:15:41.520
It was my idea.

07:15:41.580 --> 07:15:45.900
Of course it was, she said.

07:15:45.959 --> 07:15:47.340
Very clever.

07:15:47.400 --> 07:15:50.880
We are talking about false dragonettes

07:15:50.880 --> 07:15:51.060
yes?

07:15:51.119 --> 07:15:54.599
But, rumbled Mars Zear.

07:15:54.659 --> 07:15:58.319
Yes, Nautilus said, his tail twitched.

07:15:58.380 --> 07:16:02.819
But they're, uh, not quite perfect.

07:16:02.880 --> 07:16:06.119
Hmm, said blister.

07:16:06.180 --> 07:16:08.040
Worse than the originals.

07:16:08.099 --> 07:16:09.659
Is that possible?

07:16:09.720 --> 07:16:12.419
Well, different.

07:16:12.540 --> 07:16:14.520
Or else they'd be plan A?

07:16:14.580 --> 07:16:15.779
Nautilus said.

07:16:15.840 --> 07:16:16.740
Obviously.

07:16:16.799 --> 07:16:20.340
All I want to know is whether they'll do

07:16:20.340 --> 07:16:23.099
as they're told, Blister said.

07:16:23.159 --> 07:16:27.540
Um, Nautilus wrinkled his snout and

07:16:27.540 --> 07:16:28.740
stared at the sky.

07:16:28.919 --> 07:16:31.080
Maybe?

07:16:31.200 --> 07:16:36.840
This does sound promising, Blister said

07:16:36.840 --> 07:16:37.380
dryly.

07:16:37.439 --> 07:16:39.180
I can't wait to meet them.

07:16:39.240 --> 07:16:44.220
Perhaps we can take the best options from

07:16:44.220 --> 07:16:46.500
each group, Maro Seer said.

07:16:46.560 --> 07:16:49.020
Kill the rain wing, obviously.

07:16:49.080 --> 07:16:51.419
We can probably work with the original

07:16:51.419 --> 07:16:52.259
mud wing.

07:16:52.319 --> 07:16:55.200
Your night wing is useless.

07:16:55.259 --> 07:16:56.700
Blister said.

07:16:56.819 --> 07:16:59.580
Worst traitor I've ever seen.

07:16:59.639 --> 07:17:01.680
Marosir shook his head.

07:17:01.740 --> 07:17:05.099
That is very disappointing.

07:17:05.159 --> 07:17:08.759
We don't often kill off our dragonettes

07:17:08.759 --> 07:17:10.319
but, he sighed.

07:17:10.439 --> 07:17:12.060
If we must.

07:17:12.180 --> 07:17:15.540
Ah, said Nautilus.

07:17:15.599 --> 07:17:17.520
You might want to meet our other option

07:17:17.520 --> 07:17:17.880
first.

07:17:17.939 --> 07:17:20.040
I mean, not to interfere.

07:17:20.099 --> 07:17:21.479
Just a suggestion.

07:17:21.540 --> 07:17:25.979
And we'll definitely kill the sea wing.

07:17:26.040 --> 07:17:27.659
Blister snarled.

07:17:27.720 --> 07:17:30.659
Nautilus flapped his wings, backing away

07:17:30.659 --> 07:17:31.139
in a hurry.

07:17:31.200 --> 07:17:34.439
Not you, she said impatiently.

07:17:34.500 --> 07:17:36.360
Well, not right now.

07:17:36.419 --> 07:17:40.560
I thought tsunami had some potential.

07:17:40.619 --> 07:17:42.540
Maru seer muttered.

07:17:42.599 --> 07:17:46.380
Potential to annoy my tail off, blister

07:17:46.380 --> 07:17:46.919
growled.

07:17:46.979 --> 07:17:49.979
No, she definitely has to go.

07:17:50.040 --> 07:17:53.700
We have dragons working on it as we

07:17:53.700 --> 07:17:53.939
speak.

07:17:54.060 --> 07:17:55.919
Marasia promised.

07:17:55.979 --> 07:17:59.279
Recruiting assassins is surprisingly easy

07:17:59.279 --> 07:18:00.720
in the middle of a war.

07:18:00.779 --> 07:18:02.159
Good.

07:18:02.220 --> 07:18:04.979
Blister flicked her tail menacingly.

07:18:05.040 --> 07:18:09.119
Those dragonettes need to know, they're

07:18:09.119 --> 07:18:11.340
not as valuable as they think they are.

07:18:11.400 --> 07:18:14.580
Anyone can be replaced.

07:18:14.639 --> 07:18:18.000
She smiled with all her teeth.

07:18:18.060 --> 07:18:23.099
After all, there's more than one way to

07:18:23.099 --> 07:18:24.419
fulfill a prophecy.

